VALUES
  (1361, 1, 44, 32, 'For thy servant became surety for the lad unto my father, saying, If I bring him not unto thee, then I shall bear the blame to my father for ever.', '2~05650~ 4~06148~ 7~05288~ 8~05973~ 10~01~, 11~0559~, 14~0935~ 24~02398~ 27~01~ 29~03117~.'),
  (23836, 40, 20, 34, 'So Jesus had compassion on them, and touched their eyes: and immediately their eyes received sight, and they followed him.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 3~4697~ [4 5] 7~680~ 8~846~ 9~3788~: 10~2532~ 11~2112~ 12~846~ 13~3788~ 15~308~, 16~2532~ 18~190~ 19~846~.'),
  (24631, 41, 10, 32, 'And they were in the way going up to Jerusalem; and Jesus went before them: and they were amazed; and as they followed, they were afraid. And he took again the twelve, and began to tell them what things should happen unto him,', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2258~ 3~1722~ 5~3598~ 7~305~ 8~1519~ 9~2414~; 10~2532~ 11~2424~ 12~2258~ 13~4254~ 14~846~: 15~2532~ 18~2284~; 19~2532~ 22~190~, 25~5399~. 26~2532~ 28~3880~ 29~3825~ 31~1427~, 33~756~ 35~3004~ 36~846~ 39~3195~ 40~4819~ 42~846~,'),
  (11954, 14, 34, 12, 'And the men did the work faithfully: and the overseers of them were Jahath and Obadiah, the Levites, of the sons of Merari; and Zechariah and Meshullam, of the sons of the Kohathites, to set it forward; and other of the Levites, all that could skill of instruments of music.', '2~0582~ 3~06213~ 5~04399~ 6~0530~: 9~05329~ [12] 13~03189~ 15~05662~, 17~03881~, 20~01121~ 22~04847~; 24~02148~ 26~04918~, 32~06956~, [35] 36~06485~; [38 39] 41~03881~, 45~0995~ 47~03627~ 49~07892~.'),
  (12149, 15, 5, 6, 'The copy of the letter that Tatnai, governor on this side the river, and Shetharboznai, and his companions the Apharsachites, which were on this side the river, sent unto Darius the king:', '1~06573~ 4~0104~ 6~08674~, 7~06347~ 10~05675~ 12~05103~, 14~08370~, 17~03675~ 19~0671~, [21] 24~05675~ 26~05103~, 27~07972~ 28~05922~ 29~01868~ 31~04430~:'),
  (26169, 43, 3, 34, 'For he whom God hath sent speaketh the words of God: for God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him.', '0~1063~ 2~3739~ 3~2316~ 5~649~ 6~2980~ 8~4487~ 10~2316~: 11~1063~ 12~2316~ 13~1325~ 14~3756~ 16~4151~ 17~1537~ 18~3358~ [19 20]'),
  (30584, 62, 2, 18, 'Little children, it is the last time: and as ye have heard that antichrist shall come, even now are there many antichrists; whereby we know that it is the last time.', '&para; 1~3813~, 3~2076~ 5~2078~ 6~5610~: 7~2532~ 8~2531~ 11~191~ 12~3754~ 13~500~ 15~2064~, 16~2532~ 17~3568~ 19~1096~ 20~4183~ 21~500~; 22~3606~ 24~1097~ 25~3754~ 27~2076~ 29~2078~ 30~5610~.'),
  (21403, 26, 36, 35, 'And they shall say, This land that was desolate is become like the garden of Eden; and the waste and desolate and ruined cities are become fenced, and are inhabited.', '3~0559~, 4~01977~ 5~0776~ 8~08074~ 13~01588~ 15~05731~; 18~02720~ 20~08074~ 22~02040~ 23~05892~ [24 25] 26~01219~, [27] 29~03427~.'),
  (23839, 40, 21, 3, 'And if any man say ought unto you, ye shall say, The Lord hath need of them; and straightway he will send them.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ [3] 3~5100~ 4~2036~ 5~5100~ 7~5213~, 10~2046~ 11~3754~,* 13~2962~ 14~2192~ 15~5532~ 17~846~; 18~1161~ 19~2112~ 22~649~ 23~846~.'),
  (13624, 18, 31, 27, 'And my heart hath been secretly enticed, or my mouth hath kissed my hand:', '2~03820~ 5~05643~ 6~06601~, 9~06310~ 11~05401~ 13~03027~:'),
  (577, 1, 23, 2, 'And Sarah died in Kirjatharba; the same is Hebron in the land of Canaan: and Abraham came to mourn for Sarah, and to weep for her.', '1~08283~ 2~04191~ 4~07153~; [7] 8~02275~ 11~0776~ 13~03667~: 15~085~ 16~0935~ 18~05594~ 20~08283~, 23~01058~'),
  (27829, 44, 25, 17, 'Therefore, when they were come hither, without any delay on the morrow I sat on the judgment seat, and commanded the man to be brought forth.', '0~3767~, 2~846~ 4~4905~ 5~1759~, 6~4160~ 7~3367~ 8~311~ 11~1836~ 13~2523~ 14~1909~ 17~968~, 19~2753~ 21~435~ 25~71~.'),
  (13893, 18, 40, 20, 'Surely the mountains bring him forth food, where all the beasts of the field play.', '2~02022~ 5~05375~ 6~0944~, 10~02416~ 13~07704~ 14~07832~.'),
  (9633, 12, 4, 22, 'And she called unto her husband, and said, Send me, I pray thee, one of the young men, and one of the asses, that I may run to the man of God, and come again.', '2~07121~ 5~0376~, 7~0559~, 8~07971~ 13~0259~ 17~05288~, 19~0259~ 22~0860~, 26~07323~ 29~0376~ 31~0430~, 34~07725~.'),
  (11141, 13, 27, 24, 'Joab the son of Zeruiah began to number, but he finished not, because there fell wrath for it against Israel; neither was the number put in the account of the chronicles of king David.', '0~03097~ 2~01121~ 4~06870~ 5~02490~ 7~04487~, 10~03615~ 15~07110~ 17~02063~ 19~03478~; 23~04557~ 24~05927~ 27~04557~ 30~03117~ 31~01697~ 32~04428~ 33~01732~.'),
  (20120, 24, 48, 31, 'Therefore will I howl for Moab, and I will cry out for all Moab; mine heart shall mourn for the men of Kirheres.', '3~03213~ 5~04124~, 10~02199~ 13~04124~; [14 15] 17~01897~ 20~0582~ 22~07025~.'),
  (3055, 3, 12, 6, 'And when the days of her purifying are fulfilled, for a son, or for a daughter, she shall bring a lamb of the first year for a burnt offering, and a young pigeon, or a turtledove, for a sin offering, unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, unto the priest:', '&para; 3~03117~ 6~02892~ 8~04390~, 11~01121~, 15~01323~, 18~0935~ 20~03532~ 23~01121~ 24~08141~ 28~05930~, 31~01121~ 32~03123~, 35~08449~, 39~02403~, 42~06607~ 45~0168~ 48~04150~, 51~03548~:'),
  (27690, 44, 21, 10, 'And as we tarried there many days, there came down from Judaea a certain prophet, named Agabus.', '0~1161~ 2~2257~ 3~1961~ [4] 5~4119~ 6~2250~, 9~2718~ 10~575~ 11~2449~ 13~5100~ 14~4396~, 15~3686~ 16~13~.'),
  (12778, 17, 4, 7, 'And Mordecai told him of all that had happened unto him, and of the sum of the money that Haman had promised to pay to the king''s treasuries for the Jews, to destroy them.', '1~04782~ 2~05046~ 8~07136~ 14~06575~ 17~03701~ 19~02001~ 21~0559~ 23~08254~ 26~04428~ 27~01595~ 30~03064~, 32~06~'),
  (17775, 23, 5, 27, 'None shall be weary nor stumble among them; none shall slumber nor sleep; neither shall the girdle of their loins be loosed, nor the latchet of their shoes be broken:', '3~05889~ 5~03782~ 10~05123~ 12~03462~; 16~0232~ 19~02504~ 21~06605~, 24~08288~ 27~05275~ 29~05423~:'),
  (14968, 19, 69, 24, 'Pour out thine indignation upon them, and let thy wrathful anger take hold of them.', '1~08210~ 3~02195~ 9~02740~ 10~0639~ 12~05381~'),
  (8403, 10, 15, 7, 'And it came to pass after forty years, that Absalom said unto the king, I pray thee, let me go and pay my vow, which I have vowed unto the LORD, in Hebron.', '&para; 5~07093~ 6~0705~ 7~08141~, 9~053~ 10~0559~ 13~04428~, 19~03212~ 21~07999~ 23~05088~, 27~05087~ 30~03068~, 32~02275~.'),
  (1196, 1, 40, 19, 'Yet within three days shall Pharaoh lift up thy head from off thee, and shall hang thee on a tree; and the birds shall eat thy flesh from off thee.', '2~07969~ 3~03117~ 5~06547~ 7~05375~ 9~07218~ 15~08518~ 19~06086~; 22~05775~ 24~0398~ 26~01320~'),
  (8788, 11, 2, 10, 'So David slept with his fathers, and was buried in the city of David.', '1~01732~ 2~07901~ 5~01~, 8~06912~ 11~05892~ 13~01732~.'),
  (22097, 27, 12, 7, 'And I heard the man clothed in linen, which was upon the waters of the river, when he held up his right hand and his left hand unto heaven, and sware by him that liveth for ever that it shall be for a time, times, and an half; and when he shall have accomplished to scatter the power of the holy people, all these things shall be finished.', '2~08085~ 4~0376~ 5~03847~ 7~0906~, [9] 10~04605~ 12~04325~ 15~02975~, 19~07311~ 22~03225~ 26~08040~ 28~08064~, 30~07650~ 34~02416~ 36~05769~ [38 40] 43~04150~, 44~04150~, 47~02677~; 53~03615~ 55~05310~ 57~03027~ 60~06944~ 61~05971~, [64] 67~03615~.'),
  (19796, 24, 33, 12, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Again in this place, which is desolate without man and without beast, and in all the cities thereof, shall be an habitation of shepherds causing their flocks to lie down.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~; 9~04725~, 12~02720~ 14~0120~ 17~0929~, 22~05892~ 27~05116~ 29~07462~ [31] 32~06629~ 35~07257~.'),
  (25287, 42, 8, 30, 'And Jesus asked him, saying, What is thy name? And he said, Legion: because many devils were entered into him.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~1905~ 3~846~, 4~3004~, 5~5101~ 6~2076~ 7~4671~ 8~3686~? 9~1161~ 11~2036~, 12~3003~: 13~3754~ 14~4183~ 15~1140~ 17~1525~ 18~1519~ 19~846~.'),
  (5054, 5, 4, 44, 'And this is the law which Moses set before the children of Israel:', '[2] 4~08451~ 6~04872~ 7~07760~ 8~06440~ 10~01121~ 12~03478~:'),
  (7409, 9, 9, 11, 'And as they went up the hill to the city, they found young maidens going out to draw water, and said unto them, Is the seer here?', '&para; [0] 4~05927~ 6~04608~ 9~05892~, 11~04672~ 13~05291~ 15~03318~ 17~07579~ 18~04325~, 20~0559~ 23~03426~ 25~07200~'),
  (17236, 20, 29, 3, 'Whoso loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father: but he that keepeth company with harlots spendeth his substance.', '&para; 0~0376~ 1~0157~ 2~02451~ 3~08055~ 5~01~: 10~07462~ 12~02181~ 13~06~ [14] 15~01952~.'),
  (624, 1, 24, 29, 'And Rebekah had a brother, and his name was Laban: and Laban ran out unto the man, unto the well.', '&para; 1~07259~ 4~0251~, 7~08034~ [8] 9~03837~: 11~03837~ 12~07323~ 13~02351~ 16~0376~, 19~05869~.'),
  (2992, 3, 10, 10, 'And that ye may put difference between holy and unholy, and between unclean and clean;', '5~0914~ 7~06944~ 9~02455~, 12~02931~ 14~02889~;'),
  (16834, 20, 15, 18, 'A wrathful man stirreth up strife: but he that is slow to anger appeaseth strife.', '&para; 1~02534~ 2~0376~ 4~01624~ 5~04066~: [7 9] 10~0750~ 12~0639~ 13~08252~ 14~07379~.'),
  (8880, 11, 4, 28, 'Barley also and straw for the horses and dromedaries brought they unto the place where the officers were, every man according to his charge.', '0~08184~ 3~08401~ 6~05483~ 8~07409~ 9~0935~ 13~04725~ [15 16] 19~0376~ 23~04941~.'),
  (29120, 48, 3, 2, 'This only would I learn of you, Received ye the Spirit by the works of the law, or by the hearing of faith?', '0~5124~ 1~3440~ 2~2309~ 4~3129~ 5~575~ 6~5216~, 8~2983~ 10~4151~ 11~1537~ 13~2041~ 16~3551~, 17~2228~ 18~1537~ 20~189~ 22~4102~?'),
  (4169, 4, 15, 11, 'Thus shall it be done for one bullock, or for one ram, or for a lamb, or a kid.', '4~06213~ 6~0259~ 7~07794~, 10~0259~ 11~0352~, 15~07716~ 16~03532~,* 19~05795~.'),
  (19007, 24, 2, 33, 'Why trimmest thou thy way to seek love? therefore hast thou also taught the wicked ones thy ways.', '1~03190~ 4~01870~ 6~01245~ 7~0160~? 12~03925~ 15~07451~ 17~01870~.'),
  (20849, 26, 17, 15, 'But he rebelled against him in sending his ambassadors into Egypt, that they might give him horses and much people. Shall he prosper? shall he escape that doeth such things? or shall he break the covenant, and be delivered?', '2~04775~ 6~07971~ 8~04397~ 10~04714~, 14~05414~ 16~05483~ 18~07227~ 19~05971~. 22~06743~? 25~04422~ 27~06213~ [29] 33~06565~ 35~01285~, 38~04422~?'),
  (20295, 24, 52, 10, 'And the king of Babylon slew the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes: he slew also all the princes of Judah in Riblah.', '2~04428~ 4~0894~ 5~07819~ 7~01121~ 9~06667~ 12~05869~: 14~07819~ 18~08269~ 20~03063~ 22~07247~.'),
  (25038, 42, 3, 1, 'Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being governor of Judaea, and Herod being tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip tetrarch of Ituraea and of the region of Trachonitis, and Lysanias the tetrarch of Abilene,', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1722~ 3~4003~ 4~2094~ 7~2231~ 9~5086~ 10~2541~, 11~4194~ 12~4091~ 14~2230~ 16~2449~, 17~2532~ 18~2264~ 20~5075~ 22~1056~, 23~1161~ 24~846~ 25~80~ 26~5376~ 27~5075~ 29~2484~ 30~2532~ 33~5561~ 35~5139~, 36~2532~ 37~3078~ 39~5075~ 41~9~,'),
  (29434, 50, 2, 27, 'For indeed he was sick nigh unto death: but God had mercy on him; and not on him only, but on me also, lest I should have sorrow upon sorrow.', '0~1063~ 1~2532~ 4~770~ 5~3897~ 7~2288~: 8~235~ 9~2316~ 11~1653~ 13~846~; 14~1161~ 15~3756~ 17~846~ 18~3440~, 19~235~ 21~1691~ 22~2532~, 23~3363~ 26~2192~ 27~3077~ 28~1909~ 29~3077~.'),
  (26265, 43, 5, 40, 'And ye will not come to me, that ye might have life.', '0~2532~ 2~2309~ 3~3756~ 4~2064~ 5~4314~ 6~3165~, 7~2443~ 10~2192~ 11~2222~.'),
  (10894, 13, 17, 23, 'Therefore now, LORD, let the thing that thou hast spoken concerning thy servant and concerning his house be established for ever, and do as thou hast said.', '2~03068~, 5~01697~ 9~01696~ 12~05650~ 16~01004~ 18~0539~ 19~05704~ 20~05769~, 22~06213~ 26~01696~.'),
  (952, 1, 32, 20, 'And say ye moreover, Behold, thy servant Jacob is behind us. For he said, I will appease him with the present that goeth before me, and afterward I will see his face; peradventure he will accept of me.', '2~0559~ 3~01571~, 6~05650~ 7~03290~ [8] 10~0310~. 13~0559~, 16~03722~ 17~06440~ 20~04503~ 22~01980~ 24~06440~, 26~0310~ 29~07200~ 31~06440~; 35~05375~ 37~06440~.'),
  (18374, 23, 37, 13, 'Where is the king of Hamath, and the king of Arphad, and the king of the city of Sepharvaim, Hena, and Ivah?', '[1] 3~04428~ 5~02574~, 8~04428~ 10~0774~, 13~04428~ 16~05892~ 18~05617~, 19~02012~, 21~05755~?'),
  (28582, 46, 9, 26, 'I therefore so run, not as uncertainly; so fight I, not as one that beateth the air:', '0~1473~ 1~5106~ 2~3779~ 3~5143~, 4~3756~ 5~5613~ 6~84~; 7~3779~ 9~4438~, 10~3756~ 11~5613~ 14~1194~ 16~109~:'),
  (8977, 11, 7, 35, 'And in the top of the base was there a round compass of half a cubit high: and on the top of the base the ledges thereof and the borders thereof were of the same.', '3~07218~ 6~04350~ [7 8] 10~05696~ 11~05439~ 13~02677~ 15~0520~ 16~06967~: 20~07218~ 23~04350~ 25~03027~ 29~04526~ [31]'),
  (7301, 9, 3, 18, 'And Samuel told him every whit, and hid nothing from him. And he said, It is the LORD: let him do what seemeth him good.', '1~08050~ 2~05046~ 5~01697~, 7~03582~ 13~0559~, [15] 17~03068~: 20~06213~ 22~05869~ 24~02896~.'),
  (954, 1, 32, 22, 'And he rose up that night, and took his two wives, and his two womenservants, and his eleven sons, and passed over the ford Jabbok.', '3~06965~ 5~03915~, 7~03947~ 9~08147~ 10~0802~, 13~08147~ 14~08198~, 17~0259~ 18~06240~* 19~03206~, 22~05674~ 24~04569~ 25~02999~.'),
  (25559, 42, 13, 28, 'There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when ye shall see Abraham, and Isaac, and Jacob, and all the prophets, in the kingdom of God, and you yourselves thrust out.', '0~1563~ 2~2071~ 3~2805~ 4~2532~ 5~1030~ 7~3599~, 8~3752~ 11~3700~ 12~11~, 13~2532~ 14~2464~, 15~2532~ 16~2384~, 17~2532~ 18~3956~ 20~4396~, 21~1722~ 23~932~ 25~2316~, 26~1161~ 27~5209~ [28] 29~1544~ 30~1854~.'),
  (29938, 56, 2, 14, 'Who gave himself for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity, and purify unto himself a peculiar people, zealous of good works.', '0~3739~ 1~1325~ 2~1438~ 3~5228~ 4~2257~, 5~2443~ 8~3084~ 9~2248~ 10~575~ 11~3956~ 12~458~, 13~2532~ 14~2511~ 16~1438~ 18~4041~ 19~2992~, 20~2207~ 22~2570~ 23~2041~.'),
  (18287, 23, 32, 19, 'When it shall hail, coming down on the forest; and the city shall be low in a low place.', '3~01258~, 5~03381~ 8~03293~; 11~05892~ 14~08213~ 18~08218~.'),
  (25931, 42, 22, 53, 'When I was daily with you in the temple, ye stretched forth no hands against me: but this is your hour, and the power of darkness.', '0~5607~ 1~3450~ 2~5607~ 3~2596~ 4~2250~* 5~3326~ 6~5216~ 7~1722~ 9~2411~, 12~1614~ 13~3756~ 14~5495~ 15~1909~ 16~1691~: 17~235~ 18~3778~ 19~2076~ 20~5216~ 21~5610~, 22~2532~ 24~1849~ 26~4655~.'),
  (7938, 9, 27, 1, 'And David said in his heart, I shall now perish one day by the hand of Saul: there is nothing better for me than that I should speedily escape into the land of the Philistines; and Saul shall despair of me, to seek me any more in any coast of Israel: so shall I escape out of his hand.', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~0559~ 5~03820~, 9~05595~ 10~0259~ 11~03117~ 14~03027~ 16~07586~: [17 18] 20~02896~ 24~03588~ 27~04422~ 28~04422~ 31~0776~ 34~06430~; 36~07586~ 38~02976~ 42~01245~ 48~01366~ 50~03478~: 54~04422~ 58~03027~.'),
  (16936, 20, 19, 2, 'Also, that the soul be without knowledge, it is not good; and he that hasteth with his feet sinneth.', '&para; [1] 3~05315~ [4] 6~01847~, [7 8] 10~02896~; 14~0213~ [16] 17~07272~ 18~02398~.'),
  (27572, 44, 17, 33, 'So Paul departed from among them.', '0~3779~ 1~2532~* 2~3972~ 3~1831~ 4~1537~ 5~3319~ 6~846~.'),
  (29274, 49, 3, 7, 'Whereof I was made a minister, according to the gift of the grace of God given unto me by the effectual working of his power.', '0~3739~ 3~1096~ 5~1249~, 6~2596~ 9~1431~ 12~5485~ 14~2316~ 15~1325~ 17~3427~ 18~2596~ 21~1753~ 23~846~ 24~1411~.'),
  (16595, 20, 7, 11, '(She is loud and stubborn; her feet abide not in her house:', '[1] 2~01993~ 4~05637~; 6~07272~ 7~07931~ 11~01004~:'),
  (12029, 15, 1, 4, 'And whosoever remaineth in any place where he sojourneth, let the men of his place help him with silver, and with gold, and with goods, and with beasts, beside the freewill offering for the house of God that is in Jerusalem.', '2~07604~ 5~04725~ 8~01481~, 11~0582~ 14~04725~ 15~05375~ 18~03701~, 21~02091~, 24~07399~, 27~0929~, 31~05071~ 34~01004~ 36~0430~ [38] 40~03389~.'),
  (17995, 23, 17, 3, 'The fortress also shall cease from Ephraim, and the kingdom from Damascus, and the remnant of Syria: they shall be as the glory of the children of Israel, saith the LORD of hosts.', '1~04013~ 4~07673~ 6~0669~, 9~04467~ 11~01834~, 14~07605~ 16~0758~: 22~03519~ 25~01121~ 27~03478~, 28~05002~ 30~03068~ 32~06635~.'),
  (14251, 19, 24, 1, 'A Psalm of David. The earth is the LORD''S, and the fulness thereof; the world, and they that dwell therein.', '&para; [0 1~04210~ 3] 3~01732~ 5~0776~ [6] 8~03068~, 11~04393~ 14~08398~, 18~03427~'),
  (28865, 47, 3, 8, 'How shall not the ministration of the spirit be rather glorious?', '0~4459~ 1~1248~ 2~3780~ 4~1248~ 7~4151~ 8~2071~ 9~1722~ 10~3123~* 11~1391~?'),
  (1455, 1, 47, 30, 'But I will lie with my fathers, and thou shalt carry me out of Egypt, and bury me in their buryingplace. And he said, I will do as thou hast said.', '3~07901~ 6~01~, 10~05375~ 14~04714~, 16~06912~ 20~06900~. 23~0559~, 26~06213~ 30~01697~.'),
  (30217, 58, 11, 29, 'By faith they passed through the Red sea as by dry land: which the Egyptians assaying to do were drowned.', '1~4102~ 4~1224~ 6~2063~ 7~2281~ 8~5613~ 9~1223~ 10~3584~ [11] 12~3739~ 14~124~ 15~3984~ 17~2983~ 19~2666~.'),
  (21099, 26, 25, 7, 'Behold, therefore I will stretch out mine hand upon thee, and will deliver thee for a spoil to the heathen; and I will cut thee off from the people, and I will cause thee to perish out of the countries: I will destroy thee; and thou shalt know that I am the LORD.', '5~05186~ 7~03027~ 12~05414~ 16~0957~ 17~0897~* 20~01471~; 26~03772~ 29~05971~, 36~06~ 40~0776~: 43~08045~ 48~03045~ [51] 53~03068~.'),
  (3007, 3, 11, 5, 'And the coney, because he cheweth the cud, but divideth not the hoof; he is unclean unto you.', '2~08227~, 5~05927~ 7~01625~, 9~06536~ 12~06541~; [14] 15~02931~'),
  (2075, 2, 20, 19, 'And they said unto Moses, Speak thou with us, and we will hear: but let not God speak with us, lest we die.', '2~0559~ 4~04872~, 5~01696~ 12~08085~: 16~0430~ 17~01696~ 22~04191~.'),
  (2504, 2, 34, 3, 'And no man shall come up with thee, neither let any man be seen throughout all the mount; neither let the flocks nor herds feed before that mount.', '2~0376~ 5~05927~ 8~0408~ 11~0376~ 13~07200~ 17~02022~; 21~06629~ 23~01241~ 24~07462~ 25~04136~ 27~02022~.'),
  (15904, 19, 118, 26, 'Blessed be he that cometh in the name of the LORD: we have blessed you out of the house of the LORD.', '0~01288~ [1] 4~0935~ 7~08034~ 10~03068~: 13~01288~ 18~01004~ 21~03068~.'),
  (3777, 4, 4, 29, 'As for the sons of Merari, thou shalt number them after their families, by the house of their fathers;', '3~01121~ 5~04847~, 8~06485~ 12~04940~, 15~01004~ 18~01~;'),
  (9882, 12, 13, 3, 'And the anger of the LORD was kindled against Israel, and he delivered them into the hand of Hazael king of Syria, and into the hand of Benhadad the son of Hazael, all their days.', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 9~03478~, 12~05414~ 16~03027~ 18~02371~ 19~04428~ 21~0758~, 25~03027~ 27~01130~ 29~01121~ 31~02371~, [33] 34~03117~.'),
  (8692, 10, 23, 31, 'Abialbon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite,', '0~045~ 2~06164~, 3~05820~ 5~01273~,'),
  (23781, 40, 19, 9, 'And I say unto you, Whosoever shall put away his wife, except it be for fornication, and shall marry another, committeth adultery: and whoso marrieth her which is put away doth commit adultery.', '0~1161~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~ 5~3754~,* 6~302~ 7~3739~ 9~630~ 10~846~ 11~1135~, 12~1508~ [13 14] 15~1909~ 16~4202~, 17~2532~ 19~1060~ 20~243~, 22~3429~: 23~2532~ 25~1060~ 27~3588~ 30~630~ 33~3429~.'),
  (27325, 44, 11, 2, 'And when Peter was come up to Jerusalem, they that were of the circumcision contended with him,', '0~2532~ 1~3753~ 2~4074~ 5~305~ 6~1519~ 7~2414~, 11~1537~ 13~4061~ 14~1252~ 15~4314~ 16~846~,'),
  (10157, 12, 22, 4, 'Go up to Hilkiah the high priest, that he may sum the silver which is brought into the house of the LORD, which the keepers of the door have gathered of the people:', '1~05927~ 3~02518~ 5~01419~ 6~03548~, 10~08552~ 12~03701~ 15~0935~ 18~01004~ 21~03068~, 24~08104~ 27~05592~ 29~0622~ 32~05971~:'),
  (16885, 20, 17, 3, 'The fining pot is for silver, and the furnace for gold: but the LORD trieth the hearts.', '&para; 2~04715~ [3] 5~03701~, 8~03564~ 10~02091~: 13~03068~ 14~0974~ 16~03826~.'),
  (6183, 6, 13, 22, 'Balaam also the son of Beor, the soothsayer, did the children of Israel slay with the sword among them that were slain by them.', '0~01109~ 3~01121~ 5~01160~, 7~07080~, 10~01121~ 12~03478~ 13~02026~ 16~02719~ 18~0413~ 21~02491~'),
  (9426, 11, 20, 10, 'And Benhadad sent unto him, and said, The gods do so unto me, and more also, if the dust of Samaria shall suffice for handfuls for all the people that follow me.', '1~01130~ 2~07971~ 6~0559~, 8~0430~ 10~06213~ 15~03254~, 18~06083~ 20~08111~ 22~05606~ 24~08168~ 28~05971~ 30~07272~'),
  (26934, 43, 21, 20, 'Then Peter, turning about, seeth the disciple whom Jesus loved following; which also leaned on his breast at supper, and said, Lord, which is he that betrayeth thee?', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~4074~, 3~1994~, 4~991~ 6~3101~ 7~3739~ 8~2424~ 9~25~ 10~190~; 11~3739~ 12~2532~ 13~377~ 14~1909~ 15~846~ 16~4738~ 17~1722~ 18~1173~, 19~2532~ 20~2036~, 21~2962~, 22~5101~ 24~2076~ 26~3860~ 27~4571~?'),
  (10217, 12, 24, 7, 'And the king of Egypt came not again any more out of his land: for the king of Babylon had taken from the river of Egypt unto the river Euphrates all that pertained to the king of Egypt.', '2~04428~ 4~04714~ 5~03318~ 7~03254~ 13~0776~: 16~04428~ 18~0894~ 20~03947~ 23~05158~ 25~04714~ 28~05104~ 29~06578~ 35~04428~ 37~04714~.'),
  (14426, 19, 35, 7, 'For without cause have they hid for me their net in a pit, which without cause they have digged for my soul.', '2~02600~ 5~02934~ 9~07568~ [10] 12~07845~, [13] 15~02600~ 18~02658~ 21~05315~.'),
  (13711, 18, 34, 19, 'How much less to him that accepteth not the persons of princes, nor regardeth the rich more than the poor? for they all are the work of his hands.', '[0 4] 6~05375~ 9~06440~ 11~08269~, 13~05234~ 15~07771~ 17~06440~ 19~01800~? [23] 25~04639~ 28~03027~.'),
  (28308, 45, 14, 12, 'So then every one of us shall give account of himself to God.', '0~3767~ 1~686~ 3~1538~ 5~2257~ 7~1325~ 8~3056~ 9~4012~ 10~1438~ 12~2316~.'),
  (24301, 41, 3, 3, 'And he saith unto the man which had the withered hand, Stand forth.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 5~444~ 7~2192~ 9~3583~ 10~5495~, 11~1453~ 12~3319~ 13~1519~.*'),
  (25859, 42, 21, 19, 'In your patience possess ye your souls.', '0~1722~ 1~5216~ 2~5281~ 4~2932~ 5~5216~ 6~5590~.'),
  (4251, 4, 17, 2, 'Speak unto the children of Israel, and take of every one of them a rod according to the house of their fathers, of all their princes according to the house of their fathers twelve rods: write thou every man''s name upon his rod.', '0~01696~ 3~01121~ 5~03478~, 7~03947~ 14~04294~ 15~04294~ 18~01004~ [20] 21~01~, 25~05387~ 29~01004~ 32~01~ 33~06240~ 34~08147~* 35~04294~: 36~03789~ 39~0376~ 40~08034~ 43~04294~.'),
  (16401, 19, 149, 7, 'To execute vengeance upon the heathen, and punishments upon the people;', '1~06213~ 2~05360~ 5~01471~, [6] 7~08433~ 10~03816~;'),
  (11280, 14, 5, 4, 'And all the elders of Israel came; and the Levites took up the ark.', '3~02205~ 5~03478~ 6~0935~; 9~03881~ 11~05375~ 13~0727~.'),
  (25717, 42, 18, 15, 'And they brought unto him also infants, that he would touch them: but when his disciples saw it, they rebuked them.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~4374~ 4~846~ 5~2532~ 6~1025~, 7~2443~ 10~680~ 11~846~: 12~1161~ [14] 15~3101~ 16~1492~ [17] 19~2008~ 20~846~.'),
  (30536, 61, 2, 20, 'For if after they have escaped the pollutions of the world through the knowledge of the Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ, they are again entangled therein, and overcome, the latter end is worse with them than the beginning.', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 5~668~ 7~3393~ 10~2889~ 11~1722~ 13~1922~ 16~2962~ 17~2532~ 18~4990~ 19~2424~ 20~5547~, 22~1707~ 23~3825~ 24~1707~ 25~5125~, 26~1161~ 27~1096~ 28~2274~,* 31~2078~ 33~5501~ 35~846~ 38~4413~.'),
  (4193, 4, 15, 35, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, The man shall be surely put to death: all the congregation shall stone him with stones without the camp.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 7~0376~ 10~04191~ 13~04191~: 16~05712~ 18~07275~ 21~068~ 22~02351~ 24~04264~.'),
  (20604, 26, 7, 18, 'They shall also gird themselves with sackcloth, and horror shall cover them; and shame shall be upon all faces, and baldness upon all their heads.', '3~02296~ [4] 6~08242~, 8~06427~ 10~03680~ 13~0955~ [14 15] 18~06440~, 20~07144~ 24~07218~.'),
  (14459, 19, 36, 12, 'There are the workers of iniquity fallen: they are cast down, and shall not be able to rise.', '3~06466~ 5~0205~ 6~05307~: 10~01760~, 15~03201~ 17~06965~.'),
  (21925, 27, 6, 11, 'Then these men assembled, and found Daniel praying and making supplication before his God.', '&para; 0~0116~ 1~0479~ 2~01400~ 3~07284~, 5~07912~ 6~01841~ 7~01156~ 10~02604~ 11~06925~ 13~0426~.'),
  (5510, 5, 23, 4, 'Because they met you not with bread and with water in the way, when ye came forth out of Egypt; and because they hired against thee Balaam the son of Beor of Pethor of Mesopotamia, to curse thee.', '0~01697~ 2~06923~ 6~03899~ 9~04325~ 12~01870~, 16~03318~ 19~04714~; 23~07936~ 26~01109~ 28~01121~ 30~01160~ 32~06604~ 34~0763~, 36~07043~'),
  (9696, 12, 6, 14, 'Therefore sent he thither horses, and chariots, and a great host: and they came by night, and compassed the city about.', '1~07971~ 4~05483~, 6~07393~, 9~03515~ 10~02428~: 13~0935~ 15~03915~, 17~05362~ 19~05892~ 20~05362~.'),
  (8818, 11, 2, 40, 'And Shimei arose, and saddled his ass, and went to Gath to Achish to seek his servants: and Shimei went, and brought his servants from Gath.', '1~08096~ 2~06965~, 4~02280~ 6~02543~, 8~03212~ 10~01661~ 12~0397~ 14~01245~ 16~05650~: 18~08096~ 19~03212~, 21~0935~ 23~05650~ 25~01661~.'),
  (18306, 23, 33, 18, 'Thine heart shall meditate terror. Where is the scribe? where is the receiver? where is he that counted the towers?', '1~03820~ 3~01897~ 4~0367~. [6] 8~05608~? [10] 12~08254~? [14] 17~05608~ 19~04026~?'),
  (21841, 27, 3, 25, 'He answered and said, Lo, I see four men loose, walking in the midst of the fire, and they have no hurt; and the form of the fourth is like the Son of God.', '1~06032~ 3~0560~, 4~01888~, 5~0576~ 6~02370~ 7~0703~ 8~01400~ 9~08271~, 10~01981~ 13~01459~ 16~05135~, 19~0383~ 20~03809~ 21~02257~; 24~07299~ 27~07244~ 29~01821~ 31~01247~ 33~0426~.'),
  (27141, 44, 7, 9, 'And the patriarchs, moved with envy, sold Joseph into Egypt: but God was with him,', '0~2532~ 2~3966~, 5~2206~, 6~591~ 7~2501~ 8~1519~ 9~125~: 10~2532~ 11~2316~ 12~2258~ 13~3326~ 14~846~,');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (15755, 19, 108, 4, 'For thy mercy is great above the heavens: and thy truth reacheth unto the clouds.', '2~02617~ [3] 4~01419~ 7~08064~: 10~0571~ [11] 14~07834~.'),
  (16647, 20, 8, 36, 'But he that sinneth against me wrongeth his own soul: all they that hate me love death.', '3~02398~ 6~02554~ 9~05315~: 13~08130~ 15~0157~ 16~04194~.'),
  (31006, 66, 17, 15, 'And he saith unto me, The waters which thou sawest, where the whore sitteth, are peoples, and multitudes, and nations, and tongues.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~3427~, 6~5204~ 7~3739~ 9~1492~, 10~3757~ 12~4204~ 13~2521~, 14~1526~ 15~2992~, 16~2532~ 17~3793~, 18~2532~ 19~1484~, 20~2532~ 21~1100~.'),
  (28030, 45, 3, 23, 'For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God;', '0~1063~ 1~3956~ 3~264~, 4~2532~ 6~5302~ 9~1391~ 11~2316~;'),
  (12903, 18, 2, 3, 'And the LORD said unto Satan, Hast thou considered my servant Job, that there is none like him in the earth, a perfect and an upright man, one that feareth God, and escheweth evil? and still he holdeth fast his integrity, although thou movedst me against him, to destroy him without cause.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~07854~, 7~07760~ 8~03820~ 10~05650~ 11~0347~, [13 14] 20~0776~, 22~08535~ 25~03477~ 26~0376~, 29~03373~ 30~0430~, 32~05493~ 33~07451~? 38~02388~ 40~08538~, 43~05496~ 48~01104~ 51~02600~.'),
  (14436, 19, 35, 17, 'Lord, how long wilt thou look on? rescue my soul from their destructions, my darling from the lions.', '&para; 0~0136~, 6~07200~? 7~07725~ 9~05315~ 12~07722~, 14~03173~ 17~03715~.'),
  (1376, 1, 45, 13, 'And ye shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt, and of all that ye have seen; and ye shall haste and bring down my father hither.', '3~05046~ 5~01~ 9~03519~ 11~04714~, 18~07200~; 22~04116~ 25~03381~ 27~01~'),
  (16490, 20, 3, 26, 'For the LORD shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.', '2~03068~ 6~03689~, 9~08104~ 11~07272~ 14~03921~.'),
  (3383, 3, 22, 9, 'They shall therefore keep mine ordinance, lest they bear sin for it, and die therefore, if they profane it: I the LORD do sanctify them.', '3~08104~ 5~04931~, 8~05375~ 9~02399~ 13~04191~ 17~02490~ 21~03068~ 23~06942~'),
  (2560, 2, 35, 24, 'Every one that did offer an offering of silver and brass brought the Lord''s offering: and every man, with whom was found shittim wood for any work of the service, brought it.', '4~07311~ 6~08641~ 8~03701~ 10~05178~ 11~0935~ 13~03068~ 14~08641~: 21~04672~ 22~07848~ 23~06086~ 26~04399~ 29~05656~, 30~0935~ [31]'),
  (6863, 7, 11, 27, 'Wherefore I have not sinned against thee, but thou doest me wrong to war against me: the LORD the Judge be judge this day between the children of Israel and the children of Ammon.', '4~02398~ 9~06213~ 10~0853~* 12~07451~ 14~03898~ 18~03068~ 20~08199~ 22~08199~ 24~03117~ 27~01121~ 29~03478~ 32~01121~ 34~05983~.'),
  (6169, 6, 13, 9, 'From Aroer, that is upon the bank of the river Arnon, and the city that is in the midst of the river, and all the plain of Medeba unto Dibon;', '1~06177~, [3] 6~08193~ 9~05158~ 10~0769~, 13~05892~ [15] 18~08432~ 21~05158~, 25~04334~ 27~04311~ 29~01769~;'),
  (8915, 11, 6, 11, 'And the word of the LORD came to Solomon, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 8~08010~, 9~0559~,'),
  (24675, 41, 11, 24, 'Therefore I say unto you, What things soever ye desire, when ye pray, believe that ye receive them, and ye shall have them.', '0~5124~ 1~1223~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3745~ 6~3956~ 7~302~ 9~154~, 12~4336~, 13~4100~ 14~3754~ 16~2983~ [17] 18~2532~ 19~5213~ 21~2071~ [22]'),
  (12907, 18, 2, 7, 'So went Satan forth from the presence of the LORD, and smote Job with sore boils from the sole of his foot unto his crown.', '&para; 1~03318~ 2~07854~ 3~03318~ 6~06440~ 9~03068~, 11~05221~ 12~0347~ 14~07451~ 15~07822~ 18~03709~ 21~07272~ 24~06936~.'),
  (36, 1, 2, 5, 'And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the LORD God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground.', '2~07880~ 5~07704~ 6~02962~ 11~0776~, 14~06212~ 17~07704~ 18~02962~ 20~06779~: 21~03588~ 23~03068~ 24~0430~ 26~03808~ 30~04305~ 33~0776~, [35 36] 37~0369~ 39~0120~ 41~05647~ 43~0127~.'),
  (8797, 11, 2, 19, 'Bathsheba therefore went unto king Solomon, to speak unto him for Adonijah. And the king rose up to meet her, and bowed himself unto her, and sat down on his throne, and caused a seat to be set for the king''s mother; and she sat on his right hand.', '0~01339~ 2~0935~ 4~04428~ 5~08010~, 7~01696~ 11~0138~. 14~04428~ 16~06965~ 18~07125~ 21~07812~ 27~03427~ 30~03678~, 34~03678~ 37~07760~ 40~04428~ 41~0517~; 44~03427~ 48~03225~.'),
  (20703, 26, 12, 14, 'And I will scatter toward every wind all that are about him to help him, and all his bands; and I will draw out the sword after them.', '3~02219~ 6~07307~ [9] 10~05439~ 13~05828~ 18~0102~; 23~07324~ 25~02719~ 26~0310~'),
  (2383, 2, 29, 42, 'This shall be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation before the LORD: where I will meet you, to speak there unto thee.', '[0 2] 4~08548~ 6~05930~ 9~01755~ [10] 12~06607~ 15~0168~ 18~04150~ 19~06440~ 21~03068~: 25~03259~ 28~01696~'),
  (15569, 19, 103, 11, 'For as the heaven is high above the earth, so great is his mercy toward them that fear him.', '3~08064~ 6~01361~ 8~0776~, [9] 10~01396~ 13~02617~ 17~03373~'),
  (9093, 11, 10, 6, 'And she said to the king, It was a true report that I heard in mine own land of thy acts and of thy wisdom.', '2~0559~ 5~04428~, 9~0571~ 10~01697~ 13~08085~ 17~0776~ 20~01697~ 24~02451~.'),
  (12822, 17, 7, 6, 'And Esther said, The adversary and enemy is this wicked Haman. Then Haman was afraid before the king and the queen.', '1~0635~ 2~0559~, 4~06862~ 5~0376~ 6~0341~ [7] 9~07451~ 10~02001~. 12~02001~ 14~01204~ 15~06440~ 17~04428~ 20~04436~.'),
  (2902, 3, 7, 18, 'And if any of the flesh of the sacrifice of his peace offerings be eaten at all on the third day, it shall not be accepted, neither shall it be imputed unto him that offereth it: it shall be an abomination, and the soul that eateth of it shall bear his iniquity.', '[2] 5~01320~ 8~02077~ 12~08002~ 14~0398~ 16~0398~ 19~07992~ 20~03117~, 25~07521~, 30~02803~ 34~07126~ 40~06292~, 43~05315~ 45~0398~ 49~05375~ 51~05771~.'),
  (21560, 26, 41, 25, 'And there were made on them, on the doors of the temple, cherubims and palm trees, like as were made upon the walls; and there were thick planks upon the face of the porch without.', '[1 2] 3~06213~ 8~01817~ 11~01964~, 12~03742~ 15~08561~, [18] 19~06213~ 22~07023~; [24 25] 26~05646~ 27~06086~ 30~06440~ 33~0197~ 34~02351~.'),
  (30648, 62, 5, 8, 'And there are three that bear witness in earth, the Spirit, and the water, and the blood: and these three agree in one.', '0~2532~ 2~1526~ 3~5140~ 6~3140~ 7~1722~ 8~1093~, 10~4151~, 11~2532~ 13~5204~, 14~2532~ 16~129~: 17~2532~ 19~5140~ 20~1526~ 21~1519~ 22~1520~.'),
  (15437, 19, 93, 2, 'Thy throne is established of old: thou art from everlasting.', '1~03678~ [2] 3~03559~ 5~0227~: [7] 9~05769~.'),
  (11158, 13, 28, 7, 'Moreover I will establish his kingdom for ever, if he be constant to do my commandments and my judgments, as at this day.', '3~03559~ 5~04438~ 7~05769~, 11~02388~ 13~06213~ 15~04687~ 18~04941~, 22~03117~.'),
  (13058, 18, 8, 20, 'Behold, God will not cast away a perfect man, neither will he help the evil doers:', '&para; 1~0410~ 5~03988~ 7~08535~ [8] 12~02388~ 13~03027~* 16~07489~:'),
  (814, 1, 29, 15, 'And Laban said unto Jacob, Because thou art my brother, shouldest thou therefore serve me for nought? tell me, what shall thy wages be?', '&para; 1~03837~ 2~0559~ 4~03290~, [7] 9~0251~, 13~05647~ 16~02600~? 17~05046~ [20] 22~04909~ [23]'),
  (25905, 42, 22, 27, 'For whether is greater, he that sitteth at meat, or he that serveth? is not he that sitteth at meat? but I am among you as he that serveth.', '0~1063~ 1~5101~ [2] 3~3187~, 8~345~, 9~2228~ 12~1247~? [13] 14~3780~ 19~345~? 20~1161~ 21~1473~ 22~1510~ 23~3319~ 24~1722~* 25~5216~ 26~5613~ 29~1247~.'),
  (5747, 5, 31, 13, 'And that their children, which have not known any thing, may hear, and learn to fear the LORD your God, as long as ye live in the land whither ye go over Jordan to possess it.', '[1] 3~01121~, 7~03045~ [8 9] 11~08085~, 13~03925~ 15~03372~ 17~03068~ 19~0430~, 22~03117~ 24~02416~ 27~0127~ 31~05674~ 32~03383~ 34~03423~'),
  (29570, 51, 4, 12, 'Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of Christ, saluteth you, always labouring fervently for you in prayers, that ye may stand perfect and complete in all the will of God.', '0~1889~, [3] 4~1537~ 5~5216~, 7~1401~ 9~5547~, 10~782~ 11~5209~, 12~3842~ 14~75~ 15~5228~ 16~5216~ 17~1722~ 18~4335~, 19~2443~ 22~2476~ 23~5046~ 24~2532~ 25~4137~ 26~1722~ 27~3956~ 29~2307~ 31~2316~.'),
  (14475, 19, 37, 16, 'A little that a righteous man hath is better than the riches of many wicked.', '1~04592~ 5~06662~ [7] 8~02896~ 11~01995~ 13~07227~ 14~07563~.'),
  (18141, 23, 26, 2, 'Open ye the gates, that the righteous nation which keepeth the truth may enter in.', '0~06605~ 3~08179~, 6~06662~ 7~01471~ 9~08104~ 11~0529~ 14~0935~.'),
  (17944, 23, 14, 7, 'The whole earth is at rest, and is quiet: they break forth into singing.', '2~0776~ 5~05117~, [6] 8~08252~: 11~06476~ 13~07440~.'),
  (12947, 18, 4, 8, 'Even as I have seen, they that plow iniquity, and sow wickedness, reap the same.', '4~07200~, 7~02790~ 8~0205~, 10~02232~ 11~05999~, 12~07114~'),
  (2535, 2, 34, 34, 'But when Moses went in before the LORD to speak with him, he took the veil off, until he came out. And he came out, and spake unto the children of Israel that which he was commanded.', '2~04872~ 4~0935~ 5~06440~ 7~03068~ 9~01696~ 13~05493~ 15~04533~ 16~05493~, 20~03318~. 24~03318~, 26~01696~ 29~01121~ 31~03478~ [32] 36~06680~.'),
  (18264, 23, 31, 5, 'As birds flying, so will the LORD of hosts defend Jerusalem; defending also he will deliver it; and passing over he will preserve it.', '1~06833~ 2~05774~, 6~03068~ 8~06635~ 9~01598~ 10~03389~; 11~01598~ 15~05337~ [16 17] 19~06452~ 22~04422~'),
  (528, 1, 21, 11, 'And the thing was very grievous in Abraham''s sight because of his son.', '2~01697~ 4~03966~ 5~03415~ 7~085~ 8~05869~ 9~0182~ 12~01121~.'),
  (27877, 44, 27, 6, 'And there the centurion found a ship of Alexandria sailing into Italy; and he put us therein.', '1~2546~ 3~1543~ 4~2147~ 6~4143~ 8~222~ 9~4126~ 10~1519~ 11~2482~; 14~1688~ 15~2248~ 16~846~ 17~1519~.*'),
  (16882, 20, 16, 33, 'The lot is cast into the lap; but the whole disposing thereof is of the LORD.', '&para; 1~01486~ 3~02904~ 6~02436~; 10~04941~ [12] 15~03068~.'),
  (28095, 45, 6, 11, 'Likewise reckon ye also yourselves to be dead indeed unto sin, but alive unto God through Jesus Christ our Lord.', '0~3779~ 1~3049~ 2~5210~ 3~2532~ 4~1438~ 6~1511~ 7~3498~ 8~3303~ 10~266~, 11~1161~ 12~2198~ 14~2316~ 15~1722~ 16~2424~ 17~5547~ 18~2257~ 19~2962~.'),
  (24550, 41, 9, 1, 'And he said unto them, Verily I say unto you, That there be some of them that stand here, which shall not taste of death, till they have seen the kingdom of God come with power.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~281~ 7~3004~ 9~5213~, 10~3754~ 12~1526~ 13~5100~ 17~2476~ 18~5602~, 19~3748~ 20~1089~ 21~3364~ 22~1089~ 24~2288~, 25~302~ 26~2193~ 28~1492~ 30~932~ 32~2316~ 33~2064~ 34~1722~ 35~1411~.'),
  (23180, 40, 2, 1, 'Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judaea in the days of Herod the king, behold, there came wise men from the east to Jerusalem,', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2424~ 4~1080~ 5~1722~ 6~965~ 8~2449~ 9~1722~ 11~2250~ 13~2264~ 15~935~, 16~2400~, 18~3854~ 20~3097~ 21~575~ 23~395~ 24~1519~ 25~2414~,'),
  (6319, 6, 18, 19, 'And the border passed along to the side of Bethhoglah northward: and the outgoings of the border were at the north bay of the salt sea at the south end of Jordan: this was the south coast.', '2~01366~ 4~05674~ 7~03802~ 9~01031~ 10~06828~: 13~08444~ 16~01366~ 20~06828~ 21~03956~ 24~04417~ 25~03220~ 28~05045~ 29~07097~ 31~03383~: [33] 35~05045~ 36~01366~.'),
  (11718, 14, 25, 5, 'Moreover Amaziah gathered Judah together, and made them captains over thousands, and captains over hundreds, according to the houses of their fathers, throughout all Judah and Benjamin: and he numbered them from twenty years old and above, and found them three hundred thousand choice men, able to go forth to war, that could handle spear and shield.', '1~0558~ 2~06908~ 3~03063~ 4~06908~, 6~05975~ 8~08269~ 10~0505~, 12~08269~ 14~03967~, 18~01004~ [20] 21~01~, 24~03063~ 26~01144~: 29~06485~ 32~06242~ 33~08141~ 34~01121~ 36~04605~, 38~04672~ 40~07969~ 41~03967~ 42~0505~ 43~0977~ [44 45] 48~03318~ 50~06635~, 53~0270~ 54~07420~ 56~06793~.'),
  (23292, 40, 5, 48, 'Be ye therefore perfect, even as your Father which is in heaven is perfect.', '0~2071~ 1~5210~ 2~3767~ 3~5046~, 4~5618~ 6~5216~ 7~3962~ 8~3588~ 10~1722~ 11~3772~ 12~2076~ 13~5046~.'),
  (575, 1, 22, 24, 'And his concubine, whose name was Reumah, she bare also Tebah, and Gaham, and Thahash, and Maachah.', '2~06370~, 4~08034~ [5] 6~07208~, 8~03205~ 10~02875~, 12~01514~, 14~08477~, 16~04601~.'),
  (19849, 24, 35, 17, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD God of hosts, the God of Israel; Behold, I will bring upon Judah and upon all the inhabitants of Jerusalem all the evil that I have pronounced against them: because I have spoken unto them, but they have not heard; and I have called unto them, but they have not answered.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~06635~, 9~0430~ 11~03478~; 15~0935~ 17~03063~ 22~03427~ 24~03389~ 27~07451~ 31~01696~ 37~01696~ 44~08085~; 48~07121~ 55~06030~.'),
  (22542, 32, 1, 2, 'Arise, go to Nineveh, that great city, and cry against it; for their wickedness is come up before me.', '0~06965~, 1~03212~ 3~05210~, 5~01419~ 6~05892~, 8~07121~ 13~07451~ 16~05927~ 17~06440~'),
  (14003, 19, 6, 9, 'The LORD hath heard my supplication; the LORD will receive my prayer.', '1~03068~ 3~08085~ 5~08467~; 7~03068~ 9~03947~ 11~08605~.'),
  (19582, 24, 26, 1, 'In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah came this word from the LORD, saying,', '&para; 2~07225~ 5~04468~ 7~03079~ 9~01121~ 11~02977~ 12~04428~ 14~03063~ 17~01697~ 20~03068~, 21~0559~,'),
  (29309, 49, 4, 21, 'If so be that ye have heard him, and have been taught by him, as the truth is in Jesus:', '3~1489~ 6~191~ 7~846~, 8~2532~ 11~1321~ 12~1722~ 13~846~, 14~2531~ 16~225~ 17~2076~ 18~1722~ 19~2424~:'),
  (27024, 44, 3, 12, 'And when Peter saw it, he answered unto the people, Ye men of Israel, why marvel ye at this? or why look ye so earnestly on us, as though by our own power or holiness we had made this man to walk?', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~4074~ 3~1492~ [4] 6~611~ 7~4314~ 9~2992~, 11~435~ 13~2475~, 14~5101~ 16~2296~ 17~1909~ 18~5129~? 19~2228~ 20~5101~ 24~816~ 26~2254~, 28~5613~ 31~2398~ 32~1411~ 33~2228~ 34~2150~ 37~4160~ 39~846~ 41~4043~?'),
  (10336, 13, 2, 22, 'And Segub begat Jair, who had three and twenty cities in the land of Gilead.', '1~07687~ 2~03205~ 3~02971~, 6~07969~ 8~06242~ 9~05892~ 12~0776~ 14~01568~.'),
  (8249, 10, 10, 2, 'Then said David, I will shew kindness unto Hanun the son of Nahash, as his father shewed kindness unto me. And David sent to comfort him by the hand of his servants for his father. And David''s servants came into the land of the children of Ammon.', '1~0559~ 2~01732~, 5~06213~ 6~02617~ 8~02586~ 10~01121~ 12~05176~, 15~01~ 16~06213~ 17~02617~ 21~01732~ 22~07971~ 24~05162~ 28~03027~ 31~05650~ 34~01~. 36~01732~ 37~05650~ 38~0935~ 41~0776~ 44~01121~ 46~05983~.'),
  (9860, 12, 12, 2, 'And Jehoash did that which was right in the sight of the LORD all his days wherein Jehoiada the priest instructed him.', '1~03060~ 2~06213~ [3 5] 6~03477~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~ 15~03117~ 17~03077~ 19~03548~ 20~03384~'),
  (18939, 23, 66, 8, 'Who hath heard such a thing? who hath seen such things? Shall the earth be made to bring forth in one day? or shall a nation be born at once? for as soon as Zion travailed, she brought forth her children.', '2~08085~ 8~07200~ 13~0776~ 18~02342~ 20~0259~ 21~03117~? [22] 25~01471~ 27~03205~ 29~06471~? 33~01571~ 34~06726~ 35~02342~, 38~03205~ 40~01121~.'),
  (27529, 44, 16, 30, 'And brought them out, and said, Sirs, what must I do to be saved?', '0~2532~ 1~4254~ 2~846~ 3~1854~, 5~5346~, 6~2962~, 7~5101~ 8~1163~ 9~3165~ 10~4160~ 11~2443~ 13~4982~?'),
  (25546, 42, 13, 15, 'The Lord then answered him, and said, Thou hypocrite, doth not each one of you on the sabbath loose his ox or his ass from the stall, and lead him away to watering?', '1~2962~ 2~3767~ 3~611~ 4~846~, 5~2532~ 6~2036~, [7] 8~5273~, 9~3089~ 10~3756~ 12~1538~ 14~5216~ 17~4521~ 18~3089~ 19~846~ 20~1016~ 21~2228~ [22] 23~3688~ 24~575~ 26~5336~, 27~2532~ [29] 30~520~ 32~4222~?'),
  (6215, 6, 15, 6, 'And the border went up to Bethhogla, and passed along by the north of Betharabah; and the border went up to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben:', '2~01366~ 4~05927~ 6~01031~, 8~05674~ 12~06828~ 14~01026~; 17~01366~ 19~05927~ 22~068~ 24~0932~ 26~01121~ 28~07205~:'),
  (13452, 18, 24, 7, 'They cause the naked to lodge without clothing, that they have no covering in the cold.', '3~06174~ 5~03885~ 7~03830~, [9 10] 12~03682~ 15~07135~.'),
  (6557, 7, 2, 5, 'And they called the name of that place Bochim: and they sacrificed there unto the LORD.', '2~07121~ 4~08034~ 7~04725~ 8~01066~: 11~02076~ 15~03068~.'),
  (27333, 44, 11, 10, 'And this was done three times: and all were drawn up again into heaven.', '0~1161~ 1~5124~ 3~1096~ 4~1909~* 6~5151~: 7~2532~ 8~537~ 11~385~ 12~3825~ 13~1519~ 14~3772~.'),
  (1439, 1, 47, 14, 'And Joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, for the corn which they bought: and Joseph brought the money into Pharaoh''s house.', '1~03130~ 3~03950~ 6~03701~ 9~04672~ 12~0776~ 14~04714~, 18~0776~ 20~03667~, 23~07668~ 26~07666~: 28~03130~ 29~0935~ 31~03701~ 33~06547~ 34~01004~.'),
  (11228, 14, 2, 9, 'Even to prepare me timber in abundance: for the house which I am about to build shall be wonderful great.', '2~03559~ 4~06086~ 6~07230~: 9~01004~ 15~01129~ [16 17] 18~06381~ 19~01419~.'),
  (22404, 30, 2, 16, 'And he that is courageous among the mighty shall flee away naked in that day, saith the LORD.', '[1 3] 4~03820~ 5~0533~ 7~01368~ 10~05127~ 11~06174~ 14~03117~, 15~05002~ 17~03068~.'),
  (30146, 58, 9, 25, 'Nor yet that he should offer himself often, as the high priest entereth into the holy place every year with blood of others;', '0~3761~ 2~2443~ 5~4374~ 6~1438~ 7~4178~, 8~5618~ 11~749~ 12~1525~ 13~1519~ 16~39~ 17~2596~ 18~1763~ 19~1722~ 20~129~ 22~245~;'),
  (4318, 4, 20, 2, 'And there was no water for the congregation: and they gathered themselves together against Moses and against Aaron.', '4~04325~ 7~05712~: 10~06950~ 14~04872~ 17~0175~.'),
  (29787, 54, 5, 8, 'But if any provide not for his own, and specially for those of his own house, he hath denied the faith, and is worse than an infidel.', '0~1161~ 2~1536~ 3~4306~ 4~3756~ 7~2398~, 8~2532~ 9~3122~ 15~3609~, 18~720~ 20~4102~, 21~2532~ 22~2076~ 24~5501~ 26~571~.'),
  (29060, 47, 13, 1, 'This is the third time I am coming to you. In the mouth of two or three witnesses shall every word be established.', '&para; 0~5124~ [1] 3~5154~ [4] 7~2064~ 8~4314~ 9~5209~. 10~1909~ 12~4750~ 14~1417~ 15~2532~ 16~5140~ 17~3144~ 18~2476~ 19~3956~ 20~4487~ 22~2476~.'),
  (12543, 16, 9, 23, 'Their children also multipliedst thou as the stars of heaven, and broughtest them into the land, concerning which thou hadst promised to their fathers, that they should go in to possess it.', '1~01121~ 3~07235~ 7~03556~ 9~08064~, 11~0935~ 15~0776~, 20~0559~ 23~01~, 28~0935~ 30~03423~ [31]'),
  (7835, 9, 23, 18, 'And they two made a covenant before the LORD: and David abode in the wood, and Jonathan went to his house.', '2~08147~ 3~03772~ 5~01285~ 6~06440~ 8~03068~: 10~01732~ 11~03427~ 14~02793~, 16~03083~ 17~01980~ 20~01004~.'),
  (24478, 41, 7, 5, 'Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him, Why walk not thy disciples according to the tradition of the elders, but eat bread with unwashen hands?', '0~1899~ 2~5330~ 3~2532~ 4~1122~ 5~1905~ 6~846~, 7~1302~ 8~4043~ 9~3756~ 10~4675~ 11~3101~ 12~2596~ 15~3862~ 18~4245~, 19~235~ 20~2068~ 21~740~ 23~449~ 24~5495~?'),
  (25553, 42, 13, 22, 'And he went through the cities and villages, teaching, and journeying toward Jerusalem.', '0~2532~ 2~1279~ 3~2596~ 5~4172~ 6~2532~ 7~2968~, 8~1321~, 9~2532~ 10~4160~ 11~4197~* 12~1519~ 13~2419~.'),
  (16325, 19, 144, 11, 'Rid me, and deliver me from the hand of strange children, whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood:', '0~06475~ 3~05337~ 7~03027~ 9~05236~ 10~01121~, 12~06310~ 13~01696~ 14~07723~, 18~03225~ [19] 22~03225~ 24~08267~:'),
  (29211, 48, 6, 7, 'Be not deceived; God is not mocked: for whatsoever a man soweth, that shall he also reap.', '0~4105~ 1~3361~ 2~4105~; 3~2316~ 4~3456~ 5~3756~ 6~3456~: 7~1063~ 8~1437~ 9~3739~ 10~444~ 11~4687~, 12~5124~ 14~2325~ 15~2532~ 16~2325~.'),
  (16530, 20, 5, 4, 'But her end is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a twoedged sword.', '2~0319~ 4~04751~ 6~03939~, 7~02299~ 10~06310~ 11~02719~.'),
  (15539, 19, 102, 9, 'For I have eaten ashes like bread, and mingled my drink with weeping,', '3~0398~ 4~0665~ 6~03899~, 8~04537~ 10~08249~ 12~01065~,'),
  (20071, 24, 46, 17, 'They did cry there, Pharaoh king of Egypt is but a noise; he hath passed the time appointed.', '2~07121~ 4~06547~ 5~04428~ 7~04714~ [8 9] 11~07588~; 14~05674~ 17~04150~.'),
  (16588, 20, 7, 4, 'Say unto wisdom, Thou art my sister; and call understanding thy kinswoman:', '0~0559~ 2~02451~, [4] 6~0269~; 8~07121~ 9~0998~ [10] 11~04129~:'),
  (21585, 26, 43, 4, 'And the glory of the LORD came into the house by the way of the gate whose prospect is toward the east.', '2~03519~ 5~03068~ 6~0935~ 9~01004~ 12~01870~ 15~08179~ 17~06440~ [18] 19~01870~ 21~06921~.'),
  (6947, 7, 15, 11, 'Then three thousand men of Judah went to the top of the rock Etam, and said to Samson, Knowest thou not that the Philistines are rulers over us? what is this that thou hast done unto us? And he said unto them, As they did unto me, so have I done unto them.', '1~07969~ 2~0505~ 3~0376~ 5~03063~ 6~03381~ 9~05585~ 12~05553~ 13~05862~, 15~0559~ 17~08123~, 18~03045~ 23~06430~ [24] 25~04910~ [29] [31] 34~06213~ 39~0559~ 44~06213~ 50~06213~'),
  (25382, 42, 10, 7, 'And in the same house remain, eating and drinking such things as they give: for the labourer is worthy of his hire. Go not from house to house.', '0~1161~ 1~1722~ 3~846~ 4~3614~ 5~3306~, 6~2068~ 7~2532~ 8~4095~ 11~3844~ 12~846~ 13~3844~: 14~1063~ 16~2040~ 17~2076~ 18~514~ 20~846~ 21~3408~. 22~3327~ 23~3361~ 24~1537~ 25~3614~ 26~1519~ 27~3614~.'),
  (12638, 16, 12, 5, 'Miamin, Maadiah, Bilgah,', '0~04326~, 1~04573~, 2~01083~,'),
  (20269, 24, 51, 48, 'Then the heaven and the earth, and all that is therein, shall sing for Babylon: for the spoilers shall come unto her from the north, saith the LORD.', '2~08064~ 5~0776~, [9] 12~07442~ 14~0894~: 17~07703~ 19~0935~ 24~06828~, 25~05002~ 27~03068~.'),
  (31012, 66, 18, 3, 'For all nations have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her fornication, and the kings of the earth have committed fornication with her, and the merchants of the earth are waxed rich through the abundance of her delicacies.', '0~3754~ 1~3956~ 2~1484~ 4~4095~ 5~1537~ 7~3631~ 10~2372~ 12~846~ 13~4202~, 14~2532~ 16~935~ 19~1093~ 22~4203~ 23~3326~ 24~846~, 25~2532~ 27~1713~ 30~1093~ 33~4147~ 34~1537~ 36~1411~ 38~846~ 39~4764~.'),
  (11797, 14, 28, 24, 'And Ahaz gathered together the vessels of the house of God, and cut in pieces the vessels of the house of God, and shut up the doors of the house of the LORD, and he made him altars in every corner of Jerusalem.', '1~0271~ 3~0622~ 5~03627~ 8~01004~ 10~0430~, 14~07112~ 16~03627~ 19~01004~ 21~0430~, 24~05462~ 26~01817~ 29~01004~ 32~03068~, 35~06213~ 37~04196~ 40~06438~ 42~03389~.'),
  (27569, 44, 17, 30, 'And the times of this ignorance God winked at; but now commandeth all men every where to repent:', '0~3767~ 1~3303~ 2~5550~ 5~52~ 6~2316~ 8~5237~; 10~3569~ 11~3853~ 12~3956~ 13~444~ 15~3837~ 17~3340~:'),
  (23119, 39, 2, 7, 'For the priest''s lips should keep knowledge, and they should seek the law at his mouth: for he is the messenger of the LORD of hosts.', '2~03548~ 3~08193~ 5~08104~ 6~01847~, 10~01245~ 12~08451~ 15~06310~: [18] 20~04397~ 23~03068~ 25~06635~.'),
  (25297, 42, 8, 40, 'And it came to pass, that, when Jesus was returned, the people gladly received him: for they were all waiting for him.', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~, 6~1722~ 7~2424~ 9~5290~, 11~3793~ [12] 13~588~ 14~846~: 15~1063~ 17~2258~ 18~3956~ 20~4328~ 21~846~.'),
  (13495, 18, 27, 5, 'God forbid that I should justify you: till I die I will not remove mine integrity from me.', '1~02486~ 5~06663~ 9~01478~ 13~05493~ 15~08538~'),
  (14557, 19, 41, 6, 'And if he come to see me, he speaketh vanity: his heart gathereth iniquity to itself; when he goeth abroad, he telleth it.', '3~0935~ 5~07200~ [6] 8~01696~ 9~07723~: 11~03820~ 12~06908~ 13~0205~ [16] 18~03318~ 19~02351~, 21~01696~ [22]'),
  (3141, 3, 14, 25, 'And he shall kill the lamb of the trespass offering, and the priest shall take some of the blood of the trespass offering, and put it upon the tip of the right ear of him that is to be cleansed, and upon the thumb of his right hand, and upon the great toe of his right foot:', '3~07819~ 5~03532~ 9~0817~, 12~03548~ 14~03947~ [15] 18~01818~ 22~0817~, 24~05414~ [25] 28~08571~ 31~03233~ 32~0241~ 39~02891~, 43~0931~ 46~03233~ 47~03027~, 52~0931~ 55~03233~ 56~07272~:'),
  (12642, 16, 12, 9, 'Also Bakbukiah and Unni, their brethren, were over against them in the watches.', '1~01229~ 3~06042~, 5~0251~, [6] 12~04931~.'),
  (28089, 45, 6, 5, 'For if we have been planted together in the likeness of his death, we shall be also in the likeness of his resurrection:', '0~1063~ 1~1487~ 4~1096~ 6~4854~ 9~3667~ 11~846~ 12~2288~, 15~2071~ 16~2532~ [17 17~235~ 19] [21] 22~386~:'),
  (25415, 42, 10, 40, 'But Martha was cumbered about much serving, and came to him, and said, Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left me to serve alone? bid her therefore that she help me.', '0~1161~ 1~3136~ 3~4049~ 4~4012~ 5~4183~ 6~1248~, 7~1161~ 10~2186~, 12~2036~, 13~2962~, 14~3199~ 15~4671~ 16~3756~ 17~3199~ 18~3754~ 19~3450~ 20~79~ 22~2641~ 23~3165~ 25~1247~ 26~3441~? 27~2036~ 28~846~ 29~3767~ 30~2443~ 32~4878~ 33~3427~.'),
  (27706, 44, 21, 26, 'Then Paul took the men, and the next day purifying himself with them entered into the temple, to signify the accomplishment of the days of purification, until that an offering should be offered for every one of them.', '0~5119~ 1~3972~ 2~3880~ 4~435~, 7~2192~ 8~2250~ 10~48~ 11~4862~ 12~846~ 13~1524~ 14~1519~ 16~2411~, 18~1229~ 20~1604~ 23~2250~ 25~49~, 26~2193~ 27~3739~ 29~4376~ 32~4374~ 33~5228~ 34~1538~ 35~1520~ 37~846~.'),
  (13730, 18, 35, 1, 'Elihu spake moreover, and said,', '&para; 0~0453~ 1~06030~ 4~0559~,'),
  (9906, 12, 14, 2, 'He was twenty and five years old when he began to reign, and reigned twenty and nine years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem.', '2~06242~ 4~02568~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ 11~04427~, 13~04427~ 14~06242~ 16~08672~ 17~08141~ 19~03389~. 22~0517~ 23~08034~ [24] 25~03086~ 27~03389~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (23176, 40, 1, 22, 'Now all this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying,', '0~1161~ 1~3650~ 2~5124~ 4~1096~, 5~2443~ 9~4137~ 10~3588~ 12~4483~ 13~5259~ 15~2962~ 16~1223~ 18~4396~, 19~3004~,'),
  (14278, 19, 25, 18, 'Look upon mine affliction and my pain; and forgive all my sins.', '0~07200~ 3~06040~ 6~05999~; 8~05375~ 11~02403~.'),
  (2008, 2, 18, 4, 'And the name of the other was Eliezer; for the God of my father, said he, was mine help, and delivered me from the sword of Pharaoh:', '2~08034~ 5~0259~ [6] 7~0461~; 10~0430~ 13~01~, [14 16] 18~05828~, 20~05337~ 24~02719~ 26~06547~:'),
  (6956, 7, 15, 20, 'And he judged Israel in the days of the Philistines twenty years.', '2~08199~ 3~03478~ 6~03117~ 9~06430~ 10~06242~ 11~08141~.'),
  (3181, 3, 15, 8, 'And if he that hath the issue spit upon him that is clean; then he shall wash his clothes, and bathe himself in water, and be unclean until the even.', '6~02100~ 7~07556~ 12~02889~; 16~03526~ 18~0899~, 20~07364~ [21] 23~04325~, 26~02930~ 29~06153~.'),
  (1485, 1, 49, 7, 'Cursed be their anger, for it was fierce; and their wrath, for it was cruel: I will divide them in Jacob, and scatter them in Israel.', '0~0779~ [1] 3~0639~, [5 6] 7~05794~; 10~05678~, 14~07185~: 17~02505~ 20~03290~, 22~06327~ 25~03478~.'),
  (1683, 2, 6, 23, 'And Aaron took him Elisheba, daughter of Amminadab, sister of Naashon, to wife; and she bare him Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.', '1~0175~ 2~03947~ 4~0472~, 5~01323~ 7~05992~, 8~0269~ 10~05177~, 12~0802~; 15~03205~ 17~05070~, 19~030~, 20~0499~, 22~0385~.'),
  (861, 1, 30, 27, 'And Laban said unto him, I pray thee, if I have found favour in thine eyes, tarry: for I have learned by experience that the LORD hath blessed me for thy sake.', '1~03837~ 2~0559~ 11~04672~ 12~02580~ 15~05869~, [16 17] 22~05172~ 25~03068~ 27~01288~ 31~01558~.'),
  (10622, 13, 8, 39, 'And the sons of Eshek his brother were, Ulam his firstborn, Jehush the second, and Eliphelet the third.', '2~01121~ 4~06232~ 6~0251~ [7] 8~0198~ 10~01060~, 11~03266~ 13~08145~, 15~0467~ 17~07992~.'),
  (6207, 6, 14, 13, 'And Joshua blessed him, and gave unto Caleb the son of Jephunneh Hebron for an inheritance.', '1~03091~ 2~01288~ 5~05414~ 7~03612~ 9~01121~ 11~03312~ 12~02275~ 15~05159~.'),
  (5043, 5, 4, 33, 'Did ever people hear the voice of God speaking out of the midst of the fire, as thou hast heard, and live?', '[1] 2~05971~ 3~08085~ 5~06963~ 7~0430~ 9~01696~ 12~08432~ 15~0784~, 19~08085~, 21~02421~?'),
  (3990, 4, 9, 20, 'And so it was, when the cloud was a few days upon the tabernacle; according to the commandment of the LORD they abode in their tents, and according to the commandment of the LORD they journeyed.', '[1] 3~03426~, 6~06051~ 9~04557~ 10~03117~ 13~04908~; 17~06310~ 20~03068~ 22~02583~ 30~06310~ 33~03068~ 35~05265~.'),
  (20625, 26, 8, 12, 'Then said he unto me, Son of man, hast thou seen what the ancients of the house of Israel do in the dark, every man in the chambers of his imagery? for they say, The LORD seeth us not; the LORD hath forsaken the earth.', '1~0559~ 5~01121~ 7~0120~, 10~07200~ 13~02205~ 16~01004~ 18~03478~ 19~06213~ 22~02822~, 24~0376~ 27~02315~ 30~04906~? 33~0559~, 35~03068~ 36~07200~ 40~03068~ 42~05800~ 44~0776~.'),
  (26906, 43, 20, 23, 'Whose soever sins ye remit, they are remitted unto them; and whose soever sins ye retain, they are retained.', '0~5100~ 1~302~ 2~266~ 4~863~, 7~863~ 9~846~; [10] 11~5100~ 12~302~ [13] 15~2902~, 18~2902~.'),
  (6689, 7, 6, 28, 'And when the men of the city arose early in the morning, behold, the altar of Baal was cast down, and the grove was cut down that was by it, and the second bullock was offered upon the altar that was built.', '3~0582~ 6~05892~ 8~07925~ 11~01242~, 14~04196~ 16~01168~ 19~05422~, 22~0842~ 25~03772~ [27] 32~08145~ 33~06499~ 35~05927~ 38~04196~ [39 40] 41~01129~.'),
  (14850, 19, 63, 2, 'To see thy power and thy glory, so as I have seen thee in the sanctuary.', '1~07200~ 3~05797~ 6~03519~, [8] 11~02372~ 15~06944~.'),
  (2982, 3, 9, 24, 'And there came a fire out from before the LORD, and consumed upon the altar the burnt offering and the fat: which when all the people saw, they shouted, and fell on their faces.', '2~03318~ 4~0784~ 7~06440~ 9~03068~, 11~0398~ 14~04196~ 17~05930~ 20~02459~: [21] 25~05971~ 26~07200~, 28~07442~, 30~05307~ 33~06440~.'),
  (6825, 7, 10, 7, 'And the anger of the LORD was hot against Israel, and he sold them into the hands of the Philistines, and into the hands of the children of Ammon.', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 9~03478~, 12~04376~ 16~03027~ 19~06430~, 23~03027~ 26~01121~ 28~05983~.'),
  (7401, 9, 9, 3, 'And the asses of Kish Saul''s father were lost. And Kish said to Saul his son, Take now one of the servants with thee, and arise, go seek the asses.', '&para; 2~0860~ 4~07027~ 5~07586~ 6~01~ 8~06~. 10~07027~ 11~0559~ 13~07586~ 15~01121~, 16~03947~ 18~0259~ 21~05288~ 25~06965~, 26~03212~ 27~01245~ 29~0860~.'),
  (11692, 14, 24, 6, 'And the king called for Jehoiada the chief, and said unto him, Why hast thou not required of the Levites to bring in out of Judah and out of Jerusalem the collection, according to the commandment of Moses the servant of the LORD, and of the congregation of Israel, for the tabernacle of witness?', '2~04428~ 3~07121~ 5~03077~ 7~07218~, 9~0559~ 16~01875~ 19~03881~ 22~0935~ 25~03063~ 29~03389~ 31~04864~, [32 35] 37~04872~ 39~05650~ 42~03068~, 46~06951~ 48~03478~, 51~0168~ 53~05715~?'),
  (11050, 13, 24, 27, 'The sons of Merari by Jaaziah; Beno, and Shoham, and Zaccur, and Ibri.', '1~01121~ 3~04847~ 5~03269~; 6~01121~, 8~07719~, 10~02139~, 12~05681~.'),
  (25027, 42, 2, 42, 'And when he was twelve years old, they went up to Jerusalem after the custom of the feast.', '0~2532~ 1~3753~ 3~1096~ 4~1427~ 6~2094~, 7~846~ 9~305~ 10~1519~ 11~2414~ 12~2596~ 14~1485~ 17~1859~.'),
  (20930, 26, 20, 26, 'And I polluted them in their own gifts, in that they caused to pass through the fire all that openeth the womb, that I might make them desolate, to the end that they might know that I am the LORD.', '2~02930~ 7~04979~, 14~05674~ [15 16] 19~06363~ 21~07356~, 27~08074~, 34~03045~ [37] 39~03068~.'),
  (27475, 44, 15, 17, 'That the residue of men might seek after the Lord, and all the Gentiles, upon whom my name is called, saith the Lord, who doeth all these things.', '0~302~ 1~3704~ 2~2645~ 4~444~ 7~1567~ 9~2962~, 10~2532~ 11~3956~ 13~1484~, 14~1909~ 15~3739~ 16~3450~ 17~3686~ 19~1941~ 20~846~* 21~3004~ 23~2962~, 24~3588~ 25~4160~ 26~3956~ 28~5023~.'),
  (11118, 13, 27, 1, 'Now the children of Israel after their number, to wit, the chief fathers and captains of thousands and hundreds, and their officers that served the king in any matter of the courses, which came in and went out month by month throughout all the months of the year, of every course were twenty and four thousand.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 7~04557~, [8 9] 11~07218~ 12~01~ 14~08269~ 16~0505~ 18~03967~, 21~07860~ 23~08334~ 25~04428~ 28~01697~ 31~04256~, 34~0935~ 37~03318~ 38~02320~ 40~02320~ 44~02320~ 47~08141~, 49~0259~ 50~04256~ [51] 52~06242~ 54~0702~ 55~0505~.'),
  (8130, 10, 4, 3, 'And the Beerothites fled to Gittaim, and were sojourners there until this day.)', '2~0886~ 3~01272~ 5~01664~, 8~01481~ 12~03117~)'),
  (16346, 19, 145, 17, 'The LORD is righteous in all his ways, and holy in all his works.', '1~03068~ [2] 3~06662~ 7~01870~, 9~02623~ 13~04639~.'),
  (27222, 44, 8, 30, 'And Philip ran thither to him, and heard him read the prophet Esaias, and said, Understandest thou what thou readest?', '0~1161~ 1~5376~ 2~4370~ [5] 7~191~ 8~846~ 9~314~ 11~4396~ 12~2268~, 13~2532~ 14~2036~, 16~1097~ 17~687~* 18~1065~* 19~3739~ 21~314~?'),
  (20175, 24, 49, 39, 'But it shall come to pass in the latter days, that I will bring again the captivity of Elam, saith the LORD.', '8~0319~ 9~03117~, [10] 14~07725~ 16~07622~ 17~07622~* 19~05867~, 20~05002~ 22~03068~.'),
  (16457, 20, 2, 15, 'Whose ways are crooked, and they froward in their paths:', '1~0734~ [2] 3~06141~, [5] 6~03868~ 9~04570~:'),
  (9111, 11, 10, 24, 'And all the earth sought to Solomon, to hear his wisdom, which God had put in his heart.', '3~0776~ 4~01245~ 5~06440~ 6~08010~, 8~08085~ 10~02451~, 12~0430~ 14~05414~ 17~03820~.'),
  (13309, 18, 19, 3, 'These ten times have ye reproached me: ye are not ashamed that ye make yourselves strange to me.', '1~06235~ 2~06471~ 5~03637~ 10~0954~ [11] 15~01970~'),
  (21204, 26, 29, 12, 'And I will make the land of Egypt desolate in the midst of the countries that are desolate, and her cities among the cities that are laid waste shall be desolate forty years: and I will scatter the Egyptians among the nations, and will disperse them through the countries.', '3~05414~ 5~0776~ 7~04714~ 8~08077~ 11~08432~ 14~0776~ [15 16] 17~08074~, 20~05892~ 21~08432~ 23~05892~ [24 25] 27~02717~ 30~08077~ 31~0705~ 32~08141~: 36~06327~ 38~04714~ 41~01471~, 44~02219~ 48~0776~.'),
  (3586, 3, 27, 11, 'And if it be any unclean beast, of which they do not offer a sacrifice unto the LORD, then he shall present the beast before the priest:', '[2 3] 5~02931~ 6~0929~, 12~07126~ 14~07133~ 17~03068~, 21~05975~ 23~0929~ 24~06440~ 26~03548~:'),
  (12101, 15, 2, 65, 'Beside their servants and their maids, of whom there were seven thousand three hundred thirty and seven: and there were among them two hundred singing men and singing women.', '2~05650~ 5~0519~, [8 9] 10~07651~ 11~0505~ 12~07969~ 13~03967~ 14~07970~ 16~07651~: [18 19] 19~0428~ 23~03967~ 25~07891~ 28~07891~.'),
  (17082, 20, 23, 29, 'Who hath woe? who hath sorrow? who hath contentions? who hath babbling? who hath wounds without cause? who hath redness of eyes?', '&para; 2~0188~? 5~017~? 8~04079~ 9~04066~?* 12~07879~? 15~06482~ 17~02600~? 20~02448~ 22~05869~?'),
  (19620, 24, 27, 15, 'For I have not sent them, saith the LORD, yet they prophesy a lie in my name; that I might drive you out, and that ye might perish, ye, and the prophets that prophesy unto you.', '4~07971~ 6~05002~ 8~03068~, 11~05012~ 13~08267~ 16~08034~; 22~05080~, 27~06~, 31~05030~ 33~05012~'),
  (12189, 15, 7, 7, 'And there went up some of the children of Israel, and of the priests, and the Levites, and the singers, and the porters, and the Nethinims, unto Jerusalem, in the seventh year of Artaxerxes the king.', '3~05927~ [4] 7~01121~ 9~03478~, 13~03548~, 16~03881~, 19~07891~, 22~07778~, 25~05411~, 27~03389~, 30~07651~ 31~08141~ 33~0783~ 35~04428~.'),
  (11512, 14, 15, 13, 'That whosoever would not seek the LORD God of Israel should be put to death, whether small or great, whether man or woman.', '4~01875~ 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 9~03478~ 14~04191~, 15~04480~ 16~06996~ 18~01419~, 20~0376~ 22~0802~.'),
  (25035, 42, 2, 50, 'And they understood not the saying which he spake unto them.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~4920~ 3~3756~ 5~4487~ 6~3739~ 8~2980~ 10~846~.'),
  (20907, 26, 20, 3, 'Son of man, speak unto the elders of Israel, and say unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Are ye come to inquire of me? As I live, saith the Lord GOD, I will not be inquired of by you.', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 3~01696~ 6~02205~ 8~03478~, 10~0559~ 14~0559~ 16~0136~ 17~03069~; 20~0935~ 22~01875~ [25] 27~02416~, 28~05002~ 30~0136~ 31~03069~, 36~01875~'),
  (7192, 8, 3, 13, 'Tarry this night, and it shall be in the morning, that if he will perform unto thee the part of a kinsman, well; let him do the kinsman''s part: but if he will not do the part of a kinsman to thee, then will I do the part of a kinsman to thee, as the LORD liveth: lie down until the morning.', '0~03885~ 2~03915~, 9~01242~, [10] 21~01350~, 22~02896~; 28~01350~: 32~02654~ 39~01350~ 50~01350~ [53] 55~03068~ 56~02416~: 58~07901~ 61~01242~.'),
  (6058, 6, 9, 15, 'And Joshua made peace with them, and made a league with them, to let them live: and the princes of the congregation sware unto them.', '&para; 1~03091~ 2~06213~ 3~07965~ 7~03772~ 9~01285~ 15~02421~: 18~05387~ 21~05712~ 22~07650~'),
  (29033, 47, 11, 28, 'Beside those things that are without, that which cometh upon me daily, the care of all the churches.', '0~5565~ 5~3924~, 7~3588~ 9~1999~ 10~3450~ 11~2250~ 12~2596~,* 14~3308~ 16~3956~ 18~1577~.'),
  (10779, 13, 13, 11, 'And David was displeased, because the LORD had made a breach upon Uzza: wherefore that place is called Perezuzza to this day.', '1~01732~ 3~02734~, 6~03068~ 8~06555~ 10~06556~ 12~05798~: 15~04725~ 17~07121~ 18~06560~ 21~03117~.'),
  (2450, 2, 32, 7, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Go, get thee down; for thy people, which thou broughtest out of the land of Egypt, have corrupted themselves:', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~03212~, 9~03381~; 12~05971~, 15~05927~ 19~0776~ 21~04714~, 23~07843~ [24]'),
  (26237, 43, 5, 12, 'Then asked they him, What man is that which said unto thee, Take up thy bed, and walk?', '0~3767~ 2~2065~ 3~846~, 4~5101~ 5~444~ 6~2076~ 8~3588~ 9~2036~ 11~4671~, 13~142~ 14~4675~ 15~2895~, 16~2532~ 17~4043~?'),
  (1701, 2, 7, 11, 'Then Pharaoh also called the wise men and the sorcerers: now the magicians of Egypt, they also did in like manner with their enchantments.', '1~06547~ 3~07121~ 6~02450~ 9~03784~: 12~02748~ 14~04714~, 17~06213~ 20~03651~ 23~03858~.'),
  (29005, 47, 10, 18, 'For not he that commendeth himself is approved, but whom the Lord commendeth.', '0~1063~ 1~3756~ 2~1565~ 4~4921~ 5~1438~ 6~2076~ 7~1384~, 8~235~ 9~3739~ 11~2962~ 12~4921~.'),
  (3171, 3, 14, 55, 'And for the leprosy of a garment, and of a house,', '3~06883~ 6~0899~, 10~01004~,'),
  (20131, 24, 48, 42, 'And Moab shall be destroyed from being a people, because he hath magnified himself against the LORD.', '1~04124~ 4~08045~ [6] 8~05971~, 12~01431~ [13] 16~03068~.'),
  (7964, 9, 28, 15, 'And Samuel said to Saul, Why hast thou disquieted me, to bring me up? And Saul answered, I am sore distressed; for the Philistines make war against me, and God is departed from me, and answereth me no more, neither by prophets, nor by dreams: therefore I have called thee, that thou mayest make known unto me what I shall do.', '&para; 1~08050~ 2~0559~ 4~07586~, 8~07264~ 13~05927~? 15~07586~ 16~0559~, 19~03966~ 20~06887~; 23~06430~ 25~03898~ 29~0430~ 31~05493~ 35~06030~ 40~03027~ 41~05030~, 44~02472~: 48~07121~ 54~03045~ 60~06213~.'),
  (26456, 43, 9, 1, 'And as Jesus passed by, he saw a man which was blind from his birth.', '&para; 0~2532~ [2] 4~3855~, 6~1492~ 8~444~ 11~5185~ 12~1537~ [13] 14~1079~.'),
  (1969, 2, 16, 17, 'And the children of Israel did so, and gathered, some more, some less.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 8~03950~, 10~07235~, 12~04591~.'),
  (12080, 15, 2, 44, 'The children of Keros, the children of Siaha, the children of Padon,', '1~01121~ 3~07026~, 5~01121~ 7~05517~, 9~01121~ 11~06303~,'),
  (24083, 40, 26, 19, 'And the disciples did as Jesus had appointed them; and they made ready the passover.', '0~2532~ 2~3101~ 3~4160~ 4~5613~ 5~2424~ 7~4929~ 8~846~; 9~2532~ 12~2090~ 14~3957~.'),
  (7607, 9, 16, 5, 'And he said, Peaceably: I am come to sacrifice unto the LORD: sanctify yourselves, and come with me to the sacrifice. And he sanctified Jesse and his sons, and called them to the sacrifice.', '2~0559~, 3~07965~: 6~0935~ 8~02076~ 11~03068~: 12~06942~ 15~0935~ 20~02077~. 23~06942~ 24~03448~ 27~01121~, 29~07121~ 33~02077~.'),
  (3353, 3, 21, 3, 'And for his sister a virgin, that is nigh unto him, which hath had no husband; for her may he be defiled.', '3~0269~ 5~01330~, 8~07138~ 15~0376~; 21~02930~.'),
  (8354, 10, 13, 30, 'And it came to pass, while they were in the way, that tidings came to David, saying, Absalom hath slain all the king''s sons, and there is not one of them left.', '&para; 10~01870~, 12~08052~ 13~0935~ 15~01732~, 16~0559~, 17~053~ 19~05221~ 22~04428~ 23~01121~, 28~0259~ 31~03498~.'),
  (26378, 43, 7, 35, 'Then said the Jews among themselves, Whither will he go, that we shall not find him? will he go unto the dispersed among the Gentiles, and teach the Gentiles?', '0~3767~ 1~2036~ 3~2453~ 4~4314~ 5~1438~, 6~4226~ 7~3195~ 8~3778~ 9~4198~, 10~3754~ 11~2249~ 12~2147~ 13~3756~ 14~2147~ 15~846~? 16~3195~ 17~3361~* 19~4198~ 20~1519~ 22~1290~ 25~1672~, 26~2532~ 27~1321~ 29~1672~?'),
  (29439, 50, 3, 2, 'Beware of dogs, beware of evil workers, beware of the concision.', '0~991~ 2~2965~, 3~991~ 5~2556~ 6~2040~, 7~991~ 10~2699~.'),
  (17760, 23, 5, 12, 'And the harp, and the viol, the tabret, and pipe, and wine, are in their feasts: but they regard not the work of the LORD, neither consider the operation of his hands.', '2~03658~, 5~05035~, 7~08596~, 9~02485~, 11~03196~, 15~04960~: 18~05027~ 21~06467~ 24~03068~, 26~07200~ 28~04639~ 31~03027~.'),
  (27346, 44, 11, 23, 'Who, when he came, and had seen the grace of God, was glad, and exhorted them all, that with purpose of heart they would cleave unto the Lord.', '0~3739~, 3~3854~, 4~2532~ 6~1492~ 8~5485~ 10~2316~, 12~5463~, 13~2532~ 14~3870~ 16~3956~, 19~4286~ 21~2588~ 25~4357~ 27~2962~.'),
  (813, 1, 29, 14, 'And Laban said to him, Surely thou art my bone and my flesh. And he abode with him the space of a month.', '1~03837~ 2~0559~ 5~0389~ [7] 9~06106~ 12~01320~. 15~03427~ 19~03117~ 22~02320~.'),
  (7636, 9, 17, 11, 'When Saul and all Israel heard those words of the Philistine, they were dismayed, and greatly afraid.', '1~07586~ 4~03478~ 5~08085~ 7~01697~ 10~06430~, 13~02865~, 15~03966~ 16~03372~.'),
  (10871, 13, 16, 43, 'And all the people departed every man to his house: and David returned to bless his house.', '3~05971~ 4~03212~ 6~0376~ 9~01004~: 11~01732~ 12~05437~ 14~01288~ 16~01004~.'),
  (26598, 43, 12, 3, 'Then took Mary a pound of ointment of spikenard, very costly, and anointed the feet of Jesus, and wiped his feet with her hair: and the house was filled with the odour of the ointment.', '0~3767~ 1~2983~ 2~3137~ 4~3046~ 6~3464~ 8~4101~ 9~3487~,* 11~4186~, 13~218~ 15~4228~ 17~2424~, 18~2532~ 19~1591~ 20~846~ 21~4228~ 23~846~ 24~2359~: 25~1161~ 27~3614~ 29~4137~ 30~1537~ 32~3744~ 35~3464~.'),
  (23007, 38, 8, 22, 'Yea, many people and strong nations shall come to seek the LORD of hosts in Jerusalem, and to pray before the LORD.', '1~07227~ 2~05971~ 4~06099~ 5~01471~ 7~0935~ 9~01245~ 11~03068~ 13~06635~ 15~03389~, 18~02470~ 19~06440~ 21~03068~.'),
  (8716, 10, 24, 16, 'And when the angel stretched out his hand upon Jerusalem to destroy it, the LORD repented him of the evil, and said to the angel that destroyed the people, It is enough: stay now thine hand. And the angel of the LORD was by the threshingplace of Araunah the Jebusite.', '3~04397~ 5~07971~ 7~03027~ 9~03389~ 11~07843~ 14~03068~ 15~05162~ 19~07451~, 21~0559~ 24~04397~ 26~07843~ 28~05971~, 31~07227~: 32~07503~ 35~03027~. 38~04397~ 41~03068~ 45~01637~ 47~0728~ 49~02983~.'),
  (12676, 16, 12, 43, 'Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced: for God had made them rejoice with great joy: the wives also and the children rejoiced: so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard even afar off.', '2~03117~ 4~02076~ 5~01419~ 6~02077~, 8~08055~: 10~0430~ 14~08055~ 16~01419~ 17~08057~: 19~0802~ 23~03206~ 24~08055~: 28~08057~ 30~03389~ 32~08085~ 35~07350~.'),
  (22449, 30, 5, 17, 'And in all vineyards shall be wailing: for I will pass through thee, saith the LORD.', '3~03754~ [4 5] 6~04553~: 10~05674~ 11~07130~ 13~0559~ 15~03068~.'),
  (22704, 34, 1, 11, 'There is one come out of thee, that imagineth evil against the LORD, a wicked counsellor.', '[2] 4~03318~ 8~02803~ 9~07451~ 12~03068~, 14~01100~ 15~03289~.'),
  (22083, 27, 11, 38, 'But in his estate shall he honour the God of forces: and a god whom his fathers knew not shall he honour with gold, and silver, and with precious stones, and pleasant things.', '3~03653~ 6~03513~ 8~0433~ 10~04581~: 13~0433~ 16~01~ 17~03045~ 21~03513~ 23~02091~, 25~03701~, 28~03368~ 29~068~, 32~02532~.'),
  (7944, 9, 27, 7, 'And the time that David dwelt in the country of the Philistines was a full year and four months.', '2~03117~ 3~04557~ 4~01732~ 5~03427~ 8~07704~ 11~06430~ 15~03117~ 17~0702~ 18~02320~.'),
  (12649, 16, 12, 16, 'Of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam;', '1~05714~, 2~02148~; 4~01599~, 5~04918~;'),
  (646, 1, 24, 51, 'Behold, Rebekah is before thee, take her, and go, and let her be thy master''s son''s wife, as the LORD hath spoken.', '1~07259~ [2] 4~06440~, 5~03947~ [6] 8~03212~, 14~0113~ 15~01121~ 16~0802~, 19~03068~ 21~01696~.'),
  (25305, 42, 8, 48, 'And he said unto her, Daughter, be of good comfort: thy faith hath made thee whole; go in peace.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~2364~, 9~2293~: 10~4675~ 11~4102~ 13~4982~ 14~4571~ 15~4982~; 16~4198~ 17~1519~ 18~1515~.'),
  (14421, 19, 35, 2, 'Take hold of shield and buckler, and stand up for mine help.', '1~02388~ 3~04043~ 5~06793~, 8~06965~ 11~05833~.'),
  (18084, 23, 22, 23, 'And I will fasten him as a nail in a sure place; and he shall be for a glorious throne to his father''s house.', '3~08628~ [5] 7~03489~ 10~0539~ 11~04725~; 18~03519~ 19~03678~ 22~01~ 23~01004~.'),
  (14795, 19, 58, 7, 'Let them melt away as waters which run continually: when he bendeth his bow to shoot his arrows, let them be as cut in pieces.', '3~03988~ 5~04325~ [6] 8~01980~: [9] 11~01869~ [12 15] 17~02671~, 24~04135~.'),
  (13213, 18, 15, 1, 'Then answered Eliphaz the Temanite, and said,', '&para; 1~06030~ 2~0464~ 4~08489~, 6~0559~,'),
  (2079, 2, 20, 23, 'Ye shall not make with me gods of silver, neither shall ye make unto you gods of gold.', '3~06213~ 6~0430~ 8~03701~, 12~06213~ 15~0430~ 17~02091~.'),
  (8662, 10, 23, 1, 'Now these be the last words of David. David the son of Jesse said, and the man who was raised up on high, the anointed of the God of Jacob, and the sweet psalmist of Israel, said,', '&para; [2] 4~0314~ 5~01697~ 7~01732~. 8~01732~ 10~01121~ 12~03448~ 13~05002~, 16~01397~ [17 18] 20~06965~ 22~05920~, 24~04899~ 27~0430~ 29~03290~, 32~05273~ 33~02158~ 35~03478~, 36~05002~,'),
  (18148, 23, 26, 9, 'With my soul have I desired thee in the night; yea, with my spirit within me will I seek thee early: for when thy judgments are in the earth, the inhabitants of the world will learn righteousness.', '2~05315~ 5~0183~ 9~03915~; 13~07307~ 14~07130~ 20~07836~: 24~04941~ [25] 28~0776~, 30~03427~ 33~08398~ 35~03925~ 36~06664~.'),
  (27298, 44, 10, 23, 'Then called he them in, and lodged them. And on the morrow Peter went away with them, and certain brethren from Joppa accompanied him.', '0~3767~ 2~1528~ 3~846~ 4~1528~, 6~3579~ [7] 8~1161~ 11~1887~ 12~4074~ 14~1831~ 15~4862~ 16~846~, 17~2532~ 18~5100~ 19~80~ 20~575~ 21~2445~ 22~4905~ 23~846~.'),
  (13738, 18, 35, 9, 'By reason of the multitude of oppressions they make the oppressed to cry: they cry out by reason of the arm of the mighty.', '&para; 4~07230~ 6~06217~ [9 10] 12~02199~: 15~07768~ 20~02220~ 23~07227~.'),
  (21197, 26, 29, 5, 'And I will leave thee thrown into the wilderness, thee and all the fish of thy rivers: thou shalt fall upon the open fields; thou shalt not be brought together, nor gathered: I have given thee for meat to the beasts of the field and to the fowls of the heaven.', '3~05203~ [5] 8~04057~, 13~01710~ 16~02975~: 19~05307~ 22~06440~ 23~07704~; 29~0622~, 31~06908~: 34~05414~ 37~0402~ 40~02416~ 43~0776~ 47~05775~ 50~08064~.'),
  (21379, 26, 36, 11, 'And I will multiply upon you man and beast; and they shall increase and bring fruit: and I will settle you after your old estates, and will do better unto you than at your beginnings: and ye shall know that I am the LORD.', '3~07235~ 6~0120~ 8~0929~; 12~07235~ 15~06509~: 19~03427~ 24~06927~, 28~02895~ [29 30] 34~07221~: 38~03045~ [41] 43~03068~.'),
  (11986, 14, 35, 11, 'And they killed the passover, and the priests sprinkled the blood from their hands, and the Levites flayed them.', '2~07819~ 4~06453~, 7~03548~ 8~02236~ [9 10] 13~03027~, 16~03881~ 17~06584~ [18]'),
  (23103, 39, 1, 5, 'And your eyes shall see, and ye shall say, The LORD will be magnified from the border of Israel.', '2~05869~ 4~07200~, 8~0559~, 10~03068~ 13~01431~ 16~01366~ 18~03478~.'),
  (25740, 42, 18, 38, 'And he cried, saying, Jesus, thou son of David, have mercy on me.', '0~2532~ 2~994~, 3~3004~, 4~2424~, [5] 6~5207~ 8~1138~, 10~1653~ 12~3165~.'),
  (7694, 9, 18, 11, 'And Saul cast the javelin; for he said, I will smite David even to the wall with it. And David avoided out of his presence twice.', '1~07586~ 2~02904~ 4~02595~; 7~0559~, 10~05221~ 11~01732~ 15~07023~ [16 17] 19~01732~ 21~05437~ 24~06440~ 25~06471~.'),
  (2951, 3, 8, 29, 'And Moses took the breast, and waved it for a wave offering before the LORD: for of the ram of consecration it was Moses'' part; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '1~04872~ 2~03947~ 4~02373~, 6~05130~ [8] 11~08573~ 12~06440~ 14~03068~: [15] 18~0352~ 20~04394~ 23~04872~ 24~04490~; 27~03068~ 28~06680~ 29~04872~.'),
  (7236, 9, 1, 17, 'Then Eli answered and said, Go in peace: and the God of Israel grant thee thy petition that thou hast asked of him.', '1~05941~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~, 5~03212~ 7~07965~: 10~0430~ 12~03478~ 13~05414~ [14] 16~07596~ 20~07592~'),
  (28023, 45, 3, 16, 'Destruction and misery are in their ways:', '0~4938~ 1~2532~ 2~5004~ [3] 4~1722~ 5~846~ 6~3598~:'),
  (25371, 42, 9, 58, 'And Jesus said unto him, Foxes have holes, and birds of the air have nests; but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~258~ 6~2192~ 7~5454~, 8~2532~ 9~4071~ 12~3772~ [13] 14~2682~; 15~1161~ 17~5207~ 19~444~ 20~2192~ 21~3756~ 22~4226~ 24~2827~ [25] 26~2776~.'),
  (19741, 24, 32, 1, 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD in the tenth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, which was the eighteenth year of Nebuchadrezzar.', '&para; 1~01697~ 5~03414~ 8~03068~ 11~06224~ 12~08141~ 14~06667~ 15~04428~ 17~03063~, [19] 21~08141~ 22~08083~* 23~06240~* 24~08141~ 26~05019~.'),
  (29506, 51, 1, 25, 'Whereof I am made a minister, according to the dispensation of God which is given to me for you, to fulfil the word of God;', '0~3739~ 1~1473~ 3~1096~ 5~1249~, 7~2596~ 9~3622~ 11~2316~ 12~3588~ 14~1325~ 16~3427~ 17~1519~ 18~5209~, 20~4137~ 22~3056~ 24~2316~;'),
  (10799, 13, 14, 17, 'And the fame of David went out into all lands; and the LORD brought the fear of him upon all nations.', '2~08034~ 4~01732~ 6~03318~ 9~0776~; 12~03068~ 13~05414~ 15~06343~ 20~01471~.'),
  (3998, 4, 10, 5, 'When ye blow an alarm, then the camps that lie on the east parts shall go forward.', '2~08628~ 4~08643~, 7~04264~ 9~02583~ 13~06924~ 16~05265~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (27586, 44, 18, 13, 'Saying, This fellow persuadeth men to worship God contrary to the law.', '0~3004~ 1~3754~,* 2~3778~ [3] 4~374~ 5~444~ 7~4576~ 8~2316~ 9~3844~ 12~3551~.'),
  (21323, 26, 34, 1, 'And the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (25774, 42, 19, 29, 'And it came to pass, when he was come nigh to Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount called the mount of Olives, he sent two of his disciples,', '0~2532~ 4~1096~, 5~5613~ 9~1448~ 10~1519~ 11~967~ 12~2532~ 13~963~, 14~4314~ 16~3735~ 17~2564~ [18 19] 21~1636~, 23~649~ 24~1417~ 26~846~ 27~3101~,'),
  (1664, 2, 6, 4, 'And I have also established my covenant with them, to give them the land of Canaan, the land of their pilgrimage, wherein they were strangers.', '4~06965~ 6~01285~ 10~05414~ 13~0776~ 15~03667~, 17~0776~ 20~04033~, 24~01481~.'),
  (13806, 18, 38, 4, 'Where wast thou when I laid the foundations of the earth? declare, if thou hast understanding.', '&para; 0~0375~ 7~03245~ 10~0776~? 11~05046~, 14~03045~ 15~0998~.'),
  (23051, 38, 11, 14, 'Then I cut asunder mine other staff, even Bands, that I might break the brotherhood between Judah and Israel.', '3~01438~ 5~08145~ 6~04731~, [7] 8~02254~, 12~06565~ 14~0264~ 16~03063~ 18~03478~.'),
  (28078, 45, 5, 15, 'But not as the offence, so also is the free gift. For if through the offence of one many be dead, much more the grace of God, and the gift by grace, which is by one man, Jesus Christ, hath abounded unto many.', '0~235~ 1~3756~ 2~5613~ 4~3900~, 5~3779~ 6~2532~ [7] 10~5486~. 11~1063~ 12~1487~ 15~3900~ 17~1520~ 18~4183~ 20~599~, 21~4183~ 22~3123~ 24~5485~ 26~2316~, 27~2532~ 29~1431~ 30~1722~ 31~5485~, [32 33] 33~3588~ 35~1520~ 36~444~, 37~2424~ 38~5547~, 40~4052~ 41~1519~ 42~4183~.'),
  (30062, 58, 6, 2, 'Of the doctrine of baptisms, and of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.', '2~1322~ 4~909~, 5~5037~ 8~1936~ 10~5495~, 11~5037~ 13~386~ 16~3498~, 17~2532~ 19~166~ 20~2917~.'),
  (24249, 41, 1, 24, 'Saying, Let us alone; what have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of Nazareth? art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art, the Holy One of God.', '0~3004~, [2] 3~1436~; 4~5101~ 6~2254~ 8~2532~ 10~4671~, 12~2424~ 14~3479~? 17~2064~ 19~622~ 20~2248~? 22~1492~ 23~4571~ 24~5101~ 26~1488~, 29~40~ 31~2316~.'),
  (24870, 41, 15, 33, 'And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1096~ 3~1623~ 4~5610~ 6~1096~, 8~1096~ 9~4655~ 10~1909~ 12~3650~ 13~1093~ 14~2193~ 16~1766~ 17~5610~.'),
  (9026, 11, 8, 33, 'When thy people Israel be smitten down before the enemy, because they have sinned against thee, and shall turn again to thee, and confess thy name, and pray, and make supplication unto thee in this house:', '2~05971~ 3~03478~ 6~05062~ 7~06440~ 9~0341~, 13~02398~ 19~07725~ 23~03034~ 25~08034~, 27~06419~, 30~02603~ 35~01004~:'),
  (3450, 3, 23, 43, 'That your generations may know that I made the children of Israel to dwell in booths, when I brought them out of the land of Egypt: I am the LORD your God.', '2~01755~ 4~03045~ 9~01121~ 11~03478~ 13~03427~ 15~05521~, 20~03318~ 23~0776~ 25~04714~: [27] 29~03068~ 31~0430~.'),
  (19170, 24, 8, 8, 'How do ye say, We are wise, and the law of the LORD is with us? Lo, certainly in vain made he it; the pen of the scribes is in vain.', '3~0559~, [5] 6~02450~, 9~08451~ 12~03068~ [13] 17~0403~ 19~08267~ 20~06213~ [22] 24~05842~ 27~05608~ [28] 30~08267~.'),
  (15757, 19, 108, 6, 'That thy beloved may be delivered: save with thy right hand, and answer me.', '&para; 2~03039~ 5~02502~: 6~03467~ [7] 10~03225~, 12~06030~'),
  (12336, 16, 2, 20, 'Then answered I them, and said unto them, The God of heaven, he will prosper us; therefore we his servants will arise and build: but ye have no portion, nor right, nor memorial, in Jerusalem.', '1~07725~ 2~01697~* 6~0559~ 10~0430~ 12~08064~, 15~06743~ 20~05650~ 22~06965~ 24~01129~: 29~02506~, 31~06666~, 33~02146~, 35~03389~.'),
  (22102, 27, 12, 12, 'Blessed is he that waiteth, and cometh to the thousand three hundred and five and thirty days.', '0~0835~ [1] 4~02442~, 6~05060~ 9~0505~ 10~07969~ 11~03967~ 13~02568~ 15~07970~ 16~03117~.'),
  (28032, 45, 3, 25, 'Whom God hath set forth to be a propitiation through faith in his blood, to declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are past, through the forbearance of God;', '0~3739~ 1~2316~ 4~4388~ [5 6] 8~2435~ 9~1223~ 10~4102~ 11~1722~ 12~846~ 13~129~, 14~1519~ 15~1732~ 16~846~ 17~1343~ 18~1223~ 20~3929~ 22~265~ 25~4266~, 26~1722~ 28~463~ 30~2316~;'),
  (6306, 6, 18, 6, 'Ye shall therefore describe the land into seven parts, and bring the description hither to me, that I may cast lots for you here before the LORD our God.', '3~03789~ 5~0776~ [6] 7~07651~ 8~02506~, 10~0935~ [11 12] 19~03384~ 20~01486~ 24~06440~ 26~03068~ 28~0430~.'),
  (13987, 19, 5, 5, 'The foolish shall not stand in thy sight: thou hatest all workers of iniquity.', '1~01984~ 4~03320~ 7~05869~: 9~08130~ 11~06466~ 13~0205~.'),
  (8290, 10, 11, 24, 'And the shooters shot from off the wall upon thy servants; and some of the king''s servants be dead, and thy servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.', '2~03384~ 3~03384~ 7~02346~ 10~05650~; [12] 15~04428~ 16~05650~ 18~04191~, 21~05650~ 22~0223~ 24~02850~ 26~04191~'),
  (14326, 19, 29, 9, 'The voice of the LORD maketh the hinds to calve, and discovereth the forests: and in his temple doth every one speak of his glory.', '1~06963~ 4~03068~ 7~0355~ 9~02342~, 11~02834~ 13~03295~: 17~01964~ 21~0559~ [23] 24~03519~.'),
  (2342, 2, 29, 1, 'And this is the thing that thou shalt do unto them to hallow them, to minister unto me in the priest''s office: Take one young bullock, and two rams without blemish,', '&para; [2] 4~01697~ 8~06213~ 12~06942~ 21~03547~: 22~03947~ 23~0259~ 24~01241~ 25~01121~* 26~06499~, 28~08147~ 29~0352~ 31~08549~,'),
  (20642, 26, 9, 11, 'And, behold, the man clothed with linen, which had the inkhorn by his side, reported the matter, saying, I have done as thou hast commanded me.', '3~0376~ 4~03847~ 6~0906~, [8] 10~07083~ 13~04975~, 14~07725~ 16~01697~, 17~0559~, 20~06213~ 24~06680~'),
  (9587, 12, 3, 3, 'Nevertheless he cleaved unto the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, which made Israel to sin; he departed not therefrom.', '2~01692~ 5~02403~ 7~03379~ 9~01121~ 11~05028~, 14~03478~ 16~02398~; 18~05493~'),
  (15088, 19, 75, 8, 'For in the hand of the LORD there is a cup, and the wine is red; it is full of mixture; and he poureth out of the same: but the dregs thereof, all the wicked of the earth shall wring them out, and drink them.', '3~03027~ 6~03068~ [7 8] 10~03563~, 13~03196~ 15~02560~; 18~04392~ 20~04538~; 24~05064~ 27~02088~: 30~08105~ 34~07563~ 37~0776~ [40] 41~04680~, [42] 43~08354~ [44]'),
  (19176, 24, 8, 14, 'Why do we sit still? assemble yourselves, and let us enter into the defenced cities, and let us be silent there: for the LORD our God hath put us to silence, and given us water of gall to drink, because we have sinned against the LORD.', '4~03427~? 5~0622~ 10~0935~ 13~04013~ 14~05892~, 19~01826~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~ 30~01826~, 34~04325~ 36~07219~ 38~08248~, 42~02398~ 45~03068~.'),
  (14048, 19, 9, 18, 'For the needy shall not alway be forgotten: the expectation of the poor shall not perish for ever.', '2~034~ 5~05331~ 7~07911~: 9~08615~ 12~06041~ 13~06035~* [15] 16~06~ 18~05703~.'),
  (19902, 24, 37, 19, 'Where are now your prophets which prophesied unto you, saying, The king of Babylon shall not come against you, nor against this land?', '[1] 2~0346~ 4~05030~ 6~05012~ 9~0559~, 11~04428~ 13~0894~ 16~0935~ 22~0776~?'),
  (9034, 11, 8, 41, 'Moreover concerning a stranger, that is not of thy people Israel, but cometh out of a far country for thy name''s sake;', '3~05237~, [5] 9~05971~ 10~03478~, 13~0935~ 16~07350~ 17~0776~ 18~04616~ 20~08034~'),
  (12284, 15, 10, 23, 'Also of the Levites; Jozabad, and Shimei, and Kelaiah, (the same is Kelita,) Pethahiah, Judah, and Eliezer.', '3~03881~; 4~03107~, 6~08096~, 8~07041~, [11] 12~07042~,) 13~06611~, 14~03063~, 16~0461~.'),
  (30956, 66, 14, 14, 'And I looked, and behold a white cloud, and upon the cloud one sat like unto the Son of man, having on his head a golden crown, and in his hand a sharp sickle.', '0~2532~ 2~1492~, 3~2532~ 4~2400~ 6~3022~ 7~3507~, 8~2532~ 9~1909~ 11~3507~ [12] 13~2521~ 14~3664~ 17~5207~ 19~444~, 20~2192~ 21~1909~ 22~846~ 23~2776~ 25~5552~ 26~4735~, 27~2532~ 28~1722~ 29~846~ 30~5495~ 32~3691~ 33~1407~.'),
  (10037, 12, 18, 5, 'He trusted in the LORD God of Israel; so that after him was none like him among all the kings of Judah, nor any that were before him.', '1~0982~ 4~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~03478~; 10~0310~ 19~04428~ 21~03063~, [23] 26~06440~'),
  (14164, 19, 18, 37, 'I have pursued mine enemies, and overtaken them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed.', '2~07291~ 4~0341~, 6~05381~ 12~07725~ 16~03615~.'),
  (19661, 24, 29, 17, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Behold, I will send upon them the sword, the famine, and the pestilence, and will make them like vile figs, that cannot be eaten, they are so evil.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~; 9~07971~ 13~02719~, 15~07458~, 18~01698~, 21~05414~ 24~08182~ 25~08384~, 29~0398~, 33~07455~.'),
  (25562, 42, 13, 31, 'The same day there came certain of the Pharisees, saying unto him, Get thee out, and depart hence: for Herod will kill thee.', '&para; 1~846~ 2~1722~* 3~2250~ 5~4334~ 6~5100~ 9~5330~, 10~3004~ 12~846~, 15~1831~, 16~2532~ 17~4198~ 18~1782~: 19~3754~ 20~2264~ 21~2309~ 22~615~ 23~4571~.'),
  (9273, 11, 15, 16, 'And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.', '3~04421~ 5~0609~ 7~01201~ 8~04428~ 10~03478~ 13~03117~.'),
  (5978, 6, 6, 23, 'And the young men that were spies went in, and brought out Rahab, and her father, and her mother, and her brethren, and all that she had; and they brought out all her kindred, and left them without the camp of Israel.', '3~05288~ 6~07270~ 8~0935~, 11~03318~ 12~07343~, 15~01~, 18~0517~, 21~0251~, 30~03318~ 33~04940~, 35~03240~ 37~02351~ 39~04264~ 41~03478~.'),
  (19417, 24, 19, 1, 'Thus saith the LORD, Go and get a potter''s earthen bottle, and take of the ancients of the people, and of the ancients of the priests;', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~, 4~01980~ 6~07069~ 8~03335~ 9~02789~ 10~01228~, [12] 15~02205~ 18~05971~, 22~02205~ 25~03548~;'),
  (12468, 16, 7, 39, 'The priests: the children of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred seventy and three.', '1~03548~: 3~01121~ 5~03048~, 8~01004~ 10~03442~, 11~08672~ 12~03967~ 13~07657~ 15~07969~.'),
  (24708, 41, 12, 24, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, Do ye not therefore err, because ye know not the scriptures, neither the power of God?', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 7~4105~ 8~3756~ 9~5124~ 10~1223~* 11~4105~, 14~1492~ 15~3361~ 17~1124~, 18~3366~ 20~1411~ 22~2316~?'),
  (7942, 9, 27, 5, 'And David said unto Achish, If I have now found grace in thine eyes, let them give me a place in some town in the country, that I may dwell there: for why should thy servant dwell in the royal city with thee?', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~0397~, 9~04672~ 10~02580~ 13~05869~, 16~05414~ 19~04725~ 21~0259~ 22~05892~ 25~07704~, 29~03427~ 35~05650~ 36~03427~ 39~04467~ 40~05892~'),
  (7395, 9, 8, 19, 'Nevertheless the people refused to obey the voice of Samuel; and they said, Nay; but we will have a king over us;', '2~05971~ 3~03985~ 5~08085~ 7~06963~ 9~08050~; 12~0559~, 19~04428~'),
  (19241, 24, 11, 6, 'Then the LORD said unto me, Proclaim all these words in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem, saying, Hear ye the words of this covenant, and do them.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~07121~ 9~01697~ 12~05892~ 14~03063~, 18~02351~ 20~03389~, 21~0559~, 22~08085~ 25~01697~ 28~01285~, 30~06213~'),
  (12471, 16, 7, 42, 'The children of Harim, a thousand and seventeen.', '1~01121~ 3~02766~, 5~0505~ 7~06240~ 8~07651~.*'),
  (17519, 21, 10, 17, 'Blessed art thou, O land, when thy king is the son of nobles, and thy princes eat in due season, for strength, and not for drunkenness!', '0~0835~ [1] 4~0776~, 7~04428~ [8] 10~01121~ 12~02715~, 15~08269~ 16~0398~ 19~06256~, 21~01369~, 25~08358~!'),
  (2323, 2, 28, 25, 'And the other two ends of the two wreathen chains thou shalt fasten in the two ouches, and put them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod before it.', '[1 2] 3~08147~ 4~07098~ 7~08147~ 8~05688~ [9] 12~05414~ 15~08147~ 16~04865~, 18~05414~ [19] 22~03802~ 25~0646~ 26~06440~ 27~04136~.'),
  (9772, 12, 9, 8, 'For the whole house of Ahab shall perish: and I will cut off from Ahab him that pisseth against the wall, and him that is shut up and left in Israel:', '3~01004~ 5~0256~ 7~06~: 12~03772~ 14~0256~ 17~08366~ 20~07023~, 26~06113~ 28~05800~ 30~03478~:'),
  (30625, 62, 4, 6, 'We are of God: he that knoweth God heareth us; he that is not of God heareth not us. Hereby know we the spirit of truth, and the spirit of error.', '0~2249~ 1~2070~ 2~1537~ 3~2316~: 6~1097~ 7~2316~ 8~191~ 9~2257~; 11~3739~ 12~2076~ 13~3756~ 14~1537~ 15~2316~ 16~191~ 17~3756~ 18~2257~. 19~5127~ 20~1537~ 21~1097~ 23~4151~ 25~225~, 26~2532~ 28~4151~ 30~4106~.'),
  (28591, 46, 10, 8, 'Neither let us commit fornication, as some of them committed, and fell in one day three and twenty thousand.', '0~3366~ 4~4203~, 5~2531~ 6~5100~ 8~846~ 9~4203~, 10~2532~ 11~4098~ 12~1722~ 13~3391~ 14~2250~ 15~5140~ 17~1501~ 18~5505~.'),
  (27241, 44, 9, 9, 'And he was three days without sight, and neither did eat nor drink.', '0~2532~ 2~2258~ 3~5140~ 4~2250~ 5~3361~ 6~991~, 7~2532~ 8~3756~ 10~5315~ 11~3761~ 12~4095~.'),
  (25220, 42, 7, 13, 'And when the Lord saw her, he had compassion on her, and said unto her, Weep not.', '0~2532~ 3~2962~ 4~1492~ 5~846~, 8~4697~ 9~1909~ 10~846~, 11~2532~ 12~2036~ 14~846~, 15~2799~ 16~3361~.'),
  (11164, 13, 28, 13, 'Also for the courses of the priests and the Levites, and for all the work of the service of the house of the LORD, and for all the vessels of service in the house of the LORD.', '3~04256~ 6~03548~ 9~03881~, 14~04399~ 17~05656~ 20~01004~ 23~03068~, 28~03627~ 30~05656~ 33~01004~ 36~03068~.'),
  (19362, 24, 16, 17, 'For mine eyes are upon all their ways: they are not hid from my face, neither is their iniquity hid from mine eyes.', '2~05869~ [3] 7~01870~: 11~05641~ 14~06440~, 18~05771~ 19~06845~ 20~05048~ 22~05869~.'),
  (8602, 10, 21, 14, 'And the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son buried they in the country of Benjamin in Zelah, in the sepulchre of Kish his father: and they performed all that the king commanded. And after that God was entreated for the land.', '2~06106~ 4~07586~ 6~03083~ 8~01121~ 9~06912~ 13~0776~ 15~01144~ 17~06762~, 20~06913~ 22~07027~ 24~01~: 27~06213~ 31~04428~ 32~06680~. 34~0310~ 36~0430~ 38~06279~ 41~0776~.'),
  (25738, 42, 18, 36, 'And hearing the multitude pass by, he asked what it meant.', '0~1161~ 1~191~ 3~3793~ 5~1279~, 7~4441~ 8~5101~ 9~5124~ 10~1498~.'),
  (4612, 4, 28, 29, 'A several tenth deal unto one lamb, throughout the seven lambs;', '3~06241~ 5~0259~ 6~03532~, 9~07651~ 10~03532~;'),
  (3993, 4, 9, 23, 'At the commandment of the LORD they rested in the tents, and at the commandment of the LORD they journeyed: they kept the charge of the LORD, at the commandment of the LORD by the hand of Moses.', '2~06310~ 5~03068~ 7~02583~ 14~06310~ 17~03068~ 19~05265~: 21~08104~ 23~04931~ 26~03068~, 29~06310~ 32~03068~ 35~03027~ 37~04872~.'),
  (23813, 40, 20, 11, 'And when they had received it, they murmured against the goodman of the house,', '0~1161~ 4~2983~ [5] 7~1111~ 8~2596~ 13~3617~,'),
  (6077, 6, 10, 7, 'So Joshua ascended from Gilgal, he, and all the people of war with him, and all the mighty men of valour.', '&para; 1~03091~ 2~05927~ 4~01537~, 9~05971~ 11~04421~ 17~01368~ 20~02428~.'),
  (10160, 12, 22, 7, 'Howbeit there was no reckoning made with them of the money that was delivered into their hand, because they dealt faithfully.', '5~02803~ 10~03701~ 13~05414~ 16~03027~, 19~06213~ 20~0530~.'),
  (21230, 26, 30, 17, 'The young men of Aven and of Pibeseth shall fall by the sword: and these cities shall go into captivity.', '2~0970~ 4~0206~ 7~06364~ 9~05307~ 12~02719~: [15] 17~03212~ 19~07628~.'),
  (17107, 20, 24, 19, 'Fret not thyself because of evil men, neither be thou envious at the wicked;', '&para; 0~02734~ 5~07489~ [6] 10~07065~ 13~07563~;'),
  (20431, 25, 4, 2, 'The precious sons of Zion, comparable to fine gold, how are they esteemed as earthen pitchers, the work of the hands of the potter!', '1~03368~ 2~01121~ 4~06726~, 5~05537~ 8~06337~, 12~02803~ 14~02789~ 15~05035~, 17~04639~ 20~03027~ 23~03335~!'),
  (10050, 12, 18, 18, 'And when they had called to the king, there came out to them Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, which was over the household, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph the recorder.', '4~07121~ 7~04428~, 10~03318~ 13~0471~ 15~01121~ 17~02518~, [19] 22~01004~, 24~07644~ 26~05608~, 28~03098~ 30~01121~ 32~0623~ 34~02142~.'),
  (7185, 8, 3, 6, 'And she went down unto the floor, and did according to all that her mother in law bade her.', '&para; 3~03381~ 6~01637~, 8~06213~ 16~02545~ 17~06680~'),
  (1230, 1, 41, 30, 'And there shall arise after them seven years of famine; and all the plenty shall be forgotten in the land of Egypt; and the famine shall consume the land;', '3~06965~ 5~0310~ 6~07651~ 7~08141~ 9~07458~; 13~07647~ 16~07911~ 19~0776~ 21~04714~; 24~07458~ 26~03615~ 28~0776~;'),
  (12360, 16, 3, 24, 'After him repaired Binnui the son of Henadad another piece, from the house of Azariah unto the turning of the wall, even unto the corner.', '0~0310~ 2~02388~ 3~01131~ 5~01121~ 7~02582~ 8~08145~ 9~04060~, 12~01004~ 14~05838~ 17~04740~ [18 20] 24~06438~.'),
  (23901, 40, 22, 19, 'shew me the tribute money. And they brought unto him a penny.', '0~1925~ 1~3427~ 3~2778~ 4~3546~. 5~1161~ 7~4374~ 9~846~ 11~1220~.'),
  (17079, 20, 23, 26, 'My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways.', '1~01121~, 2~05414~ 5~03820~, 9~05869~ 10~07521~ 11~05341~* 13~01870~.'),
  (10282, 13, 1, 22, 'And Ebal, and Abimael, and Sheba,', '1~05858~, 3~039~, 5~07614~,'),
  (1794, 2, 10, 12, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Stretch out thine hand over the land of Egypt for the locusts, that they may come up upon the land of Egypt, and eat every herb of the land, even all that the hail hath left.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 7~05186~ 9~03027~ 12~0776~ 14~04714~ 17~0697~, 22~05927~ 25~0776~ 27~04714~, 29~0398~ 31~06212~ 34~0776~, [35] 39~01259~ 41~07604~.'),
  (7897, 9, 25, 29, 'Yet a man is risen to pursue thee, and to seek thy soul: but the soul of my lord shall be bound in the bundle of life with the LORD thy God; and the souls of thine enemies, them shall he sling out, as out of the middle of a sling.', '2~0120~ 4~06965~ 6~07291~ 10~01245~ 12~05315~: 15~05315~ 18~0113~ 21~06887~ 24~06872~ 26~02416~ 29~03068~ 31~0430~; 34~05315~ 37~0341~, 42~07049~, [43 44] 47~03709~ 48~08432~ 50~07050~.'),
  (10370, 13, 3, 1, 'Now these were the sons of David, which were born unto him in Hebron; the firstborn Amnon, of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second Daniel, of Abigail the Carmelitess:', '&para; 4~01121~ 6~01732~, 9~03205~ 13~02275~; 15~01060~ 16~0550~, 18~0293~ 20~03159~; 22~08145~ 23~01840~, 25~026~ 27~03762~:'),
  (8553, 10, 19, 34, 'And Barzillai said unto the king, How long have I to live, that I should go up with the king unto Jerusalem?', '1~01271~ 2~0559~ 5~04428~, 7~03117~ 11~02416~ 12~08141~,* 17~05927~ 20~04428~ 22~03389~?'),
  (23768, 40, 18, 31, 'So when his fellowservants saw what was done, they were very sorry, and came and told unto their lord all that was done.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 3~4889~ 4~1492~ 7~1096~, 10~4970~ 11~3076~, 12~2532~ 13~2064~ 15~1285~ 17~846~ 18~2962~ 19~3956~ 22~1096~.'),
  (3280, 3, 18, 24, 'Defile not ye yourselves in any of these things: for in all these the nations are defiled which I cast out before you:', '0~02930~ 8~0428~: 14~01471~ 16~02930~ 20~07971~ 21~06440~'),
  (8285, 10, 11, 19, 'And charged the messenger, saying, When thou hast made an end of telling the matters of the war unto the king,', '1~06680~ 3~04397~, 4~0559~, 10~03615~ 12~01696~ 14~01697~ 17~04421~ 20~04428~,'),
  (11555, 14, 18, 4, 'And Jehoshaphat said unto the king of Israel, Inquire, I pray thee, at the word of the LORD to day.', '&para; 1~03092~ 2~0559~ 5~04428~ 7~03478~, 8~01875~, 14~01697~ 17~03068~ 19~03117~.'),
  (6970, 7, 16, 14, 'And she fastened it with the pin, and said unto him, The Philistines be upon thee, Samson. And he awaked out of his sleep, and went away with the pin of the beam, and with the web.', '2~08628~ [3] 6~03489~, 8~0559~ 12~06430~ [13] 16~08123~. 19~03364~ 23~08142~, 26~05265~ 29~03489~ 32~0708~, 36~04545~.'),
  (7137, 8, 1, 3, 'And Elimelech Naomi''s husband died; and she was left, and her two sons.', '1~0458~ 2~05281~ 3~0376~ 4~04191~; 8~07604~, 11~08147~ 12~01121~.'),
  (23053, 38, 11, 16, 'For, lo, I will raise up a shepherd in the land, which shall not visit those that be cut off, neither shall seek the young one, nor heal that that is broken, nor feed that that standeth still: but he shall eat the flesh of the fat, and tear their claws in pieces.', '5~06965~ 7~07462~ 10~0776~, [11] 14~06485~ 19~03582~, 22~01245~ 25~05289~, 27~07495~ 31~07665~, 33~03557~ 36~05324~ 41~0398~ 43~01320~ 46~01277~, 48~06561~ 50~06541~ 52~06561~.'),
  (15865, 19, 116, 8, 'For thou hast delivered my soul from death, mine eyes from tears, and my feet from falling.', '3~02502~ 5~05315~ 7~04194~, 9~05869~ 11~01832~, [12] 14~07272~ 16~01762~.'),
  (27338, 44, 11, 15, 'And as I began to speak, the Holy Ghost fell on them, as on us at the beginning.', '0~1161~ 1~1722~ 2~3165~ 3~756~ 5~2980~, 7~40~ 8~4151~ 9~1968~ 10~1909~ 11~846~, 12~2532~ 13~5618~* 14~1909~ 15~2248~ 16~1722~ 18~746~.'),
  (24396, 41, 5, 22, 'And, behold, there cometh one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jairus by name; and when he saw him, he fell at his feet,', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~2064~ 4~1520~ 10~752~, 11~2383~ 13~3686~; 14~2532~ 17~1492~ 18~846~, 20~4098~ 21~4314~ 22~846~ 23~4228~,'),
  (3760, 4, 4, 12, 'And they shall take all the instruments of ministry, wherewith they minister in the sanctuary, and put them in a cloth of blue, and cover them with a covering of badgers'' skins, and shall put them on a bar:', '3~03947~ 6~03627~ 8~08335~, 11~08334~ 14~06944~, 16~05414~ [17] 20~0899~ 22~08504~, 24~03680~ 28~04372~ 30~08476~ 31~05785~, 34~05414~ [35] 38~04132~:'),
  (9176, 11, 12, 17, 'But as for the children of Israel which dwelt in the cities of Judah, Rehoboam reigned over them.', '[1 2] 4~01121~ 6~03478~ 8~03427~ 11~05892~ 13~03063~, 14~07346~ 15~04427~'),
  (19145, 24, 7, 17, 'Seest thou not what they do in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem?', '0~07200~ 5~06213~ 8~05892~ 10~03063~ 14~02351~ 16~03389~?'),
  (28404, 46, 1, 25, 'Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men; and the weakness of God is stronger than men.', '0~3754~ 2~3474~ 4~2316~ 5~2076~ 7~4680~ 8~444~; 9~2532~ 11~772~ 13~2316~ 14~2076~ 16~2478~ 17~444~.'),
  (20238, 24, 51, 17, 'Every man is brutish by his knowledge; every founder is confounded by the graven image: for his molten image is falsehood, and there is no breath in them.', '1~0120~ 3~01197~ [5] 6~01847~; 8~06884~ 10~03001~ 14~06459~: 18~05262~ [19] 20~08267~, [22 23] 25~07307~'),
  (25898, 42, 22, 20, 'Likewise also the cup after supper, saying, This cup is the new testament in my blood, which is shed for you.', '0~5615~ 1~2532~ 3~4221~ 4~3326~ 5~1172~, 6~3004~, 7~5124~ 8~4221~ [9] 11~2537~ 12~1242~ 13~1722~ 14~3450~ 15~129~, 16~3588~ 18~1632~ 19~5228~ 20~5216~.'),
  (14949, 19, 69, 5, 'O God, thou knowest my foolishness; and my sins are not hid from thee.', '1~0430~, 3~03045~ 5~0200~; 8~0819~ 11~03582~'),
  (22781, 35, 3, 4, 'And his brightness was as the light; he had horns coming out of his hand: and there was the hiding of his power.', '[1] 2~05051~ 6~0216~; 9~07161~ [10] 14~03027~: [17] 19~02253~ 22~05797~.'),
  (23144, 39, 3, 14, 'Ye have said, It is vain to serve God: and what profit is it that we have kept his ordinance, and that we have walked mournfully before the LORD of hosts?', '2~0559~, [4] 5~07723~ 7~05647~ 8~0430~: 11~01215~ [12 13] 17~08104~ 19~04931~, 24~01980~ 25~06941~ 26~06440~ 28~03068~ 30~06635~?'),
  (28174, 45, 9, 3, 'For I could wish that myself were accursed from Christ for my brethren, my kinsmen according to the flesh:', '0~1063~ 1~1473~ 3~2172~ 5~846~ 6~1511~ 7~331~ 8~575~ 9~5547~ 10~5228~ 11~3450~ 12~80~, 13~3450~ 14~4773~ 15~2596~ 18~4561~:'),
  (7708, 9, 18, 25, 'And Saul said, Thus shall ye say to David, The king desireth not any dowry, but an hundred foreskins of the Philistines, to be avenged of the king''s enemies. But Saul thought to make David fall by the hand of the Philistines.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~, 6~0559~ 8~01732~, 10~04428~ 11~02656~ 14~04119~, 17~03967~ 18~06190~ 21~06430~, 24~05358~ 27~04428~ 28~0341~. 30~07586~ 31~02803~ 34~01732~ 35~05307~ 38~03027~ 41~06430~.'),
  (19443, 24, 20, 12, 'But, O LORD of hosts, that triest the righteous, and seest the reins and the heart, let me see thy vengeance on them: for unto thee have I opened my cause.', '2~03068~ 4~06635~, 6~0974~ 8~06662~, [9] 10~07200~ 12~03629~ 15~03820~, 18~07200~ 20~05360~ 28~01540~ 30~07379~.'),
  (438, 1, 18, 10, 'And he said, I will certainly return unto thee according to the time of life; and, lo, Sarah thy wife shall have a son. And Sarah heard it in the tent door, which was behind him.', '2~0559~, 5~07725~ 6~07725~ 12~06256~ 14~02416~; 17~08283~ 19~0802~ 23~01121~. 25~08283~ 26~08085~ [27] 30~0168~ 31~06607~, [33] 35~0310~.'),
  (26483, 43, 9, 28, 'Then they reviled him, and said, Thou art his disciple; but we are Moses'' disciples.', '0~3767~ 2~3058~ 3~846~, 4~2532~ 5~2036~, 6~4771~ 7~1488~ 8~1565~ 9~3101~; 10~1161~ 11~2249~ 12~2070~ 13~3475~ 14~3101~.'),
  (30866, 66, 9, 10, 'And they had tails like unto scorpions, and there were stings in their tails: and their power was to hurt men five months.', '0~2532~ 2~2192~ 3~3769~ 4~3664~ 6~4651~, 7~2532~ 9~2258~ 10~2759~ 11~1722~ 12~846~ 13~3769~: 14~2532~ 15~846~ 16~1849~ [17] 19~91~ 20~444~ 21~4002~ 22~3376~.'),
  (20076, 24, 46, 22, 'The voice thereof shall go like a serpent; for they shall march with an army, and come against her with axes, as hewers of wood.', '1~06963~ 4~03212~ 7~05175~; 11~03212~ 14~02428~, 16~0935~ 20~07134~, 22~02404~ 24~06086~.');
