VALUES
  (25241, 42, 7, 34, 'The Son of man is come eating and drinking; and ye say, Behold a gluttonous man, and a winebibber, a friend of publicans and sinners!', '1~5207~ 3~444~ 5~2064~ 6~2068~ 7~2532~ 8~4095~; 9~2532~ 11~3004~, 12~2400~ 14~5314~ 15~444~, 16~2532~ 18~3630~, 20~5384~ 22~5057~ 23~2532~ 24~268~!'),
  (13437, 18, 23, 9, 'On the left hand, where he doth work, but I cannot behold him: he hideth himself on the right hand, that I cannot see him:', '3~08040~, 7~06213~, 11~02372~ [12] 14~05848~ 19~03225~, 23~07200~ [24]'),
  (23595, 40, 13, 46, 'Who, when he had found one pearl of great price, went and sold all that he had, and bought it.', '0~3739~, 4~2147~ 5~1520~ 6~3135~ 9~4186~, 10~565~ 12~4097~ 13~3956~ 14~3745~ 16~2192~, 17~2532~ 18~59~ 19~846~.'),
  (9562, 12, 2, 3, 'And the sons of the prophets that were at Bethel came forth to Elisha, and said unto him, Knowest thou that the LORD will take away thy master from thy head to day? And he said, Yea, I know it; hold ye your peace.', '2~01121~ 5~05030~ [7] 9~01008~ 11~03318~ 13~0477~, 15~0559~ 18~03045~ 22~03068~ 25~03947~ 27~0113~ 30~07218~ 32~03117~? 35~0559~, 38~03045~ [39] 43~02814~.'),
  (22842, 36, 3, 13, 'The remnant of Israel shall not do iniquity, nor speak lies; neither shall a deceitful tongue be found in their mouth: for they shall feed and lie down, and none shall make them afraid.', '1~07611~ 3~03478~ 6~06213~ 7~05766~, 9~01696~ 10~03577~; 14~08649~ 15~03956~ 17~04672~ 20~06310~: 24~07462~ 27~07257~, [32] 33~02729~.'),
  (20049, 24, 44, 30, 'Thus saith the LORD; Behold, I will give Pharaohhophra king of Egypt into the hand of his enemies, and into the hand of them that seek his life; as I gave Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon, his enemy, and that sought his life.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~; 7~05414~ 8~06548~ 9~04428~ 11~04714~ 14~03027~ 17~0341~, 21~03027~ 25~01245~ 27~05315~; 30~05414~ 31~06667~ 32~04428~ 34~03063~ 37~03027~ 39~05019~ 40~04428~ 42~0894~, 44~0341~, 47~01245~ 49~05315~.'),
  (780, 1, 28, 3, 'And God Almighty bless thee, and make thee fruitful, and multiply thee, that thou mayest be a multitude of people;', '1~0410~ 2~07706~ 3~01288~ 8~06509~, 10~07235~ 17~06951~ 19~05971~;'),
  (27183, 44, 7, 51, 'Ye stiffnecked and uncircumcised in heart and ears, ye do always resist the Holy Ghost: as your fathers did, so do ye.', '&para; 1~4644~ 2~2532~ 3~564~ 5~2588~ 6~2532~ 7~3775~, 8~5210~ 9~496~ 10~104~ 11~496~ 13~40~ 14~4151~: 15~5613~ 16~5216~ 17~3962~ [18] 19~2532~ [20] 21~5210~.'),
  (6127, 6, 11, 14, 'And all the spoil of these cities, and the cattle, the children of Israel took for a prey unto themselves; but every man they smote with the edge of the sword, until they had destroyed them, neither left they any to breathe.', '3~07998~ 6~05892~, 9~0929~, 11~01121~ 13~03478~ 17~0962~ 22~0120~ 24~05221~ 27~06310~ 30~02719~, 34~08045~ 37~07604~ 41~05397~.'),
  (26274, 43, 6, 2, 'And a great multitude followed him, because they saw his miracles which he did on them that were diseased.', '0~2532~ 2~4183~ 3~3793~ 4~190~ 5~846~, 6~3754~ 8~3708~ 9~846~ 10~4592~ 11~3739~ 13~4160~ 14~1909~ 18~770~.'),
  (21371, 26, 36, 3, 'Therefore prophesy and say, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Because they have made you desolate, and swallowed you up on every side, that ye might be a possession unto the residue of the heathen, and ye are taken up in the lips of talkers, and are an infamy of the people:', '1~05012~ 3~0559~, 5~0559~ 7~0136~ 8~03069~; [13] 14~08074~, 18~07602~ 21~05439~, 27~04181~ 30~07611~ 33~01471~, 38~05927~ 41~08193~ 43~03956~, [45] 47~01681~ 50~05971~:'),
  (13501, 18, 27, 11, 'I will teach you by the hand of God: that which is with the Almighty will I not conceal.', '&para; 2~03384~ 6~03027~ 8~0410~: [9] [11] 14~07706~ 18~03582~.'),
  (5013, 5, 4, 3, 'Your eyes have seen what the LORD did because of Baalpeor: for all the men that followed Baalpeor, the LORD thy God hath destroyed them from among you.', '1~05869~ 3~07200~ 6~03068~ 7~06213~ 10~01187~: 14~0376~ 16~01980~ 17~0310~* 18~01187~, 20~03068~ 22~0430~ 24~08045~ 27~07130~'),
  (4019, 4, 10, 26, 'And over the host of the tribe of the children of Asher was Pagiel the son of Ocran.', '3~06635~ 6~04294~ 9~01121~ 11~0836~ [12] 13~06295~ 15~01121~ 17~05918~.'),
  (21972, 27, 8, 2, 'And I saw in a vision; and it came to pass, when I saw, that I was at Shushan in the palace, which is in the province of Elam; and I saw in a vision, and I was by the river of Ulai.', '2~07200~ 5~02377~; 13~07200~, [16] 18~07800~ [19] 21~01002~, [23] 26~04082~ 28~05867~; 31~07200~ 34~02377~, 40~0180~ 42~0195~.'),
  (16943, 20, 19, 9, 'A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that speaketh lies shall perish.', '&para; 1~08267~ 2~05707~ 6~05352~, [8 9] 10~06315~ 11~03577~ 13~06~.'),
  (10360, 13, 2, 46, 'And Ephah, Caleb''s concubine, bare Haran, and Moza, and Gazez: and Haran begat Gazez.', '1~05891~, 2~03612~ 3~06370~, 4~03205~ 5~02771~, 7~04162~, 9~01495~: 11~02771~ 12~03205~ 13~01495~.'),
  (7042, 7, 19, 11, 'And when they were by Jebus, the day was far spent; and the servant said unto his master, Come, I pray thee, and let us turn in into this city of the Jebusites, and lodge in it.', '[0] [3] 5~02982~, 7~03117~ 9~03966~ 10~07286~; 13~05288~ 14~0559~ 17~0113~, 18~03212~, 26~05493~ 29~05892~ 32~02983~, 34~03885~'),
  (22956, 38, 5, 11, 'And he said unto me, To build it an house in the land of Shinar: and it shall be established, and set there upon her own base.', '2~0559~ 6~01129~ 9~01004~ 12~0776~ 14~08152~: 19~03559~, 21~03240~ 26~04369~.'),
  (24714, 41, 12, 30, 'And thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind, and with all thy strength: this is the first commandment.', '0~2532~ 3~25~ 5~2962~ 6~4675~ 7~2316~ 8~1537~ 9~3650~ 10~4675~ 11~2588~, 12~2532~ 13~1537~ 14~3650~ 15~4675~ 16~5590~, 17~2532~ 18~1537~ 19~3650~ 20~4675~ 21~1271~, 22~2532~ 23~1537~ 24~3650~ 25~4675~ 26~2479~: 27~3778~ [28] 30~4413~ 31~1785~.'),
  (11113, 13, 26, 28, 'And all that Samuel the seer, and Saul the son of Kish, and Abner the son of Ner, and Joab the son of Zeruiah, had dedicated; and whosoever had dedicated any thing, it was under the hand of Shelomith, and of his brethren.', '3~08050~ 5~07200~, 7~07586~ 9~01121~ 11~07027~, 13~074~ 15~01121~ 17~05369~, 19~03097~ 21~01121~ 23~06870~, 25~06942~; [26] 29~06942~ [30 33] 36~03027~ 38~08019~, 42~0251~.'),
  (20096, 24, 48, 7, 'For because thou hast trusted in thy works and in thy treasures, thou shalt also be taken: and Chemosh shall go forth into captivity with his priests and his princes together.', '4~0982~ 7~04639~ 11~0214~, 16~03920~: 18~03645~ 21~03318~ 23~01473~ [24] 26~03548~ 29~08269~ 30~03162~.'),
  (8810, 11, 2, 32, 'And the LORD shall return his blood upon his own head, who fell upon two men more righteous and better than he, and slew them with the sword, my father David not knowing thereof, to wit, Abner the son of Ner, captain of the host of Israel, and Amasa the son of Jether, captain of the host of Judah.', '2~03068~ 4~07725~ 6~01818~ 10~07218~, 12~06293~ 14~08147~ 15~0582~ 17~06662~ 19~02896~ 23~02026~ 27~02719~, 29~01~ 30~01732~ 32~03045~ [33 35] 36~074~ 38~01121~ 40~05369~, 41~08269~ 44~06635~ 46~03478~, 48~06021~ 50~01121~ 52~03500~, 53~08269~ 56~06635~ 58~03063~.'),
  (16123, 19, 125, 4, 'Do good, O LORD, unto those that be good, and to them that are upright in their hearts.', '&para; 1~02895~, 3~03068~, [5 7] 8~02896~, [10 13] 14~03477~ 17~03826~.'),
  (7207, 8, 4, 10, 'Moreover Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of Mahlon, have I purchased to be my wife, to raise up the name of the dead upon his inheritance, that the name of the dead be not cut off from among his brethren, and from the gate of his place: ye are witnesses this day.', '1~07327~ 3~04125~, 5~0802~ 7~04248~, 10~07069~ 14~0802~, 17~06965~ 19~08034~ 22~04191~ 25~05159~, 28~08034~ 31~04191~ 35~03772~ 37~05973~ 39~0251~, 43~08179~ 46~04725~: [48] 49~05707~ 51~03117~.'),
  (17951, 23, 14, 14, 'I will ascend above the heights of the clouds; I will be like the most High.', '2~05927~ 5~01116~ 8~05645~; 12~01819~ 15~05945~.'),
  (24180, 40, 27, 41, 'Likewise also the chief priests mocking him, with the scribes and elders, said,', '0~1161~* 1~3668~ 2~2532~ 5~749~ 6~1702~ [7] 8~3326~ 10~1122~ 11~2532~ 12~4245~, 13~3004~,'),
  (5107, 5, 6, 15, '(For the LORD thy God is a jealous God among you) lest the anger of the LORD thy God be kindled against thee, and destroy thee from off the face of the earth.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ [5] 7~07067~ 8~0410~ 9~07130~ 13~0639~ 16~03068~ 18~0430~ 20~02734~ 24~08045~ 29~06440~ 32~0127~.'),
  (30364, 59, 4, 11, 'Speak not evil one of another, brethren. He that speaketh evil of his brother, and judgeth his brother, speaketh evil of the law, and judgeth the law: but if thou judge the law, thou art not a doer of the law, but a judge.', '&para; 0~2635~ 1~3361~ 2~2635~ 5~240~, 6~80~. 10~2635~ [12] 13~80~, 14~2532~ 15~2919~ 16~846~ 17~80~, 19~2635~ 22~3551~, 23~2532~ 24~2919~ 26~3551~: 27~1161~ 28~1487~ 30~2919~ 32~3551~, 34~1488~ 35~3756~ 37~4163~ 40~3551~, 41~235~ 43~2923~.'),
  (1085, 1, 36, 40, 'And these are the names of the dukes that came of Esau, according to their families, after their places, by their names; duke Timnah, duke Alvah, duke Jetheth,', '[2] 4~08034~ 7~0441~ [8 9] 11~06215~, 15~04940~, 18~04725~, 21~08034~; 22~0441~ 23~08555~, 24~0441~ 25~05933~, 26~0441~ 27~03509~,'),
  (23638, 40, 14, 31, 'And immediately Jesus stretched forth his hand, and caught him, and said unto him, O thou of little faith, wherefore didst thou doubt?', '0~1161~ 1~2112~ 2~2424~ 4~1614~ [5] 6~5495~, 8~1949~ 9~846~, 10~2532~ 11~3004~ 13~846~, 18~3640~, 19~5101~ 20~1519~ 22~1365~?'),
  (19966, 24, 40, 16, 'But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam said unto Johanan the son of Kareah, Thou shalt not do this thing: for thou speakest falsely of Ishmael.', '1~01436~ 3~01121~ 5~0296~ 6~0559~ 8~03110~ 10~01121~ 12~07143~, 16~06213~ 18~01697~: 21~01696~ 22~08267~ 24~03458~.'),
  (14486, 19, 37, 27, 'Depart from evil, and do good; and dwell for evermore.', '0~05493~ 2~07451~, 4~06213~ 5~02896~; 7~07931~ 9~05769~.'),
  (24183, 40, 27, 44, 'The thieves also, which were crucified with him, cast the same in his teeth.', '0~1161~ 1~3027~ 2~2532~, 3~3588~ 5~4957~ 7~846~, 8~3679~ 10~846~ 12~846~ 13~3679~.'),
  (8071, 10, 2, 15, 'Then there arose and went over by number twelve of Benjamin, which pertained to Ishbosheth the son of Saul, and twelve of the servants of David.', '2~06965~ 5~05674~ 7~04557~ 8~06240~ 9~08147~ 10~01144~, [12] 14~0378~ 16~01121~ 18~07586~, 20~06240~ 21~08147~ 23~05650~ 25~01732~.'),
  (30340, 59, 3, 5, 'Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasteth great things. Behold, how great a matter a little fire kindleth!', '0~2532~ 1~3779~ 3~1100~ 4~2076~ 6~3398~ 7~3196~, 8~2532~ 11~3166~. 12~2400~, 14~2245~ 16~5208~ 18~3641~ 19~4442~ 20~381~!'),
  (21607, 26, 43, 26, 'Seven days shall they purge the altar and purify it; and they shall consecrate themselves.', '0~07651~ 1~03117~ 4~03722~ 6~04196~ 8~02891~ 14~04390~ 15~03027~.*'),
  (15369, 19, 89, 34, 'My covenant will I not break, nor alter the thing that is gone out of my lips.', '1~01285~ 5~02490~, 7~08138~ 13~04161~ 16~08193~.'),
  (19919, 24, 38, 15, 'Then Jeremiah said unto Zedekiah, If I declare it unto thee, wilt thou not surely put me to death? and if I give thee counsel, wilt thou not hearken unto me?', '1~03414~ 2~0559~ 4~06667~, 7~05046~ [8] 14~04191~ 18~04191~? 24~03289~, 28~08085~'),
  (23050, 38, 11, 13, 'And the LORD said unto me, Cast it unto the potter: a goodly price that I was prised at of them. And I took the thirty pieces of silver, and cast them to the potter in the house of the LORD.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~07993~ 10~03335~: 12~0145~ 13~03366~ 18~03365~ 23~03947~ 25~07970~ [26] 28~03701~, 30~07993~ 34~03335~ 37~01004~ 40~03068~.'),
  (2374, 2, 29, 33, 'And they shall eat those things wherewith the atonement was made, to consecrate and to sanctify them: but a stranger shall not eat thereof, because they are holy.', '3~0398~ 10~03722~, 12~04390~ 13~03027~* [14] 16~06942~ 20~02114~ 23~0398~ [24] [27] 28~06944~.'),
  (2592, 2, 36, 21, 'The length of a board was ten cubits, and the breadth of a board one cubit and a half.', '1~0753~ 4~07175~ [5] 6~06235~ 7~0520~, 10~07341~ 13~07175~ 14~0259~ 15~0520~ 18~02677~.'),
  (13982, 19, 4, 8, 'I will both lay me down in peace, and sleep: for thou, LORD, only makest me dwell in safety.', '2~03162~ 5~07901~ 7~07965~, 9~03462~: 12~03068~, 13~0910~ 16~03427~ 18~0983~.'),
  (19034, 24, 3, 23, 'Truly in vain is salvation hoped for from the hills, and from the multitude of mountains: truly in the LORD our God is the salvation of Israel.', '0~0403~ 2~08267~ [3 6] 9~01389~, [10 11] 13~01995~ 15~02022~: 16~0403~ 19~03068~ 21~0430~ [22] 24~08668~ 26~03478~.'),
  (22522, 31, 1, 3, 'The pride of thine heart hath deceived thee, thou that dwellest in the clefts of the rock, whose habitation is high; that saith in his heart, Who shall bring me down to the ground?', '1~02087~ 4~03820~ 6~05377~ 10~07931~ 13~02288~ 16~05553~, 18~03427~ [19] 20~04791~; 22~0559~ 25~03820~, 30~03381~ 33~0776~?'),
  (18945, 23, 66, 14, 'And when ye see this, your heart shall rejoice, and your bones shall flourish like an herb: and the hand of the LORD shall be known toward his servants, and his indignation toward his enemies.', '3~07200~ [4] 6~03820~ 8~07797~, 11~06106~ 13~06524~ 16~01877~: 19~03027~ 22~03068~ 25~03045~ 28~05650~, [30] 31~02194~ 34~0341~.'),
  (19560, 24, 25, 17, 'Then took I the cup at the LORD''S hand, and made all the nations to drink, unto whom the LORD had sent me:', '1~03947~ 4~03563~ 7~03068~ 8~03027~, 13~01471~ 15~08248~, 19~03068~ 21~07971~'),
  (5115, 5, 6, 23, 'And he brought us out from thence, that he might bring us in, to give us the land which he sware unto our fathers.', '4~03318~ 12~0935~, 14~05414~ 17~0776~ 20~07650~ 23~01~.'),
  (29002, 47, 10, 15, 'Not boasting of things without our measure, that is, of other men''s labours; but having hope, when your faith is increased, that we shall be enlarged by you according to our rule abundantly,', '0~3756~ 1~2744~ 4~1519~ [5] 6~280~, [7 8] 9~1722~ 11~245~ 12~2873~; 13~1161~ 14~2192~ 15~1680~, 17~5216~ 18~4102~ 20~837~, 25~3170~ 26~1722~ 27~5213~ 28~2596~ 30~2257~ 31~2583~ 32~4050~ 33~1519~,*'),
  (12963, 18, 5, 3, 'I have seen the foolish taking root: but suddenly I cursed his habitation.', '2~07200~ 4~0191~ 6~08327~: 8~06597~ 10~05344~ 12~05116~.'),
  (9583, 12, 2, 24, 'And he turned back, and looked on them, and cursed them in the name of the LORD. And there came forth two she bears out of the wood, and tare forty and two children of them.', '2~06437~ 3~0310~, 5~07200~ 9~07043~ 13~08034~ 16~03068~. 20~03318~ 21~08147~ 23~01677~ 27~03293~, 29~01234~ 30~0705~ 32~08147~ 33~03206~'),
  (6674, 7, 6, 13, 'And Gideon said unto him, Oh my Lord, if the LORD be with us, why then is all this befallen us? and where be all his miracles which our fathers told us of, saying, Did not the LORD bring us up from Egypt? but now the LORD hath forsaken us, and delivered us into the hands of the Midianites.', '1~01439~ 2~0559~ 5~0994~ 7~0113~, 8~03426~ 10~03068~ 19~04672~ [23] 26~06381~ 29~01~ 30~05608~ 33~0559~, 37~03068~ 40~05927~ 42~04714~? 46~03068~ 48~05203~ 51~05414~ 55~03709~ 58~04080~.'),
  (13931, 18, 41, 34, 'He beholdeth all high things: he is a king over all the children of pride.', '1~07200~ 3~01364~ [4] [6] 8~04428~ 12~01121~ 14~07830~.'),
  (21391, 26, 36, 23, 'And I will sanctify my great name, which was profaned among the heathen, which ye have profaned in the midst of them; and the heathen shall know that I am the LORD, saith the Lord GOD, when I shall be sanctified in you before their eyes.', '3~06942~ 5~01419~ 6~08034~, 9~02490~ 12~01471~, 16~02490~ 19~08432~ 24~01471~ 26~03045~ [29] 31~03068~, 32~05002~ 34~0136~ 35~03069~, 40~06942~ 45~05869~.'),
  (29151, 48, 4, 4, 'But when the fulness of the time was come, God sent forth his Son, made of a woman, made under the law,', '0~1161~ 1~3753~ 3~4138~ 6~5550~ 8~2064~, 9~2316~ 11~1821~ 12~846~ 13~5207~, 14~1096~ 15~1537~ 17~1135~, 18~1096~ 19~5259~ 21~3551~,'),
  (10893, 13, 17, 22, 'For thy people Israel didst thou make thine own people for ever; and thou, LORD, becamest their God.', '2~05971~ 3~03478~ 6~05414~ 9~05971~ 10~05704~ 11~05769~; 14~03068~, 17~0430~.'),
  (844, 1, 30, 10, 'And Zilpah Leah''s maid bare Jacob a son.', '1~02153~ 2~03812~ 3~08198~ 4~03205~ 5~03290~ 7~01121~.'),
  (7655, 9, 17, 30, 'And he turned from him toward another, and spake after the same manner: and the people answered him again after the former manner.', '2~05437~ 4~0681~ 5~04136~ 6~0312~, 8~0559~ 12~01697~: 15~05971~ 16~01697~ 18~07725~ 21~07223~ 22~01697~.'),
  (26948, 44, 1, 9, 'And when he had spoken these things, while they beheld, he was taken up; and a cloud received him out of their sight.', '0~2532~ 4~2036~ 6~5023~, 8~846~ 9~991~, 13~1869~; 14~2532~ 16~3507~ 17~5274~ 18~846~ 20~575~ 21~846~ 22~3788~.'),
  (13433, 18, 23, 5, 'I would know the words which he would answer me, and understand what he would say unto me.', '2~03045~ 4~04405~ [5] 8~06030~ 11~0995~ 15~0559~'),
  (4745, 4, 32, 21, 'And will go all of you armed over Jordan before the LORD, until he hath driven out his enemies from before him,', '2~05674~ 6~02502~ 7~05674~ 8~03383~ 9~06440~ 11~03068~, 16~03423~ 18~0341~ 20~06440~'),
  (9792, 12, 9, 28, 'And his servants carried him in a chariot to Jerusalem, and buried him in his sepulchre with his fathers in the city of David.', '2~05650~ 3~07392~ 9~03389~, 11~06912~ 15~06900~ 18~01~ 21~05892~ 23~01732~.'),
  (20762, 26, 14, 22, 'Yet, behold, therein shall be left a remnant that shall be brought forth, both sons and daughters: behold, they shall come forth unto you, and ye shall see their way and their doings: and ye shall be comforted concerning the evil that I have brought upon Jerusalem, even concerning all that I have brought upon it.', '5~03498~ 7~06413~ 12~03318~, [13] 14~01121~ 16~01323~: 21~03318~ 27~07200~ 29~01870~ 32~05949~: 37~05162~ 40~07451~ 44~0935~ 46~03389~, [47] 53~0935~'),
  (30351, 59, 3, 16, 'For where envying and strife is, there is confusion and every evil work.', '0~1063~ 1~3699~ 2~2205~ 3~2532~ 4~2052~ [5] 6~1563~ [7] 8~181~ 9~2532~ 10~3956~ 11~5337~ 12~4229~.'),
  (13879, 18, 40, 6, 'Then answered the LORD unto Job out of the whirlwind, and said,', '&para; 1~06030~ 3~03068~ 5~0347~ 9~05591~, 11~0559~,'),
  (11944, 14, 34, 2, 'And he did that which was right in the sight of the LORD, and walked in the ways of David his father, and declined neither to the right hand, nor to the left.', '2~06213~ [3 5] 6~03477~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~, 14~03212~ 17~01870~ 19~01732~ 21~01~, 23~05493~ [24] 28~03225~, 32~08040~.'),
  (27288, 44, 10, 13, 'And there came a voice to him, Rise, Peter; kill, and eat.', '0~2532~ 2~1096~ 4~5456~ 5~4314~ 6~846~, 7~450~, 8~4074~; 9~2380~, 10~2532~ 11~5315~.'),
  (4828, 4, 34, 6, 'And as for the western border, ye shall even have the great sea for a border: this shall be your west border.', '[1 2] 4~03220~ 5~01366~, 11~01419~ 12~03220~ 15~01366~: 20~03220~ 21~01366~.'),
  (25444, 42, 11, 27, 'And it came to pass, as he spake these things, a certain woman of the company lifted up her voice, and said unto him, Blessed is the womb that bare thee, and the paps which thou hast sucked.', '&para; 0~1161~ 4~1096~, 5~1722~ 6~846~ 7~3004~ 9~5023~, 11~5100~ 12~1135~ 13~1537~ 15~3793~ 17~1869~ 19~5456~, 21~2036~ 23~846~, 24~3107~ [25] 27~2836~ 29~941~ 30~4571~, 31~2532~ 33~3149~ 34~3739~ 37~2337~.'),
  (27374, 44, 12, 21, 'And upon a set day Herod, arrayed in royal apparel, sat upon his throne, and made an oration unto them.', '0~1161~ 3~5002~ 4~2250~ 5~2264~, 6~1746~ 8~937~ 9~2066~, 10~2523~ 11~1909~ 13~968~, 14~2532~ 17~1215~ 18~4314~ 19~846~.'),
  (7092, 7, 20, 31, 'And the children of Benjamin went out against the people, and were drawn away from the city; and they began to smite of the people, and kill, as at other times, in the highways, of which one goeth up to the house of God, and the other to Gibeah in the field, about thirty men of Israel.', '2~01121~ 4~01144~ 6~03318~ 7~07125~ 9~05971~, [10] 13~05423~ 16~05892~; 19~02490~ 21~05221~ 24~05971~, [25] 26~02491~, 30~06471~, 33~04546~, 36~0259~ 38~05927~ 41~01004~ 43~0430~ 44~01008~,* 47~0259~ 49~01390~ 52~07704~, 54~07970~ 55~0376~ 57~03478~.'),
  (24000, 40, 24, 33, 'So likewise ye, when ye shall see all these things, know that it is near, even at the doors.', '0~3779~ 1~2532~ 2~5210~, 3~3752~ 6~1492~ 7~3956~ 9~5023~, 10~1097~ 11~3754~ 13~2076~ 14~1451~, [15] 16~1909~ 18~2374~.'),
  (4419, 4, 22, 39, 'And Balaam went with Balak, and they came unto Kirjathhuzoth.', '1~01109~ 2~03212~ 4~01111~, 7~0935~ 9~07155~ 10~02351~.*'),
  (3260, 3, 18, 4, 'Ye shall do my judgments, and keep mine ordinances, to walk therein: I am the LORD your God.', '2~06213~ 4~04941~, 6~08104~ 8~02708~, 10~03212~ [13] 15~03068~ 17~0430~.'),
  (12766, 17, 3, 10, 'And the king took his ring from his hand, and gave it unto Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the Jews'' enemy.', '2~04428~ 3~05493~ 5~02885~ 8~03027~, 10~05414~ 13~02001~ 15~01121~ 17~04099~ 19~091~, 21~03064~ 22~06887~.'),
  (8953, 11, 7, 11, 'And above were costly stones, after the measures of hewed stones, and cedars.', '1~04605~ [2] 3~03368~ 4~068~, 7~04060~ 10~01496~, 12~0730~.'),
  (17996, 23, 17, 4, 'And in that day it shall come to pass, that the glory of Jacob shall be made thin, and the fatness of his flesh shall wax lean.', '3~03117~ [9] 11~03519~ 13~03290~ 17~01809~, 20~04924~ 23~01320~ 26~07329~.'),
  (11161, 13, 28, 10, 'Take heed now; for the LORD hath chosen thee to build an house for the sanctuary: be strong, and do it.', '1~07200~ 5~03068~ 7~0977~ 10~01129~ 12~01004~ 15~04720~: 17~02388~, 19~06213~ [20]'),
  (24548, 41, 8, 37, 'Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?', '0~2228~ 1~5101~ 2~1325~ 4~444~ 5~1325~ 7~465~ 9~846~ 10~5590~?'),
  (3263, 3, 18, 7, 'The nakedness of thy father, or the nakedness of thy mother, shalt thou not uncover: she is thy mother; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.', '1~06172~ 4~01~, 7~06172~ 10~0517~, 14~01540~: [16] 18~0517~; 22~01540~ 24~06172~.'),
  (4575, 4, 27, 15, 'And Moses spake unto the LORD, saying,', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~01696~ 5~03068~, 6~0559~,'),
  (2574, 2, 36, 3, 'And they received of Moses all the offering, which the children of Israel had brought for the work of the service of the sanctuary, to make it withal. And they brought yet unto him free offerings every morning.', '2~03947~ 3~06440~ 4~04872~ 7~08641~, 10~01121~ 12~03478~ 14~0935~ 17~04399~ 20~05656~ 23~06944~, 25~06213~ [27] 30~0935~ 35~05071~ 37~01242~.'),
  (7149, 8, 1, 15, 'And she said, Behold, thy sister in law is gone back unto her people, and unto her gods: return thou after thy sister in law.', '2~0559~, 7~02994~ 10~07725~ 13~05971~, 17~0430~: 18~07725~ 20~0310~ 24~02994~.'),
  (48, 1, 2, 17, 'But of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, thou shalt not eat of it: for in the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die.', '3~06086~ 6~01847~ 8~02896~ 10~07451~, 14~0398~ 20~03117~ 23~0398~ 27~04191~ 28~04191~.'),
  (26194, 43, 4, 23, 'But the hour cometh, and now is, when the true worshippers shall worship the Father in spirit and in truth: for the Father seeketh such to worship him.', '0~235~ 2~5610~ 3~2064~, 4~2532~ 5~3568~ 6~2076~, 7~3753~ 9~228~ 10~4353~ 12~4352~ 14~3962~ 15~1722~ 16~4151~ 17~2532~ 19~225~: 20~1063~ 21~2532~ 22~3962~ 23~2212~ 24~5108~ 26~4352~ 27~846~.'),
  (21225, 26, 30, 12, 'And I will make the rivers dry, and sell the land into the hand of the wicked: and I will make the land waste, and all that is therein, by the hand of strangers: I the LORD have spoken it.', '3~05414~ 5~02975~ 6~02724~, 8~04376~ 10~0776~ 13~03027~ 16~07451~: 22~0776~ 23~08074~, 28~04393~, 31~03027~ 33~02114~: 36~03068~ 38~01696~ [39]'),
  (22356, 29, 3, 4, 'Yea, and what have ye to do with me, O Tyre, and Zidon, and all the coasts of Palestine? will ye render me a recompense? and if ye recompense me, swiftly and speedily will I return your recompense upon your own head;', '10~06865~, 12~06721~, 16~01552~ 18~06429~? 21~07999~ 24~01576~? 28~01580~ 30~07031~ [31] 32~04120~ 35~07725~ 37~01576~ 41~07218~;'),
  (6796, 7, 9, 35, 'And Gaal the son of Ebed went out, and stood in the entering of the gate of the city: and Abimelech rose up, and the people that were with him, from lying in wait.', '1~01603~ 3~01121~ 5~05651~ 7~03318~, 9~05975~ 12~06607~ 15~08179~ 18~05892~: 20~040~ 22~06965~, 25~05971~ [27] 33~03993~.'),
  (24632, 41, 10, 33, 'Saying, Behold, we go up to Jerusalem; and the Son of man shall be delivered unto the chief priests, and unto the scribes; and they shall condemn him to death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles:', '[0] 0~3754~, 1~2400~, 4~305~ 5~1519~ 6~2414~; 7~2532~ 9~5207~ 11~444~ 14~3860~ 18~749~, 19~2532~ 22~1122~; 23~2532~ 26~2632~ 27~846~ 29~2288~, 30~2532~ 32~3860~ 33~846~ 36~1484~:'),
  (23782, 40, 19, 10, 'His disciples say unto him, If the case of the man be so with his wife, it is not good to marry.', '0~846~ 1~3101~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~1487~ 7~156~ 10~444~ 11~2076~ 12~3779~ 13~3326~ [14] 15~1135~, 17~4851~ 18~3756~ 19~4851~ 21~1060~.'),
  (2290, 2, 27, 13, 'And the breadth of the court on the east side eastward shall be fifty cubits.', '2~07341~ 5~02691~ 8~06924~ 9~06285~ 10~04217~ [11 12] 13~02572~ 14~0520~.'),
  (20550, 26, 4, 12, 'And thou shalt eat it as barley cakes, and thou shalt bake it with dung that cometh out of man, in their sight.', '3~0398~ [5] 6~08184~ 7~05692~, 11~05746~ 14~01561~ 17~06627~ 19~0120~, 22~05869~.'),
  (27686, 44, 21, 6, 'And when we had taken our leave one of another, we took ship; and they returned home again.', '0~2532~ 6~782~ 9~240~, 11~1910~ 12~1519~* 13~4143~; 14~1161~ 15~1565~ 16~5290~ 17~1519~* 18~2398~ 19~5290~.'),
  (198, 1, 8, 14, 'And in the second month, on the seven and twentieth day of the month, was the earth dried.', '3~08145~ 4~02320~, 7~07651~ 9~06242~ 10~03117~ 13~02320~, 16~0776~ 17~03001~.'),
  (18239, 23, 30, 13, 'Therefore this iniquity shall be to you as a breach ready to fall, swelling out in a high wall, whose breaking cometh suddenly at an instant.', '2~05771~ 9~06556~ 12~05307~, 14~01158~ 17~07682~ 18~02346~, 20~07667~ 21~0935~ 22~06597~ 25~06621~.'),
  (8369, 10, 14, 6, 'And thy handmaid had two sons, and they two strove together in the field, and there was none to part them, but the one smote the other, and slew him.', '2~08198~ 4~08147~ 5~01121~, 8~08147~ 10~05327~ 13~07704~, [15 16] 19~05337~ 23~0259~ 24~05221~ 26~0259~, 28~04191~'),
  (19304, 24, 14, 2, 'Judah mourneth, and the gates thereof languish; they are black unto the ground; and the cry of Jerusalem is gone up.', '0~03063~ 1~056~, 4~08179~ 6~0535~; 9~06937~ 12~0776~; 15~06682~ 17~03389~ 20~05927~.'),
  (13741, 18, 35, 12, 'There they cry, but none giveth answer, because of the pride of evil men.', '2~06817~, 6~06030~, 7~06440~ 10~01347~ 13~07451~.'),
  (15235, 19, 81, 9, 'There shall no strange god be in thee; neither shalt thou worship any strange god.', '3~02114~ 4~0410~ 11~07812~ 13~05236~ 14~0410~.'),
  (6583, 7, 3, 8, 'Therefore the anger of the LORD was hot against Israel, and he sold them into the hand of Chushanrishathaim king of Mesopotamia: and the children of Israel served Chushanrishathaim eight years.', '&para; 2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 9~03478~, 12~04376~ 16~03027~ 18~03573~ 19~04428~ 21~0763~: 24~01121~ 26~03478~ 27~05647~ 28~03573~ 29~08083~ 30~08141~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (425, 1, 17, 24, 'And Abraham was ninety years old and nine, when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.', '1~085~ [2] 3~08673~ 4~08141~ 5~01121~ 7~08672~, 11~04135~ 14~01320~ 17~06190~.'),
  (27769, 44, 23, 19, 'Then the chief captain took him by the hand, and went with him aside privately, and asked him, What is that thou hast to tell me?', '0~1161~ 3~5506~ 4~1949~ 5~846~ 8~5495~, 9~2532~ [11 12] 13~402~ 14~2398~ 15~2596~,* 17~4441~ [18] 19~5101~ 20~2076~ 21~3739~ 23~2192~ 25~518~ 26~3427~?'),
  (7132, 7, 21, 23, 'And the children of Benjamin did so, and took them wives, according to their number, of them that danced, whom they caught: and they went and returned unto their inheritance, and repaired the cities, and dwelt in them.', '2~01121~ 4~01144~ 6~06213~, 8~05375~ [9] 10~0802~, 14~04557~, 18~02342~, 21~01497~: 24~03212~ 26~07725~ 29~05159~, 31~01129~ 33~05892~, 35~03427~'),
  (23048, 38, 11, 11, 'And it was broken in that day: and so the poor of the flock that waited upon me knew that it was the word of the LORD.', '3~06565~ 6~03117~: 10~06041~ 13~06629~ 15~08104~ 18~03045~ [21] 23~01697~ 26~03068~.'),
  (14599, 19, 44, 19, 'Though thou hast sore broken us in the place of dragons, and covered us with the shadow of death.', '4~01794~ 8~04725~ 10~08577~, 12~03680~ 18~06757~.'),
  (4556, 4, 26, 61, 'And Nadab and Abihu died, when they offered strange fire before the LORD.', '1~05070~ 3~030~ 4~04191~, 7~07126~ 8~02114~ 9~0784~ 10~06440~ 12~03068~.'),
  (27389, 44, 13, 11, 'And now, behold, the hand of the Lord is upon thee, and thou shalt be blind, not seeing the sun for a season. And immediately there fell on him a mist and a darkness; and he went about seeking some to lead him by the hand.', '0~2532~ 1~3568~, 2~2400~, 4~5495~ 7~2962~ [8] 9~1909~ 10~4571~, 11~2532~ 14~2071~ 15~5185~, 16~3361~ 17~991~ 19~2246~ 20~891~ 22~2540~. 23~1161~ 24~3916~ 26~1968~ 27~1909~ 28~846~ 30~887~ 31~2532~ 33~4655~; 34~2532~ 37~4013~ 38~2212~ 45~5497~.'),
  (1501, 1, 49, 23, 'The archers have sorely grieved him, and shot at him, and hated him:', '1~02671~ 2~01167~ 5~04843~, 7~07232~ [8 9] 12~07852~:'),
  (3824, 4, 5, 27, 'And when he hath made her to drink the water, then it shall come to pass, that, if she be defiled, and have done trespass against her husband, that the water that causeth the curse shall enter into her, and become bitter, and her belly shall swell, and her thigh shall rot: and the woman shall be a curse among her people.', '7~08248~ 9~04325~, [16] 20~02930~, 23~04603~ 24~04604~ 27~0376~, 30~04325~ 34~0779~ 36~0935~ [39 40] 41~04751~, 44~0990~ 46~06638~, 49~03409~ 51~05307~: 54~0802~ 58~0423~ 59~07130~ 61~05971~.'),
  (9171, 11, 12, 12, 'So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as the king had appointed, saying, Come to me again the third day.', '1~03379~ 5~05971~ 6~0935~ 8~07346~ 10~07992~ 11~03117~, 14~04428~ 16~01696~, 17~0559~, 21~07725~ 23~07992~ 24~03117~.'),
  (26005, 42, 23, 56, 'And they returned, and prepared spices and ointments; and rested the sabbath day according to the commandment.', '2~5290~, 3~1161~ 4~2090~ 5~759~ 6~2532~ 7~3464~; 8~2532~ 9~2270~ 10~3303~* 13~4521~ 14~2596~ 17~1785~.'),
  (30801, 66, 5, 6, 'And I beheld, and, lo, in the midst of the throne and of the four beasts, and in the midst of the elders, stood a Lamb as it had been slain, having seven horns and seven eyes, which are the seven Spirits of God sent forth into all the earth.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1492~, 3~2532~, 4~2400~, 5~1722~ 7~3319~ 10~2362~ 11~2532~ 14~5064~ 15~2226~, 16~2532~ 17~1722~ 19~3319~ 22~4245~, 23~2476~ 25~721~ 26~5613~ 30~4969~, 31~2192~ 32~2033~ 33~2768~ 34~2532~ 35~2033~ 36~3788~, 37~3739~ 38~1526~ 40~2033~ 41~4151~ 43~2316~ 45~649~ 46~1519~ 47~3956~ 49~1093~.'),
  (5482, 5, 22, 6, 'If a bird''s nest chance to be before thee in the way in any tree, or on the ground, whether they be young ones, or eggs, and the dam sitting upon the young, or upon the eggs, thou shalt not take the dam with the young:', '2~06833~ 3~07064~ 4~07122~ 7~06440~ 11~01870~ 14~06086~, 18~0776~, [19 21] 23~0667~, 25~01000~, 28~0517~ 29~07257~ 32~0667~, 36~01000~, 40~03947~ 42~0517~ 45~01121~:'),
  (5735, 5, 31, 1, 'And Moses went and spake these words unto all Israel.', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~03212~ 4~01696~ 6~01697~ 9~03478~.'),
  (29558, 51, 3, 25, 'But he that doeth wrong shall receive for the wrong which he hath done: and there is no respect of persons.', '0~1161~ 4~91~ 6~2865~ 9~91~ 10~3739~ 13~91~: 14~2532~ 16~2076~ 17~3756~ 20~4382~.'),
  (17408, 21, 5, 2, 'Be not rash with thy mouth, and let not thine heart be hasty to utter any thing before God: for God is in heaven, and thou upon earth: therefore let thy words be few.', '2~0926~ 5~06310~, 10~03820~ 12~04116~ 14~03318~ [15] 16~01697~ 17~06440~ 18~0430~: 20~0430~ [21] 23~08064~, 27~0776~: 31~01697~ 33~04592~.'),
  (11852, 14, 30, 16, 'And they stood in their place after their manner, according to the law of Moses the man of God: the priests sprinkled the blood, which they received of the hand of the Levites.', '2~05975~ 5~05977~ 8~04941~, 12~08451~ 14~04872~ 16~0376~ 18~0430~: 20~03548~ 21~02236~ 23~01818~, [24 26] 29~03027~ 32~03881~.'),
  (25895, 42, 22, 17, 'And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and said, Take this, and divide it among yourselves:', '0~2532~ 2~1209~ 4~4221~, 7~2168~, 9~2036~, 10~2983~ 11~5124~, 12~2532~ 13~1266~ [14] 16~1438~:'),
  (21328, 26, 34, 6, 'My sheep wandered through all the mountains, and upon every high hill: yea, my flock was scattered upon all the face of the earth, and none did search or seek after them.', '1~06629~ 2~07686~ 6~02022~, 10~07311~ 11~01389~: 14~06629~ 16~06327~ 20~06440~ 23~0776~, 27~01875~ 29~01245~ [30 31]'),
  (19531, 24, 23, 38, 'But since ye say, The burden of the LORD; therefore thus saith the LORD; Because ye say this word, The burden of the LORD, and I have sent unto you, saying, Ye shall not say, The burden of the LORD;', '0~0518~ 3~0559~, 5~04853~ 8~03068~; 11~0559~ 13~03068~; 16~0559~ 18~01697~, 20~04853~ 23~03068~, 27~07971~ 30~0559~, 34~0559~, 36~04853~ 39~03068~;'),
  (26372, 43, 7, 29, 'But I know him: for I am from him, and he hath sent me.', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 2~1492~ 3~846~: 4~3754~ 6~1510~ 7~3844~ 8~846~, 10~2548~ 12~649~ 13~3165~.'),
  (1867, 2, 12, 46, 'In one house shall it be eaten; thou shalt not carry forth ought of the flesh abroad out of the house; neither shall ye break a bone thereof.', '1~0259~ 2~01004~ 6~0398~; 11~03318~ 15~01320~ 16~02351~ 20~01004~; 24~07665~ 26~06106~'),
  (11998, 14, 35, 23, 'And the archers shot at king Josiah; and the king said to his servants, Have me away; for I am sore wounded.', '2~03384~ 3~03384~ 5~04428~ 6~02977~; 9~04428~ 10~0559~ 13~05650~, 16~05674~; 20~03966~ 21~02470~.'),
  (23993, 40, 24, 26, 'Wherefore if they shall say unto you, Behold, he is in the desert; go not forth: behold, he is in the secret chambers; believe it not.', '0~3767~ 1~1437~ 4~2036~ 6~5213~, 7~2400~, 9~2076~ 10~1722~ 12~2048~; 13~1831~ 14~3361~ 15~1831~: 16~2400~, [17 18] 19~1722~ 22~5009~; 23~4100~ [24] 25~3361~.'),
  (12818, 17, 7, 2, 'And the king said again unto Esther on the second day at the banquet of wine, What is thy petition, queen Esther? and it shall be granted thee: and what is thy request? and it shall be performed, even to the half of the kingdom.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~ 6~0635~ 9~08145~ 10~03117~ 13~04960~ 15~03196~, [17] 19~07596~, 20~04436~ 21~0635~? 26~05414~ [30] 32~01246~? 37~06213~, [38] 41~02677~ 44~04438~.'),
  (19686, 24, 30, 10, 'Therefore fear thou not, O my servant Jacob, saith the LORD; neither be dismayed, O Israel: for, lo, I will save thee from afar, and thy seed from the land of their captivity; and Jacob shall return, and shall be in rest, and be quiet, and none shall make him afraid.', '&para; 1~03372~ 6~05650~ 7~03290~, 8~05002~ 10~03068~; 13~02865~, 15~03478~: 20~03467~ 23~07350~, 26~02233~ 29~0776~ 32~07628~; 34~03290~ 36~07725~, 41~08252~, 44~07599~, [49] 50~02729~.'),
  (23939, 40, 23, 11, 'But he that is greatest among you shall be your servant.', '0~1161~ 4~3187~ 6~5216~ 8~2071~ 9~5216~ 10~1249~.'),
  (13258, 18, 16, 11, 'God hath delivered me to the ungodly, and turned me over into the hands of the wicked.', '0~0410~ 2~05462~ 6~05760~, 10~03399~ 13~03027~ 16~07563~.'),
  (25899, 42, 22, 21, 'But, behold, the hand of him that betrayeth me is with me on the table.', '&para; 0~4133~, 1~2400~, 3~5495~ 7~3860~ 8~3165~ [9] 10~3326~ 11~1700~ 12~1909~ 14~5132~.'),
  (17989, 23, 16, 11, 'Wherefore my bowels shall sound like an harp for Moab, and mine inward parts for Kirharesh.', '2~04578~ 4~01993~ 7~03658~ 9~04124~, 13~07130~ 15~07025~.'),
  (23338, 40, 7, 12, 'Therefore all things whatsoever ye would that men should do to you, do ye even so to them: for this is the law and the prophets.', '&para; 0~3767~ 2~3956~ 3~3745~ 4~302~ 5~2309~ 6~2443~ 7~444~ 9~4160~ 11~5213~, 12~4160~ 13~5210~ 14~2532~ 15~3779~ 17~846~: 18~1063~ 19~3778~ 20~2076~ 22~3551~ 23~2532~ 25~4396~.'),
  (4659, 4, 30, 5, 'But if her father disallow her in the day that he heareth; not any of her vows, or of her bonds wherewith she hath bound her soul, shall stand: and the LORD shall forgive her, because her father disallowed her.', '3~01~ 4~05106~ 8~03117~ 11~08085~; 16~05088~, 20~0632~ 24~0631~ 26~05315~, 28~06965~: 31~03068~ 33~05545~ 37~01~ 38~05106~'),
  (12790, 17, 5, 2, 'And it was so, when the king saw Esther the queen standing in the court, that she obtained favour in his sight: and the king held out to Esther the golden sceptre that was in his hand. So Esther drew near, and touched the top of the sceptre.', '6~04428~ 7~07200~ 8~0635~ 10~04436~ 11~05975~ 14~02691~, [15] 17~05375~ 18~02580~ 21~05869~: 24~04428~ 26~03447~ 28~0635~ 30~02091~ 31~08275~ [33] 36~03027~. 38~0635~ 40~07126~, 42~05060~ 44~07218~ 47~08275~.'),
  (27206, 44, 8, 14, 'Now when the apostles which were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of God, they sent unto them Peter and John:', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~652~ 4~3588~ 6~1722~ 7~2414~ 8~191~ 9~3754~ 10~4540~ 12~1209~ 14~3056~ 16~2316~, 18~649~ 19~4314~ 20~846~ 21~4074~ 22~2532~ 23~2491~:'),
  (20158, 24, 49, 22, 'Behold, he shall come up and fly as the eagle, and spread his wings over Bozrah: and at that day shall the heart of the mighty men of Edom be as the heart of a woman in her pangs.', '4~05927~ 6~01675~ 9~05404~, 11~06566~ 13~03671~ 15~01224~: 19~03117~ 22~03820~ 26~01368~ 28~0123~ 32~03820~ 35~0802~ 38~06887~.'),
  (24457, 41, 6, 40, 'And they sat down in ranks, by hundreds, and by fifties.', '0~2532~ 3~377~ 5~4237~ 6~4237~,* 7~303~ 8~1540~, 9~2532~ 10~303~ 11~4004~.'),
  (9064, 11, 9, 5, 'Then I will establish the throne of thy kingdom upon Israel for ever, as I promised to David thy father, saying, There shall not fail thee a man upon the throne of Israel.', '3~06965~ 5~03678~ 8~04467~ 10~03478~ 12~05769~, 15~01696~ 17~01732~ 19~01~, 20~0559~, 24~03772~ 27~0376~ 30~03678~ 32~03478~.'),
  (16332, 19, 145, 3, 'Great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised; and his greatness is unsearchable.', '0~01419~ [1] 3~03068~, 5~03966~ 8~01984~; 11~01420~ [12] 13~02714~.'),
  (6399, 6, 21, 11, 'And they gave them the city of Arba the father of Anak, which city is Hebron, in the hill country of Judah, with the suburbs thereof round about it.', '2~05414~ 5~07151~ 7~0704~ 8~07153~* 10~01~ 12~06061~, [14 15] 16~02275~, 19~02022~ [20] 22~03063~, 25~04054~ 28~05439~'),
  (4749, 4, 32, 25, 'And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben spake unto Moses, saying, Thy servants will do as my lord commandeth.', '2~01121~ 4~01410~ 7~01121~ 9~07205~ 10~0559~ 12~04872~, 13~0559~, 15~05650~ 17~06213~ 20~0113~ 21~06680~.'),
  (19509, 24, 23, 16, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts, Hearken not unto the words of the prophets that prophesy unto you: they make you vain: they speak a vision of their own heart, and not out of the mouth of the LORD.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~, 6~08085~ 10~01697~ 13~05030~ 15~05012~ 21~01891~: 23~01696~ 25~02377~ 29~03820~, [30] 35~06310~ 38~03068~.'),
  (7790, 9, 21, 11, 'And the servants of Achish said unto him, Is not this David the king of the land? did they not sing one to another of him in dances, saying, Saul hath slain his thousands, and David his ten thousands?', '2~05650~ 4~0397~ 5~0559~ [8] 11~01732~ 13~04428~ 16~0776~? 20~06030~ 25~02088~ 27~04246~, 28~0559~, 29~07586~ 31~05221~ 33~0505~, 35~01732~ 38~07233~?'),
  (17668, 23, 1, 5, 'Why should ye be stricken any more? ye will revolt more and more: the whole head is sick, and the whole heart faint.', '4~05221~ 9~05627~ 12~03254~: 15~07218~ 17~02483~, 21~03824~ 22~01742~.'),
  (16907, 20, 17, 25, 'A foolish son is a grief to his father, and bitterness to her that bare him.', '&para; 1~03684~ 2~01121~ [3] 5~03708~ 8~01~, 10~04470~ 14~03205~'),
  (25244, 42, 7, 37, 'And, behold, a woman in the city, which was a sinner, when she knew that Jesus sat at meat in the Pharisee''s house, brought an alabaster box of ointment,', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~1135~ 4~1722~ 6~4172~, 7~3748~ 8~2258~ 10~268~, 13~1921~ 14~3754~ [15] 18~345~ 19~1722~ 21~5330~ 22~3614~, 23~2865~ 26~211~ 28~3464~,'),
  (24992, 42, 2, 7, 'And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid him in a manger; because there was no room for them in the inn.', '0~2532~ 3~5088~ 4~846~ 5~4416~ 6~5207~, 7~2532~ 8~4683~ 9~846~ 12~4683~, 13~2532~ 14~347~ 15~846~ 16~1722~ 18~5336~; 19~1360~ 21~2258~ 22~3756~ 23~5117~ 25~846~ 26~1722~ 28~2646~.'),
  (9711, 12, 6, 29, 'So we boiled my son, and did eat him: and I said unto her on the next day, Give thy son, that we may eat him: and she hath hid her son.', '2~01310~ 4~01121~, 7~0398~ 11~0559~ 16~0312~ 17~03117~, 18~05414~ 20~01121~, 24~0398~ 29~02244~ 31~01121~.'),
  (29191, 48, 5, 13, 'For, brethren, ye have been called unto liberty; only use not liberty for an occasion to the flesh, but by love serve one another.', '&para; 0~1063~, 1~80~, 2~5210~ 5~2564~ 6~1909~ 7~1657~; 8~3440~ [9] 10~3361~ 11~1657~ 12~1519~ 14~874~ 17~4561~, 18~235~ 19~1223~ 20~26~ 21~1398~ 23~240~.'),
  (8240, 10, 9, 6, 'Now when Mephibosheth, the son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, was come unto David, he fell on his face, and did reverence. And David said, Mephibosheth. And he answered, Behold thy servant!', '2~04648~, 4~01121~ 6~03083~, 8~01121~ 10~07586~, 12~0935~ 14~01732~, 16~05307~ 19~06440~, 22~07812~. 24~01732~ 25~0559~, 26~04648~. 29~0559~, 32~05650~!'),
  (600, 1, 24, 5, 'And the servant said unto him, Peradventure the woman will not be willing to follow me unto this land: must I needs bring thy son again unto the land from whence thou camest?', '2~05650~ 3~0559~ 8~0802~ 12~014~ 14~03212~ 15~0310~ 18~0776~: 22~07725~ 24~01121~ 25~07725~ 28~0776~ 32~03318~?'),
  (9480, 11, 21, 21, 'Behold, I will bring evil upon thee, and will take away thy posterity, and will cut off from Ahab him that pisseth against the wall, and him that is shut up and left in Israel,', '3~0935~ 4~07451~ 10~01197~ 12~0310~, 16~03772~ 18~0256~ 21~08366~ 24~07023~, 30~06113~ 32~05800~ 34~03478~,'),
  (3740, 4, 3, 43, 'And all the firstborn males by the number of names, from a month old and upward, of those that were numbered of them, were twenty and two thousand two hundred and threescore and thirteen.', '3~01060~ 4~02145~ 7~04557~ 9~08034~, 12~02320~ 13~01121~ 15~04605~, 20~06485~ 24~06242~ 26~08147~ 27~0505~ 29~03967~ 33~07969~ 34~07657~.*'),
  (23344, 40, 7, 18, 'A good tree cannot bring forth evil fruit, neither can a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit.', '1~18~ 2~1186~ 3~1410~ 4~3756~* 6~4160~ 7~4190~ 8~2590~, 9~3761~ [10] 12~4550~ 13~1186~ 15~4160~ 16~2570~ 17~2590~.'),
  (13121, 18, 11, 4, 'For thou hast said, My doctrine is pure, and I am clean in thine eyes.', '3~0559~, 5~03948~ [6] 7~02134~, 11~01249~ 14~05869~.'),
  (6014, 6, 8, 6, '(For they will come out after us) till we have drawn them from the city; for they will say, They flee before us, as at the first: therefore we will flee before them.', '4~03318~ 5~0310~ 10~05423~ 14~05892~; 18~0559~, 20~05127~ 21~06440~ 26~07223~: 30~05127~ 31~06440~'),
  (1918, 2, 14, 24, 'And it came to pass, that in the morning watch the LORD looked unto the host of the Egyptians through the pillar of fire and of the cloud, and troubled the host of the Egyptians,', '8~01242~ 9~0821~ 11~03068~ 12~08259~ 15~04264~ 18~04714~ 21~05982~ 23~0784~ 27~06051~, 29~02000~ 31~04264~ 34~04714~,'),
  (18754, 23, 55, 5, 'Behold, thou shalt call a nation that thou knowest not, and nations that knew not thee shall run unto thee because of the LORD thy God, and for the Holy One of Israel; for he hath glorified thee.', '3~07121~ 5~01471~ [6] 8~03045~ 11~01471~ [12] 13~03045~ 17~07323~ 23~03068~ 25~0430~, 30~06918~ 32~03478~; 36~06286~'),
  (4277, 4, 18, 15, 'Every thing that openeth the matrix in all flesh, which they bring unto the LORD, whether it be of men or beasts, shall be thine: nevertheless the firstborn of man shalt thou surely redeem, and the firstling of unclean beasts shalt thou redeem.', '3~06363~ 5~07358~ 8~01320~, 11~07126~ 14~03068~, [15 17] 19~0120~ 21~0929~, 27~01060~ 29~0120~ 32~06299~ 33~06299~, 36~01060~ 38~02931~ 39~0929~ 42~06299~.'),
  (5866, 6, 1, 9, 'Have not I commanded thee? Be strong and of a good courage; be not afraid, neither be thou dismayed: for the LORD thy God is with thee whithersoever thou goest.', '3~06680~ 6~02388~ 11~0553~; 14~06206~, 18~02865~: 21~03068~ 23~0430~ [24] 29~03212~.'),
  (13124, 18, 11, 7, 'Canst thou by searching find out God? canst thou find out the Almighty unto perfection?', '&para; 3~02714~ 5~04672~ 6~0433~? 9~04672~ 12~07706~ 14~08503~?'),
  (1460, 1, 48, 4, 'And said unto me, Behold, I will make thee fruitful, and multiply thee, and I will make of thee a multitude of people; and will give this land to thy seed after thee for an everlasting possession.', '1~0559~ 9~06509~, 11~07235~ 16~05414~ 20~06951~ 22~05971~; 25~05414~ 27~0776~ 30~02233~ 32~0310~ [33] 35~05769~ 36~0272~.'),
  (8096, 10, 3, 8, 'Then was Abner very wroth for the words of Ishbosheth, and said, Am I a dog''s head, which against Judah do shew kindness this day unto the house of Saul thy father, to his brethren, and to his friends, and have not delivered thee into the hand of David, that thou chargest me to day with a fault concerning this woman?', '2~074~ 3~03966~ 4~02734~ 7~01697~ 9~0378~, 11~0559~, [12] 15~03611~ 16~07218~, 19~03063~ 21~06213~ 22~02617~ 24~03117~ 27~01004~ 29~07586~ 31~01~, 34~0251~, 38~04828~, 42~04672~ 46~03027~ 48~01732~, 51~06485~ 54~03117~ 57~05771~ 60~0802~?'),
  (13710, 18, 34, 18, 'Is it fit to say to a king, Thou art wicked? and to princes, Ye are ungodly?', '[0 2] 4~0559~ 7~04428~, [8 9] 10~01100~? [11] 13~05081~, [14 15] 16~07563~?'),
  (28279, 45, 12, 18, 'If it be possible, as much as lieth in you, live peaceably with all men.', '0~1487~ 3~1415~, 8~1537~ 9~5216~, 11~1514~ 12~3326~ 13~3956~ 14~444~.'),
  (1261, 1, 42, 4, 'But Benjamin, Joseph''s brother, Jacob sent not with his brethren; for he said, Lest peradventure mischief befall him.', '1~01144~, 2~03130~ 3~0251~, 4~03290~ 5~07971~ 9~0251~; 12~0559~, 14~06435~ 15~0611~ 17~07122~.'),
  (22878, 37, 2, 14, 'Then answered Haggai, and said, So is this people, and so is this nation before me, saith the LORD; and so is every work of their hands; and that which they offer there is unclean.', '1~06030~ 2~02292~, 4~0559~, [6] 8~05971~, [11] 13~01471~ 14~06440~ 16~05002~ 18~03068~; [21] 23~04639~ 26~03027~; 31~07126~ [33] 34~02931~.'),
  (4676, 4, 31, 6, 'And Moses sent them to the war, a thousand of every tribe, them and Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, to the war, with the holy instruments, and the trumpets to blow in his hand.', '1~04872~ 2~07971~ 6~06635~, 8~0505~ [10] 11~04294~, 14~06372~ 16~01121~ 18~0499~ 20~03548~, 23~06635~, 26~06944~ 27~03627~, 30~02689~ 32~08643~ 35~03027~.'),
  (28130, 45, 7, 23, 'But I see another law in my members, warring against the law of my mind, and bringing me into captivity to the law of sin which is in my members.', '0~1161~ 2~991~ 3~2087~ 4~3551~ 5~1722~ 6~3450~ 7~3196~, 9~497~ 11~3551~ 13~3450~ 14~3563~, 15~2532~ 16~163~ 17~3165~ 19~163~ 22~3551~ 24~266~ 25~3588~ 26~5607~ 27~1722~ 28~3450~ 29~3196~.'),
  (29698, 53, 3, 4, 'And we have confidence in the Lord touching you, that ye both do and will do the things which we command you.', '0~1161~ 3~3982~ 4~1722~ 6~2962~ 7~1909~ 8~5209~, 9~3754~ 11~2532~ 12~4160~ 13~2532~ 15~4160~ 18~3739~ 20~3853~ 21~5213~.'),
  (20201, 24, 50, 26, 'Come against her from the utmost border, open her storehouses: cast her up as heaps, and destroy her utterly: let nothing of her be left.', '0~0935~ 6~07093~, 7~06605~ 9~03965~: 12~05549~ 14~06194~, 18~02763~: 24~07611~.'),
  (13422, 18, 22, 24, 'Then shalt thou lay up gold as dust, and the gold of Ophir as the stones of the brooks.', '4~07896~ 5~01220~ 6~05921~ 7~06083~, [10] 12~0211~ 15~06697~ 18~05158~.'),
  (12214, 15, 8, 4, 'Of the sons of Pahathmoab; Elihoenai the son of Zerahiah, and with him two hundred males.', '2~01121~ 4~06355~; 5~0454~ 7~01121~ 9~02228~, 14~03967~ 15~02145~.'),
  (20317, 24, 52, 32, 'And spake kindly unto him, and set his throne above the throne of the kings that were with him in Babylon,', '1~01696~ 2~02896~ 6~05414~ 8~03678~ 9~04605~ 11~03678~ 14~04428~ [16] 20~0894~,'),
  (7313, 9, 4, 9, 'Be strong, and quit yourselves like men, O ye Philistines, that ye be not servants unto the Hebrews, as they have been to you: quit yourselves like men, and fight.', '1~02388~, 3~01961~ 6~0582~, 9~06430~, 14~05647~ 17~05680~, 21~05647~ 24~01961~ 27~0582~, 29~03898~.'),
  (27860, 44, 26, 21, 'For these causes the Jews caught me in the temple, and went about to kill me.', '0~1752~ 2~5130~ 4~2453~ 5~4815~ 6~3165~ 7~1722~ 9~2411~, 12~3987~ 14~1315~ [15]'),
  (15213, 19, 80, 6, 'Thou makest us a strife unto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselves.', '1~07760~ 4~04066~ 7~07934~: 10~0341~ 11~03932~'),
  (15559, 19, 103, 1, 'A Psalm of David. Bless the LORD, O my soul: and all that is within me, bless his holy name.', '&para; [0 1] 3] 3~01732~ 4~01288~ 6~03068~, 9~05315~: 14~07130~ [16] 18~06944~ 19~08034~.'),
  (13543, 18, 29, 2, 'Oh that I were as in months past, as in the days when God preserved me;', '1~05414~ [5] 6~03391~ 7~06924~, [9] 11~03117~ [12] 13~0433~ 14~08104~'),
  (19814, 24, 34, 4, 'Yet hear the word of the LORD, O Zedekiah king of Judah; Thus saith the LORD of thee, Thou shalt not die by the sword:', '1~08085~ 3~01697~ 6~03068~, 8~06667~ 9~04428~ 11~03063~; 13~0559~ 15~03068~ 21~04191~ 24~02719~:'),
  (22912, 38, 2, 4, 'And said unto him, Run, speak to this young man, saying, Jerusalem shall be inhabited as towns without walls for the multitude of men and cattle therein:', '1~0559~ 4~07323~, 5~01696~ 7~01975~ 9~05288~, 10~0559~, 11~03389~ 14~03427~ [15] 18~06519~ 21~07230~ 23~0120~ 25~0929~ 26~08432~:'),
  (6913, 7, 13, 22, 'And Manoah said unto his wife, We shall surely die, because we have seen God.', '1~04495~ 2~0559~ 5~0802~, 8~04191~ 9~04191~, 13~07200~ 14~0430~.'),
  (11482, 14, 13, 20, 'Neither did Jeroboam recover strength again in the days of Abijah: and the LORD struck him, and he died.', '2~03379~ 3~06113~ 4~03581~ 8~03117~ 10~029~: 13~03068~ 14~05062~ 18~04191~.'),
  (15644, 19, 105, 29, 'He turned their waters into blood, and slew their fish.', '1~02015~ 3~04325~ 5~01818~, 7~04191~ 9~01710~.'),
  (27749, 44, 22, 29, 'Then straightway they departed from him which should have examined him: and the chief captain also was afraid, after he knew that he was a Roman, and because he had bound him.', '0~3767~ 1~2112~ 3~868~ 4~575~ 5~846~ 6~3588~ 7~3195~ 9~426~ 10~846~: 11~1161~ 14~5506~ 15~2532~ 17~5399~, 20~1921~ 21~3754~ 23~2076~ 25~4514~, 26~2532~ 27~3754~ 29~2258~ 30~1210~ 31~846~.'),
  (9352, 11, 18, 3, 'And Ahab called Obadiah, which was the governor of his house. (Now Obadiah feared the LORD greatly:', '1~0256~ 2~07121~ 3~05662~, [5] [9] 10~01004~. 12~05662~ 13~03373~ 15~03068~ 16~03966~:'),
  (28853, 47, 2, 13, 'I had no rest in my spirit, because I found not Titus my brother: but taking my leave of them, I went from thence into Macedonia.', '1~2192~ 2~3756~ 3~425~ 5~3450~ 6~4151~, 8~3165~ 9~2147~ 10~3361~ 11~5103~ 12~3450~ 13~80~: 14~235~ 17~657~ 19~846~, 23~1831~ 24~1519~ 25~3109~.'),
  (22804, 36, 1, 8, 'And it shall come to pass in the day of the LORD''S sacrifice, that I will punish the princes, and the king''s children, and all such as are clothed with strange apparel.', '8~03117~ 11~03068~ 12~02077~, 16~06485~ 18~08269~, 21~04428~ 22~01121~, 28~03847~ 30~05237~ 31~04403~.'),
  (7244, 9, 1, 25, 'And they slew a bullock, and brought the child to Eli.', '2~07819~ 4~06499~, 6~0935~ 8~05288~ 10~05941~.'),
  (30260, 58, 13, 3, 'Remember them that are in bonds, as bound with them; and them which suffer adversity, as being yourselves also in the body.', '0~3403~ 5~1198~, 6~5613~ 9~4887~; [10] 14~2558~, 15~5613~ 16~5607~ 17~846~ 18~2532~ 19~1722~ 21~4983~.'),
  (1997, 2, 17, 9, 'And Moses said unto Joshua, Choose us out men, and go out, fight with Amalek: to morrow I will stand on the top of the hill with the rod of God in mine hand.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~03091~, 7~0977~ 8~0582~, 11~03318~, 12~03898~ 14~06002~: 16~04279~ 19~05324~ 22~07218~ 25~01389~ 28~04294~ 30~0430~ 33~03027~.'),
  (9497, 11, 22, 9, 'Then the king of Israel called an officer, and said, Hasten hither Micaiah the son of Imlah.', '2~04428~ 4~03478~ 5~07121~ 6~0259~ 7~05631~, 9~0559~, 10~04116~ [11] 12~04321~ 14~01121~ 16~03229~.'),
  (13228, 18, 15, 16, 'How much more abominable and filthy is man, which drinketh iniquity like water?', '3~08581~ 5~0444~ [6] 7~0376~, 9~08354~ 10~05766~ 11~05766~* 13~04325~?'),
  (23389, 40, 8, 34, 'And, behold, the whole city came out to meet Jesus: and when they saw him, they besought him that he would depart out of their coasts.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~3956~ 4~4172~ 6~1831~ 7~1519~ 8~4877~ 9~2424~: 10~2532~ 13~1492~ 14~846~, 16~3870~ [17] 18~3704~ 21~3327~ 23~575~ 24~846~ 25~3725~.'),
  (5623, 5, 28, 6, 'Blessed shalt thou be when thou comest in, and blessed shalt thou be when thou goest out.', '0~01288~ [1] [3] 7~0935~, 9~01288~ [10] [12] 16~03318~.'),
  (23277, 40, 5, 33, 'Again, ye have heard that it hath been said by them of old time, Thou shalt not forswear thyself, but shalt perform unto the Lord thine oaths:', '&para; 0~3825~, 3~191~ 4~3754~ 8~4483~ 13~744~, 15~1964~ 16~3756~ 18~1964~, 19~1161~ 21~591~ 24~2962~ 25~4675~ 26~3727~:'),
  (512, 1, 20, 13, 'And it came to pass, when God caused me to wander from my father''s house, that I said unto her, This is thy kindness which thou shalt shew unto me; at every place whither we shall come, say of me, He is my brother.', '6~0430~ 10~08582~ 13~01~ 14~01004~, 17~0559~ [21] 23~02617~ 27~06213~ 32~04725~ 36~0935~, 37~0559~ [41] 43~0251~.'),
  (26157, 43, 3, 22, 'After these things came Jesus and his disciples into the land of Judaea; and there he tarried with them, and baptized.', '&para; 0~3326~ 2~5023~ 3~2064~ 4~2424~ 5~2532~ 6~846~ 7~3101~ 8~1519~ 10~1093~ 12~2449~; 13~2532~ 14~1563~ 16~1304~ 17~3326~ 18~846~, 19~2532~ 20~907~.'),
  (8503, 10, 18, 17, 'And they took Absalom, and cast him into a great pit in the wood, and laid a very great heap of stones upon him: and all Israel fled every one to his tent.', '2~03947~ 3~053~, 5~07993~ 9~01419~ 10~06354~ 13~03293~, 15~05324~ 17~03966~ 18~01419~ 19~01530~ 21~068~ 26~03478~ 27~05127~ 29~0376~ 32~0168~.'),
  (26648, 43, 13, 3, 'Jesus knowing that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that he was come from God, and went to God;', '0~2424~ 1~1492~ 2~3754~ 4~3962~ 6~1325~ 8~3956~ 9~1519~ 10~846~ 11~5495~, 12~2532~ 13~3754~ 16~1831~ 17~575~ 18~2316~, 19~2532~ 20~5217~ 21~4314~ 22~2316~;'),
  (2600, 2, 36, 29, 'And they were coupled beneath, and coupled together at the head thereof, to one ring: thus he did to both of them in both the corners.', '3~08382~ 4~04295~, 6~08382~ 7~03162~ 10~07218~ 13~0259~ 14~02885~: 17~06213~ 19~08147~ 23~08147~ 25~04740~.');
