  (29809, 54, 6, 5, 'Perverse disputings of men of corrupt minds, and destitute of the truth, supposing that gain is godliness: from such withdraw thyself.', '1~3859~ 3~444~ 5~1311~ 6~3563~, 7~2532~ 8~650~ 11~225~, 12~3543~ 14~4200~ 15~1511~ 16~2150~: 17~575~ 18~5108~ 20~868~.'),
