  (18685, 23, 51, 3, 'For the LORD shall comfort Zion: he will comfort all her waste places; and he will make her wilderness like Eden, and her desert like the garden of the LORD; joy and gladness shall be found therein, thanksgiving, and the voice of melody.', '2~03068~ 4~05162~ 5~06726~: 8~05162~ 12~02723~; 16~07760~ 18~04057~ 20~05731~, 23~06160~ 26~01588~ 29~03068~; 30~08342~ 32~08057~ 35~04672~ 37~08426~, 40~06963~ 42~02172~.'),
  (26902, 43, 20, 19, 'Then the same day at evening, being the first day of the week, when the doors were shut where the disciples were assembled for fear of the Jews, came Jesus and stood in the midst, and saith unto them, Peace be unto you.', '&para; 0~3767~ 2~1565~ 3~2250~ 5~3798~, 6~5607~ 8~3391~ [9] 12~4521~, 13~2532~ 15~2374~ 17~2808~ 18~3699~ 20~3101~ 21~2258~ 22~4863~ 23~1223~ 24~5401~ 27~2453~, 28~2064~ 29~2424~ 30~2532~ 31~2476~ 32~1519~ 34~3319~, 35~2532~ 36~3004~ 38~846~, 39~1515~ [40] 42~5213~.'),
