VALUES
  (23997, 40, 24, 30, 'And then shall appear the sign of the Son of man in heaven: and then shall all the tribes of the earth mourn, and they shall see the Son of man coming in the clouds of heaven with power and great glory.', '0~2532~ 1~5119~ 3~5316~ 5~4592~ 8~5207~ 10~444~ 11~1722~ 12~3772~: 13~2532~ 14~5119~ 15~2875~ 16~3956~ 18~5443~ 21~1093~ 22~2875~, 23~2532~ 26~3700~ 28~5207~ 30~444~ 31~2064~ 32~1909~ 34~3507~ 36~3772~ 37~3326~ 38~1411~ 39~2532~ 40~4183~ 41~1391~.'),
  (26188, 43, 4, 17, 'The woman answered and said, I have no husband. Jesus said unto her, Thou hast well said, I have no husband:', '1~1135~ 2~611~ 3~2532~ 4~2036~, 6~2192~ 7~3756~ 8~435~. 9~2424~ 10~3004~ 12~846~, 14~2036~ 15~2573~ 16~2036~ 17~3754~,* 19~2192~ 20~3756~ 21~435~:'),
  (14387, 19, 33, 12, 'Blessed is the nation whose God is the LORD; and the people whom he hath chosen for his own inheritance.', '&para; 0~0835~ [1] 3~01471~ 5~0430~ [6] 8~03068~; [9] 11~05971~ [12] 15~0977~ 19~05159~.'),
  (15846, 19, 115, 7, 'They have hands, but they handle not: feet have they, but they walk not: neither speak they through their throat.', '2~03027~, 5~04184~ 7~07272~ 12~01980~ 15~01897~ 19~01627~.'),
  (4977, 5, 2, 33, 'And the LORD our God delivered him before us; and we smote him, and his sons, and all his people.', '2~03068~ 4~0430~ 5~05414~ 7~06440~ 11~05221~ 15~01121~, 19~05971~.'),
  (13585, 18, 30, 19, 'He hath cast me into the mire, and I am become like dust and ashes.', '2~03384~ 6~02563~, 11~04911~ 12~06083~ 14~0665~.'),
  (26299, 43, 6, 27, 'Labour not for the meat which perisheth, but for that meat which endureth unto everlasting life, which the Son of man shall give unto you: for him hath God the Father sealed.', '0~2038~ 1~3361~ 4~1035~ 5~3588~ 6~622~, 7~235~ 10~1035~ 11~3588~ 12~3306~ 13~1519~ 14~166~ 15~2222~, 16~3739~ 18~5207~ 20~444~ 22~1325~ 24~5213~: 25~1063~ 26~5126~ 27~4972~ 28~2316~ 30~3962~ 31~4972~.'),
  (28835, 47, 1, 19, 'For the Son of God, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us, even by me and Silvanus and Timotheus, was not yea and nay, but in him was yea.', '0~1063~ 2~5207~ 4~2316~, 5~2424~ 6~5547~, 7~3588~ 9~2784~ 10~1722~ 11~5213~ 12~1223~ 13~2257~, [14] 15~1223~ 16~1700~ 17~2532~ 18~4610~ 19~2532~ 20~5095~, 21~1096~ 22~3756~ 23~3483~ 24~2532~ 25~3756~, 26~235~ 27~1722~ 28~846~ 29~1096~ 30~3483~.'),
  (14614, 19, 45, 8, 'All thy garments smell of myrrh, and aloes, and cassia, out of the ivory palaces, whereby they have made thee glad.', '2~0899~ [3] 5~04753~, 7~0174~, [8] 9~07102~, 13~08127~ 14~01964~, 15~04482~ 20~08055~.'),
  (10788, 13, 14, 6, 'And Nogah, and Nepheg, and Japhia,', '1~05052~, 3~05298~, 5~03309~,'),
  (28954, 47, 8, 6, 'Insomuch that we desired Titus, that as he had begun, so he would also finish in you the same grace also.', '0~1519~ 2~2248~ 3~3870~ 4~5103~, 5~2443~ 6~2531~ 9~4278~, 10~3779~ 12~2005~ 13~2532~ 14~2005~ 15~1519~ 16~5209~ 18~5026~ 19~5485~ 20~2532~.'),
  (15149, 19, 78, 27, 'He rained flesh also upon them as dust, and feathered fowls like as the sand of the sea:', '1~04305~ 2~07607~ 7~06083~, 9~03671~ 10~05775~ 14~02344~ 17~03220~:'),
  (3074, 3, 13, 17, 'And the priest shall see him: and, behold, if the plague be turned into white; then the priest shall pronounce him clean that hath the plague: he is clean.', '2~03548~ 4~07200~ [8] 10~05061~ 12~02015~ 14~03836~; 17~03548~ [20] 21~02891~ [22 23] 25~05061~: [27] 28~02889~.'),
  (8656, 10, 22, 46, 'Strangers shall fade away, and they shall be afraid out of their close places.', '0~05236~ 1~01121~ 3~05034~, 8~02296~ 13~04526~.'),
  (4543, 4, 26, 48, 'Of the sons of Naphtali after their families: of Jahzeel, the family of the Jahzeelites: of Guni, the family of the Gunites:', '[0] 2~01121~ 4~05321~ 7~04940~: 9~03183~, 11~04940~ 14~03184~: 16~01476~, 18~04940~ 21~01477~:'),
  (2572, 2, 36, 1, 'Then wrought Bezaleel and Aholiab, and every wise hearted man, in whom the LORD put wisdom and understanding to know how to work all manner of work for the service of the sanctuary, according to all that the LORD had commanded.', '&para; 1~06213~ 2~01212~ 4~0171~, 7~02450~ 8~03820~ 9~0376~, 11~01992~ 13~03068~ 14~05414~ 15~02451~ 17~08394~ 19~03045~ 22~06213~ 26~04399~ 29~05656~ 32~06944~, 38~03068~ 40~06680~.'),
  (2781, 3, 2, 14, 'And if thou offer a meat offering of thy firstfruits unto the LORD, thou shalt offer for the meat offering of thy firstfruits green ears of corn dried by the fire, even corn beaten out of full ears.', '3~07126~ 6~04503~ 9~01061~ 12~03068~, 15~07126~ 19~04503~ 22~01061~ 24~024~ 27~07033~ 30~0784~, [31] 33~01643~ 37~03759~.'),
  (3013, 3, 11, 11, 'They shall be even an abomination unto you; ye shall not eat of their flesh, but ye shall have their carcases in abomination.', '5~08263~ 11~0398~ 14~01320~, 20~05038~ 22~08262~.'),
  (11498, 14, 14, 14, 'And they smote all the cities round about Gerar; for the fear of the LORD came upon them: and they spoiled all the cities; for there was exceeding much spoil in them.', '2~05221~ 5~05892~ 7~05439~ 8~01642~; 11~06343~ 14~03068~ 20~0962~ 23~05892~; 28~07227~ 29~0961~'),
  (7069, 7, 20, 8, 'And all the people arose as one man, saying, We will not any of us go to his tent, neither will we any of us turn into his house.', '3~05971~ 4~06965~ 6~0259~ 7~0376~, 8~0559~, 12~0376~ [13 14] 15~03212~ 18~0168~, 22~0376~ [23 24] 25~05493~ 28~01004~.'),
  (5954, 6, 5, 14, 'And he said, Nay; but as captain of the host of the LORD am I now come. And Joshua fell on his face to the earth, and did worship, and said unto him, What saith my lord unto his servant?', '2~0559~, [5] 6~08269~ 9~06635~ 12~03068~ 16~0935~. 18~03091~ 19~05307~ 22~06440~ 25~0776~, 28~07812~, 30~0559~ 34~01696~ 36~0113~ 39~05650~?'),
  (4788, 4, 33, 22, 'And they journeyed from Rissah, and pitched in Kehelathah.', '2~05265~ 4~07446~, 6~02583~ 8~06954~.'),
  (21569, 26, 42, 8, 'For the length of the chambers that were in the utter court was fifty cubits: and, lo, before the temple were an hundred cubits.', '2~0753~ 5~03957~ [7] 10~02435~ 11~02691~ [12] 13~02572~ 14~0520~: 17~06440~ 19~01964~ [20] 22~03967~ 23~0520~.'),
  (27763, 44, 23, 13, 'And they were more than forty which had made this conspiracy.', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 4~4119~ 5~5062~ 6~3588~ 8~4160~ 9~5026~ 10~4945~.'),
  (7533, 9, 14, 18, 'And Saul said unto Ahiah, Bring hither the ark of God. For the ark of God was at that time with the children of Israel.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~ 4~0281~, 6~05066~ 8~0727~ 10~0430~. 13~0727~ 15~0430~ 19~03117~ 22~01121~ 24~03478~.'),
  (15717, 19, 107, 9, 'For he satisfieth the longing soul, and filleth the hungry soul with goodness.', '2~07646~ 4~08264~ 5~05315~, 7~04390~ 9~07457~ 10~05315~ 12~02896~.'),
  (4062, 4, 11, 33, 'And while the flesh was yet between their teeth, ere it was chewed, the wrath of the LORD was kindled against the people, and the LORD smote the people with a very great plague.', '3~01320~ [4] 5~02962~ 8~08127~, 12~03772~, 14~0639~ 17~03068~ 19~02734~ 22~05971~, 25~03068~ 26~05221~ 28~05971~ 31~03966~ 32~07227~ 33~04347~.'),
  (7665, 9, 17, 40, 'And he took his staff in his hand, and chose him five smooth stones out of the brook, and put them in a shepherd''s bag which he had, even in a scrip; and his sling was in his hand: and he drew near to the Philistine.', '&para; 2~03947~ 4~04731~ 7~03027~, 9~0977~ 11~02568~ 12~02512~ 13~068~ 17~05158~, 19~07760~ 23~07462~ 24~03627~ 31~03219~; 34~07050~ [35] 38~03027~: 42~05066~ 45~06430~.'),
  (8217, 10, 8, 1, 'And after this it came to pass, that David smote the Philistines, and subdued them: and David took Methegammah out of the hand of the Philistines.', '&para; 1~0310~ 8~01732~ 9~05221~ 11~06430~, 13~03665~ 16~01732~ 17~03947~ 18~04965~ 22~03027~ 25~06430~.'),
  (12624, 16, 11, 27, 'And at Hazarshual, and at Beersheba, and in the villages thereof,', '2~02705~, 5~0884~, [7] 9~01323~'),
  (11873, 14, 31, 10, 'And Azariah the chief priest of the house of Zadok answered him, and said, Since the people began to bring the offerings into the house of the LORD, we have had enough to eat, and have left plenty: for the LORD hath blessed his people; and that which is left is this great store.', '1~05838~ 3~07218~ 4~03548~ 7~01004~ 9~06659~ 10~0559~ 13~0559~, [15 16] 17~02490~ 19~0935~ 21~08641~ 24~01004~ 27~03068~, 31~07646~ 33~0398~, 36~03498~ 37~07230~: 40~03068~ 42~01288~ 44~05971~; 49~03498~ [50] 53~01995~.'),
  (25943, 42, 22, 65, 'And many other things blasphemously spake they against him.', '0~2532~ 1~4183~ 3~2087~ 4~987~ 6~3004~ 7~1519~ 8~846~.'),
  (21865, 27, 4, 19, 'Then Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, was astonied for one hour, and his thoughts troubled him. The king spake, and said, Belteshazzar, let not the dream, or the interpretation thereof, trouble thee. Belteshazzar answered and said, My lord, the dream be to them that hate thee, and the interpretation thereof to thine enemies.', '&para; 0~0116~ 1~01841~, 3~08036~ [4] 5~01096~, 7~08075~ 9~02298~ 10~08160~, 13~07476~ 14~0927~ 17~04430~ 18~06032~, 20~0560~, 21~01096~, 23~0409~ 25~02493~, 28~06591~ 30~0927~ 32~01096~ 33~06032~ 35~0560~, 37~04756~, 39~02493~ [40] 44~08131~ 48~06591~ 52~06146~.'),
  (26636, 43, 12, 41, 'These things said Esaias, when he saw his glory, and spake of him.', '1~5023~ 2~2036~ 3~2268~, 4~3753~ 6~1492~ 7~846~ 8~1391~, 9~2532~ 10~2980~ 11~4012~ 12~846~.'),
  (12419, 16, 6, 9, 'For they all made us afraid, saying, Their hands shall be weakened from the work, that it be not done. Now therefore, O God, strengthen my hands.', '5~03372~, 6~0559~, 8~03027~ 11~07503~ 14~04399~, 19~06213~. [22 23] 24~02388~ 26~03027~.'),
  (9080, 11, 9, 21, 'Their children that were left after them in the land, whom the children of Israel also were not able utterly to destroy, upon those did Solomon levy a tribute of bondservice unto this day.', '1~01121~ 4~03498~ 5~0310~ 9~0776~, 12~01121~ 14~03478~ 18~03201~ 21~02763~, 25~08010~ 26~05927~ 28~04522~ 30~05647~ 33~03117~.'),
  (17140, 20, 25, 18, 'A man that beareth false witness against his neighbour is a maul, and a sword, and a sharp arrow.', '&para; 1~0376~ 3~06030~ 4~08267~ 5~05707~ 8~07453~ [9] 11~04650~, 14~02719~, 17~08150~ 18~02671~.'),
  (28311, 45, 14, 15, 'But if thy brother be grieved with thy meat, now walkest thou not charitably. Destroy not him with thy meat, for whom Christ died.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 2~4675~ 3~80~ 5~3076~ 6~1223~ [7] 8~1033~, 9~3765~ 11~4043~ 12~3765~ 13~2596~ 14~26~.* 15~622~ 16~3361~ 17~1565~ 19~4675~ 20~1033~, 21~5228~ 22~3739~ 23~5547~ 24~599~.'),
  (21384, 26, 36, 16, 'Moreover the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (17262, 20, 30, 2, 'Surely I am more brutish than any man, and have not the understanding of a man.', '[2] 4~01198~ [6] 7~0376~, 12~0998~ 15~0120~.'),
  (10024, 12, 17, 33, 'They feared the LORD, and served their own gods, after the manner of the nations whom they carried away from thence.', '1~03373~ 3~03068~, 5~05647~ 8~0430~, 11~04941~ 14~01471~ 18~01540~'),
  (14207, 19, 21, 7, 'For the king trusteth in the LORD, and through the mercy of the most High he shall not be moved.', '&para; 2~04428~ 3~0982~ 6~03068~, 10~02617~ 14~05945~ 19~04131~.'),
  (22127, 28, 2, 13, 'And I will visit upon her the days of Baalim, wherein she burned incense to them, and she decked herself with her earrings and her jewels, and she went after her lovers, and forgat me, saith the LORD.', '3~06485~ 7~03117~ 9~01168~, 13~06999~ 18~05710~ 22~05141~ 25~02484~, 28~03212~ 29~0310~ 31~0157~, 33~07911~ 35~05002~ 37~03068~.'),
  (4907, 5, 1, 9, 'And I spake unto you at that time, saying, I am not able to bear you myself alone:', '&para; 2~0559~ 7~06256~, 8~0559~, 12~03201~ 14~05375~ 17~0905~:'),
  (13046, 18, 8, 8, 'For inquire, I pray thee, of the former age, and prepare thyself to the search of their fathers:', '&para; 1~07592~, 7~07223~ 8~07223~* 9~01755~, 11~03559~ 15~02714~ 18~01~:'),
  (18035, 23, 19, 22, 'And the LORD shall smite Egypt: he shall smite and heal it: and they shall return even to the LORD, and he shall be entreated of them, and shall heal them.', '2~03068~ 4~05062~ 5~04714~: 8~05062~ 10~07495~ [11] 15~07725~ [16] 19~03068~, 24~06279~ 29~07495~'),
  (20376, 25, 3, 13, 'He hath caused the arrows of his quiver to enter into my reins.', '4~01121~ 7~0827~ 9~0935~ 12~03629~.'),
  (13134, 18, 11, 17, 'And thine age shall be clearer than the noonday; thou shalt shine forth, thou shalt be as the morning.', '[1] 2~02465~ 5~06965~ 8~06672~; 12~05774~, 18~01242~.'),
  (12365, 16, 3, 29, 'After them repaired Zadok the son of Immer over against his house. After him repaired also Shemaiah the son of Shechaniah, the keeper of the east gate.', '0~0310~ 2~02388~ 3~06659~ 5~01121~ 7~0564~ 11~01004~. 12~0310~ 14~02388~ 16~08098~ 18~01121~ 20~07935~, 22~08104~ 25~04217~ 26~08179~.'),
  (25951, 42, 23, 2, 'And they began to accuse him, saying, We found this fellow perverting the nation, and forbidding to give tribute to Caesar, saying that he himself is Christ a King.', '0~1161~ 2~756~ 4~2723~ 5~846~, 6~3004~, 8~2147~ 9~5126~ [10] 11~1294~ 13~1484~, 14~2532~ 15~2967~ 17~1325~ 18~5411~ 20~2541~, 21~3004~ 24~1438~ 25~1511~ 26~5547~ 28~935~.'),
  (21843, 27, 3, 27, 'And the princes, governors, and captains, and the king''s counsellors, being gathered together, saw these men, upon whose bodies the fire had no power, nor was an hair of their head singed, neither were their coats changed, nor the smell of fire had passed on them.', '2~0324~, 3~05460~, 5~06347~, 8~04430~ 9~01907~, 12~03673~, 13~02370~ 14~0479~ 15~01400~, 18~01655~ 20~05135~ 22~03809~ 23~07981~, 24~03809~ 27~08177~ 30~07217~ 31~02761~, 32~03809~ 35~05622~ 36~08133~, 37~03809~ 39~07382~ 41~05135~ 43~05709~'),
  (7960, 9, 28, 11, 'Then said the woman, Whom shall I bring up unto thee? And he said, Bring me up Samuel.', '1~0559~ 3~0802~, 8~05927~ 13~0559~, 16~05927~ 17~08050~.'),
  (6916, 7, 13, 25, 'And the spirit of the LORD began to move him at times in the camp of Dan between Zorah and Eshtaol.', '2~07307~ 5~03068~ 6~02490~ 11~06470~ 14~04264~ 16~01835~ 18~06881~ 20~0847~.'),
  (29932, 56, 2, 8, 'Sound speech, that cannot be condemned; that he that is of the contrary part may be ashamed, having no evil thing to say of you.', '0~5199~ 1~3056~, 5~176~; 6~2443~ 10~1537~ 13~1727~ 16~1788~, 17~2192~ 18~3367~ 19~5337~ 20~3367~ 22~3004~ 23~4012~ 24~5216~.'),
  (11584, 14, 18, 33, 'And a certain man drew a bow at a venture, and smote the king of Israel between the joints of the harness: therefore he said to his chariot man, Turn thine hand, that thou mayest carry me out of the host; for I am wounded.', '[2] 4~04900~ 6~07198~ 9~08537~, 11~05221~ 13~04428~ 15~03478~ 18~01694~ 21~08302~: 24~0559~ 27~07395~ 28~0376~, 29~02015~ 31~03027~, 37~03318~ 40~04264~; 44~02470~.'),
  (9701, 12, 6, 19, 'And Elisha said unto them, This is not the way, neither is this the city: follow me, and I will bring you to the man whom ye seek. But he led them to Samaria.', '1~0477~ 2~0559~ [6] 9~01870~, [11] 12~02090~ 14~05892~: 15~03212~ 16~0310~* 21~03212~ 25~0376~ 28~01245~. 31~03212~ 34~08111~.'),
  (27118, 44, 6, 1, 'And in those days, when the number of the disciples was multiplied, there arose a murmuring of the Grecians against the Hebrews, because their widows were neglected in the daily ministration.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1722~ 2~5025~ 3~2250~, 6~4129~ 9~3101~ 11~4129~, 13~1096~ 15~1112~ 18~1675~ 19~4314~ 21~1445~, 22~3754~ 23~846~ 24~5503~ 26~3865~ 27~1722~ 29~2522~ 30~1248~.'),
  (3285, 3, 18, 29, 'For whosoever shall commit any of these abominations, even the souls that commit them shall be cut off from among their people.', '3~06213~ 7~08441~, 10~05315~ 12~06213~ [13] 17~03772~ 19~07130~ 21~05971~.'),
  (29906, 55, 4, 20, 'Erastus abode at Corinth: but Trophimus have I left at Miletum sick.', '0~2037~ 1~3306~ 2~1722~ 3~2882~: 4~1161~ 5~5161~ 8~620~ 9~1722~ 10~3399~ 11~770~.'),
  (4533, 4, 26, 38, 'The sons of Benjamin after their families: of Bela, the family of the Belaites: of Ashbel, the family of the Ashbelites: of Ahiram, the family of the Ahiramites:', '1~01121~ 3~01144~ 6~04940~: 8~01106~, 10~04940~ 13~01108~: 15~0788~, 17~04940~ 20~0789~: 22~0297~, 24~04940~ 27~0298~:'),
  (21331, 26, 34, 9, 'Therefore, O ye shepherds, hear the word of the LORD;', '3~07462~, 4~08085~ 6~01697~ 9~03068~;'),
  (8916, 11, 6, 12, 'Concerning this house which thou art in building, if thou wilt walk in my statutes, and execute my judgments, and keep all my commandments to walk in them; then will I perform my word with thee, which I spake unto David thy father:', '[0] 2~01004~ 7~01129~, 11~03212~ 14~02708~, 16~06213~ 18~04941~, 20~08104~ 23~04687~ 25~03212~ 31~06965~ 33~01697~ 38~01696~ 40~01732~ 42~01~:'),
  (27342, 44, 11, 19, 'Now they which were scattered abroad upon the persecution that arose about Stephen travelled as far as Phenice, and Cyprus, and Antioch, preaching the word to none but unto the Jews only.', '&para; 0~3303~ 1~3767~ 5~1289~ 6~575~ 8~2347~ 10~1096~ 11~1909~ 12~4736~ 13~1330~ 16~2193~ 17~5403~, 18~2532~ 19~2954~, 20~2532~ 21~490~, 22~2980~ 24~3056~ 26~3367~ 27~1508~ 30~2453~ 31~3440~.'),
  (3034, 3, 11, 32, 'And upon whatsoever any of them, when they are dead, doth fall, it shall be unclean; whether it be any vessel of wood, or raiment, or skin, or sack, whatsoever vessel it be, wherein any work is done, it must be put into water, and it shall be unclean until the even; so it shall be cleansed.', '[3] 9~04194~, 11~05307~, 15~02930~; [17 18] 20~03627~ 22~06086~, 24~0899~, 26~05785~, 28~08242~, 30~03627~ [31 32] [34] 35~04399~ 37~06213~, 41~0935~ 43~04325~, 48~02930~ 51~06153~; 56~02891~.'),
  (13028, 18, 7, 11, 'Therefore I will not refrain my mouth; I will speak in the anguish of my spirit; I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.', '4~02820~ 6~06310~; 9~01696~ 12~06862~ 15~07307~; 18~07878~ 21~04751~ 24~05315~.'),
  (24762, 41, 13, 34, 'For the Son of man is as a man taking a far journey, who left his house, and gave authority to his servants, and to every man his work, and commanded the porter to watch.', '[0 5] 6~5613~ 8~444~ 12~590~, 14~863~ 15~846~ 16~3614~, 17~2532~ 18~1325~ 19~1849~ 21~846~ 22~1401~, 23~2532~ 26~1538~ 27~846~ 28~2041~, 29~2532~ 30~1781~ 32~2377~ 33~2443~ 34~1127~.'),
  (8443, 10, 16, 10, 'And the king said, What have I to do with you, ye sons of Zeruiah? so let him curse, because the LORD hath said unto him, Curse David. Who shall then say, Wherefore hast thou done so?', '2~04428~ 3~0559~, 12~01121~ 14~06870~? 18~07043~, 21~03068~ 23~0559~ 26~07043~ 27~01732~. 31~0559~, 36~06213~?'),
  (4234, 4, 16, 35, 'And there came out a fire from the LORD, and consumed the two hundred and fifty men that offered incense.', '&para; 3~03318~ 5~0784~ 8~03068~, 10~0398~ 13~03967~ 15~02572~ 16~0376~ 18~07126~ 19~07004~.'),
  (9300, 11, 16, 9, 'And his servant Zimri, captain of half his chariots, conspired against him, as he was in Tirzah, drinking himself drunk in the house of Arza steward of his house in Tirzah.', '2~05650~ 3~02174~, 4~08269~ 6~04276~ [7] 8~07393~, 9~07194~ 16~08656~, 17~08354~ 19~07910~ 22~01004~ 24~0777~ [27] 28~01004~ 30~08656~.'),
  (27262, 44, 9, 30, 'Which when the brethren knew, they brought him down to Caesarea, and sent him forth to Tarsus.', '[0] 1~1161~ 3~80~ 4~1921~, 6~2609~ 7~846~ 8~2609~ 9~1519~ 10~2542~, 11~2532~ 12~1821~ 13~846~ 14~1821~ 15~1519~ 16~5019~.'),
  (30325, 59, 2, 16, 'And one of you say unto them, Depart in peace, be ye warmed and filled; notwithstanding ye give them not those things which are needful to the body; what doth it profit?', '0~1161~ 1~5100~ 2~1537~ 3~5216~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 7~5217~ 8~1722~ 9~1515~, [11] 12~2328~ 13~2532~ 14~5526~; 15~1161~ 17~1325~ 18~846~ 19~3361~ 24~2006~ 27~4983~; 28~5101~ [29 30] 31~3786~?'),
  (18714, 23, 52, 9, 'Break forth into joy, sing together, ye waste places of Jerusalem: for the LORD hath comforted his people, he hath redeemed Jerusalem.', '3~06476~, 4~07442~ 5~03162~, 8~02723~ 10~03389~: 13~03068~ 15~05162~ 17~05971~, 20~01350~ 21~03389~.'),
  (28892, 47, 4, 17, 'For our light affliction, which is but for a moment, worketh for us a far more exceeding and eternal weight of glory;', '0~1063~ 1~2257~ 2~1645~ 3~2347~, 4~3588~ 9~3910~, 10~2716~ 12~2254~ 14~5236~ 15~2596~ 16~5236~ [17] 17~1519~ 18~166~ 19~922~ 21~1391~;'),
  (1907, 2, 14, 13, 'And Moses said unto the people, Fear ye not, stand still, and see the salvation of the LORD, which he will shew to you to day: for the Egyptians whom ye have seen to day, ye shall see them again no more for ever.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 5~05971~, 6~03372~ 10~03320~, 12~07200~ 14~03444~ 17~03068~, 21~06213~ 25~03117~: 28~04714~ 32~07200~ 34~03117~, 37~07200~ 39~03254~ 42~05704~ 43~05769~.'),
  (8477, 10, 17, 20, 'And when Absalom''s servants came to the woman to the house, they said, Where is Ahimaaz and Jonathan? And the woman said unto them, They be gone over the brook of water. And when they had sought and could not find them, they returned to Jerusalem.', '2~053~ 3~05650~ 4~0935~ 7~0802~ 10~01004~, 12~0559~, [14] 15~0290~ 17~03083~? 20~0802~ 21~0559~ 27~05674~ 29~04323~ 31~04325~. 36~01245~ 40~04672~ [41] 43~07725~ 45~03389~.'),
  (11681, 14, 23, 16, 'And Jehoiada made a covenant between him, and between all the people, and between the king, that they should be the LORD''S people.', '1~03077~ 2~03772~ 4~01285~ 11~05971~, 15~04428~, 21~03068~ 22~05971~.'),
  (27466, 44, 15, 8, 'And God, which knoweth the hearts, bare them witness, giving them the Holy Ghost, even as he did unto us;', '0~2532~ 1~2316~, 5~2589~, 7~846~ 8~3140~, 9~1325~ 10~846~ 12~40~ 13~4151~, 14~2532~ 15~2531~ [16 17] 19~2254~;'),
  (23889, 40, 22, 7, 'But when the king heard thereof, he was wroth: and he sent forth his armies, and destroyed those murderers, and burned up their city.', '0~1161~ 3~935~ 4~191~ [5] 8~3710~: 9~2532~ 12~3992~ 13~846~ 14~4753~, 16~622~ 17~1565~ 18~5406~, 19~2532~ 21~1714~ 22~846~ 23~4172~.'),
  (9652, 12, 4, 41, 'But he said, Then bring meal. And he cast it into the pot; and he said, Pour out for the people, that they may eat. And there was no harm in the pot.', '2~0559~, 4~03947~ 5~07058~. 8~07993~ [9] 12~05518~; 15~0559~, 17~03332~ 20~05971~, 24~0398~. 29~07451~ 30~01697~ 32~05518~.'),
  (13617, 18, 31, 20, 'If his loins have not blessed me, and if he were not warmed with the fleece of my sheep;', '2~02504~ 5~01288~ [8] [11] 12~02552~ 15~01488~ 18~03532~;'),
  (24462, 41, 6, 45, 'And straightway he constrained his disciples to get into the ship, and to go to the other side before unto Bethsaida, while he sent away the people.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2112~ 3~315~ 4~846~ 5~3101~ 7~1684~ 8~1519~ 10~4143~, 11~2532~ 13~4254~ 14~1519~ 17~4008~ 18~4254~ 19~4314~ 20~966~, 21~2193~ 22~846~ 24~630~ 26~3793~.'),
  (24031, 40, 25, 13, 'Watch therefore, for ye know neither the day nor the hour wherein the Son of man cometh.', '0~1127~ 1~3767~, 2~3754~ 4~1492~ 5~3756~ 7~2250~ 8~3761~ 10~5610~ 11~3739~ 12~1722~ 13~5207~ 15~444~ 16~2064~.'),
  (23429, 40, 10, 2, 'Now the names of the twelve apostles are these; The first, Simon, who is called Peter, and Andrew his brother; James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother;', '0~1161~ 2~3686~ 5~1427~ 6~652~ 7~2076~ 8~5023~; 10~4413~, 11~4613~, 12~3588~ 14~3004~ 15~4074~, 16~2532~ 17~406~ 18~846~ 19~80~; 20~2385~ [21 22] 23~3588~ 24~2199~, 25~2532~ 26~2491~ 27~846~ 28~80~;'),
  (12440, 16, 7, 11, 'The children of Pahathmoab, of the children of Jeshua and Joab, two thousand and eight hundred and eighteen.', '1~01121~ 3~06355~, 6~01121~ 8~03442~ 10~03097~, 12~0505~ 14~08083~ 15~03967~ [16] 17~06240~ 18~08083~.*'),
  (678, 1, 25, 16, 'These are the sons of Ishmael, and these are their names, by their towns, and by their castles; twelve princes according to their nations.', '[1] 3~01121~ 5~03458~, [8] 10~08034~, 13~02691~, 17~02918~; 18~06240~ 19~08147~* 20~05387~ 24~0523~.'),
  (83, 1, 4, 3, 'And in process of time it came to pass, that Cain brought of the fruit of the ground an offering unto the LORD.', '&para; 2~07093~ 4~03117~ 10~07014~ 11~0935~ 14~06529~ 17~0127~ 19~04503~ 22~03068~.'),
  (26193, 43, 4, 22, 'Ye worship ye know not what: we know what we worship: for salvation is of the Jews.', '0~5210~ 1~4352~ 3~1492~ 4~3756~ 5~3739~: 7~1492~ 8~3739~ 9~2249~ 10~4352~: 11~3754~ 12~4991~ 13~2076~ 14~1537~ 16~2453~.'),
  (15282, 19, 85, 2, 'Thou hast forgiven the iniquity of thy people, thou hast covered all their sin. Selah.', '2~05375~ 4~05771~ 7~05971~, 10~03680~ 13~02403~. 14~05542~.'),
  (19052, 24, 4, 16, 'Make ye mention to the nations; behold, publish against Jerusalem, that watchers come from a far country, and give out their voice against the cities of Judah.', '2~02142~ 5~01471~; 7~08085~ 9~03389~, [10] 11~05341~ 12~0935~ 15~04801~ 16~0776~, 19~05414~ 21~06963~ 24~05892~ 26~03063~.'),
  (15660, 19, 105, 45, 'That they might observe his statutes, and keep his laws. Praise ye the LORD.', '3~08104~ 5~02706~, 7~05341~ 9~08451~. 10~01984~ 13~03050~.'),
  (14114, 19, 17, 2, 'Let my sentence come forth from thy presence; let thine eyes behold the things that are equal.', '2~04941~ 4~03318~ 7~06440~; 10~05869~ 11~02372~ 16~04339~.'),
  (3155, 3, 14, 39, 'And the priest shall come again the seventh day, and shall look: and, behold, if the plague be spread in the walls of the house;', '2~03548~ 5~07725~ 7~07637~ 8~03117~, 11~07200~: [14] 16~05061~ 18~06581~ 21~07023~ 24~01004~;'),
  (9600, 12, 3, 16, 'And he said, Thus saith the LORD, Make this valley full of ditches.', '2~0559~, 4~0559~ 6~03068~, 7~06213~ 9~05158~ 12~01356~.'),
  (19114, 24, 6, 16, 'Thus saith the LORD, Stand ye in the ways, and see, and ask for the old paths, where is the good way, and walk therein, and ye shall find rest for your souls. But they said, We will not walk therein.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 4~05975~ 8~01870~, 10~07200~, 12~07592~ 15~05769~ 16~05410~, [18] 20~02896~ 21~01870~, 23~03212~ 28~04672~ 29~04771~ 32~05315~. 35~0559~, 39~03212~ [40]'),
  (28390, 46, 1, 11, 'For it hath been declared unto me of you, my brethren, by them which are of the house of Chloe, that there are contentions among you.', '0~1063~ 4~1213~ 6~3427~ 7~4012~ 8~5216~, 9~3450~ 10~80~, 11~5259~ [13 17] 17~3588~ 19~5514~, 20~3754~ 22~1526~ 23~2054~ 24~1722~ 25~5213~.'),
  (14621, 19, 45, 15, 'With gladness and rejoicing shall they be brought: they shall enter into the king''s palace.', '1~08057~ 3~01524~ 7~02986~: 10~0935~ 13~04428~ 14~01964~.'),
  (22120, 28, 2, 6, 'Therefore, behold, I will hedge up thy way with thorns, and make a wall, that she shall not find her paths.', '&para; 4~07753~ 7~01870~ 9~05518~, 11~01443~ 13~01447~, 18~04672~ 20~05410~.'),
  (22298, 28, 14, 7, 'They that dwell under his shadow shall return; they shall revive as the corn, and grow as the vine: the scent thereof shall be as the wine of Lebanon.', '2~03427~ 5~06738~ 7~07725~; 10~02421~ [11] 13~01715~, 15~06524~ 18~01612~: 20~02143~ [22 23] 26~03196~ 28~03844~.'),
  (12924, 18, 3, 11, 'Why died I not from the womb? why did I not give up the ghost when I came out of the belly?', '&para; 1~04191~ 6~07358~? [7] [10] 14~01478~ 18~03318~ 21~0990~?'),
  (23981, 40, 24, 14, 'And this gospel of the kingdom shall be preached in all the world for a witness unto all nations; and then shall the end come.', '0~2532~ 1~5124~ 2~2098~ 5~932~ 8~2784~ 9~1722~ 10~3650~ 12~3625~ 13~1519~ 15~3142~ 17~3956~ 18~1484~; 19~2532~ 20~5119~ 23~5056~ 24~2240~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (26607, 43, 12, 12, 'On the next day much people that were come to the feast, when they heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem,', '&para; 3~1887~ 4~4183~ 5~3793~ 8~2064~ 9~1519~ 11~1859~, 14~191~ 15~3754~ 16~2424~ 18~2064~ 19~1519~ 20~2414~,'),
  (9018, 11, 8, 25, 'Therefore now, LORD God of Israel, keep with thy servant David my father that thou promisedst him, saying, There shall not fail thee a man in my sight to sit on the throne of Israel; so that thy children take heed to their way, that they walk before me as thou hast walked before me.', '2~03068~ 3~0430~ 5~03478~, 6~08104~ 9~05650~ 10~01732~ 12~01~ 15~01696~ 17~0559~, 21~03772~ 24~0376~ 27~06440~ 29~03427~ 32~03678~ 34~03478~; 35~07535~ 38~01121~ 40~08104~ 43~01870~, 46~03212~ 47~06440~ 52~01980~ 53~06440~'),
  (4029, 4, 10, 36, 'And when it rested, he said, Return, O LORD, unto the many thousands of Israel.', '3~05117~, 5~0559~, 6~07725~, 8~03068~, 11~07233~ 12~0505~ 14~03478~.'),
  (8011, 9, 30, 26, 'And when David came to Ziklag, he sent of the spoil unto the elders of Judah, even to his friends, saying, Behold a present for you of the spoil of the enemies of the LORD;', '2~01732~ 3~0935~ 5~06860~, 7~07971~ 10~07998~ 13~02205~ 15~03063~, [16] 19~07453~, 20~0559~, 23~01293~ 28~07998~ 31~0341~ 34~03068~;'),
  (28936, 47, 7, 4, 'Great is my boldness of speech toward you, great is my glorying of you: I am filled with comfort, I am exceeding joyful in all our tribulation.', '0~4183~ [1] 2~3427~ 5~3954~ 6~4314~ 7~5209~, 8~4183~ [9] 10~3427~ 11~2746~ 12~5228~ 13~5216~: 16~4137~ 18~3874~, 21~5248~ 22~5479~ 23~1909~ 24~3956~ 25~2257~ 26~2347~.'),
  (26255, 43, 5, 30, 'I can of mine own self do nothing: as I hear, I judge: and my judgment is just; because I seek not mine own will, but the will of the Father which hath sent me.', '0~1473~ 1~1410~ 2~575~ 5~1683~ 6~4160~ 7~3762~ 8~3756~:* 9~2531~ 11~191~, 13~2919~: 14~2532~ 15~1699~ 16~2920~ 17~2076~ 18~1342~; 19~3754~ 21~2212~ 22~3756~ 24~1699~ 25~2307~, 26~235~ 28~2307~ 31~3962~ 34~3992~ 35~3165~.'),
  (20811, 26, 16, 40, 'They shall also bring up a company against thee, and they shall stone thee with stones, and thrust thee through with their swords.', '4~05927~ 6~06951~ 12~07275~ 15~068~, 19~01333~ 22~02719~.'),
  (30393, 60, 1, 3, 'Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, which according to his abundant mercy hath begotten us again unto a lively hope by the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,', '&para; 0~2128~ [1] 3~2316~ 4~2532~ 5~3962~ 7~2257~ 8~2962~ 9~2424~ 10~5547~, 11~3588~ 13~2596~ 14~846~ 15~4183~ 16~1656~ 18~313~ 19~2248~ 20~313~ 21~1519~ 23~2198~ 24~1680~ 25~1223~ 27~386~ 29~2424~ 30~5547~ 31~1537~ 33~3498~,'),
  (11606, 14, 20, 10, 'And now, behold, the children of Ammon and Moab and mount Seir, whom thou wouldest not let Israel invade, when they came out of the land of Egypt, but they turned from them, and destroyed them not;', '4~01121~ 6~05983~ 8~04124~ 10~02022~ 11~08165~, 16~05414~ 17~03478~ 18~0935~, 22~0935~ 25~0776~ 27~04714~, 30~05493~ 34~08045~'),
  (4796, 4, 33, 30, 'And they departed from Hashmonah, and encamped at Moseroth.', '2~05265~ 4~02832~, 6~02583~ 8~04149~.'),
  (28706, 46, 14, 12, 'Even so ye, forasmuch as ye are zealous of spiritual gifts, seek that ye may excel to the edifying of the church.', '0~2532~ 1~3779~ 2~5210~, 4~1893~ 6~2075~ 7~2207~ 9~4151~ [10] 11~2212~ 12~2443~ 15~4052~ 16~4314~ 18~3619~ 21~1577~.'),
  (22240, 28, 10, 6, 'It shall be also carried unto Assyria for a present to king Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.', '4~02986~ 6~0804~ [7] 9~04503~ 11~04428~ 12~03377~: 13~0669~ 15~03947~ 16~01317~, 18~03478~ 21~0954~ 25~06098~.'),
  (27084, 44, 5, 9, 'Then Peter said unto her, How is it that ye have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord? behold, the feet of them which have buried thy husband are at the door, and shall carry thee out.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 5~5101~ 8~3754~ 9~5213~ 12~4856~ 14~3985~ 16~4151~ 19~2962~? 20~2400~, 22~4228~ 27~2290~ 28~4675~ 29~435~ [30] 31~1909~ 33~2374~, 34~2532~ 36~1627~ 37~4571~ 38~1627~.'),
  (2762, 3, 1, 12, 'And he shall cut it into his pieces, with his head and his fat: and the priest shall lay them in order on the wood that is on the fire which is upon the altar:', '3~05408~ 7~05409~, 10~07218~ 13~06309~: 16~03548~ 21~06186~ 24~06086~ [26] 29~0784~ [31] 34~04196~:'),
  (14684, 19, 50, 7, 'Hear, O my people, and I will speak; O Israel, and I will testify against thee: I am God, even thy God.', '&para; 0~08085~, 3~05971~, 7~01696~; 9~03478~, 13~05749~ [17] 18~0430~, [19] 21~0430~.'),
  (24614, 41, 10, 15, 'Verily I say unto you, Whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child, he shall not enter therein.', '0~281~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3739~ 6~1209~ 7~3362~ 8~1209~ 10~932~ 12~2316~ 13~5613~ 16~3813~, 18~1525~ 19~3364~ 20~1525~ 21~846~ 22~1519~.*'),
  (29000, 47, 10, 13, 'But we will not boast of things without our measure, but according to the measure of the rule which God hath distributed to us, a measure to reach even unto you.', '0~1161~ 1~2249~ 2~2744~ 3~3780~ 4~2744~ 7~1519~ [8] 9~280~, 10~235~ 11~2596~ 14~3358~ 17~2583~ 18~3739~ 19~2316~ 21~3307~ 23~2254~, 25~3358~ 27~2185~ 28~2532~ 29~891~ 30~5216~.'),
  (30946, 66, 14, 4, 'These are they which were not defiled with women; for they are virgins. These are they which follow the Lamb whithersoever he goeth. These were redeemed from among men, being the firstfruits unto God and to the Lamb.', '0~3778~ 2~1526~ 3~3739~ 4~3435~ 5~3756~ 6~3435~ 7~3326~ 8~1135~; 9~1063~ 11~1526~ 12~3933~. 13~3778~ 15~1526~ 16~3588~ 17~190~ 19~721~ 20~302~ 21~3699~ 22~5217~. 23~3778~ 25~59~ 26~575~ 28~444~, [29] 31~536~ 33~2316~ 34~2532~ 37~721~.'),
  (25144, 42, 5, 25, 'And immediately he rose up before them, and took up that whereon he lay, and departed to his own house, glorifying God.', '0~2532~ 1~3916~ 4~450~ 5~1799~ 6~846~, 9~142~ 11~3739~ 12~1909~ 13~2621~, 15~565~ 16~1519~ 18~846~ 19~3624~, 20~1392~ 21~2316~.'),
  (25777, 42, 19, 32, 'And they that were sent went their way, and found even as he had said unto them.', '0~1161~ 4~649~ 7~565~, 9~2147~ 11~2531~ 14~2036~ 16~846~.'),
  (9947, 12, 15, 14, 'For Menahem the son of Gadi went up from Tirzah, and came to Samaria, and smote Shallum the son of Jabesh in Samaria, and slew him, and reigned in his stead.', '1~04505~ 3~01121~ 5~01424~ 7~05927~ 9~08656~, 11~0935~ 13~08111~, 15~05221~ 16~07967~ 18~01121~ 20~03003~ 22~08111~, 24~04191~ 27~04427~'),
  (4320, 4, 20, 4, 'And why have ye brought up the congregation of the LORD into this wilderness, that we and our cattle should die there?', '5~0935~ 7~06951~ 10~03068~ 13~04057~, 18~01165~ 20~04191~'),
  (19973, 24, 41, 7, 'And it was so, when they came into the midst of the city, that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah slew them, and cast them into the midst of the pit, he, and the men that were with him.', '[3] 6~0935~ 9~08432~ 12~05892~, 14~03458~ 16~01121~ 18~05418~ 19~07819~ [21 23] 26~08432~ 29~0953~, 33~0582~ [35]'),
  (16958, 20, 19, 24, 'A slothful man hideth his hand in his bosom, and will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.', '&para; 1~06102~ [2] 3~02934~ 5~03027~ [7] 8~06747~, 15~07725~ 19~06310~ 20~07725~.'),
  (13284, 18, 17, 15, 'And where is now my hope? as for my hope, who shall see it?', '[2] 3~0645~ 5~08615~? 9~08615~, 12~07789~'),
  (22998, 38, 8, 13, 'And it shall come to pass, that as ye were a curse among the heathen, O house of Judah, and house of Israel; so will I save you, and ye shall be a blessing: fear not, but let your hands be strong.', '[6] 11~07045~ 14~01471~, 16~01004~ 18~03063~, 20~01004~ 22~03478~; 26~03467~ 33~01293~: 34~03372~ [36] 39~03027~ 41~02388~.'),
  (28945, 47, 7, 13, 'Therefore we were comforted in your comfort: yea, and exceedingly the more joyed we for the joy of Titus, because his spirit was refreshed by you all.', '0~5124~ 1~1223~ 3~3870~ 4~1909~ 5~5216~ 6~3874~: 8~1161~ 9~4056~ 11~3123~ 13~5463~ 14~1909~ 16~5479~ 18~5103~, 19~3754~ 20~846~ 21~4151~ 23~373~ 24~575~ 25~5216~ 26~3956~.'),
  (7166, 8, 2, 10, 'Then she fell on her face, and bowed herself to the ground, and said unto him, Why have I found grace in thine eyes, that thou shouldest take knowledge of me, seeing I am a stranger?', '2~05307~ 5~06440~, 7~07812~ 11~0776~, 13~0559~ 19~04672~ 20~02580~ 23~05869~, 28~05234~ [33] 35~05237~?'),
  (14864, 19, 64, 5, 'They encourage themselves in an evil matter: they commune of laying snares privily; they say, Who shall see them?', '1~02388~ [3] 5~07451~ 6~01697~: 8~05608~ 10~02934~ 11~04170~ 12~02934~; 14~0559~, 17~07200~'),
  (9237, 11, 14, 11, 'Him that dieth of Jeroboam in the city shall the dogs eat; and him that dieth in the field shall the fowls of the air eat: for the LORD hath spoken it.', '2~04191~ 4~03379~ 7~05892~ 10~03611~ 11~0398~; 15~04191~ 18~07704~ 21~05775~ 24~08064~ 25~0398~: 28~03068~ 30~01696~ [31]'),
  (15623, 19, 105, 8, 'He hath remembered his covenant for ever, the word which he commanded to a thousand generations.', '&para; 2~02142~ 4~01285~ 6~05769~, 8~01697~ [9] 11~06680~ 14~0505~ 15~01755~.'),
  (3385, 3, 22, 11, 'But if the priest buy any soul with his money, he shall eat of it, and he that is born in his house: they shall eat of his meat.', '3~03548~ 4~07069~ [5] 6~05315~ 7~07075~ 9~03701~, 12~0398~ 19~03211~ 22~01004~: 25~0398~ 28~03899~.'),
  (21586, 26, 43, 5, 'So the spirit took me up, and brought me into the inner court; and, behold, the glory of the LORD filled the house.', '2~07307~ 5~05375~, 7~0935~ 11~06442~ 12~02691~; 16~03519~ 19~03068~ 20~04390~ 22~01004~.'),
  (10467, 13, 6, 5, 'And Abishua begat Bukki, and Bukki begat Uzzi,', '1~050~ 2~03205~ 3~01231~, 5~01231~ 6~03205~ 7~05813~,'),
  (15952, 19, 119, 45, 'And I will walk at liberty: for I seek thy precepts.', '&para; 3~01980~ 5~07342~: 8~01875~ 10~06490~.'),
  (20384, 25, 3, 21, 'This I recall to my mind, therefore have I hope.', '&para; 2~07725~ 5~03820~, 9~03176~.'),
  (14924, 19, 68, 15, 'The hill of God is as the hill of Bashan; an high hill as the hill of Bashan.', '&para; 1~02022~ 3~0430~ [4 5] 7~02022~ 9~01316~; 11~01386~ 12~02022~ [13] 15~02022~ 17~01316~.'),
  (21034, 26, 23, 18, 'So she discovered her whoredoms, and discovered her nakedness: then my mind was alienated from her, like as my mind was alienated from her sister.', '2~01540~ 4~08457~, 6~01540~ 8~06172~: 11~05315~ 13~03363~ 19~05315~ 21~05361~ 24~0269~.'),
  (9955, 12, 15, 22, 'And Menahem slept with his fathers; and Pekahiah his son reigned in his stead.', '1~04505~ 2~07901~ 5~01~; 7~06494~ 9~01121~ 10~04427~'),
  (13234, 18, 15, 22, 'He believeth not that he shall return out of darkness, and he is waited for of the sword.', '1~0539~ 6~07725~ 9~02822~, 13~06822~ 17~02719~.'),
  (1030, 1, 35, 14, 'And Jacob set up a pillar in the place where he talked with him, even a pillar of stone: and he poured a drink offering thereon, and he poured oil thereon.', '1~03290~ 3~05324~ 5~04676~ 8~04725~ 11~01696~ [14] 16~04678~ 18~068~: 21~05258~ 24~05262~ 28~03332~ 29~08081~'),
  (10926, 13, 19, 11, 'And the rest of the people he delivered unto the hand of Abishai his brother, and they set themselves in array against the children of Ammon.', '2~03499~ 5~05971~ 7~05414~ 10~03027~ 12~052~ 14~0251~, [18] 20~06186~ 21~07125~ 23~01121~ 25~05983~.'),
  (15037, 19, 73, 8, 'They are corrupt, and speak wickedly concerning oppression: they speak loftily.', '2~04167~, 4~01696~ 5~07451~ [6] 7~06233~: 9~01696~ 10~04791~.'),
  (20677, 26, 11, 13, 'And it came to pass, when I prophesied, that Pelatiah the son of Benaiah died. Then fell I down upon my face, and cried with a loud voice, and said, Ah Lord GOD! wilt thou make a full end of the remnant of Israel?', '7~05012~, 9~06410~ 11~01121~ 13~01141~ 14~04191~. 18~05307~ 21~06440~, 23~02199~ 26~01419~ 27~06963~, 29~0559~, 30~0162~ 31~0136~ 32~03069~! 35~06213~ 38~03617~ 41~07611~ 43~03478~?'),
  (26434, 43, 8, 38, 'I speak that which I have seen with my Father: and ye do that which ye have seen with your father.', '&para; 0~1473~ 1~2980~ 3~3739~ 6~3708~ 7~3844~ 8~3450~ 9~3962~: 10~2532~ 11~5210~ 12~4160~ 13~3767~ 14~3739~ 17~3708~ 18~3844~ 19~5216~ 20~3962~.'),
  (10149, 12, 21, 22, 'And he forsook the LORD God of his fathers, and walked not in the way of the LORD.', '2~05800~ 4~03068~ 5~0430~ 8~01~, 10~01980~ 14~01870~ 17~03068~.'),
  (7279, 9, 2, 32, 'And thou shalt see an enemy in my habitation, in all the wealth which God shall give Israel: and there shall not be an old man in thine house for ever.', '3~05027~ 5~06862~ [6 7] 8~04583~, [11 12] [14] 16~03190~ 17~03478~: 25~02205~ 28~01004~ 30~03117~.'),
  (20918, 26, 20, 14, 'But I wrought for my name''s sake, that it should not be polluted before the heathen, in whose sight I brought them out.', '2~06213~ 5~08034~ 12~02490~ 13~05869~ 15~01471~, 18~05869~ 22~03318~.'),
  (13410, 18, 22, 12, 'Is not God in the height of heaven? and behold the height of the stars, how high they are!', '[0] 2~0433~ 5~01363~ 7~08064~? 9~07200~ 11~07218~ 14~03556~, 16~07311~'),
  (25621, 42, 15, 20, 'And he arose, and came to his father. But when he was yet a great way off, his father saw him, and had compassion, and ran, and fell on his neck, and kissed him.', '0~2532~ 2~450~, 4~2064~ 5~4314~ 6~1438~ 7~3962~. 8~1161~ 10~846~ 12~2089~ 15~3112~ 16~568~, 17~846~ 18~3962~ 19~1492~ 20~846~, 21~2532~ 23~4697~, 24~2532~ 25~5143~, 27~1968~ 28~1909~ 29~846~ 30~5137~, 31~2532~ 32~2705~ 33~846~.'),
  (10239, 12, 25, 9, 'And he burnt the house of the LORD, and the king''s house, and all the houses of Jerusalem, and every great man''s house burnt he with fire.', '2~08313~ 4~01004~ 7~03068~, 10~04428~ 11~01004~, 15~01004~ 17~03389~, 20~01419~ [21] 22~01004~ 23~08313~ 26~0784~.'),
  (8687, 10, 23, 26, 'Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite,', '0~02503~ 2~06407~, 3~05896~ 5~01121~ 7~06142~ 9~08621~,'),
  (21190, 26, 28, 24, 'And there shall be no more a pricking brier unto the house of Israel, nor any grieving thorn of all that are round about them, that despised them; and they shall know that I am the Lord GOD.', '7~03992~ 8~05544~ 11~01004~ 13~03478~, [15] 16~03510~ 17~06975~ [20 21] 23~05439~ 26~07590~ 31~03045~ [34] 36~0136~ 37~03069~.'),
  (16785, 20, 14, 4, 'Where no oxen are, the crib is clean: but much increase is by the strength of the ox.', '&para; 2~0504~ [3] 5~018~ [6] 7~01249~: 9~07230~ 10~08393~ [11] 14~03581~ 17~07794~.'),
  (19390, 24, 17, 24, 'And it shall come to pass, if ye diligently hearken unto me, saith the LORD, to bring in no burden through the gates of this city on the sabbath day, but hallow the sabbath day, to do no work therein;', '8~08085~ 9~08085~ 12~05002~ 14~03068~, 16~0935~ 19~04853~ 22~08179~ 25~05892~ 28~07676~ 29~03117~, 31~06942~ 33~07676~ 34~03117~, 36~06213~ 37~01115~ 38~04399~'),
  (2360, 2, 29, 19, 'And thou shalt take the other ram; and Aaron and his sons shall put their hands upon the head of the ram.', '3~03947~ 5~08145~ 6~0352~; 8~0175~ 11~01121~ 13~05564~ 15~03027~ 18~07218~ 21~0352~.'),
  (10650, 13, 9, 27, 'And they lodged round about the house of God, because the charge was upon them, and the opening thereof every morning pertained to them.', '2~03885~ 4~05439~ 6~01004~ 8~0430~, 11~04931~ [12] 17~04668~ 20~01242~ [21]'),
  (17, 1, 1, 17, 'And God set them in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth,', '1~0430~ 2~05414~ 6~07549~ 9~08064~ 12~0215~ 15~0776~,'),
  (29498, 51, 1, 17, 'And he is before all things, and by him all things consist.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~2076~ 3~4253~ 5~3956~, 6~2532~ 7~1722~ 8~846~ 10~3956~ 11~4921~.'),
  (28333, 45, 15, 14, 'And I myself also am persuaded of you, my brethren, that ye also are full of goodness, filled with all knowledge, able also to admonish one another.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1473~ 2~846~ 3~2532~ 5~3982~ 6~4012~ 7~5216~, 8~3450~ 9~80~, 10~3754~ 11~846~ 12~2532~ 13~2075~ 14~3324~ 16~19~, 17~4137~ 19~3956~ 20~1108~, 21~1410~ 22~2532~ 24~3560~ 26~240~.'),
  (26113, 43, 2, 3, 'And when they wanted wine, the mother of Jesus saith unto him, They have no wine.', '0~2532~ 3~5302~ 4~3631~, 6~3384~ 8~2424~ 9~3004~ 10~4314~ 11~846~, 13~2192~ 14~3756~ 15~3631~.'),
  (12006, 14, 36, 4, 'And the king of Egypt made Eliakim his brother king over Judah and Jerusalem, and turned his name to Jehoiakim. And Necho took Jehoahaz his brother, and carried him to Egypt.', '2~04428~ 4~04714~ 6~0471~ 8~0251~ 9~04427~ 11~03063~ 13~03389~, 15~05437~ 17~08034~ 19~03079~. 21~05224~ 22~03947~ 23~03099~ 25~0251~, 27~0935~ 30~04714~.'),
  (20139, 24, 49, 3, 'Howl, O Heshbon, for Ai is spoiled: cry, ye daughters of Rabbah, gird you with sackcloth; lament, and run to and fro by the hedges; for their king shall go into captivity, and his priests and his princes together.', '0~03213~, 2~02809~, 4~05857~ 6~07703~: 7~06817~, 9~01323~ 11~07237~, 12~02296~ 15~08242~; 16~05594~, 21~07751~ 24~01448~; 27~04428~ 29~03212~ 31~01473~, [32] 34~03548~ 37~08269~ 38~03162~.'),
  (9541, 11, 22, 53, 'For he served Baal, and worshipped him, and provoked to anger the LORD God of Israel, according to all that his father had done.', '2~05647~ 3~01168~, 5~07812~ 10~03707~ 12~03068~ 13~0430~ 15~03478~, 21~01~ 23~06213~.'),
  (26605, 43, 12, 10, 'But the chief priests consulted that they might put Lazarus also to death;', '0~1161~ 3~749~ 4~1011~ 5~2443~ 8~615~ 9~2976~ 10~2532~ 12~615~;'),
  (5531, 5, 23, 25, 'When thou comest into the standing corn of thy neighbour, then thou mayest pluck the ears with thine hand; but thou shalt not move a sickle unto thy neighbour''s standing corn.', '2~0935~ 6~07054~ 9~07453~, 13~06998~ 15~04425~ 18~03027~; 23~05130~ 25~02770~ 28~07453~ 30~07054~.'),
  (4791, 4, 33, 25, 'And they removed from Haradah, and pitched in Makheloth.', '2~05265~ 4~02732~, 6~02583~ 8~04722~.'),
  (24942, 42, 1, 38, 'And Mary said, Behold the handmaid of the Lord; be it unto me according to thy word. And the angel departed from her.', '0~1161~ 1~3137~ 2~2036~, 3~2400~ 5~1399~ 8~2962~; 10~1096~ 12~3427~ 13~2596~ 15~4675~ 16~4487~. 17~2532~ 19~32~ 20~565~ 21~575~ 22~846~.'),
  (6934, 7, 14, 18, 'And the men of the city said unto him on the seventh day before the sun went down, What is sweeter than honey? and what is stronger than a lion? And he said unto them, If ye had not plowed with my heifer, ye had not found out my riddle.', '2~0582~ 5~05892~ 6~0559~ 11~07637~ 12~03117~ 15~02775~ 17~0935~, [19] 20~04966~ 22~01706~? [25] 26~05794~ 29~0738~? 32~0559~ 35~03884~ 39~02790~ 42~05697~, 47~04672~ 49~02420~.'),
  (11065, 13, 25, 11, 'The fourth to Izri, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~07243~ 3~03339~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (22601, 33, 1, 13, 'O thou inhabitant of Lachish, bind the chariot to the swift beast: she is the beginning of the sin to the daughter of Zion: for the transgressions of Israel were found in thee.', '2~03427~ 4~03923~, 5~07573~ 7~04818~ 11~07409~: [13] 15~07225~ 18~02403~ 21~01323~ 23~06726~: 26~06588~ 28~03478~ 30~04672~'),
  (18059, 23, 21, 15, 'For they fled from the swords, from the drawn sword, and from the bent bow, and from the grievousness of war.', '2~05074~ 3~06440~ 5~02719~, 6~06440~ 8~05203~ 9~02719~, 11~06440~ 13~01869~ 14~07198~, 16~06440~ 18~03514~ 20~04421~.'),
  (21169, 26, 28, 3, 'Behold, thou art wiser than Daniel; there is no secret that they can hide from thee:', '[2] 3~02450~ 5~01840~; 9~05640~ 13~06004~'),
  (10968, 13, 21, 26, 'And David built there an altar unto the LORD, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings, and called upon the LORD; and he answered him from heaven by fire upon the altar of burnt offering.', '1~01732~ 2~01129~ 5~04196~ 8~03068~, 10~05927~ 12~05930~ 15~08002~, 17~07121~ 20~03068~; 23~06030~ 26~08064~ 28~0784~ 31~04196~ 34~05930~.'),
  (7953, 9, 28, 4, 'And the Philistines gathered themselves together, and came and pitched in Shunem: and Saul gathered all Israel together, and they pitched in Gilboa.', '2~06430~ 5~06908~, 7~0935~ 9~02583~ 11~07766~: 13~07586~ 14~06908~ 16~03478~ 17~06908~, 20~02583~ 22~01533~.'),
  (2295, 2, 27, 18, 'The length of the court shall be an hundred cubits, and the breadth fifty every where, and the height five cubits of fine twined linen, and their sockets of brass.', '1~0753~ 4~02691~ [5 6] 8~03967~ 9~0520~, 12~07341~ 13~02572~ 15~02572~, 18~06967~ 19~02568~ 20~0520~ [21] 23~07806~ 24~08336~, 27~0134~ [28] 29~05178~.'),
  (13773, 18, 36, 28, 'Which the clouds do drop and distil upon man abundantly.', '2~07834~ 4~05140~ [5] 6~07491~ 8~0120~ 9~07227~.'),
  (25030, 42, 2, 45, 'And when they found him not, they turned back again to Jerusalem, seeking him.', '0~2532~ 3~2147~ 4~846~ 5~3361~, 9~5290~ 10~1519~ 11~2419~, 12~2212~ 13~846~.'),
  (18032, 23, 19, 19, 'In that day shall there be an altar to the LORD in the midst of the land of Egypt, and a pillar at the border thereof to the LORD.', '2~03117~ 7~04196~ 10~03068~ 13~08432~ 16~0776~ 18~04714~, 21~04676~ 22~0681~ 24~01366~ 28~03068~.'),
  (11172, 13, 28, 21, 'And, behold, the courses of the priests and the Levites, even they shall be with thee for all the service of the house of God: and there shall be with thee for all manner of workmanship every willing skilful man, for any manner of service: also the princes and all the people will be wholly at thy commandment.', '3~04256~ 6~03548~ 9~03881~, [10 15] 19~05656~ 22~01004~ 24~0430~: [26 28] 35~04399~ 37~05081~ 39~02451~, 44~05656~: 47~08269~ 51~05971~ [52 53] 57~01697~.'),
  (2853, 3, 5, 18, 'And he shall bring a ram without blemish out of the flock, with thy estimation, for a trespass offering, unto the priest: and the priest shall make an atonement for him concerning his ignorance wherein he erred and wist it not, and it shall be forgiven him.', '3~0935~ 5~0352~ 7~08549~ 11~06629~, 14~06187~, 18~0817~, 21~03548~: 24~03548~ 28~03722~ 33~07684~ 36~07683~ 38~03045~ [39] 45~05545~'),
  (8846, 11, 3, 22, 'And the other woman said, Nay; but the living is my son, and the dead is thy son. And this said, No; but the dead is thy son, and the living is my son. Thus they spake before the king.', '2~0312~ 3~0802~ 4~0559~, 8~02416~ [9] 11~01121~, 14~04191~ [15] 17~01121~. 20~0559~, 24~04191~ [25] 27~01121~, 30~02416~ [31] 33~01121~. 36~01696~ 37~06440~ 39~04428~.'),
  (11255, 14, 4, 1, 'Moreover he made an altar of brass, twenty cubits the length thereof, and twenty cubits the breadth thereof, and ten cubits the height thereof.', '&para; 2~06213~ 4~04196~ 6~05178~, 7~06242~ 8~0520~ 10~0753~ 13~06242~ 14~0520~ 16~07341~ 19~06235~ 20~0520~ 22~06967~'),
  (22157, 28, 4, 15, 'Though thou, Israel, play the harlot, yet let not Judah offend; and come not ye unto Gilgal, neither go ye up to Bethaven, nor swear, The LORD liveth.', '2~03478~, 5~02181~, [6] 9~03063~ 10~0816~; 12~0935~ 16~01537~, 20~05927~ 22~01007~, 24~07650~, 26~03068~ 27~02416~.'),
  (24897, 41, 16, 13, 'And they went and told it unto the residue: neither believed they them.', '1~2548~ 2~565~ 4~518~ [5] 8~3062~: 9~3761~ 11~4100~ 12~1565~.'),
  (4166, 4, 15, 8, 'And when thou preparest a bullock for a burnt offering, or for a sacrifice in performing a vow, or peace offerings unto the LORD:', '3~06213~ 5~01241~ [6] 6~01121~ 9~05930~, [11] 13~02077~ 15~06381~ 17~05088~, 20~08002~ 23~03068~:'),
  (9232, 11, 14, 6, 'And it was so, when Ahijah heard the sound of her feet, as she came in at the door, that he said, Come in, thou wife of Jeroboam; why feignest thou thyself to be another? for I am sent to thee with heavy tidings.', '[3] 5~0281~ 6~08085~ 8~06963~ 11~07272~, 15~0935~ 18~06607~, 21~0559~, 23~0935~, 25~0802~ 27~03379~; [32 33] 34~05234~? [37] 38~07971~ [41] 42~07186~ [43]'),
  (12485, 16, 7, 56, 'The children of Neziah, the children of Hatipha.', '1~01121~ 3~05335~, 5~01121~ 7~02412~.'),
  (7806, 9, 22, 12, 'And Saul said, Hear now, thou son of Ahitub. And he answered, Here I am, my lord.', '1~07586~ 2~0559~, 3~08085~ 6~01121~ 8~0285~. 11~0559~, [14] 16~0113~.'),
  (7900, 9, 25, 32, 'And David said to Abigail, Blessed be the LORD God of Israel, which sent thee this day to meet me:', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~026~, 5~01288~ [6] 8~03068~ 9~0430~ 11~03478~, 13~07971~ 16~03117~ 18~07125~'),
  (24616, 41, 10, 17, 'And when he was gone forth into the way, there came one running, and kneeled to him, and asked him, Good Master, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?', '&para; 0~2532~ 5~1607~ 6~1519~ 8~3598~ 9~846~,* 11~4370~ 12~1520~ 13~4370~, 14~2532~ 15~1120~ 17~846~, 19~1905~ 20~846~, 21~18~ 22~1320~, 23~5101~ 26~4160~ 27~2443~ 30~2816~ 31~166~ 32~2222~?'),
  (16585, 20, 7, 1, 'My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.', '&para; 1~01121~, 2~08104~ 4~0561~, 7~06845~ 9~04687~'),
  (28884, 47, 4, 9, 'Persecuted, but not forsaken; cast down, but not destroyed;', '0~1377~, 1~235~ 2~3756~ 3~1459~; 5~2598~, 6~235~ 7~3756~ 8~622~;'),
  (25291, 42, 8, 34, 'When they that fed them saw what was done, they fled, and went and told it in the city and in the country.', '0~1161~ 3~1006~ [4] 5~1492~ 8~1096~, 10~5343~, 11~2532~ 12~565~ 14~518~ [15] 16~1519~ 18~4172~ 19~2532~ 20~1519~ 22~68~.'),
  (4592, 4, 28, 9, 'And on the sabbath day two lambs of the first year without spot, and two tenth deals of flour for a meat offering, mingled with oil, and the drink offering thereof:', '&para; 3~07676~ 4~03117~ 5~08147~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~ 12~08549~, 14~08147~ 15~06241~ 18~05560~ [19] 22~04503~, 23~01101~ 25~08081~, 29~05262~'),
  (10059, 12, 18, 27, 'But Rabshakeh said unto them, Hath my master sent me to thy master, and to thee, to speak these words? hath he not sent me to the men which sit on the wall, that they may eat their own dung, and drink their own piss with you?', '1~07262~ 2~0559~ 7~0113~ 8~07971~ 12~0113~, 17~01696~ 19~01697~? [20 21] [23 24] 27~0582~ 29~03427~ 32~02346~, 36~0398~ 39~06675~ 40~02755~,* 42~08354~ 45~07272~ 46~04325~* 47~07890~*'),
  (19952, 24, 40, 2, 'And the captain of the guard took Jeremiah, and said unto him, The LORD thy God hath pronounced this evil upon this place.', '2~07227~ 5~02876~ 6~03947~ 7~03414~, 9~0559~ 13~03068~ 15~0430~ 17~01696~ 19~07451~ 22~04725~.'),
  (29321, 49, 5, 1, 'Be ye therefore followers of God, as dear children;', '&para; 0~1096~ 1~3402~ 2~3767~ 3~3402~ 5~2316~, 6~5613~ 7~27~ 8~5043~;'),
  (21442, 26, 38, 8, 'After many days thou shalt be visited: in the latter years thou shalt come into the land that is brought back from the sword, and is gathered out of many people, against the mountains of Israel, which have been always waste: but it is brought forth out of the nations, and they shall dwell safely all of them.', '1~07227~ 2~03117~ 6~06485~: 9~0319~ 10~08141~ 13~0935~ 16~0776~ [17 18] 20~07725~ 23~02719~, [24 25] 26~06908~ 29~07227~ 30~05971~, 33~02022~ 35~03478~, 39~08548~ 40~02723~: 45~03318~ 49~05971~, 53~03427~ 54~0983~'),
  (26757, 43, 16, 16, 'A little while, and ye shall not see me: and again, a little while, and ye shall see me, because I go to the Father.', '&para; 2~3397~, 3~2532~ 5~2334~ 6~3756~ 7~2334~ 8~3165~: 9~2532~ 10~3825~, 13~3397~, 14~2532~ 17~3700~ 18~3165~, 19~3754~ 20~1473~ 21~5217~ 22~4314~ 24~3962~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (15815, 19, 112, 3, 'Wealth and riches shall be in his house: and his righteousness endureth for ever.', '0~01952~ 2~06239~ [3 4] 7~01004~: 10~06666~ 11~05975~ 13~05703~.'),
  (24109, 40, 26, 45, 'Then cometh he to his disciples, and saith unto them, Sleep on now, and take your rest: behold, the hour is at hand, and the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.', '0~5119~ 2~2064~ 3~4314~ 4~846~ 5~3101~, 6~2532~ 7~3004~ 9~846~, 11~2518~ 12~3063~, 13~2532~ [15] 16~373~: 17~2400~, 19~5610~ 22~1448~, 23~2532~ 25~5207~ 27~444~ 29~3860~ 30~1519~ 32~5495~ 34~268~.'),
  (24023, 40, 25, 5, 'While the bridegroom tarried, they all slumbered and slept.', '0~1161~ 2~3566~ 3~5549~, 5~3956~ 6~3573~ 7~2532~ 8~2518~.'),
  (29096, 48, 1, 23, 'But they had heard only, That he which persecuted us in times past now preacheth the faith which once he destroyed.', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 3~191~ 4~3440~, 5~3754~ 8~1377~ 9~2248~ 12~4218~ 13~3568~ 14~2097~ 16~4102~ 17~3739~ 18~4218~ 20~4199~.'),
  (9032, 11, 8, 39, 'Then hear thou in heaven thy dwelling place, and forgive, and do, and give to every man according to his ways, whose heart thou knowest; (for thou, even thou only, knowest the hearts of all the children of men;)', '1~08085~ 4~08064~ 6~03427~ 7~04349~, 9~05545~, 11~06213~, 13~05414~ 16~0376~ 20~01870~, 22~03824~ 24~03045~; [27] 30~03045~ 32~03824~ 36~01121~ 38~0120~;)'),
  (20214, 24, 50, 39, 'Therefore the wild beasts of the desert with the wild beasts of the islands shall dwell there, and the owls shall dwell therein: and it shall be no more inhabited for ever; neither shall it be dwelt in from generation to generation.', '6~06728~ 13~0338~ 15~03427~ [16] 19~03284~ 20~01323~ 21~03427~ 29~03427~ 31~05331~; 36~07931~ 39~01755~ 41~01755~.'),
  (1571, 2, 2, 12, 'And he looked this way and that way, and when he saw that there was no man, he slew the Egyptian, and hid him in the sand.', '2~06437~ 4~03541~ 7~03541~, 11~07200~ [13 14] 16~0376~, 18~05221~ 20~04713~, 22~02934~ 26~02344~.'),
  (27372, 44, 12, 19, 'And when Herod had sought for him, and found him not, he examined the keepers, and commanded that they should be put to death. And he went down from Judaea to Caesarea, and there abode.', '0~1161~ 1~1934~ 2~2264~ 5~1934~ 6~846~, 7~2532~ 9~2147~ 10~3361~, 12~350~ 14~5441~, 16~2753~ [18] 23~520~. 24~2532~ 27~2718~ 28~575~ 29~2449~ 30~1519~ 31~2542~, [33] 34~1304~.'),
  (922, 1, 31, 45, 'And Jacob took a stone, and set it up for a pillar.', '1~03290~ 2~03947~ 4~068~, 8~07311~ [9] 11~04676~.'),
  (20764, 26, 15, 1, 'And the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (26134, 43, 2, 24, 'But Jesus did not commit himself unto them, because he knew all men,', '0~1161~ 1~846~ 2~2424~* 3~4100~ 4~3756~ 5~4100~ 6~1438~ 8~846~, 9~1223~ 10~846~ 11~1097~ 12~3956~ [13]'),
  (14331, 19, 30, 3, 'O LORD, thou hast brought up my soul from the grave: thou hast kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.', '1~03068~, 5~05927~ 7~05315~ 10~07585~: 15~02421~, 21~03381~ 24~0953~.'),
  (24259, 41, 1, 34, 'And he healed many that were sick of divers diseases, and cast out many devils; and suffered not the devils to speak, because they knew him.', '0~2532~ 2~2323~ 3~4183~ 5~2192~ 6~2560~ 8~4164~ 9~3554~, 10~2532~ 12~1544~ 13~4183~ 14~1140~; 15~2532~ 16~863~ 17~3756~ 19~1140~ 21~2980~, 22~3754~ 24~1492~ 25~846~.'),
  (10442, 13, 5, 6, 'Beerah his son, whom Tilgathpilneser king of Assyria carried away captive: he was prince of the Reubenites.', '0~0880~ 2~01121~, 4~08407~ 5~04428~ 7~0804~ 9~01540~ [10] [12] 13~05387~ 16~07206~.'),
  (23739, 40, 18, 2, 'And Jesus called a little child unto him, and set him in the midst of them,', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~4341~ 5~3813~ 7~4341~, 9~2476~ 10~846~ 11~1722~ 13~3319~ 15~846~,'),
  (20737, 26, 13, 20, 'Wherefore thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I am against your pillows, wherewith ye there hunt the souls to make them fly, and I will tear them from your arms, and will let the souls go, even the souls that ye hunt to make them fly.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; [8] 11~03704~, 13~0859~ 15~06679~ 17~05315~ [20] 21~06524~, 25~07167~ 29~02220~, 34~05315~ 35~07971~, [36] 38~05315~ 41~06679~ [44] 45~06524~.'),
  (1876, 2, 13, 4, 'This day came ye out in the month Abib.', '1~03117~ 4~03318~ 7~02320~ 8~024~.'),
  (28010, 45, 3, 3, 'For what if some did not believe? shall their unbelief make the faith of God without effect?', '0~1063~ 1~5101~ 2~1487~ 3~5100~ 6~569~ 7~3361~?* 8~2673~ 9~846~ 10~570~ 11~2673~ 13~4102~ 15~2316~ 17~2673~?'),
  (6983, 7, 16, 27, 'Now the house was full of men and women; and all the lords of the Philistines were there; and there were upon the roof about three thousand men and women, that beheld while Samson made sport.', '2~01004~ 4~04390~ 6~0582~ 8~0802~; 12~05633~ 15~06430~ [16] [19 20] 23~01406~ 25~07969~ 26~0505~ 27~0376~ 29~0802~, 31~07200~ 33~08123~ 35~07832~.'),
  (27155, 44, 7, 23, 'And when he was full forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brethren the children of Israel.', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 2~846~ 4~4137~ 6~5063~ 7~5550~, 9~305~ 10~1909~ 11~846~ 12~2588~ 14~1980~ 15~846~ 16~80~ 18~5207~ 20~2474~.'),
  (22288, 28, 13, 13, 'The sorrows of a travailing woman shall come upon him: he is an unwise son; for he should not stay long in the place of the breaking forth of children.', '1~02256~ 5~03205~ 7~0935~ [11] 13~02450~ 14~01121~; 19~05975~ 20~06256~ [22 24] 27~04866~ 29~01121~.'),
  (17367, 21, 2, 25, 'For who can eat, or who else can hasten hereunto, more than I?', '3~0398~, 8~02363~ [9] 10~02351~'),
  (6375, 6, 19, 47, 'And the coast of the children of Dan went out too little for them: therefore the children of Dan went up to fight against Leshem, and took it, and smote it with the edge of the sword, and possessed it, and dwelt therein, and called Leshem, Dan, after the name of Dan their father.', '2~01366~ 5~01121~ 7~01835~ 9~03318~ [10 11] 16~01121~ 18~01835~ 20~05927~ 22~03898~ 24~03959~, 26~03920~ 29~05221~ 33~06310~ 36~02719~, 38~03423~ 41~03427~ 44~07121~ 45~03959~, 46~01835~, 49~08034~ 51~01835~ 53~01~.'),
  (820, 1, 29, 21, 'And Jacob said unto Laban, Give me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that I may go in unto her.', '1~03290~ 2~0559~ 4~03837~, 5~03051~ [6] 8~0802~, 11~03117~ 13~04390~, 18~0935~'),
  (22872, 37, 2, 8, 'The silver is mine, and the gold is mine, saith the LORD of hosts.', '1~03701~ [2] 6~02091~ [7] 9~05002~ 11~03068~ 13~06635~.'),
  (17917, 23, 13, 2, 'Lift ye up a banner upon the high mountain, exalt the voice unto them, shake the hand, that they may go into the gates of the nobles.', '2~05375~ 4~05251~ 7~08192~ 8~02022~, 9~07311~ 11~06963~ 14~05130~ 16~03027~, 20~0935~ 23~06607~ 26~05081~.'),
  (11245, 14, 3, 8, 'And he made the most holy house, the length whereof was according to the breadth of the house, twenty cubits, and the breadth thereof twenty cubits: and he overlaid it with fine gold, amounting to six hundred talents.', '2~06213~ 4~06944~ 5~06944~ 6~01004~, 8~0753~ [10] 12~06440~ 14~07341~ 17~01004~, 18~06242~ 19~0520~, 22~07341~ 24~06242~ 25~0520~: 28~02645~ 31~02896~ 32~02091~, [33] 35~08337~ 36~03967~ 37~03603~.'),
  (8274, 10, 11, 8, 'And David said to Uriah, Go down to thy house, and wash thy feet. And Uriah departed out of the king''s house, and there followed him a mess of meat from the king.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~0223~, 6~03381~ 9~01004~, 11~07364~ 13~07272~. 15~0223~ 17~03318~ 20~04428~ 21~01004~, 24~0310~ 27~04864~ [28 29] 32~04428~.'),
  (23837, 40, 21, 1, 'And when they drew nigh unto Jerusalem, and were come to Bethphage, unto the mount of Olives, then sent Jesus two disciples,', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3753~ 4~1448~ 5~1519~ 6~2414~, 7~2532~ 9~2064~ 10~1519~ 11~967~, 12~4314~ 14~3735~ 16~1636~, 17~5119~ 18~649~ 19~2424~ 20~1417~ 21~3101~,'),
  (25625, 42, 15, 24, 'For this my son was dead, and is alive again; he was lost, and is found. And they began to be merry.', '0~3754~ 1~3778~ 2~3450~ 3~5207~ 4~2258~ 5~3498~, 6~2532~ 9~326~ 10~2532~;* 12~2258~ 13~622~, 14~2532~ 16~2147~. 17~2532~ 19~756~ 22~2165~.'),
  (12414, 16, 6, 4, 'Yet they sent unto me four times after this sort; and I answered them after the same manner.', '2~07971~ 5~0702~ 6~06471~ 9~01697~; 12~07725~ 17~01697~.'),
  (20806, 26, 16, 35, 'Wherefore, O harlot, hear the word of the LORD:', '&para; 2~02181~, 3~08085~ 5~01697~ 8~03068~:'),
  (9747, 12, 8, 12, 'And Hazael said, Why weepeth my lord? And he answered, Because I know the evil that thou wilt do unto the children of Israel: their strong holds wilt thou set on fire, and their young men wilt thou slay with the sword, and wilt dash their children, and rip up their women with child.', '1~02371~ 2~0559~, 4~01058~ 6~0113~? 9~0559~, 12~03045~ 14~07451~ 18~06213~ 21~01121~ 23~03478~: 26~04013~ 29~07971~ 31~0784~, 35~0970~ 38~02026~ 41~02719~, 44~07376~ 46~05768~, 49~01234~ 53~02030~.'),
  (17862, 23, 10, 3, 'And what will ye do in the day of visitation, and in the desolation which shall come from far? to whom will ye flee for help? and where will ye leave your glory?', '4~06213~ 7~03117~ 9~06486~, 13~07722~ [14] 16~0935~ 18~04801~? 23~05127~ 25~05833~? 30~05800~ 32~03519~?'),
  (7980, 9, 29, 6, 'Then Achish called David, and said unto him, Surely, as the LORD liveth, thou hast been upright, and thy going out and thy coming in with me in the host is good in my sight: for I have not found evil in thee since the day of thy coming unto me unto this day: nevertheless the lords favour thee not.', '&para; 1~0397~ 2~07121~ 3~01732~, 5~0559~ [9] 11~03068~ 12~02416~, 16~03477~, 20~03318~ 24~0935~ 29~04264~ [30] 31~02896~ 34~05869~: 39~04672~ 40~07451~ 45~03117~ 48~0935~ 53~03117~: 56~05633~ 57~02896~ 59~05869~.'),
  (19336, 24, 15, 12, 'Shall iron break the northern iron and the steel?', '1~01270~ 2~07489~ 4~06828~ 5~01270~ 8~05178~?'),
  (24862, 41, 15, 25, 'And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 4~5154~ 5~5610~, 6~2532~ 8~4717~ 9~846~.'),
  (6019, 6, 8, 11, 'And all the people, even the people of war that were with him, went up, and drew nigh, and came before the city, and pitched on the north side of Ai: now there was a valley between them and Ai.', '3~05971~, [4 6] 8~04421~ [10] 14~05927~, 17~05066~, 19~0935~ 22~05892~, 24~02583~ 28~06828~ 30~05857~: [32 33] 35~01516~ 39~05857~.'),
  (235, 1, 9, 29, 'And all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years: and he died.', '3~03117~ 5~05146~ 7~08672~ 8~08141~ 9~03967~ 10~02572~ 11~08141~: 14~04191~.'),
  (2147, 2, 22, 29, 'Thou shalt not delay to offer the first of thy ripe fruits, and of thy liquors: the firstborn of thy sons shalt thou give unto me.', '3~0309~ [4 5] 11~04395~, 15~01831~: 17~01060~ 20~01121~ 23~05414~'),
  (24302, 41, 3, 4, 'And he saith unto them, Is it lawful to do good on the sabbath days, or to do evil? to save life, or to kill? But they held their peace.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 7~1832~ 10~15~ 14~4521~, 15~2228~ 18~2554~? 20~4982~ 21~5590~, 22~2228~ 24~615~? 25~1161~ 29~4623~.'),
  (20631, 26, 8, 18, 'Therefore will I also deal in fury: mine eye shall not spare, neither will I have pity: and though they cry in mine ears with a loud voice, yet will I not hear them.', '4~06213~ 6~02534~: 8~05869~ 11~02347~, 16~02550~: 20~07121~ 23~0241~ 26~01419~ 27~06963~, [28] 32~08085~'),
  (15340, 19, 89, 5, 'And the heavens shall praise thy wonders, O LORD: thy faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints.', '&para; 2~08064~ 4~03034~ 6~06382~, 8~03068~: 10~0530~ 14~06951~ 17~06918~.'),
  (24865, 41, 15, 28, 'And the scripture was fulfilled, which saith, And he was numbered with the transgressors.', '0~2532~ 2~1124~ 4~4137~, 5~3588~ 6~3004~, 7~2532~ 10~3049~ 11~3326~ 13~459~.'),
  (9490, 11, 22, 2, 'And it came to pass in the third year, that Jehoshaphat the king of Judah came down to the king of Israel.', '7~07992~ 8~08141~, 10~03092~ 12~04428~ 14~03063~ 16~03381~ 19~04428~ 21~03478~.'),
  (203, 1, 8, 19, 'Every beast, every creeping thing, and every fowl, and whatsoever creepeth upon the earth, after their kinds, went forth out of the ark.', '1~02416~, 4~07431~, 7~05775~, [8] 9~03605~ 10~07430~ 13~0776~, 16~04940~, 18~03318~ 22~08392~.'),
  (22519, 30, 9, 15, 'And I will plant them upon their land, and they shall no more be pulled up out of their land which I have given them, saith the LORD thy God.', '3~05193~ 7~0127~, 15~05428~ 19~0127~ 23~05414~ 25~0559~ 27~03068~ 29~0430~.'),
  (16239, 19, 137, 8, 'O daughter of Babylon, who art to be destroyed; happy shall he be, that rewardeth thee as thou hast served us.', '1~01323~ 3~0894~, 8~07703~; 9~0835~ [10 12] 14~07999~ 19~01580~ 20~01576~*'),
  (20576, 26, 6, 4, 'And your altars shall be desolate, and your images shall be broken: and I will cast down your slain men before your idols.', '2~04196~ 5~08074~, 8~02553~ 11~07665~: 16~05307~ 18~02491~ [19] 20~06440~ 22~01544~.'),
  (24613, 41, 10, 14, 'But when Jesus saw it, he was much displeased, and said unto them, Suffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of God.', '0~1161~ 2~2424~ 3~1492~ [4] 8~23~, 9~2532~ 10~2036~ 12~846~, 13~863~ 16~3813~ 18~2064~ 19~4314~ 20~3165~, 21~2532~ 22~2967~ 23~846~ 24~3361~: 25~1063~ 27~5108~ 28~2076~ 30~932~ 32~2316~.'),
  (3413, 3, 23, 6, 'And on the fifteenth day of the same month is the feast of unleavened bread unto the LORD: seven days ye must eat unleavened bread.', '3~06240~ 4~02568~* 5~03117~ 9~02320~ [10] 12~02282~ 15~04682~ 18~03068~: 19~07651~ 20~03117~ 23~0398~ 25~04682~.'),
  (3621, 4, 1, 12, 'Of Dan; Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.', '1~01835~; 2~0295~ 4~01121~ 6~05996~.'),
  (14859, 19, 63, 11, 'But the king shall rejoice in God; every one that sweareth by him shall glory: but the mouth of them that speak lies shall be stopped.', '2~04428~ 4~08055~ 6~0430~; 10~07650~ 14~01984~: 17~06310~ 21~01696~ 22~08267~ 25~05534~.'),
  (19858, 24, 36, 7, 'It may be they will present their supplication before the LORD, and will return every one from his evil way: for great is the anger and the fury that the LORD hath pronounced against this people.', '5~05307~ 7~08467~ 8~06440~ 10~03068~, 13~07725~ 15~0376~ 18~07451~ 19~01870~: 21~01419~ [22] 24~0639~ 27~02534~ 30~03068~ 32~01696~ 35~05971~.'),
  (23414, 40, 9, 25, 'But when the people were put forth, he went in, and took her by the hand, and the maid arose.', '0~1161~ 1~3753~ 3~3793~ 6~1544~, 9~1525~, 11~2902~ 12~846~ 15~5495~, 16~2532~ 18~2877~ 19~1453~.'),
  (19798, 24, 33, 14, 'Behold, the days come, saith the LORD, that I will perform that good thing which I have promised unto the house of Israel and to the house of Judah.', '2~03117~ 3~0935~, 4~05002~ 6~03068~, 10~06965~ 12~02896~ 13~01697~ 17~01696~ 20~01004~ 22~03478~ 26~01004~ 28~03063~.'),
  (20322, 25, 1, 3, 'Judah is gone into captivity because of affliction, and because of great servitude: she dwelleth among the heathen, she findeth no rest: all her persecutors overtook her between the straits.', '0~03063~ 4~01540~ 7~06040~, 11~07230~ 12~05656~: 14~03427~ 17~01471~, 19~04672~ 21~04494~: 24~07291~ 25~05381~ 29~04712~.'),
  (6027, 6, 8, 19, 'And the ambush arose quickly out of their place, and they ran as soon as he had stretched out his hand: and they entered into the city, and took it, and hasted and set the city on fire.', '2~0693~ 3~06965~ 4~04120~ 8~04725~, 11~07323~ 18~05186~ 20~03027~: 23~0935~ 26~05892~, 28~03920~ 31~04116~ 33~03341~ 35~05892~ 37~0784~.'),
  (29903, 55, 4, 17, 'Notwithstanding the Lord stood with me, and strengthened me; that by me the preaching might be fully known, and that all the Gentiles might hear: and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.', '0~1161~ 2~2962~ 3~3936~ 5~3427~, 6~2532~ 7~1743~ 8~3165~; 9~2443~ 10~1223~ 11~1700~ 13~2782~ 17~4135~, 18~2532~ [19] 20~3956~ 22~1484~ 24~191~: 25~2532~ 28~4506~ 30~1537~ 32~4750~ 35~3023~.'),
  (13873, 18, 39, 30, 'Her young ones also suck up blood: and where the slain are, there is she.', '2~0667~ 5~05966~ 6~01818~: 10~02491~ [11] [13] 14~01931~.'),
  (10463, 13, 6, 1, 'The sons of Levi; Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.', '&para; 1~01121~ 3~03878~; 4~01648~, 5~06955~, 7~04847~.'),
  (7519, 9, 14, 4, 'And between the passages, by which Jonathan sought to go over unto the Philistines'' garrison, there was a sharp rock on the one side, and a sharp rock on the other side: and the name of the one was Bozez, and the name of the other Seneh.', '3~04569~, 6~03129~ 7~01245~ 10~05674~ 13~06430~ 14~04673~, [15 16] 18~08127~ 19~05553~ 23~05676~, 26~08127~ 27~05553~ 31~05676~: 34~08034~ 37~0259~ [38] 39~0949~, 42~08034~ 45~0259~ 46~05573~.'),
  (14810, 19, 59, 11, 'Slay them not, lest my people forget: scatter them by thy power; and bring them down, O Lord our shield.', '0~02026~ 5~05971~ 6~07911~: 7~05128~ 11~02428~; 15~03381~, 17~0136~ 19~04043~.'),
  (22310, 29, 1, 10, 'The field is wasted, the land mourneth; for the corn is wasted: the new wine is dried up, the oil languisheth.', '1~07704~ 3~07703~, 5~0127~ 6~056~; 9~01715~ 11~07703~: 14~08492~ 17~03001~, 19~03323~ 20~0535~.'),
  (30039, 58, 4, 9, 'There remaineth therefore a rest to the people of God.', '1~620~ 2~686~ 4~4520~ 7~2992~ 9~2316~.'),
  (11704, 14, 24, 18, 'And they left the house of the LORD God of their fathers, and served groves and idols: and wrath came upon Judah and Jerusalem for this their trespass.', '2~05800~ 4~01004~ 7~03068~ 8~0430~ 11~01~, 13~05647~ 14~0842~ 16~06091~: 18~07110~ 21~03063~ 23~03389~ 27~0819~.'),
  (1934, 2, 15, 9, 'The enemy said, I will pursue, I will overtake, I will divide the spoil; my lust shall be satisfied upon them; I will draw my sword, my hand shall destroy them.', '1~0341~ 2~0559~, 5~07291~, 8~05381~, 11~02505~ 13~07998~; 15~05315~ 18~04390~ 23~07324~ 25~02719~, 27~03027~ 29~03423~'),
  (8502, 10, 18, 16, 'And Joab blew the trumpet, and the people returned from pursuing after Israel: for Joab held back the people.', '1~03097~ 2~08628~ 4~07782~, 7~05971~ 8~07725~ 10~07291~ 11~0310~ 12~03478~: 14~03097~ 16~02820~ 18~05971~.'),
  (14977, 19, 69, 33, 'For the LORD heareth the poor, and despiseth not his prisoners.', '2~03068~ 3~08085~ 5~034~, 7~0959~ 10~0615~.'),
  (14327, 19, 29, 10, 'The LORD sitteth upon the flood; yea, the LORD sitteth King for ever.', '1~03068~ 2~03427~ 5~03999~; 8~03068~ 9~03427~ 10~04428~ 12~05769~.'),
  (6120, 6, 11, 7, 'So Joshua came, and all the people of war with him, against them by the waters of Merom suddenly; and they fell upon them.', '1~03091~ 2~0935~, 6~05971~ 8~04421~ 15~04325~ 17~04792~ 18~06597~; 22~05307~'),
  (10670, 13, 10, 3, 'And the battle went sore against Saul, and the archers hit him, and he was wounded of the archers.', '2~04421~ 4~03513~ 6~07586~, 9~03384~ 10~07198~* 11~04672~ 16~02342~ 19~03384~.'),
  (21703, 26, 47, 15, 'And this shall be the border of the land toward the north side, from the great sea, the way of Hethlon, as men go to Zedad;', '[2 3] 5~01366~ 8~0776~ 11~06828~ 12~06285~, 15~01419~ 16~03220~, 18~01870~ 20~02855~, 23~0935~ 25~06657~;'),
  (214, 1, 9, 8, 'And God spake unto Noah, and to his sons with him, saying,', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~ 4~05146~, 8~01121~ 11~0559~,'),
  (15197, 19, 79, 3, 'Their blood have they shed like water round about Jerusalem; and there was none to bury them.', '1~01818~ 4~08210~ 6~04325~ 8~05439~ 9~03389~; [11 12] 15~06912~ [16]'),
  (12882, 18, 1, 4, 'And his sons went and feasted in their houses, every one his day; and sent and called for their three sisters to eat and to drink with them.', '&para; 2~01121~ 3~01980~ 5~06213~ 6~04960~* [7 8] 9~01004~, 11~0376~ 13~03117~; 15~07971~ 17~07121~ 20~07969~ 21~0269~ 23~0398~ 26~08354~'),
  (28380, 46, 1, 1, 'Paul, called to be an apostle of Jesus Christ through the will of God, and Sosthenes our brother,', '&para; 0~3972~, 1~2822~ [2 3] 5~652~ 7~2424~ 8~5547~ 9~1223~ 11~2307~ 13~2316~, 14~2532~ 15~4988~ [16] 17~80~,'),
  (6202, 6, 14, 8, 'Nevertheless my brethren that went up with me made the heart of the people melt: but I wholly followed the LORD my God.', '2~0251~ 5~05927~ 10~03820~ 13~05971~ 14~04529~: 17~04390~ 18~0310~ 20~03068~ 22~0430~.'),
  (26325, 43, 6, 53, 'Then Jesus said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Except ye eat the flesh of the Son of man, and drink his blood, ye have no life in you.', '0~3767~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~281~, 6~281~, 8~3004~ 10~5213~, 11~3362~ 13~5315~ 15~4561~ 18~5207~ 20~444~, 21~2532~ 22~4095~ 23~846~ 24~129~, 26~2192~ 27~3756~ 28~2222~ 29~1722~ 30~1438~.'),
  (28468, 46, 4, 19, 'But I will come to you shortly, if the Lord will, and will know, not the speech of them which are puffed up, but the power.', '0~1161~ 3~2064~ 4~4314~ 5~5209~ 6~5030~, 7~1437~ 9~2962~ 10~2309~, 11~2532~ 13~1097~, 14~3756~ 16~3056~ 22~5448~, 23~235~ 25~1411~.'),
  (8326, 10, 13, 2, 'And Amnon was so vexed, that he fell sick for his sister Tamar; for she was a virgin; and Amnon thought it hard for him to do any thing to her.', '1~0550~ 4~03334~, 8~02470~ 11~0269~ 12~08559~; [15] 17~01330~; 19~0550~ 20~05869~ 22~06381~ 26~06213~ 28~03972~'),
  (25129, 42, 5, 10, 'And so was also James, and John, the sons of Zebedee, which were partners with Simon. And Jesus said unto Simon, Fear not; from henceforth thou shalt catch men.', '0~1161~ 1~3668~ [2] 3~2532~ 4~2385~, 5~2532~ 6~2491~, 8~5207~ 10~2199~, 11~3739~ 12~2258~ 13~2844~ 15~4613~. 16~2532~ 17~2424~ 18~2036~ 19~4314~ 20~4613~, 21~5399~ 22~3361~; 23~575~ 24~3568~ 26~2071~ 27~2221~ 28~444~.'),
  (5804, 5, 32, 40, 'For I lift up my hand to heaven, and say, I live for ever.', '3~05375~ 5~03027~ 7~08064~, 9~0559~, 11~02416~ 13~05769~.'),
  (4149, 4, 14, 36, 'And the men, which Moses sent to search the land, who returned, and made all the congregation to murmur against him, by bringing up a slander upon the land,', '&para; 2~0582~, 4~04872~ 5~07971~ 7~08446~ 9~0776~, 11~07725~, 16~05712~ 18~03885~ 23~03318~ 25~01681~ 28~0776~,'),
  (13701, 18, 34, 9, 'For he hath said, It profiteth a man nothing that he should delight himself with God.', '3~0559~, 5~05532~ 7~01397~ 12~07521~ 15~0430~.'),
  (10298, 13, 1, 38, 'And the sons of Seir; Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah, and Dishon, and Ezar, and Dishan.', '2~01121~ 4~08165~; 5~03877~, 7~07732~, 9~06649~, 11~06034~, 13~01787~, 15~0687~, 17~01789~.'),
  (18958, 24, 1, 3, 'It came also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah, unto the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah the son of Josiah king of Judah, unto the carrying away of Jerusalem captive in the fifth month.', '5~03117~ 7~03079~ 9~01121~ 11~02977~ 12~04428~ 14~03063~, 17~08552~ 20~06240~ 21~06249~* 22~08141~ 24~06667~ 26~01121~ 28~02977~ 29~04428~ 31~03063~, 35~01540~ 37~03389~ 38~01540~ 41~02549~ 42~02320~.'),
  (12946, 18, 4, 7, 'Remember, I pray thee, who ever perished, being innocent? or where were the righteous cut off?', '&para; 0~02142~, [5] 6~06~, 8~05355~? 10~0375~ 13~03477~ 15~03582~?'),
  (26875, 43, 19, 35, 'And he that saw it bare record, and his record is true: and he knoweth that he saith true, that ye might believe.', '0~2532~ 3~3708~ [4] 6~3140~, 7~2532~ 8~846~ 9~3141~ 10~2076~ 11~228~: 13~2548~ 14~1492~ 15~3754~ 17~3004~ 18~227~, 19~2443~ 20~5210~ 22~4100~.'),
  (4152, 4, 14, 39, 'And Moses told these sayings unto all the children of Israel: and the people mourned greatly.', '1~04872~ 2~01696~ 4~01697~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~: 13~05971~ 14~056~ 15~03966~.'),
  (13007, 18, 6, 20, 'They were confounded because they had hoped; they came thither, and were ashamed.', '2~0954~ 6~0982~; 8~0935~ 12~02659~.'),
  (3605, 3, 27, 30, 'And all the tithe of the land, whether of the seed of the land, or of the fruit of the tree, is the LORD''S: it is holy unto the LORD.', '3~04643~ 6~0776~, [7] 10~02233~ 13~0776~, [14] 17~06529~ 20~06086~, [21] 23~03068~: [24 25] 26~06944~ 29~03068~.'),
  (7915, 9, 26, 3, 'And Saul pitched in the hill of Hachilah, which is before Jeshimon, by the way. But David abode in the wilderness, and he saw that Saul came after him into the wilderness.', '1~07586~ 2~02583~ 5~01389~ 7~02444~, [9] 10~06440~ 11~03452~, 14~01870~. 16~01732~ 17~03427~ 20~04057~, 23~07200~ 25~07586~ 26~0935~ 27~0310~ 31~04057~.'),
  (1222, 1, 41, 22, 'And I saw in my dream, and, behold, seven ears came up in one stalk, full and good:', '2~07200~ 5~02472~, 8~07651~ 9~07641~ 11~05927~ 13~0259~ 14~07070~, 15~04392~ 17~02896~:'),
  (27494, 44, 15, 36, 'And some days after Paul said unto Barnabas, Let us go again and visit our brethren in every city where we have preached the word of the Lord, and see how they do.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~5100~ 2~2250~ 3~3326~ 4~3972~ 5~2036~ 6~4314~ 7~921~ 8~1211~,* 12~1994~ 14~1980~ 15~2257~ 16~80~ 17~2596~ 18~3956~ 19~4172~ 20~3739~ 21~1722~ 23~2605~ 25~3056~ 28~2962~, [29 30] 31~4459~ 33~2192~.'),
  (22596, 33, 1, 8, 'Therefore I will wail and howl, I will go stripped and naked: I will make a wailing like the dragons, and mourning as the owls.', '&para; 3~05594~ 5~03213~, 8~03212~ 9~07758~ 10~07758~* 12~06174~: 15~06213~ 17~04553~ 20~08577~, 22~060~ 25~03284~ 26~01323~.*'),
  (23232, 40, 4, 13, 'And leaving Nazareth, he came and dwelt in Capernaum, which is upon the sea coast, in the borders of Zabulon and Nephthalim:', '0~2532~ 1~2641~ 2~3478~, 4~2064~ 6~2730~ 7~1519~ 8~2584~, 9~3588~ 14~3864~, 15~1722~ 17~3725~ 19~2194~ 20~2532~ 21~3508~:'),
  (7639, 9, 17, 14, 'And David was the youngest: and the three eldest followed Saul.', '1~01732~ [2] 4~06996~: 7~07969~ 8~01419~ 9~01980~ 10~0310~* 11~07586~.'),
  (1720, 2, 8, 5, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, Say unto Aaron, Stretch forth thine hand with thy rod over the streams, over the rivers, and over the ponds, and cause frogs to come up upon the land of Egypt.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~ 8~0175~, 10~05186~ 12~03027~ 15~04294~ 18~05104~, 21~02975~, 25~098~, 28~06854~ 31~05927~ 34~0776~ 36~04714~.'),
  (24915, 42, 1, 11, 'And there appeared unto him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar of incense.', '0~1161~ 2~3700~ 4~846~ 6~32~ 9~2962~ 10~2476~ 11~1537~ 14~1188~ 17~2379~ 19~2368~.');
