  (12784, 17, 4, 13, 'Then Mordecai commanded to answer Esther, Think not with thyself that thou shalt escape in the king''s house, more than all the Jews.', '1~04782~ 2~0559~ 4~07725~ 5~0635~, 6~01819~ 9~05315~ 13~04422~ 16~04428~ 17~01004~, 22~03064~.'),
  (26754, 43, 16, 13, 'Howbeit when he, the Spirit of truth, is come, he will guide you into all truth: for he shall not speak of himself; but whatsoever he shall hear, that shall he speak: and he will shew you things to come.', '0~1161~ 1~3752~ 2~1565~, 4~4151~ 6~225~, 8~2064~, 11~3594~ 12~5209~ 13~1519~ 14~3956~ 15~225~: 16~1063~ 18~2980~ 19~3756~ 20~2980~ 21~575~ 22~1438~; 23~235~ 24~302~ 25~3745~ 27~191~, [28] 31~2980~: 32~2532~ 35~312~ 36~5213~ 39~2064~.'),
  (22245, 28, 10, 11, 'And Ephraim is as an heifer that is taught, and loveth to tread out the corn; but I passed over upon her fair neck: I will make Ephraim to ride; Judah shall plow, and Jacob shall break his clods.', '1~0669~ [2 3] 5~05697~ [6 7] 8~03925~, [9] 10~0157~ 13~01758~ [14 15] 19~05674~ 22~02898~ 23~06677~: 27~0669~ 29~07392~; 30~03063~ 32~02790~, [33] 34~03290~ 38~07702~.'),
  (20294, 24, 52, 9, 'Then they took the king, and carried him up unto the king of Babylon to Riblah in the land of Hamath; where he gave judgment upon him.', '2~08610~ 4~04428~, 8~05927~ 11~04428~ 13~0894~ 15~07247~ 18~0776~ 20~02574~; 23~01696~ 24~04941~'),
  (27256, 44, 9, 24, 'But their laying await was known of Saul. And they watched the gates day and night to kill him.', '0~1161~ 1~846~ 3~1917~ 5~1097~ 7~4569~. 8~5037~ 10~3906~ 12~4439~ 13~2250~ 14~2532~ 15~3571~ 16~3704~ 17~337~ 18~846~.'),
  (2926, 3, 8, 4, 'And Moses did as the LORD commanded him; and the assembly was gathered together unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.', '1~04872~ 2~06213~ 5~03068~ 6~06680~ 10~05712~ 13~06950~ 16~06607~ 19~0168~ 22~04150~.'),
  (12936, 18, 3, 23, 'Why is light given to a man whose way is hid, and whom God hath hedged in?', '[0 3] 6~01397~ 8~01870~ 10~05641~, 13~0433~ 16~05526~?'),
  (24674, 41, 11, 23, 'For verily I say unto you, That whosoever shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea; and shall not doubt in his heart, but shall believe that those things which he saith shall come to pass; he shall have whatsoever he saith.', '0~1063~ 1~281~ 3~3004~ 5~5213~, 6~3754~ 7~302~ 8~3739~ 9~2036~ 11~5129~ 12~3735~, 15~142~, 16~2532~ 19~906~ 20~1519~ 22~2281~; 23~2532~ 24~1252~ 25~3361~ 26~1252~ 27~1722~ 28~846~ 29~2588~, 30~235~ 32~4100~ 33~3754~ 36~3739~ 38~3004~ 42~1096~; 43~846~ 45~2071~ 46~1437~ 47~3739~ 48~2036~.'),
  (13752, 18, 36, 7, 'He withdraweth not his eyes from the righteous: but with kings are they on the throne; yea, he doth establish them for ever, and they are exalted.', '1~01639~ 4~05869~ 7~06662~: 10~04428~ [11 12] 15~03678~; 19~03427~ 22~05331~, 26~01361~.'),
  (20442, 25, 4, 13, 'For the sins of her prophets, and the iniquities of her priests, that have shed the blood of the just in the midst of her,', '&para; 2~02403~ 5~05030~, [6] 8~05771~ 11~03548~, 14~08210~ 16~01818~ 19~06662~ 22~07130~'),
  (26866, 43, 19, 26, 'When Jesus therefore saw his mother, and the disciple standing by, whom he loved, he saith unto his mother, Woman, behold thy son!', '1~2424~ 2~3767~ 3~1492~ 5~3384~, 6~2532~ 8~3101~ 10~3936~, 11~3739~ 13~25~, 15~3004~ 17~846~ 18~3384~, 19~1135~, 20~2400~ 21~4675~ 22~5207~!'),
  (14159, 19, 18, 32, 'It is God that girdeth me with strength, and maketh my way perfect.', '[0 1] 2~0410~ 4~0247~ 7~02428~, 9~05414~ 11~01870~ 12~08549~.'),
  (26758, 43, 16, 17, 'Then said some of his disciples among themselves, What is this that he saith unto us, A little while, and ye shall not see me: and again, a little while, and ye shall see me: and, Because I go to the Father?', '0~3767~ 1~2036~ [2] 3~1537~ 4~846~ 5~3101~ 6~4314~ 7~240~, 8~5101~ 9~2076~ 10~5124~ 11~3739~ 13~3004~ 15~2254~, 18~3397~, 19~2532~ 21~2334~ 22~3756~ 23~2334~ 24~3165~: 25~2532~ 26~3825~, 29~3397~, 30~2532~ 33~3700~ 34~3165~: 35~2532~, 36~3754~ 37~1473~ 38~5217~ 39~4314~ 41~3962~?'),
  (18951, 23, 66, 20, 'And they shall bring all your brethren for an offering unto the LORD out of all nations upon horses, and in chariots, and in litters, and upon mules, and upon swift beasts, to my holy mountain Jerusalem, saith the LORD, as the children of Israel bring an offering in a clean vessel into the house of the LORD.', '3~0935~ 6~0251~ [7] 9~04503~ 12~03068~ 16~01471~ 18~05483~, 21~07393~, 24~06632~, 27~06505~, 31~03753~, 34~06944~ 35~02022~ 36~03389~, 37~0559~ 39~03068~, 42~01121~ 44~03478~ 45~0935~ 47~04503~ 50~02889~ 51~03627~ 54~01004~ 57~03068~.'),
  (24455, 41, 6, 38, 'He saith unto them, How many loaves have ye? go and see. And when they knew, they say, Five, and two fishes.', '0~1161~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 5~4214~ 6~740~ 8~2192~? 9~5217~ 10~2532~ 11~1492~. 12~2532~ 15~1097~, 17~3004~, 18~4002~, 19~2532~ 20~1417~ 21~2486~.'),
  (5576, 5, 26, 4, 'And the priest shall take the basket out of thine hand, and set it down before the altar of the LORD thy God.', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ 6~02935~ 10~03027~, 14~03240~ 15~06440~ 17~04196~ 20~03068~ 22~0430~.'),
  (13726, 18, 34, 34, 'Let men of understanding tell me, and let a wise man hearken unto me.', '1~0582~ 3~03824~ 4~0559~ 9~02450~ 10~01397~ 11~08085~'),
  (28295, 45, 13, 13, 'Let us walk honestly, as in the day; not in rioting and drunkenness, not in chambering and wantonness, not in strife and envying.', '2~4043~ 3~2156~, 4~5613~ 5~1722~ 7~2250~; 8~3361~ 10~2970~ 11~2532~ 12~3178~, 13~3361~ 15~2845~ 16~2532~ 17~766~, 18~3361~ 20~2054~ 21~2532~ 22~2205~.'),
  (21365, 26, 35, 12, 'And thou shalt know that I am the LORD, and that I have heard all thy blasphemies which thou hast spoken against the mountains of Israel, saying, They are laid desolate, they are given us to consume.', '3~03045~ [6] 8~03068~, [9 10] 13~08085~ 16~05007~ 20~0559~ 23~02022~ 25~03478~, 26~0559~, 30~08074~ 33~05414~ 36~0402~.'),
  (25357, 42, 9, 44, 'Let these sayings sink down into your ears: for the Son of man shall be delivered into the hands of men.', '1~5128~ 2~3056~ 4~5087~ 5~1519~ 6~5216~ 7~5210~* 8~3775~: 9~1063~ 11~5207~ 13~444~ 15~3195~ 16~3860~ 17~1519~ 19~5495~ 21~444~.'),
  (9982, 12, 16, 11, 'And Urijah the priest built an altar according to all that king Ahaz had sent from Damascus: so Urijah the priest made it against king Ahaz came from Damascus.', '1~0223~ 3~03548~ 4~01129~ 6~04196~ 11~04428~ 12~0271~ 14~07971~ 16~01834~: 18~0223~ 20~03548~ 21~06213~ [22] 24~04428~ 25~0271~ 26~0935~ 28~01834~.'),
  (17123, 20, 25, 1, 'These are also proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied out.', '&para; [1] 3~04912~ 5~08010~, 8~0582~ 10~02396~ 11~04428~ 13~03063~ 15~06275~.'),
  (7252, 9, 2, 5, 'They that were full have hired out themselves for bread; and they that were hungry ceased: so that the barren hath born seven; and she that hath many children is waxed feeble.', '[0 2] 3~07649~ 6~07936~ 9~03899~; [11 13] 14~07457~ 15~02308~: 19~06135~ 21~03205~ 22~07651~; 27~07227~ 28~01121~ 31~0535~.'),
  (6124, 6, 11, 11, 'And they smote all the souls that were therein with the edge of the sword, utterly destroying them: there was not any left to breathe: and he burnt Hazor with fire.', '2~05221~ 5~05315~ [7] 11~06310~ 14~02719~, 16~02763~ [17] 22~03498~ 24~05397~: 27~08313~ 28~02674~ 30~0784~.'),
  (21006, 26, 22, 21, 'Yea, I will gather you, and blow upon you in the fire of my wrath, and ye shall be melted in the midst thereof.', '3~03664~ 6~05301~ 11~0784~ 14~05678~, 19~05413~ 22~08432~'),
  (8653, 10, 22, 43, 'Then did I beat them as small as the dust of the earth, I did stamp them as the mire of the street, and did spread them abroad.', '3~07833~ 9~06083~ 12~0776~, 15~01854~ 19~02916~ 22~02351~, [23] 27~07554~.'),
  (18626, 23, 48, 3, 'I have declared the former things from the beginning; and they went forth out of my mouth, and I shewed them; I did them suddenly, and they came to pass.', '2~05046~ 5~07223~ 8~0227~; 12~03318~ 16~06310~, 19~08085~ 22~06213~ [23] 24~06597~, 29~0935~.'),
  (18349, 23, 36, 10, 'And am I now come up without the LORD against this land to destroy it? the LORD said unto me, Go up against this land, and destroy it.', '5~05927~ 6~01107~ 8~03068~ 11~0776~ 13~07843~ 16~03068~ 17~0559~ 21~05927~ 24~0776~, 26~07843~'),
  (26572, 43, 11, 34, 'And said, Where have ye laid him? They said unto him, Lord, come and see.', '0~2532~ 1~2036~, 2~4226~ 5~5087~ 6~846~? 8~3004~ 10~846~, 11~2962~, 12~2064~ 13~2532~ 14~1492~.'),
  (25906, 42, 22, 28, 'Ye are they which have continued with me in my temptations.', '0~1161~* 1~5210~ 2~2075~ 6~1265~ 7~3326~ 8~1700~ 9~1722~ 10~3450~ 11~3986~.'),
  (26655, 43, 13, 10, 'Jesus saith to him, He that is washed needeth not save to wash his feet, but is clean every whit: and ye are clean, but not all.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 7~3068~ 8~5532~ 9~2192~ 10~3756~* 11~2228~ 13~3538~ [14] 15~4228~, 16~235~ 17~2076~ 18~2513~ 20~3650~: 21~2532~ 22~5210~ 23~2075~ 24~2513~, 25~235~ 26~3780~ 27~3956~.'),
  (30076, 58, 6, 16, 'For men verily swear by the greater: and an oath for confirmation is to them an end of all strife.', '0~1063~ 1~444~ 2~3303~ 3~3660~ 4~2596~ 6~3187~: 7~2532~ 9~3727~ 10~1519~ 11~951~ [12] 14~846~ 16~4009~ 18~3956~ 19~485~.'),
  (9187, 11, 12, 28, 'Whereupon the king took counsel, and made two calves of gold, and said unto them, It is too much for you to go up to Jerusalem: behold thy gods, O Israel, which brought thee up out of the land of Egypt.', '2~04428~ 4~03289~, 6~06213~ 7~08147~ 8~05695~ [9] 10~02091~, 12~0559~ 18~07227~ 23~05927~ 25~03389~: 28~0430~, 30~03478~, 34~05927~ 38~0776~ 40~04714~.'),
  (1712, 2, 7, 22, 'And the magicians of Egypt did so with their enchantments: and Pharaoh''s heart was hardened, neither did he hearken unto them; as the LORD had said.', '2~02748~ 4~04714~ 5~06213~ 9~03909~: 11~06547~ 12~03820~ 14~02388~, 18~08085~ 23~03068~ 25~01696~.'),
  (12558, 16, 9, 38, 'And because of all this we make a sure covenant, and write it; and our princes, Levites, and priests, seal unto it.', '6~03772~ 8~0548~ [9] 11~03789~ [12] 15~08269~, 16~03881~, [17] 18~03548~, 19~02856~ [20 21]'),
  (1109, 1, 37, 21, 'And Reuben heard it, and he delivered him out of their hands; and said, Let us not kill him.', '1~07205~ 2~08085~ [3] 6~05337~ 11~03027~; 13~0559~, 17~05221~ 18~05315~*'),
  (24463, 41, 6, 46, 'And when he had sent them away, he departed into a mountain to pray.', '0~2532~ 4~657~ 5~846~ 6~657~, 8~565~ 9~1519~ 11~3735~ 13~4336~.'),
  (14027, 19, 8, 6, 'Thou madest him to have dominion over the works of thy hands; thou hast put all things under his feet:', '5~04910~ 8~04639~ 11~03027~; 14~07896~ [16] 19~07272~:'),
  (6874, 7, 11, 38, 'And he said, Go. And he sent her away for two months: and she went with her companions, and bewailed her virginity upon the mountains.', '2~0559~, 3~03212~. 8~07971~ [9] 10~08147~ 11~02320~: 14~03212~ 17~07464~, 19~01058~ 21~01331~ 24~02022~.'),
  (2980, 3, 9, 22, 'And Aaron lifted up his hand toward the people, and blessed them, and came down from offering of the sin offering, and the burnt offering, and peace offerings.', '1~0175~ 3~05375~ 5~03027~ 8~05971~, 10~01288~ 14~03381~ 16~06213~ 20~02403~, 24~05930~, 27~08002~.'),
  (19670, 24, 29, 26, 'The LORD hath made thee priest in the stead of Jehoiada the priest, that ye should be officers in the house of the LORD, for every man that is mad, and maketh himself a prophet, that thou shouldest put him in prison, and in the stocks.', '1~03068~ 3~05414~ 5~03548~ 10~03077~ 12~03548~, 17~06496~ 20~01004~ 23~03068~, 26~0376~ [27 28] 29~07696~, 34~05012~, 38~05414~ 41~04115~, 45~06729~.'),
  (5218, 5, 11, 4, 'And what he did unto the army of Egypt, unto their horses, and to their chariots; how he made the water of the Red sea to overflow them as they pursued after you, and how the LORD hath destroyed them unto this day;', '3~06213~ 6~02428~ 8~04714~, 11~05483~, 15~07393~; 20~04325~ 23~05488~ 24~03220~ 26~06687~ 27~06440~ 30~07291~ 31~0310~ [34] 36~03068~ 38~06~ 42~03117~;'),
  (6742, 7, 8, 16, 'And he took the elders of the city, and thorns of the wilderness and briers, and with them he taught the men of Succoth.', '2~03947~ 4~02205~ 7~05892~, 9~06975~ 12~04057~ 14~01303~, 19~03045~ 21~0582~ 23~05523~.'),
  (14030, 19, 8, 9, 'O LORD our Lord, how excellent is thy name in all the earth!', '1~03068~ 3~0113~, 5~0117~ [6] 8~08034~ 12~0776~!'),
  (2547, 2, 35, 11, 'The tabernacle, his tent, and his covering, his taches, and his boards, his bars, his pillars, and his sockets,', '1~04908~, 3~0168~, 6~04372~, 8~07165~, 11~07175~, 13~01280~, 15~05982~, 18~0134~,'),
  (14594, 19, 44, 14, 'Thou makest us a byword among the heathen, a shaking of the head among the people.', '1~07760~ 4~04912~ 7~01471~, 9~04493~ 12~07218~ 15~03816~.'),
  (29200, 48, 5, 22, 'But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, longsuffering, gentleness, goodness, faith,', '0~1161~ 2~2590~ 5~4151~ 6~2076~ 7~26~, 8~5479~, 9~1515~, 10~3115~, 11~5544~, 12~19~, 13~4102~,'),
  (2329, 2, 28, 31, 'And thou shalt make the robe of the ephod all of blue.', '&para; 3~06213~ 5~04598~ 8~0646~ 9~03632~ [10] 11~08504~.'),
  (23762, 40, 18, 25, 'But forasmuch as he had not to pay, his lord commanded him to be sold, and his wife, and children, and all that he had, and payment to be made.', '2~1161~ 3~846~ 4~2192~ 5~3361~ 7~591~, 8~846~ 9~2962~ 10~2753~ 11~846~ 14~4097~, 15~2532~ 16~846~ 17~1135~, 18~2532~ 19~5043~, 20~2532~ 21~3956~ 22~3745~ 24~2192~, 25~2532~ 29~591~.'),
  (5590, 5, 26, 18, 'And the LORD hath avouched thee this day to be his peculiar people, as he hath promised thee, and that thou shouldest keep all his commandments;', '2~03068~ 4~0559~ 7~03117~ 11~05459~ 12~05971~, 16~01696~ [20] 22~08104~ 25~04687~;'),
  (29053, 47, 12, 15, 'And I will very gladly spend and be spent for you; though the more abundantly I love you, the less I be loved.', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 4~2236~ 5~1159~ 6~2532~ 8~1550~ 9~5228~ 10~5216~ 11~5590~;* 12~1499~ 15~4056~ 17~25~ 18~5209~, 20~2276~ 23~25~.'),
  (30588, 62, 2, 22, 'Who is a liar but he that denieth that Jesus is the Christ? He is antichrist, that denieth the Father and the Son.', '0~5101~ 1~2076~ 3~5583~ 4~1508~ 7~720~ 8~3754~ 9~2424~ 10~2076~ 11~3756~* 13~5547~? 14~3778~ 15~2076~ 16~500~, 18~720~ 20~3962~ 21~2532~ 23~5207~.'),
  (21407, 26, 37, 1, 'The hand of the LORD was upon me, and carried me out in the spirit of the LORD, and set me down in the midst of the valley which was full of bones,', '&para; 1~03027~ 4~03068~ 11~03318~ 14~07307~ 17~03068~, 21~05117~ 24~08432~ 27~01237~ [29] 30~04392~ 32~06106~,'),
  (14316, 19, 28, 8, 'The LORD is their strength, and he is the saving strength of his anointed.', '1~03068~ [2] 4~05797~, [7] 9~03444~ 10~04581~ 13~04899~.'),
  (13160, 18, 12, 23, 'He increaseth the nations, and destroyeth them: he enlargeth the nations, and straiteneth them again.', '1~07679~ 3~01471~, 5~06~ 8~07849~ 10~01471~, 12~05148~ [14]'),
  (21050, 26, 23, 34, 'Thou shalt even drink it and suck it out, and thou shalt break the sherds thereof, and pluck off thine own breasts: for I have spoken it, saith the Lord GOD.', '3~08354~ [7] 8~04680~, 12~01633~ 14~02789~ 18~05423~ 21~07699~: 25~01696~ [26] 27~05002~ 29~0136~ 30~03069~.'),
  (8101, 10, 3, 13, 'And he said, Well; I will make a league with thee: but one thing I require of thee, that is, Thou shalt not see my face, except thou first bring Michal Saul''s daughter, when thou comest to see my face.', '2~0559~, 3~02896~; 6~03772~ 8~01285~ 12~0259~ 13~01697~ 15~07592~ 19~0559~, 23~07200~ 25~06440~, 28~06440~ 29~0935~ 30~04324~ 31~07586~ 32~01323~, 35~0935~ 37~07200~ 39~06440~.'),
  (28572, 46, 9, 16, 'For though I preach the gospel, I have nothing to glory of: for necessity is laid upon me; yea, woe is unto me, if I preach not the gospel!', '0~1063~ 1~1437~ 5~2097~, 6~3427~ 7~2076~ 8~3756~ 11~2745~: 12~1063~ 13~318~ 16~1945~ 17~3427~; 18~1161~, 19~3759~ 20~2076~ 22~3427~, 23~3362~ 25~2097~ 26~3362~ 28~2097~!'),
  (16075, 19, 119, 168, 'I have kept thy precepts and thy testimonies: for all my ways are before thee.', '2~08104~ 4~06490~ 7~05713~: 11~01870~ [12]'),
  (16431, 20, 1, 22, 'How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners delight in their scorning, and fools hate knowledge?', '4~06612~, 7~0157~ 8~06612~? 11~03887~ 12~02530~ 15~03944~, 17~03684~ 18~08130~ 19~01847~?'),
  (14432, 19, 35, 13, 'But as for me, when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth: I humbled my soul with fasting; and my prayer returned into mine own bosom.', '7~02470~, 9~03830~ [10] 11~08242~: 13~06031~ 15~05315~ 17~06685~; 20~08605~ 21~07725~ 25~02436~.'),
  (20904, 26, 19, 14, 'And fire is gone out of a rod of her branches, which hath devoured her fruit, so that she hath no strong rod to be a sceptre to rule. This is a lamentation, and shall be for a lamentation.', '1~0784~ 4~03318~ 7~04294~ 10~0905~, [11] 13~0398~ 15~06529~, 21~05797~ 22~04294~ [23 24] 26~07626~ 28~04910~. [30] 32~07015~, 38~07015~.'),
  (23791, 40, 19, 19, 'Honour thy father and thy mother: and, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.', '0~5091~ 1~4675~ 2~3962~ 3~2532~ [4] 5~3384~: 6~2532~, 9~25~ 10~4675~ 11~4139~ 12~5613~ 13~4572~.'),
  (7754, 9, 20, 17, 'And Jonathan caused David to swear again, because he loved him: for he loved him as he loved his own soul.', '1~03083~ 3~01732~ 5~07650~ 6~03254~, 9~0160~ 13~0157~ 17~0160~ 20~05315~.'),
  (12333, 16, 2, 17, 'Then said I unto them, Ye see the distress that we are in, how Jerusalem lieth waste, and the gates thereof are burned with fire: come, and let us build up the wall of Jerusalem, that we be no more a reproach.', '1~0559~ 6~07200~ 8~07451~ [11] 14~03389~ [15] 16~02720~, 19~08179~ 22~03341~ 24~0784~: 25~03212~, 30~01129~ 32~02346~ 34~03389~, 41~02781~.'),
  (16513, 20, 4, 14, 'Enter not into the path of the wicked, and go not in the way of evil men.', '&para; 0~0935~ 4~0734~ 7~07563~, 9~0833~ 13~01870~ 15~07451~ [16]'),
  (3932, 4, 7, 77, 'And for a sacrifice of peace offerings, two oxen, five rams, five he goats, five lambs of the first year: this was the offering of Pagiel the son of Ocran.', '3~02077~ 6~08002~, 7~08147~ 8~01241~, 9~02568~ 10~0352~, 11~02568~ 13~06260~, 14~02568~ 15~03532~ 18~01121~ 19~08141~: [21] 23~07133~ 25~06295~ 27~01121~ 29~05918~.'),
  (10226, 12, 24, 16, 'And all the men of might, even seven thousand, and craftsmen and smiths a thousand, all that were strong and apt for war, even them the king of Babylon brought captive to Babylon.', '3~0582~ 5~02428~, [6] 7~07651~ 8~0505~, 10~02796~ 12~04525~ 14~0505~, [16 17] 18~01368~ [19] 20~06213~ 22~04421~, 26~04428~ 28~0894~ 29~0935~ 30~01473~ 32~0894~.'),
  (29760, 54, 3, 13, 'For they that have used the office of a deacon well purchase to themselves a good degree, and great boldness in the faith which is in Christ Jesus.', '0~1063~ 9~1247~ 10~2573~ 11~4046~ 13~1438~ 15~2570~ 16~898~, 17~2532~ 18~4183~ 19~3954~ 20~1722~ 22~4102~ 23~3588~ 25~1722~ 26~5547~ 27~2424~.'),
  (23701, 40, 16, 19, 'And I will give unto thee the keys of the kingdom of heaven: and whatsoever thou shalt bind on earth shall be bound in heaven: and whatsoever thou shalt loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.', '0~2532~ 3~1325~ 5~4671~ 7~2807~ 10~932~ 12~3772~: 13~2532~ 14~1437~ 15~3739~ 17~1210~ 18~1909~ 19~1093~ 21~2071~ 22~1210~ 23~1722~ 24~3772~: 25~2532~ 26~1437~ 27~3739~ 29~3089~ 30~1909~ 31~1093~ 33~2071~ 34~3089~ 35~1722~ 36~3772~.'),
  (8019, 9, 31, 3, 'And the battle went sore against Saul, and the archers hit him; and he was sore wounded of the archers.', '2~04421~ 4~03513~ 6~07586~, 9~03384~ 10~07198~* 11~0582~)04672 16~03966~ 17~02342~ 20~03384~ 21~07198~*'),
  (100, 1, 4, 20, 'And Adah bare Jabal: he was the father of such as dwell in tents, and of such as have cattle.', '1~05711~ 2~03205~ 3~02989~: 7~01~ 11~03427~ 13~0168~, [15 18] 19~04735~.'),
  (3063, 3, 13, 6, 'And the priest shall look on him again the seventh day: and, behold, if the plague be somewhat dark, and the plague spread not in the skin, the priest shall pronounce him clean: it is but a scab: and he shall wash his clothes, and be clean.', '2~03548~ 4~07200~ 7~08145~ 9~07637~ 10~03117~: [13] 15~05061~ [16] 18~03544~, [19] 21~05061~ 22~06581~ 26~05785~, 28~03548~ 32~02891~: [34 35] 37~04556~: 41~03526~ 43~0899~, 46~02891~.'),
  (10375, 13, 3, 6, 'Ibhar also, and Elishama, and Eliphelet,', '0~02984~ 3~0476~, 5~0467~,');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (14129, 19, 18, 2, 'The LORD is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer; my God, my strength, in whom I will trust; my buckler, and the horn of my salvation, and my high tower.', '1~03068~ [2] 4~05553~, 7~04686~, 10~06403~; 12~0410~, 14~06697~, 19~02620~; 21~04043~, 24~07161~ 27~03468~, [28] 31~04869~.'),
  (24509, 41, 7, 35, 'And straightway his ears were opened, and the string of his tongue was loosed, and he spake plain.', '0~2532~ 1~2112~ 2~846~ 3~189~ 5~1272~, 6~2532~ 8~1199~ 10~846~ 11~1100~ 13~3089~, 14~2532~ 16~2980~ 17~3723~.'),
  (6946, 7, 15, 10, 'And the men of Judah said, Why are ye come up against us? And they answered, To bind Samson are we come up, to do to him as he hath done to us.', '2~0376~ 4~03063~ 5~0559~, 10~05927~ 15~0559~, 17~0631~ 18~08123~ 22~05927~, 24~06213~ 30~06213~'),
  (24164, 40, 27, 25, 'Then answered all the people, and said, His blood be on us, and on our children.', '0~2532~ 1~611~ 2~3956~ 4~2992~, 6~2036~, 7~846~ 8~129~ [9] 10~1909~ 11~2248~, 12~2532~ 13~1909~ 14~2257~ 15~5043~.'),
  (1637, 2, 4, 31, 'And the people believed: and when they heard that the LORD had visited the children of Israel, and that he had looked upon their affliction, then they bowed their heads and worshipped.', '2~05971~ 3~0539~: 7~08085~ 10~03068~ 12~06485~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~, 21~07200~ 24~06040~, 29~06915~ 31~07812~.'),
  (27037, 44, 3, 25, 'Ye are the children of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made with our fathers, saying unto Abraham, And in thy seed shall all the kindreds of the earth be blessed.', '0~5210~ 1~2075~ 3~5207~ 6~4396~, 7~2532~ 10~1242~ 11~3739~ 12~2316~ 13~1303~ 14~4314~ 15~2257~ 16~3962~, 17~3004~ 18~4314~ 19~11~, 20~2532~ 22~4675~ 23~4690~ 24~1757~ 25~3956~ 27~3965~ 30~1093~ 32~1757~.'),
  (9441, 11, 20, 25, 'And number thee an army, like the army that thou hast lost, horse for horse, and chariot for chariot: and we will fight against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they. And he hearkened unto their voice, and did so.', '1~04487~ 4~02428~, 7~02428~ 11~05307~, 12~05483~ 14~05483~, 16~07393~ 18~07393~: 22~03898~ 23~0854~ 27~04334~, [28] 33~02388~ 38~08085~ 41~06963~, 44~06213~.'),
  (1535, 1, 50, 24, 'And Joseph said unto his brethren, I die: and God will surely visit you, and bring you out of this land unto the land which he sware to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.', '1~03130~ 2~0559~ 5~0251~, 7~04191~: 9~0430~ 11~06485~ 12~06485~ 17~05927~ 20~0776~ 23~0776~ 26~07650~ 28~085~, 30~03327~, 33~03290~.'),
  (3629, 4, 1, 20, 'And the children of Reuben, Israel''s eldest son, by their generations, after their families, by the house of their fathers, according to the number of the names, by their polls, every male from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war;', '2~01121~ 4~07205~, 5~03478~ 7~01060~, 10~08435~, 13~04940~, 16~01004~ 19~01~, 23~04557~ 26~08034~, 29~01538~, 31~02145~ 33~06242~ 34~08141~ 35~01121~ 37~04605~, 44~03318~ 46~06635~;'),
  (18375, 23, 37, 14, 'And Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers, and read it: and Hezekiah went up unto the house of the LORD, and spread it before the LORD.', '1~02396~ 2~03947~ 4~05612~ 7~03027~ 10~04397~, 12~07121~ 15~02396~ 17~05927~ 20~01004~ 23~03068~, 25~06566~ 27~06440~ 29~03068~.'),
  (25267, 42, 8, 10, 'And he said, Unto you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom of God: but to others in parables; that seeing they might not see, and hearing they might not understand.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 4~5213~ 7~1325~ 9~1097~ 11~3466~ 14~932~ 16~2316~: 17~1161~ 19~3062~ 20~1722~ 21~3850~; 22~2443~ 23~991~ 25~991~ 26~3361~ 27~991~, 28~2532~ 29~191~ 31~4920~ 32~3361~ 33~4920~.'),
  (10322, 13, 2, 8, 'And the sons of Ethan; Azariah.', '2~01121~ 4~0387~; 5~05838~.'),
  (28266, 45, 12, 5, 'So we, being many, are one body in Christ, and every one members one of another.', '0~3779~ 1~2070~, [2] 3~4183~, 4~2070~ 5~1520~ 6~4983~ 7~1722~ 8~5547~, 9~1161~ 10~2596~ 11~1520~ 12~3196~ 15~240~.'),
  (7171, 8, 2, 15, 'And when she was risen up to glean, Boaz commanded his young men, saying, Let her glean even among the sheaves, and reproach her not:', '5~06965~ 7~03950~, 8~01162~ 9~06680~ 12~05288~, 13~0559~, 16~03950~ 20~06016~, 22~03637~'),
  (23091, 38, 14, 14, 'And Judah also shall fight at Jerusalem; and the wealth of all the heathen round about shall be gathered together, gold, and silver, and apparel, in great abundance.', '1~03063~ 4~03898~ 6~03389~; 9~02428~ 13~01471~ 15~05439~ 19~0622~, 20~02091~, 22~03701~, 24~0899~, 26~03966~ 27~07230~.'),
  (29040, 47, 12, 2, 'I knew a man in Christ above fourteen years ago, (whether in the body, I cannot tell; or whether out of the body, I cannot tell: God knoweth;) such an one caught up to the third heaven.', '1~1492~ 3~444~ 4~1722~ 5~5547~ 6~4253~ 7~1180~ 8~2094~ 9~4253~, 10~1535~* 12~1722~ 14~4983~, 16~3756~ 17~1492~; 19~1535~ 20~1622~ 23~4983~, 25~3756~ 26~1492~: 27~2316~ 28~1492~;) 31~5108~ 33~726~ 34~2193~ 36~5154~ 37~3772~.'),
  (19236, 24, 11, 1, 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD, saying,', '&para; 1~01697~ 5~03414~ 8~03068~, 9~0559~,'),
  (17512, 21, 10, 10, 'If the iron be blunt, and he do not whet the edge, then must he put to more strength: but wisdom is profitable to direct.', '2~01270~ 4~06949~, 9~07043~ 11~06440~, 15~01396~ 18~02428~: 20~02451~ [21] 22~03504~ 24~03787~.'),
  (23149, 39, 4, 1, 'For, behold, the day cometh, that shall burn as an oven; and all the proud, yea, and all that do wickedly, shall be stubble: and the day that cometh shall burn them up, saith the LORD of hosts, that it shall leave them neither root nor branch.', '&para; 3~03117~ 4~0935~, 7~01197~ 10~08574~; 14~02086~, 19~06213~ 20~07564~, 23~07179~: 26~03117~ 28~0935~ 32~03857~, 33~0559~ 35~03068~ 37~06635~, 41~05800~ 44~08328~ 46~06057~.'),
  (925, 1, 31, 48, 'And Laban said, This heap is a witness between me and thee this day. Therefore was the name of it called Galeed;', '1~03837~ 2~0559~, 4~01530~ [5] 7~05707~ 13~03117~. 17~08034~ 20~07121~ 21~01567~;'),
  (2241, 2, 26, 1, 'Moreover thou shalt make the tabernacle with ten curtains of fine twined linen, and blue, and purple, and scarlet: with cherubims of cunning work shalt thou make them.', '&para; 3~06213~ 5~04908~ [6] 7~06235~ 8~03407~ [9] 11~07806~ 12~08336~, 14~08504~, 16~0713~, 18~08438~ 19~08144~:* [20] 21~03742~ 23~02803~ 24~04639~ 27~06213~'),
  (8774, 11, 1, 49, 'And all the guests that were with Adonijah were afraid, and rose up, and went every man his way.', '3~07121~ [5] 7~0138~ 9~02729~, 12~06965~, 14~03212~ 16~0376~ 18~01870~.'),
  (10789, 13, 14, 7, 'And Elishama, and Beeliada, and Eliphalet.', '1~0476~, 3~01182~, 5~0467~.'),
  (149, 1, 6, 11, 'The earth also was corrupt before God, and the earth was filled with violence.', '&para; 1~0776~ 4~07843~ 5~06440~ 6~0430~, 9~0776~ 11~04390~ 13~02555~.'),
  (16814, 20, 14, 33, 'Wisdom resteth in the heart of him that hath understanding: but that which is in the midst of fools is made known.', '&para; 0~02451~ 1~05117~ 4~03820~ 9~0995~: [11 13] 16~07130~ 18~03684~ 21~03045~.'),
  (2426, 2, 31, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (21281, 26, 32, 24, 'There is Elam and all her multitude round about her grave, all of them slain, fallen by the sword, which are gone down uncircumcised into the nether parts of the earth, which caused their terror in the land of the living; yet have they borne their shame with them that go down to the pit.', '[1] 2~05867~ 6~01995~ 8~05439~ 10~06900~, 14~02491~, 15~05307~ 18~02719~, 22~03381~ 23~06189~ 27~08482~ 30~0776~, 32~05414~ 34~02851~ 37~0776~ 40~02416~; 44~05375~ 46~03639~ 51~03381~ 54~0953~.'),
  (4637, 4, 29, 23, 'And on the fourth day ten bullocks, two rams, and fourteen lambs of the first year without blemish:', '3~07243~ 4~03117~ 5~06235~ 6~06499~, 7~08147~ 8~0352~, [9] 10~06240~ 11~0702~* 12~03532~ 15~01121~ 16~08141~ 18~08549~:'),
  (3363, 3, 21, 13, 'And he shall take a wife in her virginity.', '3~03947~ 5~0802~ 8~01331~.'),
  (8897, 11, 5, 11, 'And Solomon gave Hiram twenty thousand measures of wheat for food to his household, and twenty measures of pure oil: thus gave Solomon to Hiram year by year.', '1~08010~ 2~05414~ 3~02438~ 4~06242~ 5~0505~ 6~03734~ 8~02406~ [9] 10~04361~ 13~01004~, 15~06242~ 16~03734~ 18~03795~ 19~08081~: 21~05414~ 22~08010~ 24~02438~ 25~08141~ 27~08141~.'),
  (30245, 58, 12, 17, 'For ye know how that afterward, when he would have inherited the blessing, he was rejected: for he found no place of repentance, though he sought it carefully with tears.', '0~1063~ 2~2467~ 3~3754~ 5~3347~ 6~2532~,* 9~2309~ 11~2816~ 13~2129~, 16~593~: 17~1063~ 19~2147~ 20~3756~ 21~5117~ 23~3341~, 24~2539~ 26~1567~ 27~846~ 28~1567~ 29~3326~ 30~1144~.'),
  (22873, 37, 2, 9, 'The glory of this latter house shall be greater than of the former, saith the LORD of hosts: and in this place will I give peace, saith the LORD of hosts.', '1~03519~ 4~0314~ 5~01004~ 9~01419~ 12~07223~, 13~05002~ 15~03068~ 17~06635~: 21~04725~ 24~05414~ 25~07965~, 26~0559~ 28~03068~ 30~06635~.'),
  (21254, 26, 31, 15, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD; In the day when he went down to the grave I caused a mourning: I covered the deep for him, and I restrained the floods thereof, and the great waters were stayed: and I caused Lebanon to mourn for him, and all the trees of the field fainted for him.', '1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~; 7~03117~ 11~03381~ 14~07585~ 18~056~: 20~03680~ 22~08415~ 27~04513~ 29~05104~ 33~07227~ 34~04325~ 36~03607~: 40~03844~ 42~06937~ 48~06086~ 51~07704~ 52~05969~'),
  (16635, 20, 8, 24, 'When there were no depths, I was brought forth; when there were no fountains abounding with water.', '[1 2] 4~08415~, 8~02342~; [10 11] 13~04599~ 14~03513~ 16~04325~.'),
  (3216, 3, 16, 10, 'But the goat, on which the lot fell to be the scapegoat, shall be presented alive before the LORD, to make an atonement with him, and to let him go for a scapegoat into the wilderness.', '2~08163~, 6~01486~ 7~05927~ 11~05799~, 14~05975~ 15~02416~ 16~06440~ 18~03068~, 22~03722~ [25] 29~07971~ 32~05799~ 35~04057~.'),
  (18965, 24, 1, 10, 'See, I have this day set thee over the nations and over the kingdoms, to root out, and to pull down, and to destroy, and to throw down, to build, and to plant.', '0~07200~, 4~03117~ 5~06485~ 9~01471~ 13~04467~, 16~05428~, 20~05422~, 23~06~, 27~02040~, 29~01129~, 32~05193~.'),
  (20366, 25, 3, 3, 'Surely against me is he turned; he turneth his hand against me all the day.', '5~07725~; 7~02015~ 9~03027~ [10 11] 14~03117~.'),
  (28901, 47, 5, 8, 'We are confident, I say, and willing rather to be absent from the body, and to be present with the Lord.', '2~2292~, [3 4] 5~2532~ 6~1161~* 7~2106~ 8~3123~ 11~1553~ 12~1537~ 14~4983~, 15~2532~ 18~1736~ 19~4314~ 21~2962~.'),
  (12121, 15, 4, 2, 'Then they came to Zerubbabel, and to the chief of the fathers, and said unto them, Let us build with you: for we seek your God, as ye do; and we do sacrifice unto him since the days of Esarhaddon king of Assur, which brought us up hither.', '2~05066~ 4~02216~, 8~07218~ 11~01~, 13~0559~ 18~01129~ 23~01875~ 25~0430~, [28] 32~02076~ 37~03117~ 39~0634~ 40~04428~ 42~0804~, 47~05927~.'),
  (24804, 41, 14, 39, 'And again he went away, and prayed, and spake the same words.', '0~2532~ 1~3825~ 4~565~, 6~4336~, 8~2036~ 10~846~ 11~3056~.'),
  (10306, 13, 1, 46, 'And when Husham was dead, Hadad the son of Bedad, which smote Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Avith.', '2~02367~ 4~04191~, 5~01908~ 7~01121~ 9~0911~, 11~05221~ 12~04080~ 15~07704~ 17~04124~, 18~04427~ 24~08034~ 27~05892~ [28] 29~05762~.'),
  (9135, 11, 11, 19, 'And Hadad found great favour in the sight of Pharaoh, so that he gave him to wife the sister of his own wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen.', '1~01908~ 2~04672~ 3~03966~ 4~02580~ 7~05869~ 9~06547~, 13~05414~ 16~0802~ 18~0269~ 22~0802~, 24~0269~ 26~08472~ 28~01377~.'),
  (6719, 7, 7, 18, 'When I blow with a trumpet, I and all that are with me, then blow ye the trumpets also on every side of all the camp, and say, The sword of the LORD, and of Gideon.', '2~08628~ 5~07782~, [10] 14~08628~ 17~07782~ 21~05439~ 25~04264~, 27~0559~, [28 29] 32~03068~, 35~01439~.'),
  (20809, 26, 16, 38, 'And I will judge thee, as women that break wedlock and shed blood are judged; and I will give thee blood in fury and jealousy.', '3~08199~ 9~05003~ 11~08210~ 12~01818~ 14~04941~; 18~05414~ 20~01818~ 22~02534~ 24~07068~.'),
  (12358, 16, 3, 22, 'And after him repaired the priests, the men of the plain.', '1~0310~ 3~02388~ 5~03548~, 7~0582~ 10~03603~.'),
  (15694, 19, 106, 34, 'They did not destroy the nations, concerning whom the LORD commanded them:', '&para; 3~08045~ 5~05971~, 9~03068~ 10~0559~'),
  (4343, 4, 20, 27, 'And Moses did as the LORD commanded: and they went up into mount Hor in the sight of all the congregation.', '1~04872~ 2~06213~ 5~03068~ 6~06680~: 10~05927~ 12~02022~ 13~02023~ 16~05869~ 20~05712~.'),
  (28282, 45, 12, 21, 'Be not overcome of evil, but overcome evil with good.', '0~3528~ 1~3361~ 2~3528~ 3~5259~ 4~2556~, 5~235~ 6~3528~ 7~2556~ 8~1722~ 9~18~.'),
  (27387, 44, 13, 9, 'Then Saul, (who also is called Paul,) filled with the Holy Ghost, set his eyes on him,', '0~1161~ 1~4569~, 2~3588~* 4~2532~ [5 6] 7~3972~,) 9~4130~ 11~40~ 12~4151~ 13~2532~,* 16~816~ 17~1519~ 18~846~,'),
  (2589, 2, 36, 18, 'And he made fifty taches of brass to couple the tent together, that it might be one.', '2~06213~ 3~02572~ 4~07165~ [5] 6~05178~ 8~02266~ 10~0168~ 11~02266~, 16~0259~.'),
  (22181, 28, 6, 5, 'Therefore have I hewed them by the prophets; I have slain them by the words of my mouth: and thy judgments are as the light that goeth forth.', '3~02672~ [4] 7~05030~; 10~02026~ 14~0561~ 17~06310~: 20~04941~ [21 22] 24~0216~ [25] 27~03318~.'),
  (10602, 13, 8, 19, 'And Jakim, and Zichri, and Zabdi,', '1~03356~, 3~02147~, 5~02067~,'),
  (28761, 46, 15, 27, 'For he hath put all things under his feet. But when he saith all things are put under him, it is manifest that he is excepted, which did put all things under him.', '0~1063~ 3~5293~ 5~3956~ 6~5259~ 7~846~ 8~4228~. 9~1161~ 10~3752~ 12~2036~ 13~3754~* 15~3956~ 18~5293~ [19 21] 22~1212~ 23~3754~ 26~1622~, 29~5293~ 31~3956~ 32~5293~ 33~846~.'),
  (28681, 46, 12, 31, 'But covet earnestly the best gifts: and yet shew I unto you a more excellent way.', '0~1161~ 2~2206~ 4~2909~ 5~5486~: 6~2532~ 7~2089~ 9~1166~ 11~5213~ 13~2596~ 14~5236~ 15~3598~.'),
  (23959, 40, 23, 31, 'Wherefore ye be witnesses unto yourselves, that ye are the children of them which killed the prophets.', '0~5620~ 3~3140~ 5~1438~, 6~3754~ 8~2075~ 10~5207~ 14~5407~ 16~4396~.'),
  (2410, 2, 30, 23, 'Take thou also unto thee principal spices, of pure myrrh five hundred shekels, and of sweet cinnamon half so much, even two hundred and fifty shekels, and of sweet calamus two hundred and fifty shekels,', '0~03947~ 5~07218~ 6~01314~, 8~01865~ 9~04753~ 10~02568~ 11~03967~ [12] 15~01314~ 16~07076~ 17~04276~ 19~04276~, [20] 22~03967~ 24~02572~ [25] 28~01314~ 29~07070~ 31~03967~ 33~02572~ [34]'),
  (5425, 5, 19, 13, 'Thine eye shall not pity him, but thou shalt put away the guilt of innocent blood from Israel, that it may go well with thee.', '1~05869~ 4~02347~ 10~01197~ [11 13] 14~05355~ 15~01818~ 17~03478~, 22~02895~'),
  (19745, 24, 32, 5, 'And he shall lead Zedekiah to Babylon, and there shall he be until I visit him, saith the LORD: though ye fight with the Chaldeans, ye shall not prosper.', '3~03212~ 4~06667~ 6~0894~, 14~06485~ 16~05002~ 18~03068~: 21~03898~ 24~03778~, 28~06743~.'),
  (24393, 41, 5, 19, 'Howbeit Jesus suffered him not, but saith unto him, Go home to thy friends, and tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee, and hath had compassion on thee.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~863~ 3~846~ 4~3756~, 5~235~ 6~3004~ 8~846~, 9~5217~ 10~4675~ 11~1519~* 12~3624~* 13~4314~ 15~4674~, 16~2532~ 17~312~ 18~846~ 21~3745~ 23~2962~ 25~4160~ 27~4671~, 28~2532~ 31~1653~ 33~4571~.'),
  (29236, 49, 1, 14, 'Which is the earnest of our inheritance until the redemption of the purchased possession, unto the praise of his glory.', '0~3739~ 1~2076~ 3~728~ 5~2257~ 6~2817~ 7~1519~ 9~629~ 13~4047~, 14~1519~ 16~1868~ 18~846~ 19~1391~.'),
  (8226, 10, 8, 10, 'Then Toi sent Joram his son unto king David, to salute him, and to bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer, and smitten him: for Hadadezer had wars with Toi. And Joram brought with him vessels of silver, and vessels of gold, and vessels of brass:', '1~08583~ 2~07971~ 3~03141~ 5~01121~ 7~04428~ 8~01732~, 10~07592~ 11~07965~* 15~01288~ 20~03898~ 22~01909~, 24~05221~ 27~01909~ 29~04421~ 30~0376~ 31~08583~. [33] 36~03027~ 37~03627~ 39~03701~, 41~03627~ 43~02091~, 45~03627~ 47~05178~:'),
  (21085, 26, 24, 20, 'Then I answered them, The word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '2~0559~ 5~01697~ 8~03068~ 12~0559~,'),
  (9086, 11, 9, 27, 'And Hiram sent in the navy his servants, shipmen that had knowledge of the sea, with the servants of Solomon.', '1~02438~ 2~07971~ 5~0590~ 7~05650~, 8~0591~ 9~0582~ 11~03045~ 14~03220~, 17~05650~ 19~08010~.'),
  (1408, 1, 46, 17, 'And the sons of Asher; Jimnah, and Ishuah, and Isui, and Beriah, and Serah their sister: and the sons of Beriah; Heber, and Malchiel.', '2~01121~ 4~0836~; 5~03232~, 7~03438~, 9~03440~, 11~01283~, 13~08294~ 15~0269~: 18~01121~ 20~01283~; 21~02268~, 23~04439~.'),
  (18280, 23, 32, 12, 'They shall lament for the teats, for the pleasant fields, for the fruitful vine.', '2~05594~ 5~07699~, 8~02531~ 9~07704~, 12~06509~ 13~01612~.'),
  (15538, 19, 102, 8, 'Mine enemies reproach me all the day; and they that are mad against me are sworn against me.', '1~0341~ 2~02778~ 6~03117~; [7] 11~01984~ 15~07650~'),
  (24618, 41, 10, 19, 'Thou knowest the commandments, Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Defraud not, Honour thy father and mother.', '1~1492~ 3~1785~, 4~3431~ 5~3361~ 7~3431~, 8~5407~ 9~3361~ 10~5407~, 11~2813~ 12~3361~ 13~2813~, 14~5576~ 15~3361~ 18~5576~, 19~650~ 20~3361~, 21~5091~ 22~4675~ 23~3962~ 24~2532~ 25~3384~.'),
  (26563, 43, 11, 25, 'Jesus said unto her, I am the resurrection, and the life: he that believeth in me, though he were dead, yet shall he live:', '0~2424~ 1~2036~ 3~846~, 4~1473~ 5~1510~ 7~386~, 8~2532~ 10~2222~: 13~4100~ 14~1519~ 15~1691~, 16~2579~ 19~599~, 23~2198~:'),
  (6363, 6, 19, 35, 'And the fenced cities are Ziddim, Zer, and Hammath, Rakkath, and Chinnereth,', '2~04013~ 3~05892~ [4] 5~06661~, 6~06863~, 8~02575~, 9~07557~, 11~03672~,'),
  (19777, 24, 32, 37, 'Behold, I will gather them out of all countries, whither I have driven them in mine anger, and in my fury, and in great wrath; and I will bring them again unto this place, and I will cause them to dwell safely:', '5~06908~ 8~0776~, 12~05080~ 16~0639~, 20~02534~, 23~01419~ 24~07110~; 30~07725~ 33~04725~, 40~03427~ 41~0983~:'),
  (4882, 4, 35, 31, 'Moreover ye shall take no satisfaction for the life of a murderer, which is guilty of death: but he shall be surely put to death.', '3~03947~ 5~03724~ 8~05315~ 11~07523~, [13] 14~07563~ 16~04191~: 21~04191~ 24~04191~.'),
  (13026, 18, 7, 9, 'As the cloud is consumed and vanisheth away: so he that goeth down to the grave shall come up no more.', '[0] 2~06051~ 4~03615~ 7~03212~: 12~03381~ 15~07585~ 18~05927~ [20]'),
  (14553, 19, 41, 2, 'The LORD will preserve him, and keep him alive; and he shall be blessed upon the earth: and thou wilt not deliver him unto the will of his enemies.', '1~03068~ 3~08104~ 8~02421~; [9] 13~0833~ 16~0776~: 21~05414~ 25~05315~ 28~0341~.'),
  (9733, 12, 7, 18, 'And it came to pass as the man of God had spoken to the king, saying, Two measures of barley for a shekel, and a measure of fine flour for a shekel, shall be to morrow about this time in the gate of Samaria:', '7~0376~ 9~0430~ 11~01696~ 14~04428~, 15~0559~, 17~05429~ 19~08184~ 22~08255~, 25~05429~ 28~05560~ 31~08255~, 35~04279~ 38~06256~ 41~08179~ 43~08111~:'),
  (22105, 28, 1, 2, 'The beginning of the word of the LORD by Hosea. And the LORD said to Hosea, Go, take unto thee a wife of whoredoms and children of whoredoms: for the land hath committed great whoredom, departing from the LORD.', '&para; 1~08462~ 4~01696~ 7~03068~ 9~01954~. 12~03068~ 13~0559~ 15~01954~, 16~03212~, 17~03947~ 21~0802~ 23~02183~ 25~03206~ 27~02183~: 30~0776~ 33~02181~ 34~02181~, [35] 36~0310~ 38~03068~.'),
  (30293, 59, 1, 11, 'For the sun is no sooner risen with a burning heat, but it withereth the grass, and the flower thereof falleth, and the grace of the fashion of it perisheth: so also shall the rich man fade away in his ways.', '0~1063~ 2~2246~ 6~393~ 7~4862~ 10~2742~, 11~2532~ 13~3583~ 15~5528~, 16~2532~ 18~438~ 19~846~ 20~1601~, 21~2532~ 23~2143~ 26~4383~ 28~846~ 29~622~: 30~3779~ 31~2532~ 32~3133~ 35~4145~ 37~3133~ 38~1722~ 39~846~ 40~4197~.'),
  (16440, 20, 1, 31, 'Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.', '3~0398~ 6~06529~ 10~01870~, 13~07646~ 17~04156~.'),
  (2805, 3, 4, 5, 'And the priest that is anointed shall take of the bullock''s blood, and bring it to the tabernacle of the congregation:', '2~03548~ 5~04899~ 7~03947~ 10~06499~ 11~01818~, 13~0935~ 17~0168~ 20~04150~:'),
  (4079, 4, 12, 15, 'And Miriam was shut out from the camp seven days: and the people journeyed not till Miriam was brought in again.', '1~04813~ 3~05462~ 4~02351~ 7~04264~ 8~07651~ 9~03117~: 12~05971~ 13~05265~ 16~04813~ 18~0622~ [20]'),
  (23003, 38, 8, 18, 'And the word of the LORD of hosts came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 7~06635~ 11~0559~,'),
  (741, 1, 27, 10, 'And thou shalt bring it to thy father, that he may eat, and that he may bless thee before his death.', '3~0935~ [4] 7~01~, 11~0398~, 13~0834~ 16~01288~ 18~06440~ 20~04194~.'),
  (20356, 25, 2, 15, 'All that pass by clap their hands at thee; they hiss and wag their head at the daughter of Jerusalem, saying, Is this the city that men call The perfection of beauty, The joy of the whole earth?', '2~05674~ 4~05606~ [5] 6~03709~ 8~01870~; 10~08319~ 12~05128~ 14~07218~ 17~01323~ 19~03389~, [20 21] 24~05892~ [26] 27~0559~ 29~03632~ 31~03308~, 33~04885~ 37~0776~?'),
  (6923, 7, 14, 7, 'And he went down, and talked with the woman; and she pleased Samson well.', '3~03381~, 5~01696~ 8~0802~; 11~03474~ 12~08123~ 13~03474~ 14~05869~.*'),
  (11492, 14, 14, 8, 'And Asa had an army of men that bare targets and spears, out of Judah three hundred thousand; and out of Benjamin, that bare shields and drew bows, two hundred and fourscore thousand: all these were mighty men of valour.', '1~0609~ 4~02428~ [5 6] 8~05375~ 9~06793~ 11~07420~, 14~03063~ 15~07969~ 16~03967~ 17~0505~; 21~01144~, 23~05375~ 24~04043~ 26~01869~ 27~07198~, 29~03967~ 31~08084~ 32~0505~: [35] 37~01368~ 39~02428~.'),
  (517, 1, 20, 18, 'For the LORD had fast closed up all the wombs of the house of Abimelech, because of Sarah Abraham''s wife.', '2~03068~ 4~06113~ 6~06113~ 9~07358~ 12~01004~ 14~040~, 15~01697~ 17~08283~ 18~085~ 19~0802~.'),
  (5745, 5, 31, 11, 'When all Israel is come to appear before the LORD thy God in the place which he shall choose, thou shalt read this law before all Israel in their hearing.', '2~03478~ 4~0935~ 6~07200~ 7~06440~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~ 14~04725~ 18~0977~, 21~07121~ 23~08451~ 26~03478~ 29~0241~.'),
  (4418, 4, 22, 38, 'And Balaam said unto Balak, Lo, I am come unto thee: have I now any power at all to say any thing? the word that God putteth in my mouth, that shall I speak.', '1~01109~ 2~0559~ 4~01111~, 8~0935~ 15~03201~ 17~03201~ 19~01696~ 21~03972~? 23~01697~ 25~0430~ 26~07760~ 29~06310~, 33~01696~.'),
  (3391, 3, 22, 17, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (13819, 18, 38, 17, 'Have the gates of death been opened unto thee? or hast thou seen the doors of the shadow of death?', '2~08179~ 4~04194~ 6~01540~ 12~07200~ 14~08179~ 19~06757~?'),
  (21912, 27, 5, 29, 'Then commanded Belshazzar, and they clothed Daniel with scarlet, and put a chain of gold about his neck, and made a proclamation concerning him, that he should be the third ruler in the kingdom.', '0~0116~ 1~0560~ 2~01113~, 5~03848~ 6~01841~ 8~0711~, [10] 12~02002~ 14~01722~ 15~05922~ 17~06676~, 21~03745~ 22~05922~ 27~01934~ 29~08531~ 30~07990~ 33~04437~.'),
  (26791, 43, 17, 17, 'Sanctify them through thy truth: thy word is truth.', '&para; 0~37~ 1~846~ 2~1722~ 3~4675~ 4~225~: 5~4674~ 6~3056~ 7~2076~ 8~225~.'),
  (18989, 24, 2, 15, 'The young lions roared upon him, and yelled, and they made his land waste: his cities are burned without inhabitant.', '2~03715~ 3~07580~ [6] 7~05414~ 8~06963~,* 11~07896~ 13~0776~ 14~08047~: 16~05892~ 18~03341~ 20~03427~.'),
  (2135, 2, 22, 17, 'If her father utterly refuse to give her unto him, he shall pay money according to the dowry of virgins.', '2~01~ 3~03985~ 4~03985~ 6~05414~ 12~08254~ 13~03701~ 17~04119~ 19~01330~.'),
  (29015, 47, 11, 10, 'As the truth of Christ is in me, no man shall stop me of this boasting in the regions of Achaia.', '2~225~ 4~5547~ 5~2076~ 6~1722~ 7~1698~ 8~3754~,* 10~3756~ 12~4972~ 13~1691~ 14~1519~ 15~3778~ 16~2746~ 17~1722~ 19~2824~ 21~882~.'),
  (13590, 18, 30, 24, 'Howbeit he will not stretch out his hand to the grave, though they cry in his destruction.', '5~07971~ [6] 7~03027~ 10~01164~, 13~07769~ 16~06365~.'),
  (8121, 10, 3, 33, 'And the king lamented over Abner, and said, Died Abner as a fool dieth?', '2~04428~ 3~06969~ 5~074~, 7~0559~, 8~04191~ 9~074~ 12~05036~ 13~04194~?'),
  (27425, 44, 13, 47, 'For so hath the Lord commanded us, saying, I have set thee to be a light of the Gentiles, that thou shouldest be for salvation unto the ends of the earth.', '0~1063~ 1~3779~ 2~1781~ 4~2962~ 5~1781~ 6~2254~, [7] 10~5087~ 11~4571~ 13~1519~ 15~5457~ 18~1484~, 20~4571~ 22~1511~ 23~1519~ 24~4991~ 25~2193~ 27~2078~ 30~1093~.'),
  (13823, 18, 38, 21, 'Knowest thou it, because thou wast then born? or because the number of thy days is great?', '0~03045~ [2] 7~03205~? [9] 11~04557~ 14~03117~ [15] 16~07227~?'),
  (18237, 23, 30, 11, 'Get you out of the way, turn aside out of the path, cause the Holy One of Israel to cease from before us.', '2~05493~ 5~01870~, 7~05186~ 11~0734~, 15~06918~ 17~03478~ 19~07673~ 21~06440~'),
  (23247, 40, 5, 3, 'Blessed are the poor in spirit: for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.', '&para; 0~3107~ [1] 3~4434~ 5~4151~: 6~3754~ 7~846~ 8~2076~ 10~932~ 12~3772~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (15814, 19, 112, 2, 'His seed shall be mighty upon earth: the generation of the upright shall be blessed.', '1~02233~ 4~01368~ 6~0776~: 8~01755~ 11~03477~ 14~01288~.'),
  (16345, 19, 145, 16, 'Thou openest thine hand, and satisfiest the desire of every living thing.', '1~06605~ 3~03027~, 5~07646~ 7~07522~ 11~02416~.'),
  (12372, 16, 4, 4, 'Hear, O our God; for we are despised: and turn their reproach upon their own head, and give them for a prey in the land of captivity:', '0~08085~, 3~0430~; 7~0939~: 9~07725~ 11~02781~ 15~07218~, 17~05414~ 21~0961~ 24~0776~ 26~07633~:'),
  (18268, 23, 31, 9, 'And he shall pass over to his strong hold for fear, and his princes shall be afraid of the ensign, saith the LORD, whose fire is in Zion, and his furnace in Jerusalem.', '4~05674~ 8~05553~ 10~04032~, 13~08269~ 16~02865~ 19~05251~, 20~05002~ 22~03068~, 24~0217~ [25] 27~06726~, 30~08574~ 32~03389~.'),
  (17527, 21, 11, 5, 'As thou knowest not what is the way of the spirit, nor how the bones do grow in the womb of her that is with child: even so thou knowest not the works of God who maketh all.', '2~03045~ [5] 7~01870~ 10~07307~, [11] 14~06106~ [15 16] 19~0990~ 25~04392~: 29~03045~ 32~04639~ 34~0430~ 36~06213~'),
  (14248, 19, 23, 4, 'Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil: for thou art with me; thy rod and thy staff they comfort me.', '3~03212~ 6~01516~ 11~06757~, 14~03372~ 16~07451~: [19] 23~07626~ 26~04938~ 28~05162~'),
  (28221, 45, 10, 17, 'So then faith cometh by hearing, and hearing by the word of God.', '1~686~ 2~4102~ [3] 4~1537~ 5~189~, 6~1161~ 7~189~ 8~1223~ 10~4487~ 12~2316~.'),
  (24813, 41, 14, 48, 'And Jesus answered and said unto them, Are ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and with staves to take me?', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 10~1831~, 11~5613~ 12~1909~ 14~3027~, 15~3326~ 16~3162~ 17~2532~ [18] 19~3586~ 21~4815~ 22~3165~?'),
  (27106, 44, 5, 31, 'Him hath God exalted with his right hand to be a Prince and a Saviour, for to give repentance to Israel, and forgiveness of sins.', '0~5126~ 2~2316~ 3~5312~ 5~846~ 7~1188~ [8 9] 11~747~ 12~2532~ 14~4990~, 17~1325~ 18~3341~ 20~2474~, 21~2532~ 22~859~ 24~266~.'),
  (5909, 6, 3, 10, 'And Joshua said, Hereby ye shall know that the living God is among you, and that he will without fail drive out from before you the Canaanites, and the Hittites, and the Hivites, and the Perizzites, and the Girgashites, and the Amorites, and the Jebusites.', '1~03091~ 2~0559~, 6~03045~ 9~02416~ 10~0410~ [11] 12~07130~ [15] 19~03423~ 21~03423~ 23~06440~ 26~03669~, 29~02850~, 32~02340~, 35~06522~, 38~01622~, 41~0567~, 44~02983~.'),
  (4012, 4, 10, 19, 'And over the host of the tribe of the children of Simeon was Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai.', '3~06635~ 6~04294~ 9~01121~ 11~08095~ [12] 13~08017~ 15~01121~ 17~06701~.'),
  (19454, 24, 21, 5, 'And I myself will fight against you with an outstretched hand and with a strong arm, even in anger, and in fury, and in great wrath.', '4~03898~ 9~05186~ 10~03027~ 14~02389~ 15~02220~, 18~0639~, 21~02534~, 24~01419~ 25~07110~.'),
  (2162, 2, 23, 13, 'And in all things that I have said unto you be circumspect: and make no mention of the name of other gods, neither let it be heard out of thy mouth.', '[3] 7~0559~ 11~08104~: 15~02142~ 18~08034~ 20~0312~ 21~0430~, 26~08085~ 27~05921~ 30~06310~.'),
  (5423, 5, 19, 11, 'But if any man hate his neighbour, and lie in wait for him, and rise up against him, and smite him mortally that he die, and fleeth into one of these cities:', '3~0376~ 4~08130~ 6~07453~, 10~0693~ 15~06965~ 19~05221~ 21~05315~ 24~04191~, 26~05127~ 28~0259~ 30~0411~ 31~05892~:'),
  (7958, 9, 28, 9, 'And the woman said unto him, Behold, thou knowest what Saul hath done, how he hath cut off those that have familiar spirits, and the wizards, out of the land: wherefore then layest thou a snare for my life, to cause me to die?', '2~0802~ 3~0559~ 8~03045~ 10~07586~ 12~06213~, 17~03772~ 22~0178~, 25~03049~, 29~0776~: 35~05367~ 38~05315~, 43~04191~?'),
  (74, 1, 3, 18, 'Thorns also and thistles shall it bring forth to thee; and thou shalt eat the herb of the field;', '1~06975~ 3~01863~ 7~06779~ 13~0398~ 15~06212~ 18~07704~;'),
  (3268, 3, 18, 12, 'Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father''s sister: she is thy father''s near kinswoman.', '3~01540~ 5~06172~ 8~01~ 9~0269~: [11] 13~01~ 15~07607~.'),
  (30909, 66, 12, 2, 'And she being with child cried, travailing in birth, and pained to be delivered.', '0~2532~ 2~2192~ 3~1722~ 4~1064~ 5~2896~, 8~5605~, 9~2532~ 10~928~ 13~5088~.'),
  (23842, 40, 21, 6, 'And the disciples went, and did as Jesus commanded them,', '0~1161~ 2~3101~ 3~4198~, 4~2532~ 5~4160~ 6~2531~ 7~2424~ 8~4367~ 9~846~,'),
  (29160, 48, 4, 13, 'Ye know how through infirmity of the flesh I preached the gospel unto you at the first.', '0~1161~ 1~1492~ 2~3754~ 3~1223~ 4~769~ 7~4561~ 11~2097~ 13~5213~ 16~4386~.'),
  (25957, 42, 23, 8, 'And when Herod saw Jesus, he was exceeding glad: for he was desirous to see him of a long season, because he had heard many things of him; and he hoped to have seen some miracle done by him.', '0~1161~ 2~2264~ 3~1492~ 4~2424~, 7~3029~ 8~5463~: 9~1063~ 11~2258~ 12~2309~ 14~1492~ 15~846~ 16~1537~ 18~2425~ [19] 20~1223~ 23~191~ 25~4183~ 26~4012~ 27~846~; 28~2532~ 30~1679~ 33~1492~ 34~5100~ 35~4592~ 36~1096~ 37~5259~ 38~846~.'),
  (8263, 10, 10, 16, 'And Hadarezer sent, and brought out the Syrians that were beyond the river: and they came to Helam; and Shobach the captain of the host of Hadarezer went before them.', '1~01928~ 2~07971~, 5~03318~ 7~0758~ [9] 10~05676~ 12~05104~: 15~0935~ 17~02431~; 19~07731~ 21~08269~ 24~06635~ 26~01928~ [27] 28~06440~'),
  (936, 1, 32, 4, 'And he commanded them, saying, Thus shall ye speak unto my lord Esau; Thy servant Jacob saith thus, I have sojourned with Laban, and stayed there until now:', '2~06680~ 4~0559~, 8~0559~ 11~0113~ 12~06215~; 14~05650~ 15~03290~ 16~0559~ 20~01481~ 22~03837~, 25~0309~'),
  (1022, 1, 35, 6, 'So Jacob came to Luz, which is in the land of Canaan, that is, Bethel, he and all the people that were with him.', '&para; 1~03290~ 2~0935~ 4~03870~, [6] 9~0776~ 11~03667~, [13] 14~01008~, 19~05971~ [21]'),
  (3694, 4, 2, 31, 'All they that were numbered in the camp of Dan were an hundred thousand and fifty and seven thousand and six hundred. They shall go hindmost with their standards.', '4~06485~ 7~04264~ 9~01835~ [10] 12~03967~ 13~0505~ 15~02572~ 17~07651~ 18~0505~ 20~08337~ 21~03967~. 24~05265~ 25~0314~ 28~01714~.'),
  (27874, 44, 27, 3, 'And the next day we touched at Sidon. And Julius courteously entreated Paul, and gave him liberty to go unto his friends to refresh himself.', '0~5037~ 2~2087~ [3] 5~2609~ 6~1519~ 7~4605~. 8~5037~ 9~2457~ 10~5364~ 11~5530~ 12~3972~, [15] 16~2010~ 18~4198~ 19~4314~ 21~5384~ 24~5177~ 25~1958~.*'),
  (14197, 19, 20, 6, 'Now know I that the LORD saveth his anointed; he will hear him from his holy heaven with the saving strength of his right hand.', '&para; 1~03045~ 5~03068~ 6~03467~ 8~04899~; 11~06030~ 15~06944~ 16~08064~ 19~03468~ 20~01369~ 24~03225~.'),
  (18514, 23, 42, 25, 'Therefore he hath poured upon him the fury of his anger, and the strength of battle: and it hath set him on fire round about, yet he knew not; and it burned him, yet he laid it not to heart.', '3~08210~ 7~02534~ 10~0639~, 13~05807~ 15~04421~: 22~03857~ 24~05439~, 27~03045~ 31~01197~ 35~07760~ [36] 39~03820~.'),
  (808, 1, 29, 9, 'And while he yet spake with them, Rachel came with her father''s sheep: for she kept them.', '&para; 3~05750~ 4~01696~ 7~07354~ 8~0935~ 11~01~ 12~06629~: 16~07462~.'),
  (9151, 11, 11, 35, 'But I will take the kingdom out of his son''s hand, and will give it unto thee, even ten tribes.', '3~03947~ 5~04410~ 9~01121~ 10~03027~, 13~05414~ [17] 18~06235~ 19~07626~.'),
  (14264, 19, 25, 4, 'shew me thy ways, O LORD; teach me thy paths.', '0~03045~ 3~01870~, 5~03068~; 6~03925~ 9~0734~.'),
  (9773, 12, 9, 9, 'And I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah:', '3~05414~ 5~01004~ 7~0256~ 10~01004~ 12~03379~ 14~01121~ 16~05028~, 20~01004~ 22~01201~ 24~01121~ 26~0281~:'),
  (24640, 41, 10, 41, 'And when the ten heard it, they began to be much displeased with James and John.', '0~2532~ 3~1176~ 4~191~ [5] 7~756~ 11~23~ 12~4012~ 13~2385~ 14~2532~ 15~2491~.'),
  (2898, 3, 7, 14, 'And of it he shall offer one out of the whole oblation for an heave offering unto the LORD, and it shall be the priest''s that sprinkleth the blood of the peace offerings.', '5~07126~ 6~0259~ 11~07133~ [12] 15~08641~ 18~03068~, [19] 24~03548~ 26~02236~ 28~01818~ 32~08002~.'),
  (15963, 19, 119, 56, 'This I had, because I kept thy precepts.', '5~05341~ 7~06490~.'),
  (4767, 4, 33, 1, 'These are the journeys of the children of Israel, which went forth out of the land of Egypt with their armies under the hand of Moses and Aaron.', '&para; [1] 3~04550~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~, 11~03318~ 15~0776~ 17~04714~ 20~06635~ 23~03027~ 25~04872~ 27~0175~.'),
  (13167, 18, 13, 5, 'O that ye would altogether hold your peace! and it should be your wisdom.', '1~05414~ 4~02790~ 7~02790~! 13~02451~.'),
  (15739, 19, 107, 31, 'Oh that men would praise the LORD for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!', '[2] 4~03034~ 6~03068~ [7] 9~02617~, [11] 14~06381~ 17~01121~ 19~0120~!'),
  (13120, 18, 11, 3, 'Should thy lies make men hold their peace? and when thou mockest, shall no man make thee ashamed?', '2~0907~ 3~02790~ 4~04962~ 7~02790~? 11~03932~, 17~03637~?'),
  (2430, 2, 31, 5, 'And in cutting of stones, to set them, and in carving of timber, to work in all manner of workmanship.', '2~02799~ 4~068~, 6~04390~ [7] 10~02799~ 12~06086~, 14~06213~ 19~04399~.'),
  (1292, 1, 42, 35, 'And it came to pass as they emptied their sacks, that, behold, every man''s bundle of money was in his sack: and when both they and their father saw the bundles of money, they were afraid.', '7~07324~ 9~08242~, 13~0376~ 14~06872~ 16~03701~ [17] 20~08242~: [23] 27~01~ 28~07200~ 30~06872~ 32~03701~, 35~03372~.'),
  (22927, 38, 3, 6, 'And the angel of the LORD protested unto Joshua, saying,', '2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~05749~ 8~03091~, 9~0559~,'),
  (16514, 20, 4, 15, 'Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.', '0~06544~ 2~05674~ 6~07847~ 11~05674~.'),
  (341, 1, 14, 1, 'And it came to pass in the days of Amraphel king of Shinar, Arioch king of Ellasar, Chedorlaomer king of Elam, and Tidal king of nations;', '&para; 7~03117~ 9~0569~ 10~04428~ 12~08152~, 13~0746~ 14~04428~ 16~0495~, 17~03540~ 18~04428~ 20~05867~, 22~08413~ 23~04428~ 25~01471~;'),
  (7743, 9, 20, 6, 'If thy father at all miss me, then say, David earnestly asked leave of me that he might run to Bethlehem his city: for there is a yearly sacrifice there for all the family.', '2~01~ 4~06485~ 5~06485~ 8~0559~, 9~01732~ 10~07592~ 11~07592~ [12] 18~07323~ 20~01035~ 22~05892~: [24 25] 27~03117~ 28~02077~ 33~04940~.'),
  (265, 1, 10, 30, 'And their dwelling was from Mesha, as thou goest unto Sephar a mount of the east.', '2~04186~ 5~04852~, 8~0935~ 10~05611~ 12~02022~ 15~06924~.'),
  (16853, 20, 16, 4, 'The LORD hath made all things for himself: yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.', '&para; 1~03068~ 3~06466~ [5] 7~04617~: 11~07563~ 14~03117~ 16~07451~.'),
  (2401, 2, 30, 14, 'Every one that passeth among them that are numbered, from twenty years old and above, shall give an offering unto the LORD.', '3~05674~ 8~06485~, 10~06242~ 11~08141~ 12~01121~ 14~04605~, 16~05414~ 18~08641~ 21~03068~.'),
  (3156, 3, 14, 40, 'Then the priest shall command that they take away the stones in which the plague is, and they shall cast them into an unclean place without the city:', '2~03548~ 4~06680~ 7~02502~ 10~068~ 12~02004~ 14~05061~ [15] 19~07993~ 20~0853~* 24~02931~ 25~04725~ 26~02351~ 28~05892~:'),
  (13155, 18, 12, 18, 'He looseth the bond of kings, and girdeth their loins with a girdle.', '1~06605~ 3~04148~ 5~04428~, 7~0631~ 9~04975~ 12~0232~.'),
  (28187, 45, 9, 16, 'So then it is not of him that willeth, nor of him that runneth, but of God that sheweth mercy.', '0~686~ 1~3767~ [2 3] 4~3756~ 8~2309~, 9~3761~ 13~5143~, 14~235~ 16~2316~ 19~1653~.'),
  (22176, 28, 5, 15, 'I will go and return to my place, till they acknowledge their offence, and seek my face: in their affliction they will seek me early.', '2~03212~ [3] 4~07725~ 7~04725~, 12~0816~, 14~01245~ 16~06440~: 19~06862~ 24~07836~.'),
  (6636, 7, 5, 6, 'In the days of Shamgar the son of Anath, in the days of Jael, the highways were unoccupied, and the travellers walked through byways.', '&para; 2~03117~ 4~08044~ 6~01121~ 8~06067~, 11~03117~ 13~03278~, 15~0734~ 17~02308~, 20~01980~ 21~03212~ 23~05410~ 24~06128~.*'),
  (21167, 26, 28, 1, 'The word of the LORD came again unto me, saying,', '&para; 1~01697~ 4~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (22266, 28, 12, 5, 'Even the LORD God of hosts; the LORD is his memorial.', '2~03068~ 3~0430~ 5~06635~; 7~03068~ [8] 10~02143~.'),
  (20340, 25, 1, 21, 'They have heard that I sigh: there is none to comfort me: all mine enemies have heard of my trouble; they are glad that thou hast done it: thou wilt bring the day that thou hast called, and they shall be like unto me.', '2~08085~ 5~0584~: [6 7] 10~05162~ 14~0341~ 16~08085~ 19~07451~; 22~07797~ 26~06213~ [27] 30~0935~ 32~03117~ [33] 36~07121~, 41~03644~'),
  (4219, 4, 16, 20, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~ 8~0175~, 9~0559~,'),
  (27080, 44, 5, 5, 'And Ananias hearing these words fell down, and gave up the ghost: and great fear came on all them that heard these things.', '0~1161~ 1~367~ 2~191~ 3~5128~ 4~3056~ 6~4098~, 11~1634~: 12~2532~ 13~3173~ 14~5401~ 15~1096~ 16~1909~ 17~3956~ 20~191~ 22~5023~.'),
  (31054, 66, 19, 21, 'And the remnant were slain with the sword of him that sat upon the horse, which sword proceeded out of his mouth: and all the fowls were filled with their flesh.', '0~2532~ 2~3062~ 4~615~ 5~1722~ 7~4501~ 11~2521~ 12~1909~ 14~2462~, 15~3588~ [16] 17~1607~ 19~1537~ 20~846~ 21~4750~: 22~2532~ 23~3956~ 25~3732~ 27~5526~ 28~1537~ 29~846~ 30~4561~.'),
  (19461, 24, 21, 12, 'O house of David, thus saith the LORD; Execute judgment in the morning, and deliver him that is spoiled out of the hand of the oppressor, lest my fury go out like fire, and burn that none can quench it, because of the evil of your doings.', '1~01004~ 3~01732~, 5~0559~ 7~03068~; 8~01777~ 9~04941~ 12~01242~, 14~05337~ [15 17] 18~01497~ 22~03027~ 25~06231~, 28~02534~ 30~03318~ 32~0784~, 34~01197~ 38~03518~ [39] 40~06440~ 43~07455~ 46~04611~.'),
  (10771, 13, 13, 3, 'And let us bring again the ark of our God to us: for we inquired not at it in the days of Saul.', '4~05437~ 6~0727~ 9~0430~ 14~01875~ 20~03117~ 22~07586~.'),
  (27744, 44, 22, 24, 'The chief captain commanded him to be brought into the castle, and bade that he should be examined by scourging; that he might know wherefore they cried so against him.', '2~5506~ 3~2753~ 4~846~ 7~71~ 8~1519~ 10~3925~, 12~2036~ 14~846~ 17~426~ 19~3148~; 20~2443~ 23~1921~ 24~156~ 25~1223~* 26~3739~ 27~2019~ 28~3779~ 29~2019~ 30~846~.'),
  (16734, 20, 12, 6, 'The words of the wicked are to lie in wait for blood: but the mouth of the upright shall deliver them.', '&para; 1~01697~ 4~07563~ [5] 9~0693~ 11~01818~: 14~06310~ 17~03477~ 19~05337~'),
  (6910, 7, 13, 19, 'So Manoah took a kid with a meat offering, and offered it upon a rock unto the LORD: and the angel did wonderously; and Manoah and his wife looked on.', '1~04495~ 2~03947~ 4~05795~ 5~01423~ 8~04503~, 10~05927~ [11] 14~06697~ 17~03068~: [19 20] 21~06213~ 22~06381~; 24~04495~ 27~0802~ 29~07200~.'),
  (23269, 40, 5, 25, 'Agree with thine adversary quickly, whiles thou art in the way with him; lest at any time the adversary deliver thee to the judge, and the judge deliver thee to the officer, and thou be cast into prison.', '0~2468~ 1~2132~* 3~4675~ 4~476~ 5~5035~, 6~3755~ 7~2193~ 8~1488~ 9~1722~ 11~3598~ 12~3326~ 13~846~; 17~3379~ 19~476~ 20~3860~ 21~4571~ 24~2923~, 25~2532~ 27~2923~ 28~3860~ 29~4571~ 32~5257~, 33~2532~ 36~906~ 37~1519~ 38~5438~.'),
  (11227, 14, 2, 8, 'Send me also cedar trees, fir trees, and algum trees, out of Lebanon: for I know that thy servants can skill to cut timber in Lebanon; and, behold, my servants shall be with thy servants,', '0~07971~ 3~0730~ 4~06086~, 6~01265~, 9~0418~, 12~03844~: 15~03045~ 18~05650~ 20~03045~ 22~03772~ 23~06086~ 25~03844~; 29~05650~ [30 31] 34~05650~,'),
  (18011, 23, 18, 5, 'For afore the harvest, when the bud is perfect, and the sour grape is ripening in the flower, he shall both cut off the sprigs with pruning hooks, and take away and cut down the branches.', '1~06440~ 3~07105~, 6~06525~ 8~08552~, 12~01155~ 14~01580~ 17~05328~, 22~03772~ 24~02150~ 27~04211~, 30~05493~ [31] 33~08456~ 35~05189~.'),
  (12453, 16, 7, 24, 'The children of Hariph, an hundred and twelve.', '1~01121~ 3~02756~, 5~03967~ 7~06240~ 8~08147~.*'),
  (7753, 9, 20, 16, 'So Jonathan made a covenant with the house of David, saying, Let the LORD even require it at the hand of David''s enemies.', '1~03083~ 2~03772~ [3 4] 7~01004~ 9~01732~, [10] 13~03068~ 15~01245~ [16] 19~03027~ 21~01732~ 22~0341~.'),
  (15862, 19, 116, 5, 'Gracious is the LORD, and righteous; yea, our God is merciful.', '0~02587~ [1] 3~03068~, 5~06662~; 8~0430~ [9] 10~07355~.'),
  (18216, 23, 29, 14, 'Therefore, behold, I will proceed to do a marvellous work among this people, even a marvellous work and a wonder: for the wisdom of their wise men shall perish, and the understanding of their prudent men shall be hid.', '4~03254~ 9~06381~ 12~05971~, [13] 16~06381~ 19~06382~: 22~02451~ 25~02450~ [26] 28~06~, 31~0998~ 34~0995~ [35] 38~05641~.'),
  (2299, 2, 28, 1, 'And take thou unto thee Aaron thy brother, and his sons with him, from among the children of Israel, that he may minister unto me in the priest''s office, even Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar, Aaron''s sons.', '&para; 1~07126~ 5~0175~ 7~0251~, 10~01121~ 14~08432~ 16~01121~ 18~03478~, 28~03547~, [29] 30~0175~, 31~05070~ 33~030~, 34~0499~ 36~0385~, 37~0175~ 38~01121~.'),
  (7108, 7, 20, 47, 'But six hundred men turned and fled to the wilderness unto the rock Rimmon, and abode in the rock Rimmon four months.', '1~08337~ 2~03967~ 3~0376~ 4~06437~ 6~05127~ 9~04057~ 12~05553~ 13~07417~, 15~03427~ 18~05553~ 19~07417~ 20~0702~ 21~02320~.'),
  (11610, 14, 20, 14, 'Then upon Jahaziel the son of Zechariah, the son of Benaiah, the son of Jeiel, the son of Mattaniah, a Levite of the sons of Asaph, came the Spirit of the LORD in the midst of the congregation;', '&para; 2~03166~ 4~01121~ 6~02148~, 8~01121~ 10~01141~, 12~01121~ 14~03273~, 16~01121~ 18~04983~, 20~03881~ 23~01121~ 25~0623~, 28~07307~ 31~03068~ 34~08432~ 37~06951~;'),
  (21842, 27, 3, 26, 'Then Nebuchadnezzar came near to the mouth of the burning fiery furnace, and spake, and said, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, ye servants of the most high God, come forth, and come hither. Then Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, came forth of the midst of the fire.', '0~0116~ 1~05020~ 3~07127~ 6~08651~ 9~03345~ 10~05135~ 11~0861~, [12] 13~06032~, 15~0560~, 16~07715~, 17~04336~, 19~05665~, 21~05649~ 25~05943~ 26~0426~, 28~05312~, 30~0858~ [31] 32~0116~ 33~07715~, 34~04336~, 36~05665~, 38~05312~ 39~04481~ 41~01459~ 44~05135~.'),
  (28684, 46, 13, 3, 'And though I bestow all my goods to feed the poor, and though I give my body to be burned, and have not charity, it profiteth me nothing.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 3~5595~ 4~3956~ 5~3450~ 6~5224~ 8~5595~ [9 10] 11~2532~ 12~1437~ 14~3860~ 15~3450~ 16~4983~ 17~2443~ 19~2545~, 20~1161~ 21~2192~ 22~3361~ 23~26~, 26~5623~ 27~3762~.'),
  (19747, 24, 32, 7, 'Behold, Hanameel the son of Shallum thine uncle shall come unto thee, saying, Buy thee my field that is in Anathoth: for the right of redemption is thine to buy it.', '1~02601~ 3~01121~ 5~07967~ 7~01730~ 9~0935~ 12~0559~, 13~07069~ 16~07704~ [18] 20~06068~: 23~04941~ 25~01353~ [26] 29~07069~ [30]'),
  (13749, 18, 36, 4, 'For truly my words shall not be false: he that is perfect in knowledge is with thee.', '1~0551~ 3~04405~ [4] [6] 7~08267~: 11~08549~ 13~01844~ [14]'),
  (28766, 46, 15, 32, 'If after the manner of men I have fought with beasts at Ephesus, what advantageth it me, if the dead rise not? let us eat and drink; for to morrow we die.', '0~1487~ 3~2596~ 5~444~ 10~2341~ 11~1722~ 12~2181~, 13~5101~ 15~3786~ 16~3427~, 17~1487~ 19~3498~ 20~1453~ 21~3756~? 24~5315~ 25~2532~ 26~4095~; 27~1063~ 29~839~ 31~599~.'),
  (22720, 34, 2, 12, 'The lion did tear in pieces enough for his whelps, and strangled for his lionesses, and filled his holes with prey, and his dens with ravin.', '1~0738~ 5~02963~ 6~01767~ 9~01484~, 11~02614~ 14~03833~, 16~04390~ 18~02356~ 20~02964~, 23~04585~ 25~02966~.'),
  (27537, 44, 16, 38, 'And the serjeants told these words unto the magistrates: and they feared, when they heard that they were Romans.', '0~1161~ 2~4465~ 3~312~ 4~5023~ 5~4487~ 8~4755~: 9~2532~ 11~5399~, 14~191~ 15~3754~ 17~1526~ 18~4514~.'),
  (7731, 9, 19, 18, 'So David fled, and escaped, and came to Samuel to Ramah, and told him all that Saul had done to him. And he and Samuel went and dwelt in Naioth.', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~01272~, 4~04422~, 6~0935~ 8~08050~ 10~07414~, 12~05046~ 16~07586~ 18~06213~ 24~08050~ 25~03212~ 27~03427~ 29~05121~.'),
  (10112, 12, 20, 6, 'And I will add unto thy days fifteen years; and I will deliver thee and this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria; and I will defend this city for mine own sake, and for my servant David''s sake.', '3~03254~ 6~03117~ 7~06240~ 8~02568~* 9~08141~; 13~05337~ 17~05892~ 21~03709~ 24~04428~ 26~0804~; 30~01598~ 32~05892~ 40~05650~ 41~01732~'),
  (19654, 24, 29, 10, 'For thus saith the LORD, That after seventy years be accomplished at Babylon I will visit you, and perform my good word toward you, in causing you to return to this place.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~, 6~06310~ 7~07657~ 8~08141~ 10~04390~ 12~0894~ 15~06485~ 18~06965~ 20~02896~ 21~01697~ 28~07725~ 31~04725~.'),
  (1801, 2, 10, 19, 'And the LORD turned a mighty strong west wind, which took away the locusts, and cast them into the Red sea; there remained not one locust in all the coasts of Egypt.', '2~03068~ 3~02015~ 5~03966~ 6~02389~ 7~03220~ 8~07307~, 11~05375~ 13~0697~, 15~08628~ 19~05488~ 20~03220~; 22~07604~ 24~0259~ 25~0697~ 29~01366~ 31~04714~.'),
  (17180, 20, 27, 2, 'Let another man praise thee, and not thine own mouth; a stranger, and not thine own lips.', '&para; 2~02114~ 3~01984~ 9~06310~; 11~05237~, 16~08193~.'),
  (26374, 43, 7, 31, 'And many of the people believed on him, and said, When Christ cometh, will he do more miracles than these which this man hath done?', '0~1161~ 1~4183~ 2~1537~ 4~3793~ 5~4100~ 6~1519~ 7~846~, 8~2532~ 9~3004~ 10~3754~,* 11~3752~ 12~5547~ 13~2064~, 16~4160~ 17~3385~* 18~4119~ 19~4592~ 21~5130~ 22~3739~ 23~3778~ [24] 26~4160~?'),
  (23278, 40, 5, 34, 'But I say unto you, Swear not at all; neither by heaven; for it is God''s throne:', '0~1161~ 1~1473~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3660~ 6~3361~ 8~3654~; 9~3383~ 10~1722~ 11~3772~; 12~3754~ 14~2076~ 15~2316~ 16~2362~:'),
  (4113, 4, 13, 33, 'And there we saw the giants, the sons of Anak, which come of the giants: and we were in our own sight as grasshoppers, and so we were in their sight.', '3~07200~ 5~05303~, 7~01121~ 9~06061~, [10 11] 14~05303~: 21~05869~ 23~02284~, 30~05869~.'),
  (11405, 14, 10, 1, 'And Rehoboam went to Shechem: for to Shechem were all Israel come to make him king.', '&para; 1~07346~ 2~03212~ 4~07927~: 7~07927~ 10~03478~ 11~0935~ 15~04427~.'),
  (26704, 43, 14, 21, 'He that hath my commandments, and keepeth them, he it is that loveth me: and he that loveth me shall be loved of my Father, and I will love him, and will manifest myself to him.', '2~2192~ 3~3450~ 4~1785~, 5~2532~ 6~5083~ 7~846~, 8~1565~ 10~2076~ 12~25~ 13~3165~: 14~1161~ 17~25~ 18~3165~ 21~25~ 22~5259~ 23~3450~ 24~3962~, 25~2532~ 26~1473~ 28~25~ 29~846~, 30~2532~ 32~1718~ 33~1683~ 35~846~.'),
  (16963, 20, 19, 29, 'Judgments are prepared for scorners, and stripes for the back of fools.', '&para; 0~08201~ 2~03559~ 4~03887~, 6~04112~ 9~01460~ 11~03684~.'),
  (16654, 20, 9, 7, 'He that reproveth a scorner getteth to himself shame: and he that rebuketh a wicked man getteth himself a blot.', '2~03256~ 4~03887~ 5~03947~ 8~07036~: 12~03198~ 14~07563~ [15 16] 19~03971~.'),
  (6424, 6, 21, 36, 'And out of the tribe of Reuben, Bezer with her suburbs, and Jahazah with her suburbs,', '6~07205~, 7~01221~ 12~03096~'),
  (12256, 15, 9, 10, 'And now, O our God, what shall we say after this? for we have forsaken thy commandments,', '4~0430~, 8~0559~ 9~0310~ 14~05800~ 16~04687~,'),
  (993, 1, 34, 8, 'And Hamor communed with them, saying, The soul of my son Shechem longeth for your daughter: I pray you give her him to wife.', '1~02544~ 2~01696~ 5~0559~, 7~05315~ 10~01121~ 11~07927~ 12~02836~ 15~01323~: 19~05414~ 23~0802~.'),
  (20825, 26, 16, 54, 'That thou mayest bear thine own shame, and mayest be confounded in all that thou hast done, in that thou art a comfort unto them.', '3~05375~ 6~03639~, 10~03637~ 16~06213~, 22~05162~'),
  (24169, 40, 27, 30, 'And they spit upon him, and took the reed, and smote him on the head.', '0~2532~ 2~1716~ 3~1519~ 4~846~, 6~2983~ 8~2563~, 9~2532~ 10~5180~ 11~846~ 12~1519~ 14~2776~.'),
  (12552, 16, 9, 32, 'Now therefore, our God, the great, the mighty, and the terrible God, who keepest covenant and mercy, let not all the trouble seem little before thee, that hath come upon us, on our kings, on our princes, and on our priests, and on our prophets, and on our fathers, and on all thy people, since the time of the kings of Assyria unto this day.', '3~0430~, 5~01419~, 7~01368~, 10~03372~ 11~0410~, 13~08104~ 14~01285~ 16~02617~, 21~08513~ 23~04591~ 24~06440~ 28~04672~ 33~04428~, 36~08269~, 40~03548~, 44~05030~, 48~01~, 53~05971~, 56~03117~ 59~04428~ 61~0804~ 64~03117~.'),
  (14220, 19, 22, 7, 'All they that see me laugh me to scorn: they shoot out the lip, they shake the head, saying,', '3~07200~ 8~03932~: 11~06358~ 13~08193~, 15~05128~ 17~07218~, [18]');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (14955, 19, 69, 11, 'I made sackcloth also my garment; and I became a proverb to them.', '1~05414~ 2~08242~ 5~03830~; 10~04912~'),
  (24460, 41, 6, 43, 'And they took up twelve baskets full of the fragments, and of the fishes.', '0~2532~ 3~142~ 4~1427~ 5~2894~ 6~4134~ 9~2801~, 10~2532~ 11~575~ 13~2486~.'),
  (28412, 46, 2, 2, 'For I determined not to know any thing among you, save Jesus Christ, and him crucified.', '0~1063~ 2~2919~ 3~3756~ 5~1492~ 7~5100~ 8~1722~ 9~5213~, 10~1508~ 11~2424~ 12~5547~, 13~2532~ 14~5126~ 15~4717~.'),
  (2496, 2, 33, 18, 'And he said, I beseech thee, shew me thy glory.', '2~0559~, 5~04994~, 6~07200~ 9~03519~.'),
  (9477, 11, 21, 18, 'Arise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, which is in Samaria: behold, he is in the vineyard of Naboth, whither he is gone down to possess it.', '0~06965~, 2~03381~ 4~07125~ 5~0256~ 6~04428~ 8~03478~, [10] 12~08111~: [14 15] 18~03754~ 20~05022~, 25~03381~ 27~03423~'),
  (3462, 3, 24, 11, 'And the Israelitish woman''s son blasphemed the name of the LORD, and cursed. And they brought him unto Moses: (and his mother''s name was Shelomith, the daughter of Dibri, of the tribe of Dan:)', '2~03482~ 3~0802~ 4~01121~ 5~05344~ 7~08034~ [8 10] 12~07043~. 15~0935~ 18~04872~: 21~0517~ 22~08034~ [23] 24~08019~, 26~01323~ 28~01704~, 31~04294~ 33~01835~:)'),
  (23891, 40, 22, 9, 'Go ye therefore into the highways, and as many as ye shall find, bid to the marriage.', '1~4198~ 2~3767~ 3~1909~ 5~3598~ 6~1327~,* 7~2532~ 10~302~ 11~3745~ 13~2147~, 14~2564~ 15~1519~ 17~1062~.'),
  (17128, 20, 25, 6, 'Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great men:', '&para; 2~01921~ 6~06440~ 9~04428~, 11~05975~ 15~04725~ 17~01419~ [18]'),
  (8657, 10, 22, 47, 'The LORD liveth; and blessed be my rock; and exalted be the God of the rock of my salvation.', '1~03068~ 2~02416~; 4~01288~ [5] 7~06697~; 9~07311~ 12~0430~ 15~06697~ 18~03468~.'),
  (20862, 26, 18, 4, 'Behold, all souls are mine; as the soul of the father, so also the soul of the son is mine: the soul that sinneth, it shall die.', '2~05315~ 7~05315~ 10~01~, 14~05315~ 17~01121~ 21~05315~ 23~02398~, 26~04191~.'),
  (3606, 3, 27, 31, 'And if a man will at all redeem ought of his tithes, he shall add thereto the fifth part thereof.', '3~0376~ 6~01350~ 7~01350~ [8] 11~04643~, 14~03254~ 17~02549~ [18]'),
  (9626, 12, 4, 15, 'And he said, Call her. And when he had called her, she stood in the door.', '2~0559~, 3~07121~ 9~07121~ 12~05975~ 15~06607~.'),
  (7202, 8, 4, 5, 'Then said Boaz, What day thou buyest the field of the hand of Naomi, thou must buy it also of Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of the dead, to raise up the name of the dead upon his inheritance.', '1~0559~ 2~01162~, 4~03117~ 6~07069~ 8~07704~ 11~03027~ 13~05281~, 16~07069~ [17] 20~07327~ 22~04125~, 24~0802~ 27~04191~, 30~06965~ 32~08034~ 35~04191~ 38~05159~.'),
  (9685, 12, 6, 3, 'And one said, Be content, I pray thee, and go with thy servants. And he answered, I will go.', '1~0259~ 2~0559~, 4~02974~, 9~03212~ 12~05650~. 15~0559~, 18~03212~.'),
  (23547, 40, 12, 48, 'But he answered and said unto him that told him, Who is my mother? and who are my brethren?', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 8~2036~ 9~846~, 10~5101~ 11~2076~ 12~3450~ 13~3384~? 14~2532~ 15~5101~ 16~1526~ 17~3450~ 18~80~?'),
  (16667, 20, 10, 2, 'Treasures of wickedness profit nothing: but righteousness delivereth from death.', '&para; 0~0214~ 2~07562~ 3~03276~ 6~06666~ 7~05337~ 9~04194~.'),
  (28783, 46, 15, 49, 'And as we have borne the image of the earthy, we shall also bear the image of the heavenly.', '0~2532~ 1~2531~ 4~5409~ 6~1504~ 9~5517~, 11~5409~ 12~2532~ 13~5409~ 15~1504~ 18~2032~.'),
  (17556, 22, 1, 10, 'Thy cheeks are comely with rows of jewels, thy neck with chains of gold.', '1~03895~ 3~04998~ 5~08447~ [6 7] 9~06677~ 11~02737~ [12 13]'),
  (27792, 44, 24, 7, 'But the chief captain Lysias came upon us, and with great violence took him away out of our hands,', '0~1161~ 3~5506~ 4~3079~ 5~3928~ [6 7] 9~3326~ 10~4183~ 11~970~ [13] 14~520~ 16~1537~ 17~2257~ 18~5495~,'),
  (12892, 18, 1, 14, 'And there came a messenger unto Job, and said, The oxen were plowing, and the asses feeding beside them:', '2~0935~ 4~04397~ 6~0347~, 8~0559~, 10~01241~ 12~02790~, 15~0860~ 16~07462~ 17~03027~'),
  (5588, 5, 26, 16, 'This day the LORD thy God hath commanded thee to do these statutes and judgments: thou shalt therefore keep and do them with all thine heart, and with all thy soul.', '&para; 1~03117~ 3~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~06680~ 10~06213~ 12~02706~ 14~04941~: 18~08104~ 20~06213~ 25~03824~, 30~05315~.'),
  (19490, 24, 22, 27, 'But to the land whereunto they desire to return, thither shall they not return.', '3~0776~ 6~05375~ 8~07725~, 13~07725~.'),
  (1624, 2, 4, 18, 'And Moses went and returned to Jethro his father in law, and said unto him, Let me go, I pray thee, and return unto my brethren which are in Egypt, and see whether they be yet alive. And Jethro said to Moses, Go in peace.', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~03212~ 4~07725~ 6~03500~ 10~02859~, 12~0559~ 17~03212~, 22~07725~ 25~0251~ [27] 29~04714~, 31~07200~ 35~05750~ 36~02416~. 38~03503~ 39~0559~ 41~04872~, 42~03212~ 44~07965~.'),
  (24526, 41, 8, 15, 'And he charged them, saying, Take heed, beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, and of the leaven of Herod.', '0~2532~ 2~1291~ 3~846~, 4~3004~, 6~3708~, 7~991~ 8~575~ 10~2219~ 13~5330~, 14~2532~ [15] 17~2219~ 19~2264~.'),
  (2622, 2, 37, 13, 'And he cast for it four rings of gold, and put the rings upon the four corners that were in the four feet thereof.', '2~03332~ 5~0702~ 6~02885~ 8~02091~, 10~05414~ 12~02885~ 15~0702~ 16~06285~ [18] 21~0702~ 22~07272~'),
  (17462, 21, 7, 24, 'That which is far off, and exceeding deep, who can find it out?', '4~07350~, 7~06013~, 12~04672~?'),
  (9779, 12, 9, 15, 'But king Joram was returned to be healed in Jezreel of the wounds which the Syrians had given him, when he fought with Hazael king of Syria.) And Jehu said, If it be your minds, then let none go forth nor escape out of the city to go to tell it in Jezreel.', '1~04428~ 2~03088~ 4~07725~ 7~07495~ 9~03157~ 12~04347~ 15~0761~ 17~05221~ 21~03898~ 23~02371~ 24~04428~ 26~0758~) 28~03058~ 29~0559~, 32~03426~ 34~05315~, [35] 37~0408~ 39~03318~ [40] 41~06412~ 45~05892~ 47~03212~ 49~05046~ [50] 52~03157~.'),
  (14854, 19, 63, 6, 'When I remember thee upon my bed, and meditate on thee in the night watches.', '2~02142~ 6~03326~, [7] 8~01897~ [13] 14~0821~.'),
  (2478, 2, 32, 35, 'And the LORD plagued the people, because they made the calf, which Aaron made.', '2~03068~ 3~05062~ 5~05971~, 6~0834~ 8~06213~ 10~05695~, 11~0834~ 12~0175~ 13~06213~.'),
