  (30641, 62, 5, 1, 'Whosoever believeth that Jesus is the Christ is born of God: and every one that loveth him that begat loveth him also that is begotten of him.', '&para; 0~3956~ 1~4100~ 2~3754~ 3~2424~ 4~2076~ 6~5547~ 8~1080~ 9~1537~ 10~2316~: 11~2532~ 13~3956~ 15~25~ 18~1080~ 19~25~ 21~2532~ 24~1080~ 25~1537~ 26~846~.'),
  (4383, 4, 22, 3, 'And Moab was sore afraid of the people, because they were many: and Moab was distressed because of the children of Israel.', '1~04124~ 3~03966~ 4~01481~ 5~06440~ 7~05971~, [10] 11~07227~: 13~04124~ 15~06973~ 17~06440~ 19~01121~ 21~03478~.'),
  (12520, 16, 8, 18, 'Also day by day, from the first day unto the last day, he read in the book of the law of God. And they kept the feast seven days; and on the eighth day was a solemn assembly, according unto the manner.', '1~03117~ 3~03117~, 6~07223~ 7~03117~ 10~0314~ 11~03117~, 13~07121~ 16~05612~ 19~08451~ 21~0430~. 24~06213~ 26~02282~ 27~07651~ 28~03117~; 32~08066~ 33~03117~ [34] 37~06116~, 41~04941~.'),
  (2451, 2, 32, 8, 'They have turned aside quickly out of the way which I commanded them: they have made them a molten calf, and have worshipped it, and have sacrificed thereunto, and said, These be thy gods, O Israel, which have brought thee up out of the land of Egypt.', '2~05493~ 4~04118~ 8~01870~ 11~06680~ 15~06213~ 18~04541~ 19~05695~, 22~07812~ 26~02076~ 29~0559~, [31] 33~0430~, 35~03478~, 40~05927~ 44~0776~ 46~04714~.'),
  (12400, 16, 5, 9, 'Also I said, It is not good that ye do: ought ye not to walk in the fear of our God because of the reproach of the heathen our enemies?', '2~0559~, [4] 6~02896~ 7~01697~ 9~06213~: 14~03212~ 17~03374~ 20~0430~ 24~02781~ 27~01471~ 29~0341~?'),
  (25068, 42, 3, 31, 'Which was the son of Melea, which was the son of Menan, which was the son of Mattatha, which was the son of Nathan, which was the son of David,', '[2 3] 5~3190~, [8 9] 11~3104~, [14 15] 17~3160~, [20 21] 23~3481~, [26 27] 29~1138~,'),
  (18620, 23, 47, 12, 'Stand now with thine enchantments, and with the multitude of thy sorceries, wherein thou hast laboured from thy youth; if so be thou shalt be able to profit, if so be thou mayest prevail.', '0~05975~ 4~02267~, 8~07230~ 11~03785~, 12~0834~ 15~03021~ 18~05271~; 25~03201~ 27~03276~, 33~06206~.'),
  (29269, 49, 3, 2, 'If ye have heard of the dispensation of the grace of God which is given me to you-ward:', '0~1489~ 3~191~ 6~3622~ 9~5485~ 11~2316~ 12~3588~ 14~1325~ 15~3427~ 16~1519~ 17~5209~:'),
  (8739, 11, 1, 14, 'Behold, while thou yet talkest there with the king, I also will come in after thee, and confirm thy words.', '4~01696~ 8~04428~, 13~0935~ 14~0310~ 17~04390~ 19~01697~.'),
  (20383, 25, 3, 20, 'My soul hath them still in remembrance, and is humbled in me.', '1~05315~ [3] 4~02142~ 6~02142~, 9~07743~'),
  (14923, 19, 68, 14, 'When the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was white as snow in Salmon.', '2~07706~ 3~06566~ 4~04428~ [9] 11~07949~ 13~06756~.'),
  (2199, 2, 24, 17, 'And the sight of the glory of the LORD was like devouring fire on the top of the mount in the eyes of the children of Israel.', '2~04758~ 5~03519~ 8~03068~ [9] 11~0398~ 12~0784~ 15~07218~ 18~02022~ 21~05869~ 24~01121~ 26~03478~.'),
  (10557, 13, 7, 14, 'The sons of Manasseh; Ashriel, whom she bare: (but his concubine the Aramitess bare Machir the father of Gilead:', '1~01121~ 3~04519~; 4~0844~, 7~03205~: [8] 10~06370~ 12~0761~ 13~03205~ 14~04353~ 16~01~ 18~01568~:'),
  (30071, 58, 6, 11, 'And we desire that every one of you do shew the same diligence to the full assurance of hope unto the end:', '0~1161~ 2~1937~ 5~1538~ 7~5216~ 9~1731~ 11~846~ 12~4710~ 13~4314~ 16~4136~ 18~1680~ 19~891~ 21~5056~:'),
  (15354, 19, 89, 19, 'Then thou spakest in vision to thy holy one, and saidst, I have laid help upon one that is mighty; I have exalted one chosen out of the people.', '&para; 2~01696~ 4~02377~ 8~02623~, 10~0559~, 13~07737~ 14~05828~ [16 18] 19~01368~; 22~07311~ [23] 24~0977~ 28~05971~.'),
  (19538, 24, 24, 5, 'Thus saith the LORD, the God of Israel; Like these good figs, so will I acknowledge them that are carried away captive of Judah, whom I have sent out of this place into the land of the Chaldeans for their good.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~0430~ 7~03478~; 10~02896~ 11~08384~, 15~05234~ 21~01546~ 23~03063~, 27~07971~ 31~04725~ 34~0776~ 37~03778~ [39] 40~02896~.'),
  (9035, 11, 8, 42, '(For they shall hear of thy great name, and of thy strong hand, and of thy stretched out arm;) when he shall come and pray toward this house;', '3~08085~ 6~01419~ 7~08034~, 11~02389~ 12~03027~, 17~05186~ 18~02220~;) 22~0935~ 24~06419~ 27~01004~;'),
  (8859, 11, 4, 7, 'And Solomon had twelve officers over all Israel, which provided victuals for the king and his household: each man his month in a year made provision.', '1~08010~ 3~06240~ 4~08147~* 5~05324~ 8~03478~, 11~03557~ 14~04428~ 17~01004~: 19~0259~ 21~02320~ 24~08141~ 26~03557~.'),
  (10787, 13, 14, 5, 'And Ibhar, and Elishua, and Elpalet,', '1~02984~, 3~0474~, 5~0467~,'),
  (18927, 23, 65, 21, 'And they shall build houses, and inhabit them; and they shall plant vineyards, and eat the fruit of them.', '3~01129~ 4~01004~, 6~03427~ [7] 11~05193~ 12~03754~, 14~0398~ 16~06529~'),
  (19602, 24, 26, 21, 'And when Jehoiakim the king, with all his mighty men, and all the princes, heard his words, the king sought to put him to death: but when Urijah heard it, he was afraid, and fled, and went into Egypt;', '2~03079~ 4~04428~, 9~01368~, 13~08269~, 14~08085~ 16~01697~, 18~04428~ 19~01245~ 24~04191~: 27~0223~ 28~08085~ 32~03372~, 34~01272~, 36~0935~ 38~04714~;'),
  (28441, 46, 3, 15, 'If any man''s work shall be burned, he shall suffer loss: but he himself shall be saved; yet so as by fire.', '2~1536~ 3~2041~ 6~2618~, 10~2210~: 11~1161~ 13~846~ 16~4982~; 17~1161~ 18~3779~ 19~5613~ 20~1223~ 21~4442~.'),
  (24854, 41, 15, 17, 'And they clothed him with purple, and platted a crown of thorns, and put it about his head,', '0~2532~ 2~1746~ 3~846~ 5~4209~, 6~2532~ 7~4120~ 9~4735~ 11~174~, 15~4060~ 16~846~ [17]'),
  (4634, 4, 29, 20, 'And on the third day eleven bullocks, two rams, fourteen lambs of the first year without blemish;', '3~07992~ 4~03117~ 5~06240~ 6~06249~* 7~06499~, 8~08147~ 9~0352~, 10~06240~ 11~0702~* 12~03532~ 15~01121~ 16~08141~ 18~08549~;'),
  (8299, 10, 12, 6, 'And he shall restore the lamb fourfold, because he did this thing, and because he had no pity.', '3~07999~ 5~03535~ 6~0706~, 7~06118~ 9~06213~ 11~01697~, 13~0834~ 17~02550~.'),
  (560, 1, 22, 9, 'And they came to the place which God had told him of; and Abraham built an altar there, and laid the wood in order, and bound Isaac his son, and laid him on the altar upon the wood.', '2~0935~ 5~04725~ 7~0430~ 9~0559~ 13~085~ 14~01129~ 16~04196~ 19~06186~ 21~06086~ 23~06186~, 25~06123~ 26~03327~ 28~01121~, 30~07760~ 34~04196~ 35~04605~ 37~06086~.'),
  (1977, 2, 16, 25, 'And Moses said, Eat that to day; for to day is a sabbath unto the LORD: to day ye shall not find it in the field.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~, 3~0398~ 6~03117~; 9~03117~ [10] 12~07676~ 15~03068~: 17~03117~ 21~04672~ 25~07704~.'),
  (23629, 40, 14, 22, 'And straightway Jesus constrained his disciples to get into a ship, and to go before him unto the other side, while he sent the multitudes away.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2112~ 2~2424~ 3~315~ 4~846~ 5~3101~ 7~1684~ 8~1519~ 10~4143~, 11~2532~ 14~4254~ 15~846~ 16~1519~ 19~4008~, 20~3739~ 21~2193~ 22~630~ 24~3793~ 25~630~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (20922, 26, 20, 18, 'But I said unto their children in the wilderness, Walk ye not in the statutes of your fathers, neither observe their judgments, nor defile yourselves with their idols:', '2~0559~ 5~01121~ 8~04057~, 9~03212~ 14~02706~ 17~01~, 19~08104~ 21~04941~, 23~02930~ 27~01544~:'),
  (2875, 3, 6, 21, 'In a pan it shall be made with oil; and when it is baken, thou shalt bring it in: and the baken pieces of the meat offering shalt thou offer for a sweet savour unto the LORD.', '2~04227~ 6~06213~ 8~08081~; [9 12] 13~07246~, 16~0935~ [19] 21~08601~ 22~06595~ 26~04503~ 29~07126~ [30] 32~05207~ 33~07381~ 36~03068~.'),
  (15413, 19, 91, 9, 'Because thou hast made the LORD, which is my refuge, even the most High, thy habitation;', '&para; 3~07760~ 5~03068~, [6 7] 9~04268~, [10] 13~05945~, 15~04583~;'),
  (6376, 6, 19, 48, 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Dan according to their families, these cities with their villages.', '[1] 3~05159~ 6~04294~ 9~01121~ 11~01835~ 15~04940~, 17~05892~ 20~02691~.'),
  (17038, 20, 22, 14, 'The mouth of strange women is a deep pit: he that is abhorred of the LORD shall fall therein.', '&para; 1~06310~ 4~02114~ [5] 7~06013~ 8~07745~: 12~02194~ 15~03068~ 17~05307~'),
  (13385, 18, 21, 21, 'For what pleasure hath he in his house after him, when the number of his months is cut off in the midst?', '2~02656~ [3] 7~01004~ 8~0310~ 12~04557~ 15~02320~ 21~02686~?'),
  (25132, 42, 5, 13, 'And he put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, I will: be thou clean. And immediately the leprosy departed from him.', '0~2532~ 3~1614~ [4] 5~5495~, 7~680~ 8~846~, 9~2036~, 11~2309~: 14~2511~. 15~2532~ 16~2112~ 18~3014~ 19~565~ 20~575~ 21~846~.'),
  (13796, 18, 37, 18, 'Hast thou with him spread out the sky, which is strong, and as a molten looking glass?', '5~07554~ 7~07834~, [8 9] 10~02389~, [11] 14~03332~ 16~07209~?'),
  (29719, 54, 1, 7, 'Desiring to be teachers of the law; understanding neither what they say, nor whereof they affirm.', '0~2309~ 2~1511~ 6~3547~ 7~3361~;* 8~3539~ 9~3383~ 10~3739~ 12~3004~, 13~3383~ 14~5101~ 15~4012~ 16~1226~.'),
  (16603, 20, 7, 19, 'For the goodman is not at home, he is gone a long journey:', '2~0376~ [3] 6~01004~, 9~01980~ 11~07350~ 12~01870~:'),
  (10510, 13, 6, 48, 'Their brethren also the Levites were appointed unto all manner of service of the tabernacle of the house of God.', '1~0251~ 4~03881~ [5] 6~05414~ 11~05656~ 14~04908~ 17~01004~ 19~0430~.'),
  (12923, 18, 3, 10, 'Because it shut not up the doors of my mother''s womb, nor hid sorrow from mine eyes.', '4~05462~ 6~01817~ [9] 10~0990~, 12~05641~ 13~05999~ 16~05869~.'),
  (3887, 4, 7, 32, 'One golden spoon of ten shekels, full of incense:', '0~0259~ 1~02091~ 2~03709~ 4~06235~ [5] 6~04392~ 8~07004~:'),
  (17648, 22, 7, 12, 'Let us get up early to the vineyards; let us see if the vine flourish, whether the tender grape appear, and the pomegranates bud forth: there will I give thee my loves.', '4~07925~ 7~03754~; 10~07200~ 13~01612~ 14~06524~, [15] 18~05563~ 19~06605~, [20] 22~07416~ 24~05132~: 28~05414~ 31~01730~.'),
  (20717, 26, 12, 28, 'Therefore say unto them, Thus saith the Lord GOD; There shall none of my words be prolonged any more, but the word which I have spoken shall be done, saith the Lord GOD.', '1~0559~ 5~0559~ 7~0136~ 8~03069~; 14~01697~ 16~04900~ 21~01697~ 25~01696~ 28~06213~, 29~05002~ 31~0136~ 32~03069~.'),
  (1013, 1, 34, 28, 'They took their sheep, and their oxen, and their asses, and that which was in the city, and that which was in the field,', '1~03947~ 3~06629~, 6~01241~, 9~02543~, [13] 16~05892~, [20] 23~07704~,'),
  (14937, 19, 68, 28, 'Thy God hath commanded thy strength: strengthen, O God, that which thou hast wrought for us.', '1~0430~ 3~06680~ 5~05797~: 6~05810~, 8~0430~, 10~02098~ 13~06466~'),
  (2019, 2, 18, 15, 'And Moses said unto his father in law, Because the people come unto me to inquire of God:', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 7~02859~, 10~05971~ 11~0935~ 15~01875~ 17~0430~:'),
  (10883, 13, 17, 12, 'He shall build me an house, and I will stablish his throne for ever.', '2~01129~ 5~01004~, 9~03559~ 11~03678~ 12~05704~ 13~05769~.'),
  (29505, 51, 1, 24, 'Who now rejoice in my sufferings for you, and fill up that which is behind of the afflictions of Christ in my flesh for his body''s sake, which is the church:', '0~3739~ 1~3568~ 2~5463~ 3~1722~ 4~3450~ 5~3804~ 6~5228~ 7~5216~, 8~2532~ 10~466~ 14~5303~ 17~2347~ 19~5547~ 20~1722~ 21~3450~ 22~4561~ 23~5228~ 24~846~ 25~4983~ 26~5228~, 28~3603~ 30~1577~:'),
  (20032, 24, 44, 13, 'For I will punish them that dwell in the land of Egypt, as I have punished Jerusalem, by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence:', '3~06485~ 6~03427~ 9~0776~ 11~04714~, 15~06485~ 16~03389~, 19~02719~, 22~07458~, 26~01698~:'),
  (7432, 9, 10, 7, 'And let it be, when these signs are come unto thee, that thou do as occasion serve thee; for God is with thee.', '6~0226~ 8~0935~ [11] 13~06213~ 15~04672~ 16~03027~ 19~0430~ [20]'),
  (27993, 45, 2, 15, 'Which shew the work of the law written in their hearts, their conscience also bearing witness, and their thoughts the mean while accusing or else excusing one another;)', '0~3748~ 1~1731~ 3~2041~ 6~3551~ 7~1123~ 8~1722~ 9~846~ 10~2588~, 11~846~ 12~4893~ 15~4828~, 16~2532~ [17] 18~3053~ 22~2723~ 23~2228~ 24~2532~ 25~626~ 27~240~ 28~3342~;)*'),
  (19769, 24, 32, 29, 'And the Chaldeans, that fight against this city, shall come and set fire on this city, and burn it with the houses, upon whose roofs they have offered incense unto Baal, and poured out drink offerings unto other gods, to provoke me to anger.', '2~03778~, 4~03898~ 7~05892~, 9~0935~ 11~03341~ 12~0784~ 15~05892~, 17~08313~ 21~01004~, 24~01406~ 28~06999~ 30~01168~, 33~05258~ 35~05262~ 37~0312~ 38~0430~, 43~03707~.'),
  (2553, 2, 35, 17, 'The hangings of the court, his pillars, and their sockets, and the hanging for the door of the court,', '1~07050~ 4~02691~, 6~05982~, 9~0134~, 12~04539~ 15~08179~ 18~02691~,'),
  (23496, 40, 11, 27, 'All things are delivered unto me of my Father: and no man knoweth the Son, but the Father; neither knoweth any man the Father, save the Son, and he to whomsoever the Son will reveal him.', '1~3956~ 3~3860~ 5~3427~ 6~5259~ 7~3450~ 8~3962~: 9~2532~ 11~3762~ 12~1921~ 14~5207~, 15~1508~ 17~3962~; 18~3761~ 19~1921~ 21~5100~ 23~3962~, 24~1508~ 26~5207~, [28] 28~2532~ 29~3739~ 30~1437~ 32~5207~ 33~1014~ 34~601~ [35]'),
  (29454, 50, 3, 17, 'Brethren, be followers together of me, and mark them which walk so as ye have us for an ensample.', '&para; 0~80~, 1~1096~ 3~4831~ 5~3450~, 6~2532~ 7~4648~ 10~4043~ 11~3779~ 12~2531~ 14~2192~ 15~2248~ 18~5179~.'),
  (15187, 19, 78, 65, 'Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.', '2~0136~ 3~03364~ 8~03463~, [9] 13~01368~ 15~07442~ 19~03196~.'),
  (14489, 19, 37, 30, 'The mouth of the righteous speaketh wisdom, and his tongue talketh of judgment.', '1~06310~ 4~06662~ 5~01897~ 6~02451~, 9~03956~ 10~01696~ 12~04941~.'),
  (22801, 36, 1, 5, 'And them that worship the host of heaven upon the housetops; and them that worship and that swear by the LORD, and that swear by Malcham;', '3~07812~ 5~06635~ 7~08064~ 10~01406~; 14~07812~ [15] 17~07650~ 20~03068~, 23~07650~ 25~04428~;'),
  (29207, 48, 6, 3, 'For if a man think himself to be something, when he is nothing, he deceiveth himself.', '0~1063~ 3~1536~ 5~1380~ 7~1511~ 8~5100~, 11~5607~ 12~3367~, 14~5422~ 15~1438~.'),
  (14519, 19, 38, 20, 'They also that render evil for good are mine adversaries; because I follow the thing that good is.', '3~07999~ 4~07451~ 6~02896~ 9~07853~; 12~07291~ [13 15] 16~02896~ [17]'),
  (15972, 19, 119, 65, 'TETH. Thou hast dealt well with thy servant, O LORD, according unto thy word.', '&para; 3~06213~ 4~02896~ 7~05650~, 9~03068~, 13~01697~.'),
  (23499, 40, 11, 30, 'For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.', '0~1063~ 1~3450~ 2~2218~ [3] 4~5543~, 5~2532~ 6~3450~ 7~5413~ 8~2076~ 9~1645~.'),
  (1374, 1, 45, 11, 'And there will I nourish thee; for yet there are five years of famine; lest thou, and thy household, and all that thou hast, come to poverty.', '4~03557~ [8 9] 10~02568~ 11~08141~ 13~07458~; 18~01004~, 26~03423~.'),
  (8466, 10, 17, 10, 'And he also that is valiant, whose heart is as the heart of a lion, shall utterly melt: for all Israel knoweth that thy father is a mighty man, and they which be with him are valiant men.', '[3 4] 5~02428~ 6~01121~,* 8~03820~ [9] 12~03820~ 15~0738~, 17~04549~ 18~04549~: 21~03478~ 22~03045~ 25~01~ [26] 29~01368~, [31] [33] [36] 37~02428~ 38~01121~.'),
  (27365, 44, 12, 12, 'And when he had considered the thing, he came to the house of Mary the mother of John, whose surname was Mark; where many were gathered together praying.', '0~5037~ 4~4894~ [5 6] 8~2064~ 9~1909~ 11~3614~ 13~3137~ 15~3384~ 17~2491~, 20~1941~ 21~3138~; 22~3757~ 23~2425~ 24~2258~ 26~4867~ 27~4336~ 28~2532~.*'),
  (22407, 30, 3, 3, 'Can two walk together, except they be agreed?', '1~08147~ 2~03212~ 3~03162~, 4~01115~ 7~03259~?'),
  (29706, 53, 3, 12, 'Now them that are such we command and exhort by our Lord Jesus Christ, that with quietness they work, and eat their own bread.', '0~1161~ 4~5108~ 6~3853~ 7~2532~ 8~3870~ 9~1223~ 10~2257~ 11~2962~ 12~2424~ 13~5547~, 14~2443~ 15~3326~ 16~2271~ 18~2038~, 20~2068~ 22~1438~ 23~740~.'),
  (12726, 17, 1, 15, 'What shall we do unto the queen Vashti according to law, because she hath not performed the commandment of the king Ahasuerus by the chamberlains?', '3~06213~ 6~04436~ 7~02060~ 10~01881~, 15~06213~ 17~03982~ 20~04428~ 21~0325~ 22~03027~ 24~05631~?'),
  (2061, 2, 20, 5, 'Thou shalt not bow down thyself to them, nor serve them: for I the LORD thy God am a jealous God, visiting the iniquity of the fathers upon the children unto the third and fourth generation of them that hate me;', '4~07812~ 9~05647~ 14~03068~ 16~0430~ [17] 19~07067~ 20~0410~, 21~06485~ 23~05771~ 26~01~ 29~01121~ 32~08029~ 34~07256~ [35] 39~08130~'),
  (12635, 16, 12, 2, 'Amariah, Malluch, Hattush,', '0~0568~, 1~04409~, 2~02407~,'),
  (17148, 20, 25, 26, 'A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a troubled fountain, and a corrupt spring.', '&para; 1~06662~ 4~04131~ 5~06440~ 7~07563~ [8 9] 11~07515~ 12~04599~, 15~07843~ 16~04726~.'),
  (23447, 40, 10, 20, 'For it is not ye that speak, but the Spirit of your Father which speaketh in you.', '0~1063~ 2~2075~ 3~3756~ 4~5210~ 6~2980~, 7~235~ 9~4151~ 11~5216~ 12~3962~ 13~3588~ 14~2980~ 15~1722~ 16~5213~.'),
  (3936, 4, 7, 81, 'One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:', '0~0259~ 1~01241~ 2~06499~, 3~0259~ 4~0352~, 5~0259~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~, 14~05930~:'),
  (25353, 42, 9, 40, 'And I besought thy disciples to cast him out; and they could not.', '0~2532~ 2~1189~ 3~4675~ 4~3101~ 5~2443~ 6~1544~ 7~846~ 8~1544~; 9~2532~ 11~1410~ 12~3756~.'),
  (7733, 9, 19, 20, 'And Saul sent messengers to take David: and when they saw the company of the prophets prophesying, and Samuel standing as appointed over them, the spirit of God was upon the messengers of Saul, and they also prophesied.', '1~07586~ 2~07971~ 3~04397~ 5~03947~ 6~01732~: 10~07200~ 12~03862~ 15~05030~ 16~05012~, 18~08050~ 19~05975~ [20] 21~05324~ 25~07307~ 27~0430~ 31~04397~ 33~07586~, 37~05012~.'),
  (320, 1, 12, 19, 'Why saidst thou, She is my sister? so I might have taken her to me to wife: now therefore behold thy wife, take her, and go thy way.', '2~0559~, [4] 6~0269~? 11~03947~ 16~0802~: 21~0802~, 22~03947~ [23] 27~03212~.'),
  (13053, 18, 8, 15, 'He shall lean upon his house, but it shall not stand: he shall hold it fast, but it shall not endure.', '2~08172~ 5~01004~, 10~05975~: 13~02388~ 20~06965~.'),
  (21419, 26, 37, 13, 'And ye shall know that I am the LORD, when I have opened your graves, O my people, and brought you up out of your graves,', '3~03045~ [6] 8~03068~, 12~06605~ 14~06913~, 17~05971~, 21~05927~ 25~06913~,'),
  (2097, 2, 21, 15, 'And he that smiteth his father, or his mother, shall be surely put to death.', '3~05221~ 5~01~, 8~0517~, 11~04191~ 14~04191~.'),
  (28465, 46, 4, 16, 'Wherefore I beseech you, be ye followers of me.', '0~3767~ 2~3870~ 3~5209~, 5~1096~ 6~3402~ 8~3450~.'),
  (27094, 44, 5, 19, 'But the angel of the Lord by night opened the prison doors, and brought them forth, and said,', '0~1161~ 2~32~ 5~2962~ 6~1223~ 7~3571~ 8~455~ 10~5438~ 11~2374~, 12~5037~ 13~1806~ 14~846~ 15~1806~, 17~2036~,'),
  (15276, 19, 84, 8, 'O LORD God of hosts, hear my prayer: give ear, O God of Jacob. Selah.', '&para; 1~03068~ 2~0430~ 4~06635~, 5~08085~ 7~08605~: 9~0238~, 11~0430~ 13~03290~. 14~05542~.'),
  (24112, 40, 26, 48, 'Now he that betrayed him gave them a sign, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he: hold him fast.', '0~1161~ 3~3860~ 4~846~ 5~1325~ 6~846~ 8~4592~, 9~3004~, 10~302~ 11~3739~ 13~5368~, 15~846~ 16~2076~ 17~846~: 18~2902~ 19~846~ 20~2902~.'),
  (12494, 16, 7, 65, 'And the Tirshatha said unto them, that they should not eat of the most holy things, till there stood up a priest with Urim and Thummim.', '2~08660~ 3~0559~ 10~0398~ 13~06944~ 15~06944~, 18~05975~ [19] 21~03548~ 23~0224~ 25~08550~.'),
  (28467, 46, 4, 18, 'Now some are puffed up, as though I would not come to you.', '0~1161~ 1~5100~ 4~5448~, 6~5613~ 7~3450~ 8~2064~ 9~3361~ 10~2064~ 11~4314~ 12~5209~.'),
  (1479, 1, 49, 1, 'And Jacob called unto his sons, and said, Gather yourselves together, that I may tell you that which shall befall you in the last days.', '&para; 1~03290~ 2~07121~ 5~01121~, 7~0559~, 10~0622~, 14~05046~ [16] 19~07122~ 23~0319~ 24~03117~.'),
  (21247, 26, 31, 8, 'The cedars in the garden of God could not hide him: the fir trees were not like his boughs, and the chestnut trees were not like his branches; nor any tree in the garden of God was like unto him in his beauty.', '1~0730~ 4~01588~ 6~0430~ 9~06004~ 13~01265~ 16~01819~ 18~05589~, 22~06196~ 27~06288~; 30~06086~ 33~01588~ 35~0430~ 37~01819~ 42~03308~.'),
  (7420, 9, 9, 22, 'And Samuel took Saul and his servant, and brought them into the parlour, and made them sit in the chiefest place among them that were bidden, which were about thirty persons.', '1~08050~ 2~03947~ 3~07586~ 6~05288~, 8~0935~ 12~03957~, 16~05414~ 19~07218~ 20~04725~ 25~07121~, [27] 29~07970~ 30~0376~.'),
  (21534, 26, 40, 48, 'And he brought me to the porch of the house, and measured each post of the porch, five cubits on this side, and five cubits on that side: and the breadth of the gate was three cubits on this side, and three cubits on that side.', '2~0935~ 6~0197~ 9~01004~, 11~04058~ [12] 13~0352~ 16~0197~, 17~02568~ 18~0520~ 23~02568~ 24~0520~ 30~07341~ 33~08179~ [34] 35~07969~ 36~0520~ 41~07969~ 42~0520~'),
  (22562, 32, 2, 5, 'The waters compassed me about, even to the soul: the depth closed me round about, the weeds were wrapped about my head.', '1~04325~ 4~0661~, [5] 8~05315~: 10~08415~ 14~05437~, 16~05488~ 19~02280~ 21~07218~.'),
  (8715, 10, 24, 15, 'So the LORD sent a pestilence upon Israel from the morning even to the time appointed: and there died of the people from Dan even to Beersheba seventy thousand men.', '2~03068~ 3~05414~ 5~01698~ 7~03478~ 10~01242~ 14~06256~ 15~04150~: 18~04191~ 21~05971~ 23~01835~ 26~0884~ 27~07657~ 28~0505~ 29~0376~.'),
  (2070, 2, 20, 14, 'Thou shalt not commit adultery.', '4~05003~.'),
  (10928, 13, 19, 13, 'Be of good courage, and let us behave ourselves valiantly for our people, and for the cities of our God: and let the LORD do that which is good in his sight.', '3~02388~, 9~02388~ 12~05971~, 16~05892~ 19~0430~: 23~03068~ 24~06213~ [25 27] 28~02896~ 31~05869~.'),
  (6684, 7, 6, 23, 'And the LORD said unto him, Peace be unto thee; fear not: thou shalt not die.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~07965~ [7] 10~03372~ 15~04191~.'),
  (18350, 23, 36, 11, 'Then said Eliakim and Shebna and Joah unto Rabshakeh, Speak, I pray thee, unto thy servants in the Syrian language; for we understand it; and speak not to us in the Jews'' language, in the ears of the people that are on the wall.', '&para; 1~0559~ 2~0471~ 4~07644~ 6~03098~ 8~07262~, 9~01696~, 15~05650~ 19~0762~; 22~08085~ [23] 25~01696~ 32~03066~, 35~0241~ 38~05971~ [40] 43~02346~.'),
  (20247, 24, 51, 26, 'And they shall not take of thee a stone for a corner, nor a stone for foundations; but thou shalt be desolate for ever, saith the LORD.', '4~03947~ 8~068~ 11~06438~, 14~068~ 16~04146~; 21~08077~ 23~05769~, 24~05002~ 26~03068~.'),
  (13529, 18, 28, 16, 'It cannot be valued with the gold of Ophir, with the precious onyx, or the sapphire.', '3~05541~ 6~03800~ 8~0211~, 11~03368~ 12~07718~, 15~05601~.'),
  (22420, 30, 4, 1, 'Hear this word, ye kine of Bashan, that are in the mountain of Samaria, which oppress the poor, which crush the needy, which say to their masters, Bring, and let us drink.', '&para; 0~08085~ 2~01697~, 4~06510~ 6~01316~, [8] 11~02022~ 13~08111~, 15~06231~ 17~01800~, 19~07533~ 21~034~, 23~0559~ 26~0113~, 27~0935~, 31~08354~.'),
  (1847, 2, 12, 26, 'And it shall come to pass, when your children shall say unto you, What mean ye by this service?', '8~01121~ 10~0559~ 18~05656~?'),
  (17612, 22, 5, 5, 'I rose up to open to my beloved; and my hands dropped with myrrh, and my fingers with sweet smelling myrrh, upon the handles of the lock.', '2~06965~ 4~06605~ 7~01730~; 10~03027~ 11~05197~ [12] 13~04753~, 16~0676~ [17] 19~05674~ 20~04753~, 23~03709~ 26~04514~.'),
  (4091, 4, 13, 11, 'Of the tribe of Joseph, namely, of the tribe of Manasseh, Gaddi the son of Susi.', '2~04294~ 4~03130~, [5] 8~04294~ 10~04519~, 11~01426~ 13~01121~ 15~05485~.'),
  (30760, 66, 2, 27, 'And he shall rule them with a rod of iron; as the vessels of a potter shall they be broken to shivers: even as I received of my Father.', '0~2532~ 3~4165~ 4~846~ 5~1722~ 7~4464~ 9~4603~; 10~5613~ 12~4632~ 15~2764~ 21~4937~: 22~2504~ 23~5613~ 24~2504~ 25~2983~ 26~3844~ 27~3450~ 28~3962~.'),
  (21162, 26, 27, 32, 'And in their wailing they shall take up a lamentation for thee, and lament over thee, saying, What city is like Tyrus, like the destroyed in the midst of the sea?', '3~05204~ 7~05375~ 9~07015~ 13~06969~ [16] [18 19] 21~06865~, 24~01822~ 27~08432~ 30~03220~?'),
  (1851, 2, 12, 30, 'And Pharaoh rose up in the night, he, and all his servants, and all the Egyptians; and there was a great cry in Egypt; for there was not a house where there was not one dead.', '1~06547~ 3~06965~ 6~03915~, 11~05650~, 15~04714~; 20~01419~ 21~06818~ 23~04714~; [25 26] 29~01004~ [31 32] 35~04191~.'),
  (25853, 42, 21, 13, 'And it shall turn to you for a testimony.', '0~1161~ 3~576~ 5~5213~ 6~1519~ 8~3142~.'),
  (9599, 12, 3, 15, 'But now bring me a minstrel. And it came to pass, when the minstrel played, that the hand of the LORD came upon him.', '2~03947~ 5~05059~. 13~05059~ 14~05059~, 17~03027~ 20~03068~'),
  (26222, 43, 4, 51, 'And as he was now going down, his servants met him, and told him, saying, Thy son liveth.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~2235~ 6~2597~, 7~846~ 8~1401~ 9~528~ 10~846~, 11~2532~ 12~518~ [13] 14~3004~ 15~3754~,* 16~4675~ 17~3816~ 18~2198~.'),
  (13534, 18, 28, 21, 'Seeing it is hid from the eyes of all living, and kept close from the fowls of the air.', '3~05956~ 6~05869~ 9~02416~, 12~05641~ 15~05775~ 18~08064~.'),
  (29919, 56, 1, 11, 'Whose mouths must be stopped, who subvert whole houses, teaching things which they ought not, for filthy lucre''s sake.', '0~3739~ 1~1993~ 2~1163~ 4~1993~, 5~3748~ 6~396~ 7~3650~ 8~3624~, 9~1321~ 11~3739~ 13~1163~ 14~3361~, 15~5484~ 16~150~ 17~2771~ 18~5484~.'),
  (2721, 2, 40, 9, 'And thou shalt take the anointing oil, and anoint the tabernacle, and all that is therein, and shalt hallow it, and all the vessels thereof: and it shall be holy.', '3~03947~ 5~04888~ 6~08081~, 8~04886~ 10~04908~, [14] 18~06942~ 23~03627~ 29~06944~.'),
  (23634, 40, 14, 27, 'But straightway Jesus spake unto them, saying, Be of good cheer; it is I; be not afraid.', '0~1161~ 1~2112~ 2~2424~ 3~2980~ 5~846~, 6~3004~, 10~2293~; 12~1510~ 13~1473~; 14~5399~ 15~3361~ 16~5399~.'),
  (26716, 43, 15, 2, 'Every branch in me that beareth not fruit he taketh away: and every branch that beareth fruit, he purgeth it, that it may bring forth more fruit.', '0~3956~ 1~2814~ 2~1722~ 3~1698~ 4~846~ 5~5342~ 6~3361~ 7~2590~ 10~142~: 11~2532~ 12~3956~ [13] 15~5342~ 16~2590~, 18~2508~ 19~846~, 20~2443~ 24~5342~ 25~4119~ 26~2590~.'),
  (16206, 19, 136, 1, 'O give thanks unto the LORD; for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.', '&para; 2~03034~ 5~03068~; [7 8] 9~02896~: 12~02617~ [13] 15~05769~.'),
  (30418, 60, 2, 3, 'If so be ye have tasted that the Lord is gracious.', '2~1512~ 5~1089~ 6~3754~ 8~2962~ [9] 10~5543~.'),
  (3240, 3, 16, 34, 'And this shall be an everlasting statute unto you, to make an atonement for the children of Israel for all their sins once a year. And he did as the LORD commanded Moses.', '5~05769~ 6~02708~ 12~03722~ 15~01121~ 17~03478~ 21~02403~ 22~0259~ 24~08141~. 27~06213~ 30~03068~ 31~06680~ 32~04872~.'),
  (1332, 1, 44, 3, 'As soon as the morning was light, the men were sent away, they and their asses.', '4~01242~ 6~0215~, 8~0582~ 11~07971~, 15~02543~.'),
  (16480, 20, 3, 16, 'Length of days is in her right hand; and in her left hand riches and honour.', '0~0753~ 2~03117~ [3] 7~03225~; [8] 12~08040~ 13~06239~ 15~03519~.'),
  (26966, 44, 2, 1, 'And when the day of Pentecost was fully come, they were all with one accord in one place.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~1722~ 3~2250~ 5~4005~ 8~4845~, 10~2258~ 11~537~ 14~3661~ 15~1909~ 17~846~.'),
  (16427, 20, 1, 18, 'And they lay wait for their own blood; they lurk privily for their own lives.', '3~0693~ [6] 7~01818~; 10~06845~ [13] 14~05315~.'),
  (23983, 40, 24, 16, 'Then let them which be in Judaea flee into the mountains:', '0~5119~ 5~1722~ 6~2449~ 7~5343~ 8~1909~ 10~3735~:'),
  (9751, 12, 8, 16, 'And in the fifth year of Joram the son of Ahab king of Israel, Jehoshaphat being then king of Judah, Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat king of Judah began to reign.', '&para; 3~02568~ 4~08141~ 6~03141~ 8~01121~ 10~0256~ 11~04428~ 13~03478~, 14~03092~ [15] 17~04428~ 19~03063~, 20~03088~ 22~01121~ 24~03092~ 25~04428~ 27~03063~ 30~04427~.'),
  (541, 1, 21, 24, 'And Abraham said, I will swear.', '1~085~ 2~0559~, 5~07650~.'),
  (19830, 24, 34, 20, 'I will even give them into the hand of their enemies, and into the hand of them that seek their life: and their dead bodies shall be for meat unto the fowls of the heaven, and to the beasts of the earth.', '3~05414~ 7~03027~ 10~0341~, 14~03027~ 18~01245~ 20~05315~: 24~05038~ 28~03978~ 31~05775~ 34~08064~, 38~0929~ 41~0776~.'),
  (1793, 2, 10, 11, 'Not so: go now ye that are men, and serve the LORD; for that ye did desire. And they were driven out from Pharaoh''s presence.', '2~03212~ [5 6] 7~01397~, 9~05647~ 11~03068~; 16~01245~. 21~01644~ 23~06547~ 24~06440~.'),
  (14682, 19, 50, 5, 'Gather my saints together unto me; those that have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.', '0~0622~ 2~02623~ 9~03772~ 11~01285~ 15~02077~.'),
  (6471, 6, 23, 4, 'Behold, I have divided unto you by lot these nations that remain, to be an inheritance for your tribes, from Jordan, with all the nations that I have cut off, even unto the great sea westward.', '0~07200~, 3~05307~ 9~01471~ 11~07604~, 15~05159~ 18~07626~, 20~03383~, 24~01471~ 29~03772~, 33~01419~ 34~03220~ 35~08121~ 36~03996~.*'),
  (13716, 18, 34, 24, 'He shall break in pieces mighty men without number, and set others in their stead.', '4~07489~ 6~03524~ 8~02714~, 10~05975~ 11~0312~'),
  (27615, 44, 19, 14, 'And there were seven sons of one Sceva, a Jew, and chief of the priests, which did so.', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 3~2033~ 4~5207~ [6] 7~5100~ 8~4630~,* 10~2453~, [11] 15~749~, 17~4160~ 18~5124~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (24693, 41, 12, 9, 'What shall therefore the lord of the vineyard do? he will come and destroy the husbandmen, and will give the vineyard unto others.', '0~5101~ 1~4160~ 2~3767~ 4~2962~ 7~290~ 8~4160~? 11~2064~ 12~2532~ 13~622~ 15~1092~, 16~2532~ 18~1325~ 20~290~ 22~243~.'),
  (30800, 66, 5, 5, 'And one of the elders saith unto me, Weep not: behold, the Lion of the tribe of Juda, the Root of David, hath prevailed to open the book, and to loose the seven seals thereof.', '0~2532~ 1~1520~ 2~1537~ 4~4245~ 5~3004~ 7~3427~, 8~2799~ 9~3361~: 10~2400~, 12~3023~ 13~5607~ 14~1537~* 16~5443~ 18~2455~, 20~4491~ 22~1138~, 24~3528~ 26~455~ 28~975~, 29~2532~ 31~3089~ 33~2033~ 34~4973~ 35~846~.'),
  (11580, 14, 18, 29, 'And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, I will disguise myself, and will go to the battle; but put thou on thy robes. So the king of Israel disguised himself; and they went to the battle.', '2~04428~ 4~03478~ 5~0559~ 7~03092~, 10~02664~ 14~0935~ 17~04421~; 19~03847~ 23~0899~. 26~04428~ 28~03478~ 29~02664~ 33~0935~ 36~04421~.'),
  (14971, 19, 69, 27, 'Add iniquity unto their iniquity: and let them not come into thy righteousness.', '0~05414~ 1~05771~ 4~05771~: 9~0935~ 12~06666~.'),
  (28658, 46, 12, 8, 'For to one is given by the Spirit the word of wisdom; to another the word of knowledge by the same Spirit;', '0~1063~ 2~3303~ 3~3739~ 4~1325~ 5~1223~ 7~4151~ 9~3056~ 11~4678~ 12~1161~;* 14~243~ 16~3056~ 18~1108~ 19~2596~ 21~846~ 22~4151~;'),
  (6026, 6, 8, 18, 'And the LORD said unto Joshua, Stretch out the spear that is in thy hand toward Ai; for I will give it into thine hand. And Joshua stretched out the spear that he had in his hand toward the city.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~03091~, 7~05186~ 9~03591~ [11] 14~03027~ 16~05857~; 20~05414~ 24~03027~. 26~03091~ 28~05186~ 30~03591~ [32 33] 36~03027~ 39~05892~.'),
  (12783, 17, 4, 12, 'And they told to Mordecai Esther''s words.', '2~05046~ 4~04782~ 5~0635~ 6~01697~.'),
  (21146, 26, 27, 16, 'Syria was thy merchant by reason of the multitude of the wares of thy making: they occupied in thy fairs with emeralds, purple, and broidered work, and fine linen, and coral, and agate.', '0~0758~ [1] 3~05503~ 8~07230~ 14~04639~: 16~05414~ 19~05801~ 21~05306~, 22~0713~, 25~07553~, 28~0948~, 30~07215~, 32~03539~.'),
  (9612, 12, 4, 1, 'Now there cried a certain woman of the wives of the sons of the prophets unto Elisha, saying, Thy servant my husband is dead; and thou knowest that thy servant did fear the LORD: and the creditor is come to take unto him my two sons to be bondmen.', '&para; 2~06817~ 4~0259~ 5~0802~ 8~0802~ 11~01121~ 14~05030~ 16~0477~, 17~0559~, 19~05650~ 21~0376~ 23~04191~; 26~03045~ 29~05650~ 31~03373~ 33~03068~: 36~05383~ 38~0935~ 40~03947~ 44~08147~ 45~03206~ 48~05650~.'),
  (4439, 4, 23, 18, 'And he took up his parable, and said, Rise up, Balak, and hear; hearken unto me, thou son of Zippor:', '3~05375~ 5~04912~, 7~0559~, 9~06965~, 10~01111~, 12~08085~; 13~0238~ 17~01121~ 19~06834~:'),
  (11259, 14, 4, 5, 'And the thickness of it was an handbreadth, and the brim of it like the work of the brim of a cup, with flowers of lilies; and it received and held three thousand baths.', '2~05672~ [5] 7~02947~, 10~08193~ 15~04639~ 18~08193~ 21~03563~, 23~06525~ 25~07799~; [26] 28~02388~ 30~03557~ 31~07969~ 32~0505~ 33~01324~.'),
  (24757, 41, 13, 29, 'So ye in like manner, when ye shall see these things come to pass, know that it is nigh, even at the doors.', '0~3779~ 1~5210~ 4~2532~, 5~3752~ 8~1492~ 10~5023~ 13~1096~, 14~1097~ 15~3754~ 17~2076~ 18~1451~, [19] 20~1909~ 22~2374~.'),
  (13856, 18, 39, 13, 'Gavest thou the goodly wings unto the peacocks? or wings and feathers unto the ostrich?', '&para; [0 1] 3~07443~ 4~03671~ 7~05965~? 9~084~ 11~02624~ 14~05133~?'),
  (25583, 42, 14, 17, 'And sent his servant at supper time to say to them that were bidden, Come; for all things are now ready.', '0~2532~ 1~649~ 2~846~ 3~1401~ 5~1173~ 6~5610~ 8~2036~ 13~2564~, 14~2064~; 15~3754~ 17~3956~ 18~2076~ 19~2235~ 20~2092~.'),
  (28607, 46, 10, 24, 'Let no man seek his own, but every man another''s wealth.', '0~2212~ 2~3367~ 3~2212~ 5~1438~, 6~235~ 8~1538~ 9~2087~ [10]'),
  (3761, 4, 4, 13, 'And they shall take away the ashes from the altar, and spread a purple cloth thereon:', '6~01878~ 9~04196~, 11~06566~ 13~0713~ 14~0899~'),
  (6565, 7, 2, 13, 'And they forsook the LORD, and served Baal and Ashtaroth.', '2~05800~ 4~03068~, 6~05647~ 7~01168~ 9~06252~.'),
  (4472, 4, 24, 21, 'And he looked on the Kenites, and took up his parable, and said, Strong is thy dwellingplace, and thou puttest thy nest in a rock.', '2~07200~ 5~07017~, 8~05375~ 10~04912~, 12~0559~, 13~0386~ 16~04186~, 19~07760~ 21~07064~ 24~05553~.'),
  (18373, 23, 37, 12, 'Have the gods of the nations delivered them which my fathers have destroyed, as Gozan, and Haran, and Rezeph, and the children of Eden which were in Telassar?', '2~0430~ 5~01471~ 6~05337~ 10~01~ 12~07843~, [13] 14~01470~, 16~02771~, 18~07530~, 21~01121~ 23~05729~ [25] 27~08515~?'),
  (12879, 18, 1, 1, 'There was a man in the land of Uz, whose name was Job; and that man was perfect and upright, and one that feared God, and eschewed evil.', '&para; 3~0376~ 6~0776~ 8~05780~, 10~08034~ [11] 12~0347~; 15~0376~ 17~08535~ 19~03477~, 23~03373~ 24~0430~, 26~05493~ 27~07451~.'),
  (27285, 44, 10, 10, 'And he became very hungry, and would have eaten: but while they made ready, he fell into a trance,', '0~1161~ 2~1096~ 4~4361~, 5~2532~ 6~2309~ 8~1089~: 9~1161~ 11~1565~ 13~3903~, 14~846~ 15~1968~ 16~1909~ 18~1611~,'),
  (4042, 4, 11, 13, 'Whence should I have flesh to give unto all this people? for they weep unto me, saying, Give us flesh, that we may eat.', '0~0370~ 4~01320~ 6~05414~ 10~05971~? 13~01058~ 16~0559~, 17~05414~ 19~01320~, 23~0398~.'),
  (14328, 19, 29, 11, 'The LORD will give strength unto his people; the LORD will bless his people with peace.', '1~03068~ 3~05414~ 4~05797~ 7~05971~; 9~03068~ 11~01288~ 13~05971~ 15~07965~.'),
  (11376, 14, 9, 4, 'And the meat of his table, and the sitting of his servants, and the attendance of his ministers, and their apparel; his cupbearers also, and their apparel; and his ascent by which he went up into the house of the LORD; there was no more spirit in her.', '2~03978~ 5~07979~, 8~04186~ 11~05650~, 14~04612~ 17~08334~, 20~04403~; 22~08248~ 26~04403~; 29~05944~ 34~05927~ 37~01004~ 40~03068~; 45~07307~'),
  (8384, 10, 14, 21, 'And the king said unto Joab, Behold now, I have done this thing: go therefore, bring the young man Absalom again.', '&para; 2~04428~ 3~0559~ 5~03097~, 10~06213~ 12~01697~: 13~03212~ 15~07725~ 18~05288~ 19~053~ 20~07725~.'),
  (29738, 54, 2, 6, 'Who gave himself a ransom for all, to be testified in due time.', '0~3588~ 1~1325~ 2~1438~ 4~487~ 5~5228~ 6~3956~, 9~3142~ 11~2398~ 12~2540~.'),
  (6201, 6, 14, 7, 'Forty years old was I when Moses the servant of the LORD sent me from Kadeshbarnea to espy out the land; and I brought him word again as it was in mine heart.', '0~0705~ 1~08141~ 2~01121~ [3] 6~04872~ 8~05650~ 11~03068~ 12~07971~ 15~06947~ 18~07270~ 20~0776~; 23~07725~ 25~01697~ 26~07725~ [28 29] 32~03824~.'),
  (24988, 42, 2, 3, 'And all went to be taxed, every one into his own city.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 2~4198~ 5~583~, 7~1538~ 8~1519~ 10~2398~ 11~4172~.'),
  (11378, 14, 9, 6, 'Howbeit I believed not their words, until I came, and mine eyes had seen it: and, behold, the one half of the greatness of thy wisdom was not told me: for thou exceedest the fame that I heard.', '2~0539~ 5~01697~, 8~0935~, 11~05869~ 13~07200~ [14] 19~02677~ 22~04768~ 25~02451~ 28~05046~ [30] 32~03254~ 34~08052~ 37~08085~.'),
  (3836, 4, 6, 8, 'All the days of his separation he is holy unto the LORD.', '2~03117~ 5~05145~ [7] 8~06918~ 11~03068~.'),
  (18986, 24, 2, 12, 'Be astonished, O ye heavens, at this, and be horribly afraid, be ye very desolate, saith the LORD.', '1~08074~, 4~08064~, 10~08175~, 13~03966~ 14~02717~, 15~05002~ 17~03068~.'),
  (2036, 2, 19, 5, 'Now therefore, if ye will obey my voice indeed, and keep my covenant, then ye shall be a peculiar treasure unto me above all people: for all the earth is mine:', '5~08085~ 7~06963~ 8~08085~, 10~08104~ 12~01285~, 19~05459~ 24~05971~: 28~0776~ [29]'),
  (4600, 4, 28, 17, 'And in the fifteenth day of this month is the feast: seven days shall unleavened bread be eaten.', '3~06240~ 4~02568~* 5~03117~ 8~02320~ [9] 11~02282~: 12~07651~ 13~03117~ 16~04682~ 18~0398~.'),
  (22759, 35, 2, 2, 'And the LORD answered me, and said, Write the vision, and make it plain upon tables, that he may run that readeth it.', '2~03068~ 3~06030~ 6~0559~, 7~03789~ 9~02377~, [12] 13~0874~ 15~03871~, 19~07323~ 21~07121~'),
  (16781, 20, 13, 25, 'The righteous eateth to the satisfying of his soul: but the belly of the wicked shall want.', '&para; 1~06662~ 2~0398~ 5~07648~ 8~05315~: 11~0990~ 14~07563~ 16~02637~.'),
  (24029, 40, 25, 11, 'Afterward came also the other virgins, saying, Lord, Lord, open to us.', '0~5305~ 1~1161~* 2~2064~ 3~2532~ 5~3062~ 6~3933~, 7~3004~, 8~2962~, 9~2962~, 10~455~ 12~2254~.'),
  (18140, 23, 26, 1, 'In that day shall this song be sung in the land of Judah; We have a strong city; salvation will God appoint for walls and bulwarks.', '&para; 2~03117~ 5~07892~ 7~07891~ 10~0776~ 12~03063~; 16~05797~ 17~05892~; 18~03444~ [20] 21~07896~ [22] 23~02346~ 25~02426~.'),
  (1710, 2, 7, 20, 'And Moses and Aaron did so, as the LORD commanded; and he lifted up the rod, and smote the waters that were in the river, in the sight of Pharaoh, and in the sight of his servants; and all the waters that were in the river were turned to blood.', '1~04872~ 3~0175~ 4~06213~ 8~03068~ 9~06680~; 13~07311~ 15~04294~, 17~05221~ 19~04325~ [21] 24~02975~, 27~05869~ 29~06547~, 33~05869~ 36~05650~; 40~04325~ [42] 45~02975~ 47~02015~ 49~01818~.'),
  (3005, 3, 11, 3, 'Whatsoever parteth the hoof, and is clovenfooted, and cheweth the cud, among the beasts, that shall ye eat.', '1~06536~ 3~06541~, 6~08156~ 7~08157~,* [8] 9~05927~ 11~01625~, 14~0929~, 18~0398~.'),
  (31074, 66, 21, 5, 'And he that sat upon the throne said, Behold, I make all things new. And he said unto me, Write: for these words are true and faithful.', '0~2532~ 3~2521~ 4~1909~ 6~2362~ 7~2036~, 8~2400~, 10~4160~ 12~3956~ 13~2537~. 14~2532~ 16~3004~ 18~3427~, 19~1125~: 20~3754~ 21~3778~ 22~3056~ 23~1526~ 24~228~ 25~2532~ 26~4103~.'),
  (10678, 13, 10, 11, 'And when all Jabeshgilead heard all that the Philistines had done to Saul,', '3~01568~ 4~03003~* 5~08085~ 9~06430~ 11~06213~ 13~07586~,'),
  (1879, 2, 13, 7, 'Unleavened bread shall be eaten seven days; and there shall no leavened bread be seen with thee, neither shall there be leaven seen with thee in all thy quarters.', '1~04682~ 4~0398~ 5~07651~ 6~03117~; 12~02557~ 14~07200~ 21~07603~ 22~07200~ 28~01366~.'),
  (12350, 16, 3, 14, 'But the dung gate repaired Malchiah the son of Rechab, the ruler of part of Bethhaccerem; he built it, and set up the doors thereof, the locks thereof, and the bars thereof.', '2~0830~ 3~08179~ 4~02388~ 5~04441~ 7~01121~ 9~07394~, 11~08269~ 13~06418~ 15~01021~; 17~01129~ 21~05975~ 23~01817~ 26~04514~ 30~01280~'),
  (1111, 1, 37, 23, 'And it came to pass, when Joseph was come unto his brethren, that they stripped Joseph out of his coat, his coat of many colours that was on him;', '&para; 6~03130~ 8~0935~ 11~0251~, 14~06584~ 15~0853~* 16~03130~ 18~0854~ 20~03801~, [21] 22~03801~ [24] 25~06446~ [27]'),
  (18540, 23, 43, 26, 'Put me in remembrance: let us plead together: declare thou, that thou mayest be justified.', '3~02142~: 6~08199~ 7~03162~: 8~05608~ 14~06663~.'),
  (5953, 6, 5, 13, 'And it came to pass, when Joshua was by Jericho, that he lifted up his eyes and looked, and, behold, there stood a man over against him with his sword drawn in his hand: and Joshua went unto him, and said unto him, Art thou for us, or for our adversaries?', '&para; 6~03091~ 9~03405~, 13~05375~ 15~05869~ 17~07200~, 21~05975~ 23~0376~ 29~02719~ 30~08025~ 33~03027~: 35~03091~ 36~03212~ 40~0559~ [43] 50~06862~?'),
  (18023, 23, 19, 10, 'And they shall be broken in the purposes thereof, all that make sluices and ponds for fish.', '4~01792~ 7~08356~ 11~06213~ 12~07938~ [13] 14~099~ 16~05315~.'),
  (11163, 13, 28, 12, 'And the pattern of all that he had by the spirit, of the courts of the house of the LORD, and of all the chambers round about, of the treasuries of the house of God, and of the treasuries of the dedicated things:', '2~08403~ 10~07307~, 13~02691~ 16~01004~ 19~03068~, 24~03957~ 26~05439~, 29~0214~ 32~01004~ 34~0430~, 38~0214~ 42~06944~:'),
  (25624, 42, 15, 23, 'And bring hither the fatted calf, and kill it; and let us eat, and be merry:', '0~2532~ 2~5342~ 4~4618~ 5~3448~, 7~2380~ [8] 9~2532~ 12~5315~, 15~2165~:'),
  (935, 1, 32, 3, 'And Jacob sent messengers before him to Esau his brother unto the land of Seir, the country of Edom.', '&para; 1~03290~ 2~07971~ 3~04397~ 5~06440~ 7~06215~ 9~0251~ 12~0776~ 14~08165~, 16~07704~ 18~0123~.'),
  (28841, 47, 2, 1, 'But I determined this with myself, that I would not come again to you in heaviness.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2919~ 3~5124~ 5~1683~, 8~2064~ 9~3361~ 10~2064~ 11~3825~ 12~4314~ 13~5209~ 14~1722~ 15~3077~.'),
  (14170, 19, 18, 43, 'Thou hast delivered me from the strivings of the people; and thou hast made me the head of the heathen: a people whom I have not known shall serve me.', '2~06403~ 6~07379~ 9~05971~; [10] 13~07760~ 16~07218~ 19~01471~: 21~05971~ [22] 26~03045~ 28~05647~'),
  (17830, 23, 8, 14, 'And he shall be for a sanctuary; but for a stone of stumbling and for a rock of offence to both the houses of Israel, for a gin and for a snare to the inhabitants of Jerusalem.', '6~04720~; 10~068~ 12~05063~ 16~06697~ 18~04383~ 20~08147~ 22~01004~ 24~03478~, 27~06341~ 31~04170~ 34~03427~ 36~03389~.'),
  (8246, 10, 9, 12, 'And Mephibosheth had a young son, whose name was Micha. And all that dwelt in the house of Ziba were servants unto Mephibosheth.', '1~04648~ 4~06996~ 5~01121~, 7~08034~ [8] 9~04316~. 13~04186~ 16~01004~ 18~06717~ [19] 20~05650~ 22~04648~.'),
  (11546, 14, 17, 14, 'And these are the numbers of them according to the house of their fathers: Of Judah, the captains of thousands; Adnah the chief, and with him mighty men of valour three hundred thousand.', '[2] 4~06486~ 10~01004~ 13~01~: 15~03063~, 17~08269~ 19~0505~; 20~05734~ 22~08269~, 27~01368~ 29~02428~ 30~07969~ 31~03967~ 32~0505~.'),
  (30681, 64, 1, 7, 'Because that for his name''s sake they went forth, taking nothing of the Gentiles.', '1~1063~ 2~5228~ 3~846~ 4~3686~ 5~5228~ 8~1831~, 9~2983~ 10~3367~ 11~575~ 13~1484~.'),
  (14230, 19, 22, 17, 'I may tell all my bones: they look and stare upon me.', '2~05608~ 5~06106~: 7~05027~ [8] 9~07200~'),
  (18329, 23, 34, 17, 'And he hath cast the lot for them, and his hand hath divided it unto them by line: they shall possess it for ever, from generation to generation shall they dwell therein.', '3~05307~ 5~01486~ 10~03027~ 12~02505~ 17~06957~: 20~03423~ 22~05704~ 23~05769~, 25~01755~ 27~01755~ 30~07931~'),
  (15856, 19, 115, 17, 'The dead praise not the LORD, neither any that go down into silence.', '1~04191~ 2~01984~ 5~03050~, 10~03381~ 12~01745~.'),
  (30969, 66, 15, 7, 'And one of the four beasts gave unto the seven angels seven golden vials full of the wrath of God, who liveth for ever and ever.', '0~2532~ 1~1520~ 2~1537~ 4~5064~ 5~2226~ 6~1325~ 9~2033~ 10~32~ 11~2033~ 12~5552~ 13~5357~ 14~1073~ 17~2372~ 19~2316~, 20~3588~ 21~2198~ 22~1519~ 23~165~ 25~165~.'),
  (23157, 40, 1, 3, 'And Judas begat Phares and Zara of Thamar; and Phares begat Esrom; and Esrom begat Aram;', '0~1161~ 1~2455~ 2~1080~ 3~5329~ 4~2532~ 5~2196~ 6~1537~ 7~2283~; 8~1161~ 9~5329~ 10~1080~ 11~2074~; 12~1161~ 13~2074~ 14~1080~ 15~689~;'),
  (7349, 9, 6, 11, 'And they laid the ark of the LORD upon the cart, and the coffer with the mice of gold and the images of their emerods.', '2~07760~ 4~0727~ 7~03068~ 10~05699~, 13~0712~ 16~05909~ 18~02091~ 21~06754~ 24~02914~.'),
  (22853, 37, 1, 4, 'Is it time for you, O ye, to dwell in your ceiled houses, and this house lie waste?', '[0 1] 2~06256~ 8~03427~ 11~05603~ 12~01004~, 15~01004~ [16] 17~02720~?'),
  (14828, 19, 60, 12, 'Through God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.', '1~0430~ 4~06213~ 5~02428~: [8 10] 13~0947~ 15~06862~.'),
  (30339, 59, 3, 4, 'Behold also the ships, which though they be so great, and are driven of fierce winds, yet are they turned about with a very small helm, whithersoever the governor listeth.', '0~2400~ 1~2532~ 3~4143~, [6 7] 7~5607~ 9~5082~, 10~2532~ [11] 12~1643~ 13~5259~ 14~4642~ 15~417~, 20~3329~ 21~5259~ 24~1646~ 25~4079~, 26~302~ 27~3699~ 28~2116~ 29~1014~ 30~3730~.*'),
  (12013, 14, 36, 11, 'Zedekiah was one and twenty years old when he began to reign, and reigned eleven years in Jerusalem.', '&para; 0~06667~ [1] 2~0259~ 4~06242~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ 11~04427~, 13~04427~ 14~06240~ 15~0259~* 16~08141~ 18~03389~.'),
  (16523, 20, 4, 24, 'Put away from thee a froward mouth, and perverse lips put far from thee.', '1~05493~ 5~06143~ 6~06310~, 8~03891~ 9~08193~ 11~07368~'),
  (27939, 44, 28, 24, 'And some believed the things which were spoken, and some believed not.', '0~2532~ 1~3303~ 2~3982~ 7~3004~, 8~1161~ 11~569~.'),
  (20520, 26, 3, 9, 'As an adamant harder than flint have I made thy forehead: fear them not, neither be dismayed at their looks, though they be a rebellious house.', '2~08068~ 3~02389~ 5~06864~ 8~05414~ 10~04696~: 11~03372~ 16~02865~ 19~06440~, [22] 24~04805~ 25~01004~.'),
  (27452, 44, 14, 22, 'Confirming the souls of the disciples, and exhorting them to continue in the faith, and that we must through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God.', '0~1991~ 2~5590~ 5~3101~, [6] 8~3870~ 10~1696~ 13~4102~, 14~2532~ 15~3754~ 16~2248~ 17~1163~ 18~1223~ 19~4183~ 20~2347~ 21~1525~ 22~1519~ 24~932~ 26~2316~.'),
  (10774, 13, 13, 6, 'And David went up, and all Israel, to Baalah, that is, to Kirjathjearim, which belonged to Judah, to bring up thence the ark of God the LORD, that dwelleth between the cherubims, whose name is called on it.', '1~01732~ 3~05927~, 6~03478~, 8~01173~, [9 10] 12~07157~, [14] 16~03063~, 19~05927~ 22~0727~ 24~0430~ 26~03068~, 28~03427~ [29] 31~03742~, 33~08034~ 35~07121~ [36 37]'),
  (8193, 10, 7, 6, 'Whereas I have not dwelt in any house since the time that I brought up the children of Israel out of Egypt, even to this day, but have walked in a tent and in a tabernacle.', '4~03427~ [6] 7~01004~ 10~03117~ 14~05927~ 16~01121~ 18~03478~ 21~04714~, 25~03117~, 28~01980~ 31~0168~ 35~04908~.'),
  (14179, 19, 19, 2, 'Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night sheweth knowledge.', '0~03117~ 2~03117~ 3~05042~ 4~0562~, 6~03915~ 8~03915~ 9~02331~ 10~01847~.'),
  (23442, 40, 10, 15, 'Verily I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment, than for that city.', '0~281~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 7~2071~ 9~414~ 12~1093~ 14~4670~ 15~2532~ 16~1116~ 17~1722~ 19~2250~ 21~2920~, 22~2228~ 24~1565~ 25~4172~.'),
  (18915, 23, 65, 9, 'And I will bring forth a seed out of Jacob, and out of Judah an inheritor of my mountains: and mine elect shall inherit it, and my servants shall dwell there.', '4~03318~ 6~02233~ 9~03290~, 13~03063~ 15~03423~ 18~02022~: 21~0972~ 23~03423~ 27~05650~ 29~07931~'),
  (10225, 12, 24, 15, 'And he carried away Jehoiachin to Babylon, and the king''s mother, and the king''s wives, and his officers, and the mighty of the land, those carried he into captivity from Jerusalem to Babylon.', '3~01540~ 4~03078~ 6~0894~, 9~04428~ 10~0517~, 13~04428~ 14~0802~, 17~05631~, 20~0352~ 21~0193~* 24~0776~, [25] 26~03212~ 29~01473~ 31~03389~ 33~0894~.'),
  (20090, 24, 48, 1, 'Against Moab thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel; Woe unto Nebo! for it is spoiled: Kiriathaim is confounded and taken: Misgab is confounded and dismayed.', '&para; 1~04124~ 3~0559~ 5~03068~ 7~06635~, 9~0430~ 11~03478~; 12~01945~ 14~05015~! 18~07703~: 19~07156~ 21~03001~ [22] 23~03920~: 24~04869~ 26~03001~ 28~02865~.'),
  (5029, 5, 4, 19, 'And lest thou lift up thine eyes unto heaven, and when thou seest the sun, and the moon, and the stars, even all the host of heaven, shouldest be driven to worship them, and serve them, which the LORD thy God hath divided unto all nations under the whole heaven.', '4~05375~ 6~05869~ 8~08064~, 12~07200~ 14~08121~, 17~03394~, 20~03556~, [21] 24~06635~ 26~08064~, 29~05080~ 31~07812~ 34~05647~ 38~03068~ 40~0430~ 42~02505~ 45~05971~ 49~08064~.'),
  (21812, 27, 2, 45, 'Forasmuch as thou sawest that the stone was cut out of the mountain without hands, and that it brake in pieces the iron, the brass, the clay, the silver, and the gold; the great God hath made known to the king what shall come to pass hereafter: and the dream is certain, and the interpretation thereof sure.', '1~06903~ 2~03606~ 3~02370~ 6~069~ 9~01505~ 12~02906~ 13~03809~ 14~03028~, 20~01855~ 22~06523~, 24~05174~, 26~02635~, 28~03702~, 31~01722~; 33~07229~ 34~0426~ 37~03046~ 40~04430~ 41~04101~ 45~01934~ 46~01836~ 47~0311~:* 50~02493~ [51] 52~03330~, 55~06591~ 57~0540~.'),
  (17689, 23, 1, 26, 'And I will restore thy judges as at the first, and thy counsellors as at the beginning: afterward thou shalt be called, The city of righteousness, the faithful city.', '3~07725~ 5~08199~ 9~07223~, 12~03289~ 16~08462~: 17~0310~ 21~07121~, 23~05892~ 25~06664~, 27~0539~ 28~07151~.'),
  (25980, 42, 23, 31, 'For if they do these things in a green tree, what shall be done in the dry?', '0~3754~ 1~1487~ 3~4160~ 5~5023~ 6~1722~ 8~5200~ 9~3586~, 10~5101~ 13~1096~ 14~1722~ 16~3584~?'),
  (7439, 9, 10, 14, 'And Saul''s uncle said unto him and to his servant, Whither went ye? And he said, To seek the asses: and when we saw that they were no where, we came to Samuel.', '1~07586~ 2~01730~ 3~0559~ 9~05288~, 10~0575~ 11~01980~ 15~0559~, 17~01245~ 19~0860~: 23~07200~ [25 26] 28~0369~, 30~0935~ 32~08050~.'),
  (24954, 42, 1, 49, 'For he that is mighty hath done to me great things; and holy is his name.', '0~3754~ 4~1415~ 6~4160~ 8~3427~ 10~3167~; 11~2532~ 12~40~ [13] 14~846~ 15~3686~.'),
  (9117, 11, 11, 1, 'But king Solomon loved many strange women, together with the daughter of Pharaoh, women of the Moabites, Ammonites, Edomites, Zidonians, and Hittites;', '&para; 1~04428~ 2~08010~ 3~0157~ 4~07227~ 5~05237~ 6~0802~, 10~01323~ 12~06547~, 16~04125~, 17~05984~, 18~0130~, 19~06722~, [20] 21~02850~;'),
  (10639, 13, 9, 16, 'And Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun, and Berechiah the son of Asa, the son of Elkanah, that dwelt in the villages of the Netophathites.', '1~05662~ 3~01121~ 5~08098~, 7~01121~ 9~01559~, 11~01121~ 13~03038~, 15~01296~ 17~01121~ 19~0609~, 21~01121~ 23~0511~, 25~03427~ 28~02691~ 31~05200~.'),
  (14811, 19, 59, 12, 'For the sin of their mouth and the words of their lips let them even be taken in their pride: and for cursing and lying which they speak.', '[0] 2~02403~ 5~06310~ [6] 8~01697~ 11~08193~ 16~03920~ 19~01347~: 22~0423~ 24~03585~ [25] 27~05608~.'),
  (19409, 24, 18, 16, 'To make their land desolate, and a perpetual hissing; every one that passeth thereby shall be astonished, and wag his head.', '1~07760~ 3~0776~ 4~08047~, [5] 7~05769~ 8~08292~ 9~08292~;* 13~05674~ 17~08074~, 19~05110~ 21~07218~.'),
  (16438, 20, 1, 29, 'For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the LORD:', '3~08130~ 4~01847~, 8~0977~ 10~03374~ 13~03068~:'),
  (30643, 62, 5, 3, 'For this is the love of God, that we keep his commandments: and his commandments are not grievous.', '0~1063~ 1~3778~ 2~2076~ 4~26~ 6~2316~, 7~2443~ 9~5083~ 10~846~ 11~1785~: 12~2532~ 13~846~ 14~1785~ 15~1526~ 16~3756~ 17~926~.'),
  (24904, 41, 16, 20, 'And they went forth, and preached every where, the Lord working with them, and confirming the word with signs following. Amen.', '0~1161~ 1~1565~ 3~1831~, 5~2784~ 7~3837~, 9~2962~ 11~4903~ [12] 13~2532~ 14~950~ 16~3056~ 17~1223~ 18~4592~ 19~1872~. 20~281~.'),
  (10408, 13, 4, 15, 'And the sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh; Iru, Elah, and Naam: and the sons of Elah, even Kenaz.', '2~01121~ 4~03612~ 6~01121~ 8~03312~; 9~05900~, 10~0425~, 12~05277~: 15~01121~ 17~0425~, 19~07073~.'),
  (17602, 22, 4, 11, 'Thy lips, O my spouse, drop as the honeycomb: honey and milk are under thy tongue; and the smell of thy garments is like the smell of Lebanon.', '1~08193~, [3] 4~03618~, 5~05197~ [6] 8~05317~: 9~01706~ 11~02461~ [12] 15~03956~; 18~07381~ 21~08008~ [22] 25~07381~ 27~03844~.'),
  (27624, 44, 19, 23, 'And the same time there arose no small stir about that way.', '0~2596~ 1~1161~ 2~1565~ 3~2540~ 5~1096~ 6~3756~ 7~3641~ 8~5017~ 9~4012~ 11~3598~.'),
  (25178, 42, 6, 20, 'And he lifted up his eyes on his disciples, and said, Blessed be ye poor: for yours is the kingdom of God.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~846~ 3~1869~ 4~846~ 5~3788~ 6~1519~ 7~846~ 8~3101~, 10~3004~, 11~3107~ [12 13] 14~4434~: 15~3754~ 16~5212~ 17~2076~ 19~932~ 21~2316~.'),
  (21531, 26, 40, 45, 'And he said unto me, This chamber, whose prospect is toward the south, is for the priests, the keepers of the charge of the house.', '2~01696~ 5~02090~ 6~03957~, 8~06440~ [9] 10~01870~ 12~01864~, [13] 16~03548~, 18~08104~ 21~04931~ 24~01004~.'),
  (12611, 16, 11, 14, 'And their brethren, mighty men of valour, an hundred twenty and eight: and their overseer was Zabdiel, the son of one of the great men.', '2~0251~, 4~01368~ 6~02428~, 8~03967~ 9~06242~ 11~08083~: 14~06496~ [15] 16~02068~, 18~01121~ [20 21] 24~01419~.'),
  (19475, 24, 22, 12, 'But he shall die in the place whither they have led him captive, and shall see this land no more.', '3~04191~ 6~04725~ 12~01540~, 15~07200~ 17~0776~'),
  (7659, 9, 17, 34, 'And David said unto Saul, Thy servant kept his father''s sheep, and there came a lion, and a bear, and took a lamb out of the flock:', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~07586~, 6~05650~ 7~07462~ 9~01~ 10~06629~, 13~0935~ 15~0738~, 18~01677~, 20~05375~ 22~07716~ 23~02089~* 27~05739~:'),
  (24734, 41, 13, 6, 'For many shall come in my name, saying, I am Christ; and shall deceive many.', '0~1063~ 1~4183~ 3~2064~ 4~1909~ 5~3450~ 6~3686~, 7~3004~ 8~3754~,* 9~1473~ 10~1510~ [11] 12~2532~ 14~4105~ 15~4183~.'),
  (27952, 45, 1, 6, 'Among whom are ye also the called of Jesus Christ:', '0~1722~ 1~3739~ 2~2075~ 3~5210~ 4~2532~ 6~2822~ 8~2424~ 9~5547~:');
