  (3110, 3, 13, 53, 'And if the priest shall look, and, behold, the plague be not spread in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in any thing of skin;', '3~03548~ 5~07200~, 9~05061~ 12~06581~ 15~0899~, 16~0176~ 19~08359~, 20~0176~ 23~06154~, 24~0176~ 27~03627~ 29~05785~;'),
  (2973, 3, 9, 15, 'And he brought the people''s offering, and took the goat, which was the sin offering for the people, and slew it, and offered it for sin, as the first.', '2~07126~ 4~05971~ 5~07133~, 7~03947~ 9~08163~, [11] 14~02403~ 17~05971~, 19~07819~ 25~02398~, 28~07223~.'),
  (2573, 2, 36, 2, 'And Moses called Bezaleel and Aholiab, and every wise hearted man, in whose heart the LORD had put wisdom, even every one whose heart stirred him up to come unto the work to do it:', '1~04872~ 2~07121~ 3~01212~ 5~0171~, 8~02450~ 9~03820~ 10~0376~, 13~03820~ 15~03068~ 17~05414~ 18~02451~, [19] 23~03820~ 26~05375~ 28~07126~ 31~04399~ 33~06213~'),
  (1289, 1, 42, 32, 'We be twelve brethren, sons of our father; one is not, and the youngest is this day with our father in the land of Canaan.', '[1] 2~08147~ 3~06240~* 4~0251~, 5~01121~ 8~01~; 9~0259~ [10] 14~06996~ [15] 17~03117~ 20~01~ 23~0776~ 25~03667~.'),
  (4366, 4, 21, 21, 'And Israel sent messengers unto Sihon king of the Amorites, saying,', '&para; 1~03478~ 2~07971~ 3~04397~ 5~05511~ 6~04428~ 9~0567~, 10~0559~,'),
  (20712, 26, 12, 23, 'Tell them therefore, Thus saith the Lord GOD; I will make this proverb to cease, and they shall no more use it as a proverb in Israel; but say unto them, The days are at hand, and the effect of every vision.', '0~0559~ 4~0559~ 6~0136~ 7~03069~; 12~04912~ 14~07673~, 24~04911~ 26~03478~; 28~01696~ 32~03117~ 35~07126~, 38~01697~ 41~02377~.'),
  (4023, 4, 10, 30, 'And he said unto him, I will not go; but I will depart to mine own land, and to my kindred.', '2~0559~ 8~03212~; 12~03212~ 16~0776~, 20~04138~.'),
  (26303, 43, 6, 31, 'Our fathers did eat manna in the desert; as it is written, He gave them bread from heaven to eat.', '0~2257~ 1~3962~ 3~5315~ 4~3131~ 5~1722~ 7~2048~; 8~2531~ 10~2076~ 11~1125~, 13~1325~ 14~846~ 15~740~ 16~1537~ 17~3772~ 19~5315~.'),
  (14000, 19, 6, 6, 'I am weary with my groaning; all the night make I my bed to swim; I water my couch with my tears.', '2~03021~ 5~0585~; 8~03915~ 12~04296~ 14~07811~; 16~04529~ 18~06210~ 21~01832~.'),
  (13824, 18, 38, 22, 'Hast thou entered into the treasures of the snow? or hast thou seen the treasures of the hail,', '2~0935~ 5~0214~ 8~07950~? 12~07200~ 14~0214~ 17~01259~,'),
  (14451, 19, 36, 4, 'He deviseth mischief upon his bed; he setteth himself in a way that is not good; he abhorreth not evil.', '1~02803~ 2~0205~ 5~04904~; 7~03320~ 11~01870~ [12 13] 15~02896~; 17~03988~ 19~07451~.'),
  (28126, 45, 7, 19, 'For the good that I would I do not: but the evil which I would not, that I do.', '0~3739~ 1~1063~ 2~18~ 5~2309~ 7~4160~ 8~3756~: 9~235~ 11~2556~ 12~3739~ 14~2309~ 15~3756~, 16~5124~ 18~4238~.'),
  (2181, 2, 23, 32, 'Thou shalt make no covenant with them, nor with their gods.', '2~03772~ 4~01285~ 10~0430~.'),
  (23209, 40, 3, 7, 'But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees come to his baptism, he said unto them, O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~1492~ 4~4183~ 7~5330~ 8~2532~ 9~4523~ 10~2064~ 11~1909~ 12~846~ 13~908~, 15~2036~ 17~846~, 19~1081~ 21~2191~, 22~5101~ 24~5263~ 25~5213~ 27~5343~ 28~575~ 30~3709~ 32~3195~?'),
  (26306, 43, 6, 34, 'Then said they unto him, Lord, evermore give us this bread.', '0~3767~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 5~2962~, 6~3842~ 7~1325~ 8~2254~ 9~5126~ 10~740~.'),
  (15363, 19, 89, 28, 'My mercy will I keep for him for evermore, and my covenant shall stand fast with him.', '1~02617~ 4~08104~ 8~05769~, 11~01285~ 14~0539~'),
  (3273, 3, 18, 17, 'Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of a woman and her daughter, neither shalt thou take her son''s daughter, or her daughter''s daughter, to uncover her nakedness; for they are her near kinswomen: it is wickedness.', '3~01540~ 5~06172~ 8~0802~ 11~01323~, 15~03947~ 17~01121~ 18~01323~, 21~01323~ 22~01323~, 24~01540~ 26~06172~; [27] [29] 32~07608~: [34] 35~02154~.'),
  (29449, 50, 3, 12, 'Not as though I had already attained, either were already perfect: but I follow after, if that I may apprehend that for which also I am apprehended of Christ Jesus.', '0~3756~ 2~3754~ 5~2235~ 6~2983~, 7~2228~ 9~2235~ 10~5048~: 11~1161~ 14~1377~, 15~1499~ 19~2638~ 21~1909~ 22~3739~ 23~2532~ 26~2638~ 27~5259~ 28~5547~ 29~2424~.'),
  (15637, 19, 105, 22, 'To bind his princes at his pleasure; and teach his senators wisdom.', '1~0631~ 3~08269~ 6~05315~; 10~02205~ 11~02449~.'),
  (11391, 14, 9, 19, 'And twelve lions stood there on the one side and on the other upon the six steps. There was not the like made in any kingdom.', '1~06240~ 2~08147~* 3~0738~ 4~05975~ 16~08337~ 17~04609~. 23~06213~ 26~04467~.'),
  (13391, 18, 21, 27, 'Behold, I know your thoughts, and the devices which ye wrongfully imagine against me.', '&para; 2~03045~ 4~04284~, 7~04209~ [8] 11~02554~'),
  (22237, 28, 10, 3, 'For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the LORD; what then should a king do to us?', '4~0559~, 8~04428~, 11~03372~ 14~03068~; 19~04428~ 20~06213~'),
  (5364, 5, 16, 16, 'Three times in a year shall all thy males appear before the LORD thy God in the place which he shall choose; in the feast of unleavened bread, and in the feast of weeks, and in the feast of tabernacles: and they shall not appear before the LORD empty:', '0~07969~ 1~06471~ 4~08141~ 8~02138~ 9~07200~ 10~06440~ 12~03068~ 14~0430~ 17~04725~ 21~0977~; 24~02282~ 27~04682~, 31~02282~ 33~07620~, 37~02282~ 39~05521~: 44~07200~ 45~06440~ 47~03068~ 48~07387~:'),
  (29725, 54, 1, 13, 'Who was before a blasphemer, and a persecutor, and injurious: but I obtained mercy, because I did it ignorantly in unbelief.', '0~3588~ 1~5607~ 2~4386~ 4~989~, 5~2532~ 7~1376~, 8~2532~ 9~5197~: 10~235~ 13~1653~, 14~3754~ 16~4160~ [17] 18~50~ 19~1722~ 20~570~.'),
  (14598, 19, 44, 18, 'Our heart is not turned back, neither have our steps declined from thy way;', '1~03820~ 4~05472~ 5~0268~, 9~0838~ 10~05186~ 13~0734~;'),
  (19646, 24, 29, 2, '(After that Jeconiah the king, and the queen, and the eunuchs, the princes of Judah and Jerusalem, and the carpenters, and the smiths, were departed from Jerusalem;)', '0~(0310~ 2~03204~ 4~04428~, 7~01377~, 10~05631~, 12~08269~ 14~03063~ 16~03389~, 19~02796~, 22~04525~, 24~03318~ 26~03389~;)'),
  (2443, 2, 31, 18, 'And he gave unto Moses, when he had made an end of communing with him upon mount Sinai, two tables of testimony, tables of stone, written with the finger of God.', '2~05414~ 4~04872~, 10~03615~ 12~01696~ 16~02022~ 17~05514~, 18~08147~ 19~03871~ 21~05715~, 22~03871~ 24~068~, 25~03789~ 28~0676~ 30~0430~.'),
  (10689, 13, 11, 8, 'And he built the city round about, even from Millo round about: and Joab repaired the rest of the city.', '2~01129~ 4~05892~ 6~05439~, 9~04407~ 11~05439~: 13~03097~ 14~02421~ 16~07605~ 19~05892~.'),
  (3859, 4, 7, 4, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (10603, 13, 8, 20, 'And Elienai, and Zilthai, and Eliel,', '1~0462~, 3~06769~, 5~0447~,'),
  (23875, 40, 21, 39, 'And they caught him, and cast him out of the vineyard, and slew him.', '0~2532~ 2~2983~ 3~846~, 5~1544~ [6] 8~1854~ 10~290~, 11~2532~ 12~615~ [13]'),
  (21809, 27, 2, 42, 'And as the toes of the feet were part of iron, and part of clay, so the kingdom shall be partly strong, and partly broken.', '[1] 3~0677~ 6~07271~ [7] 8~04481~ 10~06523~, 12~04481~ 14~02635~, [15] 17~04437~ 19~01934~ 20~07118~ 21~04481~* 22~08624~, 24~07118~ 25~04481~* 26~08406~.'),
  (27058, 44, 4, 20, 'For we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard.', '0~1063~ 1~2249~ 2~1410~ 3~3756~* 4~3361~ 5~2980~ 8~3739~ 11~1492~ 12~2532~ 13~191~.'),
  (6833, 7, 10, 15, 'And the children of Israel said unto the LORD, We have sinned: do thou unto us whatsoever seemeth good unto thee; deliver us only, we pray thee, this day.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~0559~ 8~03068~, 11~02398~: 12~06213~ 17~05869~ 18~02896~ 21~05337~ 28~03117~.'),
  (9172, 11, 12, 13, 'And the king answered the people roughly, and forsook the old men''s counsel that they gave him;', '2~04428~ 3~06030~ 5~05971~ 6~07186~, 8~05800~ 11~02205~ 12~06098~ 15~03289~'),
  (19141, 24, 7, 13, 'And now, because ye have done all these works, saith the LORD, and I spake unto you, rising up early and speaking, but ye heard not; and I called you, but ye answered not;', '5~06213~ 8~04639~, 9~05002~ 11~03068~, 14~01696~ 19~07925~ 21~01696~, 24~08085~ 28~07121~ 32~06030~'),
  (3313, 3, 19, 27, 'Ye shall not round the corners of your heads, neither shalt thou mar the corners of thy beard.', '3~05362~ 5~06285~ 8~07218~, 12~07843~ 14~06285~ 17~02206~.'),
