VALUES
  (27583, 44, 18, 10, 'For I am with thee, and no man shall set on thee to hurt thee: for I have much people in this city.', '0~1360~ 1~1473~ 2~1510~ 3~3326~ 4~4675~, 5~2532~ 7~3762~ 10~2007~ 11~4671~ 13~2559~ 14~4571~: 15~1360~ 16~3427~ 17~2076~ 18~4183~ 19~2992~ 20~1722~ 21~5026~ 22~4172~.'),
  (6527, 7, 1, 11, 'And from thence he went against the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before was Kirjathsepher:', '4~03212~ 7~03427~ 9~01688~: 12~08034~ 14~01688~ 15~06440~ [16] 17~07158~:'),
  (18153, 23, 26, 14, 'They are dead, they shall not live; they are deceased, they shall not rise: therefore hast thou visited and destroyed them, and made all their memory to perish.', '[0 1] 2~04191~, 6~02421~; [7 8] 9~07496~, 13~06965~: 17~06485~ 19~08045~ 25~02143~ 27~06~.'),
  (13070, 18, 9, 10, 'Which doeth great things past finding out; yea, and wonders without number.', '1~06213~ 3~01419~ 4~0369~ 6~02714~; 9~06381~ 11~04557~.'),
  (27450, 44, 14, 20, 'Howbeit, as the disciples stood round about him, he rose up, and came into the city: and the next day he departed with Barnabas to Derbe.', '0~1161~, 3~3101~ 6~2944~ 7~846~, 10~450~, 12~1525~ 13~1519~ 15~4172~: 16~2532~ 19~1887~ 21~1831~ 22~4862~ 23~921~ 24~1519~ 25~1191~.'),
  (1595, 2, 3, 11, 'And Moses said unto God, Who am I, that I should go unto Pharaoh, and that I should bring forth the children of Israel out of Egypt?', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~0430~, [6] 11~03212~ 13~06547~, 19~03318~ 21~01121~ 23~03478~ 26~04714~?'),
  (3928, 4, 7, 73, 'His offering was one silver charger, the weight whereof was an hundred and thirty shekels, one silver bowl of seventy shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary; both of them full of fine flour mingled with oil for a meat offering:', '1~07133~ [2] 3~0259~ 4~03701~ 5~07086~, 7~04948~ [9] 11~03967~ 13~07970~ [14] 15~0259~ 16~03701~ 17~04219~ 19~07657~ 20~08255~, 23~08255~ 26~06944~; 27~08147~ 30~04392~ 33~05560~ 34~01101~ 36~08081~ 40~04503~:'),
  (22460, 30, 6, 1, 'Woe to them that are at ease in Zion, and trust in the mountain of Samaria, which are named chief of the nations, to whom the house of Israel came!', '&para; 0~01945~ [3 4] 6~07600~ 8~06726~, 10~0982~ 13~02022~ 15~08111~, [16 17] 18~05344~ 19~07225~ 22~01471~, 26~01004~ 28~03478~ 29~0935~!'),
  (16185, 19, 135, 1, 'Praise ye the LORD. Praise ye the name of the LORD; praise him, O ye servants of the LORD.', '&para; 0~01984~ 3~03050~. 4~01984~ 7~08034~ 10~03068~; 11~01984~ [12] 15~05650~ 18~03068~.'),
  (23725, 40, 17, 15, 'Lord, have mercy on my son: for he is a lunatic, and sore vexed: for ofttimes he falleth into the fire, and oft into the water.', '0~2962~, 2~1653~ 4~3450~ 5~5207~: 6~3754~ 9~4583~, 10~2532~ 11~2560~ 12~3958~: 13~1063~ 14~4178~ 16~4098~ 17~1519~ 19~4442~, 20~2532~ 21~4178~ 22~1519~ 24~5204~.'),
  (7265, 9, 2, 18, 'But Samuel ministered before the LORD, being a child, girded with a linen ephod.', '1~08050~ 2~08334~ 3~06440~ 5~03068~, [6] 8~05288~, 9~02296~ 12~0906~ 13~0646~.'),
  (10634, 13, 9, 11, 'And Azariah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the ruler of the house of God;', '1~05838~ 3~01121~ 5~02518~, 7~01121~ 9~04918~, 11~01121~ 13~06659~, 15~01121~ 17~04812~, 19~01121~ 21~0285~, 23~05057~ 26~01004~ 28~0430~;'),
  (20036, 24, 44, 17, 'But we will certainly do whatsoever thing goeth forth out of our own mouth, to burn incense unto the queen of heaven, and to pour out drink offerings unto her, as we have done, we, and our fathers, our kings, and our princes, in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem: for then had we plenty of victuals, and were well, and saw no evil.', '3~06213~ 4~06213~ 6~01697~ 8~03318~ 13~06310~, 16~06999~ 19~04446~ 21~08064~, 25~05258~ 27~05262~ 33~06213~, 37~01~, 39~04428~, 42~08269~, 45~05892~ 47~03063~, 51~02351~ 53~03389~: [55] 58~07646~ 60~03899~, 63~02896~, 65~07200~ 67~07451~.'),
  (23643, 40, 14, 36, 'And besought him that they might only touch the hem of his garment: and as many as touched were made perfectly whole.', '0~2532~ 1~3870~ 2~846~ 3~2443~ 5~680~ 6~3440~ 7~680~ 9~2899~ 11~846~ 12~2440~: 13~2532~ 16~3745~ 17~680~ 21~1295~.'),
  (28683, 46, 13, 2, 'And though I have the gift of prophecy, and understand all mysteries, and all knowledge; and though I have all faith, so that I could remove mountains, and have not charity, I am nothing.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 3~2192~ [4 6] 7~4394~, 8~2532~ 9~1492~ 10~3956~ 11~3466~, 12~2532~ 13~3956~ 14~1108~; 15~2532~ 16~1437~ 18~2192~ 19~3956~ 20~4102~, 21~5620~ 25~3179~ 26~3735~, 27~1161~ 28~2192~ 29~3361~ 30~26~, 32~1510~ 33~3762~.'),
  (17930, 23, 13, 15, 'Every one that is found shall be thrust through; and every one that is joined unto them shall fall by the sword.', '4~04672~ 8~01856~; 14~05595~ [15 16] 18~05307~ 21~02719~.'),
  (18584, 23, 45, 14, 'Thus saith the LORD, The labour of Egypt, and merchandise of Ethiopia and of the Sabeans, men of stature, shall come over unto thee, and they shall be thine: they shall come after thee; in chains they shall come over, and they shall fall down unto thee, they shall make supplication unto thee, saying, Surely God is in thee; and there is none else, there is no God.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~03018~ 7~04714~, 9~05505~ 11~03568~ 15~05436~, 16~0582~ 18~04060~, 21~05674~ 31~03212~ 32~0310~ 35~02131~ 39~05674~, 44~07812~ 50~06419~ [53] 55~0410~ [56] [60 61] [64 65] 66~0657~ 67~0430~.'),
  (2154, 2, 23, 5, 'If thou see the ass of him that hateth thee lying under his burden, and wouldest forbear to help him, thou shalt surely help with him.', '2~07200~ 4~02543~ 8~08130~ 10~07257~ 13~04853~, 16~02308~ 18~05800~ 22~05800~ 23~05800~'),
  (29846, 55, 2, 3, 'Thou therefore endure hardness, as a good soldier of Jesus Christ.', '0~4771~ 1~3767~ 3~2553~, 4~5613~ 6~2570~ 7~4757~ 9~2424~ 10~5547~.'),
  (14714, 19, 51, 14, 'Deliver me from bloodguiltiness, O God, thou God of my salvation: and my tongue shall sing aloud of thy righteousness.', '&para; 0~05337~ 3~01818~, 5~0430~, 7~0430~ 10~08668~: [11] 13~03956~ 16~07442~ 19~06666~.'),
  (16161, 19, 132, 1, 'A Song of degrees. LORD, remember David, and all his afflictions:', '&para; 1~07892~ 3~04609~. 4~03068~, 5~02142~ 6~01732~, [7] 10~06031~:'),
  (4038, 4, 11, 9, 'And when the dew fell upon the camp in the night, the manna fell upon it.', '3~02919~ 4~03381~ 7~04264~ 10~03915~, 12~04478~ 13~03381~'),
  (18250, 23, 30, 24, 'The oxen likewise and the young asses that ear the ground shall eat clean provender, which hath been winnowed with the shovel and with the fan.', '1~0504~ 6~05895~ 8~05647~ 10~0127~ 12~0398~ 13~02548~ 14~01098~, 18~02219~ 21~07371~ 25~04214~.'),
  (6117, 6, 11, 4, 'And they went out, they and all their hosts with them, much people, even as the sand that is upon the sea shore in multitude, with horses and chariots very many.', '3~03318~, 8~04264~ 11~07227~ 12~05971~, 16~02344~ [18] 21~03220~ 22~08193~ 24~07230~, 26~05483~ 28~07393~ 29~03966~ 30~07227~.'),
  (4912, 5, 1, 14, 'And ye answered me, and said, The thing which thou hast spoken is good for us to do.', '2~06030~ 5~0559~, 7~01697~ 11~01696~ [12] 13~02896~ [14 15] 17~06213~.'),
  (9498, 11, 22, 10, 'And the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah sat each on his throne, having put on their robes, in a void place in the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets prophesied before them.', '2~04428~ 4~03478~ 6~03092~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~ 11~03427~ 12~0376~ 15~03678~, 18~03847~ 20~0899~, 24~01637~ 27~06607~ 30~08179~ 32~08111~; 36~05030~ 37~05012~ 38~06440~'),
  (8260, 10, 10, 13, 'And Joab drew nigh, and the people that were with him, unto the battle against the Syrians: and they fled before him.', '1~03097~ 3~05066~, 6~05971~ [8] 13~04421~ 16~0758~: 19~05127~ 20~06440~'),
  (10726, 13, 11, 45, 'Jediael the son of Shimri, and Joha his brother, the Tizite,', '0~03043~ 2~01121~ 4~08113~, 6~03109~ 8~0251~, 10~08491~,'),
  (26894, 43, 20, 12, 'And seeth two angels in white sitting, the one at the head, and the other at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain.', '0~2532~ 1~2334~ 2~1417~ 3~32~ 4~1722~ 5~3022~ 6~2516~, 8~1520~ 9~4314~ 11~2776~, 12~2532~ 14~1520~ 15~4314~ 17~4228~, 18~3699~ 20~4983~ 22~2424~ 24~2749~.'),
  (15142, 19, 78, 20, 'Behold, he smote the rock, that the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed; can he give bread also? can he provide flesh for his people?', '2~05221~ 4~06697~, 7~04325~ 9~02100~, 12~05158~ 13~07857~; 14~03201~ 16~05414~ 17~03899~ 19~03201~ 21~03559~ 22~07607~ 25~05971~?'),
  (2804, 3, 4, 4, 'And he shall bring the bullock unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation before the LORD; and shall lay his hand upon the bullock''s head, and kill the bullock before the LORD.', '3~0935~ 5~06499~ 8~06607~ 11~0168~ 14~04150~ 15~06440~ 17~03068~; 20~05564~ 22~03027~ 25~06499~ 26~07218~, 28~07819~ 30~06499~ 31~06440~ 33~03068~.'),
  (10612, 13, 8, 29, 'And at Gibeon dwelt the father of Gibeon; whose wife''s name was Maachah:', '2~01391~ 3~03427~ 5~01~ 7~01391~ 8~025~;* 10~0802~ 11~08034~ [12] 13~04601~:'),
  (22558, 32, 2, 1, 'Then Jonah prayed unto the LORD his God out of the fish''s belly,', '&para; 1~03124~ 2~06419~ 5~03068~ 7~0430~ 11~01710~ 12~04578~,'),
  (4295, 4, 19, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~ 8~0175~, 9~0559~,'),
  (17244, 20, 29, 11, 'A fool uttereth all his mind: but a wise man keepeth it in till afterwards.', '&para; 1~03684~ 2~03318~ 5~07307~: 8~02450~ [9] 10~07623~ 14~0268~.'),
  (10897, 13, 17, 26, 'And now, LORD, thou art God, and hast promised this goodness unto thy servant:', '2~03068~, 5~0430~, 8~01696~ 10~02896~ 13~05650~:'),
  (14639, 19, 47, 5, 'God is gone up with a shout, the LORD with the sound of a trumpet.', '&para; 0~0430~ 3~05927~ 6~08643~, 8~03068~ 11~06963~ 14~07782~.'),
  (4779, 4, 33, 13, 'And they departed from Dophkah, and encamped in Alush.', '2~05265~ 4~01850~, 6~02583~ 8~0442~.'),
  (23367, 40, 8, 12, 'But the children of the kingdom shall be cast out into outer darkness: there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.', '0~1161~ 2~5207~ 5~932~ 9~1544~ 10~1519~ 11~1857~ 12~4655~: 13~1563~ 15~2071~ 16~2805~ 17~2532~ 18~1030~ 20~3599~.'),
  (1209, 1, 41, 9, 'Then spake the chief butler unto Pharaoh, saying, I do remember my faults this day:', '&para; 1~01696~ 3~08269~ 4~08248~ 6~06547~, 7~0559~, 10~02142~ 12~02399~ 14~03117~:'),
  (17093, 20, 24, 5, 'A wise man is strong; yea, a man of knowledge increaseth strength.', '1~02450~ 2~01397~ [3] 4~05797~; 7~0376~ 9~01847~ 10~0553~ 11~03581~.'),
  (14304, 19, 27, 10, 'When my father and my mother forsake me, then the LORD will take me up.', '2~01~ 5~0517~ 6~05800~ 10~03068~ 14~0622~.'),
  (14844, 19, 62, 8, 'Trust in him at all times; ye people, pour out your heart before him: God is a refuge for us. Selah.', '&para; 0~0982~ 5~06256~; [6] 7~05971~, 9~08210~ 11~03824~ 12~06440~ 14~0430~ [15] 17~04268~ 20~05542~.'),
  (3493, 3, 25, 19, 'And the land shall yield her fruit, and ye shall eat your fill, and dwell therein in safety.', '2~0776~ 4~05414~ 6~06529~, 10~0398~ 12~07648~, 14~03427~ 17~0983~.'),
  (27629, 44, 19, 28, 'And when they heard these sayings, they were full of wrath, and cried out, saying, Great is Diana of the Ephesians.', '0~1161~ 3~191~ [4 5] 7~1096~ 8~4134~ 10~2372~, 11~2532~ 13~2896~, 14~3004~, 15~3173~ [16] 17~735~ 20~2180~.'),
  (8891, 11, 5, 5, 'And, behold, I purpose to build an house unto the name of the LORD my God, as the LORD spake unto David my father, saying, Thy son, whom I will set upon thy throne in thy room, he shall build an house unto my name.', '3~0559~ 5~01129~ 7~01004~ 10~08034~ 13~03068~ 15~0430~, 18~03068~ 19~01696~ 21~01732~ 23~01~, 24~0559~, 26~01121~, 30~05414~ 33~03678~ 39~01129~ 41~01004~ 44~08034~.'),
  (366, 1, 15, 2, 'And Abram said, Lord GOD, what wilt thou give me, seeing I go childless, and the steward of my house is this Eliezer of Damascus?', '&para; 1~087~ 2~0559~, 3~0136~ 4~03069~, 8~05414~ 12~01980~ 13~06185~, 16~04943~ 17~01121~ 19~01004~ [20] 21~01931~ 22~0461~ 24~01834~?'),
  (16969, 20, 20, 6, 'Most men will proclaim every one his own goodness: but a faithful man who can find?', '&para; 0~07230~ 1~0120~ 3~07121~ 5~0376~ 8~02617~: 11~0529~ 12~0376~ 15~04672~?'),
  (19907, 24, 38, 3, 'Thus saith the LORD, This city shall surely be given into the hand of the king of Babylon''s army, which shall take it.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~05892~ 7~05414~ 9~05414~ 12~03027~ 15~04428~ 17~0894~ 18~02428~, 21~03920~'),
  (21310, 26, 33, 21, 'And it came to pass in the twelfth year of our captivity, in the tenth month, in the fifth day of the month, that one that had escaped out of Jerusalem came unto me, saying, The city is smitten.', '&para; 7~06240~ 8~08147~* 9~08141~ 12~01546~, 15~06224~ [16] 19~02568~ [20] 23~02320~, [24] 28~06412~ 31~03389~ 32~0935~ 35~0559~, 37~05892~ 39~05221~.'),
  (17280, 20, 30, 20, 'Such is the way of an adulterous woman; she eateth, and wipeth her mouth, and saith, I have done no wickedness.', '[1] 3~01870~ 6~05003~ 7~0802~; 9~0398~, 11~04229~ 13~06310~, 15~0559~, 18~06466~ 20~0205~.'),
  (4893, 4, 36, 8, 'And every daughter, that possesseth an inheritance in any tribe of the children of Israel, shall be wife unto one of the family of the tribe of her father, that the children of Israel may enjoy every man the inheritance of his fathers.', '2~01323~, 4~03423~ 6~05159~ 9~04294~ 12~01121~ 14~03478~, 17~0802~ 19~0259~ 22~04940~ 25~04294~ 28~01~, 31~01121~ 33~03478~ 35~03423~ 37~0376~ 39~05159~ 42~01~.'),
  (486, 1, 19, 25, 'And he overthrew those cities, and all the plain, and all the inhabitants of the cities, and that which grew upon the ground.', '2~02015~ 3~0411~ 4~05892~, 8~03603~, 12~03427~ 15~05892~, 19~06780~ 22~0127~.'),
  (1149, 1, 38, 25, 'When she was brought forth, she sent to her father in law, saying, By the man, whose these are, am I with child: and she said, Discern, I pray thee, whose are these, the signet, and bracelets, and staff.', '[2] 4~03318~, 6~07971~ 11~02524~, 12~0559~, 15~0376~, [18 19] 22~02030~: 25~0559~, 26~05234~, [31] 34~02858~, 36~06616~, 38~04294~.'),
  (29497, 51, 1, 16, 'For by him were all things created, that are in heaven, and that are in earth, visible and invisible, whether they be thrones, or dominions, or principalities, or powers: all things were created by him, and for him:', '0~3754~ 1~1722~ 2~846~ 3~2936~ 5~3956~ 6~2936~, 9~1722~ 10~3772~, 11~2532~ 14~1909~ 15~1093~, 16~3707~ 17~2532~ 18~517~, 19~1535~ [20 21] 22~2362~, 23~1535~ 24~2963~, 25~1535~ 26~746~, 27~1535~ 28~1849~: 30~3956~ 32~2936~ 33~1223~ 34~846~, 35~2532~ 36~1519~ 37~846~:'),
  (19272, 24, 12, 14, 'Thus saith the LORD against all mine evil neighbours, that touch the inheritance which I have caused my people Israel to inherit; Behold, I will pluck them out of their land, and pluck out the house of Judah from among them.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~ 7~07451~ 8~07934~, 10~05060~ 12~05159~ 18~05971~ 19~03478~ 21~05157~; 27~05428~ 30~0127~, 33~05428~ 35~01004~ 37~03063~ 39~08432~'),
  (29917, 56, 1, 9, 'Holding fast the faithful word as he hath been taught, that he may be able by sound doctrine both to exhort and to convince the gainsayers.', '1~472~ 3~4103~ 4~3056~ 5~2596~ 9~1322~, 10~2443~ 13~5600~ 14~1415~ 15~1722~ 16~5198~ 17~1319~ 18~2532~ 20~3870~ 21~2532~ 23~1651~ 25~483~.'),
  (26766, 43, 16, 25, 'These things have I spoken unto you in proverbs: but the time cometh, when I shall no more speak unto you in proverbs, but I shall shew you plainly of the Father.', '1~5023~ 4~2980~ 6~5213~ 7~1722~ 8~3942~: 9~235~ 11~5610~ 12~2064~, 13~3753~ 15~2980~ 17~3765~ 18~2980~ 20~5213~ 21~1722~ 22~3942~, 23~235~ 26~312~ 27~5213~ 28~3954~ 29~4012~ 31~3962~.'),
  (24743, 41, 13, 15, 'And let him that is on the housetop not go down into the house, neither enter therein, to take any thing out of his house:', '0~1161~ 2~2597~ 5~1909~ 7~1430~ 8~3361~ 10~2597~ 11~1519~ 13~3614~, 14~3366~ 15~1525~ [16] 18~142~ 20~5100~ 22~1537~ 23~846~ 24~3614~:'),
  (7947, 9, 27, 10, 'And Achish said, Whither have ye made a road to day? And David said, Against the south of Judah, and against the south of the Jerahmeelites, and against the south of the Kenites.', '1~0397~ 2~0559~, 3~0408~ 8~06584~ 10~03117~? 12~01732~ 13~0559~, 16~05045~ 18~03063~, 22~05045~ 25~03397~, 29~05045~ 32~07017~.'),
  (13593, 18, 30, 27, 'My bowels boiled, and rested not: the days of affliction prevented me.', '1~04578~ 2~07570~, 4~01826~ 7~03117~ 9~06040~ 10~06923~'),
  (24859, 41, 15, 22, 'And they bring him unto the place Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, The place of a skull.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5342~ 3~846~ 4~1909~ 6~5117~ 7~1115~, 8~3739~ 9~2076~, 11~3177~, 13~5117~ 16~2898~.'),
  (3271, 3, 18, 15, 'Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy daughter in law: she is thy son''s wife; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.', '3~01540~ 5~06172~ 10~03618~: [12] 14~01121~ 15~0802~; 19~01540~ 21~06172~.'),
  (21890, 27, 5, 7, 'The king cried aloud to bring in the astrologers, the Chaldeans, and the soothsayers. And the king spake, and said to the wise men of Babylon, Whosoever shall read this writing, and shew me the interpretation thereof, shall be clothed with scarlet, and have a chain of gold about his neck, and shall be the third ruler in the kingdom.', '1~04430~ 2~07123~ 3~02429~ 5~05954~ 8~0826~, 10~03779~, 13~01505~. [14] 16~04430~ 17~06032~, 19~0560~ 22~02445~ [23] 25~0895~, 26~03606~ 27~0606~ 28~07123~ 29~01836~ 30~03792~, 32~02324~ 35~06591~ 39~03848~ 41~0711~, [43] 45~02002~ 47~01722~ 48~05922~ 50~06676~, 55~08523~ 56~07981~ 59~04437~.'),
  (24553, 41, 9, 4, 'And there appeared unto them Elias with Moses: and they were talking with Jesus.', '0~2532~ 2~3700~ 4~846~ 5~2243~ 6~4862~ 7~3475~: 8~2532~ 10~2258~ 11~4814~ 13~2424~.'),
  (5640, 5, 28, 23, 'And thy heaven that is over thy head shall be brass, and the earth that is under thee shall be iron.', '2~08064~ [4] 7~07218~ 10~05178~, 13~0776~ [18 19] 20~01270~.'),
  (21076, 26, 24, 11, 'Then set it empty upon the coals thereof, that the brass of it may be hot, and may burn, and that the filthiness of it may be molten in it, that the scum of it may be consumed.', '1~05975~ 3~07386~ 6~01513~ 10~05178~ 15~03179~, 18~02787~, [20] 22~02932~ 27~05413~ 29~08432~, [30] 32~02457~ 37~08552~.'),
  (31080, 66, 21, 11, 'Having the glory of God: and her light was like unto a stone most precious, even like a jasper stone, clear as crystal;', '0~2192~ 2~1391~ 4~2316~: 5~2532~ 6~846~ 7~5458~ [8] 9~3664~ 12~3037~ 14~5093~, 16~5613~ 18~2393~ 19~3037~, 22~2929~;'),
  (28568, 46, 9, 12, 'If others be partakers of this power over you, are not we rather? Nevertheless we have not used this power; but suffer all things, lest we should hinder the gospel of Christ.', '0~1487~ 1~243~ 3~3348~ [5] 6~1849~ 8~5216~, [9] 10~3756~ 11~2249~ 12~3123~? 13~235~ 15~5530~ 16~3756~ 17~5530~ 18~5026~ 19~1849~; 20~235~ 21~4722~ 23~3956~, 24~3363~ 26~1325~ 27~5100~* 28~1464~ 30~2098~ 32~5547~.'),
  (12066, 15, 2, 30, 'The children of Magbish, an hundred fifty and six.', '1~01121~ 3~04019~, 5~03967~ 6~02572~ 8~08337~.'),
  (10074, 12, 19, 5, 'So the servants of king Hezekiah came to Isaiah.', '2~05650~ 4~04428~ 5~02396~ 6~0935~ 8~03470~.'),
  (11549, 14, 17, 17, 'And of Benjamin; Eliada a mighty man of valour, and with him armed men with bow and shield two hundred thousand.', '2~01144~; 3~0450~ 6~01368~ 8~02428~, 13~05401~ 15~07198~ 17~04043~ 19~03967~ 20~0505~.'),
  (20870, 26, 18, 12, 'Hath oppressed the poor and needy, hath spoiled by violence, hath not restored the pledge, and hath lifted up his eyes to the idols, hath committed abomination,', '1~03238~ 3~06041~ 5~034~, 7~01497~ 9~01500~, 12~07725~ 14~02258~, 18~05375~ 20~05869~ 23~01544~, 25~06213~ 26~08441~,'),
  (29113, 48, 2, 16, 'Knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law, but by the faith of Jesus Christ, even we have believed in Jesus Christ, that we might be justified by the faith of Christ, and not by the works of the law: for by the works of the law shall no flesh be justified.', '0~1492~ 1~3754~ 3~444~ 4~1344~ 5~3756~ 6~1344~ 7~1537~ 9~2041~ 12~3551~, 13~3362~ 14~1223~ 16~4102~ 18~2424~ 19~5547~, 20~2532~ 21~2249~ 23~4100~ 24~1519~ 25~2424~ 26~5547~, 27~2443~ 31~1344~ 32~1537~ 34~4102~ 36~5547~, 37~2532~ 38~3756~ 39~1537~ 41~2041~ 44~3551~: 45~1360~ 46~1537~ 48~2041~ 51~3551~ 52~1344~ 53~3956~ 54~3756~* 55~4561~ 57~1344~.'),
  (27717, 44, 21, 37, 'And as Paul was to be led into the castle, he said unto the chief captain, May I speak unto thee? Who said, Canst thou speak Greek?', '0~5037~ 2~3972~ 5~3195~ 6~1521~ 7~1519~ 9~3925~, 11~3004~ 15~5506~, 16~1832~ 17~1487~* 18~3427~ 19~2036~ 20~5100~* 21~4314~ 22~4571~ 23~1161?~* 24~3588~ 25~5346~, 28~1097~ 29~1676~?'),
  (8311, 10, 12, 18, 'And it came to pass on the seventh day, that the child died. And the servants of David feared to tell him that the child was dead: for they said, Behold, while the child was yet alive, we spake unto him, and he would not hearken unto our voice: how will he then vex himself, if we tell him that the child is dead?', '7~07637~ 8~03117~, 11~03206~ 12~04191~. 15~05650~ 17~01732~ 18~03372~ 20~05046~ 24~03206~ 26~04191~: 29~0559~, 33~03206~ 36~02416~, 38~01696~ 45~08085~ 48~06963~: 52~06213~ 53~07451~ 54~06213~, 57~0559~ 61~03206~ 63~04191~?'),
  (15212, 19, 80, 5, 'Thou feedest them with the bread of tears; and givest them tears to drink in great measure.', '1~0398~ 5~03899~ 7~01832~; 11~01832~ 13~08248~ 16~07991~.'),
  (8222, 10, 8, 6, 'Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus: and the Syrians became servants to David, and brought gifts. And the LORD preserved David whithersoever he went.', '1~01732~ 2~07760~ 3~05333~ 5~0758~ 7~01834~: 10~0758~ 12~05650~ 14~01732~, [15] 16~05375~ 17~04503~. 20~03068~ 21~03467~ 22~01732~ 25~01980~.'),
  (29784, 54, 5, 5, 'Now she that is a widow indeed, and desolate, trusteth in God, and continueth in supplications and prayers night and day.', '0~1161~ 5~5503~ 6~3689~, 7~2532~ 8~3443~, 9~1679~ 10~1909~ 11~2316~, 12~2532~ 13~4357~ 15~1162~ 16~2532~ 17~4335~ 18~3571~ 19~2532~ 20~2250~.'),
  (3550, 3, 26, 21, 'And if ye walk contrary unto me, and will not hearken unto me; I will bring seven times more plagues upon you according to your sins.', '3~03212~ 4~07147~ 8~014~ 10~08085~ 15~03254~ 17~07651~ 18~03254~ 19~04347~ 25~02403~.'),
  (13019, 18, 7, 2, 'As a servant earnestly desireth the shadow, and as an hireling looketh for the reward of his work:', '2~05650~ 4~07602~ 6~06738~, 10~07916~ 11~06960~ [13 15] 17~06467~:'),
  (24186, 40, 27, 47, 'Some of them that stood there, when they heard that, said, This man calleth for Elias.', '0~1161~ 2~5100~ 4~2476~ 5~1563~, 8~191~ [9] 10~3004~ 11~3754~,* 12~3778~ [13] 15~5455~ 16~2243~.'),
  (1665, 2, 6, 5, 'And I have also heard the groaning of the children of Israel, whom the Egyptians keep in bondage; and I have remembered my covenant.', '4~08085~ 6~05009~ 9~01121~ 11~03478~, 12~0834~ 14~04714~ 17~05647~; 21~02142~ 23~01285~.'),
  (6164, 6, 13, 4, 'From the south, all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah that is beside the Sidonians unto Aphek, to the borders of the Amorites:', '2~08486~, 5~0776~ 8~03669~, 10~04632~ [12] 15~06722~, 17~0663~, 20~01366~ 23~0567~:'),
  (61, 1, 3, 5, 'For God doth know that in the day ye eat thereof, then your eyes shall be opened, and ye shall be as gods, knowing good and evil.', '1~0430~ 3~03045~ 7~03117~ 9~0398~ 13~05869~ 16~06491~, 22~0430~, 23~03045~ 24~02896~ 26~07451~.'),
  (30830, 66, 7, 4, 'And I heard the number of them which were sealed: and there were sealed an hundred and forty and four thousand of all the tribes of the children of Israel.', '0~2532~ 2~191~ 4~706~ 9~4972~: [10 12] 13~4972~ 15~1540~ [16] 17~5062~ [18] 19~5064~ 20~5505~ 21~1537~ 22~3956~ 24~5443~ 27~5207~ 29~2474~.'),
  (14379, 19, 33, 4, 'For the word of the LORD is right; and all his works are done in truth.', '2~01697~ 5~03068~ [6] 7~03477~; 11~04639~ [12 13] 15~0530~.'),
  (9641, 12, 4, 30, 'And the mother of the child said, As the LORD liveth, and as thy soul liveth, I will not leave thee. And he arose, and followed her.', '2~0517~ 5~05288~ 6~0559~, [7] 9~03068~ 10~02416~, [12] 14~05315~ 15~02416~, 19~05800~ 23~06965~, 25~03212~ 26~0310~*'),
  (26262, 43, 5, 37, 'And the Father himself, which hath sent me, hath borne witness of me. Ye have neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his shape.', '0~2532~ 2~3962~ 3~846~, 6~3992~ 7~3165~, 10~3140~ 11~4012~ 12~1700~. 14~191~ 15~3777~ 16~191~ 17~846~ 18~5456~ 21~4455~, 22~3777~ 23~3708~ 24~846~ 25~1491~.'),
  (27724, 44, 22, 4, 'And I persecuted this way unto the death, binding and delivering into prisons both men and women.', '1~3739~ 2~1377~ 3~5026~ 4~3598~ 5~891~ 7~2288~, 8~1195~ 9~2532~ 10~3860~ 11~1519~ 12~5438~ 13~5037~ 14~435~ 15~2532~ 16~1135~.'),
  (18068, 23, 22, 7, 'And it shall come to pass, that thy choicest valleys shall be full of chariots, and the horsemen shall set themselves in array at the gate.', '[6] 8~04005~ 9~06010~ 12~04390~ 14~07393~, 17~06571~ 19~07896~ 22~07896~ 25~08179~.'),
  (30979, 66, 16, 9, 'And men were scorched with great heat, and blasphemed the name of God, which hath power over these plagues: and they repented not to give him glory.', '0~2532~ 1~444~ 3~2739~ 5~3173~ 6~2738~, 7~2532~ 8~987~ 10~3686~ 12~2316~, 13~3588~ 14~2192~ 15~1849~ 16~1909~ 17~5025~ 18~4127~: 19~2532~ 21~3340~ 22~3756~ 24~1325~ 25~846~ 26~1391~.'),
  (18463, 23, 41, 3, 'He pursued them, and passed safely; even by the way that he had not gone with his feet.', '1~07291~ [3] 4~05674~ 5~07965~; [6] 9~0734~ [10] 14~0935~ 17~07272~.'),
  (17211, 20, 28, 6, 'Better is the poor that walketh in his uprightness, than he that is perverse in his ways, though he be rich.', '&para; 0~02896~ [1] 3~07326~ 5~01980~ 8~08537~, [10 12] 13~06141~ [14 15] 16~01870~, [19] 20~06223~.'),
  (21700, 26, 47, 12, 'And by the river upon the bank thereof, on this side and on that side, shall grow all trees for meat, whose leaf shall not fade, neither shall the fruit thereof be consumed: it shall bring forth new fruit according to his months, because their waters they issued out of the sanctuary: and the fruit thereof shall be for meat, and the leaf thereof for medicine.', '3~05158~ 6~08193~ 16~05927~ 18~06086~ 20~03978~, 22~05929~ 25~05034~, 29~06529~ 32~08552~: 38~01069~ 42~02320~, 45~04325~ 48~03318~ 51~04720~: 54~06529~ 59~03978~, 62~05929~ 65~08644~.'),
  (18527, 23, 43, 13, 'Yea, before the day was I am he; and there is none that can deliver out of my hand: I will work, and who shall let it?', '3~03117~ [4] [6] [9 10] 14~05337~ 18~03027~: 21~06466~, 25~07725~'),
  (23390, 40, 9, 1, 'And he entered into a ship, and passed over, and came into his own city.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1684~ 3~1519~ 5~4143~, 8~1276~, 9~2532~ 10~2064~ 11~1519~ 13~2398~ 14~4172~.'),
  (8647, 10, 22, 37, 'Thou hast enlarged my steps under me; so that my feet did not slip.', '2~07337~ 4~06806~ 10~07166~ 13~04571~.'),
  (27147, 44, 7, 15, 'So Jacob went down into Egypt, and died, he, and our fathers,', '0~1161~ 1~2384~ 3~2597~ 4~1519~ 5~125~, 6~2532~ 7~5053~, 8~846~, 9~2532~ 10~2257~ 11~3962~,'),
  (14894, 19, 66, 12, 'Thou hast caused men to ride over our heads; we went through fire and through water: but thou broughtest us out into a wealthy place.', '3~0582~ 5~07392~ 8~07218~; 10~0935~ 12~0784~ 15~04325~: 20~03318~ 23~07310~ [24]');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (22384, 30, 1, 11, 'Thus saith the LORD; For three transgressions of Edom, and for four, I will not turn away the punishment thereof; because he did pursue his brother with the sword, and did cast off all pity, and his anger did tear perpetually, and he kept his wrath for ever:', '1~0559~ 3~03068~; 5~07969~ 6~06588~ 8~0123~, 11~0702~, 16~07725~ [17 18] 23~07291~ 25~0251~ 28~02719~, 32~07843~ 34~07356~, 37~0639~ 39~02963~ 40~05703~, 43~08104~ 45~05678~ 47~05331~:'),
  (2160, 2, 23, 11, 'But the seventh year thou shalt let it rest and lie still; that the poor of thy people may eat: and what they leave the beasts of the field shall eat. In like manner thou shalt deal with thy vineyard, and with thy oliveyard.', '2~07637~ [3] 8~08058~ 10~05203~ 14~034~ 17~05971~ 19~0398~: 23~03499~ 25~02416~ 28~07704~ 30~0398~. 36~06213~ 39~03754~, [40] 43~02132~.'),
  (13668, 18, 33, 9, 'I am clean without transgression, I am innocent; neither is there iniquity in me.', '2~02134~ 4~06588~, [6] 7~02643~; [9 10] 11~05771~'),
  (29155, 48, 4, 8, 'Howbeit then, when ye knew not God, ye did service unto them which by nature are no gods.', '&para; 0~235~ 1~3303~ 2~5119~,* 5~1492~ 6~3756~ 7~2316~, 10~1398~ 15~5449~ 16~5607~ 17~3361~ 18~2316~.'),
  (24678, 41, 11, 27, 'And they come again to Jerusalem: and as he was walking in the temple, there come to him the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders,', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~2064~ 3~3825~ 4~1519~ 5~2414~: 6~2532~ 8~846~ 10~4043~ 11~1722~ 13~2411~, 15~2064~ 16~4314~ 17~846~ 20~749~, 21~2532~ 23~1122~, 24~2532~ 26~4245~,'),
  (27068, 44, 4, 30, 'By stretching forth thine hand to heal; and that signs and wonders may be done by the name of thy holy child Jesus.', '0~4571~ 1~1722~ 2~1614~ 3~4675~ 4~5495~ 5~1519~ 6~2392~; 7~2532~ 9~4592~ 10~2532~ 11~5059~ 14~1096~ 15~1223~ 17~3686~ 19~4675~ 20~40~ 21~3816~ 22~2424~.'),
  (15250, 19, 82, 8, 'Arise, O God, judge the earth: for thou shalt inherit all nations.', '0~06965~, 2~0430~, 3~08199~ 5~0776~: 9~05157~ 11~01471~.'),
  (16562, 20, 6, 13, 'He winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers;', '1~07169~ 4~05869~, 6~04448~ 9~07272~, 11~03384~ 14~0676~;'),
  (5886, 6, 2, 11, 'And as soon as we had heard these things, our hearts did melt, neither did there remain any more courage in any man, because of you: for the LORD your God, he is God in heaven above, and in earth beneath.', '6~08085~ [7 8] 10~03824~ 12~04549~, 16~06965~ 19~07307~ 22~0376~, 23~06440~ 28~03068~ 30~0430~, [32] 33~0430~ 35~08064~ 36~04605~, 39~0776~'),
  (14898, 19, 66, 16, 'Come and hear, all ye that fear God, and I will declare what he hath done for my soul.', '0~03212~ [1] 2~08085~, 6~03373~ 7~0430~, 11~05608~ 15~06213~ 18~05315~.'),
  (27181, 44, 7, 49, 'Heaven is my throne, and earth is my footstool: what house will ye build me? saith the Lord: or what is the place of my rest?', '0~3772~ [1] 2~3427~ 3~2362~, 4~1161~ 5~1093~ [6] 7~3450~ 8~5286~ 9~4228~:* 10~4169~ 11~3624~ 14~3618~ 15~3427~? 16~3004~ 18~2962~: 19~2228~ 20~5101~ [21] 23~5117~ 25~3450~ 26~2663~?'),
  (30186, 58, 10, 37, 'For yet a little while, and he that shall come will come, and will not tarry.', '0~1063~ 1~2089~ 3~3397~ 4~3745~ 5~3745~,* 10~2064~ 12~2240~, 13~2532~ 14~5549~ 15~3756~ 16~5549~.'),
  (15463, 19, 94, 23, 'And he shall bring upon them their own iniquity, and shall cut them off in their own wickedness; yea, the LORD our God shall cut them off.', '3~07725~ 8~0205~, 13~06789~ 17~07451~; [18] 20~03068~ 22~0430~ 26~06789~.'),
  (11593, 14, 19, 8, 'Moreover in Jerusalem did Jehoshaphat set of the Levites, and of the priests, and of the chief of the fathers of Israel, for the judgment of the LORD, and for controversies, when they returned to Jerusalem.', '2~03389~ 4~03092~ 5~05975~ 8~03881~, [10] 12~03548~, 16~07218~ 19~01~ 21~03478~, 24~04941~ 27~03068~, 30~07379~, 33~07725~ 35~03389~.'),
  (29857, 55, 2, 14, 'Of these things put them in remembrance, charging them before the Lord that they strive not about words to no profit, but to the subverting of the hearers.', '&para; 2~5023~ [4] 6~5279~, 7~1263~ [8] 9~1799~ 11~2962~ 14~3054~ 15~3361~ 17~3054~ 18~1519~ 19~3762~ 20~5539~, [21] 22~1909~ 24~2692~ 27~191~.'),
  (16011, 19, 119, 104, 'Through thy precepts I get understanding: therefore I hate every false way.', '2~06490~ 5~0995~: 8~08130~ 10~08267~ 11~0734~.'),
  (4451, 4, 23, 30, 'And Balak did as Balaam had said, and offered a bullock and a ram on every altar.', '1~01111~ 2~06213~ 4~01109~ 6~0559~, 8~05927~ 10~06499~ 13~0352~ [15] 16~04196~.'),
  (9595, 12, 3, 11, 'But Jehoshaphat said, Is there not here a prophet of the LORD, that we may inquire of the LORD by him? And one of the king of Israel''s servants answered and said, Here is Elisha the son of Shaphat, which poured water on the hands of Elijah.', '1~03092~ 2~0559~, [3 4] 8~05030~ 11~03068~, 15~01875~ 18~03068~ 22~0259~ 25~04428~ 27~03478~ 28~05650~ 29~06030~ 31~0559~, [33] 34~0477~ 36~01121~ 38~08202~, 40~03332~ 41~04325~ 44~03027~ 46~0452~.'),
  (5468, 5, 21, 15, 'If a man have two wives, one beloved, and another hated, and they have born him children, both the beloved and the hated; and if the firstborn son be hers that was hated:', '&para; 2~0376~ 4~08147~ 5~0802~, 6~0259~ 7~0157~, 9~0259~ 10~08130~, 14~03205~ 16~01121~, [17] 19~0157~ 22~08130~; [24] 26~01060~ 27~01121~ 32~08146~:'),
  (3603, 3, 27, 28, 'Notwithstanding no devoted thing, that a man shall devote unto the LORD of all that he hath, both of man and beast, and of the field of his possession, shall be sold or redeemed: every devoted thing is most holy unto the LORD.', '3~02764~, 6~0376~ 8~02763~ 11~03068~ [17] 19~0120~ 21~0929~, 25~07704~ 28~0272~, 31~04376~ 33~01350~: 36~02764~ [37] 38~06944~ 39~06944~ 42~03068~.'),
  (3807, 4, 5, 10, 'And every man''s hallowed things shall be his: whatsoever any man giveth the priest, it shall be his.', '2~0376~ 4~06944~ 10~0376~ 11~05414~ 13~03548~,'),
  (300, 1, 11, 31, 'And Terah took Abram his son, and Lot the son of Haran his son''s son, and Sarai his daughter in law, his son Abram''s wife; and they went forth with them from Ur of the Chaldees, to go into the land of Canaan; and they came unto Haran, and dwelt there.', '1~08646~ 2~03947~ 3~087~ 5~01121~, 7~03876~ 9~01121~ 11~02039~ 13~01121~ 14~01121~, 16~08297~ 20~03618~, 22~01121~ 23~087~ 24~0802~; 28~03318~ 32~0218~ 35~03778~, 37~03212~ 40~0776~ 42~03667~; 45~0935~ 47~02771~, 49~03427~'),
  (12351, 16, 3, 15, 'But the gate of the fountain repaired Shallun the son of Colhozeh, the ruler of part of Mizpah; he built it, and covered it, and set up the doors thereof, the locks thereof, and the bars thereof, and the wall of the pool of Siloah by the king''s garden, and unto the stairs that go down from the city of David.', '2~08179~ 5~05869~ 6~02388~ 7~07968~ 9~01121~ 11~03626~, 13~08269~ 15~06418~ 17~04709~; 19~01129~ 22~02926~ 26~05975~ 28~01817~ 31~04514~ 35~01280~ 39~02346~ 42~01295~ 44~07975~ 47~04428~ 48~01588~, 52~04609~ 55~03381~ 58~05892~ 60~01732~.'),
  (7850, 9, 24, 4, 'And the men of David said unto him, Behold the day of which the LORD said unto thee, Behold, I will deliver thine enemy into thine hand, that thou mayest do to him as it shall seem good unto thee. Then David arose, and cut off the skirt of Saul''s robe privily.', '2~0582~ 4~01732~ 5~0559~ 10~03117~ 14~03068~ 15~0559~ 21~05414~ 23~0341~ 26~03027~, 30~06213~ 37~03190~ 39~05869~. 41~01732~ 42~06965~, 45~03772~ 47~03671~ 49~07586~ 50~04598~ 51~03909~.'),
  (6822, 7, 10, 4, 'And he had thirty sons that rode on thirty ass colts, and they had thirty cities, which are called Havothjair unto this day, which are in the land of Gilead.', '3~07970~ 4~01121~ 6~07392~ 8~07970~ 10~05895~, 14~07970~ 15~05892~, 18~07121~ 19~02334~ 22~03117~, [24] 27~0776~ 29~01568~.'),
  (5695, 5, 29, 10, 'Ye stand this day all of you before the LORD your God; your captains of your tribes, your elders, and your officers, with all the men of Israel,', '&para; 1~05324~ 3~03117~ 7~06440~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~; 13~07218~ 16~07626~, 18~02205~, 21~07860~, [22] 25~0376~ 27~03478~,'),
  (22482, 30, 7, 9, 'And the high places of Isaac shall be desolate, and the sanctuaries of Israel shall be laid waste; and I will rise against the house of Jeroboam with the sword.', '3~01116~ 5~03446~ 8~08074~, 11~04720~ 13~03478~ 17~02717~; 21~06965~ 24~01004~ 26~03379~ 29~02719~.'),
  (28900, 47, 5, 7, '(For we walk by faith, not by sight:)', '0~(1063~ 2~4043~ 3~1223~ 4~4102~, 5~3756~ 6~1223~ 7~1491~:)'),
  (8366, 10, 14, 3, 'And come to the king, and speak on this manner unto him. So Joab put the words in her mouth.', '1~0935~ 4~04428~, 6~01696~ 9~01697~ 13~03097~ 14~07760~ 16~01697~ 19~06310~.'),
  (16916, 20, 18, 6, 'A fool''s lips enter into contention, and his mouth calleth for strokes.', '&para; 1~03684~ 2~08193~ 3~0935~ 5~07379~, 8~06310~ 9~07121~ 11~04112~.'),
  (4838, 4, 34, 16, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (8517, 10, 18, 31, 'And, behold, Cushi came; and Cushi said, Tidings, my lord the king: for the LORD hath avenged thee this day of all them that rose up against thee.', '2~03569~ 3~0935~; 5~03569~ 6~0559~, 7~01319~, 9~0113~ 11~04428~: 14~03068~ 16~08199~ 19~03117~ 22~03027~ 25~06965~'),
  (9164, 11, 12, 5, 'And he said unto them, Depart yet for three days, then come again to me. And the people departed.', '2~0559~ 5~03212~ [7] 8~07969~ 9~03117~, 12~07725~ 17~05971~ 18~03212~.'),
  (13567, 18, 30, 1, 'But now they that are younger than I have me in derision, whose fathers I would have disdained to have set with the dogs of my flock.', '&para; [2 4] 5~03117~ 6~06810~ 11~07832~, 13~01~ 17~03988~ 20~07896~ 23~03611~ 26~06629~.'),
  (12806, 17, 6, 4, 'And the king said, Who is in the court? Now Haman was come into the outward court of the king''s house, to speak unto the king to hang Mordecai on the gallows that he had prepared for him.', '&para; 2~04428~ 3~0559~, [5] 8~02691~? 10~02001~ 12~0935~ 15~02435~ 16~02691~ 19~04428~ 20~01004~, 22~0559~ 25~04428~ 27~08518~ 28~04782~ 31~06086~ 35~03559~'),
  (26798, 43, 17, 24, 'Father, I will that they also, whom thou hast given me, be with me where I am; that they may behold my glory, which thou hast given me: for thou lovedst me before the foundation of the world.', '&para; 0~3962~, 2~2309~ 3~2443~ 5~2548~, 6~3739~ 9~1325~ 10~3427~, 11~5600~ 12~3326~ 13~1700~ 14~3699~ 15~1473~ 16~1510~; 17~2443~ 20~2334~ 21~1699~ 22~1391~, 23~3739~ 26~1325~ 27~3427~: 28~3754~ 30~25~ 31~3165~ 32~4253~ 34~2602~ 37~2889~.'),
  (22769, 35, 2, 12, 'Woe to him that buildeth a town with blood, and stablisheth a city by iniquity!', '0~01945~ 4~01129~ 6~05892~ 8~01818~, 10~03559~ 12~07151~ 14~05766~!'),
  (1523, 1, 50, 12, 'And his sons did unto him according as he commanded them:', '2~01121~ 3~06213~ 9~06680~'),
  (13363, 18, 20, 28, 'The increase of his house shall depart, and his goods shall flow away in the day of his wrath.', '1~02981~ 4~01004~ 6~01540~, [7 9] 12~05064~ 15~03117~ 18~0639~.'),
  (9995, 12, 17, 4, 'And the king of Assyria found conspiracy in Hoshea: for he had sent messengers to So king of Egypt, and brought no present to the king of Assyria, as he had done year by year: therefore the king of Assyria shut him up, and bound him in prison.', '2~04428~ 4~0804~ 5~04672~ 6~07195~ 8~01954~: 12~07971~ 13~04397~ 15~05471~ 16~04428~ 18~04714~, 20~05927~ 22~04503~ 25~04428~ 27~0804~, [29 31] 32~08141~ 34~08141~: 37~04428~ 39~0804~ 42~06113~, 44~0631~ 47~03608~ 48~01004~.*'),
  (18092, 23, 23, 6, 'Pass ye over to Tarshish; howl, ye inhabitants of the isle.', '2~05674~ 4~08659~; 5~03213~, 7~03427~ 10~0339~.'),
  (29232, 49, 1, 10, 'That in the dispensation of the fulness of times he might gather together in one all things in Christ, both which are in heaven, and which are on earth; even in him:', '1~1519~ 3~3622~ 6~4138~ 8~2540~ 14~346~ 16~3956~ 17~1722~ 18~5547~, 19~5037~ 20~3588~ 22~1722~ 23~3772~, 24~2532~ 25~3588~ 27~1909~ 28~1093~; [29] 30~1722~ 31~846~:'),
  (22303, 29, 1, 3, 'Tell ye your children of it, and let your children tell their children, and their children another generation.', '0~05608~ 3~01121~ [7] 9~01121~ [10] 12~01121~, 15~01121~ 16~0312~ 17~01755~.'),
  (18214, 23, 29, 12, 'And the book is delivered to him that is not learned, saying, Read this, I pray thee: and he saith, I am not learned.', '2~05612~ 4~05414~ 10~03045~ 11~05612~,* 12~0559~, 13~07121~ 20~0559~, 24~03045~.'),
  (10913, 13, 18, 15, 'And Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the host; and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud, recorder.', '1~03097~ 3~01121~ 5~06870~ [6] 9~06635~; 11~03092~ 13~01121~ 15~0286~, 16~02142~.'),
  (15079, 19, 74, 22, 'Arise, O God, plead thine own cause: remember how the foolish man reproacheth thee daily.', '0~06965~, 2~0430~, 3~07378~ 6~07379~: 7~02142~ 11~05036~ 12~02781~ 14~03117~.'),
  (23020, 38, 9, 12, 'Turn you to the strong hold, ye prisoners of hope: even to day do I declare that I will render double unto thee;', '&para; 0~07725~ 5~01225~, 7~0615~ 9~08615~: 12~03117~ 15~05046~ [16] 19~07725~ 20~04932~'),
  (5818, 5, 33, 2, 'And he said, The LORD came from Sinai, and rose up from Seir unto them; he shined forth from mount Paran, and he came with ten thousands of saints: from his right hand went a fiery law for them.', '2~0559~, 4~03068~ 5~0935~ 7~05514~, 10~02224~ 12~08165~ 17~03313~ 19~02022~ 20~06290~, 23~0857~ 26~07233~ 28~06944~: 32~03225~ [33] 35~0799~ 36~0784~* 37~01881~'),
  (13954, 19, 1, 6, 'For the LORD knoweth the way of the righteous: but the way of the ungodly shall perish.', '2~03068~ 3~03045~ 5~01870~ 8~06662~: 11~01870~ 14~07563~ 16~06~.'),
  (19004, 24, 2, 30, 'In vain have I smitten your children; they received no correction: your own sword hath devoured your prophets, like a destroying lion.', '1~07723~ 4~05221~ 6~01121~; 8~03947~ 10~04148~: 13~02719~ 15~0398~ 17~05030~, 20~07843~ 21~0738~.'),
  (21114, 26, 26, 5, 'It shall be a place for the spreading of nets in the midst of the sea: for I have spoken it, saith the Lord GOD: and it shall become a spoil to the nations.', '[3 5] 7~04894~ 9~02764~ 12~08432~ 15~03220~: 19~01696~ [20] 21~05002~ 23~0136~ 24~03069~: 30~0957~ 33~01471~.'),
  (14040, 19, 9, 10, 'And they that know thy name will put their trust in thee: for thou, LORD, hast not forsaken them that seek thee.', '3~03045~ 5~08034~ 9~0982~ 14~03068~, 17~05800~ 20~01875~'),
  (13778, 18, 36, 33, 'The noise thereof sheweth concerning it, the cattle also concerning the vapour.', '1~07452~ 3~05046~ 7~04735~ 11~05927~.'),
  (26806, 43, 18, 6, 'As soon then as he had said unto them, I am he, they went backward, and fell to the ground.', '1~5613~ 2~3767~ 6~2036~ 8~846~ 9~3754~,* 10~1473~ 11~1510~ [12] 14~565~ 15~3694~ 16~1519~,* 17~2532~ 18~4098~ 21~5476~.'),
  (22749, 35, 1, 9, 'They shall come all for violence: their faces shall sup up as the east wind, and they shall gather the captivity as the sand.', '2~0935~ 5~02555~: 7~06440~ 10~04041~ [11] 14~06921~, 18~0622~ 20~07628~ 23~02344~.'),
  (8912, 11, 6, 8, 'The door for the middle chamber was in the right side of the house: and they went up with winding stairs into the middle chamber, and out of the middle into the third.', '1~06607~ 4~08484~ 5~06763~ [6] 9~03233~ 10~03802~ 13~01004~: 17~05927~ 20~03883~ 23~08484~ [24] 29~08484~ 32~07992~.'),
  (7757, 9, 20, 20, 'And I will shoot three arrows on the side thereof, as though I shot at a mark.', '3~03384~ 4~07969~ 5~02671~ 8~06654~ [9] 13~07971~ 16~04307~.'),
  (30804, 66, 5, 9, 'And they sung a new song, saying, Thou art worthy to take the book, and to open the seals thereof: for thou wast slain, and hast redeemed us to God by thy blood out of every kindred, and tongue, and people, and nation;', '0~2532~ 2~103~ 4~2537~ 5~5603~, 6~3004~, 8~1488~ 9~514~ 11~2983~ 13~975~, 14~2532~ 16~455~ 18~4973~ 19~846~: 20~3754~ 23~4969~, 24~2532~ 26~59~ 27~2248~ 29~2316~ 30~1722~ 31~4675~ 32~129~ 34~1537~ 35~3956~ 36~5443~, 37~2532~ 38~1100~, 39~2532~ 40~2992~, 41~2532~ 42~1484~;'),
  (12519, 16, 8, 17, 'And all the congregation of them that were come again out of the captivity made booths, and sat under the booths: for since the days of Jeshua the son of Nun unto that day had not the children of Israel done so. And there was very great gladness.', '3~06951~ 9~07725~ 13~07628~ 14~06213~ 15~05521~, 17~03427~ 20~05521~: 24~03117~ 26~03442~ 28~01121~ 30~05126~ 33~03117~ 37~01121~ 39~03478~ 41~06213~. 45~03966~ 46~01419~ 47~08057~.'),
  (12846, 17, 9, 3, 'And all the rulers of the provinces, and the lieutenants, and the deputies, and officers of the king, helped the Jews; because the fear of Mordecai fell upon them.', '3~08269~ 6~04082~, 9~0323~, 12~06346~, 14~06213~ 15~04399~* 18~04428~, 19~05375~ 21~03064~; 24~06343~ 26~04782~ 27~05307~'),
  (27946, 44, 28, 31, 'Preaching the kingdom of God, and teaching those things which concern the Lord Jesus Christ, with all confidence, no man forbidding him.', '0~2784~ 2~932~ 4~2316~, 5~2532~ 6~1321~ 10~4012~ 12~2962~ 13~2424~ 14~5547~, 15~3326~ 16~3956~ 17~3954~, 21~209~.'),
  (4171, 4, 15, 13, 'All that are born of the country shall do these things after this manner, in offering an offering made by fire, of a sweet savour unto the LORD.', '6~0249~ 8~06213~ 15~07126~ 20~0801~, 23~05207~ 24~07381~ 27~03068~.'),
  (30778, 66, 3, 16, 'So then because thou art lukewarm, and neither cold nor hot, I will spue thee out of my mouth.', '0~3779~ 2~3754~ 4~1488~ 5~5513~, 6~2532~ 7~3777~ 8~5593~ 9~3777~ 10~2200~, 12~3195~ 13~1692~ 14~4571~ 16~1537~ 17~3450~ 18~4750~.'),
  (5458, 5, 21, 5, 'And the priests the sons of Levi shall come near; for them the LORD thy God hath chosen to minister unto him, and to bless in the name of the LORD; and by their word shall every controversy and every stroke be tried:', '2~03548~ 4~01121~ 6~03878~ 9~05066~; 13~03068~ 15~0430~ 17~0977~ 19~08334~ 24~01288~ 27~08034~ 30~03068~; 34~06310~ 37~07379~ 40~05061~ [42]'),
  (22248, 28, 10, 14, 'Therefore shall a tumult arise among thy people, and all thy fortresses shall be spoiled, as Shalman spoiled Betharbel in the day of battle: the mother was dashed in pieces upon her children.', '3~07588~ 4~06965~ 7~05971~, 11~04013~ 14~07703~, 16~08020~ 17~07701~ 18~01009~ 21~03117~ 23~04421~: 25~0517~ 29~07376~ [31] 32~01121~.'),
  (9844, 12, 11, 7, 'And two parts of all you that go forth on the sabbath, even they shall keep the watch of the house of the LORD about the king.', '1~08147~ 2~03027~ 8~03318~ 11~07676~, 15~08104~ 17~04931~ 20~01004~ 23~03068~ 24~0413~ 26~04428~.'),
  (28888, 47, 4, 13, 'We having the same spirit of faith, according as it is written, I believed, and therefore have I spoken; we also believe, and therefore speak;', '0~1161~ 1~2192~ 3~846~ 4~4151~ 6~4102~, 8~2596~ 11~1125~, 13~4100~, 15~1352~ 18~2980~; 19~2249~ 20~2532~ 21~4100~, 22~2532~ 23~1352~ 24~2980~;'),
  (4414, 4, 22, 34, 'And Balaam said unto the angel of the LORD, I have sinned; for I knew not that thou stoodest in the way against me: now therefore, if it displease thee, I will get me back again.', '1~01109~ 2~0559~ 5~04397~ 8~03068~, 11~02398~; 14~03045~ 18~05324~ 21~01870~ 22~07125~ 29~07489~ 30~05869~,* 36~07725~.'),
  (13935, 18, 42, 4, 'Hear, I beseech thee, and I will speak: I will demand of thee, and declare thou unto me.', '0~08085~, 7~01696~: 10~07592~ 14~03045~'),
  (25675, 42, 17, 10, 'So likewise ye, when ye shall have done all those things which are commanded you, say, We are unprofitable servants: we have done that which was our duty to do.', '0~3779~ 1~2532~ 2~5210~, 3~3752~ 7~4160~ 8~3956~ 13~1299~ 14~5213~, 15~3004~ 16~3754~,* 18~2070~ 19~888~ 20~1401~ 21~3754~:* 24~4160~ 26~3739~ 29~3784~ 31~4160~.'),
  (9383, 11, 18, 34, 'And he said, Do it the second time. And they did it the second time. And he said, Do it the third time. And they did it the third time.', '2~0559~, [4] 7~08138~. [11] 14~08138~. 17~0559~, [19] 22~08027~. [26] 29~08027~.'),
  (5179, 5, 9, 16, 'And I looked, and, behold, ye had sinned against the LORD your God, and had made you a molten calf: ye had turned aside quickly out of the way which the LORD had commanded you.', '2~07200~, 7~02398~ 10~03068~ 12~0430~, [13] 15~06213~ 18~04541~ 19~05695~: 23~05493~ 24~04118~ 28~01870~ 31~03068~ 33~06680~'),
  (10176, 12, 23, 3, 'And the king stood by a pillar, and made a covenant before the LORD, to walk after the LORD, and to keep his commandments and his testimonies and his statutes with all their heart and all their soul, to perform the words of this covenant that were written in this book. And all the people stood to the covenant.', '2~04428~ 3~05975~ 6~05982~, 8~03772~ 10~01285~ 11~06440~ 13~03068~, 15~03212~ 16~0310~ 18~03068~, 21~08104~ 23~04687~ 26~05715~ 29~02708~ [32] 33~03820~ [36] 37~05315~, 39~06965~ 41~01697~ 44~01285~ 47~03789~ 50~05612~. 54~05971~ 55~05975~ 58~01285~.'),
  (28354, 45, 16, 2, 'That ye receive her in the Lord, as becometh saints, and that ye assist her in whatsoever business she hath need of you: for she hath been a succourer of many, and of myself also.', '0~2443~ 2~4327~ 3~846~ 4~1722~ 6~2962~, 8~516~ 9~40~, 10~2532~ 13~3936~ 14~846~ 15~1722~ 16~302~ 17~3739~* 18~4229~ 21~5535~ 23~5216~: 24~1063~ 25~3778~ 26~846~* 28~1096~ 30~4368~ 32~4183~, 33~2532~ 35~1700~ 36~846~* 37~2532~.'),
  (777, 1, 27, 46, 'And Rebekah said to Isaac, I am weary of my life because of the daughters of Heth: if Jacob take a wife of the daughters of Heth, such as these which are of the daughters of the land, what good shall my life do me?', '1~07259~ 2~0559~ 4~03327~, 7~06973~ 10~02416~ 11~06440~ 14~01323~ 16~02845~: 18~03290~ 19~03947~ 21~0802~ 24~01323~ 26~02845~, [30 31] 34~01323~ 37~0776~, 39~04100~ 42~02416~'),
  (19630, 24, 28, 3, 'Within two full years will I bring again into this place all the vessels of the LORD''S house, that Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon took away from this place, and carried them to Babylon:', '2~03117~ 3~08141~ 7~07725~ 10~04725~ 13~03627~ 16~03068~ 17~01004~, 19~05019~ 20~04428~ 22~0894~ 24~03947~ 27~04725~, 29~0935~ 32~0894~:'),
  (29797, 54, 5, 18, 'For the scripture saith, Thou shalt not muzzle the ox that treadeth out the corn. And, The labourer is worthy of his reward.', '0~1063~ 2~1124~ 3~3004~, 5~5392~ 6~3756~ 7~5392~ 9~1016~ 14~248~. 15~2532~, 17~2040~ [18] 19~514~ 21~846~ 22~3408~.'),
  (3492, 3, 25, 18, 'Wherefore ye shall do my statutes, and keep my judgments, and do them; and ye shall dwell in the land in safety.', '3~06213~ 5~02708~, 7~08104~ 9~04941~, 11~06213~ 16~03427~ 19~0776~ 21~0983~.'),
  (9877, 12, 12, 19, 'And the rest of the acts of Joash, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?', '2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~03101~, 12~06213~, [13] 16~03789~ 19~05612~ 22~03117~ 23~01697~ 25~04428~ 27~03063~?'),
  (12614, 16, 11, 17, 'And Mattaniah the son of Micha, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, was the principal to begin the thanksgiving in prayer: and Bakbukiah the second among his brethren, and Abda the son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun.', '1~04983~ 3~01121~ 5~04316~, 7~01121~ 9~02067~, 11~01121~ 13~0623~, [14] 16~07218~ 18~08462~ 20~03034~ 22~08605~: 24~01229~ 26~04932~ 29~0251~, 31~05653~ 33~01121~ 35~08051~, 37~01121~ 39~01559~, 41~01121~ 43~03038~.'),
  (28119, 45, 7, 12, 'Wherefore the law is holy, and the commandment holy, and just, and good.', '0~3303~ 1~5620~ 2~3551~ [3] 4~40~, 5~2532~ 7~1785~ 8~40~, 9~2532~ 10~1342~, 11~2532~ 12~18~.'),
  (25476, 42, 12, 4, 'And I say unto you my friends, Be not afraid of them that kill the body, and after that have no more that they can do.', '0~1161~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~ 5~3450~ 6~5384~, 7~5399~ 8~3361~ 9~5399~ 11~575~ 13~615~ 15~4983~, 16~2532~ 17~3326~ 18~5023~ 19~2192~ 20~5100~ 21~3361~* 22~4055~ 26~4160~.'),
  (10986, 13, 22, 14, 'Now, behold, in my trouble I have prepared for the house of the LORD an hundred thousand talents of gold, and a thousand thousand talents of silver; and of brass and iron without weight; for it is in abundance: timber also and stone have I prepared; and thou mayest add thereto.', '4~06040~ 7~03559~ 10~01004~ 13~03068~ 15~03967~ 16~0505~ 17~03603~ 19~02091~, 22~0505~ 23~0505~ 24~03603~ 26~03701~; 29~05178~ 31~01270~ 33~04948~; 38~07230~: 39~06086~ 42~068~ 45~03559~; 49~03254~'),
  (14504, 19, 38, 5, 'My wounds stink and are corrupt because of my foolishness.', '1~02250~ 2~0887~ [3] 5~04743~ 6~06440~ 9~0200~.'),
  (25820, 42, 20, 27, 'Then came to him certain of the Sadducees, which deny that there is any resurrection; and they asked him,', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~4334~ [3] 4~5100~ 7~4523~, 8~3588~ 9~483~ 12~1511~ 13~3361~ 14~386~; 17~1905~ 18~846~,'),
  (24709, 41, 12, 25, 'For when they shall rise from the dead, they neither marry, nor are given in marriage; but are as the angels which are in heaven.', '0~1063~ 1~3752~ 4~450~ 5~1537~ 7~3498~, 9~3777~ 10~1060~, 11~3777~ 15~1061~; 16~235~ 17~1526~ 18~5613~ 20~32~ 21~3588~ 23~1722~ 24~3772~.'),
  (25449, 42, 11, 32, 'The men of Nineve shall rise up in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: for they repented at the preaching of Jonas; and, behold, a greater than Jonas is here.', '1~435~ 3~3535~ 6~450~ 7~1722~ 9~2920~ 10~3326~ 11~5026~ 12~1074~, 13~2532~ 15~2632~ 16~846~: 17~3754~ 19~3340~ 20~1519~ 22~2782~ 24~2495~; 25~2532~, 26~2400~, 29~4119~ 30~2495~ [31] 32~5602~.'),
  (16754, 20, 12, 26, 'The righteous is more excellent than his neighbour: but the way of the wicked seduceth them.', '&para; 1~06662~ [2] 4~08446~ 7~07453~: 10~01870~ 13~07563~ 14~08582~'),
  (1781, 2, 9, 34, 'And when Pharaoh saw that the rain and the hail and the thunders were ceased, he sinned yet more, and hardened his heart, he and his servants.', '2~06547~ 3~07200~ 6~04306~ 9~01259~ 12~06963~ 14~02308~, 16~02398~ 18~03254~, 20~03513~ 22~03820~, 26~05650~.'),
  (2322, 2, 28, 24, 'And thou shalt put the two wreathen chains of gold in the two rings which are on the ends of the breastplate.', '3~05414~ 5~08147~ 6~05688~ [7] 9~02091~ 12~08147~ 13~02885~ [14 15] 18~07098~ 21~02833~.'),
  (27493, 44, 15, 35, 'Paul also and Barnabas continued in Antioch, teaching and preaching the word of the Lord, with many others also.', '0~3972~ 1~1161~ 2~2532~ 3~921~ 4~1304~ 5~1722~ 6~490~, 7~1321~ 8~2532~ 9~2097~ 11~3056~ 14~2962~, 15~3326~ 16~4183~ 17~2087~ 18~2532~.'),
  (16146, 19, 129, 5, 'Let them all be confounded and turned back that hate Zion.', '&para; 4~0954~ 6~05472~ 7~0268~ 9~08130~ 10~06726~.'),
  (19863, 24, 36, 12, 'Then he went down into the king''s house, into the scribe''s chamber: and, lo, all the princes sat there, even Elishama the scribe, and Delaiah the son of Shemaiah, and Elnathan the son of Achbor, and Gemariah the son of Shaphan, and Zedekiah the son of Hananiah, and all the princes.', '3~03381~ 6~04428~ 7~01004~, 10~05608~ 11~03957~: 16~08269~ 17~03427~ [19] 20~0476~ 22~05608~, 24~01806~ 26~01121~ 28~08098~, 30~0494~ 32~01121~ 34~05907~, 36~01587~ 38~01121~ 40~08227~, 42~06667~ 44~01121~ 46~02608~, 50~08269~.'),
  (16852, 20, 16, 3, 'Commit thy works unto the LORD, and thy thoughts shall be established.', '&para; 0~01556~ 2~04639~ 5~03068~, 8~04284~ 11~03559~.'),
  (14990, 19, 71, 5, 'For thou art my hope, O Lord GOD: thou art my trust from my youth.', '[2] 4~08615~, 6~0136~ 7~03069~: [8 9] 11~04009~ 14~05271~.'),
  (4516, 4, 26, 22, 'These are the families of Judah according to those that were numbered of them, threescore and sixteen thousand and five hundred.', '[1] 3~04940~ 5~03063~ 11~06485~ 16~08337~ 17~07657~* 18~0505~ 20~02568~ 21~03967~.'),
  (10934, 13, 19, 19, 'And when the servants of Hadarezer saw that they were put to the worse before Israel, they made peace with David, and became his servants: neither would the Syrians help the children of Ammon any more.', '3~05650~ 5~01928~ 6~07200~ 13~05062~ 14~06440~ 15~03478~, 18~07999~ 20~01732~, 24~05647~: 26~014~ 28~0758~ 29~03467~ 31~01121~ 33~05983~'),
  (19911, 24, 38, 7, 'Now when Ebedmelech the Ethiopian, one of the eunuchs which was in the king''s house, heard that they had put Jeremiah in the dungeon; the king then sitting in the gate of Benjamin;', '2~05663~ 4~03569~, 5~0376~ 8~05631~ 13~04428~ 14~01004~, 15~08085~ 19~05414~ 20~03414~ 23~0953~; 25~04428~ 27~03427~ 30~08179~ 32~01144~;'),
  (29307, 49, 4, 19, 'Who being past feeling have given themselves over unto lasciviousness, to work all uncleanness with greediness.', '0~3748~ 3~524~ 5~3860~ 6~1438~ 7~3860~ 9~766~, 10~1519~ 11~2039~ 12~3956~ 13~167~ 14~1722~ 15~4124~.'),
