VALUES
  (23013, 38, 9, 5, 'Ashkelon shall see it, and fear; Gaza also shall see it, and be very sorrowful, and Ekron; for her expectation shall be ashamed; and the king shall perish from Gaza, and Ashkelon shall not be inhabited.', '0~0831~ 2~07200~ [3] 5~03372~; 6~05804~ [8 10] 13~03966~ 14~02342~, 16~06138~; 19~04007~ 22~03001~; 25~04428~ 27~06~ 29~05804~, 31~0831~ 35~03427~.'),
  (23183, 40, 2, 4, 'And when he had gathered all the chief priests and scribes of the people together, he demanded of them where Christ should be born.', '0~2532~ 4~4863~ 5~3956~ 8~749~ 9~2532~ 10~1122~ 13~2992~ 14~4863~, 16~4441~ 17~3844~ 18~846~ 19~4226~ 20~5547~ 23~1080~.'),
  (13845, 18, 39, 2, 'Canst thou number the months that they fulfil? or knowest thou the time when they bring forth?', '2~05608~ 4~03391~ [5] 7~04390~? 9~03045~ 12~06256~ 16~03205~?'),
  (24662, 41, 11, 11, 'And Jesus entered into Jerusalem, and into the temple: and when he had looked round about upon all things, and now the eventide was come, he went out unto Bethany with the twelve.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~1525~ 3~1519~ 4~2414~, 5~2532~ 6~1519~ 8~2411~: 9~2532~ 16~4017~ 18~3956~, 20~2235~ 22~5610~ 23~3798~ 24~5607~, 27~1831~ 28~1519~ 29~963~ 30~3326~ 32~1427~.'),
  (27883, 44, 27, 12, 'And because the haven was not commodious to winter in, the more part advised to depart thence also, if by any means they might attain to Phenice, and there to winter; which is an haven of Crete, and lieth toward the south west and north west.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~5225~ 3~3040~ 4~5225~ 6~428~ 7~4314~ 9~3915~, 12~4119~ 13~5087~ 14~1012~* 16~321~ 18~2547~, 19~1513~ 22~4458~ 24~1410~ 25~2658~ 26~1519~ 27~5405~, [28 29] 31~3914~; [32 33] 35~3040~ 37~2914~, 39~991~ 40~2596~ 43~3047~ 44~2596~ 45~2532~ 46~5566~.'),
  (9939, 12, 15, 6, 'And the rest of the acts of Azariah, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah?', '2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~05838~, 12~06213~, [13] 16~03789~ 19~05612~ 22~03117~ 23~01697~ 25~04428~ 27~03063~?'),
  (4812, 4, 33, 46, 'And they removed from Dibongad, and encamped in Almondiblathaim.', '2~05265~ 4~01769~, 6~02583~ 8~05963~.'),
  (8964, 11, 7, 22, 'And upon the top of the pillars was lily work: so was the work of the pillars finished.', '3~07218~ 6~05982~ [7] 8~07799~ 9~04639~: 13~04399~ 16~05982~ 17~08552~.'),
  (29839, 55, 1, 14, 'That good thing which was committed unto thee keep by the Holy Ghost which dwelleth in us.', '2~2570~ 7~3872~ 8~5442~ 9~1223~ 11~40~ 12~4151~ 13~3588~ 14~1774~ 15~1722~ 16~2254~.'),
  (27136, 44, 7, 4, 'Then came he out of the land of the Chaldaeans, and dwelt in Charran: and from thence, when his father was dead, he removed him into this land, wherein ye now dwell.', '0~5119~ 2~1831~ 4~1537~ 6~1093~ 9~5466~, 11~2730~ 12~1722~ 13~5488~: 16~2547~, 17~3326~ 18~846~ 19~3962~ 21~599~, 23~3351~ 24~846~ 25~1519~ 26~5026~ 27~1093~, 28~3739~ 29~1519~* 30~5210~ 31~3568~ 32~2730~.'),
  (21748, 27, 1, 2, 'And the Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, with part of the vessels of the house of God: which he carried into the land of Shinar to the house of his god; and he brought the vessels into the treasure house of his god.', '2~0136~ 3~05414~ 4~03079~ 5~04428~ 7~03063~ 10~03027~, 12~07117~ 15~03627~ 18~01004~ 20~0430~: 23~0935~ 26~0776~ 28~08152~ 31~01004~ 34~0430~; 37~0935~ 39~03627~ 42~0214~ 43~01004~ 46~0430~.'),
  (272, 1, 11, 5, 'And the LORD came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of men builded.', '&para; 2~03068~ 4~03381~ 6~07200~ 8~05892~ 11~04026~, 14~01121~ 16~0120~ 17~01129~.'),
  (12538, 16, 9, 18, 'Yea, when they had made them a molten calf, and said, This is thy God that brought thee up out of Egypt, and had wrought great provocations;', '4~06213~ 7~04541~ 8~05695~, 10~0559~, [12] 14~0430~ 18~05927~ 21~04714~, 24~06213~ 25~01419~ 26~05007~;'),
  (5703, 5, 29, 18, 'Lest there should be among you man, or woman, or family, or tribe, whose heart turneth away this day from the LORD our God, to go and serve the gods of these nations; lest there should be among you a root that beareth gall and wormwood;', '3~03426~ 6~0376~, 8~0802~, 10~04940~, 12~07626~, 14~03824~ 16~06437~ 18~03117~ 21~03068~ 23~0430~, 25~03212~ [26] 27~05647~ 29~0430~ 32~01471~; 36~03426~ 40~08328~ 42~06509~ 43~07219~ 45~03939~;'),
  (29612, 52, 3, 6, 'But now when Timotheus came from you unto us, and brought us good tidings of your faith and charity, and that ye have good remembrance of us always, desiring greatly to see us, as we also to see you:', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~737~ 3~5095~ 4~2064~ 5~575~ 6~5216~ 7~4314~ 8~2248~, 9~2532~ 10~2097~ 11~2254~ 13~2097~ 15~5216~ 16~4102~ 17~2532~ 18~26~, 19~2532~ 20~3754~ 22~2192~ 23~18~ 24~3417~ 26~2257~ 27~3842~, 29~1971~ 31~1492~ 32~2248~, 33~2509~ 34~2249~ 35~2532~ [36 37] 38~5209~:'),
  (23135, 39, 3, 5, 'And I will come near to you to judgment; and I will be a swift witness against the sorcerers, and against the adulterers, and against false swearers, and against those that oppress the hireling in his wages, the widow, and the fatherless, and that turn aside the stranger from his right, and fear not me, saith the LORD of hosts.', '4~07126~ 8~04941~; 14~04116~ 15~05707~ 18~03784~, 22~05003~, 25~08267~ 26~07650~, 31~06231~ 33~07916~ [35] 36~07939~, 38~0490~, 41~03490~, 45~05186~ 47~01616~ [48 50] 52~03372~ 55~0559~ 57~03068~ 59~06635~.'),
  (27915, 44, 27, 44, 'And the rest, some on boards, and some on broken pieces of the ship. And so it came to pass, that they escaped all safe to land.', '0~2532~ 2~3062~, 3~3303~ 4~3739~* 5~1909~ 6~4548~, 7~1161~ 8~3739~ 9~1909~ [10 11] 12~575~ 14~5100~ 15~4143~.* 16~2532~ 17~3779~ 21~1096~, 24~1295~ 25~3956~ 26~1295~ 27~1909~ 28~1093~.'),
  (3788, 4, 4, 40, 'Even those that were numbered of them, throughout their families, by the house of their fathers, were two thousand and six hundred and thirty.', '4~06485~ 9~04940~, 12~01004~ 15~01~, 18~0505~ 20~08337~ 21~03967~ 23~07970~.'),
  (15534, 19, 102, 4, 'My heart is smitten, and withered like grass; so that I forget to eat my bread.', '1~03820~ 3~05221~, 5~03001~ 7~06212~; 11~07911~ 13~0398~ 15~03899~.'),
  (25521, 42, 12, 49, 'I am come to send fire on the earth; and what will I, if it be already kindled?', '2~2064~ 4~906~ 5~4442~ 6~1519~ 8~1093~; 9~2532~ 10~5101~ 12~2309~, 13~1487~ 15~381~ 16~2235~ 17~381~?'),
  (29901, 55, 4, 15, 'Of whom be thou ware also; for he hath greatly withstood our words.', '1~3739~ 2~5442~ 3~4771~ 4~5442~ 5~2532~; 6~1063~ 8~436~ 9~3029~ 10~436~ 11~2251~ 12~3056~.'),
  (1020, 1, 35, 4, 'And they gave unto Jacob all the strange gods which were in their hand, and all their earrings which were in their ears; and Jacob hid them under the oak which was by Shechem.', '2~05414~ 4~03290~ 7~05236~ 8~0430~ [10] 13~03027~, [15 16] 17~05141~ [19] 22~0241~; 24~03290~ 25~02934~ 29~0424~ [31] 33~07927~.'),
  (26044, 42, 24, 39, 'Behold my hands and my feet, that it is I myself: handle me, and see; for a spirit hath not flesh and bones, as ye see me have.', '0~1492~ 1~3450~ 2~5495~ 3~2532~ 4~3450~ 5~4228~, 6~3754~ 8~1510~ 9~1473~ 10~846~: 11~5584~ 12~3165~, 13~2532~ 14~1492~; 15~3754~ 17~4151~ 18~2192~ 19~3756~ 20~4561~ 21~2532~ 22~3747~, 23~2531~ 25~2334~ 26~1691~ 27~2192~.'),
  (27087, 44, 5, 12, 'And by the hands of the apostles were many signs and wonders wrought among the people; (and they were all with one accord in Solomon''s porch.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1223~ 3~5495~ 6~652~ 7~1096~ 8~4183~ 9~4592~ 10~2532~ 11~5059~ 12~1096~ 13~1722~ 15~2992~; 16~2532~* 19~2258~ 20~537~ 23~3661~ 24~1722~ 25~4672~ 26~4745~.'),
  (10833, 13, 16, 5, 'Asaph the chief, and next to him Zechariah, Jeiel, and Shemiramoth, and Jehiel, and Mattithiah, and Eliab, and Benaiah, and Obededom: and Jeiel with psalteries and with harps; but Asaph made a sound with cymbals;', '0~0623~ 2~07218~, 4~04932~ 7~02148~, 8~03273~, 10~08070~, 12~03171~, 14~04993~, 16~0446~, 18~01141~, 20~05654~: 22~03273~ 24~03627~ 25~05035~ 27~03658~; 29~0623~ 32~08085~ 34~04700~;'),
  (5258, 5, 12, 12, 'And ye shall rejoice before the LORD your God, ye, and your sons, and your daughters, and your menservants, and your maidservants, and the Levite that is within your gates; forasmuch as he hath no part nor inheritance with you.', '3~08055~ 4~06440~ 6~03068~ 8~0430~, 12~01121~, 15~01323~, 18~05650~, 21~0519~, 24~03881~ [26] 29~08179~; 30~03588~ 35~02506~ 37~05159~'),
  (20638, 26, 9, 7, 'And he said unto them, Defile the house, and fill the courts with the slain: go ye forth. And they went forth, and slew in the city.', '2~0559~ 5~02930~ 7~01004~, 9~04390~ 11~02691~ 14~02491~: 17~03318~. 21~03318~, 23~05221~ 26~05892~.'),
  (17932, 23, 13, 17, 'Behold, I will stir up the Medes against them, which shall not regard silver; and as for gold, they shall not delight in it.', '4~05782~ 6~04074~ 12~02803~ 13~03701~; [15 16] 17~02091~, 21~02654~'),
  (14183, 19, 19, 6, 'His going forth is from the end of the heaven, and his circuit unto the ends of it: and there is nothing hid from the heat thereof.', '2~04161~ [3] 6~07097~ 9~08064~, 12~08622~ 15~07098~ 22~05641~ 25~02535~'),
  (23880, 40, 21, 44, 'And whosoever shall fall on this stone shall be broken: but on whomsoever it shall fall, it will grind him to powder.', '0~2532~ 3~4098~ 4~1909~ 5~5126~ 6~3037~ 9~4917~: 10~1161~ 11~1909~ 12~302~ 13~3739~ 15~4098~, 18~3039~ 19~846~ 21~3039~.'),
  (29848, 55, 2, 5, 'And if a man also strive for masteries, yet is he not crowned, except he strive lawfully.', '0~1161~ 1~1437~ 3~5100~ 4~2532~ 5~118~ [8] 10~4737~ 11~3756~ 12~4737~, 13~3362~ 15~118~ 16~3545~.'),
  (7932, 9, 26, 20, 'Now therefore, let not my blood fall to the earth before the face of the LORD: for the king of Israel is come out to seek a flea, as when one doth hunt a partridge in the mountains.', '5~01818~ 6~05307~ 9~0776~ 12~06440~ 15~03068~: 18~04428~ 20~03478~ 23~03318~ 25~01245~ 26~0259~ 27~06550~, 32~07291~ 34~07124~ 37~02022~.'),
  (15731, 19, 107, 23, 'They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business in great waters;', '&para; 3~03381~ 6~03220~ 8~0591~, 10~06213~ 11~04399~ 13~07227~ 14~04325~;'),
  (10581, 13, 7, 38, 'And the sons of Jether; Jephunneh, and Pispah, and Ara.', '2~01121~ 4~03500~; 5~03312~, 7~06462~, 9~0690~.'),
  (16492, 20, 3, 28, 'Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.', '0~0559~ 4~07453~, 5~03212~, 8~07725~, 11~04279~ 14~05414~; 17~03426~'),
  (4744, 4, 32, 20, 'And Moses said unto them, If ye will do this thing, if ye will go armed before the LORD to war,', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 8~06213~ 10~01697~, 15~02502~ 16~06440~ 18~03068~ 20~04421~,'),
  (22499, 30, 8, 9, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the Lord GOD, that I will cause the sun to go down at noon, and I will darken the earth in the clear day:', '8~03117~, 9~05002~ 11~0136~ 12~03069~, 18~08121~ 21~0935~ 23~06672~, 27~02821~ 29~0776~ 32~0216~ 33~03117~:'),
  (11346, 14, 7, 14, 'If my people, which are called by my name, shall humble themselves, and pray, and seek my face, and turn from their wicked ways; then will I hear from heaven, and will forgive their sin, and will heal their land.', '2~05971~, 5~07121~ 8~08034~, 10~03665~ 13~06419~, 15~01245~ 17~06440~, 19~07725~ 22~07451~ 23~01870~; 27~08085~ 29~08064~, 32~05545~ 34~02403~, 37~07495~ 39~0776~.'),
  (16685, 20, 10, 20, 'The tongue of the just is as choice silver: the heart of the wicked is little worth.', '&para; 1~03956~ 4~06662~ [5 6] 7~0977~ 8~03701~: 10~03820~ 13~07563~ [14] 16~04592~.'),
  (21122, 26, 26, 13, 'And I will cause the noise of thy songs to cease; and the sound of thy harps shall be no more heard.', '5~01995~ 8~07892~ 10~07673~; 13~06963~ 16~03658~ 21~08085~.'),
  (15791, 19, 109, 27, 'That they may know that this is thy hand; that thou, LORD, hast done it.', '3~03045~ [6] 8~03027~; [9] 11~03068~, 13~06213~'),
  (21965, 27, 7, 23, 'Thus he said, The fourth beast shall be the fourth kingdom upon earth, which shall be diverse from all kingdoms, and shall devour the whole earth, and shall tread it down, and break it in pieces.', '0~03652~ 2~0560~, 4~07244~ 5~02423~ 7~01934~ 9~07244~ 10~04437~ 12~0772~, 16~08133~ 17~04481~ 18~03606~ 19~04437~, 22~0399~ 24~03606~ 25~0772~, 30~01759~, 35~01855~.'),
  (10841, 13, 16, 13, 'O ye seed of Israel his servant, ye children of Jacob, his chosen ones.', '2~02233~ 4~03478~ 6~05650~, 8~01121~ 10~03290~, 13~0972~.'),
  (14135, 19, 18, 8, 'There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured: coals were kindled by it.', '2~05927~ 4~06227~ 8~0639~, 10~0784~ 14~06310~ 15~0398~: 16~01513~ 18~01197~'),
  (2100, 2, 21, 18, 'And if men strive together, and one smite another with a stone, or with his fist, and he die not, but keepeth his bed:', '2~0582~ 3~07378~ 6~0376~ 7~05221~ 8~07453~ 11~068~, 12~0176~ [14] 15~0106~, 18~04191~ 21~05307~ [22] 23~04904~:'),
  (11739, 14, 25, 26, 'Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, first and last, behold, are they not written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel?', '2~03499~ 5~01697~ 7~0558~, 8~07223~ 10~0314~, [12] 15~03789~ 18~05612~ 21~04428~ 23~03063~ 25~03478~?'),
  (15901, 19, 118, 23, 'This is the LORD''S doing; it is marvellous in our eyes.', '3~03068~ [6] 7~06381~ 10~05869~.'),
  (21621, 26, 44, 13, 'And they shall not come near unto me, to do the office of a priest unto me, nor to come near to any of my holy things, in the most holy place: but they shall bear their shame, and their abominations which they have committed.', '5~05066~ 14~03547~ 20~05066~ 26~06944~, 30~06944~ [31] 35~05375~ 37~03639~, 40~08441~ 44~06213~.'),
  (27733, 44, 22, 13, 'Came unto me, and stood, and said unto me, Brother Saul, receive thy sight. And the same hour I looked up upon him.', '0~2064~ 1~4314~ 2~3165~, 3~2532~ 4~2186~, 6~2036~ 8~3427~, 9~80~ 10~4549~, 13~308~. 14~2504~ 16~846~ 17~5610~ 18~2504~ 20~308~ 21~1519~ 22~846~.'),
  (11494, 14, 14, 10, 'Then Asa went out against him, and they set the battle in array in the valley of Zephathah at Mareshah.', '1~0609~ 3~03318~ 4~06440~ 10~04421~ 12~06186~ 15~01516~ 17~06859~ 19~04762~.'),
  (8056, 10, 1, 27, 'How are the mighty fallen, and the weapons of war perished!', '3~01368~ 4~05307~, 7~03627~ 9~04421~ 10~06~!'),
  (22319, 29, 1, 19, 'O LORD, to thee will I cry: for the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness, and the flame hath burned all the trees of the field.', '1~03068~, 6~07121~: 9~0784~ 11~0398~ 13~04999~ 16~04057~, 19~03852~ 21~03857~ 24~06086~ 27~07704~.'),
  (15602, 19, 104, 22, 'The sun ariseth, they gather themselves together, and lay them down in their dens.', '1~08121~ 2~02224~, 6~0622~, 10~07257~ 13~04585~.'),
  (27377, 44, 12, 24, 'But the word of God grew and multiplied.', '0~1161~ 2~3056~ 4~2316~ 5~837~ 6~2532~ 7~4129~.'),
  (11979, 14, 35, 4, 'And prepare yourselves by the houses of your fathers, after your courses, according to the writing of David king of Israel, and according to the writing of Solomon his son.', '1~03559~ [2] 5~01004~ 8~01~, 11~04256~, 15~03791~ 17~01732~ 18~04428~ 20~03478~, 25~04385~ 27~08010~ 29~01121~.'),
  (9625, 12, 4, 14, 'And he said, What then is to be done for her? And Gehazi answered, Verily she hath no child, and her husband is old.', '2~0559~, [5] 8~06213~ 12~01522~ 13~0559~, 14~061~ 18~01121~, 21~0376~ 23~02204~.'),
  (22566, 32, 2, 9, 'But I will sacrifice unto thee with the voice of thanksgiving; I will pay that that I have vowed. Salvation is of the LORD.', '3~02076~ 8~06963~ 10~08426~; 13~07999~ [14] 18~05087~. 19~03444~ [20] 23~03068~.'),
  (18233, 23, 30, 7, 'For the Egyptians shall help in vain, and to no purpose: therefore have I cried concerning this, Their strength is to sit still.', '2~04714~ 4~05826~ 6~01892~, 10~07385~: 14~07121~ 16~02063~, 17~01992~ 18~07293~ [19] 22~07674~.'),
  (2464, 2, 32, 21, 'And Moses said unto Aaron, What did this people unto thee, that thou hast brought so great a sin upon them?', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~0559~ 4~0175~, 6~06213~ 8~05971~ 14~0935~ 16~01419~ 18~02401~'),
  (413, 1, 17, 12, 'And he that is eight days old shall be circumcised among you, every man child in your generations, he that is born in the house, or bought with money of any stranger, which is not of thy seed.', '4~08083~ 5~03117~ 6~01121~ 9~04135~ 14~02145~ 17~01755~, 21~03211~ 24~01004~, 26~04736~ 28~03701~ 31~05236~ 32~01121~,* [34] 38~02233~.'),
  (11526, 14, 16, 8, 'Were not the Ethiopians and the Lubims a huge host, with very many chariots and horsemen? yet, because thou didst rely on the LORD, he delivered them into thine hand.', '3~03569~ 6~03864~ 8~07230~ 9~02428~, 11~03966~ 12~07235~ 13~07393~ 15~06571~? 20~08172~ 23~03068~, 25~05414~ 29~03027~.'),
  (1186, 1, 40, 9, 'And the chief butler told his dream to Joseph, and said to him, In my dream, behold, a vine was before me;', '2~08269~ 3~08248~ 4~05608~ 6~02472~ 8~03130~, 10~0559~ 15~02472~, 18~01612~ [19] 21~06440~;'),
  (30385, 59, 5, 15, 'And the prayer of faith shall save the sick, and the Lord shall raise him up; and if he have committed sins, they shall be forgiven him.', '0~2532~ 2~2171~ 4~4102~ 6~4982~ 8~2577~, 9~2532~ 11~2962~ 13~1453~ 14~846~ 15~1453~; 17~2579~ 19~5600~ 20~4160~ 21~266~, 25~863~ 26~846~.'),
  (29251, 49, 2, 6, 'And hath raised us up together, and made us sit together in heavenly places in Christ Jesus:', '0~2532~ [3] 5~4891~, 6~2532~ [8] 10~4776~ 11~1722~ 12~2032~ [13] 14~1722~ 15~5547~ 16~2424~:'),
  (26992, 44, 2, 27, 'Because thou wilt not leave my soul in hell, neither wilt thou suffer thine Holy One to see corruption.', '0~3754~ 2~1459~ 3~3756~ 4~1459~ 5~3450~ 6~5590~ 7~1519~ 8~86~, 9~3761~ 12~1325~ 13~4675~ 15~3741~ 17~1492~ 18~1312~.'),
  (12950, 18, 4, 11, 'The old lion perisheth for lack of prey, and the stout lion''s whelps are scattered abroad.', '2~03918~ 3~06~ 5~01097~ 7~02964~, 11~03833~ 12~01121~ 15~06504~.'),
  (21346, 26, 34, 24, 'And I the LORD will be their God, and my servant David a prince among them; I the LORD have spoken it.', '3~03068~ 7~0430~, 10~05650~ 11~01732~ 13~05387~ 14~08432~ 18~03068~ 20~01696~ [21]'),
  (10421, 13, 4, 28, 'And they dwelt at Beersheba, and Moladah, and Hazarshual,', '2~03427~ 4~0884~, 6~04137~, 8~02705~,'),
  (27881, 44, 27, 10, 'And said unto them, Sirs, I perceive that this voyage will be with hurt and much damage, not only of the lading and ship, but also of our lives.', '1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~435~, 6~2334~ 7~3754~ 9~4144~ 11~3195~ 12~1510~* 13~3326~ 14~5196~ 15~2532~ 16~4183~ 17~2209~, 18~3756~ 19~3440~ 22~5414~ 23~2532~ 24~4143~, 25~235~ 26~2532~ 28~2257~ 29~5590~.'),
  (6436, 6, 22, 3, 'Ye have not left your brethren these many days unto this day, but have kept the charge of the commandment of the LORD your God.', '3~05800~ 5~0251~ 7~07227~ 8~03117~ 11~03117~, 14~08104~ 16~04931~ 19~04687~ 22~03068~ 24~0430~.'),
  (5698, 5, 29, 13, 'That he may establish thee to day for a people unto himself, and that he may be unto thee a God, as he hath said unto thee, and as he hath sworn unto thy fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.', '3~06965~ 6~03117~ 9~05971~ [13] 20~0430~, 24~01696~ 31~07650~ 34~01~, 36~085~, 38~03327~, 41~03290~.'),
  (25857, 42, 21, 17, 'And ye shall be hated of all men for my name''s sake.', '0~2532~ 3~2071~ 4~3404~ 5~5259~ 6~3956~ [7] 8~1223~ 9~3450~ 11~3686~.'),
  (7771, 9, 20, 34, 'So Jonathan arose from the table in fierce anger, and did eat no meat the second day of the month: for he was grieved for David, because his father had done him shame.', '1~03083~ 2~06965~ 5~07979~ 7~02750~ 8~0639~, 11~0398~ 13~03899~ 15~08145~ 16~03117~ 19~02320~: 23~06087~ 25~01732~, 28~01~ 32~03637~.'),
  (11900, 14, 32, 16, 'And his servants spake yet more against the LORD God, and against his servant Hezekiah.', '2~05650~ 3~01696~ [5] 8~03068~ 9~0430~, 13~05650~ 14~03169~.'),
  (23492, 40, 11, 23, 'And thou, Capernaum, which art exalted unto heaven, shalt be brought down to hell: for if the mighty works, which have been done in thee, had been done in Sodom, it would have remained until this day.', '0~2532~ 1~4771~, 2~2584~, 3~3588~ 5~5312~ 6~2193~ 7~3772~, 11~2601~ 12~2193~ 13~86~: 14~3754~ 15~1487~ 18~1411~, 19~3588~ 22~1096~ 23~1722~ 24~4671~, 27~1096~ 28~1722~ 29~4670~, 33~3306~ 34~302~* 35~3360~ 37~4594~.'),
  (19028, 24, 3, 17, 'At that time they shall call Jerusalem the throne of the LORD; and all the nations shall be gathered unto it, to the name of the LORD, to Jerusalem: neither shall they walk any more after the imagination of their evil heart.', '2~06256~ 5~07121~ 6~03389~ 8~03678~ 11~03068~; 15~01471~ 18~06960~ 23~08034~ 26~03068~, 28~03389~: 32~03212~ 35~0310~ 37~08307~ 40~07451~ 41~03820~.'),
  (22093, 27, 12, 3, 'And they that be wise shall shine as the brightness of the firmament; and they that turn many to righteousness as the stars for ever and ever.', '4~07919~ 6~02094~ 9~02096~ 12~07549~; 17~07227~ 19~06663~ 22~03556~ 24~05769~ 26~05703~.'),
  (11784, 14, 28, 11, 'Now hear me therefore, and deliver the captives again, which ye have taken captive of your brethren: for the fierce wrath of the LORD is upon you.', '1~08085~ 5~07725~ 7~07633~ 13~07617~ 16~0251~: 19~02740~ 20~0639~ 23~03068~ [24]'),
  (8905, 11, 6, 1, 'And it came to pass in the four hundred and eightieth year after the children of Israel were come out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon''s reign over Israel, in the month Zif, which is the second month, that he began to build the house of the LORD.', '&para; 7~0702~ 8~08141~ 9~03967~ 10~08084~ 11~08141~ 14~01121~ 16~03478~ 19~03318~ 22~0776~ 24~04714~, 27~07243~ 28~08141~ 30~08010~ 31~04427~ 33~03478~, 36~02320~ 37~02099~, [39] 41~08145~ 42~02320~, 47~01129~ 49~01004~ 52~03068~.'),
  (3340, 3, 20, 17, 'And if a man shall take his sister, his father''s daughter, or his mother''s daughter, and see her nakedness, and she see his nakedness; it is a wicked thing; and they shall be cut off in the sight of their people: he hath uncovered his sister''s nakedness; he shall bear his iniquity.', '3~0376~ 5~03947~ 7~0269~, 9~01~ 10~01323~, 11~0176~ 13~0517~ 14~01323~, 16~07200~ 18~06172~, 21~07200~ 23~06172~; [25] 28~02617~; 34~03772~ 37~05869~ 40~01121~ 41~05971~:* 44~01540~ 46~0269~ 47~06172~; 50~05375~ 52~05771~.'),
  (14654, 19, 48, 11, 'Let mount Zion rejoice, let the daughters of Judah be glad, because of thy judgments.', '1~02022~ 2~06726~ 3~08055~, 6~01323~ 8~03063~ 10~01523~, 14~04941~.'),
  (25946, 42, 22, 68, 'And if I also ask you, ye will not answer me, nor let me go.', '0~1161~ 1~1437~ 3~2532~ 4~2065~ [5] 7~611~ 8~3364~ 9~611~ 10~3427~, 11~2228~ [13] 14~630~.'),
  (19001, 24, 2, 27, 'Saying to a stock, Thou art my father; and to a stone, Thou hast brought me forth: for they have turned their back unto me, and not their face: but in the time of their trouble they will say, Arise, and save us.', '0~0559~ 3~06086~, [5] 7~01~; 11~068~, 16~03205~: 20~06437~ [21] 22~06203~ [27] 28~06440~: 32~06256~ 35~07451~ 38~0559~, 39~06965~, 41~03467~'),
  (12014, 14, 36, 12, 'And he did that which was evil in the sight of the LORD his God, and humbled not himself before Jeremiah the prophet speaking from the mouth of the LORD.', '2~06213~ [3 5] 6~07451~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~ 14~0430~, [15] 16~03665~ 19~06440~ 20~03414~ 22~05030~ [23] 26~06310~ 29~03068~.'),
  (4254, 4, 17, 5, 'And it shall come to pass, that the man''s rod, whom I shall choose, shall blossom: and I will make to cease from me the murmurings of the children of Israel, whereby they murmur against you.', '[6] 8~0376~ 9~04294~, 13~0977~, 15~06524~: 21~07918~ 25~08519~ 28~01121~ 30~03478~, 33~03885~'),
  (9783, 12, 9, 19, 'Then he sent out a second on horseback, which came to them, and said, Thus saith the king, Is it peace? And Jehu answered, What hast thou to do with peace? turn thee behind me.', '3~07971~ 5~08145~ 7~07392~ 8~05483~,* 10~0935~ 14~0559~, 16~0559~ 18~04428~, [19 20] 21~07965~? 23~03058~ 24~0559~, 31~07965~? 32~05437~ 34~0310~'),
  (12100, 15, 2, 64, 'The whole congregation together was forty and two thousand three hundred and threescore,', '&para; 2~06951~ 3~0259~ [4] 5~07239~ 6~0702~ 8~0505~ 9~07969~ 10~03967~ [11] 12~08346~,'),
  (24641, 41, 10, 42, 'But Jesus called them to him, and saith unto them, Ye know that they which are accounted to rule over the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and their great ones exercise authority upon them.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~4341~ 3~846~ [4 5] 7~3004~ 9~846~, 11~1492~ 12~3754~ 16~1380~ 18~757~ 21~1484~ 23~2634~ 25~846~; 26~2532~ 27~846~ 29~3173~ 31~2715~ 33~846~.'),
  (25805, 42, 20, 12, 'And again he sent a third: and they wounded him also, and cast him out.', '0~2532~ 1~4369~ 3~3992~ 5~5154~: 6~1161~ 8~5135~ 9~5126~ 10~2532~, [13] 14~1544~.'),
  (5113, 5, 6, 21, 'Then thou shalt say unto thy son, We were Pharaoh''s bondmen in Egypt; and the LORD brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand:', '3~0559~ 6~01121~, 9~06547~ 10~05650~ 12~04714~; 15~03068~ 18~03318~ 20~04714~ 23~02389~ 24~03027~:'),
  (10576, 13, 7, 33, 'And the sons of Japhlet; Pasach, and Bimhal, and Ashvath. These are the children of Japhlet.', '2~01121~ 4~03310~; 5~06457~, 7~01118~, 9~06220~. [11] 13~01121~ 15~03310~.'),
  (13427, 18, 22, 29, 'When men are cast down, then thou shalt say, There is lifting up; and he shall save the humble person.', '[1] 4~08213~, 8~0559~, [9 10] 12~01466~; 16~03467~ 18~07807~ 19~05869~.'),
  (8673, 10, 23, 12, 'But he stood in the midst of the ground, and defended it, and slew the Philistines: and the LORD wrought a great victory.', '2~03320~ 5~08432~ 8~02513~, 10~05337~ 13~05221~ 15~06430~: 18~03068~ 19~06213~ 21~01419~ 22~08668~.'),
  (8849, 11, 3, 25, 'And the king said, Divide the living child in two, and give half to the one, and half to the other.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~, 4~01504~ 6~02416~ 7~03206~ 9~08147~, 11~05414~ 12~02677~ 15~0259~, 17~02677~ 20~0259~.'),
  (25523, 42, 12, 51, 'Suppose ye that I am come to give peace on earth? I tell you, Nay; but rather division:', '1~1380~ 2~3754~ 5~3854~ 7~1325~ 8~1515~ 9~1722~ 10~1093~? 12~3004~ 13~5213~, 14~3780~; 15~235~ 16~2228~ 17~1267~:'),
  (17568, 22, 2, 5, 'Stay me with flagons, comfort me with apples: for I am sick of love.', '0~05564~ 3~0809~, 4~07502~ 7~08598~: [10] 11~02470~ 13~0160~.'),
  (29789, 54, 5, 10, 'Well reported of for good works; if she have brought up children, if she have lodged strangers, if she have washed the saints'' feet, if she have relieved the afflicted, if she have diligently followed every good work.', '2~3140~ 3~1722~ 4~2570~ 5~2041~; 6~1487~ 10~5044~ 12~1487~ 16~3580~, 17~1487~ 20~3538~ 22~40~ 23~4228~, 24~1487~ 27~1884~ 29~2346~, 30~1487~ 34~1872~ 35~3956~ 36~18~ 37~2041~.'),
  (26182, 43, 4, 11, 'The woman saith unto him, Sir, thou hast nothing to draw with, and the well is deep: from whence then hast thou that living water?', '1~1135~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~2962~, 7~2192~ 8~3777~ 11~502~, 12~2532~ 14~5421~ 15~2076~ 16~901~: 18~4159~ 19~3767~ 21~2192~ 23~2198~ 24~5204~?'),
  (5515, 5, 23, 9, 'When the host goeth forth against thine enemies, then keep thee from every wicked thing.', '&para; 2~04264~ 4~03318~ 7~0341~, 9~08104~ 13~07451~ 14~01697~.'),
  (10977, 13, 22, 5, 'And David said, Solomon my son is young and tender, and the house that is to be builded for the LORD must be exceeding magnifical, of fame and of glory throughout all countries: I will therefore now make preparation for it. So David prepared abundantly before his death.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~, 3~08010~ 5~01121~ [6] 7~05288~ 9~07390~, 12~01004~ [13 14] 17~01129~ 20~03068~ [21 22] 23~04605~ 24~01431~, 26~08034~ 29~08597~ 32~0776~: [35] 38~03559~ 42~01732~ 43~03559~ 44~07230~ 45~06440~ 47~04194~.');
