  (21493, 26, 40, 7, 'And every little chamber was one reed long, and one reed broad; and between the little chambers were five cubits; and the threshold of the gate by the porch of the gate within was one reed.', '[1] 3~08372~ [4] 5~0259~ 6~07070~ 7~0753~, 9~0259~ 10~07070~ 11~07341~; 16~08372~ [17] 18~02568~ 19~0520~; 22~05592~ 25~08179~ 26~0681~ 28~0197~ 31~08179~ 32~01004~ [33] 34~0259~ 35~07070~.'),
