  (17358, 21, 2, 16, 'For there is no remembrance of the wise more than of the fool for ever; seeing that which now is in the days to come shall all be forgotten. And how dieth the wise man? as the fool.', '[1 2] 4~02146~ 7~02450~ 9~05973~ 12~03684~ 14~05769~; 18~03528~ [19] 22~03117~ 24~0935~ 28~07911~. 31~04191~ 33~02450~ [34] 37~03684~.'),
