VALUES
  (21878, 27, 4, 32, 'And they shall drive thee from men, and thy dwelling shall be with the beasts of the field: they shall make thee to eat grass as oxen, and seven times shall pass over thee, until thou know that the most High ruleth in the kingdom of men, and giveth it to whomsoever he will.', '3~02957~ 5~04481~ 6~0606~, 9~04070~ [10 11] 12~05974~ 14~02423~ 17~01251~: 23~02939~ 24~06211~ 26~08450~, 28~07655~ 29~05732~ 31~02499~ 32~05922~ 34~05705~ 36~03046~ 40~05943~ 41~07990~ 44~04437~ 46~0606~, 48~05415~ 51~04479~ 53~06634~.'),
  (2670, 2, 39, 1, 'And of the blue, and purple, and scarlet, they made cloths of service, to do service in the holy place, and made the holy garments for Aaron; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '&para; 3~08504~, 5~0713~, 7~08438~ 8~08144~,* 10~06213~ 11~0899~ 13~08278~, 16~08334~ 19~06944~ [20] 22~06213~ 24~06944~ 25~0899~ 27~0175~; 30~03068~ 31~06680~ 32~04872~.'),
  (28918, 47, 6, 4, 'But in all things approving ourselves as the ministers of God, in much patience, in afflictions, in necessities, in distresses,', '0~235~ 1~1722~ 2~3956~ [3] 4~4921~ 5~1438~ 6~5613~ 8~1249~ 10~2316~, 11~1722~ 12~4183~ 13~5281~, 14~1722~ 15~2347~, 16~1722~ 17~318~, 18~1722~ 19~4730~,'),
  (27514, 44, 16, 15, 'And when she was baptized, and her household, she besought us, saying, If ye have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come into my house, and abide there. And she constrained us.', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 4~907~, 5~2532~ 6~846~ 7~3624~, 9~3870~ [10] 11~3004~, 12~1487~ 15~2919~ 16~3165~ 18~1511~ 19~4103~ 22~2962~, 23~1525~ 24~1519~ 25~3450~ 26~3624~, 28~3306~ [29] 30~2532~ 32~3849~ 33~2248~.'),
  (15708, 19, 106, 48, 'Blessed be the LORD God of Israel from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say, Amen. Praise ye the LORD.', '0~01288~ [1] 3~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~03478~ 8~05769~ 10~05769~: 15~05971~ 16~0559~, 17~0543~. 18~01984~ 21~03050~.'),
  (24345, 41, 4, 12, 'That seeing they may see, and not perceive; and hearing they may hear, and not understand; lest at any time they should be converted, and their sins should be forgiven them.', '0~2443~ 1~991~ 4~991~, 5~2532~ 6~3361~ 7~1492~; 8~2532~ 9~191~ 12~191~, 13~2532~ 14~3361~ 15~4920~; 19~3379~ 23~1994~, 24~2532~ [25] 26~265~ 29~863~ 30~846~.'),
  (12970, 18, 5, 10, 'Who giveth rain upon the earth, and sendeth waters upon the fields:', '1~05414~ 2~04306~ 3~06440~ 5~0776~, 7~07971~ 8~04325~ 9~06440~ 11~02351~:'),
  (28920, 47, 6, 6, 'By pureness, by knowledge, by longsuffering, by kindness, by the Holy Ghost, by love unfeigned,', '0~1722~ 1~54~, 2~1722~ 3~1108~, 4~1722~ 5~3115~, 6~1722~ 7~5544~, 8~1722~ 10~40~ 11~4151~, 12~1722~ 13~26~ 14~505~,'),
  (2004, 2, 17, 16, 'For he said, Because the LORD hath sworn that the LORD will have war with Amalek from generation to generation.', '2~0559~, 5~03050~ 7~03676~ [8] 8~03027~ 10~03068~ [11 12] 13~04421~ 15~06002~ 17~01755~ 19~01755~.'),
  (21706, 26, 47, 18, 'And the east side ye shall measure from Hauran, and from Damascus, and from Gilead, and from the land of Israel by Jordan, from the border unto the east sea. And this is the east side.', '2~06921~ 3~06285~ 6~04058~ 7~0996~ 8~02362~, 10~0996~ 11~01834~, 13~0996~ 14~01568~, 16~0996~ 18~0776~ 20~03478~ [21] 22~03383~, 25~01366~ 28~06931~ 29~03220~. [31 32] 34~06921~ 35~06285~.'),
  (7844, 9, 23, 27, 'But there came a messenger unto Saul, saying, Haste thee, and come; for the Philistines have invaded the land.', '2~0935~ 4~04397~ 6~07586~, 7~0559~, 8~04116~ 11~03212~; 14~06430~ 16~06584~ 18~0776~.'),
  (21996, 27, 8, 26, 'And the vision of the evening and the morning which was told is true: wherefore shut thou up the vision; for it shall be for many days.', '2~04758~ 5~06153~ 8~01242~ 11~0559~ [12] 13~0571~: 17~05640~ 19~02377~; [22 23] 25~07227~ 26~03117~.'),
  (23006, 38, 8, 21, 'And the inhabitants of one city shall go to another, saying, Let us go speedily to pray before the LORD, and to seek the LORD of hosts: I will go also.', '2~03427~ 4~0259~ [5] 7~01980~ 9~0259~, 10~0559~, 13~03212~ 14~01980~ 16~02470~ 17~06440~ 19~03068~, 22~01245~ 24~03068~ 26~06635~: 29~03212~'),
  (9184, 11, 12, 25, 'Then Jeroboam built Shechem in mount Ephraim, and dwelt therein; and went out from thence, and built Penuel.', '&para; 1~03379~ 2~01129~ 3~07927~ 5~02022~ 6~0669~, 8~03427~ 12~03318~ 16~01129~ 17~06439~.'),
  (2641, 2, 38, 3, 'And he made all the vessels of the altar, the pots, and the shovels, and the basins, and the fleshhooks, and the firepans: all the vessels thereof made he of brass.', '2~06213~ 5~03627~ 8~04196~, 10~05518~, 13~03257~, 16~04219~, [17] 19~04207~, 22~04289~: 25~03627~ 27~06213~ [29] 30~05178~.'),
  (11352, 14, 7, 20, 'Then will I pluck them up by the roots out of my land which I have given them; and this house, which I have sanctified for my name, will I cast out of my sight, and will make it to be a proverb and a byword among all nations.', '8~05428~ 12~0127~ 16~05414~ 20~01004~, 24~06942~ 27~08034~, 31~07993~ 34~06440~, 37~05414~ [39 40] 42~04912~ 45~08148~ 48~05971~.'),
  (7121, 7, 21, 12, 'And they found among the inhabitants of Jabeshgilead four hundred young virgins, that had known no man by lying with any male: and they brought them unto the camp to Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan.', '2~04672~ 5~03427~ 7~01568~ 8~03003~* 9~0702~ 10~03967~ 11~05291~ 12~01330~, 15~03045~ 17~0376~ 19~04904~ 22~02145~: 25~0935~ 29~04264~ 31~07887~, [33] 36~0776~ 38~03667~.'),
  (18839, 23, 60, 9, 'Surely the isles shall wait for me, and the ships of Tarshish first, to bring thy sons from far, their silver and their gold with them, unto the name of the LORD thy God, and to the Holy One of Israel, because he hath glorified thee.', '&para; 2~0339~ 4~06960~ 9~0591~ 11~08659~ 12~07223~, 14~0935~ 16~01121~ 18~07350~, 20~03701~ 23~02091~ 28~08034~ 31~03068~ 33~0430~, 38~06918~ 40~03478~, 44~06286~'),
  (20979, 26, 21, 26, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD; Remove the diadem, and take off the crown: this shall not be the same: exalt him that is low, and abase him that is high.', '1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~; 5~05493~ 7~04701~, 10~07311~ 12~05850~: [14] [16] 18~02063~: 19~01361~ [20 22] 23~08217~, 25~08213~ [26 28] 29~01364~.'),
  (13969, 19, 3, 3, 'But thou, O LORD, art a shield for me; my glory, and the lifter up of mine head.', '3~03068~, [4] 6~04043~ 10~03519~, 14~07311~ 17~07218~.'),
  (23317, 40, 6, 25, 'Therefore I say unto you, Take no thought for your life, what ye shall eat, or what ye shall drink; nor yet for your body, what ye shall put on. Is not the life more than meat, and the body than raiment?', '&para; 0~5124~ 1~1223~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 6~3361~ 7~3309~ 9~5216~ 10~5590~, 11~5101~ 14~5315~, 15~2532~ 16~5101~ 19~4095~; 22~3366~ 23~5216~ 24~4983~, 25~5101~ 29~1746~. 30~2076~ 31~3780~ 33~5590~ 35~4119~ 36~5160~, 37~2532~ 39~4983~ 41~1742~?'),
  (2391, 2, 30, 4, 'And two golden rings shalt thou make to it under the crown of it, by the two corners thereof, upon the two sides of it shalt thou make it; and they shall be for places for the staves to bear it withal.', '1~08147~ 2~02091~ 3~02885~ 6~06213~ 11~02213~ 16~08147~ 17~06763~ 21~08147~ 22~06654~ 27~06213~ [28] 34~01004~ 37~0905~ 39~05375~ 41~01992~.'),
  (298, 1, 11, 29, 'And Abram and Nahor took them wives: the name of Abram''s wife was Sarai; and the name of Nahor''s wife, Milcah, the daughter of Haran, the father of Milcah, and the father of Iscah.', '1~087~ 3~05152~ 4~03947~ 6~0802~: 8~08034~ 10~087~ 11~0802~ [12] 13~08297~; 16~08034~ 18~05152~ 19~0802~, 20~04435~, 22~01323~ 24~02039~, 26~01~ 28~04435~, 31~01~ 33~03252~.'),
  (193, 1, 8, 9, 'But the dove found no rest for the sole of her foot, and she returned unto him into the ark, for the waters were on the face of the whole earth: then he put forth his hand, and took her, and pulled her in unto him into the ark.', '2~03123~ 3~04672~ 5~04494~ 8~03709~ 11~07272~, 14~07725~ 19~08392~, 22~04325~ [23] 26~06440~ 30~0776~: 34~07971~ 36~03027~, 39~03947~, 43~0935~ 48~08392~.'),
  (21626, 26, 44, 18, 'They shall have linen bonnets upon their heads, and shall have linen breeches upon their loins; they shall not gird themselves with any thing that causeth sweat.', '3~06593~ 4~06287~ 7~07218~, 11~06593~ 12~04370~ 15~04975~; 19~02296~ [20] 26~03154~.'),
  (2399, 2, 30, 12, 'When thou takest the sum of the children of Israel after their number, then shall they give every man a ransom for his soul unto the LORD, when thou numberest them; that there be no plague among them, when thou numberest them.', '2~05375~ 4~07218~ 7~01121~ 9~03478~ 12~06485~, 16~05414~ 18~0376~ 20~03724~ 23~05315~ 26~03068~, 29~06485~ 35~05063~ [39] 40~06485~'),
  (26276, 43, 6, 4, 'And the passover, a feast of the Jews, was nigh.', '0~1161~ 2~3957~, 4~1859~ 7~2453~, 8~2258~ 9~1451~.'),
  (10041, 12, 18, 9, 'And it came to pass in the fourth year of king Hezekiah, which was the seventh year of Hoshea son of Elah king of Israel, that Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up against Samaria, and besieged it.', '&para; 7~07243~ 8~08141~ 10~04428~ 11~02396~, [13] 15~07637~ 16~08141~ 18~01954~ 19~01121~ 21~0425~ 22~04428~ 24~03478~, [25] 26~08022~ 27~04428~ 29~0804~ 31~05927~ 33~08111~, 35~06696~'),
  (26659, 43, 13, 14, 'If I then, your Lord and Master, have washed your feet; ye also ought to wash one another''s feet.', '0~1487~ 1~1473~ 2~3767~, [3] 4~2962~ 5~2532~ 6~1320~, 8~3538~ 9~5216~ 10~4228~; 11~5210~ 12~2532~ 13~3784~ 15~3538~ 17~240~ 18~4228~.'),
  (13972, 19, 3, 6, 'I will not be afraid of ten thousands of people, that have set themselves against me round about.', '4~03372~ 7~07233~ 9~05971~, 12~07896~ [13] 17~05439~.'),
  (30360, 59, 4, 7, 'Submit yourselves therefore to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you.', '1~5293~ 2~3767~ 4~2316~. 5~436~ 7~1228~, 8~2532~ 11~5343~ 12~575~ 13~5216~.'),
  (3217, 3, 16, 11, 'And Aaron shall bring the bullock of the sin offering, which is for himself, and shall make an atonement for himself, and for his house, and shall kill the bullock of the sin offering which is for himself:', '1~0175~ 3~07126~ 5~06499~ 9~02403~, [11] 18~03722~ 24~01004~, 27~07819~ 29~06499~ 33~02403~ [35]'),
  (24066, 40, 26, 2, 'Ye know that after two days is the feast of the passover, and the Son of man is betrayed to be crucified.', '1~1492~ 2~3754~ 3~3326~ 4~1417~ 5~2250~ 6~1096~ [7 9] 11~3957~, 12~2532~ 14~5207~ 16~444~ 18~3860~ 19~1519~ 21~4717~.'),
  (27161, 44, 7, 29, 'Then fled Moses at this saying, and was a stranger in the land of Madian, where he begat two sons.', '0~1161~ 1~5343~ 2~3475~ 3~1722~ 4~5129~ 5~3056~, 6~2532~ 7~1096~ 9~3941~ 10~1722~ 12~1093~ 14~3099~, 15~3757~ 17~1080~ 18~1417~ 19~5207~.'),
  (16977, 20, 20, 14, 'It is naught, it is naught, saith the buyer: but when he is gone his way, then he boasteth.', '&para; [0 1] 2~07451~, [3 4] 5~07451~, 6~0559~ 8~07069~: 13~0235~ 18~01984~.'),
  (30849, 66, 8, 6, 'And the seven angels which had the seven trumpets prepared themselves to sound.', '0~2532~ 2~2033~ 3~32~ 4~3588~ 5~2192~ 7~2033~ 8~4536~ 9~2090~ 10~1438~ 11~2443~ 12~4537~.'),
  (3782, 4, 4, 34, 'And Moses and Aaron and the chief of the congregation numbered the sons of the Kohathites after their families, and after the house of their fathers,', '&para; 1~04872~ 3~0175~ 6~05387~ 9~05712~ 10~06485~ 12~01121~ 15~06956~ 18~04940~, 22~01004~ 25~01~,'),
  (1856, 2, 12, 35, 'And the children of Israel did according to the word of Moses; and they borrowed of the Egyptians jewels of silver, and jewels of gold, and raiment:', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 9~01697~ 11~04872~; 14~07592~ 17~04714~ 18~03627~ 20~03701~, 22~03627~ 24~02091~, 26~08071~:'),
  (16793, 20, 14, 12, 'There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.', '&para; 1~03426~ 3~01870~ 6~03477~ 7~06440~ 9~0376~, 12~0319~ [14] 16~01870~ 18~04194~.'),
  (30739, 66, 2, 6, 'But this thou hast, that thou hatest the deeds of the Nicolaitanes, which I also hate.', '0~235~ 1~5124~ 3~2192~, 4~3754~ 6~3404~ 8~2041~ 11~3531~, 12~3739~ 14~2504~ 15~3404~.'),
  (16732, 20, 12, 4, 'A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband: but she that maketh ashamed is as rottenness in his bones.', '&para; 1~02428~ 2~0802~ [3] 5~05850~ 8~01167~: 13~0954~ [14] 16~07538~ 19~06106~.'),
  (24219, 40, 28, 14, 'And if this come to the governor''s ears, we will persuade him, and secure you.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 2~5124~ 3~191~ 4~1909~ 6~2232~ 7~191~, 8~2249~ 10~3982~ 11~846~, 12~2532~ 13~4160~ 14~275~* 15~5209~.'),
  (10162, 12, 22, 9, 'And Shaphan the scribe came to the king, and brought the king word again, and said, Thy servants have gathered the money that was found in the house, and have delivered it into the hand of them that do the work, that have the oversight of the house of the LORD.', '1~08227~ 3~05608~ 4~0935~ 7~04428~, 9~07725~ 11~04428~ 12~01697~ 13~07725~, 15~0559~, 17~05650~ 19~05413~ 21~03701~ 24~04672~ 27~01004~, 30~05414~ 34~03027~ 38~06213~ 40~04399~, 44~06485~ 47~01004~ 50~03068~.'),
  (1123, 1, 37, 35, 'And all his sons and all his daughters rose up to comfort him; but he refused to be comforted; and he said, For I will go down into the grave unto my son mourning. Thus his father wept for him.', '3~01121~ 7~01323~ 9~06965~ 11~05162~ 15~03985~ 18~05162~; 21~0559~, 26~03381~ 29~07585~ 32~01121~ 33~057~. 36~01~ 37~01058~'),
  (20202, 24, 50, 27, 'Slay all her bullocks; let them go down to the slaughter: woe unto them! for their day is come, the time of their visitation.', '0~02717~ 3~06499~; 7~03381~ 10~02874~: 11~01945~ 16~03117~ 18~0935~, 20~06256~ 23~06486~.'),
  (2333, 2, 28, 35, 'And it shall be upon Aaron to minister: and his sound shall be heard when he goeth in unto the holy place before the LORD, and when he cometh out, that he die not.', '5~0175~ 7~08334~: 10~06963~ 13~08085~ 16~0935~ 20~06944~ [21] 22~06440~ 24~03068~, 28~03318~ 32~04191~'),
  (15106, 19, 77, 4, 'Thou holdest mine eyes waking: I am so troubled that I cannot speak.', '1~0270~ 3~05869~ 4~08109~: 8~06470~ 12~01696~.'),
  (6883, 7, 12, 7, 'And Jephthah judged Israel six years. Then died Jephthah the Gileadite, and was buried in one of the cities of Gilead.', '1~03316~ 2~08199~ 3~03478~ 4~08337~ 5~08141~. 7~04191~ 8~03316~ 10~01569~, 13~06912~ [15 16] 18~05892~ 20~01568~.'),
  (14151, 19, 18, 24, 'Therefore hath the LORD recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his eyesight.', '3~03068~ 4~07725~ 9~06664~, 13~01252~ 16~03027~ 19~05869~.'),
  (28285, 45, 13, 3, 'For rulers are not a terror to good works, but to the evil. Wilt thou then not be afraid of the power? do that which is good, and thou shalt have praise of the same:', '0~1063~ 1~758~ 2~1526~ 3~3756~ 5~5401~ 7~18~ 8~2041~, 9~235~ 12~2556~. 14~2309~ 15~1161~ 16~3361~ 18~5399~ 21~1849~? 22~4160~ 26~18~, 27~2532~ 30~2192~ 31~1868~ 32~1537~ 34~846~:'),
  (25142, 42, 5, 23, 'Whether is easier, to say, Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Rise up and walk?', '0~5101~ 1~2076~ 2~2123~, 4~2036~, 5~4675~ 6~266~ 8~863~ 9~4671~; 10~2228~ 12~2036~, 14~1453~ 15~2532~ 16~4043~?'),
  (240, 1, 10, 5, 'By these were the isles of the Gentiles divided in their lands; every one after his tongue, after their families, in their nations.', '4~0339~ 7~01471~ 9~06504~ 11~0776~; 13~0376~ 16~03956~, 19~04940~, 22~01471~.'),
  (12044, 15, 2, 8, 'The children of Zattu, nine hundred forty and five.', '1~01121~ 3~02240~, 4~08672~ 5~03967~ 6~0705~ 8~02568~.'),
  (26972, 44, 2, 7, 'And they were all amazed and marvelled, saying one to another, Behold, are not all these which speak Galilaeans?', '0~1161~ 2~1839~ 3~3956~ 4~1839~ 5~2532~ 6~2296~, 7~3004~ 10~240~ 11~4314~,* 12~2400~, 13~1526~ 14~3756~ 15~3956~ 16~3778~ 17~3588~ 18~2980~ 19~1057~?'),
  (29118, 48, 2, 21, 'I do not frustrate the grace of God: for if righteousness come by the law, then Christ is dead in vain.', '1~114~ 2~3756~ 3~114~ 5~5485~ 7~2316~: 8~1063~ 9~1487~ 10~1343~ [11] 12~1223~ 14~3551~, 15~686~ 16~5547~ 18~599~ 20~1432~.'),
  (6474, 6, 23, 7, 'That ye come not among these nations, these that remain among you; neither make mention of the name of their gods, nor cause to swear by them, neither serve them, nor bow yourselves unto them:', '2~0935~ 6~01471~, 9~07604~ 14~02142~ 17~08034~ 20~0430~, 24~07650~ [25 26] 28~05647~ 31~07812~'),
  (13253, 18, 16, 6, 'Though I speak, my grief is not asswaged: and though I forbear, what am I eased?', '&para; 2~01696~, 4~03511~ 7~02820~: [9] 11~02308~, 15~01980~?'),
  (21611, 26, 44, 3, 'It is for the prince; the prince, he shall sit in it to eat bread before the LORD; he shall enter by the way of the porch of that gate, and shall go out by the way of the same.', '[0 1] 4~05387~; 6~05387~, 9~03427~ 13~0398~ 14~03899~ 15~06440~ 17~03068~; 20~0935~ 23~01870~ 26~0197~ [28] 29~08179~, 33~03318~ 36~01870~'),
  (10490, 13, 6, 28, 'And the sons of Samuel; the firstborn Vashni, and Abiah.', '2~01121~ 4~08050~; 6~01060~ 7~02059~, 9~029~.'),
  (4910, 5, 1, 12, 'How can I myself alone bear your cumbrance, and your burden, and your strife?', '0~0349~ 5~05375~ 7~02960~, 10~04853~, 13~07379~?'),
  (11642, 14, 21, 9, 'Then Jehoram went forth with his princes, and all his chariots with him: and he rose up by night, and smote the Edomites which compassed him in, and the captains of the chariots.', '1~03088~ 3~05674~ 6~08269~, 10~07393~ 16~06965~ 18~03915~, 20~05221~ 22~0123~ 26~05437~, 29~08269~ 32~07393~.'),
  (25204, 42, 6, 46, 'And why call ye me, Lord, Lord, and do not the things which I say?', '0~1161~ 1~5101~ 3~2564~ 4~3165~, 5~2962~, 6~2962~, 7~2532~ 8~4160~ 9~3756~ 12~3739~ 14~3004~?'),
  (14296, 19, 27, 2, 'When the wicked, even mine enemies and my foes, came upon me to eat up my flesh, they stumbled and fell.', '2~07489~, [3] 5~06862~ 8~0341~, 9~07126~ 14~0398~ 16~01320~, 18~03782~ 20~05307~.'),
  (26453, 43, 8, 57, 'Then said the Jews unto him, Thou art not yet fifty years old, and hast thou seen Abraham?', '0~3767~ 1~2036~ 3~2453~ 4~4314~ 5~846~, 7~2192~ 9~3768~ 10~4004~ 12~2094~, 13~2532~ 16~3708~ 17~11~?'),
  (29063, 47, 13, 4, 'For though he was crucified through weakness, yet he liveth by the power of God. For we also are weak in him, but we shall live with him by the power of God toward you.', '0~2532~ 1~1063~* 2~1487~ 5~4717~ 6~1537~ 7~769~, 8~235~ 10~2198~ 11~1537~ 13~1411~ 15~2316~. 16~1063~ 17~2249~ 18~2532~ 20~770~ 21~1722~ 22~846~, 23~235~ 26~2198~ 27~4862~ 28~846~ 29~1537~ 31~1411~ 33~2316~ 34~1519~ 35~5209~.'),
  (4111, 4, 13, 31, 'But the men that went up with him said, We be not able to go up against the people; for they are stronger than we.', '2~0582~ 5~05927~ 8~0559~, 12~03201~ 15~05927~ 18~05971~; [21] 22~02389~'),
  (7003, 7, 18, 3, 'When they were by the house of Micah, they knew the voice of the young man the Levite: and they turned in thither, and said unto him, Who brought thee hither? and what makest thou in this place? and what hast thou here?', '[2] 5~01004~ 7~04318~, 9~05234~ 11~06963~ 15~05288~ 17~03881~: 21~05493~ 24~0559~ 28~0935~ 30~01988~? 33~06213~ [37]'),
  (4942, 5, 1, 44, 'And the Amorites, which dwelt in that mountain, came out against you, and chased you, as bees do, and destroyed you in Seir, even unto Hormah.', '2~0567~, 4~03427~ 7~02022~, 9~03318~ 10~07125~ 13~07291~ 16~01682~ 17~06213~, 19~03807~ 22~08165~, [23] 25~02767~.'),
  (18861, 23, 61, 9, 'And their seed shall be known among the Gentiles, and their offspring among the people: all that see them shall acknowledge them, that they are the seed which the LORD hath blessed.', '2~02233~ 5~03045~ 8~01471~, 11~06631~ 12~08432~ 14~05971~: 17~07200~ 20~05234~ [24] 26~02233~ [27] 29~03068~ 31~01288~.'),
  (13344, 18, 20, 9, 'The eye also which saw him shall see him no more; neither shall his place any more behold him.', '1~05869~ [3] 4~07805~ [7 8] 10~03254~; 14~04725~ 17~07789~'),
  (27701, 44, 21, 21, 'And they are informed of thee, that thou teachest all the Jews which are among the Gentiles to forsake Moses, saying that they ought not to circumcise their children, neither to walk after the customs.', '0~1161~ 3~2727~ 4~4012~ 5~4675~, 6~3754~ 8~1321~ 9~3956~ 11~2453~ 14~2596~ 16~1484~ 17~575~ 18~646~ 19~3475~, 20~3004~ 22~846~ 23~4059~ 24~3361~ 26~4059~ [27] 28~5043~, 29~3366~ 31~4043~ 34~1485~.'),
  (4355, 4, 21, 10, 'And the children of Israel set forward, and pitched in Oboth.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 6~05265~, 8~02583~ 10~088~.'),
  (15196, 19, 79, 2, 'The dead bodies of thy servants have they given to be meat unto the fowls of the heaven, the flesh of thy saints unto the beasts of the earth.', '2~05038~ 5~05650~ 8~05414~ [9 10] 11~03978~ 14~05775~ 17~08064~, 19~01320~ 22~02623~ 25~02416~ 28~0776~.'),
  (11767, 14, 27, 3, 'He built the high gate of the house of the LORD, and on the wall of Ophel he built much.', '1~01129~ 3~05945~ 4~08179~ 7~01004~ 10~03068~, 14~02346~ 16~06077~ 18~01129~ 19~07230~.'),
  (8856, 11, 4, 4, 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the host: and Zadok and Abiathar were the priests:', '1~01141~ 3~01121~ 5~03077~ [6] 9~06635~: 11~06659~ 13~054~ [14] 16~03548~:'),
  (30183, 58, 10, 34, 'For ye had compassion of me in my bonds, and took joyfully the spoiling of your goods, knowing in yourselves that ye have in heaven a better and an enduring substance.', '0~1063~ 1~2532~ 3~4834~ 7~3450~ 8~1199~, 9~2532~ 10~4327~ 11~5479~ 12~3326~ 13~724~ 15~5216~ 16~5224~, 17~1097~ 18~1722~ 19~1438~ 22~2192~ 23~1722~ 24~3772~ 26~2909~ 27~2532~ 29~3306~ 30~5223~.'),
  (6624, 7, 4, 18, 'And Jael went out to meet Sisera, and said unto him, Turn in, my lord, turn in to me; fear not. And when he had turned in unto her into the tent, she covered him with a mantle.', '1~03278~ 3~03318~ 5~07125~ 6~05516~, 8~0559~ 12~05493~, 14~0113~, 16~05493~ 19~03372~ 26~05493~ 31~0168~, 33~03680~ 37~08063~.'),
  (25443, 42, 11, 26, 'Then goeth he, and taketh to him seven other spirits more wicked than himself; and they enter in, and dwell there: and the last state of that man is worse than the first.', '0~5119~ 2~4198~, 3~2532~ 4~3880~ [5 6] 7~2033~ 8~2087~ 9~4151~ 11~4191~ 13~1438~; 14~2532~ 17~1525~, 19~2730~ 20~1563~: 21~2532~ 23~2078~ [24] 26~1565~ 27~444~ 28~1096~ 29~5501~ 32~4413~.'),
  (11769, 14, 27, 5, 'He fought also with the king of the Ammonites, and prevailed against them. And the children of Ammon gave him the same year an hundred talents of silver, and ten thousand measures of wheat, and ten thousand of barley. So much did the children of Ammon pay unto him, both the second year, and the third.', '1~03898~ 5~04428~ 8~05984~, 10~02388~ 15~01121~ 17~05983~ 18~05414~ 22~08141~ 24~03967~ 25~03603~ 27~03701~, 29~06235~ 30~0505~ 31~03734~ 33~02406~, 35~06235~ 36~0505~ 38~08184~. 43~01121~ 45~05983~ 46~07725~ 47~02063~ 51~08145~ 52~08141~, 55~07992~.'),
  (4177, 4, 15, 19, 'Then it shall be, that, when ye eat of the bread of the land, ye shall offer up an heave offering unto the LORD.', '7~0398~ 10~03899~ 13~0776~, 17~07311~ 20~08641~ 23~03068~.'),
  (2604, 2, 36, 33, 'And he made the middle bar to shoot through the boards from the one end to the other.', '2~06213~ 4~08484~ 5~01280~ 7~01272~ 8~08432~ 10~07175~ 14~07097~ 17~07097~.'),
  (5066, 5, 5, 7, 'Thou shalt have none other gods before me.', '4~0312~ 5~0430~ 6~06440~'),
  (23203, 40, 3, 1, 'In those days came John the Baptist, preaching in the wilderness of Judaea,', '&para; 0~1161~* 1~1722~ 2~1565~ 3~2250~ 4~3854~ 5~2491~ 7~910~, 8~2784~ 9~1722~ 11~2048~ 13~2449~,'),
  (17277, 20, 30, 17, 'The eye that mocketh at his father, and despiseth to obey his mother, the ravens of the valley shall pick it out, and the young eagles shall eat it.', '1~05869~ [2] 3~03932~ [5] 6~01~, 8~0936~ 10~03349~ [11] 12~0517~, 14~06158~ 17~05158~ 21~05365~, 24~01121~ 25~05404~ 27~0398~'),
  (24261, 41, 1, 36, 'And Simon and they that were with him followed after him.', '0~2532~ 1~4613~ 2~2532~ 6~3326~ 7~846~ 9~2614~ 10~846~.'),
  (18627, 23, 48, 4, 'Because I knew that thou art obstinate, and thy neck is an iron sinew, and thy brow brass;', '2~01847~ [5] 6~07186~, 9~06203~ [10] 12~01270~ 13~01517~, 16~04696~ 17~05154~;'),
  (2242, 2, 26, 2, 'The length of one curtain shall be eight and twenty cubits, and the breadth of one curtain four cubits: and every one of the curtains shall have one measure.', '1~0753~ 3~0259~ 4~03407~ [5 6] 7~08083~ 9~06242~ 10~0520~, 13~07341~ 15~0259~ 16~03407~ 17~0702~ 18~0520~: 24~03407~ 27~0259~ 28~04060~.'),
  (3530, 3, 26, 1, 'Ye shall make you no idols nor graven image, neither rear you up a standing image, neither shall ye set up any image of stone in your land, to bow down unto it: for I am the LORD your God.', '&para; 2~06213~ 5~0457~ 8~06459~, 12~06965~ 15~04676~, 20~05414~ [21] 22~04906~ 24~068~ 27~0776~, 30~07812~ [35] 37~03068~ 39~0430~.'),
  (599, 1, 24, 4, 'But thou shalt go unto my country, and to my kindred, and take a wife unto my son Isaac.', '3~03212~ 6~0776~, 10~04138~, 12~03947~ 14~0802~ 17~01121~ 18~03327~.'),
  (11950, 14, 34, 8, 'Now in the eighteenth year of his reign, when he had purged the land, and the house, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, and Maaseiah the governor of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz the recorder, to repair the house of the LORD his God.', '&para; 3~06240~ 4~08083~* 5~08141~ 8~04427~, 12~02891~ 14~0776~, 17~01004~, 19~07971~ 20~08227~ 22~01121~ 24~0683~, 26~04641~ 28~08269~ 31~05892~, 33~03098~ 35~01121~ 37~03099~ 39~02142~, 41~02388~ 43~01004~ 46~03068~ 48~0430~.'),
  (2427, 2, 31, 2, 'See, I have called by name Bezaleel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah:', '0~07200~, 3~07121~ 5~08034~ 6~01212~ 8~01121~ 10~0221~, 12~01121~ 14~02354~, 17~04294~ 19~03063~:'),
  (16663, 20, 9, 16, 'Whoso is simple, let him turn in hither: and as for him that wanteth understanding, she saith to him,', '[1] 2~06612~, 6~05493~ [9 10] 13~02638~ 14~03820~, 16~0559~'),
  (1652, 2, 5, 15, 'Then the officers of the children of Israel came and cried unto Pharaoh, saying, Wherefore dealest thou thus with thy servants?', '&para; 2~07860~ 5~01121~ 7~03478~ 8~0935~ 10~06817~ 12~06547~, 13~0559~, 15~06213~ 20~05650~?'),
  (19021, 24, 3, 10, 'And yet for all this her treacherous sister Judah hath not turned unto me with her whole heart, but feignedly, saith the LORD.', '6~0901~ 7~0269~ 8~03063~ 11~07725~ 17~03820~, 19~08267~, 20~05002~ 22~03068~.'),
  (6403, 6, 21, 15, 'And Holon with her suburbs, and Debir with her suburbs,', '1~02473~ 4~04054~, 6~01688~ 9~04054~,'),
  (18510, 23, 42, 21, 'The LORD is well pleased for his righteousness'' sake; he will magnify the law, and make it honourable.', '1~03068~ 4~02654~ 7~06664~ 11~01431~ 13~08451~, [16] 17~0142~.'),
  (11543, 14, 17, 11, 'Also some of the Philistines brought Jehoshaphat presents, and tribute silver; and the Arabians brought him flocks, seven thousand and seven hundred rams, and seven thousand and seven hundred he goats.', '[1] 4~06430~ 5~0935~ 6~03092~ 7~04503~, 9~04853~ 10~03701~; 13~06163~ 14~0935~ 16~06629~, 17~07651~ 18~0505~ 20~07651~ 21~03967~ 22~0352~, 24~07651~ 25~0505~ 27~07651~ 28~03967~ 30~08495~.'),
  (26057, 42, 24, 52, 'And they worshipped him, and returned to Jerusalem with great joy:', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~4352~ 3~846~, 5~5290~ 6~1519~ 7~2419~ 8~3326~ 9~3173~ 10~5479~:'),
  (1492, 1, 49, 14, 'Issachar is a strong ass couching down between two burdens:', '0~03485~ [1] 3~01634~ 4~02543~ 6~07257~ 9~04942~:'),
  (29306, 49, 4, 18, 'Having the understanding darkened, being alienated from the life of God through the ignorance that is in them, because of the blindness of their heart:', '2~1271~ 3~4654~, 4~5607~ 5~526~ 8~2222~ 10~2316~ 11~1223~ 13~52~ 15~5607~ 16~1722~ 17~846~, 18~1223~ 21~4457~ 23~846~ 24~2588~:');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (14620, 19, 45, 14, 'She shall be brought unto the king in raiment of needlework: the virgins her companions that follow her shall be brought unto thee.', '3~02986~ 6~04428~ 10~07553~: 12~01330~ 14~07464~ 16~0310~ 20~0935~'),
  (18297, 23, 33, 9, 'The earth mourneth and languisheth: Lebanon is ashamed and hewn down: Sharon is like a wilderness; and Bashan and Carmel shake off their fruits.', '1~0776~ 2~056~ [3] 4~0535~: 5~03844~ 7~02659~ [8] 10~07060~: 11~08289~ 15~06160~; 17~01316~ 19~03760~ 21~05287~ [22 23]'),
  (8723, 10, 24, 23, 'All these things did Araunah, as a king, give unto the king. And Araunah said unto the king, The LORD thy God accept thee.', '[2] 4~0728~, [5] 7~04428~, 8~05414~ 11~04428~. 13~0728~ 14~0559~ 17~04428~, 19~03068~ 21~0430~ 22~07521~'),
  (12008, 14, 36, 6, 'Against him came up Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and bound him in fetters, to carry him to Babylon.', '3~05927~ 4~05019~ 5~04428~ 7~0894~, 9~0631~ 12~05178~, 14~03212~ 17~0894~.'),
  (89, 1, 4, 9, 'And the LORD said unto Cain, Where is Abel thy brother? And he said, I know not: Am I my brother''s keeper?', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~07014~, 6~0335~ [7] 8~01893~ 10~0251~? 13~0559~, 15~03045~ [17] 20~0251~ 21~08104~?'),
  (14677, 19, 49, 20, 'Man that is in honour, and understandeth not, is like the beasts that perish.', '0~0120~ [1 2] 4~03366~, 6~0995~ 9~04911~ 11~0929~ [12] 13~01820~.'),
  (18818, 23, 59, 9, 'Therefore is judgment far from us, neither doth justice overtake us: we wait for light, but behold obscurity; for brightness, but we walk in darkness.', '&para; 2~04941~ 3~07368~ 8~06666~ 9~05381~ 12~06960~ 14~0216~, 17~02822~; 19~05054~, [20] 22~01980~ 24~0653~.'),
  (16288, 19, 141, 3, 'Set a watch, O LORD, before my mouth; keep the door of my lips.', '0~07896~ 2~08108~, 4~03068~, 7~06310~; 8~05341~ 10~01817~ 13~08193~.'),
  (462, 1, 19, 1, 'And there came two angels to Sodom at even; and Lot sat in the gate of Sodom: and Lot seeing them rose up to meet them; and he bowed himself with his face toward the ground;', '&para; 2~0935~ 3~08147~ 4~04397~ 6~05467~ 8~06153~; 10~03876~ 11~03427~ 14~08179~ 16~05467~: 18~03876~ 19~07200~ [20] 22~06965~ 24~07125~ 28~07812~ 32~0639~ 35~0776~;'),
  (28022, 45, 3, 15, 'Their feet are swift to shed blood:', '0~846~ 1~4228~ [2] 3~3691~ 5~1632~ 6~129~:'),
  (7773, 9, 20, 36, 'And he said unto his lad, Run, find out now the arrows which I shoot. And as the lad ran, he shot an arrow beyond him.', '2~0559~ 5~05288~, 6~07323~, 8~04672~ 11~02671~ 14~03384~. [15] 18~05288~ 19~07323~, 21~03384~ 23~02678~ 24~05674~'),
  (23297, 40, 6, 5, 'And when thou prayest, thou shalt not be as the hypocrites are: for they love to pray standing in the synagogues and in the corners of the streets, that they may be seen of men. Verily I say unto you, They have their reward.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3752~ 3~4336~, 5~2071~ 6~3756~ 7~2071~ 8~5618~ 10~5273~ [11] 12~3754~ 14~5368~ 16~4336~ 17~2476~ 18~1722~ 20~4864~ 21~2532~ 22~1722~ 24~1137~ 27~4113~, 28~3704~ 30~302~ 32~5316~ 34~444~. 35~281~ 37~3004~ 39~5213~ 40~3754~,* 42~568~ 43~846~ 44~3408~.'),
  (15263, 19, 83, 13, 'O my God, make them like a wheel; as the stubble before the wind.', '2~0430~, 3~07896~ 7~01534~; 10~07179~ 11~06440~ 13~07307~.'),
  (30769, 66, 3, 7, 'And to the angel of the church in Philadelphia write; These things saith he that is holy, he that is true, he that hath the key of David, he that openeth, and no man shutteth; and shutteth, and no man openeth;', '&para; 0~2532~ 3~32~ 6~1577~ 7~1722~ 8~5359~ 9~1125~; 11~3592~ 12~3004~ 16~40~, 20~228~, 23~2192~ 25~2807~ 27~1138~, 30~455~, 31~2532~ 33~3762~ 34~2808~; 35~2532~ 36~2808~, 37~2532~ 39~3762~ 40~455~;'),
  (12481, 16, 7, 52, 'The children of Besai, the children of Meunim, the children of Nephishesim,', '1~01121~ 3~01153~, 5~01121~ 7~04586~, 9~01121~ 11~05300~ 12~05304~,*'),
  (17014, 20, 21, 21, 'He that followeth after righteousness and mercy findeth life, righteousness, and honour.', '&para; 2~07291~ 4~06666~ 6~02617~ 7~04672~ 8~02416~, 9~06666~, 11~03519~.'),
  (28193, 45, 9, 22, 'What if God, willing to shew his wrath, and to make his power known, endured with much longsuffering the vessels of wrath fitted to destruction:', '[0] 1~1161~ 2~1487~* 3~2316~, 4~2309~ 6~1731~ [7] 8~3709~, 9~2532~ 11~1107~ 12~846~ 13~1415~ 14~1107~, 15~5342~ 16~1722~ 17~4183~ 18~3115~ 20~4632~ 22~3709~ 23~2675~ 24~1519~ 25~684~:'),
  (20783, 26, 16, 12, 'And I put a jewel on thy forehead, and earrings in thine ears, and a beautiful crown upon thine head.', '2~05414~ 4~05141~ 7~0639~, 9~05694~ 12~0241~, 15~08597~ 16~05850~ 19~07218~.'),
  (27861, 44, 26, 22, 'Having therefore obtained help of God, I continue unto this day, witnessing both to small and great, saying none other things than those which the prophets and Moses did say should come:', '0~5177~ 1~3767~ 2~5177~ 3~1947~ 4~3844~ 5~2316~, 7~2476~ 8~891~ 9~5026~ 10~2250~, 11~3140~ 12~5037~ 14~3398~ 15~2532~ 16~3173~, 17~3004~ 20~3762~ 21~1622~ 23~5037~ 24~3739~ 25~4396~ 26~2532~ 27~3475~ 29~2980~ 30~3195~ 31~1096~:'),
  (11201, 13, 29, 29, 'Now the acts of David the king, first and last, behold, they are written in the book of Samuel the seer, and in the book of Nathan the prophet, and in the book of Gad the seer,', '2~01697~ 4~01732~ 6~04428~, 7~07223~ 9~0314~, [12] 13~03789~ 16~01697~ 18~08050~ 20~07200~, 24~01697~ 26~05416~ 28~05030~, 32~01697~ 34~01410~ 36~02374~,'),
  (8671, 10, 23, 10, 'He arose, and smote the Philistines until his hand was weary, and his hand clave unto the sword: and the LORD wrought a great victory that day; and the people returned after him only to spoil.', '1~06965~, 3~05221~ 5~06430~ 6~03588~ 8~03027~ 10~03021~, 13~03027~ 14~01692~ 17~02719~: 20~03068~ 21~06213~ 23~01419~ 24~08668~ 26~03117~; 29~05971~ 30~07725~ 31~0310~ 35~06584~.'),
  (14629, 19, 46, 6, 'The heathen raged, the kingdoms were moved: he uttered his voice, the earth melted.', '&para; 1~01471~ 2~01993~, 4~04467~ 6~04131~: 8~05414~ 10~06963~, 12~0776~ 13~04127~.'),
  (23876, 40, 21, 40, 'When the lord therefore of the vineyard cometh, what will he do unto those husbandmen?', '0~3752~ 2~2962~ 3~3767~ 6~290~ 7~2064~, 8~5101~ 11~4160~ 13~1565~ 14~1092~?'),
  (3931, 4, 7, 76, 'One kid of the goats for a sin offering:', '0~0259~ 1~08163~ 4~05795~ 8~02403~:'),
  (10692, 13, 11, 11, 'And this is the number of the mighty men whom David had; Jashobeam, an Hachmonite, the chief of the captains: he lifted up his spear against three hundred slain by him at one time.', '[2] 4~04557~ 8~01368~ 10~01732~ 12~03434~, 14~02453~, 16~07218~ 19~07991~ 20~07970~:* 23~05782~ 25~02595~ 27~07969~ 28~03967~ 29~02491~ [30 31] 33~0259~ 34~06471~.'),
  (20523, 26, 3, 12, 'Then the spirit took me up, and I heard behind me a voice of a great rushing, saying, Blessed be the glory of the LORD from his place.', '2~07307~ 5~05375~, 8~08085~ 9~0310~ 12~06963~ 15~01419~ 16~07494~, [17] 18~01288~ [19] 21~03519~ 24~03068~ 27~04725~.'),
  (5483, 5, 22, 7, 'But thou shalt in any wise let the dam go, and take the young to thee; that it may be well with thee, and that thou mayest prolong thy days.', '[0] 5~07971~ 8~0517~ 9~07971~, 11~03947~ 13~01121~ 20~03190~ [24] 27~0748~ [28] 29~03117~.'),
  (22275, 28, 12, 14, 'Ephraim provoked him to anger most bitterly: therefore shall he leave his blood upon him, and his reproach shall his Lord return unto him.', '0~0669~ [2] 4~03707~ 6~08563~: 10~05203~ 12~01818~ 17~02781~ 20~0113~ 21~07725~'),
  (18160, 23, 26, 21, 'For, behold, the LORD cometh out of his place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity: the earth also shall disclose her blood, and shall no more cover her slain.', '3~03068~ 5~03318~ 8~04725~ 10~06485~ 12~03427~ 15~0776~ 18~05771~: 20~0776~ 23~01540~ 25~01818~, 30~03680~ 32~02026~.'),
  (26398, 43, 8, 2, 'And early in the morning he came again into the temple, and all the people came unto him; and he sat down, and taught them.', '0~1161~ 4~3722~ 6~3854~ 7~3825~ 8~1519~ 10~2411~, 11~2532~ 12~3956~ 14~2992~ 15~2064~ 16~4314~ 17~846~; 18~2532~ 21~2523~, 23~1321~ 24~846~.'),
  (8258, 10, 10, 11, 'And he said, If the Syrians be too strong for me, then thou shalt help me: but if the children of Ammon be too strong for thee, then I will come and help thee.', '2~0559~, 5~0758~ 8~02388~ 14~03444~ 19~01121~ 21~05983~ 24~02388~ 30~01980~ 32~03467~'),
  (25407, 42, 10, 32, 'And likewise a Levite, when he was at the place, came and looked on him, and passed by on the other side.', '0~1161~ 1~2532~ 2~3668~ 3~3019~, 6~1096~ 7~2596~ 9~5117~, 10~2064~ 11~2532~ 12~1492~ [13 14] 21~492~.'),
  (9584, 12, 2, 25, 'And he went from thence to mount Carmel, and from thence he returned to Samaria.', '2~03212~ 6~02022~ 7~03760~, 12~07725~ 14~08111~.'),
  (11076, 13, 25, 22, 'The fifteenth to Jeremoth, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~06240~ 2~02568~ 3~03406~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (15245, 19, 82, 3, 'Defend the poor and fatherless: do justice to the afflicted and needy.', '0~08199~ 2~01800~ 4~03490~: 6~06663~ 9~06041~ 11~07326~.'),
  (19820, 24, 34, 10, 'Now when all the princes, and all the people, which had entered into the covenant, heard that every one should let his manservant, and every one his maidservant, go free, that none should serve themselves of them any more, then they obeyed, and let them go.', '4~08269~, 8~05971~, 11~0935~ 14~01285~, 15~08085~ 18~0376~ 22~05650~, 25~0376~ 27~08198~, 28~07971~ 29~02670~, 33~05647~ 41~08085~, [44] 45~07971~.'),
  (16743, 20, 12, 15, 'The way of a fool is right in his own eyes: but he that hearkeneth unto counsel is wise.', '&para; 1~01870~ 4~0191~ [5] 6~03477~ 10~05869~: 14~08085~ 16~06098~ [17] 18~02450~.'),
  (31093, 66, 21, 24, 'And the nations of them which are saved shall walk in the light of it: and the kings of the earth do bring their glory and honour into it.', '0~2532~ 2~1484~ 7~4982~ 9~4043~ 10~1722~ 12~5457~ 14~846~: 15~2532~ 17~935~ 20~1093~ 22~5342~ 23~846~ 24~1391~ 25~2532~ 26~5092~ 27~1519~ 28~846~.'),
  (25354, 42, 9, 41, 'And Jesus answering said, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you, and suffer you? Bring thy son hither.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~, 4~5599~ 5~571~ 6~2532~ 7~1294~ 8~1074~, 9~2193~ 10~4219~ 13~2071~ 14~4314~ 15~5209~, 16~2532~ 17~430~ 18~5216~? 19~4317~ 20~4675~ 21~5207~ 22~5602~.'),
  (10866, 13, 16, 38, 'And Obededom with their brethren, threescore and eight; Obededom also the son of Jeduthun and Hosah to be porters:', '1~05654~ 4~0251~, 5~08346~ 7~08083~; 8~05654~ 11~01121~ 13~03038~ 15~02621~ [16 17] 18~07778~:'),
  (18072, 23, 22, 11, 'Ye made also a ditch between the two walls for the water of the old pool: but ye have not looked unto the maker thereof, neither had respect unto him that fashioned it long ago.', '1~06213~ 4~04724~ 8~02346~ 11~04325~ 14~03465~ 15~01295~: 20~05027~ 23~06213~ 27~07200~ 31~03335~ 34~07350~.'),
  (28294, 45, 13, 12, 'The night is far spent, the day is at hand: let us therefore cast off the works of darkness, and let us put on the armour of light.', '1~3571~ 4~4298~ 5~1161~,* 7~2250~ 10~1448~: 12~659~ 13~3767~ 15~659~ 17~2041~ 19~4655~, 20~2532~ 24~1746~ 26~3696~ 28~5457~.'),
  (25643, 42, 16, 10, 'He that is faithful in that which is least is faithful also in much: and he that is unjust in the least is unjust also in much.', '3~4103~ 4~1722~ 8~1646~ 9~2076~ 10~4103~ 11~2532~ 12~1722~ 13~4183~: 14~2532~ 18~94~ 19~1722~ 21~1646~ 22~2076~ 23~94~ 24~2532~ 25~1722~ 26~4183~.'),
  (21993, 27, 8, 23, 'And in the latter time of their kingdom, when the transgressors are come to the full, a king of fierce countenance, and understanding dark sentences, shall stand up.', '4~0319~ 7~04438~, 10~06586~ 15~08552~, 17~04428~ 19~05794~ 20~06440~, 22~0995~ 24~02420~, 27~05975~.'),
  (13083, 18, 9, 23, 'If the scourge slay suddenly, he will laugh at the trial of the innocent.', '2~07752~ 3~04191~ 4~06597~, 7~03932~ 10~04531~ 13~05355~.'),
  (20242, 24, 51, 21, 'And with thee will I break in pieces the horse and his rider; and with thee will I break in pieces the chariot and his rider;', '7~05310~ 9~05483~ 12~07392~; 20~05310~ 22~07393~ 25~07392~;'),
  (8026, 9, 31, 10, 'And they put his armour in the house of Ashtaroth: and they fastened his body to the wall of Bethshan.', '2~07760~ 4~03627~ 7~01004~ 9~06252~ 10~01045~:* 13~08628~ 15~01472~ 18~02346~ 20~01052~.'),
  (25180, 42, 6, 22, 'Blessed are ye, when men shall hate you, and when they shall separate you from their company, and shall reproach you, and cast out your name as evil, for the Son of man''s sake.', '0~3107~ 2~2075~, 3~3752~ 4~444~ 6~3404~ 7~5209~, 8~2532~ 9~3752~ 12~873~ 13~5209~ [14 16] 17~2532~ 19~3679~ [20] 21~2532~ 23~1544~ 24~5216~ 25~3686~ 26~5613~ 27~4190~, 30~5207~ 32~444~ 33~1752~.'),
  (28206, 45, 10, 2, 'For I bear them record that they have a zeal of God, but not according to knowledge.', '0~1063~ 2~3140~ 3~846~ 4~3140~ 5~3754~ 7~2192~ 9~2205~ 11~2316~, 12~235~ 13~3756~ 14~2596~ 16~1922~.'),
  (24765, 41, 13, 37, 'And what I say unto you I say unto all, Watch.', '0~1161~ 1~3739~ 3~3004~ 5~5213~ 7~3004~ 9~3956~, 10~1127~.'),
  (17247, 20, 29, 14, 'The king that faithfully judgeth the poor, his throne shall be established for ever.', '&para; 1~04428~ 3~0571~ 4~08199~ 6~01800~, 8~03678~ 11~03559~ 13~05703~.'),
  (17851, 23, 9, 13, 'For the people turneth not unto him that smiteth them, neither do they seek the LORD of hosts.', '2~05971~ 3~07725~ 8~05221~ 13~01875~ 15~03068~ 17~06635~.'),
  (5268, 5, 12, 22, 'Even as the roebuck and the hart is eaten, so thou shalt eat them: the unclean and the clean shall eat of them alike.', '3~06643~ 6~0354~ 8~0398~, 12~0398~ 15~02931~ 18~02889~ 20~0398~ [21] 23~03162~.'),
  (30958, 66, 14, 16, 'And he that sat on the cloud thrust in his sickle on the earth; and the earth was reaped.', '0~2532~ 3~2521~ 4~1909~ 6~3507~ 8~906~ 9~846~ 10~1407~ 11~1909~ 13~1093~; 14~2532~ 16~1093~ 18~2325~.'),
  (7818, 9, 23, 1, 'Then they told David, saying, Behold, the Philistines fight against Keilah, and they rob the threshingfloors.', '&para; 2~05046~ 3~01732~, 4~0559~, 7~06430~ 8~03898~ 10~07084~, 13~08154~ 15~01637~.'),
  (2569, 2, 35, 33, 'And in the cutting of stones, to set them, and in carving of wood, to make any manner of cunning work.', '3~02799~ 5~068~, 7~04390~ [8] 11~02799~ 13~06086~, 15~06213~ 19~04284~ 20~04399~.'),
  (16172, 19, 132, 12, 'If thy children will keep my covenant and my testimony that I shall teach them, their children shall also sit upon thy throne for evermore.', '2~01121~ 4~08104~ 6~01285~ 9~05713~ 10~02090~ 11~02097~* 14~03925~ 17~01121~ 20~03427~ 23~03678~ 25~05703~.'),
  (18597, 23, 46, 2, 'They stoop, they bow down together; they could not deliver the burden, but themselves are gone into captivity.', '1~07164~, 4~03766~ 5~03162~; 7~03201~ 9~04422~ 11~04853~, 13~05315~ 15~01980~ 17~07628~.'),
  (15741, 19, 107, 33, 'He turneth rivers into a wilderness, and the watersprings into dry ground;', '&para; 1~07760~ 2~05104~ 5~04057~, 8~04161~ 9~04325~ 11~06774~;'),
  (3637, 4, 1, 28, 'Of the children of Issachar, by their generations, after their families, by the house of their fathers, according to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war;', '2~01121~ 4~03485~, 7~08435~, 10~04940~, 13~01004~ 16~01~, 20~04557~ 23~08034~, 25~06242~ 26~08141~ 27~01121~ 29~04605~, 36~03318~ 38~06635~;'),
  (3497, 3, 25, 23, 'The land shall not be sold for ever: for the land is mine; for ye are strangers and sojourners with me.', '&para; 1~0776~ 5~04376~ 7~06783~: 10~0776~ [11] [15] 16~01616~ 18~08453~'),
  (3077, 3, 13, 20, 'And if, when the priest seeth it, behold, it be in sight lower than the skin, and the hair thereof be turned white; the priest shall pronounce him unclean: it is a plague of leprosy broken out of the boil.', '4~03548~ 5~07200~ [9] 11~04758~ 12~08217~ 15~05785~, 18~08181~ 21~02015~ 22~03836~; 24~03548~ 28~02930~: [30] 32~05061~ 34~06883~ 35~06524~ 39~07822~.'),
  (1817, 2, 11, 6, 'And there shall be a great cry throughout all the land of Egypt, such as there was none like it, nor shall be like it any more.', '3~01961~ 5~01419~ 6~06818~ 10~0776~ 12~04714~, 17~03808~ 20~03808~ 26~03254~.'),
  (4834, 4, 34, 12, 'And the border shall go down to Jordan, and the goings out of it shall be at the salt sea: this shall be your land with the coasts thereof round about.', '2~01366~ 5~03381~ 7~03383~, 11~08444~ 18~04417~ 19~03220~: 24~0776~ 27~01367~ 30~05439~.'),
  (21193, 26, 29, 1, 'In the tenth year, in the tenth month, in the twelfth day of the month, the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~06224~ 3~08141~, 6~06224~ [7] 10~06240~ [11] 11~08147~ 14~02320~, 16~01697~ 19~03068~ 23~0559~,'),
  (4336, 4, 20, 20, 'And he said, Thou shalt not go through. And Edom came out against him with much people, and with a strong hand.', '2~0559~, 7~05674~. 9~0123~ 11~03318~ 12~07125~ 15~03515~ 16~05971~, 20~02389~ 21~03027~.'),
  (26740, 43, 15, 26, 'But when the Comforter is come, whom I will send unto you from the Father, even the Spirit of truth, which proceedeth from the Father, he shall testify of me:', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3752~ 3~3875~ 5~2064~, 6~3739~ 7~1473~ 9~3992~ 11~5213~ 12~3844~ 14~3962~, [15] 17~4151~ 19~225~, 20~3739~ 21~1607~ 22~3844~ 24~3962~, 25~1565~ 27~3140~ 28~4012~ 29~1700~:'),
  (27737, 44, 22, 17, 'And it came to pass, that, when I was come again to Jerusalem, even while I prayed in the temple, I was in a trance;', '0~1161~ 4~1096~, 7~3427~ 10~5290~ 11~1519~ 12~2419~, 13~2532~ 15~3450~ 16~4336~ 17~1722~ 19~2411~, 20~3165~ 21~1096~ 22~1722~ 24~1611~;'),
  (14254, 19, 24, 4, 'He that hath clean hands, and a pure heart; who hath not lifted up his soul unto vanity, nor sworn deceitfully.', '3~05355~ 4~03709~, 7~01249~ 8~03824~; 13~05375~ 15~05315~ 17~07723~, 19~07650~ 20~04820~.'),
  (14877, 19, 65, 8, 'They also that dwell in the uttermost parts are afraid at thy tokens: thou makest the outgoings of the morning and evening to rejoice.', '3~03427~ 7~07099~ 9~03372~ 12~0226~: 16~04161~ 19~01242~ 21~06153~ 23~07442~.'),
  (28593, 46, 10, 10, 'Neither murmur ye, as some of them also murmured, and were destroyed of the destroyer.', '0~3366~ 2~1111~, 3~2531~ 4~5100~ 6~846~ 7~2532~ 8~1111~, 9~2532~ 11~622~ 12~5259~ 14~3644~.'),
  (2754, 3, 1, 4, 'And he shall put his hand upon the head of the burnt offering; and it shall be accepted for him to make atonement for him.', '3~05564~ 5~03027~ 8~07218~ 12~05930~; 17~07521~ 22~03722~'),
  (24094, 40, 26, 30, 'And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the mount of Olives.', '0~2532~ 6~5214~, 9~1831~ 10~1519~ 12~3735~ 14~1636~.'),
  (26743, 43, 16, 2, 'They shall put you out of the synagogues: yea, the time cometh, that whosoever killeth you will think that he doeth God service.', '2~4160~ 3~5209~ 7~656~: 8~235~, 10~5610~ 11~2064~, 12~2443~ 13~3956~ 14~615~ 15~5209~ 17~1380~ 20~4374~ 21~2316~ 22~2999~.'),
  (15801, 19, 110, 6, 'He shall judge among the heathen, he shall fill the places with the dead bodies; he shall wound the heads over many countries.', '2~01777~ 5~01471~, 8~04390~ [9 10] 14~01472~; 17~04272~ 19~07218~ 21~07227~ 22~0776~.'),
  (3818, 4, 5, 21, 'Then the priest shall charge the woman with an oath of cursing, and the priest shall say unto the woman, The LORD make thee a curse and an oath among thy people, when the LORD doth make thy thigh to rot, and thy belly to swell;', '2~03548~ 4~07650~ 6~0802~ 9~07621~ 11~0423~, 14~03548~ 16~0559~ 19~0802~, 21~03068~ 22~05414~ 25~0423~ 28~07621~ 29~08432~ 31~05971~, 34~03068~ 36~05414~ 38~03409~ 40~05307~, 43~0990~ 45~06639~;'),
  (29894, 55, 4, 8, 'Henceforth there is laid up for me a crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous judge, shall give me at that day: and not to me only, but unto all them also that love his appearing.', '0~3063~ 4~606~ 6~3427~ 8~4735~ 10~1343~, 11~3739~ 13~2962~, 15~1342~ 16~2923~, 18~591~ 19~3427~ 20~1722~ 21~1565~ 22~2250~: 23~1161~ 24~3756~ 26~1698~ 27~3440~, 28~235~ 31~3956~ 32~2532~ 34~25~ 35~846~ 36~2015~.'),
  (16071, 19, 119, 164, 'Seven times a day do I praise thee because of thy righteous judgments.', '&para; 1~07651~ 3~03117~ 6~01984~ 11~06664~ 12~04941~.'),
  (11783, 14, 28, 10, 'And now ye purpose to keep under the children of Judah and Jerusalem for bondmen and bondwomen unto you: but are there not with you, even with you, sins against the LORD your God?', '3~0559~ 6~03533~ 8~01121~ 10~03063~ 12~03389~ 14~05650~ 16~08198~ [19 21] 25~07535~ 28~0819~ 31~03068~ 33~0430~?'),
  (13847, 18, 39, 4, 'Their young ones are in good liking, they grow up with corn; they go forth, and return not unto them.', '2~01121~ 6~02492~, 9~07235~ 11~01250~; 14~03318~, 16~07725~'),
  (22684, 33, 7, 11, 'In the day that thy walls are to be built, in that day shall the decree be far removed.', '[0] 2~03117~ 5~01447~ 9~01129~, [10] 12~03117~ 15~02706~ 18~07368~.'),
  (5814, 5, 32, 50, 'And die in the mount whither thou goest up, and be gathered unto thy people; as Aaron thy brother died in mount Hor, and was gathered unto his people:', '1~04191~ 4~02022~ 8~05927~, 11~0622~ 14~05971~; 16~0175~ 18~0251~ 19~04191~ 21~02022~ 22~02023~, 25~0622~ 28~05971~:'),
  (30170, 58, 10, 21, 'And having an high priest over the house of God;', '0~2532~ [1] 3~3173~ 4~2409~ 5~1909~ 7~3624~ 9~2316~;'),
  (15022, 19, 72, 13, 'He shall spare the poor and needy, and shall save the souls of the needy.', '2~02347~ 4~01800~ 6~034~, 9~03467~ 11~05315~ 14~034~.'),
  (19984, 24, 41, 18, 'Because of the Chaldeans: for they were afraid of them, because Ishmael the son of Nethaniah had slain Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, whom the king of Babylon made governor in the land.', '0~06440~ 3~03778~: 7~03372~ 11~03458~ 13~01121~ 15~05418~ 17~05221~ 18~01436~ 20~01121~ 22~0296~, 25~04428~ 27~0894~ 29~06485~ 32~0776~.'),
  (5731, 5, 30, 17, 'But if thine heart turn away, so that thou wilt not hear, but shalt be drawn away, and worship other gods, and serve them;', '3~03824~ 5~06437~, 11~08085~, 16~05080~, 18~07812~ 19~0312~ 20~0430~, 22~05647~'),
  (11120, 13, 27, 3, 'Of the children of Perez was the chief of all the captains of the host for the first month.', '2~01121~ 4~06557~ [5] 7~07218~ 11~08269~ 14~06635~ 17~07223~ 18~02320~.'),
  (4680, 4, 31, 10, 'And they burnt all their cities wherein they dwelt, and all their goodly castles, with fire.', '2~08313~ 5~05892~ 8~04186~, 13~02918~, 15~0784~.'),
  (11055, 13, 25, 1, 'Moreover David and the captains of the host separated to the service of the sons of Asaph, and of Heman, and of Jeduthun, who should prophesy with harps, with psalteries, and with cymbals: and the number of the workmen according to their service was:', '&para; 1~01732~ 4~08269~ 7~06635~ 8~0914~ 11~05656~ 14~01121~ 16~0623~, 19~01968~, 22~03038~, 25~05012~ 27~03658~, 29~05035~, 32~04700~: 35~04557~ 38~04399~ 39~0582~ 42~05656~'),
  (24560, 41, 9, 11, 'And they asked him, saying, Why say the scribes that Elias must first come?', '0~2532~ 2~1905~ 3~846~, 4~3004~, 5~3754~ 6~3004~ 8~1122~ 9~3754~ 10~2243~ 11~1163~ 12~4412~ 13~2064~?'),
  (22272, 28, 12, 11, 'Is there iniquity in Gilead? surely they are vanity: they sacrifice bullocks in Gilgal; yea, their altars are as heaps in the furrows of the fields.', '[0 1] 2~0205~ [3] 4~01568~? 8~07723~: 10~02076~ 11~07794~ 13~01537~; 16~04196~ [17] 19~01530~ 22~08525~ 25~07704~.'),
  (27889, 44, 27, 18, 'And we being exceedingly tossed with a tempest, the next day they lightened the ship;', '0~1161~ 1~2257~ 3~4971~ 7~5492~, 9~1836~ [10] 14~4160~ 15~1546~;*'),
  (7266, 9, 2, 19, 'Moreover his mother made him a little coat, and brought it to him from year to year, when she came up with her husband to offer the yearly sacrifice.', '2~0517~ 3~06213~ 6~06996~ 7~04598~, 9~05927~ [10] 14~03117~ 16~03117~, 20~05927~ 23~0376~ 25~02076~ 27~03117~ 28~02077~.'),
  (9639, 12, 4, 28, 'Then she said, Did I desire a son of my lord? did I not say, Do not deceive me?', '2~0559~, 5~07592~ 7~01121~ 10~0113~? 14~0559~, 17~07952~'),
  (19590, 24, 26, 9, 'Why hast thou prophesied in the name of the LORD, saying, This house shall be like Shiloh, and this city shall be desolate without an inhabitant? And all the people were gathered against Jeremiah in the house of the LORD.', '3~05012~ 6~08034~ 9~03068~, 10~0559~, 12~01004~ 16~07887~, 19~05892~ 22~02717~ 25~03427~? 29~05971~ 31~06950~ 33~03414~ 36~01004~ 39~03068~.'),
  (3862, 4, 7, 7, 'Two wagons and four oxen he gave unto the sons of Gershon, according to their service:', '0~08147~ 1~05699~ 3~0702~ 4~01241~ 6~05414~ 9~01121~ 11~01648~, 12~06310~ 15~05656~:'),
  (5316, 5, 14, 20, 'But of all clean fowls ye may eat.', '[0 1] 3~02889~ 4~05775~ 7~0398~.'),
  (19227, 24, 10, 17, 'Gather up thy wares out of the land, O inhabitant of the fortress.', '&para; 1~0622~ 3~03666~ 7~0776~, 9~03427~ 12~04692~.'),
  (24535, 41, 8, 24, 'And he looked up, and said, I see men as trees, walking.', '0~2532~ 3~308~, 5~3004~ 6~3754~,* 8~991~ 9~444~ 10~3708~ 11~5613~* 12~1186~, 13~4043~.'),
  (355, 1, 14, 15, 'And he divided himself against them, he and his servants, by night, and smote them, and pursued them unto Hobah, which is on the left hand of Damascus.', '2~02505~ 9~05650~, 11~03915~, 13~05221~ 16~07291~ 19~02327~, [21] 25~08040~ 27~01834~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (6476, 6, 23, 9, 'For the LORD hath driven out from before you great nations and strong: but as for you, no man hath been able to stand before you unto this day.', '2~03068~ 5~03423~ 7~06440~ 9~01419~ 10~01471~ 12~06099~: [14 15] 18~0376~ 23~05975~ 24~06440~ 28~03117~.'),
  (21415, 26, 37, 9, 'Then said he unto me, Prophesy unto the wind, prophesy, son of man, and say to the wind, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Come from the four winds, O breath, and breathe upon these slain, that they may live.', '1~0559~ 5~05012~ 8~07307~, 9~05012~, 10~01121~ 12~0120~, 14~0559~ 17~07307~, 19~0559~ 21~0136~ 22~03069~; 23~0935~ 26~0702~ 27~07307~, 29~07307~, 31~05301~ 34~02026~, 38~02421~.'),
  (23141, 39, 3, 11, 'And I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes, and he shall not destroy the fruits of your ground; neither shall your vine cast her fruit before the time in the field, saith the LORD of hosts.', '3~01605~ 5~0398~ 13~07843~ 15~06529~ 18~0127~; 22~01612~ 25~07921~ 31~07704~, 32~0559~ 34~03068~ 36~06635~.'),
  (22409, 30, 3, 5, 'Can a bird fall in a snare upon the earth, where no gin is for him? shall one take up a snare from the earth, and have taken nothing at all?', '2~06833~ 3~05307~ 6~06341~ 9~0776~, 12~04170~ [13] [17] 19~05927~ 21~06341~ 24~0127~, 27~03920~ 30~03920~?'),
  (27257, 44, 9, 25, 'Then the disciples took him by night, and let him down by the wall in a basket.', '0~1161~ 2~3101~ 3~2983~ 4~846~ 6~3571~, [9] 10~2524~ 11~5465~* 12~1223~ 14~5038~ 15~1722~ 17~4711~.'),
  (1344, 1, 44, 15, 'And Joseph said unto them, What deed is this that ye have done? wot ye not that such a man as I can certainly divine?', '1~03130~ 2~0559~ 6~04639~ [7] 12~06213~? 14~03045~ 19~0376~ 23~05172~ 24~05172~?'),
  (28232, 45, 11, 7, 'What then? Israel hath not obtained that which he seeketh for; but the election hath obtained it, and the rest were blinded', '0~5101~ 1~3767~? 2~2474~ 3~2013~ 4~3756~ 5~2013~ 6~5127~ 7~3739~ 10~1934~; 11~1161~ 13~1589~ 16~2013~, 17~1161~ 19~3062~ 21~4456~'),
  (13109, 18, 10, 14, 'If I sin, then thou markest me, and thou wilt not acquit me from mine iniquity.', '&para; 2~02398~, 5~08104~ 11~05352~ 15~05771~.'),
  (3628, 4, 1, 19, 'As the LORD commanded Moses, so he numbered them in the wilderness of Sinai.', '2~03068~ 3~06680~ 4~04872~, 7~06485~ 11~04057~ 13~05514~.'),
  (21730, 26, 48, 19, 'And they that serve the city shall serve it out of all the tribes of Israel.', '3~05647~ 5~05892~ 7~05647~ 13~07626~ 15~03478~.'),
  (30808, 66, 5, 13, 'And every creature which is in heaven, and on the earth, and under the earth, and such as are in the sea, and all that are in them, heard I saying, Blessing, and honour, and glory, and power, be unto him that sitteth upon the throne, and unto the Lamb for ever and ever.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 2~2938~ 3~3739~ 4~2076~ 5~1722~ 6~3772~, 7~2532~ 8~1722~ 10~1093~, 11~2532~ 12~5270~ 14~1093~, 15~2532~ 17~3739~ 18~2076~ 19~1909~ 21~2281~, 22~2532~ 23~3956~ 26~1722~ 27~846~, 29~191~ 30~3004~, 31~2129~, 32~2532~ 33~5092~, 34~2532~ 35~1391~, 36~2532~ 37~2904~, [38] 42~2521~ 43~1909~ 45~2362~, 46~2532~ 49~721~ 50~1519~ 51~165~ 53~165~.'),
  (11210, 14, 1, 8, 'And Solomon said unto God, Thou hast shewed great mercy unto David my father, and hast made me to reign in his stead.', '1~08010~ 2~0559~ 4~0430~, 7~06213~ 8~01419~ 9~02617~ 11~01732~ 13~01~, 19~04427~'),
  (24650, 41, 10, 51, 'And Jesus answered and said unto him, What wilt thou that I should do unto thee? The blind man said unto him, Lord, that I might receive my sight.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 4~3004~ 6~846~, 7~5101~ 8~2309~ 13~4160~ 15~4671~ 16~1161?~* 19~5185~ 20~2036~ 22~846~, 23~4462~, 24~2443~ 29~308~.'),
  (3630, 4, 1, 21, 'Those that were numbered of them, even of the tribe of Reuben, were forty and six thousand and five hundred.', '3~06485~ [6] 9~04294~ 11~07205~, [12] 13~0705~ 15~08337~ 16~0505~ 18~02568~ 19~03967~.'),
  (28408, 46, 1, 29, 'That no flesh should glory in his presence.', '0~3704~ 1~3956~ 2~3361~* 3~4561~ 5~2744~ 8~846~ 9~1799~.*'),
  (1415, 1, 46, 24, 'And the sons of Naphtali; Jahzeel, and Guni, and Jezer, and Shillem.', '2~01121~ 4~05321~; 5~03183~, 7~01476~, 9~03337~, 11~08006~.'),
  (20446, 25, 4, 17, 'As for us, our eyes as yet failed for our vain help: in our watching we have watched for a nation that could not save us.', '4~05869~ 7~03615~ 10~01892~ 11~05833~: 14~06836~ 17~06822~ 20~01471~ [21] 24~03467~ [25]'),
  (22168, 28, 5, 7, 'They have dealt treacherously against the LORD: for they have begotten strange children: now shall a month devour them with their portions.', '3~0898~ 6~03068~: 10~03205~ 11~02114~ 12~01121~: 16~02320~ 17~0398~ 21~02506~.'),
  (10702, 13, 11, 21, 'Of the three, he was more honourable than the two; for he was their captain: howbeit he attained not to the first three.', '2~07969~, 6~03513~ 9~08147~; 14~08269~: 17~0935~ [21] 22~07969~.'),
  (20533, 26, 3, 22, 'And the hand of the LORD was there upon me; and he said unto me, Arise, go forth into the plain, and I will there talk with thee.', '&para; 2~03027~ 5~03068~ 12~0559~ 15~06965~, 17~03318~ 20~01237~, 25~01696~'),
  (29597, 52, 2, 11, 'As ye know how we exhorted and comforted and charged every one of you, as a father doth his children,', '0~2509~ 2~1492~ 3~5613~ 5~3870~ 6~2532~ 7~3888~ 9~3140~ 10~1538~ 11~1520~ 13~5216~ 14~5209~,* 15~5613~ 17~3962~ [18] 19~1438~ 20~5043~,'),
  (1677, 2, 6, 17, 'The sons of Gershon; Libni, and Shimi, according to their families.', '1~01121~ 3~01648~; 4~03845~, 6~08096~, 10~04940~.'),
  (19016, 24, 3, 5, 'Will he reserve his anger for ever? will he keep it to the end? Behold, thou hast spoken and done evil things as thou couldest.', '2~05201~ [3 4] 6~05769~? 9~08104~ [10] 13~05331~? 17~01696~ 19~06213~ 21~07451~ 24~03201~.'),
  (14333, 19, 30, 5, 'For his anger endureth but a moment; in his favour is life: weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning.', '2~0639~ [3 4] 6~07281~; 9~07522~ [10] 11~02416~: 12~01065~ 14~03885~ 17~06153~, 19~07440~ [20] 23~01242~.'),
  (20888, 26, 18, 30, 'Therefore I will judge you, O house of Israel, every one according to his ways, saith the Lord GOD. Repent, and turn yourselves from all your transgressions; so iniquity shall not be your ruin.', '&para; 3~08199~ 6~01004~ 8~03478~, 10~0376~ 14~01870~, 15~05002~ 17~0136~ 18~03069~. 19~07725~, 21~07725~ [22] 26~06588~; 28~05771~ 33~04383~.'),
  (17220, 20, 28, 15, 'As a roaring lion, and a ranging bear; so is a wicked ruler over the poor people.', '&para; [0] 2~05098~ 3~0738~, 6~08264~ 7~01677~; [8 9] 11~07563~ 12~04910~ 15~01800~ 16~05971~.'),
  (43, 1, 2, 12, 'And the gold of that land is good: there is bdellium and the onyx stone.', '2~02091~ 4~01931~ 5~0776~ [6] 7~02896~: [9] 10~0916~ 13~07718~ 14~068~.'),
  (4421, 4, 22, 41, 'And it came to pass on the morrow, that Balak took Balaam, and brought him up into the high places of Baal, that thence he might see the utmost part of the people.', '7~01242~, 9~01111~ 10~03947~ 11~01109~, 15~05927~ 19~01116~ 21~01120~, 26~07200~ 28~07097~ [29] 32~05971~.'),
  (2279, 2, 27, 2, 'And thou shalt make the horns of it upon the four corners thereof: his horns shall be of the same: and thou shalt overlay it with brass.', '3~06213~ 5~07161~ 10~0702~ 11~06438~ 14~07161~ 23~06823~ 26~05178~.'),
  (25850, 42, 21, 10, 'Then said he unto them, Nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom:', '0~5119~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~1484~ 7~1453~ 8~1909~ 9~1484~, 10~2532~ 11~932~ 12~1909~ 13~932~:'),
  (8331, 10, 13, 7, 'Then David sent home to Tamar, saying, Go now to thy brother Amnon''s house, and dress him meat.', '1~01732~ 2~07971~ 3~01004~ 5~08559~, 6~0559~, 7~03212~ 11~0251~ 12~0550~ 13~01004~, 15~06213~ 17~01279~.'),
  (16786, 20, 14, 5, 'A faithful witness will not lie: but a false witness will utter lies.', '&para; 1~0529~ 2~05707~ 5~03577~: 8~08267~ 9~05707~ 11~06315~ 12~03576~.'),
  (2540, 2, 35, 4, 'And Moses spake unto all the congregation of the children of Israel, saying, This is the thing which the LORD commanded, saying,', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 6~05712~ 9~01121~ 11~03478~, 12~0559~, [14] 16~01697~ 19~03068~ 20~06680~, 21~0559~,'),
  (18083, 23, 22, 22, 'And the key of the house of David will I lay upon his shoulder; so he shall open, and none shall shut; and he shall shut, and none shall open.', '2~04668~ 5~01004~ 7~01732~ 10~05414~ 13~07926~; 17~06605~, 21~05462~; 25~05462~, 29~06605~.'),
  (5983, 6, 7, 1, 'But the children of Israel committed a trespass in the accursed thing: for Achan, the son of Carmi, the son of Zabdi, the son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, took of the accursed thing: and the anger of the LORD was kindled against the children of Israel.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~04603~ 7~04604~ 11~02764~: 13~05912~, 15~01121~ 17~03756~, 19~01121~ 21~02067~, 23~01121~ 25~02226~, 28~04294~ 30~03063~, 31~03947~ 35~02764~: 38~0639~ 41~03068~ 43~02734~ 46~01121~ 48~03478~.'),
  (12033, 15, 1, 8, 'Even those did Cyrus king of Persia bring forth by the hand of Mithredath the treasurer, and numbered them unto Sheshbazzar, the prince of Judah.', '3~03566~ 4~04428~ 6~06539~ 8~03318~ 11~03027~ 13~04990~ 15~01489~, 17~05608~ 20~08339~, 22~05387~ 24~03063~.'),
  (10962, 13, 21, 20, 'And Ornan turned back, and saw the angel; and his four sons with him hid themselves. Now Ornan was threshing wheat.', '1~0771~ 3~07725~, 5~07200~ 7~04397~; 10~0702~ 11~01121~ 14~02244~ 17~0771~ 19~01758~ 20~02406~.'),
  (26249, 43, 5, 24, 'Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that heareth my word, and believeth on him that sent me, hath everlasting life, and shall not come into condemnation; but is passed from death unto life.', '0~281~, 1~281~, 3~3004~ 5~5213~ 6~3754~,* 9~191~ 10~3450~ 11~3056~, 12~2532~ 13~4100~ 17~3992~ 18~3165~, 19~2192~ 20~166~ 21~2222~, 22~2532~ 23~2064~ 24~3756~ 25~2064~ 26~1519~ 27~2920~; 28~235~ 30~3327~ 31~1537~ 32~2288~ 33~1519~ 34~2222~.'),
  (30220, 58, 11, 32, 'And what shall I more say? for the time would fail me to tell of Gedeon, and of Barak, and of Samson, and of Jephthae; of David also, and Samuel, and of the prophets:', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~5101~ 3~3004~ 4~2089~ 5~3004~? 6~1063~ 8~5550~ 10~1952~ 11~3165~ 13~1334~ 14~4012~ 15~1066~, 16~5037~ [17] 18~913~, 19~2532~ [20] 21~4546~, 22~2532~ [23] 24~2422~; [25] 26~1138~ 27~2532~, 28~5037~ 29~4545~, 30~2532~ [31] 33~4396~:'),
  (12354, 16, 3, 18, 'After him repaired their brethren, Bavai the son of Henadad, the ruler of the half part of Keilah.', '0~0310~ 2~02388~ 4~0251~, 5~0942~ 7~01121~ 9~02582~, 11~08269~ 14~02677~ 15~06418~ 17~07084~.'),
  (19715, 24, 31, 15, 'Thus saith the LORD; A voice was heard in Ramah, lamentation, and bitter weeping; Rahel weeping for her children refused to be comforted for her children, because they were not.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~; 5~06963~ 7~08085~ 9~07414~, 10~05092~, [11] 12~08563~ 13~01065~; 14~07354~ 15~01058~ 18~01121~ 19~03985~ 22~05162~ 25~01121~, [28]'),
  (8752, 11, 1, 27, 'Is this thing done by my lord the king, and thou hast not shewed it unto thy servant, who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?', '2~01697~ 3~01961~ 6~0113~ 8~04428~, 13~03045~ [14] 17~05650~, 20~03427~ 23~03678~ 26~0113~ 28~04428~ 29~0310~'),
  (11572, 14, 18, 21, 'And he said, I will go out, and be a lying spirit in the mouth of all his prophets. And the LORD said, Thou shalt entice him, and thou shalt also prevail: go out, and do even so.', '2~0559~, 6~03318~, 10~08267~ 11~07307~ 14~06310~ 18~05030~. [20 21] 22~0559~, 25~06601~ [26] 31~03201~: 33~03318~, 35~06213~ [36]'),
  (30737, 66, 2, 4, 'Nevertheless I have somewhat against thee, because thou hast left thy first love.', '0~235~ 2~2192~ [3] 4~2596~ 5~4675~, 6~3754~ 9~863~ 10~4675~ 11~4413~ 12~26~.'),
  (12893, 18, 1, 15, 'And the Sabeans fell upon them, and took them away; yea, they have slain the servants with the edge of the sword; and I only am escaped alone to tell thee.', '2~07614~ 3~05307~ [4 5] 9~03947~; 13~05221~ 15~05288~ 18~06310~ 21~02719~; 26~04422~ 29~05046~'),
  (16918, 20, 18, 8, 'The words of a talebearer are as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.', '&para; 1~01697~ 4~05372~ [5] 7~03859~, 11~03381~ 15~02315~ 18~0990~.'),
  (15883, 19, 118, 5, 'I called upon the LORD in distress: the LORD answered me, and set me in a large place.', '1~07121~ 4~03050~ 6~04712~: 8~03050~ 9~06030~ [11 13] 17~04800~.'),
  (30561, 62, 1, 5, 'This then is the message which we have heard of him, and declare unto you, that God is light, and in him is no darkness at all.', '&para; 0~3778~ 1~2532~ 2~2076~ 4~1860~ 5~3739~ 8~191~ 9~575~ 10~846~, 11~2532~ 12~312~ 14~5213~, 15~3754~ 16~2316~ 17~2076~ 18~5457~, 19~2532~ 20~1722~ 21~846~ 22~2076~ 23~3756~ 24~4653~ 26~3762~.'),
  (26525, 43, 10, 29, 'My Father, which gave them me, is greater than all; and no man is able to pluck them out of my Father''s hand.', '0~3450~ 1~3962~, 2~3739~ 3~1325~ [4] 5~3427~, 6~2076~ 8~3187~ 9~3956~; 10~2532~ 11~3762~ [12] 14~1410~ 16~726~ [17] 19~1537~ 20~3450~ 21~3962~ 22~5495~.'),
  (27991, 45, 2, 13, '(For not the hearers of the law are just before God, but the doers of the law shall be justified.', '0~(1063~ 1~3756~ 3~202~ 6~3551~ [7] 8~1342~ 9~3844~ 10~2316~, 11~235~ 13~4163~ 16~3551~ 19~1344~.'),
  (6964, 7, 16, 8, 'Then the lords of the Philistines brought up to her seven green withs which had not been dried, and she bound him with them.', '2~05633~ 5~06430~ 7~05927~ 10~07651~ 11~03892~ 12~03499~ 17~02717~, 20~0631~'),
  (18638, 23, 48, 15, 'I, even I, have spoken; yea, I have called him: I have brought him, and he shall make his way prosperous.', '[1] 4~01696~; 8~07121~ 12~0935~ 19~01870~ 20~06743~.'),
  (13540, 18, 28, 27, 'Then did he see it, and declare it; he prepared it, yea, and searched it out.', '3~07200~ 6~05608~ 9~03559~ 15~02713~.'),
  (27859, 44, 26, 20, 'But shewed first unto them of Damascus, and at Jerusalem, and throughout all the coasts of Judaea, and then to the Gentiles, that they should repent and turn to God, and do works meet for repentance.', '0~235~ 1~518~ 2~4412~ 5~1722~ 6~1154~, 7~2532~ 9~2414~, 10~5037~ 11~1519~ 12~3956~ 14~5561~ 16~2449~, 17~2532~ [18] 21~1484~, 25~3340~ 26~2532~ 27~1994~ 28~1909~ 29~2316~, 31~4238~ 32~2041~ 33~514~ 35~3341~.'),
  (2117, 2, 21, 35, 'And if one man''s ox hurt another''s, that he die; then they shall sell the live ox, and divide the money of it; and the dead ox also they shall divide.', '3~0376~ 4~07794~ 5~05062~ 6~07453~, 9~04191~; 13~04376~ 15~02416~ 16~07794~, 18~02673~ 20~03701~ 25~04191~ [26] 30~02673~.'),
  (5645, 5, 28, 28, 'The LORD shall smite thee with madness, and blindness, and astonishment of heart:', '1~03068~ 3~05221~ 6~07697~, 8~05788~, 10~08541~ 12~03824~:'),
  (22910, 38, 2, 2, 'Then said I, Whither goest thou? And he said unto me, To measure Jerusalem, to see what is the breadth thereof, and what is the length thereof.', '1~0559~ 4~01980~ 8~0559~ 12~04058~ 13~03389~, 15~07200~ 16~04100~ [17] 19~07341~ [23] 25~0753~'),
  (16953, 20, 19, 19, 'A man of great wrath shall suffer punishment: for if thou deliver him, yet thou must do it again.', '&para; 1~01419~ 3~01632~ 4~02534~ 6~05375~ 7~06066~: 11~05337~ [12] 18~03254~.'),
  (24157, 40, 27, 18, 'For he knew that for envy they had delivered him.', '0~1063~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 4~1223~ 5~5355~ 8~3860~ 9~846~.'),
  (7672, 9, 17, 47, 'And all this assembly shall know that the LORD saveth not with sword and spear: for the battle is the Lord''s, and he will give you into our hands.', '3~06951~ 5~03045~ 8~03068~ 9~03467~ 12~02719~ 14~02595~: 17~04421~ [18] 20~03068~, 24~05414~ 28~03027~.'),
  (11071, 13, 25, 17, 'The tenth to Shimei, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~06224~ 3~08096~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (20463, 25, 5, 12, 'Princes are hanged up by their hand: the faces of elders were not honoured.', '0~08269~ 3~08518~ 6~03027~: 8~06440~ 10~02205~ 13~01921~.'),
  (24075, 40, 26, 11, 'For ye have the poor always with you; but me ye have not always.', '0~1063~ 2~2192~ 4~4434~ 5~3842~ 6~3326~ 7~1438~; 8~1161~ 9~1691~ 11~2192~ 12~3756~ 13~3842~.'),
  (29147, 48, 3, 29, 'And if ye be Christ''s, then are ye Abraham''s seed, and heirs according to the promise.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 2~5210~ [3] 4~5547~, 5~686~ 7~2075~ 8~11~ 9~4690~, 10~2532~ 11~2818~ 12~2596~ 15~1860~.'),
  (18399, 23, 37, 38, 'And it came to pass, as he was worshipping in the house of Nisroch his god, that Adrammelech and Sharezer his sons smote him with the sword; and they escaped into the land of Armenia: and Esarhaddon his son reigned in his stead.', '8~07812~ 11~01004~ 13~05268~ 15~0430~, 17~0152~ 19~08272~ 21~01121~ 22~05221~ 26~02719~; 29~04422~ 32~0776~ 34~0780~: 36~0634~ 38~01121~ 39~04427~'),
  (19065, 24, 4, 29, 'The whole city shall flee for the noise of the horsemen and bowmen; they shall go into thickets, and climb up upon the rocks: every city shall be forsaken, and not a man dwell therein.', '2~05892~ 4~01272~ 7~06963~ 10~06571~ 12~07411~ 13~07198~;* 16~0935~ 18~05645~, 21~05927~ 24~03710~: 26~05892~ [27 28] 29~05800~, 33~0376~ 34~03427~ 35~02004~.'),
  (2732, 2, 40, 20, 'And he took and put the testimony into the ark, and set the staves on the ark, and put the mercy seat above upon the ark:', '2~03947~ 4~05414~ 6~05715~ 9~0727~, 11~07760~ 13~0905~ 16~0727~, 18~05414~ 21~03727~ 22~04605~ 25~0727~:'),
  (30288, 59, 1, 6, 'But let him ask in faith, nothing wavering. For he that wavereth is like a wave of the sea driven with the wind and tossed.', '0~1161~ 3~154~ 4~1722~ 5~4102~, 6~3367~ 7~1252~. 8~1063~ 11~1252~ 13~1503~ 15~2830~ 18~2281~ 22~416~ 23~2532~ 24~4494~.'),
  (15138, 19, 78, 16, 'He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.', '1~03318~ 2~05140~ 7~05553~, 10~04325~ 13~03381~ 15~05104~.'),
  (16928, 20, 18, 18, 'The lot causeth contentions to cease, and parteth between the mighty.', '&para; 1~01486~ 3~04079~ 5~07673~, 7~06504~ 10~06099~.'),
  (4351, 4, 21, 6, 'And the LORD sent fiery serpents among the people, and they bit the people; and much people of Israel died.', '2~03068~ 3~07971~ 4~08314~ 5~05175~ 8~05971~, 11~05391~ 13~05971~; 15~07227~ 16~05971~ 18~03478~ 19~04191~.'),
  (18738, 23, 54, 6, 'For the LORD hath called thee as a woman forsaken and grieved in spirit, and a wife of youth, when thou wast refused, saith thy God.', '&para; 2~03068~ 4~07121~ 8~0802~ 9~05800~ 11~06087~ 13~07307~, 16~0802~ 18~05271~, 22~03988~, 23~0559~ 25~0430~.'),
  (6536, 7, 1, 20, 'And they gave Hebron unto Caleb, as Moses said: and he expelled thence the three sons of Anak.', '2~05414~ 3~02275~ 5~03612~, 7~04872~ 8~01696~: 11~03423~ 14~07969~ 15~01121~ 17~06061~.'),
  (5373, 5, 17, 3, 'And hath gone and served other gods, and worshipped them, either the sun, or moon, or any of the host of heaven, which I have not commanded;', '2~03212~ 4~05647~ 5~0312~ 6~0430~, 8~07812~ 12~08121~, 14~03394~, 19~06635~ 21~08064~, 26~06680~;'),
  (9950, 12, 15, 17, 'In the nine and thirtieth year of Azariah king of Judah began Menahem the son of Gadi to reign over Israel, and reigned ten years in Samaria.', '2~08141~ 3~08672~ 4~07970~ 5~08141~ 7~05838~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~ 12~04505~ 14~01121~ 16~01424~ 18~04427~ 20~03478~, [21 22] 23~06235~ 24~08141~ 26~08111~.'),
  (8737, 11, 1, 12, 'Now therefore come, let me, I pray thee, give thee counsel, that thou mayest save thine own life, and the life of thy son Solomon.', '2~03212~, 10~03289~ 11~06098~,* 15~04422~ 18~05315~, 21~05315~ 24~01121~ 25~08010~.'),
  (11152, 13, 28, 1, 'And David assembled all the princes of Israel, the princes of the tribes, and the captains of the companies that ministered to the king by course, and the captains over the thousands, and captains over the hundreds, and the stewards over all the substance and possession of the king, and of his sons, with the officers, and with the mighty men, and with all the valiant men, unto Jerusalem.', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~06950~ 5~08269~ 7~03478~, 9~08269~ 12~07626~, 15~08269~ 18~04256~ 20~08334~ 23~04428~ 25~04256~, 28~08269~ 31~0505~, 33~08269~ 36~03967~, 39~08269~ 43~07399~ 45~04735~ 48~04428~, 52~01121~, 55~05631~, 60~01368~, 66~02428~, 68~03389~.'),
  (27341, 44, 11, 18, 'When they heard these things, they held their peace, and glorified God, saying, Then hath God also to the Gentiles granted repentance unto life.', '0~1161~ 2~191~ 4~5023~, 8~2270~, 9~2532~ 10~1392~ 11~2316~, 12~3004~, 13~686~ 14~1325~ 15~2316~ 16~2534~ 19~1484~ 20~1325~ 21~3341~ 22~1519~ 23~2222~.'),
  (15567, 19, 103, 9, 'He will not always chide: neither will he keep his anger for ever.', '3~05331~ 4~07378~: 8~05201~ [9 10] 12~05769~.'),
  (3319, 3, 19, 33, 'And if a stranger sojourn with thee in your land, ye shall not vex him.', '3~01616~ 4~01481~ 9~0776~, 13~03238~'),
  (11489, 14, 14, 5, 'Also he took away out of all the cities of Judah the high places and the images: and the kingdom was quiet before him.', '3~05493~ 8~05892~ 10~03063~ 13~01116~ 16~02553~: 19~04467~ 21~08252~ 22~06440~'),
  (23002, 38, 8, 17, 'And let none of you imagine evil in your hearts against his neighbour; and love no false oath: for all these are things that I hate, saith the LORD.', '2~0376~ 5~02803~ 6~07451~ 9~03824~ 12~07453~; 14~0157~ 16~08267~ 17~07621~: [21 22] 25~08130~, 26~05002~ 28~03068~.'),
  (4777, 4, 33, 11, 'And they removed from the Red sea, and encamped in the wilderness of Sin.', '2~05265~ 5~05488~ 6~03220~, 8~02583~ 11~04057~ 13~05512~.'),
  (17726, 23, 3, 10, 'Say ye to the righteous, that it shall be well with him: for they shall eat the fruit of their doings.', '0~0559~ 4~06662~, [6 8] 9~02896~ [10 11] 15~0398~ 17~06529~ 20~04611~.'),
  (11320, 14, 6, 30, 'Then hear thou from heaven thy dwelling place, and forgive, and render unto every man according unto all his ways, whose heart thou knowest; (for thou only knowest the hearts of the children of men:)', '1~08085~ 4~08064~ 6~03427~ 7~04349~, 9~05545~, 11~05414~ 14~0376~ 19~01870~, 21~03824~ 23~03045~; 27~03045~ 29~03824~ 32~01121~ 34~0120~:)'),
  (15063, 19, 74, 6, 'But now they break down the carved work thereof at once with axes and hammers.', '4~01986~ 7~06603~ 10~03162~ 12~03781~ 14~03597~.'),
  (5238, 5, 11, 24, 'Every place whereon the soles of your feet shall tread shall be yours: from the wilderness and Lebanon, from the river, the river Euphrates, even unto the uttermost sea shall your coast be.', '1~04725~ 4~03709~ 7~07272~ 9~01869~ 15~04057~ 17~03844~, 20~05104~, 22~05104~ 23~06578~, 27~0314~ 28~03220~ 31~01366~'),
  (23802, 40, 19, 30, 'But many that are first shall be last; and the last shall be first.', '0~1161~ 1~4183~ [2 3] 4~4413~ 6~2071~ 7~2078~; 8~2532~ 10~2078~ [11 12] 13~4413~.'),
  (2275, 2, 26, 35, 'And thou shalt set the table without the veil, and the candlestick over against the table on the side of the tabernacle toward the south: and thou shalt put the table on the north side.', '3~07760~ 5~07979~ 6~02351~ 8~06532~, 11~04501~ 13~05227~ 15~07979~ 18~06763~ 21~04908~ 24~08486~: 28~05414~ 30~07979~ 33~06828~ 34~06763~.'),
  (17577, 22, 2, 14, 'O my dove, that art in the clefts of the rock, in the secret places of the stairs, let me see thy countenance, let me hear thy voice; for sweet is thy voice, and thy countenance is comely.', '&para; 2~03123~, [3 4] 7~02288~ 10~05553~, 13~05643~ [14] 17~04095~, 20~07200~ 22~04758~, 25~08085~ 27~06963~; 29~06156~ [30] 32~06963~, 35~04758~ [36] 37~05000~.'),
  (15174, 19, 78, 52, 'But made his own people to go forth like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.', '4~05971~ 7~05265~ 9~06629~, 11~05090~ 15~04057~ 18~05739~.'),
  (15279, 19, 84, 11, 'For the LORD God is a sun and shield: the LORD will give grace and glory: no good thing will he withhold from them that walk uprightly.', '2~03068~ 3~0430~ [4] 6~08121~ 8~04043~: 10~03068~ 12~05414~ 13~02580~ 15~03519~: 17~02896~ [18] 21~04513~ 25~01980~ 26~08549~.'),
  (4047, 4, 11, 18, 'And say thou unto the people, Sanctify yourselves against to morrow, and ye shall eat flesh: for ye have wept in the ears of the LORD, saying, Who shall give us flesh to eat? for it was well with us in Egypt: therefore the LORD will give you flesh, and ye shall eat.', '1~0559~ 5~05971~, 6~06942~ 10~04279~, 14~0398~ 15~01320~: 19~01058~ 22~0241~ 25~03068~, 26~0559~, 31~01320~ 33~0398~? [35 36] 37~02895~ 41~04714~: 44~03068~ 46~05414~ 48~01320~, 52~0398~.'),
  (28299, 45, 14, 3, 'Let not him that eateth despise him that eateth not; and let not him which eateth not judge him that eateth: for God hath received him.', '0~1848~ 1~3361~ 4~2068~ 5~1848~ 8~2068~ 9~3361~; 10~2532~ 11~2068~ 12~3361~ 15~2068~ 16~3361~ 17~2919~ 20~2068~: 21~1063~ 22~2316~ 24~4355~ 25~846~.'),
  (1541, 2, 1, 4, 'Dan, and Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.', '0~01835~, 2~05321~, 3~01410~, 5~0836~.'),
  (959, 1, 32, 27, 'And he said unto him, What is thy name? And he said, Jacob.', '2~0559~ [6] 8~08034~? 11~0559~, 12~03290~.'),
  (17452, 21, 7, 14, 'In the day of prosperity be joyful, but in the day of adversity consider: God also hath set the one over against the other, to the end that man should find nothing after him.', '2~03117~ 4~02896~ 6~02896~, 10~03117~ 12~07451~ 13~07200~: 14~0430~ 17~06213~ 21~05980~ 26~01700~ 28~0120~ 30~04672~ 31~03972~ 32~0310~'),
  (20305, 24, 52, 20, 'The two pillars, one sea, and twelve brazen bulls that were under the bases, which king Solomon had made in the house of the LORD: the brass of all these vessels was without weight.', '1~08147~ 2~05982~, 3~0259~ 4~03220~, 6~06240~ 7~08147~* 8~05178~ 9~01241~ [11] 14~04350~, 16~04428~ 17~08010~ 19~06213~ 22~01004~ 25~03068~: 27~05178~ 31~03627~ 34~04948~.'),
  (21767, 27, 1, 21, 'And Daniel continued even unto the first year of king Cyrus.', '1~01840~ [3] 6~0259~ 7~08141~ 9~04428~ 10~03566~.'),
  (17765, 23, 5, 17, 'Then shall the lambs feed after their manner, and the waste places of the fat ones shall strangers eat.', '3~03532~ 4~07462~ 7~01699~, 11~02723~ 15~04220~ 17~01481~ 18~0398~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (7885, 9, 25, 17, 'Now therefore know and consider what thou wilt do; for evil is determined against our master, and against all his household: for he is such a son of Belial, that a man cannot speak to him.', '2~03045~ 4~07200~ 8~06213~; 10~07451~ 12~03615~ 15~0113~, 20~01004~: [23 24] 26~01121~ 28~01100~, [30 31] 33~01696~'),
  (1073, 1, 36, 28, 'The children of Dishan are these; Uz, and Aran.', '1~01121~ 3~01789~ [4] 6~05780~, 8~0765~.'),
  (2212, 2, 25, 12, 'And thou shalt cast four rings of gold for it, and put them in the four corners thereof; and two rings shall be in the one side of it, and two rings in the other side of it.', '3~03332~ 4~0702~ 5~02885~ 7~02091~ 11~05414~ [12] 15~0702~ 16~06471~ 19~08147~ 20~02885~ [21 22] 25~0259~ 26~06763~ 30~08147~ 31~02885~ 34~08145~'),
  (29941, 56, 3, 2, 'To speak evil of no man, to be no brawlers, but gentle, shewing all meekness unto all men.', '3~987~ 5~3367~, 7~1511~ 9~269~, [10] 11~1933~, 12~1731~ 13~3956~ 14~4236~ 15~4314~ 16~3956~ 17~444~.'),
  (19712, 24, 31, 12, 'Therefore they shall come and sing in the height of Zion, and shall flow together to the goodness of the LORD, for wheat, and for wine, and for oil, and for the young of the flock and of the herd: and their soul shall be as a watered garden; and they shall not sorrow any more at all.', '3~0935~ 5~07442~ 8~04791~ 10~06726~, 14~05102~ 17~02898~ 20~03068~, 22~01715~, 25~08492~, 28~03323~, 32~01121~ 35~06629~ 39~01241~: 42~05315~ 47~07302~ 48~01588~; 53~01669~ 55~03254~'),
  (30358, 59, 4, 5, 'Do ye think that the scripture saith in vain, The spirit that dwelleth in us lusteth to envy?', '0~2228~ 2~1380~ 3~3754~ 5~1124~ 6~3004~ 8~2761~, 10~4151~ 11~3739~ 12~2730~ 13~1722~ 14~2254~ 15~1971~ 16~4314~ 17~5355~?'),
  (27214, 44, 8, 22, 'Repent therefore of this thy wickedness, and pray God, if perhaps the thought of thine heart may be forgiven thee.', '0~3340~ 1~3767~ 2~575~ 3~5026~ 4~4675~ 5~2549~, 6~2532~ 7~1189~ 8~2316~, 9~1487~ 10~686~ 12~1963~ 14~4675~ 15~2588~ 18~863~ 19~4671~.'),
  (25190, 42, 6, 32, 'For if ye love them which love you, what thank have ye? for sinners also love those that love them.', '0~2532~ 1~1487~ 3~25~ 6~25~ 7~5209~, 8~4169~ 9~5485~ 10~2076~ 11~5213~? 12~1063~ 13~268~ 14~2532~ 15~25~ 18~25~ 19~846~.'),
  (8424, 10, 15, 28, 'See, I will tarry in the plain of the wilderness, until there come word from you to certify me.', '0~07200~, 3~04102~ 6~06160~ 7~05679~* 10~04057~, 13~0935~ 14~01697~ 18~05046~'),
  (14029, 19, 8, 8, 'The fowl of the air, and the fish of the sea, and whatsoever passeth through the paths of the seas.', '1~06833~ 4~08064~, 7~01709~ 10~03220~, [11 12] 14~05674~ 16~0734~ 19~03220~.'),
  (25308, 42, 8, 51, 'And when he came into the house, he suffered no man to go in, save Peter, and James, and John, and the father and the mother of the maiden.', '0~1161~ 3~1525~ 4~1519~ 6~3614~, 8~863~ 9~3756~ 10~3762~ 13~1525~, 14~1508~ 15~4074~, 16~2532~ 17~2385~, 18~2532~ 19~2491~, 20~2532~ 22~3962~ 23~2532~ 25~3384~ 28~3816~.'),
  (3816, 4, 5, 19, 'And the priest shall charge her by an oath, and say unto the woman, If no man have lain with thee, and if thou hast not gone aside to uncleanness with another instead of thy husband, be thou free from this bitter water that causeth the curse:', '2~03548~ 8~07650~, 10~0559~ 13~0802~, 16~0376~ 18~07901~ 27~07847~ 29~02932~ [30 31] 35~0376~, 38~05352~ 41~04751~ 42~04325~ 46~0779~:'),
  (22358, 29, 3, 6, 'The children also of Judah and the children of Jerusalem have ye sold unto the Grecians, that ye might remove them far from their border.', '1~01121~ 4~03063~ 7~01121~ 9~03389~ 12~04376~ 15~01121~ 16~03125~,* 22~07368~ 25~01366~.'),
  (24998, 42, 2, 13, 'And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God, and saying,', '0~2532~ 1~1810~ 3~1096~ 4~4862~ 6~32~ 8~4128~ 11~3770~ 12~4756~ 13~134~ 14~2316~, 15~2532~ 16~3004~,'),
  (23155, 40, 1, 1, 'The book of the generation of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.', '&para; 1~976~ 4~1078~ 6~2424~ 7~5547~, 9~5207~ 11~1138~, 13~5207~ 15~11~.'),
  (21542, 26, 41, 7, 'And there was an enlarging, and a winding about still upward to the side chambers: for the winding about of the house went still upward round about the house: therefore the breadth of the house was still upward, and so increased from the lowest chamber to the highest by the midst.', '[1 2] 4~07337~, 8~05437~ 10~04605~ 14~06763~: 18~04141~ 21~01004~ 24~04605~ 26~05439~ 28~01004~: 31~07341~ 34~01004~ [35 36] 37~04605~, 40~05927~ [41] 43~08481~ [44] 47~05945~ 50~08484~.'),
  (22, 1, 1, 22, 'And God blessed them, saying, Be fruitful, and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let fowl multiply in the earth.', '1~0430~ 2~01288~ 4~0559~, 6~06509~, 8~07235~, 10~04390~ 12~04325~ 15~03220~, 18~05775~ 19~07235~ 22~0776~.'),
  (29023, 47, 11, 18, 'Seeing that many glory after the flesh, I will glory also.', '1~1893~ 2~4183~ 3~2744~ 4~2596~ 6~4561~, 9~2744~ 10~2504~.'),
  (12535, 16, 9, 15, 'And gavest them bread from heaven for their hunger, and broughtest forth water for them out of the rock for their thirst, and promisedst them that they should go in to possess the land which thou hadst sworn to give them.', '1~05414~ 3~03899~ 5~08064~ 8~07458~, 11~03318~ 12~04325~ 18~05553~ 21~06772~, 23~0559~ 29~0935~ 31~03423~ 33~0776~ 37~05375~ 38~03027~* 40~05414~'),
  (10542, 13, 6, 80, 'And out of the tribe of Gad; Ramoth in Gilead with her suburbs, and Mahanaim with her suburbs,', '4~04294~ 6~01410~; 7~07216~ 9~01568~ 12~04054~, 14~04266~ 17~04054~,'),
  (12011, 14, 36, 9, 'Jehoiachin was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned three months and ten days in Jerusalem: and he did that which was evil in the sight of the LORD.', '0~03078~ [1] 2~08083~ 3~08141~ 4~01121~ 9~04427~, 12~04427~ 13~07969~ 14~02320~ 16~06235~ 17~03117~ 19~03389~: 22~06213~ [23 25] 26~07451~ 29~05869~ 32~03068~.'),
  (21351, 26, 34, 29, 'And I will raise up for them a plant of renown, and they shall be no more consumed with hunger in the land, neither bear the shame of the heathen any more.', '4~06965~ 8~04302~ 10~08034~, 17~0622~ 19~07458~ 22~0776~, 24~05375~ 26~03639~ 29~01471~'),
  (29552, 51, 3, 19, 'Husbands, love your wives, and be not bitter against them.', '0~435~, 1~25~ [2] 3~1135~, 4~2532~ 5~4087~ 6~3361~ 7~4087~ 8~4314~ 9~846~.'),
  (28395, 46, 1, 16, 'And I baptized also the household of Stephanas: besides, I know not whether I baptized any other.', '0~1161~ 2~907~ 3~2532~ 5~3624~ 7~4734~: 8~3063~, 10~1492~ 11~3756~ 14~907~ 15~1536~ 16~243~.'),
  (8786, 11, 2, 8, 'And, behold, thou hast with thee Shimei the son of Gera, a Benjamite of Bahurim, which cursed me with a grievous curse in the day when I went to Mahanaim: but he came down to meet me at Jordan, and I sware to him by the LORD, saying, I will not put thee to death with the sword.', '[2 3] 6~08096~ 8~01121~ 10~01617~, 12~01145~ 14~0980~, 16~07043~ 20~04834~ 21~07045~ 24~03117~ 27~03212~ 29~04266~: 33~03381~ 35~07125~ 38~03383~, 41~07650~ 46~03068~, 47~0559~, 54~04191~ 57~02719~.'),
  (15640, 19, 105, 25, 'He turned their heart to hate his people, to deal subtly with his servants.', '&para; 1~02015~ 3~03820~ 5~08130~ 7~05971~, 10~05230~ 13~05650~.'),
  (8700, 10, 23, 39, 'Uriah the Hittite: thirty and seven in all.', '0~0223~ 2~02850~: 3~07970~ 5~07651~'),
  (30228, 58, 11, 40, 'God having provided some better thing for us, that they without us should not be made perfect.', '0~2316~ 2~4265~ 3~5100~ 4~2909~ 5~5100~ 6~4012~ 7~2257~, 8~3363~ 9~5048~ 10~5565~ 11~2257~ 12~5048~ 13~3363~ 16~5048~.'),
  (4405, 4, 22, 25, 'And when the ass saw the angel of the LORD, she thrust herself unto the wall, and crushed Balaam''s foot against the wall: and he smote her again.', '3~0860~ 4~07200~ 6~04397~ 9~03068~, 11~03905~ 15~07023~, 17~03905~ 18~01109~ 19~07272~ 22~07023~: 25~05221~ 27~03254~.'),
  (13484, 18, 26, 8, 'He bindeth up the waters in his thick clouds; and the cloud is not rent under them.', '2~06887~ 4~04325~ 8~05645~; 11~06051~ 14~01234~'),
  (24419, 41, 6, 2, 'And when the sabbath day was come, he began to teach in the synagogue: and many hearing him were astonished, saying, From whence hath this man these things? and what wisdom is this which is given unto him, that even such mighty works are wrought by his hands?', '0~2532~ 4~4521~ 6~1096~, 8~756~ 10~1321~ 11~1722~ 13~4864~: 14~2532~ 15~4183~ 16~191~ [17] 19~1605~, 20~3004~, 22~4159~ 24~5129~ [25] 27~5023~? 28~2532~ 29~5101~ 30~4678~ [31] 35~1325~ 37~846~, 38~3754~ 39~2532~ 40~5108~ 42~1411~ 44~1096~ 45~1223~ 46~846~ 47~5495~?'),
  (2190, 2, 24, 8, 'And Moses took the blood, and sprinkled it on the people, and said, Behold the blood of the covenant, which the LORD hath made with you concerning all these words.', '1~04872~ 2~03947~ 4~01818~, 6~02236~ [7] 10~05971~, 12~0559~, 15~01818~ 18~01285~, 21~03068~ 23~03772~ 29~01697~.'),
  (6588, 7, 3, 13, 'And he gathered unto him the children of Ammon and Amalek, and went and smote Israel, and possessed the city of palm trees.', '2~0622~ 6~01121~ 8~05983~ 10~06002~, 12~03212~ 14~05221~ 15~03478~, 17~03423~ 19~05892~ 22~08558~ 23~05899~.*'),
  (661, 1, 24, 66, 'And the servant told Isaac all things that he had done.', '2~05650~ 3~05608~ 4~03327~ 6~01697~ 10~06213~.'),
  (279, 1, 11, 10, 'These are the generations of Shem: Shem was an hundred years old, and begat Arphaxad two years after the flood:', '&para; [1] 3~08435~ 5~08035~: 6~08035~ [7] 9~03967~ 10~08141~ 11~01121~, 13~03205~ 14~0775~ 16~08141~ 17~0310~ 19~03999~:'),
  (14808, 19, 59, 9, 'Because of his strength will I wait upon thee: for God is my defence.', '[0 1] 3~05797~ 6~08104~ 10~0430~ [11] 13~04869~.'),
  (10057, 12, 18, 25, 'Am I now come up without the LORD against this place to destroy it? The LORD said to me, Go up against this land, and destroy it.', '4~05927~ 5~01107~ 7~03068~ 10~04725~ 12~07843~ 15~03068~ 16~0559~ 20~05927~ 23~0776~, 25~07843~'),
  (26699, 43, 14, 16, 'And I will pray the Father, and he shall give you another Comforter, that he may abide with you for ever;', '0~2532~ 1~1473~ 3~2065~ 5~3962~, 6~2532~ 9~1325~ 10~5213~ 11~243~ 12~3875~, 13~2443~ 16~3306~ 17~3326~ 18~5216~ 19~1519~ 20~165~;'),
  (28402, 46, 1, 23, 'But we preach Christ crucified, unto the Jews a stumblingblock, and unto the Greeks foolishness;', '0~1161~ 1~2249~ 2~2784~ 3~5547~ 4~4717~, 7~2453~ 9~4625~ 10~3303~,* 11~1161~ 14~1672~ 15~3472~;'),
  (18556, 23, 44, 14, 'He heweth him down cedars, and taketh the cypress and the oak, which he strengtheneth for himself among the trees of the forest: he planteth an ash, and the rain doth nourish it.', '3~03772~ 4~0730~, 6~03947~ 8~08645~ 11~0437~, 14~0553~ 19~06086~ 22~03293~: 24~05193~ 26~0766~, 29~01653~ 31~01431~ [32]'),
  (472, 1, 19, 11, 'And they smote the men that were at the door of the house with blindness, both small and great: so that they wearied themselves to find the door.', '2~05221~ 4~0582~ [6] 9~06607~ 12~01004~ 14~05575~, 16~06996~ 18~01419~: 22~03811~ 25~04672~ 27~06607~.'),
  (18948, 23, 66, 17, 'They that sanctify themselves, and purify themselves in the gardens behind one tree in the midst, eating swine''s flesh, and the abomination, and the mouse, shall be consumed together, saith the LORD.', '2~06942~ 5~02891~ 9~01593~ 10~0310~ 11~0259~ [12] 15~08432~, 16~0398~ 17~02386~ 18~01320~, 21~08263~, 24~05909~, 27~05486~ 28~03162~, 29~05002~ 31~03068~.'),
  (17691, 23, 1, 28, 'And the destruction of the transgressors and of the sinners shall be together, and they that forsake the LORD shall be consumed.', '2~07667~ 5~06586~ 9~02400~ [10 11] 12~03162~, 16~05800~ 18~03068~ 21~03615~.'),
  (22612, 33, 2, 8, 'Even of late my people is risen up as an enemy: ye pull off the robe with the garment from them that pass by securely as men averse from war.', '2~0865~ 4~05971~ 7~06965~ 10~0341~: 13~06584~ 15~0145~ 16~04136~ 18~08008~ 22~05674~ 24~0983~ 27~07725~ 29~04421~.'),
  (19009, 24, 2, 35, 'Yet thou sayest, Because I am innocent, surely his anger shall turn from me. Behold, I will plead with thee, because thou sayest, I have not sinned.', '2~0559~, 6~05352~, 9~0639~ 11~07725~ 17~08199~ 22~0559~, 26~02398~.'),
  (23826, 40, 20, 24, 'And when the ten heard it, they were moved with indignation against the two brethren.', '0~2532~ 3~1176~ 4~191~ [5] 10~23~ 11~4012~ 13~1417~ 14~80~.'),
  (9119, 11, 11, 3, 'And he had seven hundred wives, princesses, and three hundred concubines: and his wives turned away his heart.', '3~07651~ 4~03967~ 5~0802~, 6~08282~, 8~07969~ 9~03967~ 10~06370~: 13~0802~ 15~05186~ 17~03820~.'),
  (27567, 44, 17, 28, 'For in him we live, and move, and have our being; as certain also of your own poets have said, For we are also his offspring.', '0~1063~ 1~1722~ 2~846~ 4~2198~, 5~2532~ 6~2795~, 7~2532~ 10~2070~; 11~5613~ 12~5100~ 13~2532~ 15~5209~ 16~2596~ 17~4163~ 19~2046~, 20~1063~ 22~2070~ 23~2532~ 24~5120~ 25~1085~.'),
  (15327, 19, 88, 10, 'Wilt thou shew wonders to the dead? shall the dead arise and praise thee? Selah.', '&para; 2~06213~ 3~06382~ 6~04191~? 9~07496~ 10~06965~ [11] 12~03034~ 14~05542~.'),
  (22837, 36, 3, 8, 'Therefore wait ye upon me, saith the LORD, until the day that I rise up to the prey: for my determination is to gather the nations, that I may assemble the kingdoms, to pour upon them mine indignation, even all my fierce anger: for all the earth shall be devoured with the fire of my jealousy.', '&para; 1~02442~ 5~05002~ 7~03068~, 10~03117~ 14~06965~ 17~05706~: 20~04941~ [21] 23~0622~ 25~01471~, 29~06908~ 31~04467~, 33~08210~ 37~02195~, [38] 41~02740~ 42~0639~: 46~0776~ 49~0398~ 52~0784~ 55~07068~.'),
  (2738, 2, 40, 26, 'And he put the golden altar in the tent of the congregation before the veil:', '2~07760~ 4~02091~ 5~04196~ 8~0168~ 11~04150~ 12~06440~ 14~06532~:'),
  (14105, 19, 16, 4, 'Their sorrows shall be multiplied that hasten after another god: their drink offerings of blood will I not offer, nor take up their names into my lips.', '1~06094~ 4~07235~ [5] 6~04116~ [7] 8~0312~ [9] 12~05262~ 14~01818~ 18~05258~, 19~01077~ 21~05375~ 23~08034~ 26~08193~.'),
  (29594, 52, 2, 8, 'So being affectionately desirous of you, we were willing to have imparted unto you, not the gospel of God only, but also our own souls, because ye were dear unto us.', '0~3779~ 3~2442~ 5~5216~, 8~2106~ 11~3330~ 13~5213~, 14~3756~ 16~2098~ 18~2316~ 19~3440~, 20~235~ 21~2532~ 23~1438~ 24~5590~, 25~1360~ 27~1096~ 28~27~ 30~2254~.'),
  (25126, 42, 5, 7, 'And they beckoned unto their partners, which were in the other ship, that they should come and help them. And they came, and filled both the ships, so that they began to sink.', '0~2532~ 2~2656~ [4] 5~3353~, 6~3588~ 8~1722~ 10~2087~ 11~4143~, 15~2064~ 17~4815~ 18~846~. 19~2532~ 21~2064~, 22~2532~ 23~4130~ 24~297~ 26~4143~, 27~5620~ 29~846~ 32~1036~.'),
  (27899, 44, 27, 28, 'And sounded, and found it twenty fathoms: and when they had gone a little further, they sounded again, and found it fifteen fathoms.', '0~2532~ 1~1001~, 3~2147~ [4] 5~1501~ 6~3712~: 7~1161~ 11~1339~ 14~1024~, 16~1001~ 17~3825~, 18~2532~ 19~2147~ [20] 21~1178~ 22~3712~.'),
  (15681, 19, 106, 21, 'They forgat God their saviour, which had done great things in Egypt;', '1~07911~ 2~0410~ 4~03467~, 7~06213~ 9~01419~ 11~04714~;'),
  (17060, 20, 23, 7, 'For as he thinketh in his heart, so is he: Eat and drink, saith he to thee; but his heart is not with thee.', '3~08176~ 6~05315~, [8] 10~0398~ 12~08354~, 13~0559~ 19~03820~ [20]'),
  (6340, 6, 19, 12, 'And turned from Sarid eastward toward the sunrising unto the border of Chislothtabor, and then goeth out to Daberath, and goeth up to Japhia.', '1~07725~ 3~08301~ 4~06924~ 7~08121~ 8~04217~ 10~01366~ 12~03696~, 16~03318~ 18~01705~, 21~05927~ 23~03309~,'),
  (15331, 19, 88, 14, 'LORD, why castest thou off my soul? why hidest thou thy face from me?', '0~03068~, 4~02186~ 6~05315~? [7] 8~05641~ 11~06440~'),
  (27600, 44, 18, 27, 'And when he was disposed to pass into Achaia, the brethren wrote, exhorting the disciples to receive him: who, when he was come, helped them much which had believed through grace:', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~1014~ 6~1330~ 7~1519~ 8~882~, 10~80~ 11~1125~, 12~4389~ 14~3101~ 16~588~ 17~846~: 18~3739~, 22~3854~, 24~4820~ 25~4183~ 28~4100~ 29~1223~ 30~5485~:'),
  (30623, 62, 4, 4, 'Ye are of God, little children, and have overcome them: because greater is he that is in you, than he that is in the world.', '&para; 0~5210~ 1~2075~ 2~1537~ 3~2316~, 5~5040~, 6~2532~ 8~3528~ 9~846~: 10~3754~ 11~3187~ 15~2076~ 16~1722~ 17~5213~, 18~2228~ 22~1722~ 24~2889~.'),
  (15902, 19, 118, 24, 'This is the day which the LORD hath made; we will rejoice and be glad in it.', '[1] 3~03117~ [4] 6~03068~ 8~06213~; 11~01523~ 14~08055~'),
  (12057, 15, 2, 21, 'The children of Bethlehem, an hundred twenty and three.', '1~01121~ 3~01035~, 5~03967~ 6~06242~ 8~07969~.'),
  (30299, 59, 1, 17, 'Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and cometh down from the Father of lights, with whom is no variableness, neither shadow of turning.', '0~3956~ 1~18~ 2~1394~ 3~2532~ 4~3956~ 5~5046~ 6~1434~ 7~2076~ 9~509~, 12~2597~ 13~575~ 15~3962~ 17~5457~, 18~3844~ 19~3739~ 20~1762~ 21~3756~ 22~3883~, 23~2228~ 24~644~ 26~5157~.'),
  (16446, 20, 2, 4, 'If thou seekest her as silver, and searchest for her as for hid treasures;', '2~01245~ 5~03701~, 7~02664~ [11] 13~04301~;'),
  (4922, 5, 1, 24, 'And they turned and went up into the mountain, and came unto the valley of Eshcol, and searched it out.', '2~06437~ 5~05927~ 8~02022~, 10~0935~ 13~05158~ 15~0812~, 19~07270~.'),
  (10475, 13, 6, 13, 'And Shallum begat Hilkiah, and Hilkiah begat Azariah,', '1~07967~ 2~03205~ 3~02518~, 5~02518~ 6~03205~ 7~05838~,'),
  (5921, 6, 4, 5, 'And Joshua said unto them, Pass over before the ark of the LORD your God into the midst of Jordan, and take you up every man of you a stone upon his shoulder, according unto the number of the tribes of the children of Israel:', '1~03091~ 2~0559~ 6~05674~ 7~06440~ 9~0727~ 12~03068~ 14~0430~ 17~08432~ 19~03383~, 23~07311~ 24~0259~ 25~0376~ 29~068~ 32~07926~, 36~04557~ 39~07626~ 42~01121~ 44~03478~:'),
  (4453, 4, 24, 2, 'And Balaam lifted up his eyes, and he saw Israel abiding in his tents according to their tribes; and the spirit of God came upon him.', '1~01109~ 3~05375~ 5~05869~, 8~07200~ 9~03478~ 10~07931~ [11 13] 17~07626~; 20~07307~ 22~0430~'),
  (4638, 4, 29, 24, 'Their meat offering and their drink offerings for the bullocks, for the rams, and for the lambs, shall be according to their number, after the manner:', '2~04503~ 6~05262~ 9~06499~, 12~0352~, 16~03532~, [17 18] 22~04557~, 25~04941~:'),
  (898, 1, 31, 21, 'So he fled with all that he had; and he rose up, and passed over the river, and set his face toward the mount Gilead.', '2~01272~ 11~06965~, 14~05674~ 16~05104~, 18~07760~ 20~06440~ [21] 23~02022~ 24~01568~.'),
  (13298, 18, 18, 13, 'It shall devour the strength of his skin: even the firstborn of death shall devour his strength.', '2~0398~ 4~0905~ 7~05785~: [8] 10~01060~ 12~04194~ 14~0398~ 16~0905~.'),
  (8303, 10, 12, 10, 'Now therefore the sword shall never depart from thine house; because thou hast despised me, and hast taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be thy wife.', '3~02719~ 5~05769~ 6~05704~* 7~05493~ 10~01004~; 11~06118~ 14~0959~ 18~03947~ 20~0802~ 22~0223~ 24~02850~ 28~0802~.'),
  (7255, 9, 2, 8, 'He raiseth up the poor out of the dust, and lifteth up the beggar from the dunghill, to set them among princes, and to make them inherit the throne of glory: for the pillars of the earth are the Lord''s, and he hath set the world upon them.', '2~06965~ 4~01800~ 8~06083~, [9] 11~07311~ 13~034~ 16~0830~, 18~03427~ [19] 21~05081~, 26~05157~ 28~03678~ 30~03519~: 33~04690~ 36~0776~ [37] 39~03068~, 43~07896~ 45~08398~'),
  (6153, 6, 12, 17, 'The king of Tappuah, one; the king of Hepher, one;', '1~04428~ 3~08599~, 4~0259~; 6~04428~ 8~02660~, 9~0259~;'),
  (22929, 38, 3, 8, 'Hear now, O Joshua the high priest, thou, and thy fellows that sit before thee: for they are men wondered at: for, behold, I will bring forth my servant the BRANCH.', '&para; 0~08085~ 3~03091~ 5~01419~ 6~03548~, 10~07453~ 12~03427~ 13~06440~ [17] 18~0582~ 20~04159~: 26~0935~ 28~05650~ 30~06780~.'),
  (29361, 49, 6, 8, 'Knowing that whatsoever good thing any man doeth, the same shall he receive of the Lord, whether he be bond or free.', '0~1492~ 1~3754~ 2~5100~ 3~3739~* 4~1437~ 5~18~ 7~1538~ 8~4160~, 10~5124~ 13~2865~ 14~3844~ 16~2962~, 17~1535~ [18 19] 20~1401~ 21~1535~ 22~1658~.'),
  (8838, 11, 3, 14, 'And if thou wilt walk in my ways, to keep my statutes and my commandments, as thy father David did walk, then I will lengthen thy days.', '4~03212~ 7~01870~, 9~08104~ 11~02706~ 14~04687~, 17~01~ 18~01732~ 20~01980~, 24~0748~ 26~03117~.'),
  (17397, 21, 4, 7, 'Then I returned, and I saw vanity under the sun.', '&para; 2~07725~, 5~07200~ 6~01892~ 9~08121~.'),
  (5306, 5, 14, 10, 'And whatsoever hath not fins and scales ye may not eat; it is unclean unto you.', '4~05579~ 6~07193~ 10~0398~; [12] 13~02931~'),
  (8986, 11, 7, 44, 'And one sea, and twelve oxen under the sea;', '1~0259~ 2~03220~, 4~06240~ 5~08147~* 6~01241~ 9~03220~;'),
  (9631, 12, 4, 20, 'And when he had taken him, and brought him to his mother, he sat on her knees till noon, and then died.', '4~05375~ 7~0935~ 11~0517~, 13~03427~ 16~01290~ 18~06672~, [20] 21~04191~.'),
  (14454, 19, 36, 7, 'How excellent is thy lovingkindness, O God! therefore the children of men put their trust under the shadow of thy wings.', '1~03368~ [2] 4~02617~, 6~0430~! 9~01121~ 11~0120~ 14~02620~ 17~06738~ 20~03671~.'),
  (13274, 18, 17, 5, 'He that speaketh flattery to his friends, even the eyes of his children shall fail.', '2~05046~ 3~02506~ [5] 6~07453~, 9~05869~ 12~01121~ 14~03615~.'),
  (27246, 44, 9, 14, 'And here he hath authority from the chief priests to bind all that call on thy name.', '0~2532~ 1~5602~ 3~2192~ 4~1849~ 5~3844~ 8~749~ 10~1210~ 11~3956~ 13~1941~ 15~4675~ 16~3686~.'),
  (23212, 40, 3, 10, 'And now also the ax is laid unto the root of the trees: therefore every tree which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.', '0~1161~ 1~2235~ 2~2532~ 4~513~ 6~2749~ 7~4314~ 9~4491~ 12~1186~: 13~3767~ 14~3956~ 15~1186~ 17~4160~ 18~3361~ 19~4160~ 20~2570~ 21~2590~ 24~1581~, 25~2532~ 26~906~ 27~1519~ 29~4442~.'),
  (4492, 4, 25, 16, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (13830, 18, 38, 28, 'Hath the rain a father? or who hath begotten the drops of dew?', '0~03426~ 2~04306~ 4~01~? 8~03205~ 10~096~ 12~02919~?'),
  (10426, 13, 4, 33, 'And all their villages that were round about the same cities, unto Baal. These were their habitations, and their genealogy.', '3~02691~ [5] 7~05439~ 10~05892~, 12~01168~. [14] 16~04186~, 19~03187~.'),
  (18579, 23, 45, 9, 'Woe unto him that striveth with his Maker! Let the potsherd strive with the potsherds of the earth. Shall the clay say to him that fashioneth it, What makest thou? or thy work, He hath no hands?', '0~01945~ 4~07378~ 7~03335~! [8] 10~02789~ [11] 14~02789~ 17~0127~. 20~02563~ 21~0559~ 25~03335~ 28~06213~ 32~06467~, 36~03027~?'),
  (29670, 53, 1, 5, 'Which is a manifest token of the righteous judgment of God, that ye may be counted worthy of the kingdom of God, for which ye also suffer:', '&para; [0 1] 4~1730~ 7~1342~ 8~2920~ 10~2316~, 11~1519~ 12~5209~ 16~2661~ 19~932~ 21~2316~, 22~5228~ 23~3739~ 24~3958~ 25~2532~ 26~3958~:'),
  (22744, 35, 1, 4, 'Therefore the law is slacked, and judgment doth never go forth: for the wicked doth compass about the righteous; therefore wrong judgment proceedeth.', '2~08451~ 4~06313~, 6~04941~ 8~05331~ 10~03318~: 13~07563~ 15~03803~ 18~06662~; 20~06127~ 21~04941~ 22~03318~.'),
  (18701, 23, 51, 19, 'These two things are come unto thee; who shall be sorry for thee? desolation, and destruction, and the famine, and the sword: by whom shall I comfort thee?', '1~08147~ [2] 4~07122~ 10~05110~ 13~07701~, 15~07667~, 18~07458~, 21~02719~: 26~05162~'),
  (11337, 14, 7, 5, 'And king Solomon offered a sacrifice of twenty and two thousand oxen, and an hundred and twenty thousand sheep: so the king and all the people dedicated the house of God.', '1~04428~ 2~08010~ 3~02076~ 5~02077~ 7~06242~ 9~08147~ 10~0505~ 11~01241~, 14~03967~ 16~06242~ 17~0505~ 18~06629~: 21~04428~ 25~05971~ 26~02596~ 28~01004~ 30~0430~.'),
  (15504, 19, 98, 5, 'Sing unto the LORD with the harp; with the harp, and the voice of a psalm.', '0~02167~ 3~03068~ 6~03658~; 9~03658~, 12~06963~ 15~02172~.'),
  (23468, 40, 10, 41, 'He that receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet shall receive a prophet''s reward; and he that receiveth a righteous man in the name of a righteous man shall receive a righteous man''s reward.', '2~1209~ 4~4396~ 5~1519~ 7~3686~ 10~4396~ 12~2983~ 14~4396~ 15~3408~; 16~2532~ 19~2983~ 22~1342~ 23~1519~ 25~3686~ 29~1342~ 31~1209~ 34~1342~ 35~3408~.'),
  (6275, 6, 16, 3, 'And goeth down westward to the coast of Japhleti, unto the coast of Bethhoron the nether, and to Gezer: and the goings out thereof are at the sea.', '2~03381~ 3~03220~ 6~01366~ 8~03311~, 11~01366~ 13~01032~ 15~08481~, 18~01507~: 22~08444~ 27~03220~.'),
  (14405, 19, 34, 8, 'O taste and see that the LORD is good: blessed is the man that trusteth in him.', '1~02938~ 3~07200~ 6~03068~ [7] 8~02896~: 9~0835~ [10] 12~01397~ [13] 14~02620~'),
  (19435, 24, 20, 4, 'For thus saith the LORD, Behold, I will make thee a terror to thyself, and to all thy friends: and they shall fall by the sword of their enemies, and thine eyes shall behold it: and I will give all Judah into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he shall carry them captive into Babylon, and shall slay them with the sword.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~, 8~05414~ 11~04032~ 18~0157~: 22~05307~ 25~02719~ 28~0341~, 31~05869~ 33~07200~ [34] 38~05414~ 40~03063~ 43~03027~ 46~04428~ 48~0894~, 54~01540~ 56~0894~, 59~05221~ 63~02719~.'),
  (21580, 26, 42, 19, 'He turned about to the west side, and measured five hundred reeds with the measuring reed.', '2~05437~ 5~03220~ 6~07307~, [7] 8~04058~ 9~02568~ 10~03967~ 11~07070~ 14~04060~ 15~07070~.');
