VALUES
  (14491, 19, 37, 32, 'The wicked watcheth the righteous, and seeketh to slay him.', '1~07563~ 2~06822~ 4~06662~, 6~01245~ 8~04191~'),
  (14210, 19, 21, 10, 'Their fruit shalt thou destroy from the earth, and their seed from among the children of men.', '1~06529~ 4~06~ 7~0776~, 10~02233~ 14~01121~ 16~0120~.'),
  (27254, 44, 9, 22, 'But Saul increased the more in strength, and confounded the Jews which dwelt at Damascus, proving that this is very Christ.', '0~1161~ 1~4569~ 2~1743~ 4~3123~ 6~1743~, 7~2532~ 8~4797~ 10~2453~ 11~3588~ 12~2730~ 13~1722~ 14~1154~, 15~4822~ 16~3754~ 17~3778~ 18~2076~ 20~5547~.'),
  (23193, 40, 2, 14, 'When he arose, he took the young child and his mother by night, and departed into Egypt:', '0~1161~ 2~1453~, 4~3880~ 7~3813~ 8~2532~ 9~846~ 10~3384~ 12~3571~, 13~2532~ 14~402~ 15~1519~ 16~125~:'),
  (9377, 11, 18, 28, 'And they cried aloud, and cut themselves after their manner with knives and lancets, till the blood gushed out upon them.', '2~07121~ 3~01419~ 4~06963~,* 6~01413~ 10~04941~ 12~02719~ 14~07420~, 17~01818~ 19~08210~'),
  (8137, 10, 4, 10, 'When one told me, saying, Behold, Saul is dead, thinking to have brought good tidings, I took hold of him, and slew him in Ziklag, who thought that I would have given him a reward for his tidings:', '2~05046~ 4~0559~, 6~07586~ 8~04191~, 12~05869~ 14~01319~, 17~0270~ 21~02026~ 24~06860~, [26] 31~05414~ 37~01309~:'),
  (244, 1, 10, 9, 'He was a mighty hunter before the LORD: wherefore it is said, Even as Nimrod the mighty hunter before the LORD.', '3~01368~ 4~06718~ 5~06440~ 7~03068~: 8~03651~ 11~0559~, 14~05248~ 16~01368~ 17~06718~ 18~06440~ 20~03068~.'),
  (12994, 18, 6, 7, 'The things that my soul refused to touch are as my sorrowful meat.', '[2] 4~05315~ 5~03985~ 7~05060~ [8] 11~01741~ 12~03899~.'),
  (26645, 43, 12, 50, 'And I know that his commandment is life everlasting: whatsoever I speak therefore, even as the Father said unto me, so I speak.', '0~2532~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 4~846~ 5~1785~ 6~2076~ 7~2222~ 8~166~: 9~3739~ 10~1473~ 11~2980~ 12~3767~, 14~2531~ 16~3962~ 17~2046~ 19~3427~, 20~3779~ 22~2980~.'),
  (28200, 45, 9, 29, 'And as Esaias said before, Except the Lord of Sabaoth had left us a seed, we had been as Sodoma, and been made like unto Gomorrha.', '0~2532~ 1~2531~ 2~2268~ 4~4280~, 5~1508~ 7~2962~ 9~4519~ 11~1459~ 12~2254~ 14~4690~, 17~1096~ 18~302~* 19~5613~ 20~4670~, 21~2532~ 24~3666~ 25~302~* 26~5613~ 27~1116~.'),
  (4656, 4, 30, 2, 'If a man vow a vow unto the LORD, or swear an oath to bind his soul with a bond; he shall not break his word, he shall do according to all that proceedeth out of his mouth.', '2~0376~ 3~05087~ 5~05088~ 8~03068~, 10~07650~ 12~07621~ 14~0631~ 16~05315~ 19~0632~; 23~02490~ 25~01697~, 28~06213~ 33~03318~ 37~06310~.'),
  (211, 1, 9, 5, 'And surely your blood of your lives will I require; at the hand of every beast will I require it, and at the hand of man; at the hand of every man''s brother will I require the life of man.', '1~0389~ 3~01818~ 6~05315~ 9~01875~; 12~03027~ 15~02416~ 19~01875~, 23~03027~ 25~0120~; 28~03027~ 31~0376~ 32~0251~ 35~01875~ 37~05315~ 39~0120~.'),
  (5911, 6, 3, 12, 'Now therefore take you twelve men out of the tribes of Israel, out of every tribe a man.', '2~03947~ 4~06240~ 5~08147~* 6~0376~ 10~07626~ 12~03478~, 15~0259~ 16~07626~ 18~0376~.'),
  (22695, 34, 1, 2, 'God is jealous, and the LORD revengeth; the LORD revengeth, and is furious; the LORD will take vengeance on his adversaries, and he reserveth wrath for his enemies.', '&para; 0~0410~ [1] 2~07072~, 5~03068~ 6~05358~; 8~03068~ 9~05358~, [11] 12~02534~ 13~01167~;* 15~03068~ 18~05358~ 21~06862~, 24~05201~ [25] 28~0341~.'),
  (10261, 13, 1, 1, 'Adam, Sheth, Enosh,', '&para; 0~0121~, 1~08352~, 2~0583~,'),
  (29351, 49, 5, 31, 'For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and shall be joined unto his wife, and they two shall be one flesh.', '0~473~ 2~5127~ 3~2641~ 5~444~ 6~2641~ 7~846~ 8~3962~ 9~2532~ 10~3384~, 11~2532~ 14~4347~ 15~4314~ 16~846~ 17~1135~, 18~2532~ 20~1417~ 22~2071~ 23~3391~ 24~1519~* 25~4561~.'),
  (4884, 4, 35, 33, 'So ye shall not pollute the land wherein ye are: for blood it defileth the land: and the land cannot be cleansed of the blood that is shed therein, but by the blood of him that shed it.', '4~02610~ 6~0776~ [9] 11~01818~ 13~02610~ 15~0776~: 18~0776~ 21~03722~ 24~01818~ 27~08210~ 32~01818~ 36~08210~'),
  (14385, 19, 33, 10, 'The LORD bringeth the counsel of the heathen to nought: he maketh the devices of the people of none effect.', '1~03068~ 2~06331~ 4~06098~ 7~01471~ 9~06331~: 11~05106~ 13~04284~ 16~05971~ 19~05106~.'),
  (26105, 43, 1, 46, 'And Nathanael said unto him, Can there any good thing come out of Nazareth? Philip saith unto him, Come and see.', '0~2532~ 1~3482~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~1410~ 7~5100~ 9~18~ 10~1511~ 12~1537~ 13~3478~? 14~5376~ 15~3004~ 17~846~, 18~2064~ 19~2532~ 20~1492~.'),
  (9846, 12, 11, 9, 'And the captains over the hundreds did according to all things that Jehoiada the priest commanded: and they took every man his men that were to come in on the sabbath, with them that should go out on the sabbath, and came to Jehoiada the priest.', '2~08269~ 5~03967~ 6~06213~ [10] 12~03077~ 14~03548~ 15~06680~: 18~03947~ 20~0376~ 22~0582~ 27~0935~ 30~07676~, 36~03318~ 39~07676~, 41~0935~ 43~03077~ 45~03548~.'),
  (5627, 5, 28, 10, 'And all people of the earth shall see that thou art called by the name of the LORD; and they shall be afraid of thee.', '2~05971~ 5~0776~ 7~07200~ 11~07121~ 14~08034~ 17~03068~; 22~03372~'),
  (10644, 13, 9, 21, 'And Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah was porter of the door of the tabernacle of the congregation.', '[0] 1~02148~ 3~01121~ 5~04920~ [6] 7~07778~ 10~06607~ 13~0168~ 16~04150~.'),
  (28803, 46, 16, 11, 'Let no man therefore despise him: but conduct him forth in peace, that he may come unto me: for I look for him with the brethren.', '0~1848~ 1~3361~ 2~5100~ 3~3767~ 4~1848~ 5~846~: 6~1161~ 7~4311~ 8~846~ 9~4311~ 10~1722~ 11~1515~, 12~2443~ 15~2064~ 16~4314~ 17~3165~: 18~1063~ 21~1551~ 22~846~ 23~3326~ 25~80~.'),
  (1349, 1, 44, 20, 'And we said unto my lord, We have a father, an old man, and a child of his old age, a little one; and his brother is dead, and he alone is left of his mother, and his father loveth him.', '2~0559~ 5~0113~, 7~03426~ 9~01~, 12~02205~, 15~03206~ 19~02208~, 22~06996~; 25~0251~ 27~04191~, 32~03498~ 35~0517~, 38~01~ 39~0157~'),
  (20386, 25, 3, 23, 'They are new every morning: great is thy faithfulness.', '[0 1] 2~02319~ 4~01242~: 5~07227~ [6] 8~0530~.'),
  (30241, 58, 12, 13, 'And make straight paths for your feet, lest that which is lame be turned out of the way; but let it rather be healed.', '0~2532~ 1~4160~ 2~3717~ 3~5163~ 5~5216~ 6~4228~, 8~3363~ 11~5560~ 17~1624~; 18~1161~ 20~2390~ 21~3123~ 23~2390~.'),
  (4046, 4, 11, 17, 'And I will come down and talk with thee there: and I will take of the spirit which is upon thee, and will put it upon them; and they shall bear the burden of the people with thee, that thou bear it not thyself alone.', '4~03381~ 6~01696~ 13~0680~ 16~07307~ [18] 23~07760~ [24] 30~05375~ 32~04853~ 35~05971~ 40~05375~ [41]'),
  (10296, 13, 1, 36, 'The sons of Eliphaz; Teman, and Omar, Zephi, and Gatam, Kenaz, and Timna, and Amalek.', '1~01121~ 3~0464~; 4~08487~, 6~0201~, 7~06825~, 9~01609~, 10~07073~, 12~08555~, 14~06002~.'),
  (13086, 18, 9, 26, 'They are passed away as the swift ships: as the eagle that hasteth to the prey.', '3~02498~ 4~05973~ 6~016~ 7~0591~: 10~05404~ [11] 12~02907~ 15~0400~.'),
  (28587, 46, 10, 4, 'And did all drink the same spiritual drink: for they drank of that spiritual Rock that followed them: and that Rock was Christ.', '0~2532~ 1~4095~ 2~3956~ 3~4095~ 5~846~ 6~4152~ 7~4188~: 8~1063~ 10~4095~ 11~1537~ 13~4152~ 14~4073~ 17~190~: 18~1161~ 20~4073~ 21~2258~ 22~5547~.'),
  (26354, 43, 7, 11, 'Then the Jews sought him at the feast, and said, Where is he?', '0~3767~ 2~2453~ 3~2212~ 4~846~ 5~1722~ 7~1859~, 8~2532~ 9~3004~, 10~4226~ 11~2076~ 12~1565~?'),
  (11411, 14, 10, 7, 'And they spake unto him, saying, If thou be kind to this people, and please them, and speak good words to them, they will be thy servants for ever.', '2~01696~ 5~0559~, 9~02896~ 12~05971~, 14~07521~ 17~01696~ 18~02896~ 19~01697~ 26~05650~ 28~03117~.'),
  (14929, 19, 68, 20, 'He that is our God is the God of salvation; and unto GOD the Lord belong the issues from death.', '[0 2] 4~0410~ [5] 7~0410~ 9~04190~; 12~03069~ 14~0136~ [15] 17~08444~ 19~04194~.'),
  (27956, 45, 1, 10, 'Making request, if by any means now at length I might have a prosperous journey by the will of God to come unto you.', '1~1189~, 5~1513~ 6~2235~ 8~4218~ 14~2137~ 15~1722~ 17~2307~ 19~2316~ 21~2064~ 22~4314~ 23~5209~.'),
  (25622, 42, 15, 21, 'And the son said unto him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in thy sight, and am no more worthy to be called thy son.', '0~1161~ 2~5207~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 6~3962~, 9~264~ 10~1519~ 11~3772~, 12~2532~ 13~1799~ 14~4675~ 15~1799~, 16~2532~ 17~1510~ 19~3765~ 20~514~ 23~2564~ 24~4675~ 25~5207~.'),
  (25908, 42, 22, 30, 'That ye may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.', '0~2443~ 3~2068~ 4~2532~ 5~4095~ 6~1909~ 7~3450~ 8~5132~ 9~1722~ 10~3450~ 11~932~, 12~2532~ 13~2523~ 14~1909~ 15~2362~ 16~2919~ 18~1427~ 19~5443~ 21~2474~.'),
  (17734, 23, 3, 18, 'In that day the Lord will take away the bravery of their tinkling ornaments about their feet, and their cauls, and their round tires like the moon,', '2~03117~ 4~0136~ 7~05493~ 9~08597~ [11] 13~05914~ [14 16] [18] 19~07636~, [21] 26~07720~,'),
  (2317, 2, 28, 19, 'And the third row a ligure, an agate, and an amethyst.', '2~07992~ 3~02905~ 5~03958~, 7~07618~, 10~0306~.'),
  (3918, 4, 7, 63, 'One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:', '0~0259~ 1~01241~ 2~06499~, 3~0259~ 4~0352~, 5~0259~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~, 14~05930~:'),
  (27904, 44, 27, 33, 'And while the day was coming on, Paul besought them all to take meat, saying, This day is the fourteenth day that ye have tarried and continued fasting, having taken nothing.', '0~1161~ 1~3739~ 2~891~ 3~2250~ 5~1096~ 6~3195~, 7~3972~ 8~3870~ [9] 10~537~ 12~3335~ 13~5160~, 14~3004~, 16~4594~ 19~5065~ 20~2250~ 24~4328~ 26~1300~ 27~777~, 29~4355~ 30~3367~.'),
  (16913, 20, 18, 3, 'When the wicked cometh, then cometh also contempt, and with ignominy reproach.', '&para; 2~07563~ 3~0935~, [4] 5~0935~ 7~0937~, 10~07036~ 11~02781~.'),
  (20250, 24, 51, 29, 'And the land shall tremble and sorrow: for every purpose of the LORD shall be performed against Babylon, to make the land of Babylon a desolation without an inhabitant.', '2~0776~ 4~07493~ 6~02342~: 9~04284~ 12~03068~ 15~06965~ 17~0894~, 19~07760~ 21~0776~ 23~0894~ 25~08047~ 28~03427~.'),
  (17340, 21, 1, 16, 'I communed with mine own heart, saying, Lo, I am come to great estate, and have gotten more wisdom than all they that have been before me in Jerusalem: yea, my heart had great experience of wisdom and knowledge.', '1~01696~ 5~03820~, 6~0559~, 13~01431~, 16~03254~ 18~02451~ [21] 25~06440~ 28~03389~: 31~03820~ 33~07235~ 34~07200~ 36~02451~ 38~01847~.'),
  (15415, 19, 91, 11, 'For he shall give his angels charge over thee, to keep thee in all thy ways.', '5~04397~ 6~06680~ 10~08104~ 15~01870~.'),
  (4986, 5, 3, 5, 'All these cities were fenced with high walls, gates, and bars; beside unwalled towns a great many.', '2~05892~ [3] 4~01219~ 6~01364~ 7~02346~, 8~01817~, 10~01280~; 12~06521~ 13~05892~ 15~03966~ 16~07235~.'),
  (11358, 14, 8, 4, 'And he built Tadmor in the wilderness, and all the store cities, which he built in Hamath.', '2~01129~ 3~08412~ 6~04057~, 10~04543~ 11~05892~, 14~01129~ 16~02574~.'),
  (20311, 24, 52, 26, 'So Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them, and brought them to the king of Babylon to Riblah.', '1~05018~ 3~07227~ 6~02876~ 7~03947~ 10~03212~ 14~04428~ 16~0894~ 18~07247~.'),
  (29749, 54, 3, 2, 'A bishop then must be blameless, the husband of one wife, vigilant, sober, of good behaviour, given to hospitality, apt to teach;', '1~1985~ 2~3767~ 3~1163~ 4~1511~ 5~423~, 7~435~ 9~3391~ 10~1135~, 11~3524~, 12~4998~, 15~2887~, 18~5382~, 21~1317~;'),
  (15908, 19, 119, 1, 'ALEPH. Blessed are the undefiled in the way, who walk in the law of the LORD.', '&para; 1~0835~ [2] 4~08549~ 7~01870~, 9~01980~ 12~08451~ 15~03068~.'),
  (23461, 40, 10, 34, 'Think not that I am come to send peace on earth: I came not to send peace, but a sword.', '0~3543~ 1~3361~ 2~3754~ 5~2064~ 7~906~ 8~1515~ 9~1909~ 10~1093~: 12~2064~ 13~3756~ 15~906~ 16~1515~, 17~235~ 19~3162~.'),
  (23635, 40, 14, 28, 'And Peter answered him and said, Lord, if it be thou, bid me come unto thee on the water.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~611~ 3~846~ 5~2036~, 6~2962~, 7~1487~ 9~1488~ 10~4771~, 11~2753~ 12~3165~ 13~2064~ 14~4314~ 15~4571~ 16~1909~ 18~5204~.'),
  (14285, 19, 26, 3, 'For thy lovingkindness is before mine eyes: and I have walked in thy truth.', '2~02617~ [3] 6~05869~: 10~01980~ 13~0571~.'),
  (25110, 42, 4, 35, 'And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him. And when the devil had thrown him in the midst, he came out of him, and hurt him not.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~2008~ 3~846~, 4~3004~, 7~5392~, 8~2532~ 9~1831~ 11~1537~ 12~846~. 13~2532~ 16~1140~ 18~4496~ 19~846~ 20~1519~ 22~3319~, 24~1831~ 26~575~ 27~846~, 29~984~ 30~846~ 31~3367~.'),
  (28129, 45, 7, 22, 'For I delight in the law of God after the inward man:', '0~1063~ 2~4913~ 5~3551~ 7~2316~ 8~2596~ 10~2080~ 11~444~:'),
  (10365, 13, 2, 51, 'Salma the father of Bethlehem, Hareph the father of Bethgader.', '0~08007~ 2~01~ 4~01035~, 5~02780~ 7~01~ 9~01013~.'),
  (5279, 5, 13, 1, 'If there arise among you a prophet, or a dreamer of dreams, and giveth thee a sign or a wonder,', '&para; 2~06965~ 3~07130~ 6~05030~, 9~02492~ 11~02472~, 13~05414~ 16~0226~ 19~04159~,'),
  (9429, 11, 20, 13, 'And, behold, there came a prophet unto Ahab king of Israel, saying, Thus saith the LORD, Hast thou seen all this great multitude? behold, I will deliver it into thine hand this day; and thou shalt know that I am the LORD.', '3~05066~ 4~0259~ 5~05030~ 7~0256~ 8~04428~ 10~03478~, 11~0559~, 13~0559~ 15~03068~, 18~07200~ 21~01419~ 22~01995~? 26~05414~ 30~03027~ 32~03117~; 36~03045~ [39] 41~03068~.'),
  (30281, 58, 13, 24, 'Salute all them that have the rule over you, and all the saints. They of Italy salute you.', '0~782~ 1~3956~ 6~2233~ 8~5216~, 9~2532~ 10~3956~ 12~40~. 14~575~ 15~2482~ 16~782~ 17~5209~.'),
  (27556, 44, 17, 17, 'Therefore disputed he in the synagogue with the Jews, and with the devout persons, and in the market daily with them that met with him.', '0~3303~ 1~3767~ 2~1256~ 3~1722~ 5~4864~ 8~2453~, 9~2532~ 13~4576~, 14~2532~ 15~1722~ 17~58~ 18~2250~ 19~2596~* 20~3956~* 21~4314~ 26~3909~.'),
  (22209, 28, 8, 6, 'For from Israel was it also: the workman made it; therefore it is not God: but the calf of Samaria shall be broken in pieces.', '2~03478~ [3] 7~02796~ 8~06213~ [12] 14~0430~: 17~05695~ 19~08111~ 24~07616~.'),
  (872, 1, 30, 38, 'And he set the rods which he had pilled before the flocks in the gutters in the watering troughs when the flocks came to drink, that they should conceive when they came to drink.', '2~03322~ 4~04731~ 8~06478~ 9~05227~ 11~06629~ 14~07298~ 17~04325~ 18~08268~ 21~06629~ 22~0935~ 24~08354~, 28~03179~ 31~0935~ 33~08354~.'),
  (13017, 18, 6, 30, 'Is there iniquity in my tongue? cannot my taste discern perverse things?', '1~03426~ 2~05766~ 5~03956~? 8~02441~ 9~0995~ 11~01942~?'),
  (6161, 6, 13, 1, 'Now Joshua was old and stricken in years; and the LORD said unto him, Thou art old and stricken in years, and there remaineth yet very much land to be possessed.', '&para; 1~03091~ 3~02204~ [4] 5~0935~ 7~03117~; 10~03068~ 11~0559~ 16~02204~ [17] 18~0935~ 20~03117~, 23~07604~ 25~03966~ 26~07235~ 27~0776~ 30~03423~.'),
  (30059, 58, 5, 13, 'For every one that useth milk is unskilful in the word of righteousness: for he is a babe.', '0~1063~ 2~3956~ 4~3348~ 5~1051~ [6] 7~552~ 10~3056~ 12~1343~: 13~1063~ 15~2076~ 17~3516~.'),
  (23582, 40, 13, 33, 'Another parable spake he unto them; The kingdom of heaven is like unto leaven, which a woman took, and hid in three measures of meal, till the whole was leavened.', '0~243~ 1~3850~ 3~2980~ 5~846~; 7~932~ 9~3772~ 10~2076~ 11~3664~ 13~2219~, 14~3739~ 16~1135~ 17~2983~, 19~1470~ 20~1519~ 21~5140~ 22~4568~ 24~224~, 25~2193~ 27~3650~ 28~3739~ 29~2220~.'),
  (28165, 45, 8, 33, 'Who shall lay any thing to the charge of God''s elect? It is God that justifieth.', '0~5101~ 4~1458~ 7~2596~ 9~2316~ 10~1588~? [11 12] 13~2316~ 15~1344~.'),
  (4135, 4, 14, 22, 'Because all those men which have seen my glory, and my miracles, which I did in Egypt and in the wilderness, and have tempted me now these ten times, and have not hearkened to my voice;', '3~0582~ 6~07200~ 8~03519~, 11~0226~, 14~06213~ 16~04714~ 20~04057~, 23~05254~ 24~0853~* 28~06235~ 29~06471~, 33~08085~ 36~06963~;'),
  (15971, 19, 119, 64, 'The earth, O LORD, is full of thy mercy: teach me thy statutes.', '&para; 1~0776~, 3~03068~, 5~04390~ 8~02617~: 9~03925~ 12~02706~.'),
  (25977, 42, 23, 28, 'But Jesus turning unto them said, Daughters of Jerusalem, weep not for me, but weep for yourselves, and for your children.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~4762~ 3~4314~ 4~846~ 5~2036~, 6~2364~ 8~2419~, 9~2799~ 10~3361~ 11~1909~ 12~1691~, 13~4133~ 14~2799~ 15~1909~ 16~1438~, 17~2532~ 18~1909~ 19~5216~ 20~5043~.'),
  (30343, 59, 3, 8, 'But the tongue can no man tame; it is an unruly evil, full of deadly poison.', '0~1161~ 2~1100~ 3~1410~ 4~3762~ 5~444~ 6~1150~; [7 8] 10~183~ 11~2556~, 12~3324~ 14~2287~ 15~2447~.'),
  (1563, 2, 2, 4, 'And his sister stood afar off, to wit what would be done to him.', '2~0269~ 3~03320~ 5~07350~, 7~03045~ 11~06213~'),
  (26475, 43, 9, 20, 'His parents answered them and said, We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind:', '0~846~ 1~1118~ 2~611~ 3~846~ 4~2532~ 5~2036~, 7~1492~ 8~3754~ 9~3778~ 10~2076~ 11~2257~ 12~5207~, 13~2532~ 14~3754~ 17~1080~ 18~5185~:'),
  (27507, 44, 16, 8, 'And they passing by Mysia came down to Troas.', '0~1161~ 3~3928~ 4~3465~ 6~2597~ 7~1519~ 8~5174~.'),
  (11258, 14, 4, 4, 'It stood upon twelve oxen, three looking toward the north, and three looking toward the west, and three looking toward the south, and three looking toward the east: and the sea was set above upon them, and all their hinder parts were inward.', '1~05975~ 3~06240~ 4~08147~* 5~01241~, 6~07969~ 7~06437~ 10~06828~, 12~07969~ 13~06437~ 16~03220~, 18~07969~ 19~06437~ 22~05045~, 24~07969~ 25~06437~ 28~04217~: 31~03220~ [32 33] 34~04605~ 41~0268~ [42] 43~01004~.'),
  (5708, 5, 29, 23, 'And that the whole land thereof is brimstone, and salt, and burning, that it is not sown, nor beareth, nor any grass groweth therein, like the overthrow of Sodom, and Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboim, which the LORD overthrew in his anger, and in his wrath:', '[0 1] 4~0776~ [6] 7~01614~, 9~04417~, [10] 11~08316~, [12] 16~02232~, 18~06779~, 21~06212~ 22~05927~ 26~04114~ 28~05467~, 30~06017~, 31~0126~, 33~06636~, 36~03068~ 37~02015~ 40~0639~, 44~02534~:'),
  (21116, 26, 26, 7, 'For thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I will bring upon Tyrus Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon, a king of kings, from the north, with horses, and with chariots, and with horsemen, and companies, and much people.', '2~0559~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~; 9~0935~ 11~06865~ 12~05019~ 13~04428~ 15~0894~, 17~04428~ 19~04428~, 22~06828~, 24~05483~, 27~07393~, 30~06571~, 32~06951~, 34~07227~ 35~05971~.'),
  (18401, 23, 38, 2, 'Then Hezekiah turned his face toward the wall, and prayed unto the LORD,', '1~02396~ 2~05437~ 4~06440~ 7~07023~, 9~06419~ 12~03068~,'),
  (14633, 19, 46, 10, 'Be still, and know that I am God: I will be exalted among the heathen, I will be exalted in the earth.', '1~07503~, 3~03045~ [6] 7~0430~: 11~07311~ 14~01471~, 18~07311~ 21~0776~.'),
  (24565, 41, 9, 16, 'And he asked the scribes, What question ye with them?', '0~2532~ 2~1905~ 4~1122~, 5~5101~ 7~4802~ 8~4314~ 9~846~?'),
  (30290, 59, 1, 8, 'A double minded man is unstable in all his ways.', '2~1374~ 3~435~ [4] 5~182~ 6~1722~ 7~3956~ 8~846~ 9~3598~.'),
  (8410, 10, 15, 14, 'And David said unto all his servants that were with him at Jerusalem, Arise, and let us flee; for we shall not else escape from Absalom: make speed to depart, lest he overtake us suddenly, and bring evil upon us, and smite the city with the edge of the sword.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 6~05650~ [8] 12~03389~, 13~06965~, 17~01272~; [22] 23~06413~ 24~06440~ 25~053~: 27~04116~ 29~03212~, 32~05381~ 34~04116~, 36~05080~ 37~07451~ 41~05221~ 43~05892~ 46~06310~ 49~02719~.'),
  (16163, 19, 132, 3, 'Surely I will not come into the tabernacle of my house, nor go up into my bed;', '4~0935~ 7~0168~ 10~01004~, 13~05927~ 16~03326~ 17~06210~;*'),
  (11033, 13, 24, 10, 'The seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to Abijah,', '1~07637~ 3~06976~, 5~08066~ 7~029~,'),
  (16805, 20, 14, 24, 'The crown of the wise is their riches: but the foolishness of fools is folly.', '&para; 1~05850~ 4~02450~ [5] 7~06239~: [8] 10~0200~ 12~03684~ [13] 14~0200~.'),
  (5205, 5, 10, 13, 'To keep the commandments of the LORD, and his statutes, which I command thee this day for thy good?', '1~08104~ 3~04687~ 6~03068~, 9~02708~, 12~06680~ 15~03117~ 18~02896~?'),
  (22946, 38, 5, 1, 'Then I turned, and lifted up mine eyes, and looked, and behold a flying roll.', '&para; 2~07725~, 5~05375~ 7~05869~, 9~07200~, 13~05774~ 14~04039~.'),
  (11735, 14, 25, 22, 'And Judah was put to the worse before Israel, and they fled every man to his tent.', '1~03063~ 6~05062~ 7~06440~ 8~03478~, 11~05127~ 13~0376~ 16~0168~.'),
  (17182, 20, 27, 4, 'Wrath is cruel, and anger is outrageous; but who is able to stand before envy?', '0~02534~ [1] 2~0395~, 4~0639~ [5] 6~07858~; [9] 12~05975~ 13~06440~ 14~07068~?'),
  (21588, 26, 43, 7, 'And he said unto me, Son of man, the place of my throne, and the place of the soles of my feet, where I will dwell in the midst of the children of Israel for ever, and my holy name, shall the house of Israel no more defile, neither they, nor their kings, by their whoredom, nor by the carcases of their kings in their high places.', '&para; 2~0559~ 5~01121~ 7~0120~, 9~04725~ 12~03678~, 15~04725~ 18~03709~ 21~07272~, 25~07931~ 28~08432~ 31~01121~ 33~03478~ 35~05769~, 38~06944~ 39~08034~, 42~01004~ 44~03478~ 47~02930~, [48] 52~04428~, 55~02184~, 59~06297~ 62~04428~ 66~01116~.'),
  (16223, 19, 136, 18, 'And slew famous kings: for his mercy endureth for ever:', '1~02026~ 2~0117~ 3~04428~: 6~02617~ [7] 9~05769~:'),
  (22414, 30, 3, 10, 'For they know not to do right, saith the LORD, who store up violence and robbery in their palaces.', '2~03045~ 5~06213~ 6~05229~, 7~05002~ 9~03068~, 11~0686~ 13~02555~ 15~07701~ 18~0759~.'),
  (11266, 14, 4, 12, 'To wit, the two pillars, and the pommels, and the chapiters which were on the top of the two pillars, and the two wreaths to cover the two pommels of the chapiters which were on the top of the pillars;', '[0 1] 3~08147~ 4~05982~, 7~01543~, 10~03805~ [11 12] 15~07218~ 19~05982~, 22~08147~ 23~07639~ 25~03680~ 27~08147~ 28~01543~ 31~03805~ [33] 36~07218~ 39~05982~;'),
  (14584, 19, 44, 4, 'Thou art my King, O God: command deliverances for Jacob.', '3~04428~, 5~0430~: 6~06680~ 7~03444~ 9~03290~.'),
  (2673, 2, 39, 4, 'They made shoulderpieces for it, to couple it together: by the two edges was it coupled together.', '1~06213~ 2~03802~ [7] 8~02266~: 11~08147~ 12~07098~ 13~07099~* 17~02266~.'),
  (12199, 15, 7, 17, 'That thou mayest buy speedily with this money bullocks, rams, lambs, with their meat offerings and their drink offerings, and offer them upon the altar of the house of your God which is in Jerusalem.', '0~06903~ 1~03606~ 3~07066~ 4~0629~ 6~01836~ 7~03702~ 8~08450~, 9~01798~, 10~0563~, 14~04504~ 18~05261~, 20~07127~ 21~01994~ 22~05922~ 24~04056~ 27~01005~ 30~0426~ [32] 34~03390~.'),
  (16333, 19, 145, 4, 'One generation shall praise thy works to another, and shall declare thy mighty acts.', '0~01755~ 1~01755~ 3~07623~ 5~04639~ 10~05046~ 13~01369~.'),
  (22079, 27, 11, 34, 'Now when they shall fall, they shall be holpen with a little help: but many shall cleave to them with flatteries.', '4~03782~, 8~05826~ 11~04592~ 12~05828~: 14~07227~ 16~03867~ 20~02519~.'),
  (28411, 46, 2, 1, 'And I, brethren, when I came to you, came not with excellency of speech or of wisdom, declaring unto you the testimony of God.', '&para; 1~2504~, 2~80~, 5~2064~ 6~4314~ 7~5209~, 8~2064~ 9~3756~ 10~2596~ 11~5247~ 13~3056~ 14~2228~ 16~4678~, 17~2605~ 19~5213~ 21~3142~ 23~2316~.'),
  (11892, 14, 32, 8, 'With him is an arm of flesh; but with us is the LORD our God to help us, and to fight our battles. And the people rested themselves upon the words of Hezekiah king of Judah.', '[2] 4~02220~ 6~01320~; [10] 12~03068~ 14~0430~ 16~05826~ 20~03898~ 22~04421~. 25~05971~ 26~05564~ 30~01697~ 32~03169~ 33~04428~ 35~03063~.'),
  (8538, 10, 19, 19, 'And said unto the king, Let not my lord impute iniquity unto me, neither do thou remember that which thy servant did perversely the day that my lord the king went out of Jerusalem, that the king should take it to his heart.', '1~0559~ 4~04428~, 8~0113~ 9~02803~ 10~05771~ 16~02142~ 20~05650~ 22~05753~ 24~03117~ 27~0113~ 29~04428~ 31~03318~ 33~03389~, 36~04428~ 38~07760~ 42~03820~.');
