  (28330, 45, 15, 11, 'And again, Praise the Lord, all ye Gentiles; and laud him, all ye people.', '0~2532~ 1~3825~, 2~134~ 4~2962~, 5~3956~ 6~134~ 7~1484~; 8~2532~ 9~1867~ 10~846~, 12~3956~ 13~2992~.'),
  (18720, 23, 52, 15, 'So shall he sprinkle many nations; the kings shall shut their mouths at him: for that which had not been told them shall they see; and that which they had not heard shall they consider.', '3~05137~ 4~07227~ 5~01471~; 7~04428~ 9~07092~ 11~06310~ [15] 20~05608~ 24~07200~; [26] 31~08085~ 34~0995~.'),
  (8896, 11, 5, 10, 'So Hiram gave Solomon cedar trees and fir trees according to all his desire.', '&para; 1~02438~ 2~05414~ 3~08010~ 4~0730~ 5~06086~ 7~01265~ 8~06086~ [9 10] 13~02656~.'),
  (454, 1, 18, 26, 'And the LORD said, If I find in Sodom fifty righteous within the city, then I will spare all the place for their sakes.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~, 6~04672~ 8~05467~ 9~02572~ 10~06662~ 11~08432~ 13~05892~, 17~05375~ 20~04725~'),
  (11922, 14, 33, 5, 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts of the house of the LORD.', '2~01129~ 3~04196~ 7~06635~ 9~08064~ 12~08147~ 13~02691~ 16~01004~ 19~03068~.'),
  (2252, 2, 26, 12, 'And the remnant that remaineth of the curtains of the tent, the half curtain that remaineth, shall hang over the backside of the tabernacle.', '2~05629~ 4~05736~ 7~03407~ 10~0168~, 12~02677~ 13~03407~ 15~05736~, 17~05628~ 20~0268~ 23~04908~.'),
  (30817, 66, 6, 8, 'And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death, and Hell followed with him. And power was given unto them over the fourth part of the earth, to kill with sword, and with hunger, and with death, and with the beasts of the earth.', '0~2532~ 2~1492~, 3~2532~ 4~2400~ 6~5515~ 7~2462~: 8~2532~ 9~846~ 10~3686~ 12~2521~ 13~1883~ 14~846~ 16~2288~, 17~2532~ 18~86~ 19~190~ 20~3326~ 21~846~. 22~2532~ 23~1849~ 25~1325~ 27~846~ 28~1909~ 31~5067~ 34~1093~, 36~615~ 37~1722~ 38~4501~, 39~2532~ 40~1722~ 41~3042~, 42~2532~ 43~1722~ 44~2288~, 45~2532~ 46~5259~ 48~2342~ 51~1093~.'),
  (29692, 53, 2, 15, 'Therefore, brethren, stand fast, and hold the traditions which ye have been taught, whether by word, or our epistle.', '0~3767~ 1~686~,* 2~80~, 4~4739~, 5~2532~ 6~2902~ 8~3862~ 9~3739~ 13~1321~, 14~1535~ 15~1223~ 16~3056~, 17~1223~ 18~1535~* 19~2257~ 20~1992~.'),
  (27428, 44, 13, 50, 'But the Jews stirred up the devout and honourable women, and the chief men of the city, and raised persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and expelled them out of their coasts.', '0~1161~ 2~2453~ 4~3951~ 6~4576~ 7~2532~ 8~2158~ 9~1135~, 10~2532~ 13~4413~ 16~4172~, 17~2532~ 18~1892~ 19~1375~ 20~1909~ 21~3972~ 22~2532~ 23~921~, 24~2532~ 25~1544~ 26~846~ 28~575~ 29~846~ 30~3725~.'),
  (13416, 18, 22, 18, 'Yet he filled their houses with good things: but the counsel of the wicked is far from me.', '2~04390~ 4~01004~ 6~02896~ [7] 10~06098~ 13~07563~ 15~07368~'),
  (10879, 13, 17, 8, 'And I have been with thee whithersoever thou hast walked, and have cut off all thine enemies from before thee, and have made thee a name like the name of the great men that are in the earth.', '9~01980~, 13~03772~ 16~0341~ 18~06440~ 22~06213~ 25~08034~ 28~08034~ 32~01419~ [34] 37~0776~.'),
  (28127, 45, 7, 20, 'Now if I do that I would not, it is no more I that do it, but sin that dwelleth in me.', '0~1161~ 1~3739~ 2~1487~ 3~4160~ 4~5124~ 5~1473~ 6~2309~ 7~3756~, 11~3765~ 12~2089~* 13~1473~ 15~2716~ 16~846~, 17~235~ 18~266~ 20~3611~ 21~1722~ 22~1698~.'),
  (6850, 7, 11, 14, 'And Jephthah sent messengers again unto the king of the children of Ammon:', '1~03316~ 2~07971~ 3~04397~ 4~03254~ 7~04428~ 10~01121~ 12~05983~:'),
  (6156, 6, 12, 20, 'The king of Shimronmeron, one; the king of Achshaph, one;', '1~04428~ 3~08112~, 4~0259~; 6~04428~ 8~0407~, 9~0259~;'),
  (26280, 43, 6, 8, 'One of his disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter''s brother, saith unto him,', '0~1520~ 1~1537~ 2~846~ 3~3101~, 4~406~, 5~4613~ 6~4074~ 7~80~, 8~3004~ 10~846~,'),
  (8156, 10, 5, 17, 'But when the Philistines heard that they had anointed David king over Israel, all the Philistines came up to seek David; and David heard of it, and went down to the hold.', '&para; 3~06430~ 4~08085~ 8~04886~ 9~01732~ 10~04428~ 12~03478~, 15~06430~ 17~05927~ 19~01245~ 20~01732~; 22~01732~ 23~08085~ [24 25] 28~03381~ 31~04686~.'),
  (12357, 16, 3, 21, 'After him repaired Meremoth the son of Urijah the son of Koz another piece, from the door of the house of Eliashib even to the end of the house of Eliashib.', '0~0310~ 2~02388~ 3~04822~ 5~01121~ 7~0223~ 9~01121~ 11~06976~ 12~08145~ 13~04060~, 16~06607~ 19~01004~ 21~0475~ 25~08503~ 28~01004~ 30~0475~.'),
  (24608, 41, 10, 9, 'What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder.', '0~3739~ 1~3767~ 2~2316~ 5~4801~, 6~5563~ 7~3361~ 8~444~ 10~5563~.'),
  (19460, 24, 21, 11, 'And touching the house of the king of Judah, say, Hear ye the word of the LORD;', '3~01004~ 6~04428~ 8~03063~, [9] 10~08085~ 13~01697~ 16~03068~;'),
  (22545, 32, 1, 5, 'Then the mariners were afraid, and cried every man unto his god, and cast forth the wares that were in the ship into the sea, to lighten it of them. But Jonah was gone down into the sides of the ship; and he lay, and was fast asleep.', '2~04419~ 4~03372~, 6~02199~ 8~0376~ 11~0430~, 14~02904~ 16~03627~ [18] 21~0591~ 24~03220~, 26~07043~ [27] 31~03124~ 34~03381~ 37~03411~ 40~05600~; 43~07901~, 47~07290~.'),
  (12242, 15, 8, 32, 'And we came to Jerusalem, and abode there three days.', '2~0935~ 4~03389~, 6~03427~ 8~07969~ 9~03117~.'),
  (9370, 11, 18, 21, 'And Elijah came unto all the people, and said, How long halt ye between two opinions? if the LORD be God, follow him: but if Baal, then follow him. And the people answered him not a word.', '&para; 1~0452~ 2~05066~ 6~05971~, 8~0559~, 10~05921~ 11~06452~ 14~08147~ 15~05587~? 18~03068~ [19] 20~0430~, 25~01168~, [26] 27~03212~ 28~0310~* 32~05971~ 33~06030~ 37~01697~.'),
  (3891, 4, 7, 36, 'On the fifth day Shelumiel the son of Zurishaddai, prince of the children of Simeon, did offer:', '2~02549~ 3~03117~ 4~08017~ 6~01121~ 8~06701~, 9~05387~ 12~01121~ 14~08095~, [15 16]'),
  (15077, 19, 74, 20, 'Have respect unto the covenant: for the dark places of the earth are full of the habitations of cruelty.', '1~05027~ 4~01285~: 7~04285~ 11~0776~ 13~04390~ 16~04999~ 18~02555~.'),
  (26365, 43, 7, 22, 'Moses therefore gave unto you circumcision; (not because it is of Moses, but of the fathers;) and ye on the sabbath day circumcise a man.', '0~3475~ 1~5124~ 2~1223~* 3~1325~ 5~5213~ 6~4061~; 7~3756~* 9~3754~ 11~2076~ 12~1537~ 13~3475~, 14~235~ 15~1537~ 17~3962~;) 18~2532~ 19~4059~ 20~1722~ 23~4521~ 24~4059~ 26~444~.'),
  (19432, 24, 20, 1, 'Now Pashur the son of Immer the priest, who was also chief governor in the house of the LORD, heard that Jeremiah prophesied these things.', '&para; 1~06583~ 3~01121~ 5~0564~ 7~03548~, [9] 11~06496~ 12~05057~ 15~01004~ 18~03068~, 19~08085~ 21~03414~ 22~05012~ 24~01697~.'),
  (12482, 16, 7, 53, 'The children of Bakbuk, the children of Hakupha, the children of Harhur,', '1~01121~ 3~01227~, 5~01121~ 7~02709~, 9~01121~ 11~02744~,'),
  (4736, 4, 32, 12, 'Save Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenezite, and Joshua the son of Nun: for they have wholly followed the LORD.', '1~03612~ 3~01121~ 5~03312~ 7~07074~, 9~03091~ 11~01121~ 13~05126~: 17~04390~ 18~0310~ 20~03068~.'),
  (10194, 12, 23, 21, 'And the king commanded all the people, saying, Keep the passover unto the LORD your God, as it is written in the book of this covenant.', '2~04428~ 3~06680~ 6~05971~, 7~0559~, 8~06213~ 10~06453~ 13~03068~ 15~0430~, [17 18] 19~03789~ 22~05612~ 25~01285~.'),
  (12570, 16, 10, 12, 'Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah,', '0~02139~, 1~08274~, 2~07645~,'),
  (26859, 43, 19, 19, 'And Pilate wrote a title, and put it on the cross. And the writing was, JESUS OF NAZARETH THE KING OF THE JEWS.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~1161~* 2~4091~ 3~1125~ 5~5102~, 6~2532~ 7~5087~ [8] 9~1909~ 11~4716~. 12~1161~ 14~1125~ 15~2258~, 16~2424~ 18~3480~ 20~935~ 23~2453~.'),
  (26232, 43, 5, 7, 'The impotent man answered him, Sir, I have no man, when the water is troubled, to put me into the pool: but while I am coming, another steppeth down before me.', '2~770~ 3~611~ 4~846~, 5~2962~, 7~2192~ 8~3756~ 9~444~, 10~3752~ 12~5204~ 14~5015~, 15~2443~ 16~906~ 17~3165~ 18~1519~ 20~2861~: 21~1161~ 22~3739~ 23~1722~* 24~1473~ 26~2064~, 27~243~ 29~2597~ 30~4253~ 31~1700~.'),
  (5568, 5, 25, 15, 'But thou shalt have a perfect and just weight, a perfect and just measure shalt thou have: that thy days may be lengthened in the land which the LORD thy God giveth thee.', '[0] 5~08003~ 7~06664~ 8~068~, 10~08003~ 12~06664~ 13~0374~ 19~03117~ 22~0748~ 25~0127~ 28~03068~ 30~0430~ 31~05414~'),
  (11028, 13, 24, 5, 'Thus were they divided by lot, one sort with another; for the governors of the sanctuary, and governors of the house of God, were of the sons of Eleazar, and of the sons of Ithamar.', '3~02505~ 5~01486~, 7~0428~ 9~0428~; 12~08269~ 15~06944~, 17~08269~ [18 20] 22~0430~, 26~01121~ 28~0499~, 32~01121~ 34~0385~.'),
  (13871, 18, 39, 28, 'She dwelleth and abideth on the rock, upon the crag of the rock, and the strong place.', '1~07931~ 3~03885~ 6~05553~, 9~08127~ 12~05553~, 16~04686~.'),
  (9143, 11, 11, 27, 'And this was the cause that he lifted up his hand against the king: Solomon built Millo, and repaired the breaches of the city of David his father.', '[2] 4~01697~ 8~07311~ [9] 10~03027~ 13~04428~: 14~08010~ 15~01129~ 16~04407~, [17] 18~05462~ 20~06556~ 23~05892~ 25~01732~ 27~01~.'),
  (9322, 11, 16, 31, 'And it came to pass, as if it had been a light thing for him to walk in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, that he took to wife Jezebel the daughter of Ethbaal king of the Zidonians, and went and served Baal, and worshipped him.', '12~07043~ 16~03212~ 19~02403~ 21~03379~ 23~01121~ 25~05028~, 28~03947~ 30~0802~ 31~0348~ 33~01323~ 35~0856~ 36~04428~ 39~06722~, 41~03212~ 43~05647~ 44~01168~, 46~07812~'),
  (25979, 42, 23, 30, 'Then shall they begin to say to the mountains, Fall on us; and to the hills, Cover us.', '0~5119~ 3~756~ 5~3004~ 8~3735~, 9~4098~ 10~1909~ 11~2248~; 12~2532~ 15~1015~, 16~2572~ 17~2248~.'),
  (18037, 23, 19, 24, 'In that day shall Israel be the third with Egypt and with Assyria, even a blessing in the midst of the land:', '2~03117~ 4~03478~ 7~07992~ 9~04714~ 12~0804~, [13] 15~01293~ 18~07130~ 21~0776~:'),
  (30233, 58, 12, 5, 'And ye have forgotten the exhortation which speaketh unto you as unto children, My son, despise not thou the chastening of the Lord, nor faint when thou art rebuked of him:', '0~2532~ 3~1585~ 5~3874~ 6~3748~ 7~1256~ 9~5213~ 10~5613~ 12~5207~, 13~3450~ 14~5207~, 15~3643~ 16~3361~ 17~3643~ 19~3809~ 22~2962~, 23~3366~ 24~1590~ 28~1651~ 29~5259~ 30~846~:'),
  (26617, 43, 12, 22, 'Philip cometh and telleth Andrew: and again Andrew and Philip tell Jesus.', '0~5376~ 1~2064~ 2~2532~ 3~3004~ 4~406~: 5~2532~ 6~3825~ 7~406~ 8~2532~ 9~5376~ 10~3004~ 11~2424~.'),
  (5969, 6, 6, 14, 'And the second day they compassed the city once, and returned into the camp: so they did six days.', '2~08145~ 3~03117~ 5~05437~ 7~05892~ 8~0259~ 9~06471~,* 11~07725~ 14~04264~: 17~06213~ 18~08337~ 19~03117~.'),
  (11401, 14, 9, 29, 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, first and last, are they not written in the book of Nathan the prophet, and in the prophecy of Ahijah the Shilonite, and in the visions of Iddo the seer against Jeroboam the son of Nebat?', '2~07605~ 5~01697~ 7~08010~, 8~07223~ 10~0314~, [11] 14~03789~ 17~01697~ 19~05416~ 21~05030~, 25~05016~ 27~0281~ 29~07888~, 33~02378~ 35~03260~ 37~02374~ 39~03379~ 41~01121~ 43~05028~?'),
  (21088, 26, 24, 23, 'And your tires shall be upon your heads, and your shoes upon your feet: ye shall not mourn nor weep; but ye shall pine away for your iniquities, and mourn one toward another.', '2~06287~ [3 4] 7~07218~, 10~05275~ 13~07272~: 17~05594~ 19~01058~; 24~04743~ 27~05771~, 29~05098~ 30~0376~ 32~0251~.'),
  (30642, 62, 5, 2, 'By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God, and keep his commandments.', '0~1722~ 1~5129~ 3~1097~ 4~3754~ 6~25~ 8~5043~ 10~2316~, 11~3752~ 13~25~ 14~2316~, 15~2532~ 16~5083~ 17~846~ 18~1785~.'),
  (23248, 40, 5, 4, 'Blessed are they that mourn: for they shall be comforted.', '0~3107~ [1] 4~3996~: 5~3754~ 6~846~ 9~3870~.'),
  (28292, 45, 13, 10, 'Love worketh no ill to his neighbour: therefore love is the fulfilling of the law.', '0~26~ 1~2038~ 2~3756~ 3~2556~ 6~4139~: 7~3767~ 8~26~ [9] 11~4138~ 14~3551~.'),
  (17023, 20, 21, 30, 'There is no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against the LORD.', '&para; [0 1] 3~02451~ 5~08394~ 7~06098~ 10~03068~.'),
  (25237, 42, 7, 30, 'But the Pharisees and lawyers rejected the counsel of God against themselves, being not baptized of him.', '0~1161~ 2~5330~ 3~2532~ 4~3544~ 5~114~ 7~1012~ 9~2316~ 10~1519~ 11~1438~, 12~907~ 13~3361~ 14~907~ 15~5259~ 16~846~.'),
  (25150, 42, 5, 31, 'And Jesus answering said unto them, They that are whole need not a physician; but they that are sick.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 3~2036~ 4~4314~ 5~846~, 9~5198~ 10~2192~ 11~5532~* 12~3756~ 14~2395~; 15~235~ 18~2192~ 19~2560~.'),
  (30433, 60, 2, 18, 'Servants, be subject to your masters with all fear; not only to the good and gentle, but also to the froward.', '0~3610~, [1] 2~5293~ [4] 5~1203~ 6~1722~ 7~3956~ 8~5401~; 9~3756~ 10~3440~ 13~18~ 14~2532~ 15~1933~, 16~235~ 17~2532~ 20~4646~.'),
  (10379, 13, 3, 10, 'And Solomon''s son was Rehoboam, Abia his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son,', '&para; 1~08010~ 2~01121~ [3] 4~07346~, 5~029~ 7~01121~, 8~0609~ 10~01121~, 11~03092~ 13~01121~,'),
  (21879, 27, 4, 33, 'The same hour was the thing fulfilled upon Nebuchadnezzar: and he was driven from men, and did eat grass as oxen, and his body was wet with the dew of heaven, till his hairs were grown like eagles'' feathers, and his nails like birds'' claws.', '2~08160~ 5~04406~ 6~05487~ 7~05922~ 8~05020~: 12~02957~ 13~04481~ 14~0606~, 17~0399~ 18~06211~ 20~08450~, 23~01655~ 25~06647~ 28~02920~ 30~08065~, 31~05705~ 33~08177~ 35~07236~ 37~05403~ [38] 41~02953~ 43~06853~ [44]'),
  (3174, 3, 15, 1, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and to Aaron, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~ 8~0175~, 9~0559~,'),
  (28919, 47, 6, 5, 'In stripes, in imprisonments, in tumults, in labours, in watchings, in fastings;', '0~1722~ 1~4127~, 2~1722~ 3~5438~, 4~1722~ 5~181~, 6~1722~ 7~2873~, 8~1722~ 9~70~, 10~1722~ 11~3521~;'),
  (2565, 2, 35, 29, 'The children of Israel brought a willing offering unto the LORD, every man and woman, whose heart made them willing to bring for all manner of work, which the LORD had commanded to be made by the hand of Moses.', '1~01121~ 3~03478~ 4~0935~ 7~05071~ 10~03068~, 12~0376~ 14~0802~, 15~0834~ 16~03820~ 19~05068~ 21~0935~ 26~04399~, 29~03068~ 31~06680~ 34~06213~ 37~03027~ 39~04872~.'),
  (22617, 33, 2, 13, 'The breaker is come up before them: they have broken up, and have passed through the gate, and are gone out by it: and their king shall pass before them, and the LORD on the head of them.', '1~06555~ 4~05927~ 5~06440~ 10~06555~, 14~05674~ 16~08179~, 20~03318~ 25~04428~ 27~05674~ 28~06440~ 32~03068~ 35~07218~'),
  (27846, 44, 26, 7, 'Unto which promise our twelve tribes, instantly serving God day and night, hope to come. For which hope''s sake, king Agrippa, I am accused of the Jews.', '0~1519~ 1~3739~ [2] 3~2257~ 5~1429~, 6~1616~ 7~1722~* 8~3000~ [9] 10~2250~ 11~2532~ 12~3571~, 13~1679~ 15~2658~. 16~4012~ 17~3739~ 19~1680~, 20~935~ 21~67~, 24~1458~ 25~5259~ 27~2453~.'),
  (16062, 19, 119, 155, 'Salvation is far from the wicked: for they seek not thy statutes.', '&para; 0~03444~ [1] 2~07350~ 5~07563~: 8~01875~ 11~02706~.'),
  (11711, 14, 24, 25, 'And when they were departed from him, (for they left him in great diseases,) his own servants conspired against him for the blood of the sons of Jehoiada the priest, and slew him on his bed, and he died: and they buried him in the city of David, but they buried him not in the sepulchres of the kings.', '4~03212~ 9~05800~ 12~07227~ 13~04251~,) 16~05650~ 17~07194~ 22~01818~ 25~01121~ 27~03077~ 29~03548~, 31~02026~ 35~04296~, 38~04191~: 41~06912~ 45~05892~ 47~01732~, 50~06912~ 55~06913~ 58~04428~.'),
  (24853, 41, 15, 16, 'And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium; and they call together the whole band.', '0~1161~ 2~4757~ 3~520~ 4~846~ 5~520~ 6~2080~ 8~833~, 9~3603~ 10~4232~; 11~2532~ 14~4779~ 16~3650~ 17~4686~.'),
  (22141, 28, 3, 4, 'For the children of Israel shall abide many days without a king, and without a prince, and without a sacrifice, and without an image, and without an ephod, and without teraphim:', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 6~03427~ 7~07227~ 8~03117~ 11~04428~, 15~08269~, 19~02077~, 23~04676~, 27~0646~, [29] 30~08655~:'),
  (3461, 3, 24, 10, 'And the son of an Israelitish woman, whose father was an Egyptian, went out among the children of Israel: and this son of the Israelitish woman and a man of Israel strove together in the camp;', '&para; 2~01121~ 5~03482~ 6~0802~, 8~01121~ [9] 11~04713~ 12~0376~,* 14~03318~ 15~08432~ 17~01121~ 19~03481~ 20~03478~:* 23~01121~ 26~03482~ [27] 30~0376~ 32~03478~ 34~05327~ 37~04264~;'),
  (29628, 52, 4, 9, 'But as touching brotherly love ye need not that I write unto you: for ye yourselves are taught of God to love one another.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~4012~ 4~5360~ 6~2192~ 7~5532~* 8~3756~ 11~1125~ 13~5213~: 14~1063~ 15~5210~ 16~846~ 17~2075~ 20~2312~ 21~1519~ 22~25~ 24~240~.'),
  (8208, 10, 7, 21, 'For thy word''s sake, and according to thine own heart, hast thou done all these great things, to make thy servant know them.', '2~01697~ 9~03820~, 12~06213~ 16~01420~, 20~05650~ 21~03045~ [22]'),
  (29161, 48, 4, 14, 'And my temptation which was in my flesh ye despised not, nor rejected; but received me as an angel of God, even as Christ Jesus.', '0~2532~ 1~3450~ 2~3986~ 5~1722~ 6~3450~ 7~4561~ 9~1848~ 10~3756~, 11~3761~ 12~1609~; 13~235~ 14~1209~ 15~3165~ 16~5613~ 18~32~ 20~2316~, [21] 22~5613~ 23~5547~ 24~2424~.'),
  (24060, 40, 25, 42, 'For I was an hungered, and ye gave me no meat: I was thirsty, and ye gave me no drink:', '0~1063~ 4~3983~, 5~2532~ 7~1325~ 8~3427~ 9~3756~ 10~5315~: 13~1372~, 14~2532~ 16~4222~ 17~3165~ 18~3756~ 19~4222~:'),
  (18811, 23, 59, 2, 'But your iniquities have separated between you and your God, and your sins have hid his face from you, that he will not hear.', '2~05771~ 4~0914~ 5~0996~ 9~0430~, 12~02403~ 14~05641~ [15] 16~06440~ 23~08085~.'),
  (12501, 16, 7, 72, 'And that which the rest of the people gave was twenty thousand drams of gold, and two thousand pound of silver, and threescore and seven priests'' garments.', '[1] 4~07611~ 7~05971~ 8~05414~ [9] 10~08147~ 11~07239~ 12~01871~ 14~02091~, 17~0505~ 18~04488~ 20~03701~, 22~08346~ 24~07651~ 25~03548~ 26~03801~.'),
  (2975, 3, 9, 17, 'And he brought the meat offering, and took an handful thereof, and burnt it upon the altar, beside the burnt sacrifice of the morning.', '2~07126~ 5~04503~, 7~04390~ 9~03709~ 12~06999~ [13] 16~04196~, 17~0905~ 20~05930~ 23~01242~.'),
  (24202, 40, 27, 63, 'Saying, Sir, we remember that that deceiver said, while he was yet alive, After three days I will rise again.', '0~3004~, 1~2962~, 3~3415~ 4~3754~ 5~1565~ 6~4108~ 7~2036~, 11~2089~ 12~2198~, 13~3326~ 14~5140~ 15~2250~ 19~1453~.'),
  (19315, 24, 14, 13, 'Then said I, Ah, Lord GOD! behold, the prophets say unto them, Ye shall not see the sword, neither shall ye have famine; but I will give you assured peace in this place.', '1~0559~ 3~0162~, 4~0136~ 5~03069~! 8~05030~ 9~0559~ 15~07200~ 17~02719~, 22~07458~; 26~05414~ 28~0571~ 29~07965~ 32~04725~.'),
  (12560, 16, 10, 2, 'Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah,', '0~08304~, 1~05838~, 2~03414~,'),
  (10097, 12, 19, 28, 'Because thy rage against me and thy tumult is come up into mine ears, therefore I will put my hook in thy nose, and my bridle in thy lips, and I will turn thee back by the way by which thou camest.', '2~07264~ 7~07600~ 10~05927~ 13~0241~, 17~07760~ 19~02397~ 22~0639~, 25~04964~ 28~08193~, 34~07725~ 37~01870~ 41~0935~.'),
  (25882, 42, 22, 4, 'And he went his way, and communed with the chief priests and captains, how he might betray him unto them.', '0~2532~ 4~565~, 7~4814~ 10~749~ 11~2532~ 12~4755~, 13~4459~ 16~3860~ 17~846~ 19~846~.'),
  (26932, 43, 21, 18, 'Verily, verily, I say unto thee, When thou wast young, thou girdedst thyself, and walkedst whither thou wouldest: but when thou shalt be old, thou shalt stretch forth thy hands, and another shall gird thee, and carry thee whither thou wouldest not.', '0~281~, 1~281~, 3~3004~ 5~4671~, 6~3753~ 8~2258~ 9~3501~, 11~2224~ 12~4572~, 13~2532~ 14~4043~ 15~3699~ 17~2309~: 18~1161~ 19~3752~ 23~1095~, 27~1614~ 28~4675~ 29~5495~, 30~2532~ 31~243~ 33~2224~ 34~4571~, 35~2532~ 36~5342~ [37] 38~3699~ 40~2309~ 41~3756~.'),
  (13825, 18, 38, 23, 'Which I have reserved against the time of trouble, against the day of battle and war?', '3~02820~ 6~06256~ 8~06862~, 11~03117~ 13~07128~ 15~04421~?'),
  (22204, 28, 8, 1, 'Set the trumpet to thy mouth. He shall come as an eagle against the house of the LORD, because they have transgressed my covenant, and trespassed against my law.', '&para; [0] 2~07782~ 5~02441~. [6 8] 11~05404~ 14~01004~ 17~03068~, 21~05674~ 23~01285~, 25~06586~ 28~08451~.'),
  (11063, 13, 25, 9, 'Now the first lot came forth for Asaph to Joseph: the second to Gedaliah, who with his brethren and sons were twelve:', '2~07223~ 3~01486~ 5~03318~ 7~0623~ 9~03130~: 11~08145~ 13~01436~, 17~0251~ 19~01121~ [20] 21~06240~ 22~08147~:*'),
  (19276, 24, 13, 1, 'Thus saith the LORD unto me, Go and get thee a linen girdle, and put it upon thy loins, and put it not in water.', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~ 6~01980~ 8~07069~ 11~06593~ 12~0232~, 14~07760~ 18~04975~, 20~0935~ 24~04325~.'),
  (9858, 12, 11, 21, 'Seven years old was Jehoash when he began to reign.', '0~07651~ 1~08141~ 2~01121~ [3] 4~03060~ 9~04427~.'),
  (20838, 26, 17, 4, 'He cropped off the top of his young twigs, and carried it into a land of traffic; he set it in a city of merchants.', '2~06998~ 4~07218~ 8~03242~, 10~0935~ 14~0776~ 16~03667~; 18~07760~ 22~05892~ 24~07402~.'),
  (26199, 43, 4, 28, 'The woman then left her waterpot, and went her way into the city, and saith to the men,', '1~1135~ 2~3767~ 3~863~ 4~846~ 5~5201~, 6~2532~ 9~565~ 10~1519~ 12~4172~, 13~2532~ 14~3004~ 17~444~,'),
  (7310, 9, 4, 6, 'And when the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said, What meaneth the noise of this great shout in the camp of the Hebrews? And they understood that the ark of the LORD was come into the camp.', '3~06430~ 4~08085~ 6~06963~ 9~08643~, 11~0559~, [13] 15~06963~ 18~01419~ 19~08643~ 22~04264~ 25~05680~? 28~03045~ 31~0727~ 34~03068~ 36~0935~ 39~04264~.'),
  (1923, 2, 14, 29, 'But the children of Israel walked upon dry land in the midst of the sea; and the waters were a wall unto them on their right hand, and on their left.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~01980~ 7~03004~ [8] 11~08432~ 14~03220~; 17~04325~ [18] 20~02346~ 26~03225~, 30~08040~.'),
  (3751, 4, 4, 3, 'From thirty years old and upward even until fifty years old, all that enter into the host, to do the work in the tabernacle of the congregation.', '1~07970~ 2~08141~ 3~01121~ 5~04605~ 8~02572~ 9~08141~ 10~01121~, 13~0935~ 16~06635~, 18~06213~ 20~04399~ 23~0168~ 26~04150~.'),
  (25662, 42, 16, 28, 'For I have five brethren; that he may testify unto them, lest they also come into this place of torment.', '0~1063~ 2~2192~ 3~4002~ 4~80~; 5~3704~ 8~1263~ 10~846~, 11~3363~ 12~846~ 13~2532~ 14~2064~ 15~1519~ 16~5126~ 17~5117~ 19~931~.'),
  (22041, 27, 10, 17, 'For how can the servant of this my lord talk with this my lord? for as for me, straightway there remained no strength in me, neither is there breath left in me.', '1~01963~ 2~03201~ 4~05650~ 8~0113~ 9~01696~ 13~0113~? 18~06258~ 20~05975~ 22~03581~ 28~05397~ 29~07604~'),
  (16981, 20, 20, 18, 'Every purpose is established by counsel: and with good advice make war.', '&para; [0] 1~04284~ 3~03559~ 5~06098~: 9~08458~ 10~06213~ 11~04421~.'),
  (26202, 43, 4, 31, 'In the mean while his disciples prayed him, saying, Master, eat.', '0~1161~* 1~1722~ 3~3342~ 6~3101~ 7~2065~ 8~846~, 9~3004~, 10~4461~, 11~5315~.'),
  (10828, 13, 15, 29, 'And it came to pass, as the ark of the covenant of the LORD came to the city of David, that Michal the daughter of Saul looking out at a window saw king David dancing and playing: and she despised him in her heart.', '[5] 7~0727~ 10~01285~ 13~03068~ 14~0935~ 17~05892~ 19~01732~, 21~04324~ 23~01323~ 25~07586~ 27~08259~ 30~02474~ 31~07200~ 32~04428~ 33~01732~ 34~07540~ 36~07832~: 39~0959~ 43~03820~.'),
  (1893, 2, 13, 21, 'And the LORD went before them by day in a pillar of a cloud, to lead them the way; and by night in a pillar of fire, to give them light; to go by day and night:', '2~03068~ 3~01980~ 4~06440~ 7~03119~ 10~05982~ 13~06051~, 15~05148~ 18~01870~; 21~03915~ 24~05982~ 26~0784~, 30~0215~; 32~03212~ 34~03119~ 36~03915~:'),
  (23845, 40, 21, 9, 'And the multitudes that went before, and that followed, cried, saying, Hosanna to the son of David: Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord; Hosanna in the highest.', '0~1161~ 2~3793~ 5~4254~, 6~2532~ 8~190~, 9~2896~, 10~3004~, 11~5614~ 14~5207~ 16~1138~: 17~2127~ [18] 21~2064~ 22~1722~ 24~3686~ 27~2962~; 28~5614~ 29~1722~ 31~5310~.'),
  (17499, 21, 9, 15, 'Now there was found in it a poor wise man, and he by his wisdom delivered the city; yet no man remembered that same poor man.', '3~04672~ 7~04542~ 8~02450~ 9~0376~, 14~02451~ 15~04422~ 17~05892~; 20~0120~ 21~02142~ 24~04542~ 25~0376~.'),
  (21983, 27, 8, 13, 'Then I heard one saint speaking, and another saint said unto that certain saint which spake, How long shall be the vision concerning the daily sacrifice, and the transgression of desolation, to give both the sanctuary and the host to be trodden under foot?', '2~08085~ 3~0259~ 4~06918~ 5~01696~, 7~0259~ 8~06918~ 9~0559~ 12~06422~ [13] 15~01696~, [18 19] 21~02377~ [22] 24~08548~ [25] 28~06588~ 30~08074~, 32~05414~ 35~06944~ 38~06635~ 43~04823~?');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (25976, 42, 23, 27, 'And there followed him a great company of people, and of women, which also bewailed and lamented him.', '0~1161~ 2~190~ 3~846~ 5~4183~ 6~4128~ 8~2992~, 9~2532~ 11~1135~, 12~3739~ 13~2532~ 14~2875~ 15~2532~ 16~2354~ 17~846~.'),
  (4768, 4, 33, 2, 'And Moses wrote their goings out according to their journeys by the commandment of the LORD: and these are their journeys according to their goings out.', '1~04872~ 2~03789~ 5~04161~ 9~04550~ 12~06310~ 15~03068~: [18] 20~04550~ 25~04161~.'),
  (5396, 5, 18, 6, 'And if a Levite come from any of thy gates out of all Israel, where he sojourned, and come with all the desire of his mind unto the place which the LORD shall choose;', '3~03881~ 4~0935~ 6~0259~ 9~08179~ 13~03478~, 16~01481~, 18~0935~ 22~0185~ 25~05315~ 28~04725~ 31~03068~ 33~0977~;'),
  (16158, 19, 131, 1, 'A Song of degrees of David. LORD, my heart is not haughty, nor mine eyes lofty: neither do I exercise myself in great matters, or in things too high for me.', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3~04609~ 5] 5~01732~ 6~03068~, 8~03820~ 11~01361~, 14~05869~ 15~07311~: 19~01980~ 23~01419~, 28~06381~'),
  (21437, 26, 38, 3, 'And say, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Behold, I am against thee, O Gog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal:', '1~0559~, 3~0559~ 5~0136~ 6~03069~; [9] 13~01463~, 15~07218~ 16~05387~ 18~04902~ 20~08422~:'),
  (25434, 42, 11, 17, 'But he, knowing their thoughts, said unto them, Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and a house divided against a house falleth.', '0~1161~ 1~846~, 2~1492~ 3~846~ 4~1270~, 5~2036~ 7~846~, 8~3956~ 9~932~ 10~1266~ 11~1909~ 12~1438~ 16~2049~; 17~2532~ 19~3624~ [20] 21~1909~ 23~3624~ 24~4098~.'),
  (21357, 26, 35, 4, 'I will lay thy cities waste, and thou shalt be desolate, and thou shalt know that I am the LORD.', '2~07760~ 4~05892~ 5~02723~, 10~08077~, 14~03045~ [17] 19~03068~.'),
  (21524, 26, 40, 38, 'And the chambers and the entries thereof were by the posts of the gates, where they washed the burnt offering.', '2~03957~ 5~06607~ [7] 10~0352~ 13~08179~, 16~01740~ 19~05930~.'),
  (7729, 9, 19, 16, 'And when the messengers were come in, behold, there was an image in the bed, with a pillow of goats'' hair for his bolster.', '3~04397~ 6~0935~, [8 9] 11~08655~ 14~04296~, 17~03523~ 19~05795~ [20] 23~04763~.'),
  (208, 1, 9, 2, 'And the fear of you and the dread of you shall be upon every beast of the earth, and upon every fowl of the air, upon all that moveth upon the earth, and upon all the fishes of the sea; into your hand are they delivered.', '4~04172~ 9~02844~ 14~02416~ 17~0776~, 21~05775~ 24~08064~, 28~07430~ [29] 31~0127~, 36~01709~ 39~03220~; 42~03027~ 45~05414~.'),
  (15191, 19, 78, 69, 'And he built his sanctuary like high palaces, like the earth which he hath established for ever.', '2~01129~ 4~04720~ 6~07311~ [7] 10~0776~ 14~03245~ 16~05769~.'),
  (11731, 14, 25, 18, 'And Joash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, The thistle that was in Lebanon sent to the cedar that was in Lebanon, saying, Give thy daughter to my son to wife: and there passed by a wild beast that was in Lebanon, and trode down the thistle.', '1~03101~ 2~04428~ 4~03478~ 5~07971~ 7~0558~ 8~04428~ 10~03063~, 11~0559~, 13~02336~ [15] 17~03844~ 18~07971~ 21~0730~ [23] 25~03844~, 26~0559~, 27~05414~ 29~01323~ 32~01121~ 34~0802~: 38~05674~ 40~07704~ 41~02416~ [43] 45~03844~, 48~07429~ 50~02336~.'),
  (8822, 11, 2, 44, 'The king said moreover to Shimei, Thou knowest all the wickedness which thine heart is privy to, that thou didst to David my father: therefore the LORD shall return thy wickedness upon thine own head;', '1~04428~ 2~0559~ 5~08096~, 7~03045~ 10~07451~ 13~03824~ 16~03045~, 19~06213~ 21~01732~ 23~01~: 26~03068~ 28~07725~ 30~07451~ 34~07218~;'),
  (16108, 19, 123, 1, 'A Song of degrees. Unto thee lift I up mine eyes, O thou that dwellest in the heavens.', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3] 3~04609~ 8~05375~ 10~05869~, 14~03427~ 17~08064~.'),
  (23647, 40, 15, 4, 'For God commanded, saying, Honour thy father and mother: and, He that curseth father or mother, let him die the death.', '0~1063~ 1~2316~ 2~1781~, 3~3004~, 4~5091~ 5~4675~ 6~3962~ 7~2532~ 8~3384~: 9~2532~, 12~2551~ 13~3962~ 14~2228~ 15~3384~, 18~5053~ 20~2288~.'),
  (393, 1, 16, 8, 'And he said, Hagar, Sarai''s maid, whence camest thou? and whither wilt thou go? And she said, I flee from the face of my mistress Sarai.', '2~0559~, 3~01904~, 4~08297~ 5~08198~, 6~0335~ 8~0935~? 13~03212~? 16~0559~, 18~01272~ 21~06440~ 24~01404~ 25~08297~.'),
  (13108, 18, 10, 13, 'And these things hast thou hid in thine heart: I know that this is with thee.', '[2] 5~06845~ 8~03824~: 10~03045~ [13]'),
  (3521, 3, 25, 47, 'And if a sojourner or stranger wax rich by thee, and thy brother that dwelleth by him wax poor, and sell himself unto the stranger or sojourner by thee, or to the stock of the stranger''s family:', '3~01616~ 5~08453~ 7~05381~ 9~03027~, 12~0251~ [13 14] 18~04134~, 20~04376~ 24~01616~ [25] 26~08453~ 32~06133~ 35~01616~ 36~04940~:'),
  (9899, 12, 13, 20, 'And Elisha died, and they buried him. And the bands of the Moabites invaded the land at the coming in of the year.', '&para; 1~0477~ 2~04191~, 5~06912~ 9~01416~ 12~04124~ 13~0935~ 15~0776~ 19~0935~ 22~08141~.'),
