VALUES
  (7391, 9, 8, 15, 'And he will take the tenth of your seed, and of your vineyards, and give to his officers, and to his servants.', '5~06237~ 8~02233~, 12~03754~, 14~05414~ 17~05631~, 21~05650~.'),
  (22388, 30, 1, 15, 'And their king shall go into captivity, he and his princes together, saith the LORD.', '2~04428~ 4~01980~ 6~01473~, 10~08269~ 11~03162~, 12~0559~ 14~03068~.'),
  (10038, 12, 18, 6, 'For he clave to the LORD, and departed not from following him, but kept his commandments, which the LORD commanded Moses.', '2~01692~ 5~03068~, [6] 7~05493~ 10~0310~ 13~08104~ 15~04687~, 18~03068~ 19~06680~ 20~04872~.'),
  (19905, 24, 38, 1, 'Then Shephatiah the son of Mattan, and Gedaliah the son of Pashur, and Jucal the son of Shelemiah, and Pashur the son of Malchiah, heard the words that Jeremiah had spoken unto all the people, saying,', '&para; 1~08203~ 3~01121~ 5~04977~, 7~01436~ 9~01121~ 11~06583~, 13~03116~ 15~01121~ 17~08018~, 19~06583~ 21~01121~ 23~04441~, 24~08085~ 26~01697~ 28~03414~ 30~01696~ 34~05971~, 35~0559~,'),
  (20506, 26, 2, 5, 'And they, whether they will hear, or whether they will forbear, (for they are a rebellious house,) yet shall know that there hath been a prophet among them.', '5~08085~, 10~02308~, [13] 15~04805~ 16~01004~,) 19~03045~ 25~05030~ 26~08432~'),
  (28091, 45, 6, 7, 'For he that is dead is freed from sin.', '0~1063~ 4~599~ 6~1344~ 7~575~ 8~266~.'),
  (27630, 44, 19, 29, 'And the whole city was filled with confusion: and having caught Gaius and Aristarchus, men of Macedonia, Paul''s companions in travel, they rushed with one accord into the theatre.', '0~2532~ 2~3650~ 3~4172~ 5~4130~ 7~4799~: 8~5037~ 10~4884~ 11~1050~ 12~2532~ 13~708~, 16~3110~, 17~3972~ 20~4898~, 22~3729~ 25~3661~ 26~1519~ 28~2302~.'),
  (4511, 4, 26, 17, 'Of Arod, the family of the Arodites: of Areli, the family of the Arelites.', '1~0720~, 3~04940~ 6~0722~: 8~0692~, 10~04940~ 13~0692~.'),
  (444, 1, 18, 16, 'And the men rose up from thence, and looked toward Sodom: and Abraham went with them to bring them on the way.', '&para; 2~0582~ 4~06965~ 8~08259~ 9~06440~ 10~05467~: 12~085~ 13~01980~ 21~07971~.'),
  (11804, 14, 29, 4, 'And he brought in the priests and the Levites, and gathered them together into the east street,', '3~0935~ 5~03548~ 8~03881~, 12~0622~ 15~04217~ 16~07339~,'),
  (3841, 4, 6, 13, 'And this is the law of the Nazarite, when the days of his separation are fulfilled: he shall be brought unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation:', '[2] 4~08451~ 7~05139~, 8~03117~ 10~03117~ 13~05145~ 15~04390~: 19~0935~ 22~06607~ 25~0168~ 28~04150~:'),
  (17856, 23, 9, 18, 'For wickedness burneth as the fire: it shall devour the briers and thorns, and shall kindle in the thickets of the forest, and they shall mount up like the lifting up of smoke.', '1~07564~ 2~01197~ 5~0784~: 8~0398~ 10~08068~ 12~07898~, 15~03341~ 18~05442~ 21~03293~, 26~055~ [27] 30~01348~ 32~06227~.'),
  (2749, 2, 40, 37, 'But if the cloud were not taken up, then they journeyed not till the day that it was taken up.', '3~06051~ 7~05927~, 10~05265~ 14~03117~ 19~05927~.'),
  (25822, 42, 20, 29, 'There were therefore seven brethren: and the first took a wife, and died without children.', '1~2258~ 2~3767~ 3~2033~ 4~80~: 5~2532~ 7~4413~ 8~2983~ 10~1135~, 12~599~ 14~815~.'),
  (15332, 19, 88, 15, 'I am afflicted and ready to die from my youth up: while I suffer thy terrors I am distracted.', '[1] 2~06041~ 6~01478~ [8] 9~05290~ [11] 13~05375~ 15~0367~ 18~06323~.'),
  (8093, 10, 3, 5, 'And the sixth, Ithream, by Eglah David''s wife. These were born to David in Hebron.', '2~08345~, 3~03507~, 5~05698~ 6~01732~ 7~0802~. 10~03205~ 12~01732~ 14~02275~.'),
  (4368, 4, 21, 23, 'And Sihon would not suffer Israel to pass through his border: but Sihon gathered all his people together, and went out against Israel into the wilderness: and he came to Jahaz, and fought against Israel.', '1~05511~ 4~05414~ 5~03478~ 7~05674~ 10~01366~: 12~05511~ 13~0622~ 16~05971~ 17~0622~, 20~03318~ 21~07125~ 22~03478~ 25~04057~: 28~0935~ 30~03096~, 32~03898~ 34~03478~.'),
  (20685, 26, 11, 21, 'But as for them whose heart walketh after the heart of their detestable things and their abominations, I will recompense their way upon their own heads, saith the Lord GOD.', '[1 3] 5~03820~ 6~01980~ 9~03820~ 13~08251~ 16~08441~, 19~05414~ 21~01870~ 25~07218~, 26~05002~ 28~0136~ 29~03069~.'),
  (6550, 7, 1, 34, 'And the Amorites forced the children of Dan into the mountain: for they would not suffer them to come down to the valley:', '2~0567~ 3~03905~ 5~01121~ 7~01835~ 10~02022~: 15~05414~ 19~03381~ 22~06010~:'),
  (7948, 9, 27, 11, 'And David saved neither man nor woman alive, to bring tidings to Gath, saying, Lest they should tell on us, saying, So did David, and so will be his manner all the while he dwelleth in the country of the Philistines.', '1~01732~ 2~02421~ 4~0376~ 6~0802~ 7~02421~, 9~0935~ [10] 12~01661~, 13~0559~, 17~05046~ 20~0559~, 22~06213~ 23~01732~, [26 27] 29~04941~ 32~03117~ 34~03427~ 37~07704~ 40~06430~.'),
  (15335, 19, 88, 18, 'Lover and friend hast thou put far from me, and mine acquaintance into darkness.', '0~0157~ 2~07453~ 6~07368~ [9] 11~03045~ 13~04285~.'),
  (4428, 4, 23, 7, 'And he took up his parable, and said, Balak the king of Moab hath brought me from Aram, out of the mountains of the east, saying, Come, curse me Jacob, and come, defy Israel.', '3~05375~ 5~04912~, 7~0559~, 8~01111~ 10~04428~ 12~04124~ 14~05148~ 17~0758~, 21~02042~ 24~06924~, [25] 26~03212~, 27~0779~ 29~03290~, 31~03212~, 32~02194~ 33~03478~.'),
  (15882, 19, 118, 4, 'Let them now that fear the LORD say, that his mercy endureth for ever.', '4~03373~ 6~03068~ 7~0559~, 10~02617~ [11] 13~05769~.'),
  (30532, 61, 2, 16, 'But was rebuked for his iniquity: the dumb ass speaking with man''s voice forbad the madness of the prophet.', '0~1161~ 1~2192~ 2~1649~ 4~2398~ 5~3892~: 7~880~ 8~5268~ 9~5350~ 10~1722~ 11~444~ 12~5456~ 13~2967~ 15~3913~ 18~4396~.'),
  (4249, 4, 16, 50, 'And Aaron returned unto Moses unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation: and the plague was stayed.', '1~0175~ 2~07725~ 4~04872~ 7~06607~ 10~0168~ 13~04150~: 16~04046~ 18~06113~.'),
  (24891, 41, 16, 7, 'But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter that he goeth before you into Galilee: there shall ye see him, as he said unto you.', '0~235~ 3~5217~, 4~2036~ 5~846~ 6~3101~ 7~2532~ 8~4074~ 9~3754~ 12~4254~ 13~5209~ 14~1519~ 15~1056~: 16~1563~ 19~3700~ 20~846~, 21~2531~ 23~2036~ 25~5213~.'),
  (6907, 7, 13, 16, 'And the angel of the LORD said unto Manoah, Though thou detain me, I will not eat of thy bread: and if thou wilt offer a burnt offering, thou must offer it unto the LORD. For Manoah knew not that he was an angel of the LORD.', '2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~0559~ 8~04495~, 11~06113~ 16~0398~ 19~03899~: 21~0518~ 24~06213~ 27~05930~, 30~05927~ 34~03068~. 36~04495~ 37~03045~ [41] 43~04397~ 46~03068~.'),
  (30391, 60, 1, 1, 'Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the strangers scattered throughout Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,', '&para; 0~4074~, 2~652~ 4~2424~ 5~5547~, 8~3927~ 9~1290~ 11~4195~, 12~1053~, 13~2587~, 14~773~, 15~2532~ 16~978~,'),
  (1660, 2, 5, 23, 'For since I came to Pharaoh to speak in thy name, he hath done evil to this people; neither hast thou delivered thy people at all.', '3~0935~ 5~06547~ 7~01696~ 10~08034~, 14~07489~ 17~05971~; 21~05337~ 23~05971~ 25~05337~.'),
  (22770, 35, 2, 13, 'Behold, is it not of the LORD of hosts that the people shall labour in the very fire, and the people shall weary themselves for very vanity?', '[1 2] 6~03068~ 8~06635~ 11~05971~ 13~03021~ 16~01767~ 17~0784~, 20~03816~ 22~03286~ 25~01767~ 26~07385~?'),
  (15613, 19, 104, 33, 'I will sing unto the LORD as long as I live: I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.', '2~07891~ 5~03068~ 10~02416~: 13~02167~ 17~0430~ 22~05750~.'),
  (14515, 19, 38, 16, 'For I said, Hear me, lest otherwise they should rejoice over me: when my foot slippeth, they magnify themselves against me.', '2~0559~, [3 4] [6] 9~08055~ 14~07272~ 15~04131~, 17~01431~ [18]'),
  (22431, 30, 4, 12, 'Therefore thus will I do unto thee, O Israel: and because I will do this unto thee, prepare to meet thy God, O Israel.', '4~06213~ 8~03478~: [9] 10~06118~ 13~06213~ 17~03559~ 19~07125~ 21~0430~, 23~03478~.'),
  (9520, 11, 22, 32, 'And it came to pass, when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, that they said, Surely it is the king of Israel. And they turned aside to fight against him: and Jehoshaphat cried out.', '7~08269~ 10~07393~ 11~07200~ 12~03092~, 15~0559~, [18] 20~04428~ 22~03478~. 26~05493~ 28~03898~ 32~03092~ 34~02199~.'),
  (29926, 56, 2, 2, 'That the aged men be sober, grave, temperate, sound in faith, in charity, in patience.', '3~4246~ 4~1511~ 5~3524~, 6~4586~, 7~4998~, 8~5198~ 10~4102~, 12~26~, 14~5281~.'),
  (17324, 20, 31, 31, 'Give her of the fruit of her hands; and let her own works praise her in the gates.', '0~05414~ 4~06529~ 7~03027~; 12~04639~ 13~01984~ 17~08179~.'),
  (17716, 23, 2, 22, 'Cease ye from man, whose breath is in his nostrils: for wherein is he to be accounted of?', '0~02308~ 3~0120~, 5~05397~ [6] 9~0639~: 17~02803~?'),
  (15725, 19, 107, 17, 'Fools because of their transgression, and because of their iniquities, are afflicted.', '&para; 0~0191~ 1~01870~ 4~06588~, 9~05771~, 11~06031~.'),
  (22305, 29, 1, 5, 'Awake, ye drunkards, and weep; and howl, all ye drinkers of wine, because of the new wine, for it is cut off from your mouth.', '0~06974~, 2~07910~, 4~01058~; 6~03213~, 9~08354~ 11~03196~, 16~06071~; 21~03772~ 24~06310~.'),
  (25375, 42, 9, 62, 'And Jesus said unto him, No man, having put his hand to the plow, and looking back, is fit for the kingdom of God.', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 4~846~, 6~3762~, 8~1911~ 9~846~ 10~5495~ 11~1909~ 13~723~, 14~2532~ 15~991~ 16~3694~ 17~1519~,* 18~2076~ 19~2111~ 20~1519~ 22~932~ 24~2316~.'),
  (9084, 11, 9, 25, 'And three times in a year did Solomon offer burnt offerings and peace offerings upon the altar which he built unto the LORD, and he burnt incense upon the altar that was before the LORD. So he finished the house.', '1~07969~ 2~06471~ 5~08141~ 7~08010~ 8~05927~ 10~05930~ 13~08002~ 16~04196~ 19~01129~ 22~03068~, 26~06999~ 29~04196~ [31] 32~06440~ 34~03068~. 37~07999~ 39~01004~.'),
  (13747, 18, 36, 2, 'Suffer me a little, and I will shew thee that I have yet to speak on God''s behalf.', '0~03803~ 3~02191~, 7~02331~ [10 11] 14~04405~ 16~0433~'),
  (17811, 23, 7, 20, 'In the same day shall the Lord shave with a razor that is hired, namely, by them beyond the river, by the king of Assyria, the head, and the hair of the feet: and it shall also consume the beard.', '3~03117~ 6~0136~ 7~01548~ 10~08593~ 13~07917~, [14] 17~05676~ 19~05104~, 22~04428~ 24~0804~, 26~07218~, 29~08181~ 32~07272~: 37~05595~ 39~02206~.'),
  (28029, 45, 3, 22, 'Even the righteousness of God which is by faith of Jesus Christ unto all and upon all them that believe: for there is no difference:', '0~1161~ 2~1343~ 4~2316~ [5 6] 7~1223~ 8~4102~ 10~2424~ 11~5547~ 12~1519~ 13~3956~ 14~2532~ 15~1909~ 16~3956~ 19~4100~: 20~1063~ 22~2076~ 23~3756~ 24~1293~:'),
  (11966, 14, 34, 24, 'Thus saith the LORD, Behold, I will bring evil upon this place, and upon the inhabitants thereof, even all the curses that are written in the book which they have read before the king of Judah:', '1~0559~ 3~03068~, 7~0935~ 8~07451~ 11~04725~, 15~03427~ [17] 20~0423~ 23~03789~ 26~05612~ 30~07121~ 31~06440~ 33~04428~ 35~03063~:'),
  (31089, 66, 21, 20, 'The fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, sardius; the seventh, chrysolyte; the eighth, beryl; the ninth, a topaz; the tenth, a chrysoprasus; the eleventh, a jacinth; the twelfth, an amethyst.', '1~3991~, 2~4557~; 4~1623~, 5~4556~; 7~1442~, 8~5555~; 10~3590~, 11~969~; 13~1766~, 15~5116~; 17~1182~, 19~5556~; 21~1734~, 23~5192~; 25~1428~, 27~271~.'),
  (24814, 41, 14, 49, 'I was daily with you in the temple teaching, and ye took me not: but the scriptures must be fulfilled.', '1~2252~ 2~2596~ 3~2250~* 4~4314~ 5~5209~ 6~1722~ 8~2411~ 9~1321~, 10~2532~ 12~2902~ 13~3165~ 14~3756~: 15~235~ 17~1124~ 18~2443~ 20~4137~.'),
  (9437, 11, 20, 21, 'And the king of Israel went out, and smote the horses and chariots, and slew the Syrians with a great slaughter.', '2~04428~ 4~03478~ 6~03318~, 8~05221~ 10~05483~ 12~07393~, 14~05221~ 16~0758~ 19~01419~ 20~04347~.'),
  (1799, 2, 10, 17, 'Now therefore forgive, I pray thee, my sin only this once, and entreat the LORD your God, that he may take away from me this death only.', '2~05375~, 7~02403~ 10~06471~, 12~06279~ 14~03068~ 16~0430~, 21~05493~ 25~04194~'),
  (4911, 5, 1, 13, 'Take you wise men, and understanding, and known among your tribes, and I will make them rulers over you.', '0~03051~ 2~02450~ 3~0582~, 5~0995~, 7~03045~ 10~07626~, 14~07760~ 16~07218~'),
  (11643, 14, 21, 10, 'So the Edomites revolted from under the hand of Judah unto this day. The same time also did Libnah revolt from under his hand; because he had forsaken the LORD God of his fathers.', '2~0123~ 3~06586~ 7~03027~ 9~03063~ 12~03117~. 15~06256~ [16] 18~03841~ 19~06586~ 23~03027~; 27~05800~ 29~03068~ 30~0430~ 33~01~.'),
  (15430, 19, 92, 10, 'But my horn shalt thou exalt like the horn of an unicorn: I shall be anointed with fresh oil.', '2~07161~ 5~07311~ [7 9] 11~07214~: 15~01101~ 17~07488~ 18~08081~.'),
  (25869, 42, 21, 29, 'And he spake to them a parable; Behold the fig tree, and all the trees;', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~2036~ 4~846~ 6~3850~; 7~1492~ 10~4808~, 11~2532~ 12~3956~ 14~1186~;'),
  (8168, 10, 6, 4, 'And they brought it out of the house of Abinadab which was at Gibeah, accompanying the ark of God: and Ahio went before the ark.', '2~05375~ 7~01004~ 9~041~ [11] 13~01390~, 14~05973~ 16~0727~ 18~0430~: 20~0283~ 21~01980~ 22~06440~ 24~0727~.'),
  (25293, 42, 8, 36, 'They also which saw it told them by what means he that was possessed of the devils was healed.', '0~1161~ 1~2532~ 3~1492~ [4] 5~518~ 6~846~ 9~4459~ 16~1139~ 18~4982~.'),
  (3232, 3, 16, 26, 'And he that let go the goat for the scapegoat shall wash his clothes, and bathe his flesh in water, and afterward come into the camp.', '4~07971~ 6~08163~ 9~05799~ 11~03526~ 13~0899~, 15~07364~ 17~01320~ 19~04325~, 21~0310~ 22~0935~ 25~04264~.'),
  (28113, 45, 7, 6, 'But now we are delivered from the law, that being dead wherein we were held; that we should serve in newness of spirit, and not in the oldness of the letter.', '0~1161~ 1~3570~ 4~2673~ 5~575~ 7~3551~, 10~599~ 11~3739~ 12~1722~ 14~2722~; 15~5620~ 16~2248~ 18~1398~ 19~1722~ 20~2538~ 22~4151~, 23~2532~ 24~3756~ [25] 27~3821~ 30~1121~.'),
  (10782, 13, 13, 14, 'And the ark of God remained with the family of Obededom in his house three months. And the LORD blessed the house of Obededom, and all that he had.', '2~0727~ 4~0430~ 5~03427~ 8~01004~ 10~05654~ 13~01004~ 14~07969~ 15~02320~. 18~03068~ 19~01288~ 21~01004~ 23~05654~,'),
  (9412, 11, 19, 17, 'And it shall come to pass, that him that escapeth the sword of Hazael shall Jehu slay: and him that escapeth from the sword of Jehu shall Elisha slay.', '[6] 9~04422~ 11~02719~ 13~02371~ 15~03058~ 16~04191~: 20~04422~ 23~02719~ 25~03058~ 27~0477~ 28~04191~.'),
  (5404, 5, 18, 14, 'For these nations, which thou shalt possess, hearkened unto observers of times, and unto diviners: but as for thee, the LORD thy God hath not suffered thee so to do.', '2~01471~, 6~03423~, 7~08085~ 11~06049~, 14~07080~: 20~03068~ 22~0430~ 25~05414~ [28 29]'),
  (20793, 26, 16, 22, 'And in all thine abominations and thy whoredoms thou hast not remembered the days of thy youth, when thou wast naked and bare, and wast polluted in thy blood.', '4~08441~ 7~08457~ 11~02142~ 13~03117~ 16~05271~, 20~05903~ 22~06181~, [23] 25~0947~ 28~01818~.'),
  (26594, 43, 11, 56, 'Then sought they for Jesus, and spake among themselves, as they stood in the temple, What think ye, that he will not come to the feast?', '0~3767~ 3~2212~ 4~2424~, 5~2532~ 6~3004~ 7~3326~ 8~240~, 11~2476~ 12~1722~ 14~2411~, 15~5101~ 16~1380~ 17~5213~, 18~3754~ 20~2064~ 21~3364~ 22~2064~ 23~1519~ 25~1859~?'),
  (11589, 14, 19, 4, 'And Jehoshaphat dwelt at Jerusalem: and he went out again through the people from Beersheba to mount Ephraim, and brought them back unto the LORD God of their fathers.', '1~03092~ 2~03427~ 4~03389~: 8~03318~ 9~07725~ 12~05971~ 14~0884~ 16~02022~ 17~0669~, 21~07725~ 24~03068~ 25~0430~ 28~01~.'),
  (25930, 42, 22, 52, 'Then Jesus said unto the chief priests, and captains of the temple, and the elders, which were come to him, Be ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and staves?', '0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 6~749~, 7~2532~ 8~4755~ 11~2411~, 12~2532~ 14~4245~, 17~3854~ 18~1909~ 19~846~, 23~1831~, 24~5613~ 25~1909~ 27~3027~, 28~3326~ 29~3162~ 30~2532~ 31~3586~?'),
  (8415, 10, 15, 19, 'Then said the king to Ittai the Gittite, Wherefore goest thou also with us? return to thy place, and abide with the king: for thou art a stranger, and also an exile.', '1~0559~ 3~04428~ 5~0863~ 7~01663~, 9~03212~ 14~07725~ 17~04725~, 19~03427~ 22~04428~: [25] 27~05237~, 31~01540~.'),
  (25099, 42, 4, 24, 'And he said, Verily, I say unto you, No prophet is accepted in his own country.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 3~281~ 5~3004~ 7~5213~ 8~3754~,* 9~3762~ 10~4396~ 11~2076~ 12~1184~ 13~1722~ 15~846~ 16~3968~.'),
  (30380, 59, 5, 10, 'Take, my brethren, the prophets, who have spoken in the name of the Lord, for an example of suffering affliction, and of patience.', '0~2983~, 1~3450~ 2~80~, 4~4396~, 5~3739~ 7~2980~ 10~3686~ 13~2962~, 16~5262~ 19~2552~, 20~2532~ 22~3115~.'),
  (20447, 25, 4, 18, 'They hunt our steps, that we cannot go in our streets: our end is near, our days are fulfilled; for our end is come.', '1~06679~ 3~06806~, 7~03212~ 10~07339~: 12~07093~ 14~07126~, 16~03117~ 18~04390~; 21~07093~ 23~0935~.'),
  (18955, 23, 66, 24, 'And they shall go forth, and look upon the carcases of the men that have transgressed against me: for their worm shall not die, neither shall their fire be quenched; and they shall be an abhorring unto all flesh.', '4~03318~, 6~07200~ 9~06297~ 12~0582~ 15~06586~ 20~08438~ 23~04191~, 27~0784~ 29~03518~; 35~01860~ 38~01320~.'),
  (24260, 41, 1, 35, 'And in the morning, rising up a great while before day, he went out, and departed into a solitary place, and there prayed.', '0~2532~ 3~4404~, 5~450~ 8~3029~ 10~1773~, 13~1831~, 14~2532~ 15~565~ 16~1519~ 18~2048~ 19~5117~, 21~2546~ 22~4336~.'),
  (2568, 2, 35, 32, 'And to devise curious works, to work in gold, and in silver, and in brass,', '2~02803~ 4~04284~, 6~06213~ 8~02091~, 11~03701~, 14~05178~,'),
  (4179, 4, 15, 21, 'Of the first of your dough ye shall give unto the LORD an heave offering in your generations.', '2~07225~ 5~06182~ 8~05414~ 11~03068~ 14~08641~ 17~01755~.'),
  (10589, 13, 8, 6, 'And these are the sons of Ehud: these are the heads of the fathers of the inhabitants of Geba, and they removed them to Manahath:', '[2] 4~01121~ 6~0261~: 10~07218~ 13~01~ 16~03427~ 18~01387~, 21~01540~ 24~04506~:'),
  (12058, 15, 2, 22, 'The men of Netophah, fifty and six.', '1~0582~ 3~05199~, 4~02572~ 6~08337~.'),
  (1845, 2, 12, 24, 'And ye shall observe this thing for an ordinance to thee and to thy sons for ever.', '3~08104~ 5~01697~ 8~02706~ 14~01121~ 15~05704~ 16~05769~.'),
  (18261, 23, 31, 2, 'Yet he also is wise, and will bring evil, and will not call back his words: but will arise against the house of the evildoers, and against the help of them that work iniquity.', '[3] 4~02450~, 7~0935~ 8~07451~, 13~05493~ 15~01697~: 18~06965~ 21~01004~ 24~07489~, 28~05833~ 32~06466~ 33~0205~.'),
  (4016, 4, 10, 23, 'And over the host of the tribe of the children of Manasseh was Gamaliel the son of Pedahzur.', '3~06635~ 6~04294~ 9~01121~ 11~04519~ [12] 13~01583~ 15~01121~ 17~06301~.'),
  (23097, 38, 14, 20, 'In that day shall there be upon the bells of the horses, HOLINESS UNTO THE LORD; and the pots in the LORD''S house shall be like the bowls before the altar.', '2~03117~ 8~04698~ 11~05483~, 12~06944~ 15~03068~; 18~05518~ 21~03068~ 22~01004~ 27~04219~ 28~06440~ 30~04196~.'),
  (8091, 10, 3, 3, 'And his second, Chileab, of Abigail the wife of Nabal the Carmelite; and the third, Absalom the son of Maacah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur;', '2~04932~, 3~03609~, 5~026~ 7~0802~ 9~05037~ 11~03761~; 14~07992~, 15~053~ 17~01121~ 19~04601~ 21~01323~ 23~08526~ 24~04428~ 26~01650~;'),
  (17487, 21, 9, 3, 'This is an evil among all things that are done under the sun, that there is one event unto all: yea, also the heart of the sons of men is full of evil, and madness is in their heart while they live, and after that they go to the dead.', '[1] 3~07451~ [6] 9~06213~ 12~08121~, [14 15] 16~0259~ 17~04745~ 23~03820~ 26~01121~ 28~0120~ 30~04390~ 32~07451~, 34~01947~ [35] 38~03824~ 41~02416~, 43~0310~ [45 46] 49~04191~.'),
  (10242, 12, 25, 12, 'But the captain of the guard left of the poor of the land to be vinedressers and husbandmen.', '2~07227~ 5~02876~ 6~07604~ 9~01803~ 12~0776~ [13 14] 15~03755~ 17~03009~'),
  (685, 1, 25, 23, 'And the LORD said unto her, Two nations are in thy womb, and two manner of people shall be separated from thy bowels; and the one people shall be stronger than the other people; and the elder shall serve the younger.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 6~08147~ 7~01471~ [8] 11~0990~, 14~08147~ 16~03816~ 19~06504~ 22~04578~; [24 25] 26~03816~ 29~0553~ [31 32] 33~03816~; 36~07227~ 38~05647~ 40~06810~.'),
  (24203, 40, 27, 64, 'Command therefore that the sepulchre be made sure until the third day, lest his disciples come by night, and steal him away, and say unto the people, He is risen from the dead: so the last error shall be worse than the first.', '0~2753~ 1~3767~ 4~5028~ 7~805~ 8~2193~ 10~5154~ 11~2250~, 12~3379~ 13~846~ 14~3101~ 15~2064~ 17~3571~, 19~2813~ 20~846~ 21~2813~, 22~2532~ 23~2036~ 26~2992~, 29~1453~ 30~575~ 32~3498~: 33~2532~ 35~2078~ 36~4106~ 38~2071~ 40~5501~ 42~4413~.'),
  (22624, 33, 3, 7, 'Then shall the seers be ashamed, and the diviners confounded: yea, they shall all cover their lips; for there is no answer of God.', '3~02374~ 5~0954~, 8~07080~ 9~02659~: 14~05844~ 16~08222~; [18 19] 21~04617~ 23~0430~.'),
  (18085, 23, 22, 24, 'And they shall hang upon him all the glory of his father''s house, the offspring and the issue, all vessels of small quantity, from the vessels of cups, even to all the vessels of flagons.', '3~08518~ 8~03519~ 11~01~ 12~01004~, 14~06631~ 17~06849~, 19~03627~ 21~06996~ 25~03627~ 27~0101~, 32~03627~ 34~05035~.'),
  (4578, 4, 27, 18, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Take thee Joshua the son of Nun, a man in whom is the spirit, and lay thine hand upon him;', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~03947~ 8~03091~ 10~01121~ 12~05126~, 14~0376~ [17] 19~07307~, 21~05564~ 23~03027~'),
  (20168, 24, 49, 32, 'And their camels shall be a booty, and the multitude of their cattle a spoil: and I will scatter into all winds them that are in the utmost corners; and I will bring their calamity from all sides thereof, saith the LORD.', '2~01581~ 6~0957~, 9~01995~ 12~04735~ 14~07998~: 18~02219~ 21~07307~ [23 24] 27~07112~ 28~06285~; 32~0935~ 34~0343~ 37~05676~ 39~05002~ 41~03068~.'),
  (21570, 26, 42, 9, 'And from under these chambers was the entry on the east side, as one goeth into them from the utter court.', '4~03957~ [5] 7~03996~ 8~0935~* 12~06921~, 15~0935~ 17~02007~ 20~02435~ 21~02691~.'),
  (30248, 58, 12, 20, '(For they could not endure that which was commanded, And if so much as a beast touch the mountain, it shall be stoned, or thrust through with a dart:', '0~(1063~ 2~5342~ 3~3756~ 4~5342~ 8~1291~, 13~2579~ 15~2342~ 16~2345~ 18~3735~, 22~3036~, 23~2228~ 25~2700~ 28~1002~:'),
  (13536, 18, 28, 23, 'God understandeth the way thereof, and he knoweth the place thereof.', '0~0430~ 1~0995~ 3~01870~ 7~03045~ 9~04725~'),
  (26143, 43, 3, 8, 'The wind bloweth where it listeth, and thou hearest the sound thereof, but canst not tell whence it cometh, and whither it goeth: so is every one that is born of the Spirit.', '1~4151~ 2~4154~ 3~3699~ 5~2309~, 6~2532~ 8~191~ 10~5456~ 11~846~, 12~235~ 13~1492~ 14~3756~ 15~1492~ 16~4159~ 18~2064~, 19~2532~ 20~4226~ 22~5217~: 23~3779~ 24~2076~ 26~3956~ 29~1080~ 30~1537~ 32~4151~.'),
  (11573, 14, 18, 22, 'Now therefore, behold, the LORD hath put a lying spirit in the mouth of these thy prophets, and the LORD hath spoken evil against thee.', '4~03068~ 6~05414~ 8~08267~ 9~07307~ 12~06310~ 16~05030~, 19~03068~ 21~01696~ 22~07451~'),
  (10937, 13, 20, 3, 'And he brought out the people that were in it, and cut them with saws, and with harrows of iron, and with axes. Even so dealt David with all the cities of the children of Ammon. And David and all the people returned to Jerusalem.', '3~03318~ 5~05971~ [7] 11~07787~ [12] 14~04050~, 17~02757~ 19~01270~, 22~04050~. 25~06213~ 26~01732~ 30~05892~ 33~01121~ 35~05983~. 37~01732~ 41~05971~ 42~07725~ 44~03389~.'),
  (7921, 9, 26, 9, 'And David said to Abishai, Destroy him not: for who can stretch forth his hand against the LORD''S anointed, and be guiltless?', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~052~, 5~07843~ 12~07971~ 14~03027~ 17~03068~ 18~04899~, 21~05352~?'),
  (22207, 28, 8, 4, 'They have set up kings, but not by me: they have made princes, and I knew it not: of their silver and their gold have they made them idols, that they may be cut off.', '4~04427~, 12~07786~, 15~03045~ [16] 20~03701~ 23~02091~ 26~06213~ 28~06091~, 34~03772~.'),
  (14203, 19, 21, 3, 'For thou preventest him with the blessings of goodness: thou settest a crown of pure gold on his head.', '2~06923~ 6~01293~ 8~02896~: 10~07896~ 12~05850~ 15~06337~ 18~07218~.'),
  (17865, 23, 10, 6, 'I will send him against an hypocritical nation, and against the people of my wrath will I give him a charge, to take the spoil, and to take the prey, and to tread them down like the mire of the streets.', '2~07971~ 6~02611~ 7~01471~, 11~05971~ 14~05678~ 20~06680~, 22~07997~ 24~07998~, 27~0962~ 29~0957~, 34~07760~ 35~04823~* 38~02563~ 41~02351~.'),
  (6187, 6, 13, 26, 'And from Heshbon unto Ramathmizpeh, and Betonim; and from Mahanaim unto the border of Debir;', '2~02809~ 4~07434~, 6~0993~; 9~04266~ 12~01366~ 14~01688~;'),
  (29640, 52, 5, 3, 'For when they shall say, Peace and safety; then sudden destruction cometh upon them, as travail upon a woman with child; and they shall not escape.', '0~1063~ 1~3752~ 4~3004~, 5~1515~ 6~2532~ 7~803~; 8~5119~ 9~160~ 10~3639~ 12~2186~ 13~846~, 14~5618~ 15~5604~ 16~1722~ 20~2192~ 21~1064~;* 22~2532~ 24~1628~ 25~3364~ 26~1628~.'),
  (26968, 44, 2, 3, 'And there appeared unto them cloven tongues like as of fire, and it sat upon each of them.', '0~2532~ 2~3700~ 4~846~ 5~1266~ 6~1100~ 8~5616~ 10~4442~, 11~5037~ 13~2523~ 14~1909~ 15~1520~ 16~1538~ 17~846~.');
