VALUES
  (4463, 4, 24, 12, 'And Balaam said unto Balak, Spake I not also to thy messengers which thou sentest unto me, saying,', '1~01109~ 2~0559~ 4~01111~, 5~01696~ 11~04397~ 14~07971~ 17~0559~,'),
  (23525, 40, 12, 26, 'And if Satan cast out Satan, he is divided against himself; how shall then his kingdom stand?', '0~2532~ 1~1487~ 2~4567~ 4~1544~ 5~4567~, 8~3307~ 9~1909~ 10~1438~; 11~4459~ 12~2476~ 13~3767~ 14~846~ 15~932~ 16~2476~?'),
  (11877, 14, 31, 14, 'And Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, the porter toward the east, was over the freewill offerings of God, to distribute the oblations of the LORD, and the most holy things.', '1~06981~ 3~01121~ 5~03232~ 7~03881~, 9~07778~ 12~04217~, [13] 17~05071~ 19~0430~, 21~05414~ 23~08641~ 26~03068~, 29~06944~ 31~06944~.'),
  (30116, 58, 8, 8, 'For finding fault with them, he saith, Behold, the days come, saith the Lord, when I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah:', '0~1063~ 2~3201~ 4~846~, 6~3004~, 7~2400~, 9~2250~ 10~2064~, 11~3004~ 13~2962~, 14~2532~ 17~4931~ 19~2537~ 20~1242~ 21~1909~ 23~3624~ 25~2474~ 26~2532~ 27~1909~ 29~3624~ 31~2455~:'),
  (30033, 58, 4, 3, 'For we which have believed do enter into rest, as he said, As I have sworn in my wrath, if they shall enter into my rest: although the works were finished from the foundation of the world.', '0~1063~ 2~3588~ 4~4100~ 6~1525~ 7~1519~ 8~2663~, 9~2531~ 11~2046~, 12~5613~ 15~3660~ 16~1722~ 17~3450~ 18~3709~, 19~1487~ 22~1525~ 23~1519~ 24~3450~ 25~2663~: 26~2543~ 28~2041~ 30~1096~ 31~575~ 33~2602~ 36~2889~.'),
  (26004, 42, 23, 55, 'And the women also, which came with him from Galilee, followed after, and beheld the sepulchre, and how his body was laid.', '0~1161~ 2~1135~ 3~2532~, 4~3748~ 5~2258~ 6~4905~* 8~846~ 9~1537~ 10~1056~, 12~2628~, 14~2300~ 16~3419~, 17~2532~ 18~5613~ 19~846~ 20~4983~ 22~5087~.'),
  (4000, 4, 10, 7, 'But when the congregation is to be gathered together, ye shall blow, but ye shall not sound an alarm.', '3~06951~ 8~06950~, 11~08628~, 18~07321~.'),
  (6751, 7, 8, 25, 'And they answered, We will willingly give them. And they spread a garment, and did cast therein every man the earrings of his prey.', '2~0559~, 5~05414~ 6~05414~ [7] 10~06566~ 12~08071~, 15~07993~ 18~0376~ 20~05141~ 23~07998~.'),
  (21295, 26, 33, 6, 'But if the watchman see the sword come, and blow not the trumpet, and the people be not warned; if the sword come, and take any person from among them, he is taken away in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at the watchman''s hand.', '3~06822~ 4~07200~ 6~02719~ 7~0935~, 9~08628~ 12~07782~, 15~05971~ 18~02094~; 21~02719~ 22~0935~, 24~03947~ [25] 26~05315~ 33~03947~ 36~05771~; 39~01818~ 42~01875~ 45~06822~ 46~03027~.'),
  (25747, 42, 19, 2, 'And, behold, there was a man named Zacchaeus, which was the chief among the publicans, and he was rich.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, [2 3] 5~435~ 6~2564~ 7~3686~* 8~2195~, 9~846~ 10~2532~* 11~2258~ 16~754~, 17~2532~ 18~3778~ 19~2258~ 20~4145~.'),
  (30568, 62, 2, 2, 'And he is the propitiation for our sins: and not for ours only, but also for the sins of the whole world.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~2076~ 4~2434~ 5~4012~ 6~2257~ 7~266~: 8~1161~ 9~3756~ 10~4012~ 11~2251~ 12~3440~, 13~235~ 14~2532~ 15~4012~ [16 18] 20~3650~ 21~2889~.'),
  (9640, 12, 4, 29, 'Then he said to Gehazi, Gird up thy loins, and take my staff in thine hand, and go thy way: if thou meet any man, salute him not; and if any salute thee, answer him not again: and lay my staff upon the face of the child.', '2~0559~ 4~01522~, 6~02296~ 8~04975~, 10~03947~ 12~04938~ 15~03027~, 19~03212~: 22~04672~ 24~0376~, 25~01288~ 30~0376~ 31~01288~ 36~06030~: 38~07760~ 40~04938~ 43~06440~ 46~05288~.'),
  (22464, 30, 6, 5, 'That chant to the sound of the viol, and invent to themselves instruments of music, like David;', '1~06527~ 4~06310~ 7~05035~, [8] 9~02803~ 12~03627~ 14~07892~, 16~01732~;'),
  (10432, 13, 4, 39, 'And they went to the entrance of Gedor, even unto the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks.', '2~03212~ 5~03996~ 7~01446~, [8] 12~04217~ 15~01516~, 17~01245~ 18~04829~ 21~06629~.'),
  (2993, 3, 10, 11, 'And that ye may teach the children of Israel all the statutes which the LORD hath spoken unto them by the hand of Moses.', '4~03384~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~ 11~02706~ 14~03068~ 16~01696~ 21~03027~ 23~04872~.'),
  (19683, 24, 30, 7, 'Alas! for that day is great, so that none is like it: it is even the time of Jacob''s trouble; but he shall be saved out of it.', '0~01945~! 3~03117~ [4] 5~01419~, 7~0369~ [9] [13] 16~06256~ 18~03290~ 19~06869~; 24~03467~'),
  (16712, 20, 11, 15, 'He that is surety for a stranger shall smart for it: and he that hateth suretiship is sure.', '&para; 3~06148~ 6~02114~ 8~07321~ 9~07451~* [10 11] 15~08130~ 16~08628~ 18~0982~.'),
  (25981, 42, 23, 32, 'And there were also two other, malefactors, led with him to be put to death.', '&para; 0~1161~ 3~2532~ 4~1417~ 5~2087~, 6~2557~, 7~71~ 8~4862~ 9~846~ 14~337~.'),
  (28082, 45, 5, 19, 'For as by one man''s disobedience many were made sinners, so by the obedience of one shall many be made righteous.', '0~1063~ 1~5618~ 2~1223~ 3~1520~ 4~444~ 5~3876~ 6~4183~ 8~2525~ 9~268~, 10~2532~ 11~3779~* 12~1223~ 14~5218~ 16~1520~ 17~2525~ 18~4183~ 20~2525~ 21~1342~.'),
  (7629, 9, 17, 4, 'And there went out a champion out of the camp of the Philistines, named Goliath, of Gath, whose height was six cubits and a span.', '3~03318~ 5~01143~ 6~0376~ 9~04264~ 12~06430~, 13~08034~ 14~01555~, 16~01661~, 18~01363~ [19] 20~08337~ 21~0520~ 24~02239~.'),
  (21330, 26, 34, 8, 'As I live, saith the Lord GOD, surely because my flock became a prey, and my flock became meat to every beast of the field, because there was no shepherd, neither did my shepherds search for my flock, but the shepherds fed themselves, and fed not my flock;', '[0] 2~02416~, 3~05002~ 5~0136~ 6~03069~, 10~06629~ 13~0957~, 16~06629~ 18~0402~ 21~02416~ 24~07704~, [26 27] 29~07462~, 33~07462~ 34~01875~ 37~06629~, 40~07462~ 41~07462~ 44~07462~ 47~06629~;'),
  (6252, 6, 15, 43, 'And Jiphtah, and Ashnah, and Nezib,', '1~03316~, 3~0823~, 5~05334~,'),
  (14383, 19, 33, 8, 'Let all the earth fear the LORD: let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.', '3~0776~ 4~03372~ 6~03068~: 10~03427~ 13~08398~ 16~01481~'),
  (16274, 19, 140, 2, 'Which imagine mischiefs in their heart; continually are they gathered together for war.', '1~02803~ 2~07451~ [4] 5~03820~; 6~03117~ 10~01481~ [11] 12~04421~.'),
  (11488, 14, 14, 4, 'And commanded Judah to seek the LORD God of their fathers, and to do the law and the commandment.', '1~0559~ 2~03063~ 4~01875~ 6~03068~ 7~0430~ 10~01~, 13~06213~ 15~08451~ 18~04687~.'),
  (23449, 40, 10, 22, 'And ye shall be hated of all men for my name''s sake: but he that endureth to the end shall be saved.', '0~2532~ 2~2071~ 4~3404~ 5~5259~ 6~3956~ [7] 8~1223~ 9~3450~ 11~3686~: 12~1161~ 14~3778~ 15~5278~ 16~1519~ 18~5056~ 21~4982~.'),
  (739, 1, 27, 8, 'Now therefore, my son, obey my voice according to that which I command thee.', '3~01121~, 4~08085~ 6~06963~ 10~0834~ 12~06680~'),
  (17725, 23, 3, 9, 'The shew of their countenance doth witness against them; and they declare their sin as Sodom, they hide it not. Woe unto their soul! for they have rewarded evil unto themselves.', '&para; 1~01971~ 4~06440~ 8~06030~; 11~05046~ 13~02403~ 15~05467~, 17~03582~ [18] 20~0188~ 23~05315~! 27~01580~ 28~07451~'),
  (4690, 4, 31, 20, 'And purify all your raiment, and all that is made of skins, and all work of goats'' hair, and all things made of wood.', '1~02398~ [3] 4~0899~, 9~03627~ 11~05785~, 14~04639~ 16~05795~ [17] 21~03627~ 23~06086~.'),
  (5323, 5, 14, 27, 'And the Levite that is within thy gates; thou shalt not forsake him; for he hath no part nor inheritance with thee.', '2~03881~ [4] 7~08179~; 11~05800~ 17~02506~ 19~05159~'),
  (24570, 41, 9, 21, 'And he asked his father, How long is it ago since this came unto him? And he said, Of a child.', '0~2532~ 2~1905~ 3~846~ 4~3962~, 6~4214~ 8~2076~ 9~5550~ 10~5613~ 11~5124~ 12~1096~ 14~846~? 15~1161~ 17~2036~, 20~3812~.'),
  (2384, 2, 29, 43, 'And there I will meet with the children of Israel, and the tabernacle shall be sanctified by my glory.', '4~03259~ 7~01121~ 9~03478~, [11 12] 15~06942~ 18~03519~.'),
  (21559, 26, 41, 24, 'And the doors had two leaves apiece, two turning leaves; two leaves for the one door, and two leaves for the other door.', '2~01817~ 4~08147~ 5~01817~ [6] 7~08147~ 8~04142~ 9~01817~; 10~08147~ [11] 14~0259~ 15~01817~, 17~08147~ 18~01817~ 21~0312~ [22]'),
  (8144, 10, 5, 5, 'In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months: and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty and three years over all Israel and Judah.', '1~02275~ 3~04427~ 5~03063~ 6~07651~ 7~08141~ 9~08337~ 10~02320~: 13~03389~ 15~04427~ 16~07970~ 18~07969~ 19~08141~ 22~03478~ 24~03063~.'),
  (12823, 17, 7, 7, 'And the king arising from the banquet of wine in his wrath went into the palace garden: and Haman stood up to make request for his life to Esther the queen; for he saw that there was evil determined against him by the king.', '&para; 2~04428~ 3~06965~ 6~04960~ 8~03196~ 11~02534~ [12] 15~01055~ 16~01594~: 18~02001~ 20~05975~ 23~01245~ 26~05315~ 28~0635~ 30~04436~; 33~07200~ 37~07451~ 38~03615~ 43~04428~.'),
  (2163, 2, 23, 14, 'Three times thou shalt keep a feast unto me in the year.', '0~07969~ 1~07272~ 6~02287~ 11~08141~.'),
  (12853, 17, 9, 10, 'The ten sons of Haman the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews, slew they; but on the spoil laid they not their hand.', '1~06235~ 2~01121~ 4~02001~ 6~01121~ 8~04099~, 10~06887~ 13~03064~, 14~02026~ 19~0961~ 20~07971~ 24~03027~.'),
  (6258, 6, 15, 49, 'And Dannah, and Kirjathsannah, which is Debir,', '1~01837~, 3~07158~, [5] 6~01688~,'),
  (5211, 5, 10, 19, 'Love ye therefore the stranger: for ye were strangers in the land of Egypt.', '0~0157~ 4~01616~: 8~01616~ 11~0776~ 13~04714~.'),
  (15121, 19, 77, 19, 'Thy way is in the sea, and thy path in the great waters, and thy footsteps are not known.', '1~01870~ [2] 5~03220~, 8~07635~ 11~07227~ 12~04325~, 15~06119~ 18~03045~.'),
  (23712, 40, 17, 2, 'And was transfigured before them: and his face did shine as the sun, and his raiment was white as the light.', '0~2532~ 2~3339~ 3~1715~ 4~846~: 5~2532~ 6~846~ 7~4383~ 9~2989~ 10~5613~ 12~2246~, 13~1161~ 14~846~ 15~2440~ 16~1096~ 17~3022~ 18~5613~ 20~5457~.'),
  (28328, 45, 15, 9, 'And that the Gentiles might glorify God for his mercy; as it is written, For this cause I will confess to thee among the Gentiles, and sing unto thy name.', '0~1161~ 3~1484~ 5~1392~ 6~2316~ 7~5228~ [8] 9~1656~; 10~2531~ 13~1125~, 14~1223~ 15~5124~ 16~1223~ 19~1843~ 21~4671~ 22~1722~ 24~1484~, 25~2532~ 26~5567~ 28~4675~ 29~3686~.'),
  (20919, 26, 20, 15, 'Yet also I lifted up my hand unto them in the wilderness, that I would not bring them into the land which I had given them, flowing with milk and honey, which is the glory of all lands;', '4~05375~ 6~03027~ 11~04057~, 16~0935~ 20~0776~ 24~05414~ [25] 26~02100~ 28~02461~ 30~01706~, [32] 34~06643~ 37~0776~;'),
  (4573, 4, 27, 13, 'And when thou hast seen it, thou also shalt be gathered unto thy people, as Aaron thy brother was gathered.', '4~07200~ 10~0622~ 13~05971~, 15~0175~ 17~0251~ 19~0622~.'),
  (1388, 1, 45, 25, 'And they went up out of Egypt, and came into the land of Canaan unto Jacob their father,', '&para; 3~05927~ 6~04714~, 8~0935~ 11~0776~ 13~03667~ 15~03290~ 17~01~,'),
  (17454, 21, 7, 16, 'Be not righteous over much; neither make thyself over wise: why shouldest thou destroy thyself?', '2~06662~ 4~07235~; 8~03148~ 9~02449~: 13~08074~'),
  (11686, 14, 23, 21, 'And all the people of the land rejoiced: and the city was quiet, after that they had slain Athaliah with the sword.', '3~05971~ 6~0776~ 7~08055~: 10~05892~ 12~08252~, 17~04191~ 18~06271~ 21~02719~.'),
  (28523, 46, 7, 20, 'Let every man abide in the same calling wherein he was called.', '0~3306~ 2~1538~ 3~3306~ 4~1722~ 6~5026~ 7~2821~ 8~3739~ 9~1722~ 11~2564~.'),
  (15124, 19, 78, 2, 'I will open my mouth in a parable: I will utter dark sayings of old:', '2~06605~ 4~06310~ 7~04912~: 10~05042~ 12~02420~ 14~06924~:'),
  (19640, 24, 28, 13, 'Go and tell Hananiah, saying, Thus saith the LORD; Thou hast broken the yokes of wood; but thou shalt make for them yokes of iron.', '0~01980~ 2~0559~ 3~02608~, 4~0559~, 6~0559~ 8~03068~; 11~07665~ 13~04133~ 15~06086~; 19~06213~ 22~04133~ 24~01270~.'),
  (24369, 41, 4, 36, 'And when they had sent away the multitude, they took him even as he was in the ship. And there were also with him other little ships.', '0~2532~ 5~863~ 7~3793~, 9~3880~ 10~846~ 12~5613~ 14~2258~ 15~1722~ 17~4143~. 18~1161~ 20~2258~ 21~2532~ 22~3326~ 23~846~ 24~243~ 26~4142~.'),
  (17022, 20, 21, 29, 'A wicked man hardeneth his face: but as for the upright, he directeth his way.', '&para; 1~07563~ 2~0376~ 3~05810~ 5~06440~: [7 8] 10~03477~, 12~0995~ 14~01870~.'),
  (17621, 22, 5, 14, 'His hands are as gold rings set with the beryl: his belly is as bright ivory overlaid with sapphires.', '1~03027~ [2 3] 4~02091~ 5~01550~ 6~04390~ 9~08658~: 11~04578~ [12 13] 14~06247~ 15~08127~ 16~05968~ [17] 18~05601~.'),
  (14217, 19, 22, 4, 'Our fathers trusted in thee: they trusted, and thou didst deliver them.', '1~01~ 2~0982~ 6~0982~, 10~06403~'),
  (19671, 24, 29, 27, 'Now therefore why hast thou not reproved Jeremiah of Anathoth, which maketh himself a prophet to you?', '6~01605~ 7~03414~ 9~06069~, 14~05012~'),
  (18968, 24, 1, 13, 'And the word of the LORD came unto me the second time, saying, What seest thou? And I said, I see a seething pot; and the face thereof is toward the north.', '2~01697~ 5~03068~ 11~08145~, 12~0559~, 14~07200~ 18~0559~, 20~07200~ 22~05301~ 23~05518~; 26~06440~ [28] 29~06440~ 31~06828~.'),
  (15545, 19, 102, 15, 'So the heathen shall fear the name of the LORD, and all the kings of the earth thy glory.', '2~01471~ 4~03372~ 6~08034~ 9~03068~, 13~04428~ 16~0776~ 18~03519~.'),
  (29580, 52, 1, 4, 'Knowing, brethren beloved, your election of God.', '0~1492~, 1~80~ 2~25~, 3~5216~ 4~1589~ 5~5259~ 6~2316~.'),
  (26152, 43, 3, 17, 'For God sent not his Son into the world to condemn the world; but that the world through him might be saved.', '0~1063~ 1~2316~ 2~649~ 3~3756~ 4~846~ 5~5207~ 6~1519~ 8~2889~ 9~2443~ 10~2919~ 12~2889~; 13~235~ 14~2443~ 16~2889~ 17~1223~ 18~846~ 21~4982~.'),
  (28188, 45, 9, 17, 'For the scripture saith unto Pharaoh, Even for this same purpose have I raised thee up, that I might shew my power in thee, and that my name might be declared throughout all the earth.', '0~1063~ 2~1124~ 3~3004~ 5~5328~, 7~1519~ 8~3754~* 9~5124~ 11~846~ 14~1825~ 15~4571~ 16~1825~, 17~3704~ 20~1731~ 21~3450~ 22~1411~ 23~1722~ 24~4671~, 25~2532~ 26~3704~ 27~3450~ 28~3686~ 31~1229~ 32~1722~ 33~3956~ 35~1093~.'),
  (7218, 8, 4, 21, 'And Salmon begat Boaz, and Boaz begat Obed,', '1~08012~ 2~03205~ 3~01162~, 5~01162~ 6~03205~ 7~05744~,'),
  (5717, 5, 30, 3, 'That then the LORD thy God will turn thy captivity, and have compassion upon thee, and will return and gather thee from all the nations, whither the LORD thy God hath scattered thee.', '3~03068~ 5~0430~ 7~07725~ 9~07622~, 12~07355~ 17~07725~ 19~06908~ 24~05971~, 27~03068~ 29~0430~ 31~06327~'),
  (20953, 26, 20, 49, 'Then said I, Ah Lord GOD! they say of me, Doth he not speak parables?', '1~0559~ 3~0162~ 4~0136~ 5~03069~! 7~0559~ 13~04911~ 14~04912~?'),
  (4116, 4, 14, 3, 'And wherefore hath the LORD brought us unto this land, to fall by the sword, that our wives and our children should be a prey? were it not better for us to return into Egypt?', '4~03068~ 5~0935~ 9~0776~, 11~05307~ 14~02719~, 17~0802~ 20~02945~ 24~0957~? 28~02896~ 32~07725~ 34~04714~?'),
  (6749, 7, 8, 23, 'And Gideon said unto them, I will not rule over you, neither shall my son rule over you: the LORD shall rule over you.', '1~01439~ 2~0559~ 8~04910~ 14~01121~ 15~04910~ 19~03068~ 21~04910~'),
  (9375, 11, 18, 26, 'And they took the bullock which was given them, and they dressed it, and called on the name of Baal from morning even until noon, saying, O Baal, hear us. But there was no voice, nor any that answered. And they leaped upon the altar which was made.', '2~03947~ 4~06499~ 7~05414~ 11~06213~ [12] 14~07121~ 17~08034~ 19~01168~ 21~01242~ 24~06672~, 25~0559~, 27~01168~, 28~06030~ [31 32] 33~0369~ 34~06963~, 38~06030~. 41~06452~ 44~04196~ 47~06213~.'),
  (1777, 2, 9, 30, 'But as for thee and thy servants, I know that ye will not yet fear the LORD God.', '6~05650~, 8~03045~ 14~03372~ 15~06440~* 17~03068~ 18~0430~.'),
  (4639, 4, 29, 25, 'And one kid of the goats for a sin offering; beside the continual burnt offering, his meat offering, and his drink offering.', '1~0259~ 2~08163~ 5~05795~ [6] 9~02403~; 12~08548~ 14~05930~, 17~04503~, 21~05262~.'),
  (2050, 2, 19, 19, 'And when the voice of the trumpet sounded long, and waxed louder and louder, Moses spake, and God answered him by a voice.', '3~06963~ 6~07782~ 7~06963~ 8~01980~, 11~02390~ 13~03966~, 14~04872~ 15~01696~, 17~0430~ 18~06030~ 22~06963~.'),
  (25887, 42, 22, 9, 'And they said unto him, Where wilt thou that we prepare?', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~4226~ 7~2309~ 10~2090~?'),
  (30496, 61, 1, 1, 'Simon Peter, a servant and an apostle of Jesus Christ, to them that have obtained like precious faith with us through the righteousness of God and our Saviour Jesus Christ:', '&para; 0~4826~ 1~4074~, 3~1401~ 4~2532~ 6~652~ 8~2424~ 9~5547~, 14~2975~ 16~2472~ 17~4102~ 19~2254~ 20~1722~ 22~1343~ 24~2316~ 25~2532~ 26~2257~ 27~4990~ 28~2424~ 29~5547~:'),
  (27260, 44, 9, 28, 'And he was with them coming in and going out at Jerusalem.', '0~2532~ 2~2258~ 3~3326~ 4~846~ 6~1531~ 7~2532~ 9~1607~ 10~1722~ 11~2419~.'),
  (9676, 12, 5, 21, 'So Gehazi followed after Naaman. And when Naaman saw him running after him, he lighted down from the chariot to meet him, and said, Is all well?', '1~01522~ 2~07291~ 3~0310~ 4~05283~. 7~05283~ 8~07200~ [9] 10~07323~ 11~0310~ 15~05307~ 18~04818~ 20~07125~ 23~0559~, [24] 26~07965~?'),
  (2583, 2, 36, 12, 'Fifty loops made he in one curtain, and fifty loops made he in the edge of the curtain which was in the coupling of the second: the loops held one curtain to another.', '0~02572~ 1~03924~ 2~06213~ 5~0259~ 6~03407~, 8~02572~ 9~03924~ 10~06213~ 14~07097~ 17~03407~ [19] 22~04225~ 25~08145~: 27~03924~ 28~06901~ 29~0259~ [30] 32~0259~.'),
  (2665, 2, 38, 27, 'And of the hundred talents of silver were cast the sockets of the sanctuary, and the sockets of the veil; an hundred sockets of the hundred talents, a talent for a socket.', '3~03967~ 4~03603~ 6~03701~ 8~03332~ 10~0134~ 13~06944~, 16~0134~ 19~06532~; 21~03967~ 22~0134~ 25~03967~ 26~03603~, 28~03603~ 31~0134~.'),
  (5459, 5, 21, 6, 'And all the elders of that city, that are next unto the slain man, shall wash their hands over the heifer that is beheaded in the valley:', '3~02205~ 6~05892~, [7 8] 9~07138~ 12~02491~ [13] 15~07364~ 17~03027~ 20~05697~ 23~06202~ 26~05158~:'),
  (29041, 47, 12, 3, 'And I knew such a man, (whether in the body, or out of the body, I cannot tell: God knoweth;)', '0~2532~ 2~1492~ 3~5108~ 5~444~, 6~1535~* 8~1722~ 10~4983~, 11~1535~ 12~1622~ 15~4983~, 17~3756~ 18~1492~: 19~2316~ 20~1492~;)'),
  (15494, 19, 97, 7, 'Confounded be all they that serve graven images, that boast themselves of idols: worship him, all ye gods.', '0~0954~ 5~05647~ 7~06459~, 9~01984~ 12~0457~: 13~07812~ [16] 17~0430~.'),
  (19826, 24, 34, 16, 'But ye turned and polluted my name, and caused every man his servant, and every man his handmaid, whom he had set at liberty at their pleasure, to return, and brought them into subjection, to be unto you for servants and for handmaids.', '2~07725~ 4~02490~ 6~08034~, 10~0376~ 12~05650~, 15~0376~ 17~08198~, 21~07971~ 23~02670~ 26~05315~, 28~07725~, 33~03533~, 39~05650~ 42~08198~.'),
  (2963, 3, 9, 5, 'And they brought that which Moses commanded before the tabernacle of the congregation: and all the congregation drew near and stood before the LORD.', '2~03947~ [3] 5~04872~ 6~06680~ 7~06440~ 9~0168~ 12~04150~: 16~05712~ 18~07126~ 20~05975~ 21~06440~ 23~03068~.'),
  (10953, 13, 21, 11, 'So Gad came to David, and said unto him, Thus saith the LORD, Choose thee', '1~01410~ 2~0935~ 4~01732~, 6~0559~ 10~0559~ 12~03068~, 13~06901~'),
  (15560, 19, 103, 2, 'Bless the LORD, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits:', '0~01288~ 2~03068~, 5~05315~, 7~07911~ 11~01576~:'),
  (11084, 13, 25, 30, 'The three and twentieth to Mahazioth, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~07969~ 3~06242~ 5~04238~, [6] 8~01121~, 11~0251~, [12] 13~06240~ 14~08147~:*'),
  (4194, 4, 15, 36, 'And all the congregation brought him without the camp, and stoned him with stones, and he died; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '3~05712~ 4~03318~ 6~02351~ 8~04264~, 10~07275~ 13~068~, 16~04191~; 19~03068~ 20~06680~ 21~04872~.'),
  (4293, 4, 18, 31, 'And ye shall eat it in every place, ye and your households: for it is your reward for your service in the tabernacle of the congregation.', '3~0398~ 7~04725~, 11~01004~: [14] 16~07939~ 17~02500~ 19~05656~ 22~0168~ 25~04150~.'),
  (17198, 20, 27, 20, 'Hell and destruction are never full; so the eyes of man are never satisfied.', '&para; 0~07585~ 2~011~ 3~010~* 5~03808~ 6~07646~; 9~05869~ 11~0120~ 14~07646~.'),
  (6139, 6, 12, 3, 'And from the plain to the sea of Chinneroth on the east, and unto the sea of the plain, even the salt sea on the east, the way to Bethjeshimoth; and from the south, under Ashdothpisgah:', '3~06160~ 6~03220~ 8~03672~ 11~04217~, 15~03220~ 18~06160~, [19] 21~04417~ 22~03220~ 25~04217~, 27~01870~ 29~01020~; 33~08486~, 35~0798~ 36~0794~:*'),
  (14522, 19, 39, 1, 'To the chief Musician, even to Jeduthun, A Psalm of David. I said, I will take heed to my ways, that I sin not with my tongue: I will keep my mouth with a bridle, while the wicked is before me.', '&para; [0 3~05329~, [4] 6~03038~, 8~04210~ 10] 10~01732~ 12~0559~, 16~08104~ 19~01870~, 22~02398~ 26~03956~: 29~08104~ 31~06310~ 34~04269~, 37~07563~'),
  (17419, 21, 5, 13, 'There is a sore evil which I have seen under the sun, namely, riches kept for the owners thereof to their hurt.', '1~03426~ 3~02470~ 4~07451~ [5] 8~07200~ 11~08121~, [12] 13~06239~ 14~08104~ 17~01167~ 21~07451~.'),
  (18415, 23, 38, 16, 'O Lord, by these things men live, and in all these things is the life of my spirit: so wilt thou recover me, and make me to live.', '1~0136~, [4 5] 6~02421~, [11 12] 14~02416~ 17~07307~: 21~02492~ 27~02421~.'),
  (4020, 4, 10, 27, 'And over the host of the tribe of the children of Naphtali was Ahira the son of Enan.', '3~06635~ 6~04294~ 9~01121~ 11~05321~ [12] 13~0299~ 15~01121~ 17~05881~.'),
  (2879, 3, 6, 25, 'Speak unto Aaron and to his sons, saying, This is the law of the sin offering: In the place where the burnt offering is killed shall the sin offering be killed before the LORD: it is most holy.', '0~01696~ 2~0175~ 6~01121~, 7~0559~, [9] 11~08451~ 15~02403~: 18~04725~ 22~05930~ 24~07819~ 28~02403~ 30~07819~ 31~06440~ 33~03068~: [35] 36~06944~ 37~06944~.'),
  (24492, 41, 7, 18, 'And he saith unto them, Are ye so without understanding also? Do ye not perceive, that whatsoever thing from without entereth into the man, it cannot defile him;', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~2075~ 6~5210~ 7~3779~ 9~801~ 10~2532~? 12~3539~ 13~3756~ 14~3539~, 15~3754~ 17~3956~ 19~1855~ 20~1531~ 21~1519~ 23~444~, [24] 25~1410~ 26~3756~* 27~2840~ 28~846~;'),
  (17970, 23, 15, 1, 'The burden of Moab. Because in the night Ar of Moab is laid waste, and brought to silence; because in the night Kir of Moab is laid waste, and brought to silence;', '&para; 1~04853~ 3~04124~. 7~03915~ 8~06144~ 10~04124~ 13~07703~, [14] 17~01820~; 21~03915~ 22~07024~ 24~04124~ 27~07703~, [28] 31~01820~;'),
  (2013, 2, 18, 9, 'And Jethro rejoiced for all the goodness which the LORD had done to Israel, whom he had delivered out of the hand of the Egyptians.', '1~03503~ 2~02302~ 6~02896~ 9~03068~ 11~06213~ 13~03478~, 17~05337~ 21~03027~ 24~04714~.'),
  (9073, 11, 9, 14, 'And Hiram sent to the king sixscore talents of gold.', '1~02438~ 2~07971~ 5~04428~ 6~06242~ 7~03967~* 8~03603~ 10~02091~.'),
  (1951, 2, 15, 26, 'And said, If thou wilt diligently hearken to the voice of the LORD thy God, and wilt do that which is right in his sight, and wilt give ear to his commandments, and keep all his statutes, I will put none of these diseases upon thee, which I have brought upon the Egyptians: for I am the LORD that healeth thee.', '1~0559~, 5~08085~ 6~08085~ 9~06963~ 12~03068~ 14~0430~, 17~06213~ 21~03477~ 24~05869~, 28~0238~ 31~04687~, 33~08104~ 36~02706~, 39~07760~ 43~04245~ 49~07760~ 52~04714~: [55] 57~03068~ 59~07495~'),
  (18296, 23, 33, 8, 'The highways lie waste, the wayfaring man ceaseth: he hath broken the covenant, he hath despised the cities, he regardeth no man.', '1~04546~ 3~08074~, 6~05674~ 7~0734~* 8~07673~: 11~06565~ 13~01285~, 16~03988~ 18~05892~, 20~02803~ 22~0582~.'),
  (3991, 4, 9, 21, 'And so it was, when the cloud abode from even unto the morning, and that the cloud was taken up in the morning, then they journeyed: whether it was by day or by night that the cloud was taken up, they journeyed.', '[1] 3~03426~, 6~06051~ 9~06153~ 12~01242~, [14] 16~06051~ 19~05927~ 22~01242~, 25~05265~: [27 28] 30~03119~ 33~03915~ 36~06051~ 39~05927~, 41~05265~.'),
  (4987, 5, 3, 6, 'And we utterly destroyed them, as we did unto Sihon king of Heshbon, utterly destroying the men, women, and children, of every city.', '3~02763~ 7~06213~ 9~05511~ 10~04428~ 12~02809~, 14~02763~ 16~04962~, 17~0802~, 19~02945~, 22~05892~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (14510, 19, 38, 11, 'My lovers and my friends stand aloof from my sore; and my kinsmen stand afar off.', '1~0157~ 4~07453~ 5~05975~ 7~05048~ 9~05061~; 12~07138~ 13~05975~ 15~07350~.'),
  (29548, 51, 3, 15, 'And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, to the which also ye are called in one body; and be ye thankful.', '0~2532~ 1~1018~ 3~1515~ 5~2316~ 6~1018~ 7~1722~ 8~5216~ 9~2588~, 10~1519~ 12~3739~ 13~2532~ 16~2564~ 17~1722~ 18~1520~ 19~4983~; 20~2532~ 22~1096~ 23~2170~.'),
  (23520, 40, 12, 21, 'And in his name shall the Gentiles trust.', '0~2532~ 1~1722~ 2~846~ 3~3686~ 4~1679~ 6~1484~ 7~1679~.'),
  (7854, 9, 24, 8, 'David also arose afterward, and went out of the cave, and cried after Saul, saying, My lord the king. And when Saul looked behind him, David stooped with his face to the earth, and bowed himself.', '0~01732~ 2~06965~ 6~03318~ 9~04631~, 11~07121~ 12~0310~ 13~07586~, 14~0559~, 16~0113~ 18~04428~. 21~07586~ 22~05027~ 23~0310~ 25~01732~ 26~06915~ 29~0639~ 32~0776~, 34~07812~'),
  (22543, 32, 1, 3, 'But Jonah rose up to flee unto Tarshish from the presence of the LORD, and went down to Joppa; and he found a ship going to Tarshish: so he paid the fare thereof, and went down into it, to go with them unto Tarshish from the presence of the LORD.', '1~03124~ 3~06965~ 5~01272~ 7~08659~ 10~06440~ 13~03068~, 16~03381~ 18~03305~; 21~04672~ 23~0591~ 24~0935~ 26~08659~: 29~05414~ 31~07939~ 35~03381~ 39~0935~ 43~08659~ 46~06440~ 49~03068~.'),
  (24038, 40, 25, 20, 'And so he that had received five talents came and brought other five talents, saying, Lord, thou deliveredst unto me five talents: behold, I have gained beside them five talents more.', '1~2532~ 5~2983~ 6~4002~ 7~5007~ 8~4334~ 10~4374~ 11~243~ 12~4002~ 13~5007~, 14~3004~, 15~2962~, 17~3860~ 19~3427~ 20~4002~ 21~5007~: 22~2396~, 25~2770~ 26~1909~ 27~846~ 28~4002~ 29~5007~ 30~243~.'),
  (21543, 26, 41, 8, 'I saw also the height of the house round about: the foundations of the side chambers were a full reed of six great cubits.', '1~07200~ 4~01363~ 7~01004~ 9~05439~: 11~04328~ 15~06763~ [16] 18~04393~ 19~07070~ 21~08337~ 22~0679~ 23~0520~.'),
  (5612, 5, 27, 21, 'Cursed be he that lieth with any manner of beast. And all the people shall say, Amen.', '0~0779~ [1] 4~07901~ 9~0929~. 13~05971~ 15~0559~, 16~0543~.'),
  (28161, 45, 8, 29, 'For whom he did foreknow, he also did predestinate to be conformed to the image of his Son, that he might be the firstborn among many brethren.', '&para; 0~3754~ 1~3739~ 4~4267~, 5~4309~ 6~2532~ 8~4309~ [9 10] 11~4832~ 14~1504~ 16~846~ 17~5207~, 18~1519~ 19~846~ 21~1511~ 23~4416~ 24~1722~ 25~4183~ 26~80~.'),
  (1158, 1, 39, 4, 'And Joseph found grace in his sight, and he served him: and he made him overseer over his house, and all that he had he put into his hand.', '1~03130~ 2~04672~ 3~02580~ 6~05869~, 9~08334~ 15~06485~ 18~01004~, [21] 23~03426~ 25~05414~ 28~03027~.'),
  (20960, 26, 21, 7, 'And it shall be, when they say unto thee, Wherefore sighest thou? that thou shalt answer, For the tidings; because it cometh: and every heart shall melt, and all hands shall be feeble, and every spirit shall faint, and all knees shall be weak as water: behold, it cometh, and shall be brought to pass, saith the Lord GOD.', '6~0559~ 10~0584~ 15~0559~, 18~08052~; 21~0935~: 24~03820~ 26~04549~, 29~03027~ 32~07503~, 35~07307~ 37~03543~, 40~01290~ 43~03212~ [44] 45~04325~: 48~0935~, 54~01961~, 55~05002~ 57~0136~ 58~03069~.'),
  (12040, 15, 2, 4, 'The children of Shephatiah, three hundred seventy and two.', '1~01121~ 3~08203~, 4~07969~ 5~03967~ 6~07657~ 8~08147~.'),
  (5644, 5, 28, 27, 'The LORD will smite thee with the botch of Egypt, and with the emerods, and with the scab, and with the itch, whereof thou canst not be healed.', '1~03068~ 3~05221~ 7~07822~ 9~04714~, 13~02914~ 14~06076~,* 18~01618~, 22~02775~, 25~03201~ 28~07495~.'),
  (18184, 23, 28, 11, 'For with stammering lips and another tongue will he speak to this people.', '2~03934~ 3~08193~ 5~0312~ 6~03956~ 9~01696~ 12~05971~.'),
  (8131, 10, 4, 4, 'And Jonathan, Saul''s son, had a son that was lame of his feet. He was five years old when the tidings came of Saul and Jonathan out of Jezreel, and his nurse took him up, and fled: and it came to pass, as she made haste to flee, that he fell, and became lame. And his name was Mephibosheth.', '1~03083~, 2~07586~ 3~01121~, 6~01121~ [7 8] 9~05223~ [11] 12~07272~. 15~02568~ 16~08141~ 17~01121~ 20~08052~ 21~0935~ 23~07586~ 25~03083~ 28~03157~, 31~0539~ 34~05375~, 36~05127~: 45~02648~ 47~05127~, 50~05307~, 53~06452~. 56~08034~ [57] 58~04648~.'),
  (24390, 41, 5, 16, 'And they that saw it told them how it befell to him that was possessed with the devil, and also concerning the swine.', '0~2532~ 3~1492~ [4] 5~1334~ 6~846~ 7~4459~ 9~1096~ 17~1139~, 18~2532~ [19] 20~4012~ 22~5519~.'),
  (12539, 16, 9, 19, 'Yet thou in thy manifold mercies forsookest them not in the wilderness: the pillar of the cloud departed not from them by day, to lead them in the way; neither the pillar of fire by night, to shew them light, and the way wherein they should go.', '4~07227~ 5~07356~ 6~05800~ 11~04057~: 13~05982~ 16~06051~ 17~05493~ 22~03119~, 24~05148~ 28~01870~; 31~05982~ 33~0784~ 35~03915~, 39~0215~, 42~01870~ 46~03212~.'),
  (19402, 24, 18, 9, 'And at what instant I shall speak concerning a nation, and concerning a kingdom, to build and to plant it;', '[1 2] 3~07281~ 6~01696~ 9~01471~, 13~04467~, 15~01129~ 18~05193~ [19]'),
  (13851, 18, 39, 8, 'The range of the mountains is his pasture, and he searcheth after every green thing.', '1~03491~ 4~02022~ [5] 7~04829~, 10~01875~ 11~0310~ 14~03387~.'),
  (9083, 11, 9, 24, 'But Pharaoh''s daughter came up out of the city of David unto her house which Solomon had built for her: then did he build Millo.', '1~06547~ 2~01323~ 4~05927~ 8~05892~ 10~01732~ 13~01004~ [15] 17~01129~ 23~01129~ 24~04407~.'),
  (17081, 20, 23, 28, 'She also lieth in wait as for a prey, and increaseth the transgressors among men.', '4~0693~ [6] 8~02863~, 10~03254~ 12~0898~ 14~0120~.'),
  (19619, 24, 27, 14, 'Therefore hearken not unto the words of the prophets that speak unto you, saying, Ye shall not serve the king of Babylon: for they prophesy a lie unto you.', '1~08085~ 5~01697~ 8~05030~ 10~0559~ 13~0559~, 17~05647~ 19~04428~ 21~0894~: 24~05012~ 26~08267~'),
  (3895, 4, 7, 40, 'One kid of the goats for a sin offering:', '0~0259~ 1~08163~ 4~05795~ 8~02403~:'),
  (8345, 10, 13, 21, 'But when king David heard of all these things, he was very wroth.', '&para; 2~04428~ 3~01732~ 4~08085~ 8~01697~, 11~03966~ 12~02734~.'),
  (13021, 18, 7, 4, 'When I lie down, I say, When shall I arise, and the night be gone? and I am full of tossings to and fro unto the dawning of the day.', '3~07901~, 5~0559~, 9~06965~, 12~06153~ 14~04059~? 18~07646~ 23~05076~ 29~05399~.'),
  (23192, 40, 2, 13, 'And when they were departed, behold, the angel of the Lord appeareth to Joseph in a dream, saying, Arise, and take the young child and his mother, and flee into Egypt, and be thou there until I bring thee word: for Herod will seek the young child to destroy him.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~846~ 4~402~, 5~2400~, 7~32~ 10~2962~ 11~5316~ 13~2501~ 14~2596~ 16~3677~, 17~3004~, 18~1453~, 20~3880~ 23~3813~ 24~2532~ 25~846~ 26~3384~, 27~2532~ 28~5343~ 29~1519~ 30~125~, 31~2532~ 33~2468~ 34~1563~ 35~2193~ 36~302~ 37~2036~ 38~4671~ 39~2036~: 40~1063~ 41~2264~ 42~3195~ 43~2212~ 46~3813~ 48~622~ 49~846~.'),
  (30036, 58, 4, 6, 'Seeing therefore it remaineth that some must enter therein, and they to whom it was first preached entered not in because of unbelief:', '0~1893~ 1~3767~ 3~620~ 5~5100~ 7~1525~ 8~846~ 9~1519~,* 10~2532~ 16~4386~ 17~2097~ 18~1525~ 19~3756~ 20~1525~ 21~1223~ 23~543~:'),
  (21297, 26, 33, 8, 'When I say unto the wicked, O wicked man, thou shalt surely die; if thou dost not speak to warn the wicked from his way, that wicked man shall die in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at thine hand.', '2~0559~ 5~07563~, 7~07563~ [8] 11~04191~ 12~04191~; 17~01696~ 19~02094~ 21~07563~ 24~01870~, 26~07563~ [27] 29~04191~ 32~05771~; 35~01818~ 38~01245~ 41~03027~.'),
  (15056, 19, 73, 27, 'For, lo, they that are far from thee shall perish: thou hast destroyed all them that go a whoring from thee.', '5~07369~ 9~06~: 12~06789~ 18~02181~'),
  (30121, 58, 8, 13, 'In that he saith, A new covenant, he hath made the first old. Now that which decayeth and waxeth old is ready to vanish away.', '0~1722~ 3~3004~, 5~2537~ [6] 9~3822~ 11~4413~ 12~3822~. 13~1161~ 16~3822~ 17~2532~ 19~1095~ [20] 21~1451~ 24~854~.'),
  (24280, 41, 2, 10, 'But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, (he saith to the sick of the palsy,)', '0~1161~ 1~2443~ 4~1492~ 5~3754~ 7~5207~ 9~444~ 10~2192~ 11~1849~ 12~1909~ 13~1093~ 15~863~ 16~266~, 18~3004~ 24~3885~,)'),
  (28661, 46, 12, 11, 'But all these worketh that one and the selfsame Spirit, dividing to every man severally as he will.', '0~1161~ 1~3956~ 2~5023~ 3~1754~ 5~1520~ 6~2532~ 8~846~ 9~4151~, 10~1244~ 13~1538~ 14~2398~ 15~2531~ 17~1014~.'),
  (9058, 11, 8, 65, 'And at that time Solomon held a feast, and all Israel with him, a great congregation, from the entering in of Hamath unto the river of Egypt, before the LORD our God, seven days and seven days, even fourteen days.', '3~06256~ 4~08010~ 5~06213~ 7~02282~, 10~03478~ 14~01419~ 15~06951~, 18~0935~ 21~02574~ 24~05158~ 26~04714~, 27~06440~ 29~03068~ 31~0430~, 32~07651~ 33~03117~ 35~07651~ 36~03117~, [37] 38~06240~ 39~0702~* 40~03117~.'),
  (11457, 14, 12, 11, 'And when the king entered into the house of the LORD, the guard came and fetched them, and brought them again into the guard chamber.', '1~01767~ 3~04428~ 4~0935~ 7~01004~ 10~03068~, 12~07323~ 13~0935~ 15~05375~ 20~07725~ 23~07323~ 24~08372~.'),
  (20670, 26, 11, 6, 'Ye have multiplied your slain in this city, and ye have filled the streets thereof with the slain.', '2~07235~ 4~02491~ 7~05892~, 11~04390~ 13~02351~ 17~02491~.'),
  (3384, 3, 22, 10, 'There shall no stranger eat of the holy thing: a sojourner of the priest, or an hired servant, shall not eat of the holy thing.', '&para; 3~02114~ 4~0398~ [5] 8~06944~: 10~08453~ 13~03548~, 17~07916~, 20~0398~ [21] 24~06944~.'),
  (18619, 23, 47, 11, 'Therefore shall evil come upon thee; thou shalt not know from whence it riseth: and mischief shall fall upon thee; thou shalt not be able to put it off: and desolation shall come upon thee suddenly, which thou shalt not know.', '2~07451~ 3~0935~ 9~03045~ 13~07837~: 15~01943~ 17~05307~ 24~03201~ 28~03722~: 30~07722~ 32~0935~ 35~06597~, [36] 40~03045~.'),
  (27676, 44, 20, 34, 'Yea, ye yourselves know, that these hands have ministered unto my necessities, and to them that were with me.', '0~1161~, 2~846~ 3~1097~, 4~3754~ 5~3778~ 6~5495~ 8~5256~ 10~3450~ 11~5532~, 12~2532~ 16~5607~ 17~3326~ 18~1700~.'),
  (24399, 41, 5, 25, 'And a certain woman, which had an issue of blood twelve years,', '0~2532~ 2~5100~ 3~1135~, 6~1722~ 7~4511~ 9~5607~ 10~129~* 11~1427~ 12~2094~,'),
  (5518, 5, 23, 12, 'Thou shalt have a place also without the camp, whither thou shalt go forth abroad:', '5~03027~ 6~02351~ 8~04264~, 13~03318~ 14~02351~:'),
  (12730, 17, 1, 19, 'If it please the king, let there go a royal commandment from him, and let it be written among the laws of the Persians and the Medes, that it be not altered, That Vashti come no more before king Ahasuerus; and let the king give her royal estate unto another that is better than she.', '2~02895~ 4~04428~, 7~03318~ 9~04438~ 10~01697~ 12~06440~, 17~03789~ 20~01881~ 23~06539~ 26~04074~, 31~05674~, 33~02060~ 34~0935~ 37~06440~ 38~04428~ 39~0325~; 43~04428~ 44~05414~ 47~04438~ 49~07468~ 52~02896~'),
  (27977, 45, 1, 31, 'Without understanding, covenantbreakers, without natural affection, implacable, unmerciful:', '1~801~, 2~802~, 5~794~, 6~786~, 7~415~:'),
  (18406, 23, 38, 7, 'And this shall be a sign unto thee from the LORD, that the LORD will do this thing that he hath spoken;', '[2 3] 5~0226~ 10~03068~, 13~03068~ 15~06213~ 17~01697~ 21~01696~;'),
  (18104, 23, 23, 18, 'And her merchandise and her hire shall be holiness to the LORD: it shall not be treasured nor laid up; for her merchandise shall be for them that dwell before the LORD, to eat sufficiently, and for durable clothing.', '2~05504~ 5~0868~ 8~06944~ 11~03068~: 16~0686~ 19~02630~; 22~05504~ 28~03427~ 29~06440~ 31~03068~, 33~0398~ 34~07654~, 37~06266~ 38~04374~.'),
  (7682, 9, 17, 57, 'And as David returned from the slaughter of the Philistine, Abner took him, and brought him before Saul with the head of the Philistine in his hand.', '2~01732~ 3~07725~ 6~05221~ 9~06430~, 10~074~ 11~03947~ 14~0935~ 16~06440~ 17~07586~ 20~07218~ 23~06430~ 26~03027~.'),
  (13669, 18, 33, 10, 'Behold, he findeth occasions against me, he counteth me for his enemy,', '2~04672~ 3~08569~ 7~02803~ 11~0341~,'),
  (3140, 3, 14, 24, 'And the priest shall take the lamb of the trespass offering, and the log of oil, and the priest shall wave them for a wave offering before the LORD:', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ 6~03532~ 10~0817~, 13~03849~ 15~08081~, 18~03548~ 20~05130~ [22] 25~08573~ 26~06440~ 28~03068~:'),
  (22223, 28, 9, 6, 'For, lo, they are gone because of destruction: Egypt shall gather them up, Memphis shall bury them: the pleasant places for their silver, nettles shall possess them: thorns shall be in their tabernacles.', '4~01980~ 7~07701~: 8~04714~ 12~06908~, 13~04644~ 15~06912~ 18~04261~ [19] 22~03701~, 23~07057~ 25~03423~ 27~02336~ [28 29] 32~0168~.'),
  (25298, 42, 8, 41, 'And, behold, there came a man named Jairus, and he was a ruler of the synagogue: and he fell down at Jesus'' feet, and besought him that he would come into his house:', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~2064~ 5~435~ 6~3686~ 7~3739~* 8~2383~, 9~2532~ 10~846~ 11~5225~ 13~758~ 16~4864~: 17~2532~ 20~4098~ 21~3844~ 22~2424~ 23~4228~, 25~3870~ 26~846~ 30~1525~ 31~1519~ 32~846~ 33~3624~:'),
  (13938, 18, 42, 7, 'And it was so, that after the LORD had spoken these words unto Job, the LORD said to Eliphaz the Temanite, My wrath is kindled against thee, and against thy two friends: for ye have not spoken of me the thing that is right, as my servant Job hath.', '&para; [3] 5~0310~ 7~03068~ 9~01696~ 11~01697~ 13~0347~, 15~03068~ 16~0559~ 18~0464~ 20~08489~, 22~0639~ 24~02734~ 30~08147~ 31~07453~: 36~01696~ [39 42] 43~03559~, 46~05650~ 47~0347~ [48]'),
  (15517, 19, 99, 9, 'Exalt the LORD our God, and worship at his holy hill; for the LORD our God is holy.', '0~07311~ 2~03068~ 4~0430~, 6~07812~ 9~06944~ 10~02022~; 13~03068~ 15~0430~ [16] 17~06918~.'),
  (16253, 19, 139, 5, 'Thou hast beset me behind and before, and laid thine hand upon me.', '2~06696~ 4~0268~ 6~06924~, 8~07896~ 10~03709~'),
  (25818, 42, 20, 25, 'And he said unto them, Render therefore unto Caesar the things which be Caesar''s, and unto God the things which be God''s.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~591~ 6~5106~ 8~2541~ 12~3588~ 13~2541~, 14~2532~ 16~2316~ 20~3588~ 21~2316~.'),
  (29771, 54, 4, 8, 'For bodily exercise profiteth little: but godliness is profitable unto all things, having promise of the life that now is, and of that which is to come.', '0~1063~ 1~4984~ 2~1129~ 3~2076~ 4~5624~* 5~3641~ 6~4314~:* 7~1161~ 8~2150~ 9~2076~ 10~5624~ 11~4314~ 13~3956~, 14~2192~ 15~1860~ 18~2222~ 21~3568~, 22~2532~ 28~3195~.'),
  (4084, 4, 13, 4, 'And these were their names: of the tribe of Reuben, Shammua the son of Zaccur.', '[2] 4~08034~: 7~04294~ 9~07205~, 10~08051~ 12~01121~ 14~02139~.'),
  (11243, 14, 3, 6, 'And he garnished the house with precious stones for beauty: and the gold was gold of Parvaim.', '2~06823~ 4~01004~ 6~03368~ 7~068~ 9~08597~: 12~02091~ [13] 14~02091~ 16~06516~.'),
  (5270, 5, 12, 24, 'Thou shalt not eat it; thou shalt pour it upon the earth as water.', '3~0398~ 7~08210~ 11~0776~ 13~04325~.'),
  (28778, 46, 15, 44, 'It is sown a natural body; it is raised a spiritual body. There is a natural body, and there is a spiritual body.', '2~4687~ 4~5591~ 5~4983~; 8~1453~ 10~4152~ 11~4983~. 13~2076~ 15~5591~ 16~4983~, 17~2532~ 19~2076~ 21~4152~ 22~4983~.'),
  (18568, 23, 44, 26, 'That confirmeth the word of his servant, and performeth the counsel of his messengers; that saith to Jerusalem, Thou shalt be inhabited; and to the cities of Judah, Ye shall be built, and I will raise up the decayed places thereof:', '1~06965~ 3~01697~ 6~05650~, 8~07999~ 10~06098~ 13~04397~; 15~0559~ 17~03389~, 21~03427~; 25~05892~ 27~03063~, 31~01129~, 36~06965~ 39~02723~'),
  (10931, 13, 19, 16, 'And when the Syrians saw that they were put to the worse before Israel, they sent messengers, and drew forth the Syrians that were beyond the river: and Shophach the captain of the host of Hadarezer went before them.', '3~0758~ 4~07200~ 11~05062~ 12~06440~ 13~03478~, 15~07971~ 16~04397~, 19~03318~ 21~0758~ [23] 24~05676~ 26~05104~: 28~07780~ 30~08269~ 33~06635~ 35~01928~ [36] 37~06440~'),
  (22259, 28, 11, 10, 'They shall walk after the LORD: he shall roar like a lion: when he shall roar, then the children shall tremble from the west.', '2~03212~ 3~0310~ 5~03068~: 8~07580~ 11~0738~: 15~07580~, 18~01121~ 20~02729~ 23~03220~.'),
  (2044, 2, 19, 13, 'There shall not an hand touch it, but he shall surely be stoned, or shot through; whether it be beast or man, it shall not live: when the trumpet soundeth long, they shall come up to the mount.', '4~03027~ 5~05060~ 10~05619~ 12~05619~, 13~0176~ 14~03384~ 15~03384~; [17 18] 19~0929~ 20~0518~ 21~0376~, 25~02421~: 28~03104~ 30~04900~, 34~05927~ 37~02022~.'),
  (10960, 13, 21, 18, 'Then the angel of the LORD commanded Gad to say to David, that David should go up, and set up an altar unto the LORD in the threshingfloor of Ornan the Jebusite.', '&para; 2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~0559~ 7~01410~ 9~0559~ 11~01732~, 13~01732~ 16~05927~, 19~06965~ 21~04196~ 24~03068~ 27~01637~ 29~0771~ 31~02983~.'),
  (8452, 10, 16, 19, 'And again, whom should I serve? should I not serve in the presence of his son? as I have served in thy father''s presence, so will I be in thy presence.', '1~08145~, 5~05647~? [6 7] [9] 12~06440~ 15~01121~? 19~05647~ 22~01~ 23~06440~, 30~06440~.'),
  (26629, 43, 12, 34, 'The people answered him, We have heard out of the law that Christ abideth for ever: and how sayest thou, The Son of man must be lifted up? who is this Son of man?', '1~3793~ 2~611~ 3~846~, 4~2249~ 6~191~ 8~1537~ 10~3551~ 11~3754~ 12~5547~ 13~3306~ 14~1519~ 15~165~: 16~2532~ 17~4459~ 18~3004~ 19~4771~ 20~3754~,* 22~5207~ 24~444~ 25~1163~ 28~5312~? 29~5101~ 30~2076~ 31~3778~ 32~5207~ 34~444~?'),
  (24658, 41, 11, 7, 'And they brought the colt to Jesus, and cast their garments on him; and he sat upon him.', '0~2532~ 2~71~ 4~4454~ 5~4314~ 6~2424~, 7~2532~ 8~1911~ 9~846~ 10~2440~ 11~1911~ 12~846~; 13~2532~ 15~2523~ 16~1909~ 17~846~.'),
  (18116, 23, 24, 12, 'In the city is left desolation, and the gate is smitten with destruction.', '2~05892~ 4~07604~ 5~08047~, 8~08179~ 10~03807~ 12~07591~.'),
  (30136, 58, 9, 15, 'And for this cause he is the mediator of the new testament, that by means of death, for the redemption of the transgressions that were under the first testament, they which are called might receive the promise of eternal inheritance.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5124~ 3~1223~ 5~2076~ 7~3316~ 10~2537~ 11~1242~, 12~3704~ 14~1096~ 16~2288~, 17~1519~ 19~629~ 22~3847~ [23 24] 25~1909~ 27~4413~ 28~1242~, 32~2564~ 34~2983~ 36~1860~ 38~166~ 39~2817~.'),
  (18994, 24, 2, 20, 'For of old time I have broken thy yoke, and burst thy bands; and thou saidst, I will not transgress; when upon every high hill and under every green tree thou wanderest, playing the harlot.', '&para; 3~05769~ 6~07665~ 8~05923~, [9] 10~05423~ 12~04147~; 15~0559~, 19~05674~ 23~01364~ 24~01389~ 28~07488~ 29~06086~ 31~06808~, 34~02181~.'),
  (30736, 66, 2, 3, 'And hast borne, and hast patience, and for my name''s sake hast laboured, and hast not fainted.', '0~2532~ 2~941~, 3~2532~ 4~2192~ 5~5281~, 6~2532~ 7~1223~ 8~3450~ 10~3686~ 11~1223~ 12~2872~, 13~2532~ 14~2577~ 15~3756~ 16~2577~.'),
  (14256, 19, 24, 6, 'This is the generation of them that seek him, that seek thy face, O Jacob. Selah.', '[1] 3~01755~ 7~01875~ 10~01245~ 12~06440~, 14~03290~. 15~05542~.'),
  (6905, 7, 13, 14, 'She may not eat of any thing that cometh of the vine, neither let her drink wine or strong drink, nor eat any unclean thing: all that I commanded her let her observe.', '3~0398~ [6] 8~03318~ 11~01612~, 15~08354~ 16~03196~ 19~07941~, 21~0398~ 23~02932~ [24] 28~06680~ 32~08104~.'),
  (20987, 26, 22, 2, 'Now, thou son of man, wilt thou judge, wilt thou judge the bloody city? yea, thou shalt shew her all her abominations.', '2~01121~ 4~0120~, 7~08199~, 10~08199~ 12~01818~ 13~05892~? 17~03045~ 21~08441~.'),
  (3219, 3, 16, 13, 'And he shall put the incense upon the fire before the LORD, that the cloud of the incense may cover the mercy seat that is upon the testimony, that he die not:', '3~05414~ 5~07004~ 8~0784~ 9~06440~ 11~03068~, 14~06051~ 17~07004~ 19~03680~ 22~03727~ [24] 27~05715~, 30~04191~'),
  (7286, 9, 3, 3, 'And ere the lamp of God went out in the temple of the LORD, where the ark of God was, and Samuel was laid down to sleep;', '3~05216~ 5~0430~ 7~03518~ 10~01964~ 13~03068~, 16~0727~ 18~0430~ [19] 21~08050~ 24~07901~ [25 26]'),
  (4960, 5, 2, 16, 'So it came to pass, when all the men of war were consumed and dead from among the people,', '8~0582~ 10~04421~ 12~08552~ 14~04191~ 16~07130~ 18~05971~,'),
  (19337, 24, 15, 13, 'Thy substance and thy treasures will I give to the spoil without price, and that for all thy sins, even in all thy borders.', '1~02428~ 4~0214~ 7~05414~ 10~0957~ 12~04242~, [14] 18~02403~, 23~01366~.'),
  (11090, 13, 26, 5, 'Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Peulthai the eighth: for God blessed him.', '0~05988~ 2~08345~, 3~03485~ 5~07637~, 6~06469~ 8~08066~: 10~0430~ 11~01288~'),
  (16153, 19, 130, 4, 'But there is forgiveness with thee, that thou mayest be feared.', '[1 2] 3~05547~ 10~03372~.'),
  (4066, 4, 12, 2, 'And they said, Hath the LORD indeed spoken only by Moses? hath he not spoken also by us? And the LORD heard it.', '2~0559~, 5~03068~ 7~01696~ 10~04872~? 14~01696~ 20~03068~ 21~08085~ [22]'),
  (26337, 43, 6, 65, 'And he said, Therefore said I unto you, that no man can come unto me, except it were given unto him of my Father.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~, 3~5124~ 4~1223~ 5~2046~ 7~5213~, 8~3754~ 10~3762~ 11~1410~ 12~2064~ 13~4314~ 14~3165~, 15~3362~ 17~5600~ 18~1325~ 20~846~ 21~1537~ 22~3450~ 23~3962~.'),
  (10515, 13, 6, 53, 'Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son.', '0~06659~ 2~01121~, 3~0290~ 5~01121~.'),
  (385, 1, 15, 21, 'And the Amorites, and the Canaanites, and the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.', '2~0567~, 5~03669~, 8~01622~, 11~02983~.'),
  (23107, 39, 1, 9, 'And now, I pray you, beseech God that he will be gracious unto us: this hath been by your means: will he regard your persons? saith the LORD of hosts.', '5~02470~ 6~06440~* 7~0410~ 12~02603~ 20~03027~: 23~05375~ 25~06440~? 26~0559~ 28~03068~ 30~06635~.'),
  (7105, 7, 20, 44, 'And there fell of Benjamin eighteen thousand men; all these were men of valour.', '2~05307~ 4~01144~ 5~06240~ 6~08083~* 7~0505~ 8~0376~; [11] 12~0582~ 14~02428~.'),
  (25947, 42, 22, 69, 'Hereafter shall the Son of man sit on the right hand of the power of God.', '0~575~ 1~3568~* 2~2071~ 4~5207~ 6~444~ 7~2521~ 8~1537~ 11~1188~ 14~1411~ 16~2316~.'),
  (2409, 2, 30, 22, 'Moreover the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (27168, 44, 7, 36, 'He brought them out, after that he had shewed wonders and signs in the land of Egypt, and in the Red sea, and in the wilderness forty years.', '0~3778~ 1~1806~ 2~846~ 3~1806~, 8~4160~ 9~5059~ 10~2532~ 11~4592~ 12~1722~ 14~1093~ 16~125~, 17~2532~ 18~1722~ 20~2063~ 21~2281~, 22~2532~ 23~1722~ 25~2048~ 26~5062~ 27~2094~.'),
  (23109, 39, 1, 11, 'For from the rising of the sun even unto the going down of the same my name shall be great among the Gentiles; and in every place incense shall be offered unto my name, and a pure offering: for my name shall be great among the heathen, saith the LORD of hosts.', '3~04217~ 6~08121~ 11~03996~ 16~08034~ [17 18] 19~01419~ 22~01471~; 26~04725~ 27~06999~ [28 29] 30~05066~ 33~08034~, 36~02889~ 37~04503~: 40~08034~ [41 42] 43~01419~ 46~01471~, 47~0559~ 49~03068~ 51~06635~.'),
  (28545, 46, 8, 2, 'And if any man think that he knoweth any thing, he knoweth nothing yet as he ought to know.', '0~1161~ 3~1536~ 4~1380~ 7~1492~ 9~5100~, 11~1097~ 12~3762~ 13~3764~ 14~2531~ 16~1163~ 18~1097~.'),
  (2089, 2, 21, 7, 'And if a man sell his daughter to be a maidservant, she shall not go out as the menservants do.', '3~0376~ 4~04376~ 6~01323~ 10~0519~, 15~03318~ 18~05650~ 19~03318~.'),
  (17468, 21, 8, 1, 'Who is as the wise man? and who knoweth the interpretation of a thing? a man''s wisdom maketh his face to shine, and the boldness of his face shall be changed.', '&para; [1] 4~02450~ [5] 8~03045~ 10~06592~ 13~01697~? 15~0120~ 16~02451~ 19~06440~ 21~0215~, 24~05797~ 27~06440~ 30~08132~.'),
  (21956, 27, 7, 14, 'And there was given him dominion, and glory, and a kingdom, that all people, nations, and languages, should serve him: his dominion is an everlasting dominion, which shall not pass away, and his kingdom that which shall not be destroyed.', '3~03052~ 5~07985~, 7~03367~, 10~04437~, 12~03606~ 13~05972~, 14~0524~, 16~03961~, 18~06399~ 21~07985~ [22] 24~05957~ 25~07985~, 28~03809~ 30~05709~, 33~04437~ [34] 37~03809~ 39~02255~.'),
  (26369, 43, 7, 26, 'But, lo, he speaketh boldly, and they say nothing unto him. Do the rulers know indeed that this is the very Christ?', '0~2532~, 1~2396~, 3~2980~ 4~3954~, 5~2532~ 7~3004~ 8~3762~ 10~846~. 11~1097~ 13~758~ 14~1097~ 15~230~ 16~3379~* 17~3754~ 18~3778~ 19~2076~ 21~230~ 22~5547~?'),
  (5707, 5, 29, 22, 'So that the generation to come of your children that shall rise up after you, and the stranger that shall come from a far land, shall say, when they see the plagues of that land, and the sicknesses which the LORD hath laid upon it;', '3~01755~ 5~0314~ 8~01121~ 12~06965~ 13~0310~ 17~05237~ 20~0935~ 23~07350~ 24~0776~, 26~0559~, 29~07200~ 31~04347~ 34~0776~, 37~08463~ 40~03068~ 42~02470~'),
  (13398, 18, 21, 34, 'How then comfort ye me in vain, seeing in your answers there remaineth falsehood?', '2~05162~ 6~01892~, 10~08666~ 12~07604~ 13~04604~?'),
  (1765, 2, 9, 18, 'Behold, to morrow about this time I will cause it to rain a very grievous hail, such as hath not been in Egypt since the foundation thereof even until now.', '2~04279~ 5~06256~ 11~04305~ 13~03966~ 14~03515~ 15~01259~, 20~03644~ 22~04714~ 23~04480~ 25~03245~ 26~03117~*'),
  (27892, 44, 27, 21, 'But after long abstinence Paul stood forth in the midst of them, and said, Sirs, ye should have hearkened unto me, and not have loosed from Crete, and to have gained this harm and loss.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~5225~ 2~4183~ 3~5119~ 4~776~* 5~3972~ 7~2476~ 8~1722~ 10~3319~ 12~846~, 14~2036~, 15~435~ 16~5599~,* 18~1163~ 19~3303~* 21~3980~ 23~3427~, 25~3361~ 27~321~ 28~575~ 29~2914~, 30~5037~ 33~2770~ 34~5026~ 35~5196~ 36~2532~ 37~2209~.'),
  (9466, 11, 21, 7, 'And Jezebel his wife said unto him, Dost thou now govern the kingdom of Israel? arise, and eat bread, and let thine heart be merry: I will give thee the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite.', '1~0348~ 3~0802~ 4~0559~ 10~06213~ 12~04410~ 14~03478~? 15~06965~, [16] 17~0398~ 18~03899~, 22~03820~ 24~03190~: 27~05414~ 30~03754~ 32~05022~ 34~03158~.'),
  (31035, 66, 19, 2, 'For true and righteous are his judgments: for he hath judged the great whore, which did corrupt the earth with her fornication, and hath avenged the blood of his servants at her hand.', '0~3754~ 1~228~ 2~2532~ 3~1342~ [4] 5~846~ 6~2920~: 7~3754~ 10~2919~ 12~3173~ 13~4204~, 14~3748~ 16~5351~ 18~1093~ 19~1722~ 20~846~ 21~4202~, 22~2532~ 24~1556~ 26~129~ 28~846~ 29~1401~ 30~1537~ 31~846~ 32~5495~.');
